INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'Jesus the Messiah was Fully Human', '<p>Jesus as a human being is distinguished from God, his Father, according to Jesus&rsquo; statement to Peter in Matthew 26 where Jesus tells Peter that he could ask his Father for legions of angels to help him.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 26:47-53</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-30', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '6:14', 0, 0, 'Trinity, Judas', 'PoCzFHJXbro', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PoCzFHJXbro/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2, 1, 'What Exactly is a Biblical Unitarian?', '<p>This teaching explains the definitions of the words Unitarian, Trinitarian, Universalism, and Universalist, and the origins of each. Also covered are the many names of the one true God, and the differentiation between Holy Spirit and holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 51:11; Acts 2:38</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-11-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:47', 0, 0, 'trinity Yahweh, Revelation', '4YXPujczGCk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4YXPujczGCk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(3, 1, 'Insights and Commentary on John 1:14 (Part 2)', '<p>In the Old Testament, the presence of God, which dwelled in the Temple, left and didn&rsquo;t return. In John&rsquo;s gospel, Jesus thinks and speaks like he is God&rsquo;s new Temple - where God&rsquo;s presence dwells. The &ldquo;word&rdquo; and &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; in the prologue of John come and pitch their tent in the embodiment of Jesus, who, being the presence of God&rsquo;s given word, functions as the purpose of God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 8:10-11; Ezek. 10:18; Mal. 3:1; John 1:14; 2:9; 1 Cor. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-02-13', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:37', 0, 0, 'logos, tabernacle', 'ftM4cY7e4Zw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ftM4cY7e4Zw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active pending review', 1, 0, null),
(4, 1, 'Insights and Commentary on John 1:14 (Part 1)', '<p>God&rsquo;s powerful, creative speech (word) and His kind interactions with His creation (wisdom) are personified and ultimately embodied in the human Jesus. The things that God started in the Old Testament we now see being fulfilled in the New Testament.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 31:10-31; John 1:14.</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-02-06', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '7:48', 0, 0, 'logos, flesh', 'GsfLm9421Ew', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GsfLm9421Ew/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active pending review', 1, 0, null),
(5, 1, 'Insights and Commentary on John 1:10-11', '<p>The use of the words &ldquo;he&rdquo; and &ldquo;him&rdquo; are explained as personification of God&rsquo;s powerful words, drawing from themes from the Jewish writings of the time regarding God&rsquo;s wisdom. Ultimately, these were embodied in Jesus who came to his own (the Jews). John is actually drawing upon the Jewish traditions to explain the significance and ministry of Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 33:6; John 1: 3, 10-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-01-30', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '6:45', 0, 0, 'logos', 'Bt8rl6tneHE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Bt8rl6tneHE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active pending review', 1, 0, null),
(6, 1, 'Insights and Commentary on John 1:5', '<p>In John 1:5, light and darkness are metaphors for the characteristics of people who follow God&lsquo;s light and those who don&rsquo;t. The ultimate embodiment of light is Jesus. In Jewish writings, wisdom acts like light and darkness cannot prevail against it. Through God&lsquo;s powerful speech, which brings wisdom, God is illuminating this fallen creation and bringing about redemption and salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:2-3; John 1:5; 8:12</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-01-23', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '6:19', 0, 0, null, '7u222hAiEQ4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7u222hAiEQ4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active pending review', 1, 0, null),
(7, 1, 'Insights and Commentary on John 1:4', '<p>God&rsquo;s word is what brings about light and life, and that is what was formerly said about wisdom. &ldquo;Word&rdquo; and &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; are overlapping themes in John 1. The connection between them, along with the use of personification, are important to properly understanding this verse.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:3; 1:26-27; Prov. 3:18; 8:35; John 1:4</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-01-16', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '5:37', 0, 0, null, 'yOt0YHFvPlU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yOt0YHFvPlU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active pending review', 1, 0, null),
(8, 1, 'Understanding John 1:3', '<p>This teaching clarifies &ldquo;who&rdquo; and &ldquo;what&rdquo; the Logos is in John 1:3. The &ldquo;Word&rdquo; or &ldquo;Logos&rdquo; is the personification of who God is and is not a person; however, ultimately, the Logos is embodied in Jesus, who spoke the words of God.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:3; Ps. 33:6; 104:24; 136:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-01-09', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:24', 0, 0, null, 'b77QHL7RjQ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b77QHL7RjQ0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 59, null),
(9, 1, 'Understanding John 1:1', '<p>This teaching explains the complicated verse John 1:1. Drawing on Gen. 1:1, we stand in awe of God&rsquo;s powerful and creative spoken word. We see the personification of God&rsquo;s heart and character and finally understand that the &ldquo;word&rdquo; fully expresses who God is.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:1; Job 10:13; 23:14; 27:11; Prov. 8:23-30</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2018-01-02', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '8:51', 0, 0, 'plan', 'QJ2mn_TDjCQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QJ2mn_TDjCQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(10, 1, 'Understanding Personification in Scripture', '<p>God uses personification in Scripture to accentuate His attributes. Personification does not refer to real people, but rather it is a poetic way of revealing characteristics about the one personified. In this case, it reveals how God interacts with His creation.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:21-23; 8:12, 17; Ps. 61:7, 85; 10:28; 96:6; 43:3; 23:6; 25:21; Isa. 51:9; 55:11; John 1:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2017-12-19', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:52', 0, 0, 'character, essence', 'KFcc1QR4tFI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KFcc1QR4tFI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(11, 1, 'Lady Wisdom Personified', '<p>God&rsquo;s wise interaction with the world is expressed in the personification of wisdom as a woman. Throughout Proverbs, Lady Wisdom is described, and finally brought into vivid images in Proverbs 31. This is ultimately embodied in Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 3:15; 2:9; 8:13; 9:1, 3, 5, 19; 1:21; 8:30; 31:10-31</p> <p>Teacher: Dustin Smith</p>', '2017-12-12', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:00', 0, 0, 'instruction', 'rgkJVbKXlw8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rgkJVbKXlw8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(12, 1, 'What is the First and Greatest Commandment?', '<p>It is important to understand what the first and greatest commandment is and how the depth of the Hebrew language can be lost in translation. The first and greatest commandment is identified as the <em>Shema</em> in Deuteronomy. This teaching explores the meaning of the <em>Shema</em>.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4-5; 1 Cor. 8:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-09-06', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:32', 0, 0, 'trinity', 'MHVbxHgbGC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MHVbxHgbGC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 31, null),
(13, 1, 'Navigating as a Biblical Unitarian in a Trinitarian World', '<p>This is a sharing demonstrating how as a Biblical Unitarian one can use wisdom without compromise and navigate among Trinitarians in this world, being respectful but not conceding their beliefs about the truth of who God and Jesus Christ are.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-09-06', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '3:57', 0, 0, null, '5kpbelRPSvM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5kpbelRPSvM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(14, 1, 'The Root of David', '<p>In the Bible there are many titles for Jesus Christ, and each tells us something about him. In this sharing, two important titles of Jesus, &ldquo;the root of Jesse&rdquo; and &ldquo;the root of David,&rdquo; are discussed. These titles point to the hope and stability that Jesus Christ embodies.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 11:1-10; Rom. 15:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-01', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:28', 0, 0, 'branch', 'AnJFU2TdD2A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AnJFU2TdD2A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(15, 1, 'Seeing the Glory of God in Jesus Christ', '<p>During Old Testament times, Yahweh met His people at His dwelling place, the Tent of Meeting. The Tent was filled with the glory of God and it foreshadowed His future meeting place with believers in Jesus Christ. We can now see the glory of God through Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-05-16', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:25', 0, 0, null, 'FGuwkYAnpFY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FGuwkYAnpFY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 16, null),
(16, 1, 'Can we pray to Jesus?', '<p>At the Last Supper Jesus said, &ldquo;ask anything in my name and I will do it,&rdquo; and then a short time later he said &ldquo;you will not ask me anything.&rdquo; This teaching explains how those statements do not contradict each other.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:13-14; 16:22-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-04-12', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:42', 0, 0, null, 'NqP9M670n5c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NqP9M670n5c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 65, null),
(17, 1, 'Does John 1:18 say that Jesus is God or Son?', '<p>Various translations over the years have confused &ldquo;God&rdquo; and &ldquo;Son&rdquo; in John 1:18. As we study the Bible, it is of utmost importance to use a good translation, as translators promote the doctrines they believe.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:18; 3:16, 18</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-22', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:40', 0, 0, 'trinity, begotten', 'W_BGX28er9Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/W_BGX28er9Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 59, null),
(18, 1, 'If Jesus is called Lord, does that make him God?', '<p>In the New Testament, both God and Jesus are called &ldquo;Lord.&rdquo; This causes confusion about whether or not that makes Jesus God. Understanding the meaning of the Greek word translated &ldquo;Lord&ldquo; and how people in the first century used it in language resolves the confusion.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:20; 7:21; 10:24; 20:8; 21:30, 40; 27:63; Mark 13:35; Luke 16:3; John 12:21; 20:15; Acts 10:4; 25:26; 1 Cor. 8:5; 1 Pet. 3:6; Rev. 7:14.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-04', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:49', 0, 0, 'trinity', 'iP2zj-NGorU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iP2zj-NGorU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(19, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 6)', '<p>Do we usurp God&lsquo;s authority by praying to Jesus Christ? This is a debated question. To pray means to ask. In numerous verses, we see that Jesus Christ instructed his disciples to ask him for help and we find many examples of them doing so. We need to learn to ask both God and Jesus to be personally involved in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 12:8; 26:35; 1 Kings 18:24; 2 Kings 5:11; John 14:12-14; Acts 1:23-25; 7:59; Rom. 10:13; 1 Cor. 1:1-2; 2 Cor. 12:8-9; 2 Tim. 2:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-28', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:53', 24, 6, 'calling', 'Hsqask3d7cA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Hsqask3d7cA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(20, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 5)', '<p>This teaching illustrates that Jesus Christ healed people when he walked the earth and he continues to heal people today. He also gives grace and peace, and he participates in our suffering. He intercedes with emotion for what we are going through and is actively involved in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:4, 32-34; Rom. 8:26; 1 Cor. 12:26; 16:23; Eph. 1:2; 1 Thess. 5:28; 1 John 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-28', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:24', 24, 5, 'persecution', 'OdnCZB1r3q0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OdnCZB1r3q0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(21, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching examines a difficult section of Scripture where Jesus is called &ldquo;the Spirit,&rdquo; a name he was given after his resurrection. Jesus continues to intercede for us, so we should ask for his help. Jesus also strengthens, protects, comforts, encourages, guides, and directs us. He does these things in multiple ways.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:7; 18:9; Rom. 8:26-27, 34; 1 Cor. 16:7; 2 Thess. 3:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-28', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:14', 24, 4, 'revelation, vision', '5lpjnL4ARxA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5lpjnL4ARxA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(22, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 3)', '<p>We learn about how busy Jesus Christ is today. As the Head of the Body of Christ, he organizes it. However, the verse that says this is frequently misunderstood. Jesus Christ creates positions in the Body and gives the ministries to fill them. Every member of the Body has a ministry and Jesus gives revelation, direction, and guidance regarding how to best fulfill it.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:10, 17; Gal. 1:11-12; Eph. 4:7-8, 11; Col. 1:15-19; Rev. 1:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-28', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:11', 24, 3, 'service, angel, apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastors, teachers, authorities, rulers, thrones, dominions, powers, principalities, firstborn', 'kOdNuEXmOIM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kOdNuEXmOIM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(23, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 2)', '<p>The Bible says that Jesus Christ is the Head of the Body of Christ and guides and directs it. We also see from Scripture that Jesus gets people born again and adds to those being saved, causing the Body of Christ to grow. The role of both God and Jesus is explained.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:18; Acts 2:32-33, 47; 5:32; Rom. 5:5; Eph. 1:22-23; 4:15; Col. 1:18; 2:18-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:05', 24, 2, 'Unitarian, trinity, salvation, revelation', 'PEVi018OLF8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PEVi018OLF8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(24, 1, 'What is Jesus Christ doing today? (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching is first in a series. In this one, we see the wonderful relationship between God the Creator and Jesus Christ, who was the Lamb of God. Jesus is second in authority and was made Lord by God. &ldquo;Lord&rdquo; means &ldquo;one has power and authority over others.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 41:44; Matt. 28:18; Acts 2:36; 7:56; Rom. 10:9; Eph. 1:18-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:22', 24, 1, 'trinity, salvation, confession, power, Stephen', '044WY1rdSqk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/044WY1rdSqk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(25, 1, 'Hear, O Israel! …the LORD is one!', '<p>Known in Judaism as &ldquo;The Shema,&rdquo; Deuteronomy 6:4 has been the centerpiece of Jewish prayer services for thousands of years and declares that &ldquo;Yahweh is our God, Yahweh is one.&rdquo; &ldquo;One&rdquo; in Hebrew is <em>echad</em> and in 960 uses in the Hebrew Bible it has no hint of being a compound unity inferring a godhead.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4; Matt. 28:19; James 2:19; 1 Tim. 2:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-31', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:38', 0, 0, 'trinity, Unitarian', '-4okmZ_78Xc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-4okmZ_78Xc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(26, 1, 'Verses used to Support the Trinity - Jude 1:5', '<p>The NET and ESV translations of the Bible say &ldquo;Jesus&rdquo; saved a people out of Egypt. All the other Bible versions say it was &ldquo;the Lord.&rdquo; Why the difference? Maybe it was a scribal copying error, or possibly religious pressure. There is no reference to Jesus leading Israel out of Egypt, nor did Jesus ever say he did. This teaching draws a conclusion to understanding Jude 1:5.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Jude 1:5</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-17', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '9:54', 57, 11, null, 'Nr2iQSDqC6c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Nr2iQSDqC6c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(27, 1, 'Did Mary Believe Jesus was God?', '<p>Mary, the mother of Jesus, heard along with her other sons that Jesus was preaching and healing people. Since Mary knew from an angel that Jesus was the Messiah, perhaps she was thinking he should be doing other things, like freeing Israel from Roman rule. This teaching also demonstrates that Mary knew Jesus was not God.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 8:19-21; Mark 3:20-21, 30-35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-15', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:33', 0, 0, null, '7TgGDcAhqBU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7TgGDcAhqBU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(28, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Genesis 22:8', '<p>When Abraham took Isaac to sacrifice him to God, Isaac asked where the sacrificial lamb was. Abraham said that God Himself would provide the lamb. This simply means that God would provide the lamb. It does not mean that God Himself would be that lamb.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 22:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-14', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '7:21', 57, 3, null, 'Lg9QzkUY5KI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Lg9QzkUY5KI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(29, 1, 'Verses used to Support the Trinity - John 8:58', '<p>Many Christians believe that when Jesus said &ldquo;Before Abraham was, I am&rdquo; in John 8:58 (KJV), he was referring to Exodus 3:14 and declaring himself to be God. But is that the case? This teaching delves into the meaning and usages of the Greek phrase &ldquo;<em>egō eime</em>&rdquo; (&ldquo;I am <em>he</em>&rdquo; or &ldquo;I am <em>the one</em>&rdquo;) and demonstrates that it is a phrase of self-identification, that is, the speaker is simply identifying himself.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; Exod. 3:14; John 1:1-9; 8:24; Mark 13:6; Matt. 14:27; Acts 26:29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-30', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:06', 57, 8, 'Abraham', 'ryHKLdl--Gc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ryHKLdl--Gc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 57, null),
(30, 1, 'Hebrews 1:8 - Verses used to Support the Doctrine of the Trinity', '<p>BiblicalUnitarian.com/verses is dedicated to helping you understand the verses that people try to use to support the doctrine of the Trinity.</p>', '2012-11-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:18', 0, 0, null, 'pcOiuMktRrU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pcOiuMktRrU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'inactive due to our understanding of Heb 1:8 changing.', 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(31, 1, 'Why did the Jews execute Jesus?', '<p>Jesus was not executed because he claimed to be God. Each of the four Gospels has a clear record that shows the Jews&rsquo; concern was whether or not he was the Christ, the Son of God. Jesus was finally asked this in a specific way which required his answer. When he said that he was indeed the Christ, this met the Jews&rsquo; definition of blasphemy, which was a capital offense.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 5:1; Matt. 26:63-65; Mark 15:12; John 10:24; 19:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-11-09', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '7:15', 0, 0, null, 'CQReQMW_Aw4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CQReQMW_Aw4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(32, 1, 'Consequences of Believing in the Trinity (Part 3)', '<p>The Trinitarian view of the holy spirit is misleading. God&rsquo;s Word declares that Holy Spirit is one of God&rsquo;s names and that God gives His spiritual nature, holy spirit, His gift, to believers at the new birth. When Trinitarians make the holy spirit a person, they are actually creating an idol.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:18; Luke 1:35; John 7:39; Acts 10:45; 2:28; 15:8; Eph.1:13; Rev. 22:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-17', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:19', 23, 3, null, 'n3osxfmL7uM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/n3osxfmL7uM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(33, 1, 'Consequences of Believing in the Trinity (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching continues to emphasize that the Bible is &ldquo;the&rdquo; textbook of truth. False theology fosters complacency, confusion, and contradiction. Trusting tradition muzzles or denies the truth. Finally, we need to know God&rsquo;s son, Jesus, as a man fully committed to working in unity with his Father.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:5; Num. 23:19; Acts 2:27; John 10:30; 17:11; 14:12; Luke 34:39; James 1:13; 1 Cor. 11:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-17', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:18', 23, 2, 'Knowledge', 'Wpg-gimse6w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Wpg-gimse6w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(34, 1, 'Consequences of Believing in the Trinity (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching shows there are consequences to believing wrong doctrine. Not knowing who God is, relying on the idea of mystery, manipulating vocabulary, and not following logic impede truth. The church needs to follow the Bible as the textbook, rather than the interpretations of men.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4; Isa. 1:18; Prov. 4:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-17', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:34', 23, 1, 'falsehood', 'w9B8ypkRV-g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w9B8ypkRV-g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(35, 1, 'The Jurisdiction of Satan', '<p>This teaching addresses questions such as: Who is causing all the problems in the world today? How are these problems represented to God? How are these problems dealt with? By what means do we understand the answers to these questions today?</p> <p>Verses: Luke 10:1-3, 17-19, 23; Rev. 12:1, 3-4, 7-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-05', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:31', 0, 0, 'Warfare, Angels, Satan', 'oIwSG1lgXyM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oIwSG1lgXyM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(36, 1, 'The Names and Titles of Jesus Christ', '<p>Jesus Christ is referred to in Scripture by approximately seventy-five different names, each describing one of his attributes. After his resurrection he is sometimes called &ldquo;the Spirit.&rdquo; This name refers to his life force being spirit-powered, in contrast to the soul-powered life which all mankind has during their &ldquo;natural&rdquo; lives.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:45; Rev. 1:10-13, 17-19; 2:7, 11, 17, 29; 3:6, 13, 22; 14:13; 22:17; 2 Cor. 3:17-18; Acts 10:19-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-01', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:15', 0, 0, null, 'Obo8-T0elA4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Obo8-T0elA4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 42, null),
(37, 1, 'Jesus Christ: a Life-Giving Spirit (Part 2)', '<p>People are born with a soul-powered body, but when they are raised from the dead to everlasting life, they will have a spirit-powered body. It will be the same kind of body that the resurrected Jesus has - with flesh and bone, but also able to pass through walls and change locations quickly.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 24:36-39; 1 Cor. 15:44, 45, 49; 2 Cor. 3:17; Phil. 3:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-30', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:17', 0, 0, 'ghost', 'u5UcLzPsShw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/u5UcLzPsShw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(38, 1, 'Jesus Christ: a Life-Giving Spirit (Part 1)', '<p>Adam was created with a soul-powered body; soul-powered bodies die. At the resurrection, Jesus will raise the dead and judge them to everlasting life or death. To those judged worthy, he will give the same kind of spirit powdered body that God energized in him when He raised him from the dead. Those found unworthy will perish forever.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:35, 42; John 5:17-19, 25-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-30', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:03', 0, 0, null, 'cIa45tOQOaE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cIa45tOQOaE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(39, 1, 'Verses that Support the Biblical Unitarian Position (Part 3)', '<p>To clearly define who Jesus Christ is, we need to dig deeply into Scripture for verses that are incontrovertible. Searching for truth can be challenging due to the many translations of the Bible. In our pursuit of accuracy, we look for the indisputable verses, and understand difficult verses in light of the indisputable ones.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 12:29, 30; 1 Tim. 2:5; John 1:1, 15; 10:29, 30, 34; 20:28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-07-02', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:14', 58, 3, 'tradition, trinity', 'zmWt156z_co', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zmWt156z_co/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(40, 1, 'Verses That Support the Biblical Unitarian Position (Part 2)', '<p>Trinitarian doctrine does not line up with clear biblical scriptures which define the identity of Christ. Multiple scriptures present Jesus as the created Son of God who was made Lord and Christ, who was a servant of God, who was in subjection to God, who received his authority from God and who was an heir of God.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:28; 17:3; 5:19; Acts 2:36; 4:24, 25, 27, 29, 30; 1 Cor. 15:22-28; Matt. 28:18; Phil. 2:9; Eph. 1:22, 23; Rom. 8:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-06-12', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:23', 58, 2, null, 'dKRSShwXYY8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dKRSShwXYY8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(41, 1, 'Verses That Support the Biblical Unitarian Position (Part 1)', '<p>The scriptures teach a simple, straightforward message that Jesus is the created Son of God. There is no need to manipulate Scripture to prove the doctrine of the Trinity when the Bible clearly states that Jesus was fully man and served the one exalted God of the universe.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:5; John 20:17; 1 Cor. 11:3; 3:22, 23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-06-08', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:09', 58, 1, 'servant', 'TFQ8ehq-erU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TFQ8ehq-erU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(42, 1, 'Does God Appear in Human Form? (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching shares insight into the many occasions when Yahweh has appeared in human form to people, both in the Old and New Testaments. In the future God Himself, who created us, loves us, and wants to have fellowship with us, will be with us for eternity.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:8; 12:7; 18:1; 28:13; Exod. 24:9-11; 1 Sam. 3:10; 1 Kings 3:5; 9:2; 11:9; Isa. 6:1, 5; Ezek. 1:26; Dan 7:9-10, 13; Amos 7:7; Acts 7:56; 5:1-7; Rev. 4:2; 5:1-7; 21:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:29', 0, 0, null, 'haHu8Yv6uwk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/haHu8Yv6uwk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(43, 1, 'Does God Appear in Human Form? (Part 1)', '<p>God created mankind so that He could intimately fellowship with us. Does He appear in human form to people or has no man seen God at any time? This teaching clears up this apparent contradiction and sheds light on some common misconceptions about God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:8; 18:1-2; Exod. 33:20; John 1:18; 14:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:42', 0, 0, 'glory, Yahweh', 'Ihftg5mfMgk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ihftg5mfMgk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(44, 1, 'Understanding Colossians 2:9', '<p>The Colossian church was not holding Christ as the head, so Paul exhorted them that the fullness of what God is lives bodily in Christ, and in him, we believers have that fullness too. We can have an impact in the world&mdash;for the works that he did, we can do also.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:23; 3:14-19; 4:13; Col. 2:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-27', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:03', 0, 0, null, 'P7TiOACN_2Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/P7TiOACN_2Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 49, null),
(45, 1, 'The Scriptural Case for Jesus Being the Human Son of God', '<p>This is a two-hour documentary from Restoration Fellowship moderated by Anthony Buzzard, with many theologians, academic scholars, rabbis, and laymen contributing. They discuss many reasons why the Bible points to Jesus as the son of God and not God himself. This is a comprehensive Scripture review on this theological debate concerning who Jesus is.</p> <p>Verses: Matt 16:16; Mark 12:28, 29; Deut. 6:4; John 1:1; Ps. 110:1; 1 John 5:7; 1 Tim. 2:5; 3:16; John 1:1; 8:28, 54; 10:30; 17:1-3; 2 Cor. 5:19; Isa. 9:6; 44:24; Phil. 2:5-11; Heb. 2:17</p> <p>Teacher: Anthony Buzzard</p>', '2011-11-18', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '1:59:20', 0, 0, 'Savior, Messiah, God, Jesus', 'LXADpdG6Uqc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LXADpdG6Uqc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'debate, not a teaching. Not active', 1, 0, null),
(46, 1, 'Revised and Improved BiblicalUnitarian.com Web Site', '<p>This video clip is a slideshow announcing improvements to the BiblicalUnitarian.com web site.</p>', '2011-11-11', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '0:34', 0, 0, null, '-Hz-i1vPFEg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-Hz-i1vPFEg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'promo, deactivated', 1, 0, null),
(47, 1, 'How Many is God? - Is God 1 or 3-in-1?', '<p>This clip from an Anthony Buzzard lecture contrasts the unitarian view of God as one, versus the trinitarian view that God is three persons with all three being one.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4</p> <p>Teacher: Sir Anthony Buzzard</p>', '2011-11-08', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '2:38', 0, 0, null, 'kOG-4_3vThE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kOG-4_3vThE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated', 1, 1, null),
(48, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Colossians 1:15-17', '<p>As a photograph is an image of a person, so Jesus is the image of God. Images are representations, not the original thing. God gave Jesus creative power and the context of Jesus&rsquo; creativity is the church, of which he is the head.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:18; 1 Cor. 11:7; Eph. 2:15; 4:8, 11; Col. 1:15-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-11-02', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:08', 57, 10, 'Church, Gifts, Jesus Christ, Law, New Covenant, Trinity', 'z-3kqcycivQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/z-3kqcycivQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(49, 1, 'Bible verses commonly used to try to support the Trinity', '<p>BiblicalUnitarian.com/verses is dedicated to help you understand the verses that people try to use to support the doctrine of the Trinity.</p>', '2011-10-20', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '1:36', 0, 0, null, 'K-V3AQs3JfY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/K-V3AQs3JfY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'promo, not active', 1, 1, null),
(50, 1, 'Debate: Anthony Buzzard vs Drew Ayers', '<p>Anthony Buzzard and Drew Ayers present their arguments to support or refute the stated resolution, in true debate style with rebuttals and closing statements, but with the addition of Q&amp;A at the end. Anthony Buzzard argues against the resolution and challenges audience members who agree with the resolution to take a couple of years to consider his arguments and search them out themselves.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26; 2:24; Exod. 3:1-14; Num. 2:64; Deut. 6:4; 2 Sam. 7:14; 2 Chron. 30:12; Pss. 82:6; 110:1; Isa. 41:1-4; 43:10, 12-13; 44:6, 24; 46:4; Matt. 1:20; Mark 12:28; John 1:1-3, 14; 5:18; 8:23-24, 56-59; 10:27-33; 13:18-19; 17:3, 11,22; 20:25-28; Acts 20:28; 1 Cor. 8:6; Col. 1:16; 1 Tim. 6:16; Titus 2:11-13; Heb. 1:8, 10; 2 Pet. 1:1, 11; 1 John 5:20; Rev. 1:8-11, 17-18; 2:8; 4:8-11; 5:1-3, 7, 11-14; 21:7; 22:12-13, 16.</p> <p>Teachers: Anthony Buzzard and Drew Ayers</p>', '2011-09-23', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '2:24:21', 0, 0, 'monotheism, polytheism, worship, creator, savior, Messiah', 'Po3PxtJIqZc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Po3PxtJIqZc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(51, 1, 'Mark 2:7 - Who can forgive sins but God alone?', '<p>As Christians, we have the holy spirit of God in us and powerful authority on earth as His ambassadors. As we walk in the spirit as God&rsquo;s representatives, we have the authority to do what He asks us to do, even to forgive sins.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 2:5-12; John 20:22-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-09-16', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '9:46', 0, 0, 'authority', 'hzPS9IkZWSo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hzPS9IkZWSo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(52, 1, 'Why is Jesus called Immanuel?', '<p>Names in the Bible are symbolic and bring meaning to enhance our understanding. Immanuel, &ldquo;God is with us,&rdquo; tells us that God will deliver in a unique and powerful way. He is with us through His Son, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 7:10-16; Matt. 1:22-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-09-16', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:12', 0, 0, 'trinity, unitarian', 'IRbVc8PLTdE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IRbVc8PLTdE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 39, null),
(53, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - John 1:1 (Part 2)', '<p>Is Jesus Christ God or the created Son of God? This teaching focuses on the Greek word <em>logos</em> from John 1:1. <em>L</em><em>ogos</em> has a wide range of meanings, and in John 1:1 it refers to the expression of God and His communication of His plans, purposes, and wisdom.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-09-15', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:26', 57, 7, 'trinity', 'VIM5IoG2Jb0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VIM5IoG2Jb0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 552, null),
(54, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - John 1:1 (Part 1)', '<p>Is Jesus Christ God or the created Son of God? This teaching explores the phrase &ldquo;and the Word was God&rdquo; from John 1:1, focusing on the Greek word <em><u>theos,</u></em> which is translated as &ldquo;God&rdquo; or &ldquo;god&rdquo;. In this instance, <em>theos</em> may legitimately be translated without the use of the indefinite article, or &ldquo;what God was, the Word was&rdquo;. The Word of God has the attributes of God.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-09-14', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '12:29', 57, 6, 'trinity', 'UhjyogASfWc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UhjyogASfWc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 10, null),
(55, 1, 'Verses Used to support the Trinity - John 10:30', '<p>Jesus said in this verse, &ldquo;I and the Father are one.&rdquo; In the context of this verse, Jesus is saying that no one is going to take sheep out of his or the Father&rsquo;s hand. In other New Testament passages, when two are considered one, the meaning is being of the same purpose, as in John 10:30, not that each one is identical to the other.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:30; John 17:21; 1 Cor. 3:6, 8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-25', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '9:12', 57, 9, null, 'k0JVVlWQonI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k0JVVlWQonI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 13, null),
(56, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Gen. 16:7 and Zech. 1:12', '<p>Both Genesis 16:7 and Zechariah 1:12 have the phrase &ldquo;the angel of the Lord.&rdquo; Some mainstream teachings insinuate this phrase refers to Jesus. This teaching presents four reasons why people believe it could be Jesus and four rebuttals why it is not.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 16:7; Zech. 1:12; Matt. 1:20, 24; John 10:35; Ps. 82:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-25', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:17', 57, 2, null, 'yLoyXPjJc2c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yLoyXPjJc2c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 27, null),
(57, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Genesis 1:1', '<p>The title <em>Elohim</em> can be singular or plural. It is also called a uni-plural noun because it can be singular while referring to a group. Rulers, judges, divine ones, angels, and God are all called <em>Elohim.</em> Use of a singular or plural pronoun associated with <em>Elohim</em> can help determine if it is singular or plural. In Genesis 1:1, it is singular with no hint of a compound nature.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1, 8; 35:2; Exod. 18:11; 21:6; 22:20; Judg. 6:31; Ps. 8:4, 5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-25', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:41', 57, 1, 'trinity', 'Rj7g8NCYEPM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Rj7g8NCYEPM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 76, null),
(58, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Deuteronomy 6:4', '<p>Faithful Jews of the Old and New Testament times were adamant about worshiping only one God whose personal name is Yahweh. This practice was in contrast to neighboring peoples who worshipped multiple gods. The Hebrew word for &ldquo;one,&rdquo; or &ldquo;alone,&rdquo; <em>echad,</em> never refers to a plurality. Jesus acknowledged this as he answered the question from the Pharisees when they asked him what the most important commandment was.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4-5; Gen. 1:5; 11:1; Mark 12:28-34</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-25', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '8:30', 57, 4, 'trinity', 'G0mnCaD_oIE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/G0mnCaD_oIE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(59, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Isaiah 9:6', '<p>The prophecy in Isaiah 9:6 calls the Messiah &ldquo;mighty God&rdquo; and &ldquo;everlasting Father.&rdquo; Although this seems to identify him as God, many men with authority in Scripture are called &ldquo;god,&rdquo; and some Bibles translate &ldquo;el&rdquo; as &ldquo;divine hero&rdquo; or &ldquo;mighty leader.&rdquo; &ldquo;Everlasting&rdquo; is also translated as &ldquo;age&rdquo; and &ldquo;father&rdquo; often refers to an &ldquo;important person.&rdquo; Thus, this verse can legitimately prophesize Jesus as leader of the coming Messianic Age.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 9:6; Ps. 82:1-7; John 10:34; Ezek. 31:11; 32:21; Isa. 9:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-23', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:30', 57, 5, 'trinity', '4kCUj5GDtPw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4kCUj5GDtPw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 44, null),
(60, 1, 'Verses Used to Support the Trinity - Genesis 1:26', '<p>It is often believed that when God said &ldquo;Let us make humankind in our image &hellip;&rdquo; He was speaking of Himself and a triune godhead. However, the word &ldquo;us&rdquo; can refer to a plural of majesty or to other beings nearby. This teaching gives examples of both in Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26; Ezra 4:7, 18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-22', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '6:28', 0, 0, null, '_ZAvHhFGFAI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_ZAvHhFGFAI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'This teaching focuses mostly on the plural of majesty, hence is inactive', 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(61, 1, 'Jesus Christ: Son of God - What does Son of God mean?', '<p>The phrase &ldquo;son of God&rdquo; means &ldquo;a created being from God.&rdquo; Adam, angels, and Christians are all called sons of God. Jesus Christ, the only begotten Son of God, is so called because he too was a created being from God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 6:2; Job 1:6; 2:1; Ps. 29:1; Dan. 3:25, 28; Luke 3:38; 20:35-36; 2 Cor. 5:17; Eph. 2:10; 1 John 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-06-17', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '11:16', 0, 0, null, 'EFiveawRXLY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EFiveawRXLY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 106, null),
(62, 1, 'Do You Have to Believe in the Trinity to be Saved?', '<p>Many churches teach that you have to believe in the Trinity to be saved. The Bible tells us what we need to believe in order to be saved. Does that include the Trinity? This teaching provides the biblical answer and advocates for Christians to be unified in the faith.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4; Acts 2:22, 24, 41, 47; 16:29-31; Matt. 19:16-17; Mark 12:29; John 4:25-26; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-06-10', 'BiblicalUnitarian', 0, '10:31', 0, 0, 'Lord, Yahweh, Messiah, confess, salvation', 'ClFbGDAYRIg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ClFbGDAYRIg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(63, 1, 'Developing Greater Intimacy with God', '<p>Through speaking in tongues, we can develop our intimacy with God, increase the power of prayer in our lives, and increase our confidence in the hope. Speaking in tongues is the evidence of the resurrected Christ in us and a witness that we are children of God.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 24:44-49; Acts 1:1-8; 2:1-4, 38-40; 5:29-32; 10:30-46; 11:1-18; 1 Cor. 14:1-5, 14-18; Eph. 8:18; Jude 20; Eph. 5:18; John 7:37-39; Mark 14:32-36; Gal. 4:1-7; Rom. 8:11-17</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-05-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:33', 0, 0, 'spirit, manifestations, thanksgiving, heirs', 'T-s7dAgqQxg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T-s7dAgqQxg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(64, 1, 'The Origin and Fall of Adam and Eve', '<p>This teaching is an in depth presentation on the meaning of &ldquo;created,&rdquo; &ldquo;made,&rdquo; and &ldquo;formed,&rdquo; and provides understanding on the origin of life on earth and what it means to be created in God&rsquo;s image. This includes a study of the fall of Adam and Eve and what God meant when He said &ldquo;in the day you eat of it you will die, yes die.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:24-25; 3:1-14; 2:15-17; 1:1; 2:4; Isa. 45:12, 18; Gen. 1:25; 2:19; 1:26-27; 9:6; 5:1; 2:7-8; Eccles. 7:9; Zech. 12:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:54', 0, 0, 'serpent, naked, crafty, evil, soul', '-2tqh1eRk68', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-2tqh1eRk68/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(65, 1, 'Overview of Colossians and Philemon', '<p>This comprehensive 4-hour webinar covers the entire books of Colossians and Philemon. Paul is writing from prison to Colossae to proclaim the Lordship of Jesus the Messiah, to make known the Sacred Secret, to declare that Paul&rsquo;s suffering is for their benefit, to address outside religious pressure, and to give instruction on the application of Jesus&rsquo; Lordship in their lives and relationships. The letter to Philemon encourages him to welcome back his escaped slave, Onesimus, as a fellow brother in Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Colossians and Philemon</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler and David Hutchings</p>', '2020-04-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '3:48:45', 0, 0, 'hope, head, body, regulations', 'BWPawo3KgfI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BWPawo3KgfI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(66, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues', '<p>The interpretation of tongues is a manifestation of the gift of holy spirit. This teaching takes us from the first experience of speaking in tongues on the Day of Pentecost to understanding the distinction between speaking in tongues in our personal communication with God and interpretation of tongues in a worship service.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:7-10; Gal. 1:11-12; Job 6:4; 7:11; Ps. 34:18; 51:17; 77:6; 1 Cor. 14:32; Heb. 5:13-14; 1 Cor. 14:1-22; Isa. 28:7-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:04', 0, 0, 'prophesy, prophecy, spirit, prayer, edification, thanksgiving, worship', 'WYlvkKQJ7T8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WYlvkKQJ7T8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(67, 1, 'Overview of the Book of Philemon', '<p>Paul sends a letter from prison to a friend and fellow worker in Colossae named Philemon concerning his escaped slave Onesimus who was of great service to Paul during his imprisonment.</p> <p>Verses: Philem. 1-25</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p> <p>Due to a technical issue, the beginning of this recording is cut off. We apologize for the inconvenience.</p>', '2020-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:19', 0, 0, 'encouragement, slave, prison, brother', 'T4k9mtJnQrA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T4k9mtJnQrA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(68, 1, 'How the Gift of Holy Spirit Works in Us', '<p>When we are born again of holy spirit, we become empowered to serve others through our individual ministries and to be witnesses about what the Lord has done. Learn how the Lord works in us in different ways at different times through our senses or our awareness of spiritual urgings.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8; 2:38; 1 Cor. 12:13; Eph. 4:4-6; 1:13-14; Acts 2:32-33; Joel 2:28; Acts 10:37-38; Num. 11:10-17, 25; Judg. 14:5-6; 1 Sam. 11:5-6; Acts 10:34-46; Judg. 6:33-34; 2 Chron. 24:18-21; Luke 24:48-49; Judg. 3:9-10; Exod. 28:3; Exod. 31:2-3 Luke 1:41; Acts 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:08', 0, 0, 'born, power, filled, clothed, promise', 'VUD9NlsYen4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VUD9NlsYen4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(69, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/26/2020) - Strength in Unity', '<p>This teaching titled &ldquo;Strength in Unity&rdquo; by Janet Speakes comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:47', 0, 0, null, 'ziDtIU0BuqQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ziDtIU0BuqQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(70, 1, 'Usages of &lsquo;spirit&rsquo; in the Bible.', '<p>Being better witnesses for Jesus Christ is aided by understanding how to walk in the power of the holy spirit. Seeing the different ways the word &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; is used in Scripture adds greatly to that understanding.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8; 10:38; John 4:23-24; Heb. 1:7; John 3:2-8; Heb. 1:7; Ezek. 37:1-14; John 3:2-8; 2 Cor. 3:17; Rev. 1:9-10; Num. 11:17; John 7:39; Luke 8:54-55; James 2:26; Luke 24:36; 1 Cor 15:44; 14:12, 32</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:15', 0, 0, 'breath, resurrection, body, life', 'LeehKsEnthk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LeehKsEnthk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 42, null),
(71, 1, 'Beloved Fellow-workers of Paul', '<p>Paul gives instruction to the people of Colossi. He sent his beloved friends and fellow workers for God a letter (the Epistle to the Colossians) to encourage them to show love to one another and to establish for them that we are all equal in Gods eyes.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 4:7-18</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-04-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:08:03', 0, 0, 'Servants, Encouragement', 'm3mls_H1LEA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m3mls_H1LEA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(72, 1, 'Stand Faithful, It&rsquo;s Worth It!', '<p>This teaching provides answers to the benefits of staying faithful. We are encouraged to be steadfast and avoid the temptations of life; to be defenders of the faith and steadfast in our support of God.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 73:1-28; Heb. 2:14; 2 Cor. 4:4; 1 John 5:15; Eph. 4:32</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:39', 0, 0, null, 'wRaI5byobfs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wRaI5byobfs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(73, 1, 'The Last Supper and the New Covenant', '<p>Jesus demonstrated at the Last Supper that his death would be the fulfillment of his perfect sacrifice, which allows believers forgiveness of all our sins, once and for all. Jesus established the new, everlasting covenant for those who believe.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 26:26; Luke 22:17-21; Rom. 8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:20:42', 0, 0, null, 'k29PY3ryqMg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k29PY3ryqMg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(74, 1, 'Faith in Practice', '<p>This teaching presents discussion of and suggestions on spending quiet time with the Lord. The teacher offers three keys to making prayerfulness consistent in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 4:2-6</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:57', 0, 0, null, 'WbCGNnLRI_U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WbCGNnLRI_U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(75, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (Easter, 2020) - Covenants: Part 10 (The New Covenant)', '<p>This is part 10 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2020-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:36', 0, 0, null, 'CqthgyV5vpE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CqthgyV5vpE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(76, 1, 'The Death, Burial and Resurrection of Jesus', '<p>This teaching chronicles the details of the last days of Jesus&rsquo; life - his arrest in the garden, his trials before the High Priest and Pilate, his crucifixion, his death, his burial, and the victory of his resurrection.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 23:44-50; Matt. 12:40; Genesis 8:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:25', 0, 0, null, 'U_SQvZCCaLQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U_SQvZCCaLQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(77, 1, 'The Last Supper of Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching expounds the details of Jesus&rsquo; coming betrayal and being taken into custody. He was well-aware of his coming suffering and torment, in spite of his innocence. In Jesus&rsquo; perfect walk with his Father, he completed his purpose.</p> <p>Verses: John 12:23-27; John 12:44</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:53', 0, 0, null, 'zvnuFrP4a7g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zvnuFrP4a7g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(78, 1, 'Practicing the Lordship of Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching on the final verses of Colossians 3 addresses the practical aspects of various relationships in the Body of Christ &ndash; husbands, wives, children, servants and masters. We are all to be subject to the Lordship of Jesus Christ in our lives. As such, we are all servants of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:18-25; 4:1</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-04-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:28', 0, 0, null, 'a5kJPHXS-RI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/a5kJPHXS-RI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(79, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/01/2020) - Revelation: Part 4', '<p>**Just realized I forgot to upload chapter 5&#39;s teaching! Enjoy.</p>', '2020-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:36', 0, 0, null, '6QyDxp7-9zg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6QyDxp7-9zg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe teaching on Revelation', 1, 0, null),
(80, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/05/2020) - Revelation: Part 6', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:08', 0, 0, null, 'h4RcsjTDAGI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/h4RcsjTDAGI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(81, 1, 'Gideon&rsquo;s Call', '<p>Gideon pushes through fear to end Israel&rsquo;s famine caused by the 7-year Midianite oppression. God appears to Gideon as an angel and promises &ldquo;Surely I will be with you.&rdquo; There are many keys in this well-known record that can be applied to our lives today.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:45', 0, 0, null, 'BsfCDeFPfAA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BsfCDeFPfAA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(82, 1, 'Jesus&rsquo; Last Week on Earth', '<p>This teaching chronicles the last 7 days of Jesus&rsquo; life, and the events leading up to his crucifixion: the Last Supper, Jesus&rsquo; arrest, the two mock trials he experienced, the beatings and humiliation he endured, Peter&rsquo;s denials, and more. It&rsquo;s helpful to have a good understanding of this most significant event in human history.</p> <p>Verses: John 17-18; Matt. 26:57-63; Luke 22:66</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:41', 0, 0, 'Last Days; Lords Supper; Persecution', 'oSgIC2wGA-o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oSgIC2wGA-o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(83, 1, 'Who we are as Christians', '<p>This teaching explains some of the things that God tells us to do, especially &ldquo;love Yahweh your God, walk in His ways and keep His commandments&rdquo; so that He can bless us. Yahweh warns us of the consequences if we turn away and do not listen.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:11-20; Phil. 4:2-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:19', 0, 0, 'everlasting', '_9NcZmuUrn8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_9NcZmuUrn8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(84, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/29/2020) - Covenants: Part 9', '<p>This is part 9 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2020-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:13', 0, 0, null, '0WUq-_D4_2k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0WUq-_D4_2k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(85, 1, 'Making Jesus Lord in Every Aspect of our Lives', '<p>We are encouraged to seek things from above, not on the earth. The peace of Christ is to be the umpire in our hearts, and we are to always be giving thanks to God the Father through him.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:41', 0, 0, 'Encouragement; Attitude', 'rN7IY9H7gfI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rN7IY9H7gfI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(86, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/22/2020) - Revelation: Part 5', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:33', 0, 0, null, 'hxGL8M6s704', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hxGL8M6s704/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(87, 1, 'Judges, the &lsquo;No Excuse&rsquo; Book of the Bible', '<p>This teaching is an overview of the book of Judges. There are 12 judges in the Book of Judges, each one with a shortcoming, and yet each one prospering and accomplishing their &ldquo;divine appointment&rdquo; through God&rsquo;s covering and equipping of each one as only He could do. We are to focus on the strengths that we have, and use those to fulfill our ministries.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:58', 0, 0, 'Gideon Samson', '8Q8FrqSL6Tw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8Q8FrqSL6Tw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(88, 1, 'The Lord Jesus, Your Rock In Every Circumstance', '<p>How strong is your Lord in a storm? Who or what do you lean on in a storm - religion, government, yourself? How real is Christ in your life? Listen to this fellowship teaching to consider the answers to these questions.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 2:16-23; Heb. 8:5; 10:1; Matt. 15</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:56', 0, 0, 'Lordship, Asceticism', 'Frn4sfT11ws', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Frn4sfT11ws/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(89, 1, 'God Gave Us Everything We Need', '<p>Jewish synagogues in Corinth contained scrolls of the Law of Moses and the Tanakh of the prophets. During Paul&rsquo;s stay there, he taught in those synagogues about Jesus the Messiah from the Old Testament scriptures that the people understood, and then showed them how Jesus fulfilled all the law and prophets. Enjoy this deep exploration into Colossians 2:8-23 with historical and cultural context, and discover its profound relevance to today.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 2:1; Col. 2:8-23; Eph. 3:19; Heb. 2:14-15; 2 Tim. 4:5-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:10', 0, 0, 'Trinity, spirit, Salvation, Identity', 'DwX-MKti6Ko', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DwX-MKti6Ko/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(90, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (3/15/2020) - Abraham and Isaac', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:02', 0, 0, null, 'hX6ueL-cQBo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hX6ueL-cQBo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(91, 1, 'Is Jesus Lord Of Every Area Of Your Life?', '<p>What does it look like to behave like Jesus, firmly rooted, built up and established, so that you can endure through the pressures and pleasures of life? How strong is your Lord in a storm? Learn relevant answers to these questions from this real letter to the Colossians, written by a real person to real people who shared similar challenges to ours.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 2:6-15; Matt. 13:18-23; 1 Cor. 3:10-14</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:38', 0, 0, 'endurance', 'a_TcfbUHEBs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/a_TcfbUHEBs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(92, 1, 'How Your Inner Self is Strengthened and How to Break the Sin Cycle', '<p>This 2-part teaching discusses the inner self and why there is still sin in the world after the sacrifice of Christ. How am I stronger as a Christian because of the way holy spirit has worked in my life? What happens with the everyday sins in the world after the perfect sacrifice of Jesus Christ? Consider some biblical answers to these questions in this fellowship video.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:14-17; Rom. 7:21-23; 2 Cor. 4:8-10, 16-18; Col. 1:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:36', 0, 0, 'forgiveness', 'WMx3gbSzILM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WMx3gbSzILM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(93, 1, 'What is the Sacred Secret for the Church?', '<p>Paul establishes himself as a legitimate teacher to the Colossians and expresses his great love and concern for them even though they have never seen him face to face. He admonishes them to be encouraged and be knit together in love. In this section of Colossians Paul also reveals an aspect of the sacred secret.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:24-2:5</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p> <p>Due to a technical issue, the beginning of this teaching was not recorded. We apologize for the inconvenience.</p>', '2020-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:08', 0, 0, 'mystery', 'oe152ZDoqBU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oe152ZDoqBU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(94, 1, 'Is Jesus Christ the Head of the Church?', '<p>Paul wrote to show the Colossians that Jesus Christ is the one their focus should be on, not their ancient pagan roots, Gnosticism, or Judaism ways. He goes on to show how and why Jesus Christ is qualified to be that one.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:30', 0, 0, 'firstborn', 'GcuHNHw66ro', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GcuHNHw66ro/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(95, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Plan of Redemption', '<p>The Good News is about redemption, what that is, and the hope that is embedded in it. Jesus&rsquo; role and position and our role and position in God&rsquo;s plan is explained.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:15-23</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-02-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '54:15', 0, 0, 'Firstborn, reconciliation, image, rescued', '6IVDSivOKmc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6IVDSivOKmc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(96, 1, 'Remain Steadfast in the Faith', '<p>This teaching is about the Apostle Paul&rsquo;s exhortation to young Timothy to show the importance of staying in sound doctrine, not being ashamed of the Gospel, and not letting others belittle us because of our youth.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:17-37; 1 Tim. 1:3-7; 4:1-5, 12; 6:3-5, 20-21; 2 Tim. 1:8-17; 2:15-19; 3:1-17; 4:1-4, 9-18</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-02-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:47', 0, 0, 'Ashamed, Suffering, Youth, Encourage, Persecution', 'oVt3TqsFoDY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oVt3TqsFoDY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(97, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (2/24/2020) - Covenants: Part 8', '<p>This is part 8 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2020-02-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:23', 0, 0, null, 'eAQECl2bAZA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eAQECl2bAZA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(98, 1, 'Three Major Concepts of the Gospel', '<p>Paul was thankful for the Colossians because of their acceptance of the Good News that had been delivered to them by Epaphras. Subsequently he prayed continually for them, that they would be filled with the knowledge and wisdom of the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-02-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:36', 0, 0, null, 'DWapnsEB19U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DWapnsEB19U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(99, 1, 'Choose this Day Whom You Will Serve', '<p>We are shown the importance of serving God only, and no other gods. In our day and time, these gods can seem harmless, like lucky charms, or perhaps even the horoscope. We must choose whom we will serve.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 24:1-29; 2 Cor. 5:20; Deut. 6:10-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:32', 0, 0, 'Habit, Legate', 'QqWP28kJsI8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QqWP28kJsI8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(100, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (2/2/2020) - God''s Stewards: Part 1', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:36', 0, 0, null, 'RDh2GuhaWvg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RDh2GuhaWvg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(101, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (2/16/2020) - The Book of Revelation: Part 3', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:50', 0, 0, null, '437yE09O8d0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/437yE09O8d0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(102, 1, 'Backdrop of the Time and Writing of Colossians', '<p>An overview from the Book of Acts, of when and from where Paul wrote this letter to the Colossians, especially concerning which missionary trip he was on and the area of the Roman empire which had heard the Good News.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:1, 6; 19:8-10; 28:16-20, 23, 30-31</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:48', 0, 0, 'Asia, Ephesus, Achaia, Journey', 'TJ4wOfhj4zw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TJ4wOfhj4zw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(103, 1, 'Life is Hard', '<p>The grace of God works in our Christian walk, but life is definitely not a smooth path. We are to serve one another with the gifts God has given us and not be ashamed or surprised when suffering shows up.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Pet. 4:7-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:11', 0, 0, 'Sensible, Hospitality, Grumbling, Bitterness', 'ZfyVv-iKz78', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZfyVv-iKz78/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(104, 1, 'Fanning Your Gift into Flame', '<p>A review of many problems that existed within the Corinthian church alerts us to the importance of heeding our calling in the Body of Christ. We gain insight into the special relationship the Apostle Paul had with Timothy. Each believer has a unique God-given ability to serve and bless others.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:6; 1 Cor. 12:12-27, 31</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p> <p>Note: This teaching was inspired by Jeff Tyler&rsquo;s teaching called &ldquo;<a href="https://spirittruth.podbean.com/e/stir-up-the-gift/" target="_blank">Stir Up the Gift</a>.&rdquo;</p>', '2020-02-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:00', 0, 0, null, 'KKX1vkQrnT4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KKX1vkQrnT4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(105, 1, 'Think About What Christ has Done for You', '<p>The first part of this teaching explains the meaning of the names Melchizedek and Adoni-Zedek, then uses an illustration from Jeremiah for a lesson on the spiritual battle we all face every day. The second part is an in-depth teaching on the meaning and significance of the sin offering. We learn about the Christian believer&rsquo;s righteousness in God&rsquo;s sight because Christ died in our place.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 14:18; Josh. 10:1; Jer. 12:1, 5; Lev. 1:1-5; 2 Cor. 5:20-21; Rom. 5:6-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:24', 0, 0, 'names, atonement', 'HSs5XpowlPI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HSs5XpowlPI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(106, 1, 'Seek the Things Which are Above', '<p>As we seek those things which are above, we shine as lights in the world. Jesus set the example of how we should resist following &ldquo;man-made&rdquo; religious rules and traditions. This teaching illustrates how we grow up in Christ by avoiding pitfalls of doctrines and commandments of people.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 2:8-23; 3:1-14; Matt. 15:1-20; Eph. 4:14-15</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2020-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:09', 0, 0, null, 'nbryrUW0DsQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nbryrUW0DsQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(107, 1, 'Don''t Complain', '<p>This record in the book of Joshua shows how to deal with complaining and complainers in a godly way. Israelite tribal boundaries come into play as the leader Joshua had to take a firm stand when the children of Joseph, Ephraim and Manasseh, complained about their allotment and used various tactics to try to get their own way.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 17:14-18; Judg. 1:27-29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:49', 0, 0, null, 'HxVzDF5KT_E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HxVzDF5KT_E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(108, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (1/26/2019) - Covenants: Part 7', '<p>This is part 7 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2020-01-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:45', 0, 0, null, 'uEhDD5CcEbM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uEhDD5CcEbM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(109, 1, 'The Mighty Works of God', '<p>Throughout the Bible we see the mighty works of God &mdash; in His Creation, in God&rsquo;s preserving of the Israelite people until the arrival of Jesus Christ, on the Day of Pentecost, in the revealing of the Sacred Secret, and much more to come in the future. We can be so comforted and encouraged to know that we are actually a part of the mighty works of God.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:1-11; Gen. 1; 2:2-3; Ps. 19:1-4; 139:1-3, 13-14; Luke 1:46-49; John 3:16-17; Rom. 10:9; Eph. 1:3-14</p> <p>Teacher: Pat Sweeney</p>', '2020-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:42', 0, 0, 'encouragement', '_RdDNTIv54A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_RdDNTIv54A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(110, 1, 'Serving Others through the Lordship of Jesus Christ', '<p>In order to truly love and serve others, we need to understand what it means that Jesus is our Lord, and then understand what to do with that information. This teaching will strengthen and encourage you as you approach relationships within the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:1; 12:1-2; Heb. 5:1-9; 2:9, 14-18</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Bolen</p>', '2020-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:41', 0, 0, null, 'w4pYji1Ttv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w4pYji1Ttv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(111, 1, 'Bringing the Spiritual Reality of Peace into the Human Realm', '<p>God wants us to experience peace with Him and with each other. Jesus proclaimed the good news of peace. The spiritual reality is that we are at peace with God and each other now. This teaching offers great insight as to how to carry out that spiritual reality and live it together.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:11-25; 2:1-22; 3:1-21; 4:1-6; Col. 3:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-01-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:55', 0, 0, null, 'mZNmsolFGCY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mZNmsolFGCY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(112, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (1/19/20) - The Book of Revelation: Part 2', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:50', 0, 0, null, 'Ud7ibi1ibqo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ud7ibi1ibqo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(113, 1, 'The Marriage Banquet of the Lamb', '<p>Jesus speaks of a great feast in the Messianic Kingdom on a number of occasions. This teaching invites you to consider yourself at this giant banquet in the future Messianic Kingdom that will be held for the righteous &ndash; those people who trust God. We look forward with hope to an abundance of food and wine along with generous portions of peace, prosperity and joy.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 8:5-13; Isa. 25:6; Rev. 19:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-01-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:24', 0, 0, 'millennium', 'XP5ein10wbI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XP5ein10wbI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(114, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (1/13/20) - Doing it God''s Way', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-01-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:39', 0, 0, null, 'DEZ0QdR-rJI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DEZ0QdR-rJI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(115, 1, 'Speaking In Tongues', '<p>This begins with a fellowship discussion of changes in understanding of scripture over time through study and research. The focus then shifts to a study of speaking in tongues, including the records from Acts where people spoke in tongues upon receiving the gift of holy spirit, the importance of speaking in tongues, and doing it in love.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:4-5, 8; Acts 2:1-11; Acts 8:13-17; Acts 10:34-46; 1 Cor. 13</p> <p>Teacher: Rob Woods</p>', '2020-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:11', 0, 0, 'basics', 'nQDJAzkLT7U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nQDJAzkLT7U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(116, 1, 'Happy New Year Resolution', '<p>It&rsquo;s a new year! This teaching offers encouragement to make it a &ldquo;driving ambition&rdquo; to be pleasing to the Lord as our touchstone going forward into the new year. We want to live in a way that pleases the Lord now, and we want to live in a way that the Lord will be pleased with us on the Day of Judgement.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:00', 0, 0, 'rewards, suffering', 'jLHgBLb7dG4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jLHgBLb7dG4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(117, 1, 'The Good News of Ephesians', '<p>This fellowship is a group discussion of the use of the phrase &ldquo;Good News&rdquo; which is used seven times in the Book of Ephesians. Hear how we are blessed to be sealed and at peace with God because of The Good News.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:13; 2:17; 3:6-8; 6:15, 19</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2020-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:00:04', 0, 0, 'gospel', 'NsjTKQGAobM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NsjTKQGAobM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(118, 1, 'The Christmas Story: The Shepherds and the Magi', '<p>This teaching dispels some of the traditions surrounding the Christmas story from the Gospels of Matthew and Luke. The Gospel of Luke describes the shepherds&rsquo; angelic encounter and their visit to see Mary, Joseph and the baby Jesus in a manger. The Gospel of Matthew describes a much later visit by the Magi to Mary, Joseph and the child Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:8-24, 39-40; Matt. 2:1-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:12', 0, 0, 'angels, herod', 'jKYYZGQWPL0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jKYYZGQWPL0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(119, 1, 'The Christmas Story: Joseph and Mary', '<p>The Gospels of Luke and Matthew weave together distinct details of the birth of Jesus through the lives of Joseph and Mary. As descendants of the house of David, both Joseph and Mary respond to their godly calling with humility and obedience.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:26-56; 2:1-7; Matt. 1:18-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:06:16', 0, 0, 'genealogy', 'f01vQt2ckcc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f01vQt2ckcc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(120, 1, 'Giving at Christmas', '<p>Gift-giving traditions at Christmas encourage the godly attributes of generosity and thoughtfulness. Consider Christmas as a loving and godly reminder to reset habits of cheerful giving to the poor and needy.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 15:1-11; Ps. 37:14; 72:1-4; 112:5-9; Matt. 19:16-22; Acts 2:44-45; 4:33-35; 2 Cor. 9:6-8; Gal. 6:9-19</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2020-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:03', 0, 0, null, 'zd3WVTVH-HU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zd3WVTVH-HU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
