(121, 1, 'Be Hospitable', '<p>The importance of hospitality is emphasized throughout Scripture. Hospitality is more highly valued in Eastern cultures than western, but the Church Epistles encourage believers, especially leaders in the Church, to practice hospitality.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 58:1-8; 1 Tim. 3:1-2; Titus 1:7; 1 Pet. 4:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:54', 0, 0, 'witnessing', 'Vzd3f8BTwbs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vzd3f8BTwbs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(122, 1, 'The Christmas Story: Zechariah and Elizabeth', '<p>The birth story of John the Baptist is told through the experience of John&rsquo;s parents (Zechariah and Elizabeth) in Luke 1. The Messiah that believers had been waiting 4,000 years to see was about to come, and John would be the messenger and forerunner of the Messiah prophesied about in the Old Testament.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:5-25, 57-80</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:12:47', 0, 0, null, 'qur_UN51sPY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qur_UN51sPY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(123, 1, 'Encouragement Through the Scriptures Brings Hope', '<p>Psalm 89 is used to poignantly illustrate how Jesus, because he studied and knew the Scriptures, must have drawn encouragement and hope through them. The culture and landscape surrounding him surely made the Scriptures live. Understand why the Biblical landscape is called the &ldquo;Fifth Gospel&rdquo;.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 89; Rom. 15:4</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-01-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:33:09', 0, 0, 'patience, perseverance, instruction, faithfulness', 'omMu4n0BOX0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/omMu4n0BOX0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(124, 1, 'Wage War On Your Sin', '<p>The subtleties between Old Testament circumcision and that in the New Testament are explained. The battle which needed to be fought and won before Joshua and the Israelites conquered the 31 kingdom-cities in the Promised Land is exposed, as well as the take-away for believers today.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:2-3; Gal. 6:11-13; Josh. 12:7; Gen. 17:9-14; Josh. 5:2-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:26', 0, 0, 'Gilgal, foreskins', 'dvecq063UAU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dvecq063UAU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(125, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (1/5/20) - The Book of Revelation: Part 1', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:23', 0, 0, null, 'odE8WEVbKVs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/odE8WEVbKVs/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(126, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/19/20) - The Messianic Secret', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:55', 0, 0, null, 'BYzvfD4DMPg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BYzvfD4DMPg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(127, 1, 'The Secret of Contentment and the Quality of Generosity', '<p>This section in Philippians contains two primary themes: being content no matter the circumstances and the quality of generosity. The ultimate understanding of these principles is often missed or not taught, but gives added insight and helps Christians set more realistic expectations in their lives.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 4:10-23</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-12-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:28', 0, 0, 'rejoicing, thankfulness, need', '6xeHn4JXw5Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6xeHn4JXw5Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(128, 1, 'Be Assured   God is Working', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2019-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:53', 0, 0, null, '_QaejzBSXeQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_QaejzBSXeQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(129, 1, 'The Purpose of Fellowship - Encouragement', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2019-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:53', 0, 0, null, 'GL9ig0hUqvw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GL9ig0hUqvw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(130, 1, 'No More Regrets in My Life - Ever', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2019-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:08', 0, 0, null, 'ZHoiNLF-pEY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZHoiNLF-pEY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(131, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/24/2019) - Covenants: Part 6', '<p>This is part 6 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:20', 0, 0, null, 'u3Vne7yMZcs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/u3Vne7yMZcs/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(132, 1, 'Next Gen', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2019-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:20', 0, 0, null, 'E9GdYjfrE0k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E9GdYjfrE0k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(133, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/17/2020) - Covenants: Part 5', '<p>This is part 5 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-11-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:40', 0, 0, null, '091DMjpIaO0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/091DMjpIaO0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(134, 1, 'Knowing God Through the Lord Jesus', '<p>From the beginning, God has had a purpose for man. Through the ages, He has provided ways to attain that purpose. By examining verses throughout the Bible, we see the various ways God provided to achieve this. Finally, in the epistles we find the pinnacle of what a person can do in this life.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:7-11; Gen. 1:27; 3:15; Eccles. 12:13; John 14:1-10; 17:1-3, 20-22, 25, 26; Eph. 1:3-10</p> <p>Teacher: Pat Sweeney</p>', '2019-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:13', 0, 0, 'experience, holy, spirit, gift', 'hU8NPtwZO6o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hU8NPtwZO6o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(135, 1, 'Pressing Toward The Prize While Looking At The Hope', '<p>This study examines the goal Christians should strive to achieve. It also uncovers the keys that enable them to press forward even while experiencing the sufferings of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:12-4:1; 1 Cor. 9:24-27</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:36', 0, 0, 'race, mature, relationship', 'WFQTBUgzNHs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WFQTBUgzNHs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(136, 1, 'Experiencing The Lord Jesus In Our Lives Every Day', '<p>When Jesus was physically present with his disciples on the earth, they were interacting, experiencing, learning, growing, and being encouraged and comforted by him every day. Not only can we experience Jesus through the Scriptures, but also we can understand how the promise of the Father that Jesus sent after he ascended enables us to experience Jesus individually, uniquely, and in a multiplicity of ways.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 3:5; Luke 24:13-53; John 16:1-18; 1 Pet. 1:23; 2 Pet. 1:4; 2 Cor. 5:17; Gal. 5:17; John 16:9-15; 14:18, 20-21,26; 15:26; 16:13-14</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Bolen</p>', '2019-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:19:37', 0, 0, 'trinity, power, endurance, relationship', 'AwvrTvNvjxU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AwvrTvNvjxU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(137, 1, 'Are You A Guardian of Truth?', '<p>Paul encourages believers to keep the traditions that they have learned and seen in him. He warns Timothy of false teachers and doctrines, and of those who have already fallen away from those traditions. An early Christian document is used to illustrate how quickly the teachings of Paul disintegrated and disappeared. Looking at Paul&rsquo;s words to Timothy, we must decide what we need to do with the truth we have.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 11:1-2; 2 Thess. 2:15; 3:6-15; 1 Tim. 4:1-3, 12-16; 6:20-21; 2 Tim. 1:8-12; 2:15-19</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:46', 0, 0, 'vigilance, relationship, reprove, admonish', 'ubOuZcRFh6U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ubOuZcRFh6U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(138, 1, 'Keys To Always Rejoicing In The Lord', '<p>In this section of Philippians, Paul addresses the Judaizers about having confidence in circumcision of the flesh and not having confidence in Jesus Christ in whom true circumcision lies. Paul tells them that all the accomplishments of his past are nothing compared to the exceeding greatness of knowing Christ personally and experientially now and having hope of this in the future. He discloses three keys to always rejoicing in the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-11-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:12:41', 0, 0, 'humility, righteousness', 'UTVhILx9GqQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UTVhILx9GqQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(139, 1, 'Fighting the Good Fight of Faith', '<p>Paul exhorts Timothy to stand up and &ldquo;fight the good fight&rdquo;. The devil has devised many causes in the world. Christians should not be distracted by them or complacent but instead take a stand for the &ldquo;good&rdquo; fight. They must determine what the &ldquo;good&rdquo; fight is, know that God loves them, and make themselves known in a world of darkness.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 1:18, 3-4, 6; 1 Tim. 4:7; 2 Tim. 1:16-17, 23; Titus 1:13-14; 3:9; 1 Tim. 2:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:22', 0, 0, 'worldliness, genealogies, witchcraft, politics', '9Xjk3PyRA-g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9Xjk3PyRA-g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(140, 1, 'Contending Together in the Faith - One Heart/One Soul', '<p>We are encouraged to build significant relationships in the body of Christ. Following the Biblical examples (or relationships) of Paul and Timothy and Epaphroditus, we learn how to help others to grow up into their &ldquo;best selves&rdquo; in serving and loving others - no matter how difficult the life event.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 2:19-30; Acts 16:1-5; 17:14,15; 1 Thess. 3:1-7; 1 Cor. 4:14-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:16:22', 0, 0, 'emulate, service', 'te6SR9QRtYs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/te6SR9QRtYs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(141, 1, 'Obedience to God Produces Great Rewards', '<p>This teaching encourages inward and outward holiness and obedience to God&rsquo;s Commands. The record of Joshua leading Israel into the Promised Land illustrates how through complete obedience one experiences God&rsquo;s presence and success.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 3:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:01', 0, 0, 'reward, trust, commandments, revelation, relationship, leadership, miracles', 'y-eMQnO_khM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y-eMQnO_khM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(142, 1, 'Christ: Our Highest Example of Humility and Service', '<p>In-depth study of the book of Philippians continues in this on-line fellowship meeting. What does it mean that Jesus took the form of a servant? The Greek word for &ldquo;form&rdquo; &ndash; &ldquo;morphe&rdquo; &ndash; is explained. Through the example of Christ, we learn how to choose to empty ourselves of worldly pride and status and to put on obedient service to others.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:27; 2:1-18; Heb. 12:2; 2 Pet. 5:5-7; 2 Tim. 4:6-8</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p> <p><small>(Note: the first couple minutes of this teaching were not recorded due to a technical issue)</small></p>', '2019-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:14', 0, 0, null, '8xloNuihdrc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8xloNuihdrc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(143, 1, 'Transformation Through the Power of Choice', '<p>Through the historical account of the believers in Philippi, we receive a rich understanding of what it means to put off human arrogance, and to be transformed into the humility of Christ. Through transformation, we can choose to &ldquo;get over ourselves&rdquo; and become like Christ, selfless for others.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 2:5-18; Rom. 1:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:31', 0, 0, 'trinity, servant, humble', 'wvSylL5Wj00', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wvSylL5Wj00/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(144, 1, 'Praying Before Meals', '<p>This teaching encourages prayer before meals out of gratitude for all that Christ accomplished for us. Though prayer before meals is not a commandment, Jesus gave us the example to pray before eating, as did Paul. Also woven into this message is our sacred covenant with Jesus. Prayer before meals is a wonderful reminder that Jesus is the bread of life.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 8:6-9; 14:22; Matt. 15:35-38; 26:26; John 6:19-13, Luke 24:13, 28; 22:17; Acts 27:33-37; 1 Cor. 10:16; John 13:1</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2019-10-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:24', 0, 0, 'blessing, thanksgiving, covenant', '7QQqPrA-gNg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7QQqPrA-gNg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(145, 1, 'Contending Selflessly for the Faith', '<p>As citizens of heaven, we are urged to stand firm in one spirit, one heart, one soul, and one mind while we contend together for the faith. We are exhorted not to fear or be intimidated by our enemies, because we have been given the privilege to stand as fellow laborers with Christ. As believers, we have a godly obligation to look out for the best interests of others.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:27-30; 2:1-4; 3:17; 4:1-4; 1 Cor. 15:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-10-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:06', 0, 0, 'citizenship, commitment, laborers, suffer', 'MmrcLAmFIMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MmrcLAmFIMY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(146, 1, 'Seek Godly Wisdom and Live out His Truth', '<p>This teaching from the Book of Ecclesiastes makes multiple points: God is the giver of all life; enjoy life because it is temporary; when a person dies, their life force is gone until the resurrection; the whole purpose of mankind is to fear God and to keep His commandments.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 12:1-14; 3:18-23; 9:2-6; Prov. 12:7; 2:6-9; Phil. 3:21; Titus 1:9; Matt. 5:29-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:40', 0, 0, 'death, Gehenna, breath, wisdom, truth', 'TwMlCcppKzU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TwMlCcppKzU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(147, 1, 'Philippians 1:12-26: Paul&rsquo;s Prison Experience', '<p>This is Part 3 of a verse-by-verse study of Philippians. Several types of Roman incarceration are described, including Paul&rsquo;s experience. Paul writes why he was encouraged while in prison and exhorts those who read the letter to advance the good news of Christ. Paul&rsquo;s focus is the spread the gospel whether he is alive or dead, however, he looks forward to being with the believers of Philippi again.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:12-26</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-10-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:01', 0, 0, 'Boldness, Rejoice', '1ehF8ygBxvo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1ehF8ygBxvo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(148, 1, 'God Wants You to Enjoy Life!', '<p>Sometimes evil people thrive and righteous people suffer, which seems unjust. Life is unpredictable, so God recommends we enjoy life now. Enjoy what you eat and drink, and be joyful in this life you have, for the dead have no enjoyment and know nothing.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 8:12-15; 9:1-8; Jer. 12:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:17', 0, 0, null, 'CTTu4uV7WLc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CTTu4uV7WLc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(149, 1, 'Philippians 1:1-11: Paul&rsquo;s Greeting', '<p>This is part 2 of a verse-by-verse study of Philippians. This section covers who the book is from (Paul and Timothy), who it is to (believers at Philippi), and an encouraging greeting. Paul acknowledges the Philippians&rsquo; gift sent to him in prison, their love for one another, and their continuing in the faith by serving their local church.</p> <p>Verses: Phil 1:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-10-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:05', 0, 0, 'Joy, Prayer', 'HG3s14uQn7A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HG3s14uQn7A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(150, 1, 'How God Works in Our Circumstances', '<p>Jesus said he didn&rsquo;t do anything on his own but followed the Father&rsquo;s lead. So should we. Scripture is full of examples where God &ldquo;goes to bat&rdquo; for His people. In the same way that a vine can produce no fruit unless attached to a branch, so we, the vine, are dependent on God, the branch, to succeed, especially in the spiritual realm.</p> <p>Verses: John 5:30; 15:5; Eccles. 9:11; Ps. 33:16; Exod. 14:5-28; Josh. 6:1-20; 10:5-15; 2 Chron. 20:1-12, 22-24.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:10', 0, 0, 'Union, Jericho, Miracles', 'gs4i52j5Kxo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gs4i52j5Kxo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(151, 1, 'An Introduction to the Book of Philippians', '<p>This study addresses the background of Paul&rsquo;s letter to the Philippians from the viewpoint of the Book of Acts - the cities Paul visited and the people he traveled with and encountered along his second missionary journey. The emphasis is on being led by the holy spirit which applies today, too. The spirit-led life is not always a smooth road, but there are blessings along the way.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:1-40</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-10-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:08:38', 0, 0, 'Lystra, Lydia, Timothy, Jail, Missions', 'FlBJa5rO0MY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FlBJa5rO0MY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(152, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/22/2019) - Covenants: Part 4', '<p>This is part 4 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:11', 0, 0, null, 'muD8jIxKGdg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/muD8jIxKGdg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(153, 1, 'God and the Devil Are at War and God Needs Us to Fight for Him', '<p>The whole world is under the power of &ldquo;the evil one.&rdquo; Jesus exposed the evil in the world as being of the Devil. But God is a warrior and is leading His Church in this spiritual battle. God has called us to join Him in continuing to fight against the dark powers of this age.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 4:3-6; 1 John 5:19; 2 Cor. 4:4; John 12:31; Heb. 2:14-15; Exod. 15:1-3; John 8:37-44; Matt. 28:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:30', 0, 0, 'Wickedness, Murderer, Death', 'oVdQW-k2v_w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oVdQW-k2v_w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(154, 1, 'The Power of Words', '<p>Our words are powerful. They reflect what is in our hearts and can impact others for good or for evil. Believers are called to speak the truth in love and rejoice always. The words of Christ should dwell richly in us, so we should guard the words that come out of our mouths.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:34-37; James 3:2-7; Eph. 4:15; Ps. 141:3; Col. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Regina Dundon</p>', '2019-09-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '19:40', 0, 0, 'Power, Confession, Ambassador, Love', 'PCPJhwSgmJw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PCPJhwSgmJw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(155, 1, 'Be Strong and Courageous in Living Life', '<p>God wants us to be wise and disciplined. Fools show contempt for wisdom and instruction. They make poor decisions, which makes life harder than necessary. Wisdom is personified as a woman calling out to people to heed her words of truth. The path of life is uphill, but with God&rsquo;s wisdom, it becomes less difficult.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 1:2-9; Prov. 1:1-6; 8:1-8, 17-21; 9:1-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:03:34', 0, 0, 'Understanding, Proverbs, Knowledge', 'UUTsw1Tib7s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UUTsw1Tib7s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(156, 1, 'Maintaining Joy in the Midst of Suffering', '<p>Life is hard and comes with disappointment and suffering. Jesus is our example, who did no wrong, yet he also suffered. His life and death provided for us a future hope of a better life to come. In the meantime, our hardships are an opportunity for God&rsquo;s strength to work through us in order to endure and prevail over difficulties.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:1-11; John 10:2-3; James 1:2-4; 1 Pet. 2:18-24; Heb. 12:1-2; 2 Cor. 12:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Bolen</p>', '2019-09-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:52', 0, 0, 'Trust, Tribulation, Weakness', 'AbxV5ewuCFk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AbxV5ewuCFk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(157, 1, 'A Christian&rsquo;s Choice', '<p>This teaching is an exposition of Ecclesiastes chapter 7 which presents a series of life choices. The believer&rsquo;s choice what to focus on: the fallen world or the things of God.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 7:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:38', 0, 0, 'death', 'E7yl5BQgkFs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E7yl5BQgkFs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(158, 1, 'Walking Worthy of the Calling - Humility', '<p>Humility is a quality that Christians are urged to take on in order to walk in a manner worthy of God&rsquo;s calling. We learn what humility is by reviewing what is written in Scripture about it and looking at those who humbled themselves before God.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:1-2; Col. 2:8-19, 23; Luke 18:9-4; 1:38, 46-48; Phil. 3:8; 2:1-7; James 1:9-10; 4:6-7; 1 Pet. 5:5-7; Matt. 5:3-12; Isa. 57:12-15</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2019-09-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:20:55', 0, 0, 'Selflessness, Exalted, Attitude', 'xELmF-A8RW8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xELmF-A8RW8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(159, 1, 'Determine to Make Your Life Fulfilling', '<p>This teaching is an exposition of Ecclesiastes chapter 6 and looks at the question &ldquo;How do you view this life?&rdquo; God&rsquo;s warns us to be wary of evil and exhorts us to grab hold of our life and be joyful.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 6:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:49', 0, 0, 'thankfulness, contentment', '2Tw62sjnkEY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2Tw62sjnkEY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(160, 1, 'God Keeps His Word', '<p>God&rsquo;s Word is trustworthy because He promises He will keep His word. He will do what He says He will. As Christians, we are to be imitators of God and do what we say we will do. It is important to be trustworthy, to keep our word, and to be honest.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:1; Num. 23:19; Lev. 19:12; Isa. 38:4; Heb. 6:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:02', 0, 0, 'oath, vow', 'U2HknCIGidM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U2HknCIGidM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(161, 1, 'Should Christians keep the Sabbath?', '<p>The focus of this teaching is to understand when, how, and why the Sabbath became a part of the Mosaic Law and whether or not it applies to Christians today.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 2:16-17, 13-14; Rom. 14:5-8; Gen. 2:1-2; Exod. 16:1-2, 13-30; 19:1; 20:1-2, 13-30; Deut. 1:3; 5:6, 12-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-08-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:19', 0, 0, 'Shadow, Manna, Creation', 'hnTl5taDbQE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hnTl5taDbQE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(162, 1, 'A Christian&rsquo;s Balanced Walk', '<p>In order to understand Scripture and have a balanced walk with God, Christians need to read the whole Bible, not just one or two verses here and there. A study of the permanence of salvation is used as an example of the importance of understanding scripture.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:16; 1:9; Rom. 10:9-10; Gal. 2:16; Eph. 1:13; Gal. 5:16-21; 2 Cor. 1:22-23; 5:5; 1 Cor. 3:10-17; Eph. 2:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Mina Hacker</p>', '2019-08-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:42', 0, 0, 'grace, incorruption', 'AgOhucK0_EU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AgOhucK0_EU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(163, 1, 'Signs of the Ends of the Age', '<p>Old Testament prophets in Isaiah 65 and Daniel 9 foretold the types of events that may indicate the time of the Second Coming - events such as forest fires, hailstorms, earthquakes, hurricanes, groups vs groups, to name a few. As things become darker, light becomes brighter. We are to point others to the Bible where we read that these things are to be expected. We may die, however we won&rsquo;t perish!</p> <p>Verses: Luke 21:5-28; Matt. 24-25; Isa. 65; Dan. 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-08-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:38', 0, 0, 'courage, hope, ethnos, famine; plagues', 'qc4jwUUyZ-4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qc4jwUUyZ-4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(164, 1, 'We Cannot Retire from our Calling', '<p>We have learned that God wants everyone to be saved and to come to a full knowledge of the truth (1 Tim. 2:4). We now learn through multiple scriptures that everyone is &ldquo;called&rdquo; by God, but not everyone answers the call. Those of us who do answer that call become &ldquo;called ones,&rdquo; and the gifts of this calling are irrevocable. Retirement from our calling is not an option.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:28-30; Matt. 22:1-14; 2 Thess. 2:13-14; Rom. 11:9; Eph. 1:15; 4:1; 2 Tim. 1:8-12</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-08-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '54:22', 0, 0, 'chosen, Calvinism', 'NrW3Jz5KKDA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NrW3Jz5KKDA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(165, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/13/2019) - Covenants Part 3: Abraham', '<p>This is part 3 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-08-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:01', 0, 0, null, 'ciS-1TT0dh4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ciS-1TT0dh4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(166, 1, 'Keep Your Eyes on Jesus', '<p>Beautiful and precious thoughts are presented from Hebrews in this teaching. Hebrews encourages us with phrases such as &ldquo;Pay closer attention&hellip;lest we drift away,&rdquo; &ldquo;He really cares for us,&rdquo; &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t harden your hearts,&rdquo; &ldquo;Exhort one another,&rdquo; &ldquo;Let us be diligent,&rdquo; &ldquo;Hold firmly to our confessions,&rdquo; &ldquo;Press on to maturity,&rdquo; and, of course, &ldquo;&hellip;without faith, it is impossible to please God.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 1:1; 2:1, 5; 3:1, 5, 13; 4:11, 12, 16; 5:11; 6:9, 11, 12</p> <p>Teacher: David Hanson</p>', '2019-08-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:15', 0, 0, 'Maturity', 'QouF52to2Gk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QouF52to2Gk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'From Gabe''s fellowship', 1, 0, null),
(167, 1, 'Rewards: Being faithful over a few things', '<p>Over history, the Church has not effectively dealt with the concept of rewards. Throughout the Gospels Jesus mentions &ldquo;Well done, good and faithful servant,&rdquo; indicating some future repayment. Throughout the Sermon on the Mount, as well as several parables, Jesus makes it clear that rewards are pending for those who further God&rsquo;s kingdom. To be great among people, we are to be the best servants.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:1-19; 6:3-21; 10:40; 16:27-28; 18:1-5; 19:27-30; 20:40, 44; 25:14; Luke 19:12; 1 Cor. 6:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:11', 0, 0, null, 'LCATrNZV9IQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LCATrNZV9IQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(168, 1, 'Experiencing Joy While Serving God and His People', '<p>This teaching focuses on the life of the Apostle Paul as recorded in the letters of Philippians and Timothy. We learn about the joy that permeated Paul&rsquo;s life of service despite his challenges and hardships. We also learn about his discipling of Timothy and Epaphroditus, exhorting them and other faithful followers to &ldquo;&hellip;entrust to reliable men who will also be qualified to teach others.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1, 2; Acts 16; 1 Tim. 1; 2 Tim 1-2; 1 Thess. 3</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2019-08-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:07', 0, 0, null, 'OprN7yrzt1w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OprN7yrzt1w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(169, 1, 'What It Means to be a Worker with God', '<p>In 1 Thessalonians, we learn about Paul&rsquo;s and Timothy&rsquo;s glory and joy through their commitment to be workers together in the Ministry of Reconciliation. They chose to &ldquo;live for Him who died for them,&rdquo; no longer living for themselves. As ambassadors, we are empowered and equipped for this, our highest prize, to be His fellow-worker. God depends on our commitment to do His work here on earth.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 1:4, 2:17, 3:1; 2 Cor. 5:1-20, 6:1-10; Acts 9:1-31; 6:1-48</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Bolen</p>', '2019-07-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:48', 0, 0, null, 'BTWglGvBy7g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BTWglGvBy7g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(170, 1, 'Jesus Did Not Retire After the Resurrection!', '<p>We learn from both Ephesians and Colossians that once Jesus&rsquo; work on this earth was finished, his new role began, that of being the head of the church. He is uniting the willing and called ones adopted into God&rsquo;s family and equipped with spiritual gifts. Jesus is &ldquo;coordinating&rdquo; those whose goal is to edify and build up the Church until we have all obtained the unity of the faith.</p> <p>Verses: John 17:1-3; Eph. 1:1-4, 9-10, 4:11-15; Col. 1:12-18</p> <p>Teacher: Patrick Sweeney</p>', '2019-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:46', 0, 0, 'Sealed; Body; Ambassadors; Unite', 'lbgTsLKWO1Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lbgTsLKWO1Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(171, 1, 'Thwart the Devil: Support God&rsquo;s Leaders', '<p>Powerful records from the Old Testament can help Christians learn spiritual principles which apply to current times and events. Both God and the devil need leaders. If God&rsquo;s leaders don&rsquo;t step forward, a lot of God&rsquo;s work does not get done. If the devil&rsquo;s leaders can be stopped, a lot of his work will fall apart. Supporting godly leaders is important in seeing God&rsquo;s purposes accomplished.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 8:22-9:57</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:27', 0, 0, 'holiness, demons, unity, Gideon, Baal, character', 'gCyg4aj43Uc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gCyg4aj43Uc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(172, 1, 'Stopping the Cycle of Sin', '<p>In everyday life, people get hurt and are sinned against by others. Each person decides how to respond to that. In this study, we gain an understanding of the meanings of &ldquo;sin&rdquo; and &ldquo;forgiveness&ldquo;. We learn the detriments of not forgiving, and the benefits of enduring for Christ&rsquo;s sake.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:29; Col. 1:24; 1 Cor. 6:5-8; Gen. 4:4-8, 50:17; Lev. 16:8-10; Matt. 6:12; 18:21-23; 1 Pet. 3:9-11; Matt. 5:10-12, 44; 1 Pet. 2:20-23; 4:13</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2019-07-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:18:20', 0, 0, 'injustice, persecution', '-3-U2HSm5d0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-3-U2HSm5d0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(173, 1, 'The Beatitudes', '<p>Teaching by Gabe Hickman covering the basic understanding of the Beatitudes</p>', '2019-07-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '20:12', 0, 0, null, 'PjylwpLXSkI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PjylwpLXSkI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(174, 1, 'Understanding an Aspect of Discerning of Spirits', '<p>The spiritual ability to discern what people are speaking when they claim to be speaking by the spirit of God reveals false speaking, teachings, and people, and therefore helps us divide truth from error.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:2, 4, 8; 1 Cor. 12:7-11; 1 Cor. 14:29-33, 36; 1 John 4:1-6; 1 John 3:18</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2019-07-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:38', 0, 0, 'false prophets, demons', 'pkvLN4t0sHs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pkvLN4t0sHs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(175, 1, 'The Unique Day of God', '<p>Nestled between significant events of the End Times there will be a &ldquo;unique day.&rdquo; Although there are aspects of this unique day that only God knows, we can learn when it happens and other details about it from various Bible prophecies. The earth and everything in it will be completely changed and there is much to look forward to.</p> <p>Verses: Zech. 14:1-7; Dan. 9:21-27; Matt. 25:31-32; Ezek. 47:1-10; Isa. 11:6-9, 32:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:31', 0, 0, 'eschatology, rapture, judgment', 'F1-kc_HltF0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F1-kc_HltF0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 42, null),
(176, 1, 'Basics of Prophecy', '<p>Teaching by Gabe Hickman covering the basic fundamentals of the manifestation of prophecy and its function in the Christian Church</p>', '2019-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:24', 0, 0, null, 'HKU9b954vuk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HKU9b954vuk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(177, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/07/2019) - Covenants Part 2 - Up to Abraham', '<p>This is part 2 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:45', 0, 0, null, 'v-kcVsRMsMU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/v-kcVsRMsMU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(178, 1, 'Rebuilding the Habitation of God', '<p>Zerubbabel was directed to rebuild the Temple in Jerusalem, after the Israelites were freed from Babylon. The work was full of struggles and challenges, but God encouraged them. Zerubbabel is a &ldquo;type&rdquo; (image, foreshadowing) of Christ and rebuilding of the Temple was a &ldquo;type&rdquo; of the one Christ will build. Christians can apply the lessons taught here when considering God&rsquo;s present habitation in the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 15:4; Ezra 1:1-4; Hag. 1:1-15; 2:1-23; 1 Cor. 6:19; 3:16; Isa. 5:20; Exod. 23:20-29; 1 Cor. 15:53; Zech. 8:9-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-07-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:37', 0, 0, 'separate, perseverance, sanctify', 'fyH9YAsOGkI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fyH9YAsOGkI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(179, 1, 'Life Can Be Tough but We Can Endure', '<p>Difficult times are designed by the Adversary to try to cause believers to stumble and fall away from God. By looking at examples of righteous people in Hebrews 11, we can draw encouragement. Even through their sufferings, they chose to trust God and hope to the end. They had firm confidence that God would keep His word and so can we.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 14:22; Heb. 11:1-40, 12:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-07-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:35', 0, 0, 'believe, trust, faith, peace, rest', 'lcOJS2igGXk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lcOJS2igGXk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(180, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Be Fooled: Rebellion Against God Has Consequences', '<p>In order to present the whole picture of who Christ is, Christians should fully proclaim him &ndash; the loving Savior and the firm Judge. Multitudes of people today are not saved or are not pursuing godly lives and they need to know that Jesus will deal with disobedience. Mature Christians must share this, wisely and lovingly.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 11:1-4; Rev. 5:5; 1 John 4:15-10; Ps. 2:1-12; Rom. 15:18-19; Rev. 20:11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:57', 0, 0, 'Gehenna, Hades, Hell, Millennium', 'Ith0X7tctw4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ith0X7tctw4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(181, 1, 'Being Ready to Give an Answer for the Hope that is in You', '<p>Knowing that God will fulfill His prophecies is key to being able to give an answer to others for the hope that we have. As an example, comparing verses in Psalm 22 to those written 1500 years later in Matthew 27, one can see the prophecy of Psalm 22 being fulfilled. This is just one confirmation that God keeps His word. It gives the believer confidence to speak for God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Pet. 3:15; Ps. 22:1-18; Matt. 27:45-50</p> <p>Teacher: David Lindsey</p>', '2019-07-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:48', 0, 0, 'forsaken, suffering, sanctify', 'we4UmqRHRPI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/we4UmqRHRPI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(182, 1, 'Sin is a Heavy Burden', '<p>In this teaching, sin is referred to as a weight, a debt, and a stain. Sin is pictured as accumulated &ldquo;real estate&rdquo; in the mind that manifests itself as a great burden. God has provided ways for man&rsquo;s burdens to be carried away or forgiven. As Christians, our sins have been washed in Christ&rsquo;s blood and now we are asked to practice that same forgiveness to others.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:9; Zeph. 3:5; Luke 6:22-23; 11:4; Col. 1:9; Isa. 1:4; 5:18; 40:2; Lev. 1:1; 16:2; 24:15; Exod. 32:31-32; Ps. 32:1; 51:1-2, 7; Mic. 7:18; Matt. 6:12; 18:21; Rom. 6:7, 23; James 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:41', 0, 0, 'grace', 'LwuoWrM7s8M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LwuoWrM7s8M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(183, 1, 'Extravagant Answers to Jesus&rsquo; Prayer', '<p>From the Gospel of John, we explore the intimate and moving prayer of Jesus to the Father during the Last Supper. The New Testament scriptures reveal how God answered his prayer. The spirit of God&rsquo;s love, combined with spiritual power, enables believers to walk as lights in the world.</p> <p>Verses: John 17:1-25; 13:34-35; Isa. 50:4-9; Heb. 12:2, 3; Eph. 1:19-21; 6:10, 11; 2:13-19; 4:1-7; Acts 1:7, 8, 19, 20</p> <p>Teacher: Janet Speakes</p>', '2019-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:03:05', 0, 0, 'faithful, empowerment', 'IutKfdG7BRU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IutKfdG7BRU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(184, 1, 'Righteousness: What is it?', '<p>Righteousness in the Old Testament is defined as &ldquo;doing the right thing&rdquo;; whereas in the New Testament, because of the work of Christ, we are declared &ldquo;legally righteous&rdquo;. Having free will to choose good or evil, we are encouraged to imitate Jesus by looking out for the best interests of others.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:1; 4:8; 1 Pet. 1:5; Rom. 3:23, 24; 5:1; 10:4; 2 Tim. 3:16; 2:22; 2 Chron. 12:5, 6; 37:21, 32; Prov. 11:10; Jer. 23:1-5; Matt. 5:6, 10, 20; 6:33; Luke 11:46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-06-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:08:50', 0, 0, 'obedience, choices, salt, light, love', 'yXPeZ14sJSw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yXPeZ14sJSw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(185, 1, 'Understanding Suffering', '<p>In this world, we see through a glass darkly, not knowing all the spiritual implications that are working behind the scenes. While we have knowledge of the Devil that Job did not have, we do not always understand why God intervenes in our lives at times, and not at others. Whether we see deliverance from our troubles in this life or not, we can trust God and know that in the end His justice will prevail.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 5:19; Eccles. 12:13; Ps. 1:5; Job 8:20-22; 31:2, 24; 38:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Gabe Hickman</p>', '2019-06-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:21:53', 0, 0, 'justice, pride, accusers, Satan', 'QjdddoDC4V0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QjdddoDC4V0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(186, 1, 'The Mission', '<p>This teaching reminds us that God has always yearned for mankind to be close to Him. God first called Israel to be a living witness to the world. Then, through Israel came the Messiah, Jesus Christ, and now as Christians, we are called to be ambassadors of this same loving God.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 4:1-9; 7:17, 29; 11:18; Exod. 19:5; 1 Tim. 2:3; 4:1; 2 Cor. 5:20; Jer. 31:31</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-06-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:00:23', 0, 0, 'love, relationship, know', 'jH9jHZsMHl0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jH9jHZsMHl0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(187, 1, 'Listen, Act, and See God Move', '<p>This recording is a testimony of one man&rsquo;s experience of trusting God, listening to Him and obeying His instructions. Whether in travel plans, impromptu teachings, praying for others or discerning the motives of men, God faithfully reveals what needs to be known.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:10; 1 Cor. 12:24</p> <p>Teacher: Shawn Skow</p>', '2019-06-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:37:59', 0, 0, 'faithful, committed, servant', 'vDLbxDBy0WI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vDLbxDBy0WI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(188, 1, 'Suffering for Christ - Part 3', '<p>This fellowship teaching deals with our perspective on suffering. Christians often experience persecution or hardship as a result of doing the will of God. Remembering how Jesus Christ suffered for us and keeping our eyes on the Hope will help us to suffer righteously, by continuing to love people, speaking the word with wisdom and enduring hardship.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:1-11; 1 Pet. 3:8-22; 4:12-19; Heb. 11:32-40; 1 Tim. 6:3-12</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2019-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:05:59', 0, 0, 'endurance, character, hope, righteous, reconciliation, wrath, boasting, patient, repentance, godliness, steadfastness, afflicted, resurrection, contentment', '7qZ0M6Nz5p4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7qZ0M6Nz5p4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(189, 1, 'Cultural Background of the Life and Times of Jesus Christ', '<p>Some of the topics covered in this teaching include regional geography, local culture and customs during the life of Jesus. It also looks at a variety of topics from how papyrus was made, to following the Magi&rsquo;s path, to travelling through Jesus&rsquo; early childhood and on into the days of his ministry.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:27; Lev. 12:1-8; Matt. 2:19-23; Luke 2:41-52; 4:14-30; John 2:12</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:55', 0, 0, 'Offering, Israel, Archelaus, Galilee, Judea, Nazareth, Capernaum, Jerusalem, Passover, Temple', '5QVk66QSfCQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5QVk66QSfCQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(190, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/01/2019) - Covenants Part 1 - Beersheba', '<p>This is part 1 of a teaching series by Doug Campbell discussing covenants and the learnings from the 2019 STF Spring Bible Study. It was done at Gabe Hickman&rsquo;s Sunday noon virtual fellowship.</p>', '2019-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:42', 0, 0, null, 'NuQF64nkVEQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NuQF64nkVEQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(191, 1, 'Pray at all Times, Speak Boldly, Love with Trust', '<p>The Book of Ephesians begins with grace and peace and ends with grace and peace. The last seven verses of chapter six of Ephesians concludes this teaching series with focus on prayer, speaking the good news with boldness, and loving one another and our Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:18-20; John 7:1-13, 25-29; Acts 4:24-31; Eph. 6:21-24</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-05-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:58', 0, 0, 'Tychicus, ambassador, petitions, perseverance, feast, encourage', 'N0lVQUoNEm0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N0lVQUoNEm0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(192, 1, 'Biblical Metaphors Describe Who We Are in Christ', '<p>Many Bible verses metaphorically describe characteristics of the Christian believer. The more we know about who we are in Christ and what we need to do to be able to live a godly Christian life and be the best ambassadors that we can be, the more blessed God and Christ will be and the more blessed we will be as well.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 6:1, 10; Eph. 5:1; Rom. 8:17; Matt. 4:19; 2 Cor. 5:20; Acts 1:8; 9:32-40; 2 Tim. 2:3; 1 Cor. 9:24-27; 1 Pet. 2:5; 2 Tim. 2:20-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:14:55', 0, 0, 'Brothers, Sisters, Children, Fishermen, Ambassadors, Witnesses, Soldiers, Athletes', 'XLoL8A8OKVI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XLoL8A8OKVI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(193, 1, 'Be Empowered in the Lord', '<p>This is an expositional teaching on Ephesians 6:10-18 following verse by verse and word by word through aspects of the armor of God. Knowing who we are and what we have in Christ, we want to be effective in the spiritual battle. In order to do that, we must take up the whole armor of God.</p> <p>Verses: Ephesians 6:10-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:19', 0, 0, 'belt, breastplate, shield, helmet, truth, righteousness, peace, trust, salvation, spirit, prayers, petitions', '5vg-OeJ9zCY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5vg-OeJ9zCY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(194, 1, 'The Fear of the Lord', '<p>The word &ldquo;fear,&rdquo; both in Hebrew and Greek, has a wide semantic range all the way from &ldquo;terror&rdquo; to &ldquo;respect&rdquo; and occasionally &ldquo;awe.&rdquo; Some common misconceptions about the fear of God are discussed. We can have a &ldquo;healthy fear&rdquo; of God by better understanding God&rsquo;s character and our responsibility as Christians.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 10:28; 1 Cor. 3:10-15; Eph. 5:21; Col. 3:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:42:42', 0, 0, 'body, soul, hell, Gehenna, submit, obey', 'RGiLzLLCH5k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RGiLzLLCH5k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(195, 1, 'Submit to One Another', '<p>What does it mean to submit to one another in the fear of Christ? This very insightful teaching together with thoughtful group discussion covers areas of submitting to one another in the context of children, fathers, servants and masters.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:21; 6:1-9; Exod. 20:12; Ps. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:22:39', 0, 0, 'serve, promise, obey, attitude, slave, free, partiality', 'l7G8h8lESls', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/l7G8h8lESls/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(196, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost Arrives', '<p>This teaching provides a historical overview of the Day of Pentecost. God had mighty, secret plans to begin the Church on the Day of Pentecost following the resurrection of His Son. Today, with hindsight, we can see the significance of God&rsquo;s plan for the Christian Church and the outpouring of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 19:9, 16-20, 24-25; 20:1-3; 23:14; 34:23; Deut. 16:16; Lev. 23:2-4, 9-11, 15-17; John 7:37-39; 14:17-18; Ezek. 11:19; 36:26-27; Luke 24:49; Acts 1:4; 2:33; Eph. 1:13; Luke 24:50-53; 1 Cor 3:16; Acts 2:1-2, 5, 8-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:18', 0, 0, 'house, Gentiles, Jews, law, sabbath, sin, spirit, temple, tongues', 'PxBdCEpSVNo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PxBdCEpSVNo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(197, 1, 'Submit Yourselves One to Another', '<p>This teaching focuses on the section of Ephesians that expounds the responsibilities each Christian has in his relationships with others. Particular attention is paid to the relationship of Christ to the Church, followed by the relationship between husbands and wives. There is much work to be done and this section of scripture helps clarify who is responsible to do what.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:21-33</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-05-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:18:42', 0, 0, 'blemish, body, bride, freewill, head, lordship, nourish, respect, worthy', 'vE1QN3SQwrU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vE1QN3SQwrU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(198, 1, 'Suffering for Christ - Part 2', '<p>This teaching, Part 2 of a 3-part series, continues discussing the grace of the Lord. He warns us that bad things are likely to happen as we stand for him, but we can walk through tough times with grace and joy. The believer can expect difficult times, but he will be equipped to accomplish all things required of him by the Lord and to bear much fruit.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:15-31; 15:1-27; 16:1-2; Phil. 1:27-30; 4:12</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2019-05-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:12', 0, 0, 'friend, helper, love, miracles, orphan, peace, power, strengthen, union', '7LWnr0pcWKQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7LWnr0pcWKQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(199, 1, 'The New Covenant - Entering God&rsquo;s Rest', '<p>The Book of Hebrews was written to born-again Jewish Christians who had a strong understanding of Judaism and the Law. This teaching focuses on how Jesus Christ fulfilled the old covenant and how God initiated the new covenant by way of him.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 3:7-19; 6:1-12; 10:25-31; 9:15-28</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-05-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:52', 0, 0, 'death, discipline, inheritance, heart, obedience, offerings, persecution, rebellion, rewards, salvation, Timothy, warning, works, testament', 'EdXiDz_bC7A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EdXiDz_bC7A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(200, 1, 'The Tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting, the Temple and the Christian Church', '<p>Teaching presented by Gabe Hickman</p>', '2019-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:40', 0, 0, null, '7jRHall8xIU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7jRHall8xIU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(201, 1, 'The Easter Story - What&rsquo;s the Big Deal?', '<p>The first Feast of Pentecost foreshadows the long-awaited day of Pentecost in the Book of Acts. Learn how God&rsquo;s desire to have open communication with His people became a reality following the sacrifice of the ultimate Lamb of God, Jesus Christ. What a difference the commitment of our Lord and Savior made to his Father and to mankind.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 12:5-13; 19:1, 14-15; 20:1-21; Matt. 26:26-29; Luke 24:1-8; Acts 2:1-4, 17-21, 36</p> <p>Teacher: John Hickman</p>', '2019-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:25', 0, 0, 'bitterness, blemish, Egypt, kingdom, Passover', 'piB4JQWhBVY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/piB4JQWhBVY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(202, 1, 'Suffering for Christ - Part 1', '<p>If Paul was doing the will of the Lord Jesus, why did he have to face so many hardships? Why do bad things happen to good people? Some of the greatest people who ever lived, as recorded by Scripture, suffered trying times. What is it to be sustained by the grace of God and the Lord Jesus?</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 12:9; Heb. 5:7-9; John 13:21-38; 14:1-17; 16:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2019-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:38', 0, 0, 'ask, intercession, helper, love, Peter, Paul, pray, spirit, thorn, tongues', '0_R2xafvfNc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0_R2xafvfNc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(203, 1, 'Walk in a Manner Worthy of Your Calling', '<p>Christians are instructed on ways to live a godly life. Comparisons are made between the Christian walk and the Gentile walk. When a person is born again his behavior needs to change. This study provides some ways the Christian can transform from the old self (walking in the futility of their mind) to the new self (walking in love).</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:22-32; 5:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:23:12', 0, 0, 'children, forgive, goodness, greed, idolater, immoral, impure, kind, obscenity, reward, tenderness', 'ZFnOVlA0Eps', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZFnOVlA0Eps/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(204, 1, 'God Loves All People and Gives Us a Choice', '<p>People need salvation. The way to salvation has been paved through the sacrifice of Jesus Christ. Because He loves us, God allows mankind to make the choice to come to Him. Christians have the high calling to act as ambassadors for Christ and lead people to the way of everlasting life. The teaching is followed by group discussion covering covenants and the Millennial Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 5:27-32; 22:20; Prov. 1:7; 9:10; Isa. 63:1-5; Matt. 25:31-34, 41, 46; 26:28; Isa. 65:17-23; Rev. 20:7-9; Jer. 34:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-04-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:33:56', 0, 0, 'confess, fear, fellowship, goats, saved, sheep, sin, wisdom', 'gFriwE1FGLg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gFriwE1FGLg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(205, 1, 'Growing Up in the Body of Christ', '<p>There are two ways man can choose to live his life. One is to wander through it aimlessly, in the &ldquo;futility of the mind like the Gentiles do.&rdquo; What God desires is for His children to walk as renewed &ldquo;in the spirit of their minds&rdquo; with the truth as it resides in Jesus. The Christian is instructed in the ways to live a purposeful, godly life in an unjust world.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:1, 17-32</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-04-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:09', 0, 0, 'adversary, anger, behavior, bitterness, edifying, hardhearted, ignorant, malice, stubborn, tenderhearted, truth, walk, world', '9pSeQUJ4-7U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9pSeQUJ4-7U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(206, 1, 'I Go to Prepare a Place for You', '<p>Jesus&rsquo; statement in John 14:2, &ldquo;I go to prepare a place for you&rdquo;, has been misunderstood due to the traditional teaching that when people die, their souls go immediately to heaven and live with God and Jesus forever. Jesus was going to heaven &ldquo;to prepare a place for you&rdquo;, but the &ldquo;place&rdquo; is the future Kingdom on earth.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-04-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:57:02', 0, 0, 'Rapture', 'LzfOljPBEig', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LzfOljPBEig/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(207, 1, 'Know Your Ministry, and Grow in it', '<p>Every Christian receives a gifting from Jesus Christ when they become born again and part of God&rsquo;s family. Jesus Christ also provides gift ministries to help individuals carry out their giftings. Our aim is to grow and mature in our unique gifting and function within the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ephesians 4:7-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:19:08', 0, 0, null, 'TDuy-fX1JKw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TDuy-fX1JKw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(208, 1, 'The Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>2 Thessalonians 2:1-6 provides evidence that Paul taught a pre-tribulation Rapture to the first century believers. Paul reminds them he had taught them that the Rapture would occur before the seven years of tribulation described in Daniel and in the Book of Revelation.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 7:25; 9:21-27; Matt. 24:1-22; 32-33; Luke 21:7-11; 1 Thess.1:9-11; 4:16-18; 2 Thess. 2:1-6; Rev. 6:15-17; 11:1-6; 12:6; 14:9-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-04-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:03:18', 0, 0, 'Armageddon, Anti-Christ', '1RPgv2QK58U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1RPgv2QK58U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(209, 1, 'Keep the Unity of the Spirit', '<p>In this presentation of Ephesians 4:1-6, the emphasis is that God calls believers to walk worthy of His calling by cultivating a rich soil of humility, meekness, patience, forbearance and diligence to keep the unity of the spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:35', 0, 0, null, 'qCGO2hRTrTs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qCGO2hRTrTs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(210, 1, 'Be Faithful in the Little Things', '<p>Faithful stewardship requires us to make wise choices in this lifetime. Being faithful in little things and stewarding all of our resources will result in peace, contentment, and great gain both now and in the future Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 24:1; Prov. 19:17; Eccles. 5:10-13; Matt. 24:14-30; Luke 16:1-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:02', 0, 0, 'wealth', 'pKzncwVbAvk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pKzncwVbAvk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(211, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Prayer for the Body of Christ', '<p>In this continuation of the study of the Book of Ephesians, Paul&rsquo;s second prayer for believers is the focus. This is God&rsquo;s prayer for the Body of Christ, that every believer would see the immensity of His love and plan for our salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:14-21</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-03-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:10:22', 0, 0, null, 'eezMxn0iv38', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eezMxn0iv38/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(212, 1, 'The Administration of the Grace of God', '<p>The Administration of the Grace of God is also called &ldquo;the Administration of the Sacred Secret,&rdquo; which began on the day of Pentecost and will end at the Rapture of the Church. The new rules for the &ldquo;Administration of the Sacred Secret&rdquo; were hidden in God until He revealed them to Paul. Paul reveals them in his letter to the Ephesians.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:16', 0, 0, 'Dispensationalism, Fellow-Heirs', 'qQMZoVBXiKc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qQMZoVBXiKc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(213, 1, 'Joseph - A Type of Christ', '<p>This teaching examines the life of Joseph in the Old Testament and how it parallels to the life of Jesus Christ. Joseph interpreted a dream Pharaoh had and was made second in command over Egypt. Through Jesus Christ&rsquo;s obedience to God, he was made the head of the church and sits at the right hand of God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 41:1-57; Matt. 3:16-17; 28:18-20; Acts 2:25-41; 1 Cor. 11:3; 15:24-28; Eph. 1:22-23; Phil. 2:9-11; Col. 1:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2019-03-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:43', 0, 0, 'salvation', 'XCBG8QdsMWQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XCBG8QdsMWQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(214, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Plan of Redemption', '<p>Ephesians 3 is the climax of the first two chapters in which the Apostle Paul explains to the Christians at Ephesus, and to all the &ldquo;holy and faithful in Christ,&rdquo; the revelation from God to them regarding the Administration of Grace.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:07:03', 0, 0, 'secret, mystery', 'bdvj21oCjWI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bdvj21oCjWI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(215, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Promise of Restoration', '<p>This teaching explains through scriptures and illustration how the Ark of the Covenant of the Old Testament moved to the Temple Mount in Jerusalem and why a wall of partition was built around it to separate the Jews from the Gentiles. As declared in Ephesians, Jesus Christ&rsquo;s death and resurrection broke down this wall of partition making them both one group.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:11-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:51', 0, 0, 'Secret, mystery', 'N0jF72IOpXg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N0jF72IOpXg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(216, 1, 'Reconciliation of Jew and Gentile through the Cross', '<p>In this section of Ephesians, the Apostle Paul explains to the Gentiles at Ephesus who they were without Christ, but now with Christ they have access to God through him and have become fellow citizens with Israel and members of the household of God.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:11-22</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:11:29', 0, 0, null, 'Ipw5Uk8mhuQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ipw5Uk8mhuQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(217, 1, 'The Seven Letters in the Book of Revelation', '<p>It is important for today&rsquo;s Christian to understand the greatness of the hope of Christ&#39;s return. Through a study of the Greek word &ldquo;<em>nikao,</em>&rdquo; translated &quot;overcome&quot;, this teaching explains that the 7 letters in the Book of Revelation are not written to Christians who look forward to the Hope, but to people who are left behind after the Rapture and will be going through the Tribulation.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:31-39; 1 John 2:13-14; 4:4; 5:1-5; Rev. 2:7; 2:11; 2:17; 3:4-5; 3:21</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:11', 0, 0, 'Jews', 'yrkFbFa2avQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yrkFbFa2avQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(218, 1, 'Free Stuff', '<p>This teaching is a review of gifts, free stuff, given to Christian believers by God through His Son Jesus Christ. It focuses on the words grace, gifts and righteousness used in Scripture to further explain the irrevocable gifts that God has given to us by simply believing in Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 1:1-6; 92:12-13; 10:2; Mal. 3:16-18; 4:1-3; Acts 2:36; Rom. 3:19-28; 5:1-21; 6:20-23; 11:29; Eph. 1:3-8</p> <p>Teacher: Doug Campbell</p>', '2019-03-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:59', 0, 0, 'Reconciliation', 'VP7Kpl5Z55A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VP7Kpl5Z55A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(219, 1, 'The Three Distinct Sections of Eph. 2:1-10', '<p>This teaching explains the 3 parts of Ephesians 2:1-10 with emphasis on the Greek word &ldquo;<em>aion</em>,&rdquo; which is translated &ldquo;ways&rdquo; and &ldquo;ages&rdquo; in this section. The emphasis is on today&rsquo;s Christian truly understanding that it is by grace we have our salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:30; Rom. 12:1-2; Gal. 5:16-17; Eph. 2:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:47', 0, 0, 'morals', '4gv7tCwTIPk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4gv7tCwTIPk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(220, 1, 'Salvation By Grace Through Trust', '<p>Ephesians 2:1-10 is about the first step toward God&rsquo;s great purpose - salvation of the individual by grace through trust. All people receiving salvation begin dead in transgressions, but now by God, they have been made alive through Christ and seated in heavenly places. People are not saved by works, but God designed them to do good works after they are saved.</p> <p>Verses: John 6:28-29; Eph.2:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-02-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:20', 0, 0, 'Faith, gift, masterpiece, trespasses, sin, seated', 'T7d3k5nOOBw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T7d3k5nOOBw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(221, 1, 'Understanding the Perspective of Old Testament Believers Regarding the Tribulation', '<p>Old Testament and Gospel-period believers knew that a time of great tribulation would come, but they had no idea how it was linked to the Messiah&rsquo;s coming. They did not know he would arrive, die, rise, ascend, and come back to the earth at a later time. Also, the Rapture was brand-new, comforting information to the early Christians.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 22:10; Isa. 9:6-7; 11:1-9; 61:1-3; 63:1-6; 65:17-23; Ezek. 37:11-12; Dan. 7:13; 12:1, 21; Mic. 5:2-4; Zech. 9:9-10; Matt. 16:21-22; 24:1-12; 25:14, 31-41; John 12:32-34; 1 Cor. 15:51-52; Eph. 2:6; Phil. 3:20; 1 Thess. 1:10; 4:13-18; Rev. 6:15-17; 14:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:11:54', 0, 0, 'judgment, heaven, hell, sheep, goat, resurrection, secret, mystery', 'PfNi663Lj0I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PfNi663Lj0I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(222, 1, 'Be in Good Health', '<p>It is God&rsquo;s will for us to be in good health. There is a definite relationship between a person&rsquo;s thought habits and what goes on in the body. There are biblical keys to help us make decisions that will improve both mental health and physical health. Some examples are being disciplined, changing our thoughts and behaviors, and changing influences around us.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:165; 139:23; Prov. 3:5-8; 4:23; 15:30; 16:24; 17:22; John 1:1-2; Acts 14:21-22; Rom. 14:19; 1 Cor. 15:33; 2 Cor. 10:5; Gal. 5:23; Eph. 4:31-32; Phil. 4:6; Col. 3:15; Heb. 2:14-15; 9:27; 1 Pet. 3:10-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:23', 0, 0, 'depression, fear, heart, gentleness, hope, peace, shame, thankfulness, weakness, wisdom, worry, stress, anxiety', 'LoBkccZabWs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LoBkccZabWs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(223, 1, 'Experiencing Ephesians In Love', '<p>In Ephesians, there is a significant focus on &ldquo;love,&rdquo; not only with God and Jesus Christ, but also in relationship with other people. &ldquo;Love&rdquo; is defined and numerous aspects are examined to help Christians more completely understand how and why we are to love, whom we are to love, and what love looks like.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:34; Eph. 1:4,15; 2:4-6; 3:16-19; 4:1-2, 15-16; 5:1-2, 25-33; 6:23-24</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:00:25', 0, 0, 'holiness, husbands, humility, leadership, maturity, imitator, sacrifice, unity, rooted, wives, agape', '-J8CexLo1Wk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-J8CexLo1Wk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(224, 1, 'Developing Spiritual Sensitivity', '<p>This teaching begins with Paul&rsquo;s prayer in Ephesians 1 about a &ldquo;spirit of wisdom and revelation&hellip;&rdquo; Grasping the meaning of that prayer requires understanding of the usages of the word &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; in the Bible. It also requires understanding what revelation is and how it can be given. This information will spur Christians to recognize the &ldquo;wisdom and revelation&rdquo; they have received and to make a real difference in the world.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 9:15; 11:4-7; Isa. 11:1-4; Jer. 1:4-9; 2 Kings 4:38-40; 6:15-17; Matt. 9:4; Mark 5:28-30; Rom. 8:26; 1 Cor. 14:12, 32; 2 Cor. 3:17; Gal. 1:11-12; Eph. 1:17; 2 Thess. 2:1-2, 7-8; Heb. 5:14; 1 John 4:1; Rev. 2:1, 7-8, 11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:05:05', 0, 0, 'demons, discernment, power, test, judge, prophecy', 'dKWCbyU5WQw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dKWCbyU5WQw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(225, 1, 'Hear, Believe, Be Sealed – To the Praise of His Glory', '<p>This teaching is a detailed explanation of Ephesians 1:13-14. The meaning of the phrases &ldquo;sealed with the promised holy spirit&rdquo; and &ldquo;to the praise of his glory&rdquo; are discussed in particular depth.</p> <p>Verses: John 7:37; Eph. 1:6, 12-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:11:52', 0, 0, 'guarantee, salvation, possession', 'PIDbAtih7x4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PIDbAtih7x4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(226, 1, 'What To Pray For Our Fellow Christians', '<p>The Apostle Paul, by his example, tells us what to pray for our fellow Christians. The main points of Paul&rsquo;s prayer in Ephesians 1 are that God would give us spiritual wisdom and revelation, that we would know our hope and our future inheritance, and that we would know the greatness of God&rsquo;s power. These are the same things we should pray for each other.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 14:12; Eph. 1:15-23; 2 Pet. 1:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:25:56', 0, 0, 'resurrection, rewards, discernment, spirit', 'oRzI2WhjoQI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oRzI2WhjoQI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(227, 1, 'You Are God&rsquo;s Possession – Sealed And Guaranteed An Inheritance', '<p>This teaching focuses on what it means to be claimed as God&rsquo;s &ldquo;possession,&rdquo; the meaning of &ldquo;sealed&rdquo; with the promised holy spirit, and what the guarantee of our salvation is. Reasons for believing in the permanence of salvation in the Age of Grace are given.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 3:17-4; Eph. 1:2, 7, 11-14</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler and John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:40:02', 0, 0, 'children, Church, ransom, redeemed, rewards', 'E7Z6ovLKUEI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E7Z6ovLKUEI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(228, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Purpose of the Ages', '<p>From the beginning of creation, God had a purpose. Through our faith in Jesus Christ, God adopted us into his family. In Christ, God offered us, through our free choice, adoption, redemption, forgiveness, grace, wisdom and the sacred secret. To this end, ultimately, we will unite in the future under one head, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:3-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-01-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:26:34', 0, 0, 'plan', 'Fzg23shHefY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Fzg23shHefY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(229, 1, 'The Heart of God', '<p>This teaching deals with fundamental truths concerning the heart of God. God made us acceptable to Himself by this critical truth - by our new birth in Jesus, we are now &ldquo;in union with Christ.&rdquo; Among other truths considered in this teaching are: our calling, being &ldquo;holy ones&rdquo;, grace and peace, and do the Church Epistles apply today.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:18; Eph. 1:1-5; 2 Pet. 1:4</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler and John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:21', 0, 0, 'purpose', 'SgRJ6a7sdKg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SgRJ6a7sdKg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(230, 1, 'Ephesians 1:3-14', '<p>Teaching done by Gabe Hickman on 1/13/19 at the Noon ET virtual fellowship</p>', '2019-01-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:52', 0, 0, null, 'uTGE294XkyI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uTGE294XkyI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(231, 1, 'Trust God - Let go!', '<p>This teaching is about the biblical principle of trusting God and letting go of the weights that hinder our Christian walk. Looking at OT people and the Apostle Paul, we see historical evidence of real people who &ldquo;let go and totally trusted God&rdquo;. We are exhorted to fix our eyes on Jesus - the one who let go of everything and trusted God to the fullest.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:1-16; Heb. 11:1-40; 12:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:34:07', 0, 0, 'Hope, promise', 'sUSX3uqCBXU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sUSX3uqCBXU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(232, 1, 'The Birth of Our Messiah', '<p>This teaching presents the birth of Jesus from his arrival in Bethlehem to his departure to Egypt as a young child, contrasting traditional ideas with the cultural practices of the time. There was great rejoicing and celebration at Jesus&rsquo; birth, including the Shekinah glory exploding across the Judean landscape as the shepherds tended their flocks. Later, the Magi came to find the child who would be King of the Jews.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:1-15; Luke 2:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2018-12-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:20:35', 0, 0, 'glory, celebration', 'ZMihsiE8V6w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZMihsiE8V6w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(233, 1, 'Overview of Ephesians', '<p>We are encouraged to embrace the Book of Ephesians as a letter - experiencing the full message as opposed to &ldquo;cherry picking&rdquo; scripture. Ephesians reveals God&rsquo;s purpose for us in Christ. Because of what God has given us through grace, we are to be unified, continually maturing in Christ. Ephesians shows us how to &ldquo;grow up in him&rdquo; through our behaviors.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:1-6:24</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:49:25', 0, 0, 'union, salvation, reconciliation, equip', 'fYQ6QRYnPiU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fYQ6QRYnPiU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(234, 1, 'Commit to the Course', '<p>On Paul&rsquo;s third missionary journey, he calls for a meeting with the elders from Ephesus. At this meeting, from Paul&rsquo;s personal testimony and witness, we see the evolving of the principles, practices and behaviors that will become the Book of the Ephesians. We are admonished to walk in humility, trust Jesus, be fearless in trials, not shrink from our calling, be alert, be givers and &ldquo;finish the course.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:1-38; 28:16, 30, 31</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '2:11:17', 0, 0, 'loyalty, function, heart, Acts', '2vRXbP7gXQg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2vRXbP7gXQg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(235, 1, 'A Wonderful Aspect of the Christmas Story', '<p>This teaching is an inside look at Mary&rsquo;s acceptance of the message given her by the Angel Gabriel, her visit to her relative Elizabeth, and her humility and trust. It also highlights the obedient action Joseph took on the dreams given to him by God.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 34:2; 38:6; 71:19; Matt. 1:18-24; Luke 1:26-39, 48, 56</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2018-12-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:15:38', 0, 0, 'Betrothal, Angels, Marriage', 'o5UwmAEjHpc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/o5UwmAEjHpc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(236, 1, 'The Power in a Name', '<p>This teaching takes a look at ancient Biblical culture pertaining to deities. It was believed that the power of a deity was contained in its name, because the name carried the reputation of who it represented and what the deity could do. This applies to both demonic and godly spiritual beings.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 12:8; 48:16; Exod. 3:13; 23:13, Ps. 124:8; Matt. 10:41-42; Acts 1:8; 2:38; 4:8; 19:13-41</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler / John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-11-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:30:56', 0, 0, 'Artemis', 'N5bMvFkOSLo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N5bMvFkOSLo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(237, 1, 'The Way to Intimate Fellowship', '<p>In order to have intimacy with each other, with God, and with Jesus Christ, one needs to have proper living, proper loving, and proper learning. Intimacy comes by continuously abiding in these three concepts.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:41', 0, 0, null, 'pIOWGzHep9Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pIOWGzHep9Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(238, 1, 'Importance of Speaking in Tongues and Prophesying', '<p>This teaching explains why water baptism remained so prominent in the First Century Church and expounds on the importance of receiving the gift of holy spirit into manifestation.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:5; 10:44; 19:1-8, 11; 1 Cor.14:20-22</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler, John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-11-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:52:38', 0, 0, null, '96gLn7gKrUk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/96gLn7gKrUk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 40, null),
(239, 1, 'The Importance of Ephesus in the Proclamation of the Gospel', '<p>This teaching explains the importance of the city of Ephesus and the area of Asia Minor during the Book of Acts. It traces the missionary paths of Paul and explains the importance of his decision to leave Priscilla and Aquila in Ephesus as he journeyed to Jerusalem.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 18:18-28</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-11-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:28:18', 0, 0, 'Magic', 'rEZ65rqGzTM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rEZ65rqGzTM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(240, 1, 'Conditioned by God', '<p>God brought us out of the path of death into a wonderful life in Christ. As His people, we should promote the good news about the &ldquo;sacred secret,&rdquo; an important concept in the Church Epistles, which was lost for the most part after the first century church.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:29-38; Eph. 6:18-24</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:51', 0, 0, null, '1IZ7U0eSc10', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1IZ7U0eSc10/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(241, 1, 'We are a letter from Christ', '<p>The letter from Christ is written on tablets, which are our hearts of flesh. The church is diverse with many parts. The road of truth we walk is narrow between false religion and other evil.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 21:17; 14:7-8; Matt. 7:13-14; Luke 15:11-32; 1 Cor. 14:23; 2 Cor. 3:3</p> <p>Teacher: Joe McCormick</p>', '2018-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '57:56', 0, 0, 'forgiveness', 'jx7lTZD0PrA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jx7lTZD0PrA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(242, 1, 'Prayer Changes Things', '<p>This weekly fellowship recording features a sharing by one of God&rsquo;s mighty prayer warriors concerning her own deliverance as well as delivering others through prayer. We are reminded that God has given us authority to pray at all times with all kinds of prayers and petitions and that we all have a responsibility in the body of Christ to pray.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 12:1-19; Heb. 5:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Donna Cutuli</p>', '2018-10-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:36:52', 0, 0, 'intercession, armor, stronghold', '1k-V7VrqhPA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1k-V7VrqhPA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(243, 1, 'Jesus Loved Mary, Martha, and Lazarus', '<p>It is easy to be distracted from our ministry by difficult circumstances. This weekly fellowship teaching about the Jesus&rsquo; visits to Mary and Martha&rsquo;s house as well as his raising of Lazarus shows that being tuned into the spiritual reality behind our circumstances will strengthen our relationship with Jesus. He loves us and is our friend.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 10:38-42; John 11:1-57; 12:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2018-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:39:35', 0, 0, 'resurrection, anxious, anointing, anger', 'NqLZIaIAaFw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NqLZIaIAaFw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(244, 1, 'The Faithful Obedience of Abraham and Isaac', '<p>The record of Abraham&rsquo;s willingness to sacrifice his son Isaac, believing that God was able to raise him up, is an example to us and was an example to Jesus Christ that God is able to do and will do what He has promised.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 22:1-19; Heb. 11:8-12, 17-19</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2018-10-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:05', 0, 0, 'Test, Faithfulness, Promises, Moriah', 'D_QljAtjJlQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/D_QljAtjJlQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(245, 1, 'Estranged from the Covenants Based on the Promise', '<p>The promises made under the Old Testament covenant were not available to the Gentiles, who were excluded and considered &ldquo;dead&rdquo; in their sins. When Jesus Christ ushered in the New Covenant, the &ldquo;Sacred Secret&rdquo; was revealed: that in union with Christ the Gentiles became fellow heirs, fellow members of the Body of Christ, and partakers of the promise.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 31:31-34; Joel 2:32; Eph. 2:11-22; 3:1-6; Rom. 8:16-17; 10:11-13; 2 Tim. 2:11-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-10-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:44', 0, 0, 'salvation, circumcision, peace, reconcile, citizen', 'xfMAOHbPtFE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xfMAOHbPtFE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(246, 1, 'Thoughts on the Sacred Secret', '<p>Teaching by Gabe Hickman at the Noon ET Zoom Fellowship</p>', '2018-10-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '19:15', 0, 0, null, '7-gWCmiQF8M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7-gWCmiQF8M/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(247, 1, 'Ephesus, The Magnificent Capital of Asia', '<p>This teaching explores the setting of the large city of Ephesus, home to the Temple of Artemis, one of the 7 wonders of the ancient world. It was a Roman provincial capital and port city and was bustling with commerce and mysticism. Paul taught there for 2 years and it subsequently became a stronghold for Christianity.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 19:1-12, 23-41; 20:1-37; 1 Cor. 15:32; 16:5-20; 1Tim. 1:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-10-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:19', 0, 0, 'baptism, synagogue, exorcists', 'MGFygpijlv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MGFygpijlv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(248, 1, 'Despite Any Circumstance, We Represent God', '<p>This open fellowship style video includes some discussion after a story-filled teaching. The Syrian general Naaman was healed of leprosy and became a prophetic picture of the one Body of Christ, with both Jews and Gentiles included. Hear how the Pharisees reacted when Jesus cited this record of a Gentile being healed.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 5:1-19, Isa. 49:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2018-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:40', 0, 0, null, 'J7uEmcR6N9k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J7uEmcR6N9k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(249, 1, 'Praise and Worship', '<p>This &ldquo;Home Style&rdquo; fellowship includes prayer and discussion following a sharing that covers a brief history of praise in various church and ministry settings. It&rsquo;s a colorful journey through emotions, outward appearance, and interpersonal communications via words to better understand how God uses words to communicate with us. Hear about joyful praise and worship in response to what God has done for us all.</p> <p>Verses: Neh. 8:8, 12; 2 Cor. 10:4-5; Exod. 15:1-2; 2 Chron. 20:21-22; Ps. 150:1-6; John 4:23</p> <p>Teacher: Joe McCormick</p>', '2018-09-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:33:26', 0, 0, null, '5TBcTKt__5o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5TBcTKt__5o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(250, 1, 'Be Strong and Courageous', '<p>God tells Joshua that He will be with him just as He was with Moses. He says He will also be with us always if we lean into His Word for support. We are to study His Word often and hold fast to it. We must be strong and courageous, as God told Joshua to be.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 1:1-3, 5-9, 17; 2:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2018-09-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:33:14', 0, 0, 'Covenant', 'aPPynxs6_Iw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aPPynxs6_Iw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(251, 1, 'God&rsquo;s View of Living A Long Life: What Really Matters', '<p>God has a perspective on life which includes the next age and the new heaven and earth. The goal in this life is to be joyful in the journey. Faith, hope and love play an important part in a successful life here on the earth.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 23:21; 1 Cor. 9:24; Eph. 4:32; 5:1-2, 21; 1 Tim. 4:8; 1 John 4:7; Phil. 3:14</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2018-09-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:29:11', 0, 0, null, '-1KkjgWQblw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-1KkjgWQblw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(252, 1, 'Are Drugs Evil?', '<p>This teaching discusses the good and bad effects of natural chemicals and natural substances in our environment, substances that can benefit or harm us. The Bible warns us of the harmful effects of alcohol and substance abuse. We are encouraged to remain sober and avoid behavior that would be a danger to ourselves or others around us. There are many natural therapies that God has provided to keep us healthy.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1-3; Eph. 5:18-19; 1 Tim. 3:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2018-08-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:39:17', 0, 0, null, '6vA4sEQNIGU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6vA4sEQNIGU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(253, 1, 'Medicine and the Word of God', '<p>God wants His people to be healthy and He has made it possible for us to be so in nature&rsquo;s abundance. We need good health in order to work the works that God has called us to do. The responsibility for our lives rests on the choices we make, and we must choose wisely.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:1-27; Matt. 9-12; 10:1; 10:8; Luke 4-18, 23</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2018-08-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:39:33', 0, 0, null, 'bYm1smtq5uA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bYm1smtq5uA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(254, 1, 'The Big Lie About Death', '<p>God does not want us to be ignorant on the subject of death. The ancient Greeks define death as &ldquo;the total absence of life.&rdquo; According to Scripture, the living know they will die, but the dead know nothing. We as Christians will wait until Jesus Christ returns to be raised into everlasting life.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:5; Eccles. 9:5; John 8:44; 10:10; Rom. 6:23; 1 Cor. 15:26; Heb. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: Carol DeMars</p>', '2018-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:40:47', 0, 0, null, '7VoryqMrWME', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7VoryqMrWME/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(255, 1, 'You can''t get through it Until you go through it', '<p>We must rely on God and His Son Jesus as we go through the trials of our lives. God and His Son will give us the courage and strength to endure the difficulties of life.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Isa. 40:28-31; Josh. 1:1; John 10:10</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Andy Trimble</p>', '2018-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '16:11', 0, 0, 'covenant', 'f5b-6kqrO70', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f5b-6kqrO70/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(256, 1, 'Pray in the Spirit - You Can&rsquo;t Go Wrong!', '<p>Speaking in Tongues is perfect prayer. As we do this, we are involving Jesus Christ directly and intimately, we are praising God, and we are building ourselves up as well. We are also to pray with our understanding, as speaking in tongues does not replace that, and do both with faith and trust.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:1-8; 2:1-21; 10:46; 1 Cor. 14:1; 14:13-17; Eph. 6:14-18; Jude 1:20</p> <p>Teacher: Pat Sweeney</p>', '2018-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:27:35', 0, 0, 'Manifestation', 'sB8QW5wXMus', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sB8QW5wXMus/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(257, 1, 'Put on the Whole Armor of God!', '<p>Taken primarily from Ephesians 6, this teaching demonstrates how we are to present ourselves as the Sons of God that we are. Consider that when we dress in a certain way, we will act that way. We are indeed soldiers of God, and we need to be arrayed in the armor God has provided through Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 41:37-46; 1 Sam. 17:1-58; Eph. 6:10-18</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-08-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:38', 0, 0, null, 'tNywiHEGQHQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tNywiHEGQHQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(258, 1, 'Be Active, Not Passive!', '<p>The Bible teaches us that God wants us to be active and to take a stand. To stand for Him, we need to be prepared for battle. As we learn from Ephesians 6, He has empowered and equipped us to do so. We are not to back down, and always to be looking for ways to overcome evil with good.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1; Eph. 4:14; 6:10-18; 2 Tim. 3:12; 1 Pet. 5:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: Shaun Skow</p>', '2018-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:25:18', 0, 0, 'Confidence', 'pTuR__LUyO0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pTuR__LUyO0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(259, 1, 'Unity of the Spirit', '<p>The Book of Ephesians is often referred to as the apex of the Christian Epistles, with chapters 1-3 focusing on doctrine - what God and Jesus did for us - and chapters 4-6 - what we are to do with that information. We are called to guard and preserve a spirit of unity, and the basis of this unity is truth.</p> <p>Verses: John 17:17; 1 Cor. 1:10-13; Eph. 2:1-8; 4:1-6; Phil. 4:5; Col. 3:12-15; Heb. 10:24; 1 Pet. 3:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-07-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '2:15:37', 0, 0, 'Calling, Agape', 'u6_nAE8W1fk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/u6_nAE8W1fk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(260, 1, 'We Can Be a Weapon of Mass Construction!', '<p>Romans 15 encourages us to be filled with joy and peace, so that we can abound in hope. Jehoshaphat, King of Judah, when surrounded by 3 enemy nations, called out to Yahweh, promising to keep his eyes on Him. Yahweh brought Judah victory as the 3 enemies turned on each other. Judah sang praises and thanksgiving to Yahweh. Philippians teaches that we are best when we respond, not react.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 20:3-21; Rom. 15:2; 15:13; Phil. 4:4-7</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2018-07-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:26:58', 0, 0, 'Conflict', 'd0uf36NvTBU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/d0uf36NvTBU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(261, 1, 'Your Heart is God&rsquo;s Garden', '<p>The Book of Isaiah, specifically Chapter 28, teaches us that God speaks in a whisper. We must be quiet and patient to listen, allowing Him to teach us. He is wonderful in counsel and excellent in wisdom.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 28:9; 28:23-29</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2018-07-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:45', 0, 0, 'Sowing, Reaping', 'HfVHA5XAJf0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HfVHA5XAJf0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(262, 1, 'Galatians 6:1-10', '<p>The 6<sup>th</sup> chapter of Galatians contains an array of practical exhortations that every Christian should be aware of. We are to lead &lsquo;spirit-filled lives&rsquo; through actions. We are to help one another, share with one another, and love one another. We may be called to restore a brother, or simply share their burden, doing so with meekness and gentleness.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 11:28-30; Gal. 6:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2018-07-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '2:04:35', 0, 0, 'Burden, Koinonia', 'I4eZ1ZZYVLs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I4eZ1ZZYVLs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(263, 1, 'The Book of Haggai', '<p>In the book of Haggai, the tribes of Judah and Benjamin return to Jerusalem from captivity in Babylon to rebuild Solomon&rsquo;s temple, but the people fail to make Yahweh&rsquo;s house a priority. Rather they place their needs above the reconstruction of the temple at a costly price.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 7:14; Hag. 1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:11:21', 0, 0, null, 'WvWc4l-pI7M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WvWc4l-pI7M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(264, 1, 'Understanding Literal and Figurative Statements in the Bible', '<p>Readers of the Bible often struggle to know when to take it literally and when to take it figuratively. Often when a section of Scripture is hard to understand, it is excused as figurative or metaphorical. This teaching offers explanations regarding figures of speech and metaphors and helps clarify how to appropriately understand what is written in the Word of God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:36-38; Eph. 1:1-2; Matt. 1:18-20; 3:16-17; 11:25; 1 Peter 1:23-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:36', 0, 0, 'corruptible, incorruptible, seed', '1-e5yh_GiN8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1-e5yh_GiN8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(265, 1, 'Romans 8:28', '<p>This Teaching by Gabe Hickman on 6-24-18 Discusses Romans 8 and the reason for which nothing can separate us from the love of God, or the love of Christ.</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:21', 0, 0, null, 'y79HfkpX368', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y79HfkpX368/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(266, 1, 'Jesus Is the Bread of Life and Fountain of Living Waters', '<p>Are you hungry? Are you thirsty? There is a desire within man to know God. He hungers for the word of God and thirsts for the spirit of God. This teaching expounds the ways that Jesus, the Son of God, fulfills the desires of anyone who hungers and thirsts after righteousness.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 8:1-3; Jer.15:16; John 4:7-26; 6:25-35; 7:37-39; Luke 4:1; 1 Pet. 2:1-2; Ps. 34:8-10; Rev. 3:20</p> <p>Teacher: Doug Campbell</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:12', 0, 0, 'bread, temptation', 'OQg_-Eecq4I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OQg_-Eecq4I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(267, 1, 'Speaking In Tongues', '<p>God desires worship from those whom He has created. In this day and time God has provided His children with the ability to speak in tongues to praise and worship Him. This teaching provides Christians with the biblical reasons why we should all speak in tongues.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:11; 10:46; 1 Cor. 13:1; 14:2, 4-5, 14, 16-17, 22; 1 John 3:24; Jude 20; Ps. 89:5-8; Rev. 4:2-11; 7:11-12; Rom. 8:26-27</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:46', 0, 0, 'angels, sign', 'IGyxXMRzYF4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IGyxXMRzYF4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(268, 1, 'The Book of Galatians (Part 8)', '<p>This teaching helps Christians make the transition from legalism to grace while avoiding stumbling blocks. Christ has set us free from the chains of sin and bondage. We therefore need to live based on grace while refraining from legalism. We came to Christ by faith and must live in the grace and freedom of that calling.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 2:21; 5:1-12</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler and Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:59:43', 0, 0, 'circumcision, faith, freedom, hope, inheritance, righteousness, slavery, trust', '7Iu9jY69fFM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7Iu9jY69fFM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(269, 1, 'The Book of Galatians (Part 7)', '<p>It is imperative that Christians resist falling back into practices based in the law of the Old Testament. This teaching shares how submitting to the rule of law is equal to turning back the clock to a previous stage in God&rsquo;s relationship to man. Christians are encouraged to live in the freedom and grace God made available through Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Galatians 3:7, 28-29; 4:1-31</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler and Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:52:57', 0, 0, 'covenant, Gentiles, heirs, inheritance, promise, slave', 'QsOhnsvONmg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QsOhnsvONmg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(270, 1, 'The Book of Galatians (Part 6)', '<p>Man could never be truly changed by way of the Old Testament Law. In Abrahamic times people needed the Law in order to live together and develop an environment into which the Messiah could come to bring deliverance to God&rsquo;s people. The Law served to reveal sin, but now Jesus Christ is the new promise and man&rsquo;s salvation is to be based on trust in him.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:6; 3:2-29</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler and Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2018-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:55:09', 0, 0, 'covenant, curse, heir, inheritance, promise, seed', 'mbs9ruOEGsw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mbs9ruOEGsw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(271, 1, 'Sunday Noon Fellowship - Philippians 3:11', '<p>Teaching done by Dennis Hickman on the heart of Paul when writing Philippians.</p>', '2018-06-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:27', 0, 0, null, 'yn_9IlMpDEw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yn_9IlMpDEw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'marked inactive, death was not a gain to Paul', 1, 0, null),
(272, 1, 'A Study of Galatians (Part 5)', '<p>Part five of this study of the Epistle to the Galatians delves into the Law of Moses and justification by trust (faith). Abraham was declared righteous because he believed God. Even after the Law and commandments were instituted by God in the Old Testament, faith was still the essence of the Law. This is a detailed team teaching along with open fellowship discussion.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 15:1-6; Rom. 9:9-12; Gal. 3:2-18</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler, Jerry Wierwille, John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '2:03:02', 0, 0, null, 'TSmj5wWC6_Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TSmj5wWC6_Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(273, 1, 'Acts 19: Paul in Ephesus', '<p>This record of the Apostle Paul&rsquo;s ministry in Ephesus provides great keys to effective witnessing. Paul looked for advantageous places to preach the Word. If people were not receptive, he knew when to move on. When we know the power of baptism in the spirit and how it makes us one with Christ, we can expect miracles as we minister to people.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 19:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:06', 0, 0, null, 'ckTEUMplPF8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ckTEUMplPF8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(274, 1, 'A Study of Galatians (Part 4)', '<p>When Jewish Christians in Jerusalem decided to separate themselves from the Gentile Christians and go back to observing the Torah&rsquo;s laws of food, circumcision, feast days, and so on, the Apostle Paul found it necessary to confront and correct them. Issues involving hypocrisy, reputation, and personal income all came into play. This is a detailed team teaching along with open fellowship discussion.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 2:11-21</p> <p>Teachers: Jeff Tyler, Jerry Wierwille, John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:37:57', 0, 0, 'righteous, faith, trust', 'UcBy79zdEns', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UcBy79zdEns/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(275, 1, 'A Study of Galatians (Part 3)', '<p>The Book of Galatians is believed to be the earliest of the Church Epistles written. This teaching presents evidence of the geographic locations of the Galatian churches Paul visited. The purpose of Paul&rsquo;s visit to Jerusalem is discussed, as well as issues that came up between Paul, Peter, and John. This is a detailed team teaching along with open fellowship discussion.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 2:1-10</p> <p>Teachers: John Schoenheit, Jerry Wierwille, Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:42:10', 0, 0, 'good news, circumcision, ministry, apostle', '9WX8QiTi7JU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9WX8QiTi7JU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(276, 1, 'Psalm 119', '<p>This presentation is a reading of Psalm 119. This is the longest of the Psalms with 176 verses. Known as an acrostic, each stanza begins with a letter of the Hebrew alphabet. After reading the entire psalm, participants in the fellowship group share their insights.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119</p> <p>Teacher: Andy Trimble</p>', '2018-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:19', 0, 0, null, '2GwTAYTNsbI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2GwTAYTNsbI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(277, 1, 'Galatians Chapter 1', '<p>This is an expository teaching on the first chapter of Galatians in an interactive format. A timeline of Paul&rsquo;s life following his conversion, up to the writing of this letter, is developed and explains why it was necessary for Paul to establish his credibility as an apostle. A lively discussion follows, which brings added insight to the topic.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:1-24</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '2:08:15', 0, 0, null, 'tR3nAvaPf7E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tR3nAvaPf7E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(278, 1, 'Introduction to Galatians', '<p>This is an interactive teaching explaining the background of events leading up to the first doctrinal crisis in Christianity. It traces the Church&rsquo;s development from Pentecost to the Jerusalem Council, which addressed Jews in the Church.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:6-8; 7:54-60; 8:1-3; 9:1-30; 10:9-16; 11:1-3, 15-30; 12:25; 13:1-6, 13-15, 32-39, 44-52; 14:1-7, 21-28; 15:1</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:33:24', 0, 0, 'Paul', 'JYBs5OwuzP8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JYBs5OwuzP8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(279, 1, 'Romans Chapter 8', '<p>Romans is the great book that establishes the believer&rsquo;s righteousness. This teaching opens with a brief overview of Romans chapters 1-7, then moves into an expository teaching of chapter 8.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:1-39</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:57', 0, 0, 'Condemnation, Guilt', 'eYLRrYPBwlA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eYLRrYPBwlA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(280, 1, 'First STF Community Fellowship', '<p>In this first STF Community fellowship, the group discusses the goals and purposes of this meeting time.</p>', '2018-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:13:35', 0, 0, null, 'wdPFcBFcSVU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wdPFcBFcSVU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated, not a teaching', 1, 0, null),
(281, 1, 'Ephesians 1:3-14', '<p>Ephesians 1:3-14 is one long sentence, a complete thought with many phrases and modifiers. A diagram of this one long sentence reveals simply that God is blessed that we have been sealed with holy spirit to the praise of His glory.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:3-14; Heb. 6:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-05-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:16:47', 0, 0, 'sealed', 'PrBMQAEp_Zw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PrBMQAEp_Zw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(282, 1, 'A Discussion on Grace', '<p>Grace is a favor done voluntarily by one individual for another. Taking advantage of the rich library of study aids available to us today, this teaching expands our understanding of the grace in which we stand as Christians.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:1-2; Gal. 1:6-8, 11; 3:1-9; 5:1-9</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:30', 0, 0, 'boasting', 'K5FCUTmAB6M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/K5FCUTmAB6M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(283, 1, 'Overview of the Book of Judges', '<p>Judges describes 12 people who rose up to lead Israel in the years following the death of Joshua. It contains many lessons in leadership and describes many events in which God made His people victorious in spite of being outnumbered.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 3:7, 9, 12-14, 31; 4:4; 6:11-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Hickman</p>', '2018-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:14', 0, 0, null, 'Sq2Wz19Flcg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Sq2Wz19Flcg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(284, 1, 'The Christian Process', '<p>This teaching presents a simple flow chart for Christian living, with illustrations from the Old Testament showing how the principles in the chart have worked for God&rsquo;s people in the past.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 2:8; 42:9-17; Ezek. 5:11; Dan. 1:6-7, 17-21; 2:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2018-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:01', 0, 0, 'prayer', '4yew9ov2jB4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4yew9ov2jB4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(285, 1, 'Song of Solomon', '<p>Teaching Done by Gabe Hickman discussing the implications of the writings in Song of Songs.</p>', '2018-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:52', 0, 0, null, 'gP2zYkblH_g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gP2zYkblH_g/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(286, 1, 'Align your Thoughts with God&rsquo;s', '<p>As we pray, study, contemplate, and speak aloud the words of God from the scriptures, we will begin to understand how God thinks, and we will see how Jesus demonstrated his understanding of his Father by his words.</p> <p>Verses: Ex. 21:2-4, 22, 33-34; 22:5; Josh. 1:6-8; Ps. 1:1-2; Isa. 55:6-8; Rom. 12:1; 1 Cor. 10:32-33; 11:1; Eph. 5:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:46', 0, 0, null, 'v_Souq5niZo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/v_Souq5niZo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(287, 1, 'Empowered to Endure', '<p>This teaching explains how to have the power to endure hardship and how to develop our spiritual wisdom and understanding. Knowing these things builds our ability to have patience while we wait on the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:9-11; Ps. 27:13-14; 62:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:47', 0, 0, 'suffering, prayer, endurance', 'DkFxCnwkH3Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DkFxCnwkH3Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(288, 1, 'God Wants Us to Have a Good Life', '<p>God has set before us life and good, and death and evil. This life includes a good life now as well as the promise of everlasting life in the future. This message contrasts the requirements for a good life before Christ came with the righteousness based on trust available now by following Romans 10:9-10.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:11-20; Rom. 10:5-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:39', 0, 0, 'saved, law, believe, heart', '-I6dXvew2vE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-I6dXvew2vE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(289, 1, 'The Steadfast Love of God', '<p>This teaching presents a discussion about the consistency of God&rsquo;s love. We as his children are to offer the same loving support to each other. God&rsquo;s promise to never leave us alone is a great encouragement and statement of His consistent love.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 13:6; Ps. 118:1-6; Heb. 13:5; Gal. 6:2; Heb. 6:10</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-04-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:45', 0, 0, 'faithfulness', 'BnEcwZNrhOI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BnEcwZNrhOI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(290, 1, 'Is the Coronavirus the Judgement of God?', '<p>God wants us to be aware that there is a war between good and evil going on all around us. We need to be vigilant and watch for signs of this in our lives. We need to remain in prayer and study the Bible for understanding of how, with God&rsquo;s help, to defend ourselves in this war.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 7:15; 1 John 5:19; Luke 4; John 10:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:50', 0, 0, null, 'dwRa-7bTm60', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dwRa-7bTm60/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2160, null),
(291, 1, 'Fix Your Eyes On Jesus', '<p>It is important for us to focus on our faith when times of trouble enter our lives. This teaching encourages us to keep our eyes fixed on Jesus, not on the waves around us, when we face difficult times.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 14</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Dugan</p>', '2020-04-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:15', 0, 0, null, 'tsUVOO2qEdo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tsUVOO2qEdo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(292, 1, 'The Inner Self', '<p>Where is the real you? Your inner self is the real you, the you that talks to yourself, that has feelings and attitudes. What are &ldquo;kidneys&rdquo; in the Bible? Our inner self gets worn out, bogged down, and it&rsquo;s up to us to renew it. This teaching contains keys on how to control our minds.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:22-23; 2 Cor. 4:16; Eph. 3:16; Ps. 7:9; 16:7; Jer. 17:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-04-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '17:30', 0, 0, 'Renewed encourage', 'VDkE-oTGvt8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VDkE-oTGvt8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 54, null),
(293, 1, 'Challenging Times Present Opportunities', '<p>Challenging times should cause us to push forward and result in refining and strengthening our character and resolve. Obstacles can become opportunities.</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Dugan</p>', '2020-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:49', 0, 0, 'encouragement', 'XGWE5cWOYvY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XGWE5cWOYvY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(294, 1, 'Should Christians Be Afraid Of Death?', '<p>There is a difference between healthy fear and unhealthy fear. Regarding the fear of death, we are to be confident in our salvation, to be convinced that God will raise us up, and that we will receive a new and perfect body.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 2:14-15; Matt. 10:28; Rom. 10:9; 2 Tim. 4:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:32', 0, 0, 'Joy; Excitement; Newness', 'IU8hnC2bvyM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IU8hnC2bvyM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(295, 1, 'Controlling Your Imagination in Difficult Times', '<p>Our imaginations have &ldquo;goods and bads.&rdquo; We need to focus on faith and trust as we envision the future. We are encouraged to not lean on our own understanding, but to focus on how we can help others.</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Dugan</p>', '2020-03-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:51', 0, 0, null, 'H0uMfZnKGMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H0uMfZnKGMY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(296, 1, 'Let God Be Your Refuge', '<p>Tough times call for strong faith. God is always with us, even in times of crisis. We can trust in God for daily comfort and encouragement because He knows how to care for us better than any man or government. Amidst all the change in this world, God is constant and helps us stay grounded.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 118:8; 2 Tim. 1:7</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-03-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:00', 0, 0, 'Assurance, Worry, Fear', '22lXspPrSFA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/22lXspPrSFA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(297, 1, 'Feeling Anxious? Watch This!', '<p>All the preparations we may do to prevent fear or anxiety are just not enough, we have to trust in God. Your God loves you; His love is consistent and it never fails.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:7</p> <p>Teachers: Janet Speakes, Jerry Wierwille, Renee Dugan, John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:45', 0, 0, 'worry, encouragement', 'W7HWIeuh3Y8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/W7HWIeuh3Y8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(298, 1, 'Our Certain God During Uncertain Times', '<p>Change can be difficult to manage as disruptions to normal daily routines cause tensions between the way things were and the way things are. Here are 3 specific tips you will find helpful making adjustments to successfully maneuver through change.</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Dugan</p>', '2020-03-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:05', 0, 0, 'Anxiety, Depression, Stress', 'Qbt6Pdh73zI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Qbt6Pdh73zI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(299, 1, 'Becoming One Flesh - God&rsquo;s Advice For Couples', '<p>Whether during a global pandemic or an extended power outage, too much free time can increase stress. With more time together in the home than normal, couples can find it difficult to be loving, especially when isolated from their normal world of activities. Learn how to increase your skill sets to be more loving, supportive, and kind in stressful circumstances.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:21-24; Eph. 5:21-33; 1 Pet. 3:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '23:27', 0, 0, 'Quarantine, Isolation, Marriage, Family', 'fFdhwBYSY-U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fFdhwBYSY-U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 28, null),
(300, 1, 'Let The Peace Of Christ Be The Umpire In Your Heart', '<p>What does it mean to be the &ldquo;Umpire&rdquo; of your heart? Who rules your heart? It takes great personal maturity to genuinely let the peace of Christ &ldquo;make the call&rdquo; in your life. Learn some great biblical insights about this lifelong quest.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:23', 0, 0, 'sacrifice', 'Hg94tV6arA0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Hg94tV6arA0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(301, 1, 'Why We Should Control Our Emotions', '<p>God created us to have many deep, life-enriching emotions. However, since we live in an emotionally undisciplined culture, emotions can be difficult to control. How did Jesus control His emotions when He was treated so unfairly? What will you do when you are mistreated? This teaching encourages us to respond in a Christ-like way.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:10; 4:31-32; Col. 3:8; Phil. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:05', 0, 0, 'obedience, maturity', '7xVdO-_LB_Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7xVdO-_LB_Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(302, 1, 'Does God Speak to Men?', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit teaches on whether God speaks to men or not.</p>', '2020-02-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 0, 0, null, 'NeYrgh3zoMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NeYrgh3zoMY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 2, null),
(303, 1, 'Speaking the Truth in Love', '<p>We can be more effective Christians by being a positive life-changing influence on ourselves and others. We are encouraged to get involved in other people&rsquo;s lives without fear by speaking the truth in love.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:15; Prov. 28:28; Josh. 1:6, 7, 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:31', 0, 0, 'Obedience, Happiness, Strong, Courageous, Growing', 'tmRBELcgw0o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tmRBELcgw0o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(304, 1, 'Hold the Things of Earth Loosely', '<p>Caleb is an example in scripture of one who willingly accepted God&rsquo;s decisions of &ldquo;who would possess what&rdquo; in the Promised Land. He was thankful for what he did receive. Jesus also taught us to be thankful and on guard against greed.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 14:6, 9-15; 15:13-15; 21:1-4, 8-11; Luke 12:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:53', 0, 0, 'Stuff, Tribe, Spies, Wilderness, Wandering', 'F_VkppfbpzE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F_VkppfbpzE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(305, 1, 'We Are Declared Righteous', '<p>When we know about the accomplished work of Jesus Christ for believers, then we never have to feel unworthy or not good enough to be saved. We never have to doubt that when we pray, God hears us. This teaching gives a clear illustration of how the Christian receives righteous standing before God.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:20-21; Rom. 5:6-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-02-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:49', 0, 0, 'Sin offering, Lamb', 'bX40e4sDTjY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bX40e4sDTjY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(306, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Armageddon?', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit explains what the Bible has to say about the battle of Armageddon.</p>', '2020-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:33', 0, 0, null, 'fYpyVAGRFJ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fYpyVAGRFJ0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(307, 1, 'Can You Be Good Enough To Get To Heaven?', '<p>If I am a good person, why do I need Jesus? Isn&rsquo;t just trying to be a good person enough for us to make it to heaven? This teaching shows why it is of utmost importance that Christ died for our sins, and that when we believe that God raised him from the dead and we make him our Lord, we will be saved.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23; 6:23; 1 Cor. 15:3; Rom. 5:6, 8; Acts 4:12; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:29', 0, 0, 'wages, death', 'UWfSKyb6FV4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UWfSKyb6FV4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(308, 1, 'Focus On Others', '<p>Paying attention to the needs and interests of others is an easy concept to grasp mentally but can be hard to put into action. It takes focus and effort to do the will of God by putting others ahead of ourselves.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 2:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:48', 0, 0, null, 'hBXcOtXrRRc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hBXcOtXrRRc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(309, 1, 'Christ Died In Our Place', '<p>Believers are encouraged to focus on the accomplished work of Christ as a platform for strength in their daily lives. Our union with Christ includes the honor, privilege, and ability to act in his stead as ambassadors.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:3-5; Rom. 5:6-11; 2 Cor. 5:20-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:45', 0, 0, 'atonement', 'wrEfAyq7_YA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wrEfAyq7_YA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(310, 1, 'Make War on Your Sin', '<p>Christ died as a sin offering in our place and we are completely righteous before God. It can be like walking a tight rope to accept this and yet pay attention to our sin and shortcomings and obey Him. A record in Joshua illustrates why this is important to do.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:6-10; 2 Cor. 5:21; Gen. 17:9-11, 14; Josh. 5:1-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-01-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:41', 0, 0, 'circumcision, covenant, battle', 'SO7banNrmEY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SO7banNrmEY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(311, 1, 'What is the Mystery or Sacred Secret?', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit teaches on the Greek word Musterion and how a better translation would be Sacred Secret.</p>', '2019-12-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:57', 0, 0, null, 'ii3xYgiE_pI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ii3xYgiE_pI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(312, 1, 'Did The Magi Follow A Christmas Star To Bethlehem?', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit teaches on the Magi (Wise Men) and whether they followed a star to Bethlehem.</p>', '2019-12-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:46', 0, 0, null, '_O1g14Z_UnA', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_O1g14Z_UnA&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_O1g14Z_UnA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(313, 1, 'A Biblical Overview of the True Christmas Story', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit shares on the true Christmas Story.</p>', '2019-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:31', 0, 0, null, 'xcI4O2-H-uk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xcI4O2-H-uk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate, so not active', 1, 0, null),
(314, 1, '7 Tips on Becoming a Better Teacher', '<p>In this teaching from 2016, John Schoenheit shares some tips on how to become a more effective teacher of God&#39;s word.</p>', '2019-12-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '28:57', 0, 0, null, 'MS31ooOsJhY', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MS31ooOsJhY&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MS31ooOsJhY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(315, 1, 'Reading and Learning the Bible', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit teaches on reading and learning the Bible.</p>', '2019-11-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:33', 0, 0, null, 'lxa9CCyxD_U', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lxa9CCyxD_U&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lxa9CCyxD_U/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(316, 1, 'The Last Trumpet', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit looks at the Biblical phrases &quot;The Last Trump&quot; and &quot;The Last Trumpet&quot; and explains what they mean.</p>', '2019-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:20', 0, 0, null, 'dxIrhecW_tI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dxIrhecW_tI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate teaching, so not active', 1, 0, null),
(317, 1, '3 Guys Named Joe - Joseph from Genesis, Joseph - Mary''s husband & Joseph of Arimathea', '<p>In this teaching from 2015, Gary Theisen teaches on three guys in the Bible that were named Joe.</p>', '2019-11-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:45', 0, 0, null, 'hPjRwiZh8-Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hPjRwiZh8-Y/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(318, 1, 'The Wall Peg of Love', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit shares on &quot;The &#39;Wall Peg&#39; of Love.&quot;</p>', '2019-11-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:31', 0, 0, null, 'dBBIduxNyX4', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dBBIduxNyX4&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dBBIduxNyX4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(319, 1, 'Being a Christian is like being a Pumpkin', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit presents an analogy of how being a Christian can be similar to being a pumpkin.</p>', '2019-11-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:09', 0, 0, null, 'B82NY-SiN_g', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B82NY-SiN_g&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/B82NY-SiN_g/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(320, 1, 'The Serpent in the Garden of Eden', '<p>Was the serpent in the Garden of Eden a literal snake? Figures of speech in the Bible answer this question. The Hebrew word for snake, &ldquo;nachash&rdquo;, or shining one, also reveals the devil&rsquo;s appearance. Through understanding the use of language, we learn that the Biblical account of the serpent in the Garden of Eden is an actual event and not a fable. The devil&rsquo;s tactics then are the same he uses today.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:1-4; 2 Cor. 11:3, 13-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '23:01', 0, 0, 'deception', 'cpsQdYMZr50', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cpsQdYMZr50/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 52, null),
(321, 1, 'Make Yourself Holy', '<p>In this teaching, John The Bible teaches that we are to be holy, both inwardly and outwardly. Holiness manifests itself through us when we know and are obedient to God&rsquo;s commandments. There are rewards for obedience.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 3:5; Lev. 20:7; John 14:21-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:20', 0, 0, 'sanctify', 'cak2diicT60', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cak2diicT60/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(322, 1, 'How Much is Owed? Forgiveness, Grace, Mercy', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit shares on &quot;How Much is Owed?&quot;</p>', '2019-10-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:59', 0, 0, null, 'NvIaD-My7bI', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NvIaD-My7bI&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NvIaD-My7bI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(323, 1, 'It&rsquo;s Okay To Enjoy Your Life', '<p>God created His creation to be enjoyed. To this end, in this earthly life, there is a time to labor, to laugh, to rejoice, and to enjoy the fruits of our works. As a bonus, Christians can rest in the joy of our hope, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 6:45-52; Titus 2:6; Phil. 3:1; 4:4; Isa. 22:12, 13; 1 Cor. 15:32; Eccles. 2:24; 3:4, 12, 13; 5:18; 8:15; 9:7; 11:8, 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '25:11', 0, 0, 'happiness', 'KedfDz4ThcY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KedfDz4ThcY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(324, 1, 'Sowing in Tears, Reaping in Joy - Some Good Decisions are Tough to Make', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit encourages viewers to make the right decision, even if it isn&#39;t always easy.</p>', '2019-09-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:48', 0, 0, null, 'Pvz4TikAI9g', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pvz4TikAI9g&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Pvz4TikAI9g/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(325, 1, 'When the Going Gets Tough', '<p>Life is difficult and when the going gets tough, we need to remember our hope for a better future. That brings peace to our hearts. The prophet Jeremiah is an illustration of this principle, which is simple to understand but not easy to do. In all things, we are to not be anxious, but to let the peace of God rule in our hearts.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 12:1-5; Phil. 4:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:14', 0, 0, 'Attitude, Complaining', 'DhulyrIfF0k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DhulyrIfF0k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(326, 1, 'Grace - Undeserved Divine Favor', '<p>In this teaching from 2017, John Schoenheit talks about the definition of grace and a common misunderstanding of it.</p>', '2019-09-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:40', 0, 0, null, 'RcgydDJOpLM', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RcgydDJOpLM&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RcgydDJOpLM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(327, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Wait To Get Saved', '<p>This teaching focuses on reasons why people should not wait to become saved. Salvation is an easy gift to receive because Jesus Christ paid the price for our salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9-10; Eccles. 8:8; Acts 16:30-31; 1 John 5:3; Matt. 11:29-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:21', 0, 0, 'death, sin', 'SRQr4ndEByQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SRQr4ndEByQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(328, 1, 'Love is Not Approval', '<p>In this teaching from 2016, John Schoenheit talks about the differences between Love and Approval, and what it means to love people with a godly love.</p>', '2019-08-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:03', 0, 0, null, '8KiR0gt-yvw', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8KiR0gt-yvw&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8KiR0gt-yvw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(329, 1, 'The Kingdom of Heaven is a Treasure', '<p>This teaching explains what the Kingdom of Heaven is by looking at the words of Christ in two parables in the Book of Matthew. Making God our priority is a better and lasting possession than possessing &ldquo;stuff&rdquo; on this earth.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:44-46; Eccles. 5:3; Heb. 10:32-34</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-08-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:09', 0, 0, 'purposeful, rewards, priority', 'Gb3b3uGYfOk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gb3b3uGYfOk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(330, 1, 'Keep Up The Fight', '<p>In this teaching from 2017 John Schoenheit encourages believers to be ambassadors for Christ, and to continue fighting for truth.</p>', '2019-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:48', 0, 0, null, 'hTcyIeYHmXY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hTcyIeYHmXY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(331, 1, 'Should we question the Bible?', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit explores the question of whether or not we should question the Bible.</p>', '2019-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:56', 0, 0, null, 'dDFnt6q2CpM', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dDFnt6q2CpM&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dDFnt6q2CpM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(332, 1, 'What does the Bible say about God?', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit of Spirit and Truth Fellowship International shows us some of the specific ways the Bible describes God.</p>', '2019-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:02', 0, 0, null, 'aczWdtd-MII', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aczWdtd-MII/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate, not active', 1, 0, null),
(333, 1, 'Should We Be Authentic?', '<p>There&#39;s a lot of talk today about being &ldquo;authentic&rdquo; and &ldquo;saying what&rsquo;s on your heart,&rdquo; but what does the Bible say about telling others how you feel? In this teaching from 2016, John Schoenheit explores that question.</p>', '2019-07-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:05', 0, 0, null, 'ME93vXD5NJc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ME93vXD5NJc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate, hence not active', 1, 0, null),
(334, 1, 'Life is Short - Make Plans', '<p>Our time on earth is limited. We may not know the limit, but it is limited. That&#39;s why in this 2016 teaching John Schoenheit talks about how it&#39;s so important that we make plans and make the most of our lives.</p>', '2019-07-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:46', 0, 0, null, 'LmYiD46j5QU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LmYiD46j5QU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(335, 1, 'Figures of Speech used in the Bible - Synecdoche', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about Synecdoche, a figure of speech found in verses like Jeremiah 26:9, Matthew 3:5, and 2 Kings 8:9.</p>', '2019-07-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:54', 0, 0, null, '4jNcaoJN758', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4jNcaoJN758&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4jNcaoJN758/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(336, 1, 'Jesus Christ - The Lamb and the Lion', '<p>The Devil and his cohorts have an aggressive program to get people to live ungodly lives and make them feel like it doesn&rsquo;t matter. When Jesus Christ walked the earth the first time, he came as the sacrificial Lamb. When he comes to rule the earth, he will come as the Lion and rule with an iron rod. Submission to God matters now and in the age to come.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:10; 2 Pet. 1:4; Eph. 5:1-5; James 3:1; John 1:29; Rev. 5:5; Ps. 2:1-4, 6, 8-9, 12; Isa. 11:1-5; Rev. 20:13-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '25:57', 0, 0, 'enemies, hell, Satan, salvation, temptation, rebellion', 'oj6oqIJdzSc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oj6oqIJdzSc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 40, null),
(337, 1, 'Righteousness: Treating God and Others Right', '<p>Righteousness has two meanings in the scriptures: one is about our right standing before God and the other is about how we live in honesty, truth, kindness and justice. As we please God by living righteously, we will encounter persecution on earth, but like Jesus, we will &ldquo;fear not&rdquo; as we look forward to our future hope.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23, 24; 10:9; 2 Tim. 3:16; 2:22; 3:12; Gal. 6:10; Phil. 4:8; Ps. 11:7; 37:21; 1 Sam. 12:7; Matt. 5:6, 10, 20; 6:23; Luke 11:46; Jer. 23:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '30:15', 0, 0, 'heart, serve, genuine, declaration, choice', 'AMxVtDtkM5c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AMxVtDtkM5c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(338, 1, 'You Are the Salt of the Earth', '<p>Jesus recognized salt as being essential for life. Salt has many positive properties, however, once it becomes rancid, it is not only worthless, but can cause harm to the things that it touches. Jesus encouraged believers to live like the essential salt of the earth.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:36', 0, 0, 'ambassador, light, custom', 'zZ1T1KdOYbk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zZ1T1KdOYbk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(339, 1, 'Three Consequences of Sin', '<p>In this teaching from 2017, John Schoenheit discusses the three major consequences of sin.</p>', '2019-06-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:00', 0, 0, null, '7BU8UY1LL1s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7BU8UY1LL1s/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(340, 1, 'Love Your Neighbor As Yourself', '<p>In this teaching from 2016 John Schoenheit discusses the second commandment and a misunderstanding associated with it.</p>', '2019-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:29', 0, 0, null, '4VcMZ9Nr_p0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4VcMZ9Nr_p0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(342, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible - Asyndeton', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit shares on the figure of speech asyndeton.</p>', '2019-05-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:42', 0, 0, null, 'zZDPvZ2Hs1I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zZDPvZ2Hs1I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(343, 1, 'Figures of Speech used in the Bible - Antonomasia', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit shares on the figure of speech antonomasia.</p>', '2019-05-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:45', 0, 0, null, 'Rz8QPS1B3gw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Rz8QPS1B3gw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(344, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible - Polysyndeton', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit shares on the figure of speech polysyndeton.</p>', '2019-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:13', 0, 0, null, 'txQNuADkDE4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/txQNuADkDE4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(345, 1, 'We''re Not Okay On Our Own: We Need Jesus', '<p>There is good news and bad news. Bad news: Everyone will face challenges in this fallen world. We all need help. Good news: God sent His Son to make possible a much better next life. As the Lord&rsquo;s ambassadors, Christians are called to share the gift of salvation that is ours through the work of our Savior.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:4; Luke 5:27-32; Prov. 1:7; 9:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:35', 0, 0, 'death, devil, knowledge, Pharisees, salvation, sinner, truth, wisdom', 'cBv1vEcWZBM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cBv1vEcWZBM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(346, 1, 'Reasons Why the Resurrection is Believable', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit talks about some reasons why the resurrection of Jesus Christ is believable.</p>', '2019-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:00', 0, 0, null, 'PIIPqkkCO38', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PIIPqkkCO38&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PIIPqkkCO38/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(347, 1, 'Jesus Christ - Our Approach Offering', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit talks about how Jesus Christ is our approach offering.</p>', '2019-04-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, null, 'I_gzyonVX90', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I_gzyonVX90&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I_gzyonVX90/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(348, 1, 'Parable of the Talents', '<p>Everyone has gifts or talents to support the Body of Christ. In the parable of the talents we are encouraged to remain faithful and to do the best we can with what we have to store up rewards in the future Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:14-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '27:39', 0, 0, null, 'iwYDD7LJr5Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iwYDD7LJr5Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'fix scripture ref', 1, 7, null),
(349, 1, 'Godliness with Contentment is Great Gain', '<p>This teaching reminds us that life is not fair. 1 Timothy 6:6 prompts us to approach life with joy and peace. We can work at being content and enjoy ourselves while blessing God and His people.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 5:16-18; 1 Tim. 6:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:42', 0, 0, null, 'NP3CQ6WEjH0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NP3CQ6WEjH0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(350, 1, 'The Calling of the Disciples of Jesus', '<p>The Disciples followed Jesus for a reason, and in this teaching from 2015, John Schoenheit explains why they would drop what they were doing to follow him.</p>', '2019-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:47', 0, 0, null, 'fIbT6xCqLPs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fIbT6xCqLPs/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'dup, so not active', 0, 0, null),
(351, 1, 'Controlling Your Tongue', '<p>God created us to live in a social context and to interact with all kinds of people in a variety of situations. As Christians, we derive great value in being careful about our words and making a diligent effort to control what comes out of our mouths.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:29; James 3:2-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:08', 0, 0, null, '-WtaFWN-hAg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-WtaFWN-hAg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(352, 1, 'Either For or Against Christ', '<p>There is no middle ground regarding the Christian&rsquo;s stand for God and Jesus Christ. This teaching clarifies what it is to be for or against Jesus Christ as is stated in Matthew 12:30.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:30; Eph. 2:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:49', 0, 0, 'character', '1qD1NQsJJM0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1qD1NQsJJM0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(353, 1, 'Our Relationship with Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching examines a section of Jesus&rsquo; teaching at the Last Supper. How believers frame in their minds their relationship with Jesus Christ will determine how they move forward in that relationship.</p> <p>Verses: John 15:9-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:32', 0, 0, null, 'qyheLyjxcNw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qyheLyjxcNw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(354, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible (Metonymy)', '<p>In this teaching from 2012 John Schoenheit shares on the figure of speech Metonymy found in the Bible.</p>', '2019-03-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:25', 0, 0, null, 'Zv9iNKxTqu0', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zv9iNKxTqu0&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Zv9iNKxTqu0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(355, 1, 'Spiritual Warfare and Prayer', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit teaches on the subject of prayer and the spiritual battle. He explains why our prayers matter and shows examples from the Bible.</p>', '2019-02-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:22', 0, 0, null, 'cBlcTrXYiU4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cBlcTrXYiU4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(356, 1, 'The Opportunities Around You', '<p>This teaching focuses on three records in which Jesus Christ recognized an opportunity to serve God. In each, he focused only on one person, but they ultimately led to changing the lives of many people. As believers we also need to pay attention to the opportunities before us to serve God. We do not know when one small act may lead to something much bigger.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 9:9-10; Luke 19:9-10; John 4:3-35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:32', 0, 0, 'evangelism, service, outreach, harvest', 'D0W2WgBJGFM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/D0W2WgBJGFM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(357, 1, 'How to Pray', '<p>In this teaching prayer is defined: what it is, what it is not, what you need to do and what you do not need to do. The focus is on three points: prayer is easy, God wants you to do it, and it is vitally important to do.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 25:21; Matt. 6:6-8; 10:30; 29:39; Luke 11:3, 5-6, 8; Rom. 12:12; Eph. 6:18; Col. 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:17; Heb. 4:16; James 4:2; 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:51', 0, 0, 'ask, boldness, receive', 'WbFC94w6ypQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WbFC94w6ypQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 49, null),
(358, 1, 'Forgiveness - Why We Need To Forgive', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit talks about forgiveness and why it&#39;s so important that we forgive.</p>', '2019-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 0, 0, null, 'XiSFMK1XNcg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XiSFMK1XNcg&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XiSFMK1XNcg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(359, 1, 'The Four Men Crucified with Christ', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit shares about the other men that were crucified with Jesus Christ.</p>', '2019-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:48', 0, 0, null, 'Jyysnj3ekIY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Jyysnj3ekIY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(360, 1, 'Our Sin and God''s Mercy', '<p>When God created Adam and Eve, He told them not to eat of the tree of knowledge (Genesis 2:17). But Adam and Eve disobeyed God and through that disobedience, sin entered the world. In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about our sin and God&#39;s mercy.</p>', '2019-01-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:23', 0, 0, null, 'Hr5fTPz-Uu8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Hr5fTPz-Uu8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(361, 1, 'The Christian Life isn''t Easy', '<p>In this teaching from xxxx</p>', '2019-01-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:46', 0, 0, null, 'QSrCiYiKe_E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QSrCiYiKe_E/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate, not active', 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(362, 1, 'Divinely Instructed - Commentary on the Magi', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit looks at the Magi and their task of going to see the newborn Christ.</p>', '2019-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 0, 0, null, 'o_-JbbWt34g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/o_-JbbWt34g/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(363, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Death Penalty?', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit shares on what the Bible says about capital punishment.</p>', '2018-12-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:07', 0, 0, null, 'fqQdNDpwTP8', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fqQdNDpwTP8&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fqQdNDpwTP8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(364, 1, 'Who do you think you are?', '<p>One of our goals as Christians is to believe what the Bible says about us. We are to reject the mental conditioning of the world, and instead be imitators of God. Think as God thinks!</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:14; Rom. 8:37; 1 Cor. 3:9; 2 Cor. 5:20; 3:2-6; Eph. 5:1; Phil. 4:13; 1 John 3:1; 4:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-12-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:38', 0, 0, 'transformation, renew', 'BXZGu5JHnmE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BXZGu5JHnmE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(365, 1, 'Complaining Does Not Help', '<p>Though complaining is a human universal act, biblically speaking, Jesus never complained. To complain is harmful in at least four ways, discussed in this teaching. As believers our goal should be to capture our thoughts, speak words of grace, and imitate Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:4, 6, 7; Acts 14:22; 2 Cor. 4:4; 10:5; Eph. 4:29; Phil. 2:14, 15; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:56', 0, 0, 'self- control, choice, edification', 'ZPsroPdprSk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZPsroPdprSk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 25, null),
(366, 1, 'An Overview of Figures of Speech used in the Bible (Ellipsis, Polysyndeton, Asyndeton...)', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, John Schoenheit gives us a brief overview of some figures of speech used in the Bible.</p>', '2018-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:13', 0, 0, null, 'z9bb1VULx7k', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z9bb1VULx7k&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/z9bb1VULx7k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(367, 1, 'Our Freewill Choice: Everlasting Life or Everlasting Death', '<p>In this teaching from 2012 John Schoenheit discusses Free Will and how we can choose our destiny.</p>', '2018-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:11', 0, 0, null, 'zR4Z7USsTzY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zR4Z7USsTzY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(368, 1, 'Flying Beneath the World''s Radar', '<p>In this teaching from 2016, John Schoenheit explains how it&#39;s becoming more and more important for Christians to walk in wisdom and walk by the Spirit.</p>', '2018-11-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:48', 0, 0, null, 'vLeCu7GWcdI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vLeCu7GWcdI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(369, 1, 'Looking at Ourselves and Others the Way God Does', '<p>This teaching shows how the world views people quite differently from the way God views people. The world devalues people by nearly always looking at the outward appearance and finding flaws, but God looks at the heart.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:25; 1 Sam. 16:6-7; John 10:10; Rom. 12:1-2; Eph. 4:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:38', 0, 0, null, 'atAa2JCvgOc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/atAa2JCvgOc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(370, 1, 'The Wisdom Model Of Living Life', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit explains the wisdom model of living life.</p>', '2018-11-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:04', 0, 0, null, 'vwcLrJK-v4I', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwcLrJK-v4I&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vwcLrJK-v4I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(371, 1, 'Where did the word Rapture come from?', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit looks at the root of the word Rapture and where it came from.</p>', '2018-11-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:40', 0, 0, null, 'rIoBCiRFyCA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rIoBCiRFyCA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(372, 1, 'Guard Your Heart', '<p>Protect your heart more than anything else by paying attention to what you say, see, and do, by speaking godly words, focusing your eyes straight ahead, and walking a godly path.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:20-27; Eccles. 5:2; Mark 7:14-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:17', 0, 0, 'health, life, morality', 'ok4g7T7wguA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ok4g7T7wguA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(373, 1, 'Lessons from Ezekiel 11', '<p>While Ezekiel was in captivity God gave him a vision about the evil rulers back in Jerusalem and instructed him to prophesy against them. We must deal with evil rulers today, and God enlists us to help Him deal with these evil circumstances through prayer, prophecy and other actions.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 11:1-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '34:31', 0, 0, 'meat, caldron, remnant, sanctuary', 'o4yrkoBB9uc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/o4yrkoBB9uc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(374, 1, 'The Walk of Love', '<p>Ephesians 5 continues the instruction to put on the new way of life by walking in love and being imitators of God. Allowing Christ to shine upon us and walking in the spirit will help us live wisely.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: Janet Speaks</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:29', 0, 0, 'disobedience, fruit, light, darkness, thanksgiving', 'RiNH2uS0MQw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RiNH2uS0MQw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(375, 1, 'We Are Now Fellow Heirs In Union With Christ', '<p>The multifaceted wisdom of God that He kept secret throughout the ages has now been revealed. We now have received the good news that Gentiles and Jews are united together in union with Christ into one body, and are sealed with the promised holy spirit</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:11-22; 3:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '32:48', 0, 0, 'grace, citizenship, salvation, peace, administration', 'VBHm9jZSM0w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VBHm9jZSM0w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(376, 1, 'Your God-given Armor – Ephesians 6:10-24', '<p>Find out how God has equipped us to stand effectively in today&rsquo;s world. A continuing pursuit of accurate knowledge of Scripture is essential to being able to &ldquo;wrestle&rdquo; daily for &ldquo;the long haul.&rdquo; Find in-depth insight about what God has given us and how to make the most of it so you can stand on truth in this world.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:10-24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '34:07', 0, 0, 'Strength, Wrestle, Belt, Breastplate, Shield, Sword', '86RzKe8F-VI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/86RzKe8F-VI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(377, 1, 'How One Family Applies Ephesians', '<p>To make successful relationships possible, it takes all that God has provided us in the first 4 chapters of Ephesians. Learn valuable lessons concerning 3 types of relationships discussed: husbands and wives, parents and children, leaders and workers. Personal examples are shared from the Theisen family&rsquo;s journey as they walk out principles from Ephesians 5:21-6:4.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:21-6:4</p> <p>Teacher: Theisen Family (Gary, Karen, Grace)</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '52:03', 0, 0, 'Submit, Obey, Intimacy, Employment', 'RKwDwNCGhlc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RKwDwNCGhlc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(378, 1, 'The Practical Walk of Newness', '<p>We are all familiar with our personal tendencies toward worldly behavior. But what about the behavior of the new life Jesus bought for us? Learn how we can walk out the journey of the new man one small victory at a time. God has provided choices for us that will help us be more like His Son.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:15-32</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:39', 0, 0, 'Growth, Choice', 'vtxX--7yuW4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vtxX--7yuW4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(379, 1, 'Why Does God Love Us?', '<p>Ephesians 2:6 tells us God has raised us up and seated us with Christ, but why? The next verse tells us why - so that God could have forever to show us how much He loves us. We are God&rsquo;s masterpiece even if we don&rsquo;t feel like it. This short video delves deeply into why God has done so much for us.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:7-10</p> <p>Teacher: Gabe Hickman</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:52', 0, 0, null, '_kSg6IMXYOs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_kSg6IMXYOs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(380, 1, 'How God Changed Our Position And Condition', '<p>Before the wholeness of Christ became a personal reality, each of us was living in a condition of deadness, pursuing our own desires. &ldquo;But God &hellip;&rdquo; two words that change our condition and position eternally. This short video emphasizes the great change from death to life that God has brought about for each of us.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:53', 0, 0, null, 'd39_6SuVLtY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/d39_6SuVLtY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(381, 1, 'Paul''s Prayer in Ephesians 1', '<p>Explore this record of Paul as he prays for wisdom, insight, and revelation that we would come to know Jesus Christ more deeply as our Lord. Our rich inheritance from God is included and is more than a bonus, it is the promise of the hope of His calling, the riches of His glorious inheritance, and the surpassing greatness of His power.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:15-23</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:44', 0, 0, null, '0cHU2LoV48Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0cHU2LoV48Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(382, 1, 'God is Blessed with You', '<p>Explore the in-depth opening phrases of Paul&rsquo;s letter to the Ephesians. Hear about how everything we have is from God, who placed us in union with Christ and secured our future when we simply said &ldquo;Yes, I believe.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:33', 0, 0, null, 'U_BbTcul2zY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U_BbTcul2zY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(383, 1, 'Ezekiel - We Are All Useful to God', '<p>Uncover many hidden truths regarding your usefulness to God in this in-depth look at the life of Ezekiel. You are a fellow worker with God. He considers you important and useful, so hang in there through difficult times and God will reward you richly.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 1:1-4; 2:1-4; 40:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:16', 0, 0, null, 'FCIwmYckwv0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FCIwmYckwv0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(384, 1, 'Take Time With God', '<p>God is asking us to spend time with Him. How do we spend our free time? Spending time with God in prayer and study of His Word is valuable to us and a good way to spend our time.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 11:1; 18:1; Rom. 12:12; Eph. 6:18; Col. 4:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-09-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:19', 0, 0, null, 'FbkOUFUw0pA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FbkOUFUw0pA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(385, 1, 'Holy Not Happy - God Wants Us Holy', '<p>The Bible tells us that we must strive to be holy. We will go through many trials as we walk our path in life. God directs us to make good choices and trust Him. Reading and studying His word will help to guide us into holiness.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 11:4; 20:7: Matt. 5:4; Rom. 12:1; 1 Pet. 1:15-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-09-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:31', 0, 0, null, 'fwvLo1Lssqo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fwvLo1Lssqo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(387, 1, 'Was Jesus teaching about The Rapture in Matthew 24?', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit talks about Matthew 24 and whether Jesus was talking about the rapture</p>', '2018-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:29', 0, 0, null, 'hJGAJp6DUyY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hJGAJp6DUyY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(388, 1, 'Wisdom and Self-Control', '<p>God wants us to be successful in our lives. We are to seek wisdom and be vigilantly attentive so we can achieve this. Success requires planning and discipline.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:7; 5:23; Gal. 5:20-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-08-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:34', 0, 0, null, 'GBr4nCdGqsw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GBr4nCdGqsw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(389, 1, 'What does the Bible say about suffering?', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit shows some specific ways of how the Bible describes God.</p>', '2018-08-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:01', 0, 0, null, 'BxttScYUcWA', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BxttScYUcWA&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BxttScYUcWA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(390, 1, 'Rewards in the Kingdom', '<p>God promises us future rewards to motivate us to do good works for Him now. We know in the end that Jesus will return to the earth and we will be judged and repaid for our work we have done. In Christ&rsquo;s Kingdom we will each have a job which will be determined by the work we do for God while we are living now.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 12:13-14; Ezek. 33:20; Isa. 35:1-2; Jer. 17:10; Dan. 2:34-35; Hab. 2:14; Matt. 5:5; 16:27; Acts 3:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:05:58', 0, 0, null, 'lPz_aUCMHcM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lPz_aUCMHcM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 145, null),
(391, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Karma?', '<p>The Bible supports the often-used adage &ndash; &lsquo;What goes around comes around.&rsquo; Throughout the Psalms and Proverbs, we learn that when we do evil, we open ourselves up to pathways for evil to attack us. Evil eagerly pursues sinners. Often, those who dig a pit to bring harm to others will ultimately fall into it themselves.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 7:14; 9:15; 10:2; 57:6; Prov. 1:17-18, 29-31; 5:22; 11:19; 13:21; 17:11; 26:27; 28:10; Jer. 2:19; Ezek. 11:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-08-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:59', 0, 0, null, '3VMNmtkYUEQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3VMNmtkYUEQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(392, 1, 'Dealing with Evil', '<p>In this teaching from 2011, John Schoenheit talks about dealing with evil, and standing firm in righteousness.</p>', '2018-08-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:36', 0, 0, null, 'nUdX350EbTQ', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nUdX350EbTQ&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nUdX350EbTQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(393, 1, 'Register for the 2018 STF National Event!', '<p>Free registration and all the event details are available here: https://www.stfonline.org/event-items/2018-national-event</p>', '2018-08-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:31', 0, 0, null, '_NQQ-wnBZRY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_NQQ-wnBZRY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'inactive invitation', 1, 0, null),
(394, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Lying?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about what the Bible has to say about lying or telling half truths.</p>', '2018-07-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 0, 0, null, 'EhhLIDDFGnE', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EhhLIDDFGnE&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EhhLIDDFGnE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(395, 1, 'Is Jesus Crying Over You?', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit answers the question of whether Jesus is crying over us.</p>', '2018-07-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:33', 0, 0, null, 'FdLO0BEJ1Ao', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FdLO0BEJ1Ao&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FdLO0BEJ1Ao/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(396, 1, 'God Loved Us First', '<p>Our faces are like the moon - they reflect light. They are bright when blessed, dim when troubled. We reflect the glory of Christ when we really grasp the love of Christ and that he has set us free.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:6-10; 7:15-25; 1 Cor. 6:12; 10:23; 2 Cor. 3:17-18; Gal. 5:1, 13; 1 John 4:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-07-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:33', 0, 0, 'Freedom, Liberty', 'S3mhOcMF630', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S3mhOcMF630/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(397, 1, 'How to Find Your Ministry', '<p>Every believer has a ministry, a way of serving in the Body of Christ. The Lord will give each believer the grace needed to do what He has called them to do. This teaching helps the believer clarify what his way of serving in the Body of Christ may be.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:7-8, 11-12; Romans 12:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:22', 0, 0, 'apostle, evangelist, fellow-laborers, gifts, mercy, pastor, prophet, service, teach', 'Henk5w99lYk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Henk5w99lYk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(398, 1, 'Modesty - Who Are You Serving?', '<p>Everything a person does either serves God or the devil. There is no neutral ground. The devil constantly pressures cultures to turn away from God. There is a day coming when we will face the judgement seat of Christ. We need to understand the expectations of God and choose a lifestyle that is pleasing to him.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 10:21-23; 2 Cor 5:10; Eccles. 12:13-14; Matt. 12:30; Prov. 4:7; 1 Tim. 2:9; 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-06-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:41', 0, 0, 'leadership, respect, success, wisdom', 'sAUapN7eZJs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sAUapN7eZJs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(401, 1, 'Romans 10:9 - Take Jesus as Lord', '<p>What does it mean to take Jesus as Lord? It is important for Christians to know that just going to church on Sunday or believing in a historical Jesus, meaning merely that you believe he existed, is not enough. Receiving eternal life involves a mind and heart of commitment to trust Christ as our Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:21, 22; 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-06-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:14', 0, 0, 'salvation, righteousness, saved, confess', '3vwO0jCcTJo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3vwO0jCcTJo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 43, null),
(402, 1, 'Deal With Things As They Are', '<p>In this teaching from 2011, John Schoenheit shares on dealing with things as they are.</p>', '2018-06-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 0, 0, null, '6OupyJNA1YQ', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6OupyJNA1YQ&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6OupyJNA1YQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(403, 1, 'Can Anything Separate Us From the Love of God?', '<p>That a person is saved from everlasting death through faith in Christ Jesus is the theme of the book of Romans. Throughout the first eight chapters, many verses are highlighted that speak about our assurance of salvation. In the last five verses of chapter eight we see that nothing, not even ourselves, can ever separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:35-39</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '58:12', 0, 0, 'secure', 'dbTuuaX3HT4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dbTuuaX3HT4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 53, null),
(404, 1, 'Submission in Christ', '<p>In this teaching from 2011, John Schoenheit talks about submission in Christ and obeying the Lord.</p>', '2018-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:37', 0, 0, null, '5m1HjFvMptE', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5m1HjFvMptE&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5m1HjFvMptE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(405, 1, 'The Purpose of God''s Word', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit talks about what the purpose of the Bible is.</p>', '2018-05-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:19', 0, 0, null, 'yz0khkzA4lI', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yz0khkzA4lI&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yz0khkzA4lI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(406, 1, 'Romans 8:1 - No Condemnation', '<p>The Good News in the epistle to the Romans (and to us) is that everyone who trusts in Jesus Christ is declared righteous in the sight of God. By studying the context of Romans 8:1, as well as the scope of Scripture, the meaning of the verse becomes clear. The phrase &ldquo;no condemnation&rdquo; points to our ultimate future &ndash; eternal life.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:1; Rev. 20:11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '26:55', 0, 0, 'righteousness, sin, salvation', 'FiBC_w7wA8o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FiBC_w7wA8o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 33, null),
(407, 1, 'Are There Lost Books Of the Bible?', '<p>In this teaching from XXXX, John Schoenheit talks about whether there are lost or missing books of the Bible.</p>', '2018-05-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:29', 0, 0, null, 'UsOhEKJ0KIg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UsOhEKJ0KIg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(408, 1, 'Joy and Thankfulness', '<p>Joy and happiness are feelings that we will enjoy if we cultivate the habit of being thankful and joyful. These are attitudes believers should adopt in response to God&rsquo;s commands.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:20-21; Luke 10:17; Eph. 5:20; Phil. 3:1; 4:4; Col. 3:15, 17; 1 Thess. 5:16, 18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:27', 0, 0, null, 'uxIF-Qbr51g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uxIF-Qbr51g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(409, 1, 'Guard Your Heart', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, John Schoenheit talks about how important it is for us to guard our hearts.</p>', '2018-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:54', 0, 0, null, 'V7f3BMUCCTk', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V7f3BMUCCTk&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V7f3BMUCCTk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(410, 1, 'Keep Your Peace and Joy in Troubled Times', '<p>The Adversary, the Devil, is always after God and Christ, which translates into God&rsquo;s people being attacked for their stand. If Christians know this spiritual war is around them all the time, they do not need to be surprised by the suffering they incur. There is a way to draw comfort and find peace and joy in spite of troubled times.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; Ps. 89:46-51; 1 Cor. 10:13; 2 Cor. 1:5; Phil. 4:4; 2 Tim. 3:12; 1 Pet. 4:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-04-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, 'persecution', 'LhKcvHpt64I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LhKcvHpt64I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(411, 1, 'You Are The Soil!', '<p>In the parable of the sower and the seeds, the Bible is comparing us to soil. By paying attention to the descriptions of what happens to the seed that is sown in different types of soil, we learn that if we want to be successful in life, we need to decide what kind of soil we will be and what results we want.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:1-9, 18-23.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-04-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:14', 0, 0, 'fruit', 'dpILCJQpPMk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dpILCJQpPMk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(412, 1, 'God Will Handle Your Anxiety', '<p>Sometimes God tells us to do things that seem impossible, such as to not be anxious about anything. How is this possible? God wants to handle things for us just like parents would for their children. We also find additional advice and the outcome is highly desirable.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 4:6-8; 1 Pet. 5:7.</p> <p>Teacher: Franklin Smith</p>', '2018-04-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:51', 0, 0, 'prayer, petitions, thanksgiving, requests, supplication, righteousness, praise, praiseworthy, heart, mind', 'mzE1BoVQzi4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mzE1BoVQzi4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated at Franklin''s request', 1, 0, null),
(413, 1, 'Trust Like a Mustard Seed', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit teaches on the differences between faith and trust.</p>', '2018-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:28', 0, 0, null, '9Mj_6zOrQ7k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9Mj_6zOrQ7k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(415, 1, 'Dance at the Presence of Yahweh!', '<p>The Hebrew word &ldquo;<em>chiyl</em>&rdquo; has two basic meanings and can be translated &ldquo;tremble&rdquo; or &ldquo;dance&rdquo;. Which should be used in this verse? The answer is both! God, in His infinite wisdom, is producing something to put us in deep thought, prayer, and self-reflection. There is something you can do to assure that you dance at the presence of Yahweh.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 37:20, 35-38; 98:8-9; 114:1-8; Isa. 35:1, 2, 5-7; 55:12-13; Rom. 8:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:32', 0, 0, 'righteousness, praise, rejoice, wicked', 'hplMp9Hg07E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hplMp9Hg07E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(416, 1, 'The Baptism of Jesus Christ - Commentary from the REV', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit discusses the baptism of Jesus Christ.</p>', '2018-03-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:25', 0, 0, null, 'FJ0rqOEfvM8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FJ0rqOEfvM8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(417, 1, 'A new understanding of Philippians 4:13', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit shows us a new perspective on Philippians 4:13.</p>', '2018-03-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:40', 0, 0, null, 'wdSAG-LYodk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wdSAG-LYodk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 0, 0, null),
(418, 1, 'The Obedience Model of Pleasing God', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about pleasing God with our obedience.</p>', '2018-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:28', 0, 0, null, 'QtaVzQ0Wvys', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QtaVzQ0Wvys&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QtaVzQ0Wvys/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(419, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Soul?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about what the Bible has to say about the soul.</p>', '2018-02-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:47', 0, 0, null, 'U0Hb4cB098M', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U0Hb4cB098M&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U0Hb4cB098M/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(420, 1, 'Know what you want and go for it!', '<p>In this teaching from XXXX, John Schoenheit talks about how we should ask for things from God.</p>', '2018-02-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:24', 0, 0, null, 'ozyDJO5jZX4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ozyDJO5jZX4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(421, 1, 'How to Love God - An action, not just a feeling', '<p>In this teaching from 2011, Dan Gallagher talks about how we are supposed to love God.</p>', '2018-02-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:23', 0, 0, null, 'bAEVdz2zRFw', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bAEVdz2zRFw&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bAEVdz2zRFw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(422, 1, 'Is Everything That Happens God''s Will?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about whether everything that happens is God&#39;s will or not.</p>', '2018-01-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:32', 0, 0, null, 'b5XClawWYB4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b5XClawWYB4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'This teaching is a repost, so it''s not active', 0, 0, null),
(423, 1, 'Why Bother to Know the Truth?', '<p>In this video from 2015, Franklin Smith talks about why knowing the truth is so important.</p>', '2018-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:57', 0, 0, null, 'YRmU-ImIrac', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YRmU-ImIrac&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YRmU-ImIrac/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(424, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Foul Language?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit gives Biblical examples on why we shouldn&#39;t use foul language.</p>', '2018-01-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:53', 0, 0, null, 'bHbUqLNpNAQ', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bHbUqLNpNAQ&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bHbUqLNpNAQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(425, 1, 'Are You On God''s Train?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit talks about how we should all make sure we&#39;re on &quot;God&#39;s train&quot;.</p>', '2018-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:58', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 'eIlr361WM8A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eIlr361WM8A/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null);
