(426, 1, 'The Simple Church - getting together in Jesus'' name', '<p>In this teaching from 2010, Dan Gallagher discusses the simple church.</p>', '2017-12-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:07', 0, 0, null, 'LgzpAyuLBEY', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LgzpAyuLBEY&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LgzpAyuLBEY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(428, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Heaven?', '<p>In this teaching from 2013, John Schoenheit shows us what the Bible has to say about the future kingdom.</p>', '2017-12-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:43', 0, 0, null, 'ZS2Ign6faBc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZS2Ign6faBc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(429, 1, 'Keys to Walking with Spiritual Power', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, Dan Gallagher shares on how Jesus Christ has given us a Power of Attorney.</p>', '2017-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:52', 0, 0, null, 'jXxmdsl7upk', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jXxmdsl7upk&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jXxmdsl7upk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(430, 1, 'Why did Jesus move to Capernaum?', '<p>In this teaching from 2014, John Schoenheit explores the question of why Jesus moved to Capernaum.</p>', '2017-12-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:42', 0, 0, null, 'PIEe3I43n7o', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PIEe3I43n7o&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PIEe3I43n7o/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 1, null),
(431, 1, 'Grace - Undeserved Divine Favor', '<p>From our act of humble obedience to God in receiving Jesus as Lord and Savior, we receive the &ldquo;gift of grace&rdquo; that is beyond our grasp to comprehend. Our genuine humility, obedience, and submission toward God opens us up to a relationship with Him in His magnificent grace.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9-10; Prov. 3:33, 34; James 4:6, 7; 1 Pet. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:15', 0, 0, 'love', 'wVcRloNi1QQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wVcRloNi1QQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(432, 1, 'The Spiritual Battle - Desensitized to Evil', '<p>In this teaching from 2013 Dan Gallagher speaks about the spiritual battle, and how we&#39;ve become desensitized to evil.</p>', '2017-11-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:51', 0, 0, null, 'zwYouKNkBgQ', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zwYouKNkBgQ&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zwYouKNkBgQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(433, 1, 'We Are God&rsquo;s Beacons of the Light', '<p>Don&rsquo;t focus on the outward appearance of the lighthouse, but rather focus on the light within the lighthouse that sends out rays of life, safety and joy. Jesus is the light that lives within us that shines out to a world in darkness.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 4:6-16; 12:7-10; Rom. 7:14-19; Heb. 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-11-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:53', 0, 0, 'ambassadors', '7dI-VUqNxL8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7dI-VUqNxL8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(434, 1, 'Love Comes From God - How to be Loving', '<p>In this teaching from 2009, Jackson Trigg talks about love and how we should work to be more loving.</p>', '2017-11-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:40', 0, 0, null, '2DrDg2RWzno', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2DrDg2RWzno/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(435, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Ghosts?', '<p>In this teaching from 2012, John Schoenheit discusses what the Bible has to say about ghosts.</p>', '2017-10-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 0, 0, null, '9C3CwNY-Ezw', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9C3CwNY-Ezw&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9C3CwNY-Ezw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(436, 1, 'Don''t Bury Your Talent', '<p>Every believer is given abilities to be used for God&rsquo;s benefit. We are exhorted not to compare ourselves to others and not to be held back by fear. To use our talents is a choice - so, say &ldquo;yes&rdquo; to God&rsquo;s blessings and experience the joy of the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:14-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-10-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:31', 0, 0, 'rewards', '_WKPMEuFuno', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_WKPMEuFuno/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(437, 1, 'Live Love - Even when You Don&rsquo;t Feel Like It', '<p>This teaching acknowledges our imperfections in the flesh yet encourages us to go forth into the world to love effectively and fiercely like our savior Jesus did. Believers are to &ldquo;walk out&rdquo; their salvation by loving the unlovable. Conflict presents an opportunity to face issues, to speak the truth in love and to offer life and hope instead of shame and marginalization.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 4:7, 8; John 13:1-38; 10:17, 18; 17:6, 20; Rom. 12:9, 16, 17, 18; Col. 1:27; Eph. 4:15; 2 Pet. 1:8, 9; 1 Pet. 4:11; Isa. 52:13, 14; Zech. 13:7; Phil. 3:10</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2017-09-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:51:48', 0, 0, 'mission, suffering, endure', 'KR0IJhcwAMg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KR0IJhcwAMg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(438, 1, 'Inner Peace Not Outer Peace', '<p>This teaching presents seven keys to being peaceful. We need to recognize that life is not easy. We will have difficulties in our lives, but if we are equipped with the knowledge of how to care for ourselves, we can handle the issues of life.</p> <p>Verses: Ecc. 5:13; Ps. 23:5; Prov. 3:25; Matt. 14:13; Luke 21:25-26; Acts 14:21; Phil. 4:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-09-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '54:45', 0, 0, null, 'i5pwna7yWHg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/i5pwna7yWHg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(439, 1, 'STF National Conference - Praise & Worship', null, '2017-09-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '35:38', 0, 0, null, 'l35iWrDhYLg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/l35iWrDhYLg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not a teaching', 1, 0, null),
(440, 1, 'Human Trafficking:  How You Can Help', '<p>Human trafficking is a very real and difficult problem in our world today. Jesus calls us to help, to reach out to those in trouble. This sharing addresses how we, in our own ways, can help those entrapped in sex trafficking situations to get help.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 58:6-14;</p> <p>Teacher: Karen and Grace Theisen</p>', '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:23:22', 0, 0, null, 'sSdnTB2WIME', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sSdnTB2WIME/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(441, 1, 'Apologetics Seminar: Learn How to Discuss Our Beliefs With Confidence', '<p>This teaching addresses how to be ready with answers when questions come up regarding Jesus Christ and his Father God. Our beliefs affect our world view and these, along with our experiences and life history, determine how we see God in our lives. Let&rsquo;s set ourselves up to feel confident when discussing our beliefs.</p> <p>Teachers: Jerry Wierwille and John Truitt</p>', '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:29:23', 0, 0, null, '0XXB1wW-C4w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0XXB1wW-C4w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(442, 1, 'The Heart is the Dwelling Place of our Lord', '<p>Our hearts determine our relationship with God. It is important to make a space where God can dwell in our hearts in order for us to thrive. To heal deep heart wounds, we must study, pray, and praise Him, and slowly our wounds will heal.</p> <p>Verses: Pss. 139:23; 133:1; Prov. 4:23; 27:19; Jer. 17:9; Matt. 22:37; Mark 14:35; Luke 6:45; John 17:20; Rom. 12:16; 12:19; Eph. 4:3; 1 Cor. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Caitlyn Theisen</p>', '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:00:26', 0, 0, null, 'hYF88UrfH48', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hYF88UrfH48/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(443, 1, 'Be Invested in Your Relationship with God', '<p>In order for our relationship with our Lord to grow, it is important to nurture it. We reap what we sow. Where we spend our time produces the most growth, good or bad. We each have a gift that we have been given from God. The Body of Christ has many members and each is to use his unique gift to use for service to the Body.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:1; Rom. 12:3; 1 Cor. 12:4-14</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '51:56', 0, 0, null, 'YfpW3BDSa4E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YfpW3BDSa4E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(444, 1, 'STF National Conference - Praise and Worship', null, '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '33:09', 0, 0, null, 'VOcDI9cQPxU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VOcDI9cQPxU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not a teaching', 1, 0, null),
(445, 1, 'Locked in with the Lord', '<p>Jesus had an eternal perspective, meaning he kept his focus on God&rsquo;s purposes, not his own will. In our lives, it is our duty to be loving and to do God&rsquo;s will. We are to use Jesus as an example for how to live a godly life.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:43-48; Mark 14:32-36; Luke 22:49-53; 23:39: John 4-34; 8:23-28; Acts 16:25-34; 1 Cor. 15:56-58; 2 Cor. 4:12-18; Eph. 5:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2017-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '38:23', 0, 0, 'Salvation', 'JEy9vQj40Zo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JEy9vQj40Zo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(446, 1, 'Jesus (Isa) infiltrates Islam', '<p>This sharing reflects on the importance of opening our hearts to pray for Muslims. When Muslims convert to Christianity, often their lives become endangered and they must go underground for safety from those who would kill them. When we show tenderness to newly-converted Muslims, it continues our mission of building the Christian Church.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 16:7-16: Matt. 16:24-28</p> <p>Teacher: Janet Speakes</p>', '2017-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:13:51', 0, 0, null, 'USc7PPoS97g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/USc7PPoS97g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(447, 1, 'STF National Conference - Update on the Revised English Version (REV)', '<p>Recorded Live - An update the work being done on the RevisedEnglishVersion.com - Work on the Old Testament, Proverbs, ​and Psalms.</p>', '2017-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:03:08', 0, 0, null, 'XhMy80Sh68w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XhMy80Sh68w/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'this is news, not a teaching', 1, 0, null),
(448, 1, 'Working Together with God', '<p>God had a plan to reconcile with mankind so that He could have a family. Every person decides if he wants to enlist in that plan or not. We are encouraged to not waste this grace, but rather to discover our way of service. We are trained, equipped, and instructed in how to work effectively on God&rsquo;s &ldquo;team.&rdquo; We are responsible to stay ignited in our calling.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:3-8; 2 Cor. 5:17-21; Eph. 1:3-5, 11, 13-14; 6:1-4; Phil. 1:6; 2:1-5, 8-9, 12-16; 2 Tim. 1:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2017-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:00:35', 0, 0, 'purpose, ministry, labor, fruit, gifts', '7ZNUYz9w5Bk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7ZNUYz9w5Bk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(449, 1, 'Make The Best Use Of Your Time Because God Needs You', '<p>God has given each of us a limited amount of time in this life and what we do with our time affects all eternity. Every day we can make the decision to deny ourselves and instead do the good works God has prepared for us. He needs us to do what He has called us to do.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 9:23; 1 Cor. 13:5; Eph. 2:10; 1 Tim. 2:4; Heb. 10:24</p> <p>Teacher: Ryan Maher</p>', '2017-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:20', 0, 0, 'selfishness, sacrifice, kindness, compassion, love, habits, calling, service, redemption', 'X1GyGeXdwqA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X1GyGeXdwqA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(450, 1, 'It Is Not Good For Man To Be Alone', '<p>God never designed man to be alone. In the Scriptures, both God and Jesus provide for us not to be alone physically or spiritually. In contrast, the devil works constantly to create aloneness and to separate us from God and from each other. Christians need to ensure that God&rsquo;s design is working in the Body of Christ and that the devil&rsquo;s scheme is thwarted.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:18; 3:1-5; Job 1:6-11; Matt. 4:1-10; John 10:10; 13:34-35; 14:15-18, 25-26; 16:7, 13-14; Acts 2:41-47; Heb. 2:14; 10:24-25; Rev. 12:9-10; 21:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Truitt</p>', '2017-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '32:05', 0, 0, 'Adversary, fellowship, family, hope, loneliness, love, Satan, comforter, temptation, deceive, pleasure', 'TkqikhFx9-s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TkqikhFx9-s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(451, 1, 'Keys to Being at Peace', '<p>God and Jesus Christ want us to have complete peace in our lives. This peace is different from the kind of peace offered by the world. We are encouraged to put into practice the keys which allow us to have the unique peace only God and Jesus can give.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 23:5; Eccles. 1:18; John 10:10; Phil. 4:6-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-09-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:32', 0, 0, 'pure, joy, mind, prayer, supplication, thanksgiving, worldliness, worry, depression, petitions, heart', 'Kh6UXtJCnJA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Kh6UXtJCnJA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 77, null),
(452, 1, 'September 23, 2017 and The Great Sign', '<p>This is not a teaching, but rather a statement of STF&rsquo;s official position regarding September 23, 2017 and &ldquo;the great sign.&rdquo;</p>', '2017-08-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:51', 0, 0, 'eschatology', '_Tfj3bdyZG4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_Tfj3bdyZG4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(454, 1, 'Prepare to Win', '<p>To win at anything in life, we have to have the will to prepare to win. Jesus Christ qualified us to run the race, but we have to run it if we want to win. Winning means standing at the judgment seat and hearing &ldquo;well done.&rdquo;</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-07-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:13', 0, 0, 'discipline, endurance, perseverance', '_Pnubp0sUh4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_Pnubp0sUh4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(455, 1, 'Faith - What it is Not', '<p>Faith is not &ldquo;magical thinking.&rdquo; Faith and wisdom go hand in hand. Peter, Noah, and Abraham all received promises from God, and trusted in Him to fulfill them. Faith is having a promise, doing your best, and having confidence that God will make a way. If you start applying wisdom in what you do, you may see God help you be more effective in trusting him.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:7; Heb. 11:6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:28', 0, 0, 'believing', 'sAqirveTpvY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sAqirveTpvY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(456, 1, 'Complain To Someone Who Can Help', '<p>The Bible specifically directs us where to turn when we have complaints. Instead of complaining to everyone around us who cannot help, we should go to a source that can.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 142:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Franklin Smith</p>', '2017-06-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:23', 0, 0, 'supplication, distress', 'wI43bkBjWAI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wI43bkBjWAI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated at Franklin''s request', 1, 0, null),
(458, 1, 'Lessons on Dealing with A Giant', '<p>Everyone&rsquo;s life has &ldquo;giants.&rdquo; If we prepare for them, confront them, refuse to accept living with them, then, with God as our ally, our giants will fall. If we face the facts, then we can &ldquo;faith&rdquo; the facts.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-06-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:26', 0, 0, 'honesty', '31vJwcCXIdE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/31vJwcCXIdE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(459, 1, 'Is God Listening?', '<p>This is a personal message from God to His children. God tells us that He has a plan for us; He listens when we speak to Him and He promises that when we seek Him, we will find Him.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 9:11-13</p> <p>Teacher: Franklin Smith</p>', '2017-06-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:18', 0, 0, 'dependable, gracious, loving', 'HrNr7qmbFmk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HrNr7qmbFmk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated at Franklin''s request', 1, 0, null),
(460, 1, 'How to Be a Genuine Comforter', '<p>When a person is going through a horrific experience, we should not criticize, give advice, or offer platitudes. Instead, we should, figuratively speaking, walk alongside them, hold their hand, and offer a comforting presence.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-06-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:59', 0, 0, null, 'X2YlgnoT78M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X2YlgnoT78M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(461, 1, 'Three Sources of Adversity', '<p>Adversity is often due to life itself, foolish choices, or spiritual conflicts. Despite the source, persevere and do not grumble. Invite God into the battle so He can teach you, train you, and discipline you to become more like Him.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:28; 2:12-15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-05-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:37', 0, 0, null, 'b6WBoEWz2vE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b6WBoEWz2vE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(462, 1, 'Relationship Essentials', '<p>Solid relationships are built on two essential factors: truth and love. In order to have healthy relationships, we should all reject superficiality for candid truth and reject selfishness for sacrificial love.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-05-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:18', 0, 0, 'communication', '-X0ZLYrXMsA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-X0ZLYrXMsA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(463, 1, 'What exactly is Grace?', '<p>Everyone agrees that grace is &ldquo;undeserved favor&rdquo; from God. But beyond that there is quite a theological argument raging over what &ldquo;undeserved favor&rdquo; means. There are two main sides to the argument and depending on which side you choose, it affects not only your interpretation of Scripture, but your expectation of how God will work in your life.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 4:33; Rom 6:1, 23; 1 Pet. 5:5; James 4:6; Titus 2:11, 12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-05-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:45', 0, 0, 'predestination', 'jYb9PD6yTR0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jYb9PD6yTR0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(464, 1, 'The Importance of A Pure Heart', '<p>If we harden our hearts against God&rsquo;s requests, He is not inclined to respond to ours. God is looking for a people with pure hearts who genuinely &ldquo;try&rdquo; to love Him with all their heart, soul, mind and strength. The goal is not in being perfect, but in the trying to be our best.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 7:9; 6:19, 20; James 4:6; Prov. 15:8; 21:27; 28:9; Isa. 59:1-3; Ezek. 8:17, 18; Hosea 5:5, 6; Amos 5:21-24; Mic. 3:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-05-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:30', 0, 0, null, 'oEM1AZ6BAyc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oEM1AZ6BAyc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(465, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Be Angry at God', '<p>God is our total resource for living life well. Filling our minds and hearts with God&rsquo;s wisdom, which He says is supreme, helps us to make wise choices, to overcome the power of Satan in the world and to recognize that life is not a &ldquo;free lunch.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 19:3; 4:7; Deut. 30:19; 1 John 5:19; Gen. 3:17, 19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-04-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:16', 0, 0, 'blame', 'Q0dAq9p-vNc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Q0dAq9p-vNc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(466, 1, 'Keep Up the Fight', '<p>Evil never admits it is wrong. Satan said that once Job lost everything, he would curse God to His face. In spite of the calamities in Job&rsquo;s life, he never cursed God. We can never stop fighting evil or stop speaking the truth. One way we fight evil is by &ldquo;being kind to everyone, able to teach, patiently enduring evil&rdquo; so that others may come from darkness to light.</p> <p>Verses: Job 1-2; John 8:44; Matt. 28:2-4, 11-13; 2 Tim. 2:25-26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-03-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:41', 0, 0, 'wrestle, ambassador', 'VlL6-AWVWVU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VlL6-AWVWVU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(467, 1, 'See Me, See Jesus', '<p>In real life we fall short of being imitators of Christ, but by humbly admitting our mistakes, we move forward toward the goal of being like him, to the end that when someone sees us, they see Jesus.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-03-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:09', 0, 0, 'ambassador', 'zi8j1AHpIg8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zi8j1AHpIg8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(468, 1, 'Who&rsquo;s Ruling on the Throne of Your Heart?', '<p>Our heart is like the throne room of our life. We should pay attention to whom we allow to sit on that throne as we are living our lives and loving God with all of our heart, soul and might.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4-9; Prov. 6:20-23</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-03-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:44', 0, 0, 'lordship, love, commandments', 'jR4qXMfCPTg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jR4qXMfCPTg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(469, 1, 'Three Consequences of Sin', '<p>If we understand the consequences of sin, we can become energized to live out our convictions for Jesus Christ. Three main consequences of sin are: 1) it messes up your life, 2) you lose future rewards in the Messianic Kingdom, and 3) you invite possible demonic oppression. Understanding these consequences helps us to live righteously before God.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:31, 32; 13:21; 17:11; 1 Cor. 3:14, 15; 2 John 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-03-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:54', 0, 0, 'choices, behavior, obedience', 'FwH2ofAQw3c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FwH2ofAQw3c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(470, 1, 'Two Doorways Into Your Heart', '<p>We guard our hearts by paying attention to what we are looking at and what we are listening to. Allowing Godly information into the midst of our hearts will be life and heath to our whole body.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:1-5; 4:20-23; 1 Cor. 15:33</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-02-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:26', 0, 0, 'character, thoughts, actions', 'JyhdUPIzPm0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JyhdUPIzPm0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(471, 1, 'Kindness - Being Kind to Others', '<p>We are instructed repeatedly in Scripture to be kind. It is a fruit of the spirit. However, our sin nature often pulls us in the wrong direction. We have to continually be mindful of being kind even when the world around us is unkind.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:35; Rom. 7:14-15; Gal. 5:22-23; Col. 3:12; 2 Tim 3:1-4; 1 Cor. 15:33</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:41', 0, 0, 'love, godliness, lovingkindness', 'QdAJ-tMBLz4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QdAJ-tMBLz4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(472, 1, 'Hearts of Flesh', '<p>When we are having struggles with our character, we are having a &ldquo;heart problem.&rdquo; Being born again we have a new heart but the old stony one still nags us. This teaching addresses how we are affected by this.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 11:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:58', 0, 0, 'spirit, disobedience', 'nS2O7v8b3Kg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nS2O7v8b3Kg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(473, 1, 'Are You Really Saved?', '<p>To be saved requires more than believing that Jesus was an actual historical figure. We must make a personal commitment that he is our Lord, and believe that God raised him out from among the dead.</p> <p>Verses: John 9:35-38; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-02-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:12', 0, 0, 'confession, salvation, Messiah, resurrection, lordship', 'mmwrJmfTWmo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mmwrJmfTWmo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(474, 1, 'The Prophetic Perfect Idiom', '<p>This figure of speech explains why some future events in the Bible are described in the past tense. This idiom expresses a promise that the event will absolutely happen in the future.</p> <p>Verses: many examples</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-01-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:25', 0, 0, 'interpretation, translation', 'SrPOV0EB8Oc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SrPOV0EB8Oc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(475, 1, 'What is the Figure of Speech &lsquo;Personification&rsquo;?', '<p>When Scripture gives human characteristics to inanimate objects, that is a figure of speech called &ldquo;Personification.&rdquo; This figure helps simplify complex ideas, abstract concepts, human emotion, and poetic interpretation in Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: many examples</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-01-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:30', 0, 0, 'interpretation, translation', 'xhz2AvqfWXQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xhz2AvqfWXQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(476, 1, 'How to make Teachings that Stick', '<p>The Bible uses many stories and parables to communicate truth. Our presentations can be improved to have a greater impact by using stories. A story should be credible, informative, and passionate.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 12:1-15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-01-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:46', 0, 0, 'parable, sharing', 'JgHTy_IDyn4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JgHTy_IDyn4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(477, 1, 'When the Going Gets Tough', '<p>In this teaching from XXXX. Life is tough, but in this teaching John Schoenheit talks about how we can do well in difficult times.</p>', '2016-12-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:07', 0, 0, null, '2tw7Ic3milE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2tw7Ic3milE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Duplicate', 1, 0, null),
(478, 1, 'Do A Good Turn', '<p>In this sharing on how we can be better ambassadors for the Lord Jesus Christ, a Boy Scouts illustration provides an example of going above and beyond what is expected of us in our normal responsibilities of daily life. Jesus said, &ldquo;And just as you want people to do to you, do the same to them.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Luke 6:31</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-12-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:05', 0, 0, 'Humility, Service', '1xFnCuNHxGY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1xFnCuNHxGY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(479, 1, 'Boxes we Build', '<p>As truth seekers we want to grow spiritually. Don&rsquo;t let mental &ldquo;boxes&rdquo; hinder you from seeing the greatness of what God is doing in your life. In this teaching, examples of different kinds of boxes illustrate key principles for spiritual growth.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-12-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:27', 0, 0, null, 'rFqhL34rAH0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rFqhL34rAH0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(480, 1, 'Beams and Motes', '<p>Employing an illustration about working with wood, this teaching talks about Matthew 7:3-5, that we should first remove the beam out of our own eye before helping others with the speck in their eye.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-12-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:21', 0, 0, 'holy, pearls', 'QYJjuXsASNY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QYJjuXsASNY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(481, 1, '7 Tips on How to Become a Better Teacher', '<p>Develop your teaching skills with these guidelines. Tips on timing, emphasis, presentation, and much more will help you bring God&rsquo;s heart and God&rsquo;s message to people so that your listeners can be inspired and learn to be more like Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:2; Col. 4:2; 1 Tim. 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '28:56', 0, 0, 'overseer', 'QGEAc8LrQbI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QGEAc8LrQbI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(482, 1, 'Keys to Understanding Proverbs', '<p>Many of the Proverbs have more than one meaning, and many words in a Proverb have more than one meaning, which makes understanding this book both challenging and fun. This teaching focuses on Proverbs 1:31, which has a double meaning. As we get to know and understand Proverbs, we better know and understand God.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:6, 31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-12-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:35', 0, 0, 'amphibologia, wisdom, judgment, wise', 'cmaqnRc-Guk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cmaqnRc-Guk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(483, 1, 'Be Prepared', '<p>As the Boy Scout motto indicates, preparation is a huge key to successful living. This teaching shares insight from the Bible about ways we need to prepare and how preparation applies to our lives both mentally and spiritually.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:7; Luke 3:4; 1 Pet. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-11-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:14', 0, 0, 'wisdom, holy, hope', 'PvfZUEVfYYE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PvfZUEVfYYE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(484, 1, 'The Fear of God', '<p>Why do we have awe and respect for God? It is because we love Him, but also because He is God and He is very powerful. This teaching talks about the difference between healthy and unhealthy fear. We should have a fear of God that motivates us to live in a way that is pleasing to Him.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:7; 9:10; 2 Cor. 5:10; Eph. 2:10; 1 John 1:9; Rev. 20:11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-11-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:22', 0, 0, 'honor, judgment, knowledge', '408xM-wHJoE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/408xM-wHJoE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(485, 1, 'Citizens of Heaven', '<p>God tells us that our true citizenship is in heaven. We should not let anything divide us in the Body of Christ; rather we should let the world see that we are His followers by how we love one another even when we differ on politics.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-11-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:54', 0, 0, null, 'kb6xIKwgLe0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kb6xIKwgLe0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(486, 1, 'Life&rsquo;s Final Exam', '<p>Life is full of tests in schools, professions, trades, and more. Are you prepared for life&rsquo;s final exam? The judgment seat of Christ is not going to be a multiple choice quiz. This teaching will help you learn how to be prepared for life&rsquo;s final exam.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9, 10; 2 Cor. 5:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-11-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:24', 0, 0, null, 'Vh5GqIij_AM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vh5GqIij_AM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(487, 1, 'Forged in Fire', '<p>This teaching discusses the process of shaping metals by forging them into knives, hammers, horseshoes, shovels, and more. How does this apply to our spiritual life and the development of our character? In God&rsquo;s workshop we can become tools useful for His praise and glory.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:03', 0, 0, 'prepare, guarantee', 'OLysgUDuyUY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OLysgUDuyUY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(488, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Obscenity?', '<p>This teaching discusses the Greek word translated &ldquo;obscenity&rdquo; in the REV. As Christians, we are not to use it. The teaching goes on to illustrate why doing so aligns ourselves with Satan. In contrast, we are encouraged to do things that wage war against our sin nature and to let Jesus Christ be our model.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:2; Eph. 5:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-10-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:52', 0, 0, 'vulgarity, swearing, cussing, cursing, profanity, obedience, discipline, repentance, humility, self-control, worldliness, ungodliness, strength', 'hMnmNLW2ES4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hMnmNLW2ES4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(489, 1, 'Flying Beneath the Worlds Radar', '<p>As the world becomes less and less accepting of Christian values and practices, it is becoming more important for us to fly beneath the world&rsquo;s radar. The teaching discusses three tactics in particular that help Christians do this. These will protect us and make us more effective in society.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 17:19; 22:16; 28:12; Luke 18:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-10-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:38', 0, 0, 'prayer, revelation', 'LYLuNOb_2ZM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LYLuNOb_2ZM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(490, 1, 'The Gospel can cause Offense', '<p>There is significant social pressure to be tolerant and to not be offensive to anyone. The very nature of the Gospel is going to cause offense to many. Jesus called himself a stumbling stone. We are encouraged to overcome any fear of sharing the Gospel with others and to not worry that they may be offended.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:16; 1 Pet. 2:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-10-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:52', 0, 0, 'conflict, acceptance', 'Nb7kvYCZeUs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Nb7kvYCZeUs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(491, 1, 'Life is Short - Make Plans', '<p>We have a limited amount of time to live our lives. Without planning, it is as though our lives are stolen from us. There is a proper way to live and we are not rewarded unless we conduct our lives in a godly way, making the best use of our time. We must plan deliberately and stick to our plans.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 8:6-8; Matt. 2:19; Eph. 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:40', 0, 0, 'discipline, redeem', 'pdKd6ZDVrdE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pdKd6ZDVrdE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(492, 1, 'Who is the Bride of Christ?', '<p>In this teaching, the Bride of Christ is explained. Answers are given as to why God would portray the Bride as He does, and why there is so much confusion about her identity. Four specific figures of speech are discussed, with the view to understanding what meaning is being revealed in the biblical text.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 1:3; Prov. 8:1; Isa. 55:12; Joel 1:10; Matt. 7:6; John 15:5; 2 Cor. 11:2; Eph. 5:25-27; Rev. 21:2, 9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:54', 0, 0, 'metaphor, personification, Israel, covenant', '9llawESTlSg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9llawESTlSg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(493, 1, 'What Is the Wise Thing to Do?', '<p>Sometimes you may ask, &ldquo;What do I feel like doing?&rdquo; The better question is, &ldquo;What is the wise thing to do?&rdquo; Everything you do has consequences. It is wise to think of your life&rsquo;s journey with long-term vision. If you start asking yourself the better question, you will receive many benefits.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 94:8; Prov. 4:7; 9:12; 14:8, 16; Heb. 11:24-26; James 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:08', 0, 0, 'foolishness, rewards, Hope, discipline', 'YLz-FYthMVk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YLz-FYthMVk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(494, 1, 'Thriving Behind Enemy Lines', '<p>Although as Christians our citizenship is in heaven, we live in a world which is under the power of Satan. The spiritual battle is all around us. This teaching describes three strategies we can employ to not only help us survive, but also to thrive behind &ldquo;enemy lines.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Luke 6:28; John 10:10, 16; Eph. 6:12; Phil. 3:20; Heb. 10:25; 1 Pet. 1:13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-08-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:43', 0, 0, 'control, Devil/Slanderer, worldliness, Adversary, division, fear, sober-minded, alert, love', 'lsLwNWOirPE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lsLwNWOirPE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(495, 1, 'Living Behind Enemy Lines', '<p>Satan is the god of this present world and is in control of its systems, creating a spiritual battle always around us. Once a person receives salvation through Jesus Christ, his citizenship changes and he becomes a citizen of heaven, but is still in that battle. Christians are to look for their Savior coming from heaven and to not be entangled or discouraged living &ldquo;behind enemy lines.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 4:4; Phil. 3:20; Heb. 11:10, 13; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-08-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:50', 0, 0, 'blinded', '5dwbTo8h4TI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5dwbTo8h4TI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(496, 1, 'What is the Purpose of Christian Meetings?', '<p>The purpose of Christian meetings is to promote Christian fellowship. Teachings, which are different from fellowship, should produce like-mindedness. It is important to understand the definition of &ldquo;fellowship&rdquo; to determine if it is happening in Christian meetings. In order for us to grow as Christians, we need to be in a venue where what is shared produces like-mindedness which makes possible true fellowship.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:25; 1 John 1:1, 3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-08-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:27', 0, 0, 'growth, exhort, encourage, maturity, trust', 'lZHfkRRb2zc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lZHfkRRb2zc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(497, 1, 'Let My People Go', '<p>God told Moses to tell Pharaoh, &ldquo;Let my people go.&rdquo; God wanted His enslaved people to be free. Because the whole world lies in the power of Satan, people continue to be enslaved. God&rsquo;s heart has not changed. He wants His people to be free. This teaching gives keys to living in His freedom.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 9:1; Luke 4:18; Rom. 10:9-10; 2 Cor. 4:4; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-08-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:33', 0, 0, 'Adversary, oppressed', 'aquzdz0OkZg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aquzdz0OkZg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(498, 1, 'What Does It Mean To Be A Christian?', '<p>A Christian is one who is born of flesh from their earthly parents and born a second time of holy spirit. The second birth is your choice by deciding to make Jesus your Lord and to believe God raised him from the dead. This second birth imparts God&rsquo;s nature into you and it is permanent. You can&rsquo;t lose it, just as you can&rsquo;t be unborn from your earthly parents.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9-10; 1 Pet. 1:3,23; Titus 2:5; James 1:18; Col. 3:10; 2 Pet. 1:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-07-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '17:07', 0, 0, 'saved, Sealed, Saint', 'JMsVYUEHQ_U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JMsVYUEHQ_U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(499, 1, 'Love Your Neighbor As Yourself', '<p>God has called us to a high standard. Though the world around us may grow cold, God&rsquo;s great second commandment admonishes us to &ldquo;give out&rdquo; love anyway. As we love ourselves, let us also love others regardless of their behavior.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:19; 24:12; Eph. 5:25-29; 2 Tim. 3:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:22', 0, 0, 'obey, selfless', 'mBWNEmViNi4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mBWNEmViNi4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(500, 1, 'Should We Be Authentic?', '<p>People wonder &ldquo;Should I be authentic in my communications?&rdquo; Is it important for others to know how I really feel? Not always! God&rsquo;s word tells us to love our neighbor as ourselves. We are taught to use no corrupt talk, only such as is good for edifying others, speaking with grace, our words seasoned with salt. We are not to be selfish or self-centered.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:29; Col. 4:6; Matt. 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-07-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:03', 0, 0, 'honesty', '_S4UBMv5-84', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_S4UBMv5-84/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(501, 1, 'Be Kind to One Another', '<p>Sometimes we speak to others out of selfishness, not first considering how our words will affect them. In contrast, God wants us to consider how our words will impact others before we speak them. This is part of walking in love, which results in peaceful relations between people.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:2-3; Rom. 14:1-10, 13, 19; James 1:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:46', 0, 0, 'Disputes, Contempt, Stumbling', 'GM5jWfViR78', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GM5jWfViR78/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(502, 1, 'The Sin That Entangles', '<p>One way to think about how we can become entangled in sin is to think about the thorns of a berry bush. If we are not careful, our sleeve will get caught on the thorns. Jesus has provided a way to God that is free of the entanglement of sin. But if we step off the path of following him, we will get caught by the thorns of sin and entangled in them like in the berry bush.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-07-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:45', 0, 0, null, 'nGIVVYPvhG8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nGIVVYPvhG8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(504, 1, 'The Power of Stories', '<p>Stories help us learn. The Bible is full of stories telling us about how to live; for example, how to be brave, courageous, and faithful. Stories bind us together as the people of God, and we also all tell ourselves stories about how we perceive the world around us. However, those stories may be true or false. Stories that are unbiasedly accurate are a reflection of a pure heart.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 51:10; Matt. 5:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-06-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:38', 0, 0, null, 'j7Wz8su5wxE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/j7Wz8su5wxE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(505, 1, 'Decisions Have Consequences', '<p>When we make a choice there are consequences, and even if we don&rsquo;t choose, that is still a decision that comes with consequences. In the Bible, God continually tells us to make the right choice. This is vividly portrayed with the metaphor of sowing and reaping in Scripture. We need to be mindful of what we are sowing (i.e., choosing) in our life if we want to reap good things from God.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-06-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:03', 0, 0, null, 'ZX5dl235ep4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZX5dl235ep4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(506, 1, 'Making Difficult Decisions', '<p>In everyone&rsquo;s life comes times with difficult decisions. Rather than deciding casually or impulsively, better to count the cost of each option, get advice from wise friends, and after making the decision, take action and don&rsquo;t second guess your decision.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 9:57-61; 19:28-29; Prov. 15:22; Eccles. 11:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-05-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:30', 0, 0, 'Emotions, Success, Wisdom', 'WIzL5V30p1o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WIzL5V30p1o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(507, 1, 'God''s Love and the Lake of Fire', '<p>God shows his love toward us by not controlling us, but, through our free will, gives us the choice of blessings or curses, life or death. His will is that everyone be saved and come to the knowledge of the truth, but He is not going to force that on us. It is our decision.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; Rom.6:23; Rev. 20:11-15; Deut. 30:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-04-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:59', 0, 0, 'judgment', 'F4m0weTqgOQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F4m0weTqgOQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(508, 1, 'God''s Divine Council (Part 4)', '<p>The teacher emphasizes that God is the &ldquo;Most High,&rdquo; the creator, the originator, lover, source of power and life AND the last word. Yet God enlists the help of His created beings (His Divine Council) to assist in the affairs of His creation. The concept of serving, loving and magnifying God is still the goal of the church today.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 14:13, 14; 6:8; Job 1:6; Ps. 89:7; 1 Kings 22:19; Gen. 1:26; 3:22; 11:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:17', 30, 4, 'helpers, glorify, magnify', 'G4dbeUCZvZo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/G4dbeUCZvZo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(509, 1, 'God''s Divine Council (Part 3)', '<p>The 24 elders of the heavenly inner council of God work in unity with &ldquo;the Most High&rdquo; to administer His creation. This council of heavenly beings, called &ldquo;watchers&rdquo;, testify as to how they assisted God in His decrees against King Nebuchadnezzar and will assist against the antichrist in the final days of the Tribulation.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 4:13, 17, 24; 7:9, 10, 25-26; Rev. 4:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:27', 30, 3, 'decrees, authority', 'CuEicEhwm3A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CuEicEhwm3A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(510, 1, 'God''s Divine Council (Part 2)', '<p>Scripture reveals that God created order in the spiritual realm as well as the physical. Clearly, there are different ranks of spiritual authority in the heavenlies that help administer God&rsquo;s creation. It is powerful to know that among these created beings, God has His own inner council.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:21; 3:14; 1 Cor. 12:17; Rev. 4:6; Zech. 5:9; Isa. 34:14; Jude 1:9; Ps. 89:5-7; Job 1:6; 15:8; 2 Cor. 5:17; Jer. 23:16-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:22', 30, 2, 'angels', 'ECE6tDSw85o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ECE6tDSw85o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(511, 1, 'God''s Divine Council (Part 1)', '<p>From the beginning, God has had a pattern of organizing positions of authority, both human and spiritual, within His creation. He never wanted to rule as a tyrant, and through His divine loving nature, He expressed His love by trusting and giving authority to His creation. We see this pattern exhibited from Genesis to Revelation.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:15; 1:28; Deut. 16:18; Eph. 1:22; 4:11; 6:12; Matt. 28:18; 19:28; Rev. 3:4; 2 Cor. 10:8; Isa. 1:26; Jer. 23:4; Mal. 3:6; Ps. 7:17; Heb. 7:1; Col. 1:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '17:10', 30, 1, 'order, leadership', 'kmeVKcRrGLw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kmeVKcRrGLw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 58, null),
(512, 1, 'A Mountaintop Experience', '<p>Mountains were often the places of sacred events in the Bible. Scripture teaches that if we want to dwell on God&rsquo;s mountain, we are to walk blamelessly, do that which is right, speak truth, be full of mercy and kindness to others, and honor God.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 15; Rev. 21:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-04-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:27', 0, 0, 'awe, symbolism, majesty', 'ACxAPBsDyTg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ACxAPBsDyTg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(513, 1, 'Love is Not Approval', '<p>Love and approval are not equal. Approval may feel good, but it may not line up with God&rsquo;s will. Love may involve Godly reproof which can sting in the moment, but ultimately brings out our best.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:21; Luke 17:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:37', 0, 0, 'obedience', '4shdUoNDZpA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4shdUoNDZpA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(514, 1, 'Weather and Godliness', '<p>Scripture makes it clear that the earth is a war zone between God and the devil. People play a significant role in this struggle. If the people of earth obey God&rsquo;s commands, they are blessed. If they choose to live in the ways of the world, they are cursed. Weather is a measure of people&rsquo;s relationship to God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 5:19; Exod. 15:3; Deut. 28:1-12, 15-23; 11:13, 14, 16; Lev. 18:24; Ps. 107:33, 34; Jer. 3:24; 12:4; 23:19; Amos 4:6-7, 9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-12-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:14', 0, 0, 'alertness, signs', 'lsQ_yB4mzgY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lsQ_yB4mzgY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(515, 1, 'Preparing for the Times Ahead', '<p>Jesus told his disciples to be prepared for the unexpected curves in life. Scripture reiterates this truth many times and it is still true for us today. We too must be prepared for sudden disasters and be prepared to witness to people.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Pet. 3:15; Luke 22:35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-12-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:19', 0, 0, null, 'JbafKAZjvpc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JbafKAZjvpc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(516, 1, 'Keeping Your Boat Afloat', '<p>This teaching is about keeping your spiritual boat afloat. By being alert to the thoughts and patterns of the world, to sin and wicked temptations, and by casting the weights in your life onto the Lord, you will stay afloat.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-11-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:04', 0, 0, 'transformation, discipline, renewed', 'of7O-GcTVYY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/of7O-GcTVYY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(517, 1, 'That''s Ironic', '<p>Irony is the incongruity between an actual result of a situation and the expected result. Throughout Scripture, we see that God uses irony to get our attention and to show us how He is constantly working in life&rsquo;s issues.</p> <p>Verses: Refers to Joseph, Esther, Ruth, King David, Jesus, Pilate, etc.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:06', 0, 0, null, 'owUCze4alT4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/owUCze4alT4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(518, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Live on Autopilot', '<p>Not thinking about what you are doing is like being on autopilot and can lead to vacuous living. It is better to be consciously thinking about what you are doing and your surroundings so that should God inspire you to say or do something, you are tuned in to Him.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:26; 14:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:21', 0, 0, 'Understanding', 'O2NNraJ-1r8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/O2NNraJ-1r8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(519, 1, 'Get paired to God', '<p>Just as our cell phone can be paired to external speakers, so should we be paired with God to receive and respond to His input. This short message encourages us to be tuned in to God daily.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-08-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:16', 0, 0, null, 'dLPJmywj7rs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dLPJmywj7rs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(520, 1, 'Three Guys Named Joe', '<p>Joseph, son of Jacob, Joseph, husband of Mary, and Joseph, a Sanhedrin leader, lived at different times and in different circumstances. However, when confronted with tough decisions, they all made Godly decisions that blessed their worlds. They are models for us today to act, speak, and obey God&rsquo;s word when making difficult life decisions.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 37-50; Matt. 1:19; Mark 15:43</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2015-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:26', 0, 0, null, '3FUvX09GNuY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3FUvX09GNuY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(521, 1, 'Who do you say that I am?', '<p>During Christ&rsquo;s ministry, many wanted to know who he was and where he got the power and authority to do and say what he did. This video covers the responses to this question from the ruling Jews, the common people, and his disciples. It is the question everyone must answer eventually.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:13-16; 21:9, 10; Luke 22:70</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-08-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:40', 0, 0, 'Sanhedrin', 'T0ghdW94x0M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T0ghdW94x0M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(523, 1, 'Why Bother to Know the Truth?', '<p>Jesus said that if you believe his words, then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free. When Jesus spoke, his words often opposed peoples&rsquo; common thinking of what was truth. Freedom comes from believing truth. Captivity comes from believing error. What you believe determines your thoughts and actions.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:31-36; Rom. 10:17; 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: Franklin Smith</p>', '2015-05-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, 'Disciple, Righteousness', 'WoT7i4_Dj_A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WoT7i4_Dj_A/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated at Franklin''s request', 1, 0, null),
(524, 1, 'The Ministry of Reconciliation', '<p>Whether we want it or not, the ministry of reconciliation is the gift that God has given to all Christians. Witnessing our Christian faith to other people is a skill that can be learned and developed. This teaching presents several strategies for engaging others about where they will spend eternity.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:17-20; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Franklin Smith</p>', '2015-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 0, 0, 'Saved, Confess, Believe', 'rN4xw4cDxXI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rN4xw4cDxXI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated at Franklin''s request', 1, 0, null),
(525, 1, 'The Death and Resurrection of Jesus Christ (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching details and chronicles the events from Jesus&rsquo; burial through the several visits to the tomb by Mary (the mother of James and Joses) and Mary Magdalene, ending with their encounter with two angels who announce that Jesus has arisen. A concluding summary of the entire week of Jesus&rsquo; death is given at the end of this session.</p> <p>Verses: Matt 28:1; John 20:1; Luke 24:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:58', 0, 0, 'Passover, Feast', 'f5j_ZDwJSwE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f5j_ZDwJSwE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(526, 1, 'The Death and Resurrection of Jesus Christ (Part 3)', '<p>This teaching details and chronicles the events from Jesus&rsquo; death to his resurrection, including the days of the week the events occurred. It clarifies that there were two Sabbath days in that time frame, which when not understood has added considerable confusion to sorting the events of this time period. It also solidifies that Jesus was in the tomb for three days and three nights.</p> <p>Verses: John 19:31; Lev. 23:5, 6; Luke 23:50-54; Matt. 27:62-66; 28:1; Mark 16:1; Luke 23:56</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:05', 0, 0, 'Passover, Feast', 'D5l2xxxWmJA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/D5l2xxxWmJA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(527, 1, 'The Death and Resurrection of Jesus Christ (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching details and chronicles the events from Jesus&rsquo; trials before the Sanhedrin and before Pilate and Herod through his torture and crucifixion. It clarifies the sequence, day, and time of the events.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 22:70, 71; 23:1-13; John 19:14; Mark 15:15-37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:01', 0, 0, 'Passover', 'WCK7R3vg1Vw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WCK7R3vg1Vw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(528, 1, 'The Death and Resurrection of Jesus Christ (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching sets forth the events that immediately precede Christ&rsquo;s crucifixion and resurrection. Using the full scope of the four Gospels, a remarkable detailing of those events is presented.</p> <p>Verses: John 19:31; 20:1; 18:12, 13, 24; Matt. 12:39, 40; Luke 23:52-54; 22:66</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p><a href="https://truthortradition.com/pdf/last_supper_to_resurrection.pdf" target="_blank">PDF Chart</a></p>', '2015-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:03', 0, 0, 'accuracy', 'YFf5HgJq5wY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YFf5HgJq5wY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 29, null),
(529, 1, 'Numbing Out or Fully Engaged?', '<p>Life has its seasons of joy and pain. Joy we embrace, but pain may produce avoidance. If we choose to fully engage with God, He will provide the security to face unpleasant challenges. So do not hide or make sinful choices, but rather be vulnerable as you engage in life.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 3:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:43', 0, 0, null, '1f8XhbuLcpY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1f8XhbuLcpY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(530, 1, 'Are You a Skunk or a Rose?', '<p>God sometimes associates good and evil with smell in Scripture. Wicked behavior produces a foul stink or smell of death, while generous acts of good produce a sweet-smelling fragrance to God. What are you producing?</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 38:5; Eccles. 10:1; Gen. 8:21; Exod. 29:18; 2 Cor. 2:14; Phil. 4:18; Eph. 5:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:33', 0, 0, null, 'ItrrUyOqxbA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ItrrUyOqxbA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(531, 1, 'Getting Rid of the Wicked', '<p>Proverbs teaches about the importance of leadership eliminating the wicked from righteous organizations. Evil must be removed to receive blessings and success. God&rsquo;s Word insists on diligent action to remove stubborn and evil people. There is no easy way to do something hard, but it still must be done.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 28:28; 20:26; 22:10; 10:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:53', 0, 0, null, 'DqiwqCXm8Tc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DqiwqCXm8Tc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(532, 1, 'Practice the presence of God', '<p>This reflection encourages us to not drift through our daily lives on &ldquo;auto-pilot,&rdquo; but rather to engage with people in every situation in order to practice the guidance of God for the benefit of learning, or for service to others.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-01-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:48', 0, 0, null, 'h2P0hh6YVUw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/h2P0hh6YVUw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(533, 1, 'The Calling of the Disciples of Jesus', '<p>By examining the calling of Jesus&rsquo; disciples, we learn some amazing truths about culture, history, timing, and experience. Brotherhood, friendship, and experience play leading roles in determining how the disciples built total trust in and commitment to Jesus&rsquo; imperative call to &ldquo;Follow Me!&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: John 1:35-51; 2:1, 2; Matt. 4:18; Mark 1:16; Luke 5:10; 21:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-01-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:40', 0, 0, 'friendship', 'I8wJWIL5jYE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I8wJWIL5jYE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(534, 1, 'Our Thoughts - The Key to Self-Control', '<p>There is a war going on between the flesh and the spirit. The environment of the world is not going to change, but we can choose to change our thoughts and actions. Self-control requires us to mentally stay away from the temptations of our sin nature and vigilantly focus our minds on healthy, uplifting thoughts.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:16, 17, 19-21; Phil. 4:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-12-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:41', 0, 0, 'renewed', 'fGt6IYRr7UI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fGt6IYRr7UI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(535, 1, 'Plug into the Ultimate Source of Power', '<p>In order to be recharged and alert to spiritual matters, we need to plug into God. This brief reflection offers 3 pathways to a fruitful walk with God: through the written Word, developing a personal relationship with Jesus Christ, and through the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-12-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:45', 0, 0, null, 'fTiDTn1Iv74', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fTiDTn1Iv74/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(536, 1, 'Trust Like a Mustard Seed', '<p>The mustard seed parable in Scripture symbolically illustrates great trust in God. As humans, we limit ourselves by looking at worldly circumstances. In contrast, with Biblical focus, we obey God, pray, act on His promises, and therefore build up great faith to fulfill the purpose He has for our lives. The mustard seed parable targets faith, not circumstances.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:31; 17:14-20; Luke 17:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-12-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:47', 0, 0, 'believe', 'w1ch4GbqYJs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/w1ch4GbqYJs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(537, 1, 'How to use the STF Mobile App', '<p>This video is a comprehensive overview of how to download and use the <a href="http://STFonline.org/">STFonline.org</a> app for tapping into the multiple teaching tools of the ministry. Blogs, seminars, podcasts, The Sower, the REV and Commentary and more are available on this app.</p>', '2014-11-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:52', 0, 0, null, 'XPmS27V3Sfc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XPmS27V3Sfc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(538, 1, 'The Last Trumpet', '<p>Verses in 1 Corinthians 15 clearly express some attributes of the Rapture of the Christian Church, but the phrase &ldquo;at the last trumpet&rdquo; can be more difficult to grasp. This teaching illustrates that the Corinthian culture was immersed in athletics and explains why God communicated truth to the Corinthians in terms they could understand. It is then we see what that phrase signifies.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:2; Rom. 10:9; 1 Cor. 4:9; 9:24-26; 7:18; 15:51-52; 1 Thess. 4:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:26', 0, 0, 'tribulation, secret, mystery, incorruptible', 'hnEJJAcGUnc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hnEJJAcGUnc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 40, null),
(539, 1, '7 Reasons Why We Believe in a Rapture before the Great Tribulation', '<p>This teaching lists seven reasons to believe the Rapture occurs before the Great Tribulation begins. Specific scripture references for each reason are given and explained in greater context.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 26:14; Isa. 13:9, 11-13; 61:2; Jer. 30:7; Dan. 9:24-26; Matt. 23:35; 24:30; 1 Cor. 15:51-52; Gal. 3:28; 1 Thess. 4:15-17; 2 Thess. 2:1-3.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:25', 0, 0, 'judgment, wrath, resurrection, secret, mystery, gathering, rebellion, lawlessness', 'Ii-iqapb2zs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ii-iqapb2zs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 47, null),
(540, 1, 'Was Jesus teaching about The Rapture in Matthew 24?', '<p>This teaching answers the question of whether Jesus was referring to the Rapture in Matthew 24. The answer lies in understanding the uniqueness of the Christian church, the context of what Jesus said in Matthew 24, the audience to whom Jesus was speaking, and various prophecies to Israel.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 37:12-14; Matt. 24:30-31, 37-41; 25:31-34, 41, 46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:50', 0, 0, 'resurrection', 'H5_Xj2KhFQ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H5_Xj2KhFQ0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 51, null),
(541, 1, 'Where did the word Rapture come from?', '<p>Some Christians do not believe in the Rapture because they say it is not found in the Bible. Others believe in it but will not call it the Rapture. The teacher demonstrates where the word &ldquo;rapture&rdquo; comes from and how the event is clearly described and is truly unique to Christians.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 4:15-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-09-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:01', 0, 0, 'trumpet', 'T-5bT7W9o6A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T-5bT7W9o6A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(542, 1, 'Why do some people not believe in The Rapture?', '<p>The Bible clearly talks about an event unique to Christians called &ldquo;the Rapture.&rdquo; There are two primary reasons many Christians do not believe in it. One has to do with it not being mentioned in the Old Testament or by Jesus. Another is related to the Apostle Paul. This teaching addresses both.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 21:20; 1 Thess. 4:15-17; 2 Tim. 1:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-09-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 0, 0, 'orthodoxy, trumpet', 'GLo1ngo9sSE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GLo1ngo9sSE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(543, 1, 'Why did Jesus move to Capernaum?', '<p>Using information from Scripture, the culture of the time, history, and archaeology, several reasons are identified as to why Jesus would move to Capernaum from his hometown Nazareth. Embedded in his choice is a lesson for all Christians.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 8:5-9; Mark 2:14; Luke 4:28-31; John 2:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-09-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:03', 0, 0, 'witnessing, Galilee', '3NaOUlRPz2Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3NaOUlRPz2Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(544, 1, 'World Love or the Love of God?', '<p>There are two ways to love: with worldly love or with the love of God. This teaching defines what motivates each and compares a number of characteristics of each, thus enabling a person to identify which way he is loving.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-07-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:55', 0, 0, 'commitment, forgiveness, endurance', 'QBVVGlVxeKU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QBVVGlVxeKU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(545, 1, 'Old Covenant or New?', '<p>This sharing gives a general description of the basic differences between the Old and New Covenants and challenges the audience to determine under which Covenant they are conducting their lives.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-07-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:21', 0, 0, 'Israel, resurrection, persecution', '5p1cT1LwW3A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5p1cT1LwW3A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(546, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Examples from events (Part 7)', '<p>Historical events, such as the Old Testament feasts, are foreshadows of the coming times concerning the Messiah&rsquo;s life, death, and resurrection, the gift of holy spirit, and the Messiah&rsquo;s return. God uses these events originally in context of the Old Testament, but they also point to future events concerning the savior of the world, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 2:16, 17; Heb. 4:4-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:52', 0, 0, 'Passover, Pentecost, Fruits, Trumpets, Atonement, Booths', '2mLmGw9Uyxo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2mLmGw9Uyxo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(547, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Examples from Things (Part 6)', '<p>Physical objects like bread, stones, components of the Tabernacle, and even colors have significant meaning when used in the Old Testament and then show up again in the New Testament. All these are used to draw attention to the importance of seemingly insignificant details in the original usage.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 78:23; John 6:32-35; Exod. 25:9; Heb. 8:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:20', 0, 0, 'Manna, Rock, Cornerstone', 'L_cRBAttjC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/L_cRBAttjC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(548, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Examples from places (Part 5)', '<p>Geographical features like mountains or nations, are sometimes used in Old Testament records, seemingly without significance, but later on show up in Scripture as the location of an important event, often with Jesus at the center. This is another way God, the Author of Scripture, uses the literary technique of prophetic foreshadowing to amplify a significant point.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 22:2; 2 Chron. 3:1; Hosea 11:1; Matt. 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:20', 0, 0, 'Moriah, Egypt, Temple', 'yW83Ii7NfCM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yW83Ii7NfCM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(549, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Examples from people (Part 4)', '<p>Joseph, the son of Jacob, had many similar life experiences to Jesus, such as: he was loved by his father, a shepherd of sheep, obeyed his father, was envied by his brothers, was mocked, others would bow down to him, and many more. This is just one example of how certain characteristics of one person foreshadow another prophetically.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Gen. 37:3, 10, 11</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:51', 0, 0, null, '4FWEevfourM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4FWEevfourM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(550, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Examples from people (Part 3)', '<p>King David of the Old Testament had many of the same attributes as Jesus Christ, so many that it&rsquo;s hard to say that it was coincidental. This is an example of biblical prophetic foreshadowing, that one person had very similar qualities to Jesus who lived about 1000 years later.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 34:23, 24; Jer. 39:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:58', 0, 0, 'Shepherd, Bethlehem', 's647hqF_PeM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/s647hqF_PeM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(551, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - the New Testament (Part 2)', '<p>Abraham&rsquo;s sons Ishmael and Isaac are representative biblical foreshadows of two peoples, Arabs and Israelites, who strive against one another culturally. They also represent two realms, the earthly and heavenly, that strive against one another spiritually. Another foreshadowing example is God&rsquo;s judgment on the evil people of Sodom and Gomorrah by fire and brimstone pointing to His judgement on unrighteous people in the lake of fire.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 4:22-25; 2 Pet. 2:46</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:10', 0, 0, 'Figurative, Shadow, Type', 'ivSEZdBZi14', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ivSEZdBZi14/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(552, 1, 'Prophetic Foreshadows - Introduction (Part 1)', '<p>This video is an introduction to the literary technique of biblical prophetic foreshadows where the Author, God, weaves into Scripture hints and clues of information that may at the time seem insignificant but later will become very important to understanding a story or a principle. Like a real life shadow, it resembles an object, but without the detail that will become known later.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:10', 0, 0, null, 'hyIO0GW0kJY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hyIO0GW0kJY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(553, 1, 'The Feast of Booths - Feasts of Israel (Part 10)', '<p>The Feast of Booths is a seven-day fall feast in remembrance of the time Israel left Egypt and wandered in the wilderness. During that time God provided for their needs and protected them from their enemies. For the Church, it is a harbinger of Christ&rsquo;s future Millennial Kingdom on earth.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:34-43</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:19', 34, 10, 'Tabernacles, Ingathering', 'FXJ_5UJ1GOk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FXJ_5UJ1GOk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(554, 1, 'The Day of Atonement - Feasts of Israel (Part 9)', '<p>The holiest day of the Jewish year is the day of atonement, also an important feast day in Israel. The high priest went into the Holy of Holies in the Temple to ritually cleanse himself and Israel. One goat was sacrificed, and one was released to die in the wilderness, carrying away the sins of Israel. In the same way, Jesus&rsquo; death is the Church&rsquo;s atonement for forgiveness of sin.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:26-28; Acts 27:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:17', 34, 9, null, 'urb7d6vzr-E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/urb7d6vzr-E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(555, 1, 'The Feast of Trumpets - Feasts of Israel (Part 8)', '<p>The Feast of Trumpets is the first fall feast celebrated on Tishri 1 which is in September or October. It begins with the first sliver of the new moon appearing and initiates a call to assembly, an announcement, an awakening, or possibly the Rapture.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:24, 25; 1 Cor. 15:51, 52; 1 Thess. 4:16; Matt. 24:31; Rev. 11:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:39', 34, 8, 'Horn, Blowing', 's4elhtEaKaA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/s4elhtEaKaA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(556, 1, 'The Feast of Pentecost - Feasts of Israel (Part 7)', '<p>As the fourth and final of the spring feasts, the Feast of Pentecost occurs 50 days after Passover, and is also known as the Feast of Weeks. It was at this feast that the gift of holy spirit was poured out to the 12 apostles and the Body of Christ was birthed.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:15-17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:26', 34, 7, null, 'cAL4BAlBpG8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cAL4BAlBpG8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(557, 1, 'The Feast of First Fruits - Feasts of Israel (Part 6)', '<p>This teaching discusses the Feast of the First Fruits which occurred in the spring of the year. It illustrates that the symbolism related to this feast is fulfilled in the accomplishments of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:9-14; John 20:17; Rom. 8:23, 11:16; 1 Cor. 15:20-23; James 1:18; 1 Peter 2:24</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:52', 34, 6, null, '0kfPNKBbl3k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0kfPNKBbl3k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(558, 1, 'The Feast of Unleavened Bread - Feasts of Israel (Part 5)', '<p>The Feast of Unleavened Bread follows immediately after Passover. The unleavened bread is the bread of haste and affliction. It is symbolized as &ldquo;dead&rdquo; bread. Other symbolisms connected with unleavened bread are highlighted.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:6; Deut. 16:3-4; Matt. 16:6; 1 Cor. 5:6-8, 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:46', 34, 5, null, 'ZYKctrHNwUI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZYKctrHNwUI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(559, 1, 'The Feast of Passover - Feasts of Israel (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching explains when and why the Feast of Passover was established. Its original purpose was to protect the Israelites from the angel of death. The teaching parallels the original Passover with Jesus Christ who is our Passover.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 23:4-5; Ps. 41:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:45', 34, 4, null, '98lvg6kBxUI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/98lvg6kBxUI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(560, 1, 'More Background on the Feasts of Israel - Feasts of Israel (Part 3)', '<p>This teaching explains that the Israelites used a lunar calendar in determining feast days, but over time introduced solar year adjustments, which impacted the day on which particular feasts fell.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 20:5; Ezra 3:4-6; 1 Thess. 5:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:13', 34, 3, null, 'O7B1orwBKMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/O7B1orwBKMY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(561, 1, 'Background on the Feasts of Israel - Feasts of Israel (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching gives an overview of the feasts that Israel was to keep and categorizes them into four springtime feasts and three fall feasts. The feasts are a foreshadowing of man&rsquo;s redemption. Some of the feasts had more than one name which can make them confusing to study.</p> <p>Verses: John 20:17; Acts 12:3, 20:6; 1 Cor. 5:7; 15:20; Col. 2:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:41', 34, 2, null, '5Il4ATQqCp8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5Il4ATQqCp8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(562, 1, 'Introduction to the Feasts of Israel - Feasts of Israel (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching explains the feasts that Israel was to observe as described in the Old Testament. The feasts had significance and meaning in relation to God&rsquo;s plan of redemption for mankind which makes them important for us to understand even today.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-04-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:19', 34, 1, null, 'pLH3kAghP5A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pLH3kAghP5A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(563, 1, 'Divinely Instructed - Commentary on the Magi', '<p>The Magi of Matthew 2 were &ldquo;divinely instructed&rdquo; by God because they were seeking and praying for His direction. The instruction was to not return to Herod in Jerusalem, so they returned to their country by another road.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:7, 12, 22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-04-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 0, 0, null, 'bzSNNs1j18o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bzSNNs1j18o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(564, 1, 'The Baptism of Jesus Christ - Commentary from the REV', '<p>This teaching details the order of events before, during, and after the baptism of Jesus and explains how this shows that there is a distinction between John the Baptist&rsquo;s ministry and the ministry of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 3:13-17; Mark 1:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-04-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:46', 0, 0, null, 'lZYHU1LAjdU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lZYHU1LAjdU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 64, null),
(565, 1, 'A new understanding of Philippians 4:13', '<p>This teaching takes a fresh look at Philippians 4:13, an often-quoted verse of Scripture. The emphasis is about the continuous empowering that Christ does in a believer so they can face any situation that may arise.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:7; Phil. 3:21; 4:12-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-03-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:01', 0, 0, null, 'oT7DK5yFb0Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oT7DK5yFb0Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 45, null),
(566, 1, 'Prophetic Ministry: Keys to Walking in the Prophetic Ministry (Part 5)', '<p>The keys to successfully walking in any of the equipping ministries are fundamentally the same. This teaching describes five essential keys to successfully walk in the prophetic as well as developing a positive, Christian lifestyle.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:03', 50, 5, 'character, courage, holiness, obedience, prayer, truth, wisdom', '3tUakykLmfQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3tUakykLmfQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(567, 1, 'Prophetic Ministry: What is a True or False Prophet? (Part 4)', '<p>What is a true prophet? Can a person be declared a false prophet if his words do not come to pass? This teaching helps the listener understand the conditional nature of prophecy.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 28:9; Jonah 3:4, 10; 2 Peter 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:52', 50, 4, 'Balaam, future, heart', 'Noda9-DR85Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Noda9-DR85Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(568, 1, 'Prophetic Ministry: Differences Between New and Old Testament Prophets (Part 3)', '<p>Much of what we know about prophetic ministry is gleaned from reading records of various Old Testament prophets. This teaching looks at some of those records. Clarification of the differences between the manifestation of prophecy and the role of a prophet within the Body of Christ are also examined.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:55', 50, 3, 'curse, edification, exhortation, foretelling', '-q1w43XWvHU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-q1w43XWvHU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(569, 1, 'Prophetic Ministry: What is a Prophet - the Long Answer (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching expounds the role of a prophet. Hebrew terminology, from the Old Testament, is used to explain the various ways a prophet fulfills his duties. This provides deeper insights into the ways the prophet serves today as the eyes and ears of the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 21:9; Jer. 1:5, 7, 9; Micah 2:11; 1 Sam. 9:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:19', 50, 2, 'prophecy, seer, spokesperson', 'EWJtW_fsWs4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EWJtW_fsWs4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(570, 1, 'Prophetic Ministry: What is a Prophet? - the Short Answer (Part 1)', '<p>This video describes the role of a prophet as one of the five equipping ministries in the Body of Christ listed in Ephesians 4. Their job is to prepare God&rsquo;s people for works of service by hearing the voice of God or the Lord Jesus and delivering the message as directed.</p> <p>Verses: Eph 4:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-03-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:06', 50, 1, 'spokesperson', 'xbNpjDrJgQw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xbNpjDrJgQw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(572, 1, 'Study the Word, &ldquo;Berean Style&rdquo;', '<p>This teaching delivers a reminder about how Christians should seek after God, examine His Word, and utilize it in everyday life, by examining the behavior of the Berean Christians mentioned in Acts 17:11.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 17:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-02-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:07', 0, 0, 'attitude, skill, study', '-mANp-sDo1Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-mANp-sDo1Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(573, 1, 'Keep Yourself From Idols', '<p>God is to be our source of blessing. He is a jealous God and does not want his children to put anything else above their relationship with Him. This video teaches what idols are and how to avoid them.</p> <p>Verses: Exo. 20:1-6; 1 John 5:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-02-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:15', 0, 0, 'demons, punish, worship, worthy', 'meaqZb-ABvw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/meaqZb-ABvw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(574, 1, 'Lazarus and John 11 (Part 3)', '<p>This is the conclusion of the deeper look into the account of Jesus and Lazarus. It helps clarify what people believed about resurrection in the time of Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: John 11:19-44, 53</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:41', 31, 3, 'Mary, Martha', 'CFDQSxmGmiA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CFDQSxmGmiA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(575, 1, 'Lazarus and John 11 (Part 2)', '<p>Part 2 of this series takes a deeper look at the account of Lazarus. It answers the question why the Lord waited four days before arriving at the tomb of his friend.</p> <p>Verses: John 11:5-8, 11-15, 17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:08', 31, 2, null, 'jp75CVFRiC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jp75CVFRiC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(576, 1, 'Understanding the Story of Lazarus in John 11 (Part 1)', '<p>In part one of this 3-part series, the teacher draws attention to several &ldquo;sticky&rdquo; verses in the story of Lazarus in the Gospel of John. He notes that readers must become knowledgeable of the geography and culture to have a clear understanding of this section and clarifies the phrase &ldquo;this sickness is not unto death&rdquo; in verse 4.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:31, 40:11:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 31, 0, 'love', 'ODn-VDrO6kA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ODn-VDrO6kA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(577, 1, 'Know what you want and go for it!', '<p>Often in Scripture God tells historical events in a way that teaches us a lesson. One example is the story of blind Bartimaeus in the Gospel of Mark. Bartimaeus shows us the importance of being specific, focused, and undeterred by comments of those around us to receive the healing that we desire.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 10:46-52; Luke 11:1, 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-11-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:43', 0, 0, 'morals', 'rx__mS7vqMw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rx__mS7vqMw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(578, 1, 'An exciting announcement about the REV', '<p>UPDATE: You can now order our REV bible through our Online Store! Go here to check it out! http://www.stfonline.org/buytherev/</p>', '2013-11-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '0:51', 0, 0, null, 'sFQYEduSQy0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sFQYEduSQy0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'promo, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(579, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Halloween?', '<p>Many things that are a part of today&rsquo;s society, such as Halloween, were not specifically part of Biblical cultures. But Scripture offers guidance for us to learn how we should behave during this holiday. Christians are in a spiritual battle and need to remember we are to honor God and not the Adversary.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 12:30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-10-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:23', 0, 0, 'Lucifer', 'yDlR42NUfDM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yDlR42NUfDM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(580, 1, 'The Spiritual Battle - Desensitized to Evil', '<p>Christians need to keep their spiritual eyes open and not become immersed in this world. Instead we must immerse ourselves in God&rsquo;s Word so that we do not become desensitized by the evil of this world.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:44</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:11', 0, 0, null, '4-ynGE9DRNA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4-ynGE9DRNA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(581, 1, 'An Analogy of Motorcycling & Spiritual Discipline', '<p>This teaching draws parallels between motorcycling and spiritual discipline through explaining how the teacher&rsquo;s years of experience as a rider have made him a safe and disciplined rider. This analogy shows the importance of godliness becoming a lifestyle for Christians to gain spiritual discipline.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:54', 0, 0, null, '9xPAGSW0F60', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9xPAGSW0F60/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(582, 1, 'Eliminate Toxic Thinking', '<p>Would you knowingly eat toxic waste? Of course not! In this teaching we learn that as followers of Jesus Christ, we have a choice to conform to this world with toxic thoughts or upgrade them to be more Godly thoughts which are pleasing to Him.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 12:1-2, 9-14, 18-19, 21</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:28', 0, 0, null, '7P-_DlCXb78', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7P-_DlCXb78/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(583, 1, 'A Message of Knowledge or Wisdom (Part 5)', '<p>In the Bible, God has given many examples of messages of knowledge and messages of wisdom. Part 5 of this series looks at Scripture to explain the difference between these two manifestations of the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 6:13-15; 12:1-2; Exod. 17:5-6; Josh. 5:2, 9; 1 Sam. 9:15-16; 1 King 14:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:47', 56, 5, null, 'r00zK5cuKFw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/r00zK5cuKFw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(584, 1, 'A Message of Knowledge or Wisdom (Part 4)', '<p>Part 4 of this series explains the preference for the translation &ldquo;message&rdquo; instead of &ldquo;word&rdquo; of knowledge and &ldquo;word&rdquo; of wisdom. This segment also explains the 7 ways the messages of knowledge and of wisdom can be received from God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 9:16; 11:6; 2 Kings 3:15; Luke 11:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:26', 56, 4, 'Discipline', 'Hl9JDCnP4_I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Hl9JDCnP4_I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(585, 1, 'A Message of Knowledge or Wisdom (Part 3)', '<p>Part 3 of this series goes into detail regarding the manifestation of the message of knowledge: what it is, what it is not, and how important it is to live godly lives so that we can recognize a message of knowledge when it is given.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:11', 56, 3, 'Discipline', 'g5CG-sCz3ik', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/g5CG-sCz3ik/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(586, 1, 'A Message of Knowledge or Wisdom (Part 2)', '<p>This segment continues the discussion of the manifestations of a message of knowledge and a message of wisdom. Many examples are shown from the Old Testament of people receiving revelation via the gift of holy spirit that seems to come from the five senses.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 15:1-2; Judg. 3:9-10; 1 Sam. 16:12; Ps. 51:11; Exod. 19:25; 20:1-2, 18-19; Deut. 4:9-13; Dan. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:08', 56, 2, null, 'f27MUpHf2UQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f27MUpHf2UQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(587, 1, 'A Message of Knowledge or Wisdom (Part 1)', '<p>A message of knowledge is receiving information from God or Jesus Christ; a message of wisdom is what to do with that information. In this teaching, these two revelation manifestations are defined and explained. God wants to communicate with us directly and personally. Every Christian can hear from God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:7; Num. 11:11, 14, 16-17, 24-25, 29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:08', 56, 1, 'spirit', 'rXRjWw6uOkQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rXRjWw6uOkQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(588, 1, 'The Giver, the Gift, and the Manifestations (Part 3)', '<p>The purpose of manifesting holy spirit is for the common good of believers &ndash; so they can be helped and blessed by God and each other. In this teaching, the nine manifestations of 1 Corinthians 12 are set forth in three groups &ndash; revelation manifestations, power manifestations, and worship manifestations.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:7-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:13', 0, 0, 'message', 'JMgd-u_Qw88', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JMgd-u_Qw88/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(589, 1, 'The Giver, the Gift, and the Manifestations (Part 2)', '<p>This segment illustrates why we need to know the difference between a gift and a manifestation. Working through the list of the nine ways each and every believer can bring the gift of holy spirit into evidence, we learn how Christians can walk in the power of God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 11:17; 12:1, 7-10; 14:1-2, 12, 37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:03', 0, 0, 'spirit, message', 'hifth_hbQqI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hifth_hbQqI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(590, 1, 'The Giver, the Gift, and the Manifestations (Part 1)', '<p>What are the manifestations of the gift of holy spirit and how do we use them? This three-part series defines the differences between Holy Spirit which is God, the gift of holy spirit which He gives, and the outward manifestation of that gift that every Christian has been given.</p> <p>Verses: John 5:30; Acts 1:8; 2:33; Eph. 1:3; 1 Pet. 1:23; 2 Pet. 1:4; Rev 1:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:56', 0, 0, 'witness, blessing, promises', 'sDVyJ1mCghg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sDVyJ1mCghg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(591, 1, 'Introduction to the Manifestations', '<p>This is a brief introduction to Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship&rsquo;s seminar on the manifestations of holy spirit and walking in spiritual power. We pray this teaching series blesses you in your walk with God and the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:31', 0, 0, 'receive, witness', 'Vs1z-dxK0rc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vs1z-dxK0rc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(592, 1, 'An Explanation of Psalm 139 - Open View (Part 14)', '<p>This video provides an explanation of Psalm 139 and how it can be understood in light of the Open View of God, and gives insight into interpreting Hebrew poetry.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 139</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:31', 12, 14, null, '1ntbVNAG8bE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1ntbVNAG8bE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(593, 1, 'The Citadel & Map of Jerusalem - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 28)', '<p>The tour group visits the Citadel on the western side of Jerusalem. This was Herod&rsquo;s Palace where the Magi came and the place where Jesus was put on trial before Pontius Pilate. This segment also visits a topographical sculpture of Jerusalem, a model of the modern city, and a model of the ancient city, tracing various sites and events.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:09', 27, 28, 'Mount, Olives, Praetorium, temple', 'Qlx0imPte_o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Qlx0imPte_o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(594, 1, 'City Gates, Water Tunnel, Temple Steps - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 27)', '<p>Beginning at the outer gate of Jerusalem where elders would sit and people would gather, the tour moves on to an ancient water tunnel cut out of stone. This section of the tour concludes with a visit to the main entrance to the Temple and a teaching about why the Temple steps were made to be uneven in length and height.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 18:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:43', 27, 27, 'mikvah', '4JAy5kvkrjg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4JAy5kvkrjg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(595, 1, 'Sea of Galilee, Caesarea, Ancient Tomb - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 26)', '<p>This teaching describes, on location, various sites on the 2000 Bible Lands Tour. The Bible Lands are often referred to as the Fifth Gospel, in that the viewer can gain a better understanding of the Lord Jesus&rsquo; ministry by experiencing the locations in which he conducted his ministry.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:24', 27, 26, null, '37vVtKsuUAA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/37vVtKsuUAA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(596, 1, 'Joppa -  Israel Tour 2000 (Part 25)', '<p>This teaching explores the records from the Word of God, on location in Israel, that transpired in or near the ancient city of Joppa, and refers to the Bible Lands as the Fifth Gospel in that seeing the land helps bring the records to life.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:32-42; 10:9-23; 2 Chron. 2:1, 11-16; Jon. 1:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '24:29', 27, 25, null, 'Gz6YARAqoQM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gz6YARAqoQM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(597, 1, 'Hazazon-Tamar/ Ein Gedi - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 24)', '<p>This portion of the Bible Lands Tour includes on-site teachings of a few significant biblical records: the record of David and Saul and their interaction in the caves during the time David was fleeing from Saul, and the record of Jehoshaphat.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> 2 Chron. 20:1-2; 1 Sam. 24:6-22</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:43', 27, 24, null, 'ciRii_s78Kc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ciRii_s78Kc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(598, 1, 'Biblical Tents, Lamps and Culture - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 23)', '<p>This teaching from the Bible Lands Tour provides information on traditional tents used in Israel in biblical times and even still today. It additionally shows the lamps used during those biblical times.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 13:17-19; Ps. 133:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:03', 27, 23, null, 'Dr5zpCeN6Ts', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Dr5zpCeN6Ts/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(599, 1, 'Israel Tour 2014 Promo', '<p>To sign up for this Tour, visit http://www.STFonline.org/israel2014</p>', '2013-05-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:09', 0, 0, null, 'PsEC_lK3Gaw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PsEC_lK3Gaw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Old news..', 1, 0, null),
(600, 1, 'We can have faith in God - Open View (Part 13)', '<p>This final teaching in the series on the Open View of God recaps the highlights and addresses why or faith in God should be based on His trustworthy character and not the belief that He knows everything. The decisions we make whether to utilize the entablements we have been gifted make a tremendous difference in the movement of God today and in the future.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:59', 12, 13, 'trust', 'M4-c2mWInS0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/M4-c2mWInS0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(601, 1, 'How could Jesus have been sinless? - Open View (Part 12)', '<p>Was the Lord Jesus preordained to live a sinless life or was his sinless life a moment-by-moment decision that he made? This teaching addresses this question and sheds light on God&rsquo;s corrective and retributive justice.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:59', 12, 12, null, 'ARazDF-WS3o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ARazDF-WS3o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(602, 1, 'Does God decide who will be saved? - Open View (Part 11)', '<p>This teaching addresses a topic that has been controversial in the Church for centuries: the idea of predestination and whether God decides who will be saved. Arguing from the viewpoint of the Open View of God, this teaching answers that all-important question.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:4-6; Rom. 8:29; 11:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:04', 12, 11, 'foreknowledge', 'RhRlCFKO4V4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RhRlCFKO4V4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(603, 1, 'We can have Confidence in God - Open View (Part 10)', '<p>This teaching shares how God, who made the rules of the universe, must work within the parameters He created, and addresses challenging questions such as: does God have the capability to make His words come true? Should our confidence in God be based on the supposition that He knows everything that is going to happen?</p> <p>Verses: Num. 23:19; 1Sam. 15:29; Isa. 30:18; 48:3; Mal. 3:6; 2 Pet. 3:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 12, 10, null, 'SxVoPuaaqgg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SxVoPuaaqgg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(604, 1, 'Objections to the Open View of God - Open View (Part 9)', '<p>God has the power to bring about the final end as He promised and has demonstrated throughout history. Does this mean God is in control of everything that happens on earth? Does He change His mind? Is God a coworker with man? This teaching explores these questions in relation to God&rsquo;s interactions with mankind.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 12, 9, null, 'Gz3Zt_a_qRI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gz3Zt_a_qRI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(605, 1, 'People in the Bible believed in the Open View - Open View (Part 8)', '<p>Historical people of the Bible interacted &ldquo;in time&rdquo; with God. This truth applies today. Our God does not live in a fixed eternal program, but rather He invites us to join Him in experiencing life together in a real, meaningful, and trusting relationship.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 18:23-33; Exod. 3:18; 32:10-14, 33; 1 Kings 21:20-29; 2 Kings 20:1-6; Amos 7:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:17', 12, 8, 'communication', 'uF3FAW3sEmg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uF3FAW3sEmg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(606, 1, 'God has expectations that aren''t being met - Open View (Part 7)', '<p>The scriptures state that God has unmet expectations. If God is perfect and His knowledge is fixed, then He would not need to expect anything. The &ldquo;Open View&rdquo; or &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; contends that God operates &ldquo;in time&rdquo; along with a His creation and is able to change. There are many scriptures that confirm that God does change His mind in response to the choices of men.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 5:2; Jer. 3:6, 7; 26:3; Ezek. 22:30, 31; 12:3; 1 Chron. 21:15; Ex. 32:14; 1 Sam. 2:27-31; Num. 14:10; Gen. 4:7; 18:26; Isa. 1:19; Deut. 30:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:00', 12, 7, 'relationship, journey', 'JnteglTqO-8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JnteglTqO-8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(607, 1, 'Does God know what''s going to happen in the Future? - Open View (Part 6)', '<p>This teaching illustrates that God adjusts His actions according to the choices of mankind. There are numerous predictive scriptures that present the &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; and show God changing His mind based on the actions of people.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 18:1-11; 34:4; 52:10-11; 2 Sam. 7:11-13; 12:10; 1 Kings 11:11; 21:21, 29; 2 Kings 20:1, 5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:44', 12, 6, null, 'kEjEHmz0hTI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kEjEHmz0hTI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(608, 1, 'God is not responsible for Evil - Open View (Part 5)', '<p>This teaching compares how the &ldquo;Knowledge Model&rdquo; and the &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; address evil. Through proofs from Scripture we see that God cannot contradict who He is and through Scripture we also see how He works.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:8; Isa. 48:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 12, 5, null, '2sbC3aJgqt4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2sbC3aJgqt4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(609, 1, 'Does God have real Emotions? - Open View (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching provides multiple examples of how God makes a prediction and follows through to make it happen. The &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; presents a God that is emotional, personal, passionate, and involved. He invites trust, relationship, belief in His Word and that our prayers matter.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 62:5; 59:16; Ps. 78:40; 2:4; Exod. 32:14; 4:14; Deut. 32:16; Zech. 1:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:37', 12, 4, null, '1a_o4OE4430', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1a_o4OE4430/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(610, 1, 'The Two Models for Predicting the Future - Open View (Part 3)', '<p>This teaching explores two ways for determining how God predicts the future. The &ldquo;Knowledge Model&rdquo; says God can predict the future because &ldquo;He knows it,&rdquo; while the &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; says God can predict the future because &ldquo;He can do it.&rdquo; We must choose the model that best enables us to build a trusting relationship with God.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 46:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:01', 12, 3, null, '4Gs0D25qSJY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4Gs0D25qSJY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(611, 1, 'What is the Open View of God? - Open View (Part 2)', '<p>The common belief is that God is &ldquo;outside of time,&rdquo; and that things are unchangeable, which limits our trust in Him; however, understanding the &ldquo;Power Model&rdquo; or &ldquo;Open View of God&rdquo; puts God &ldquo;in time,&rdquo; making Him all-powerful and capable to cause change and to bring His promises into fruition.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 14:13; Num. 23:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:30', 12, 2, 'trust', '9ycp6a6OAIw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9ycp6a6OAIw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(612, 1, 'An Overview of the Open View of God - Open View (Part 1)', '<p>Many Christians believe that God is all-powerful and all-knowing, but is this really the case? Does God really know everything that&#39;s going to happen throughout time before it happens? What does this say about free will and all the Evil that happens in the world?</p> <p>In this 13 part series John Schoenheit looks into the topic of Open Theism, or the Open View of God. This viewpoint can help explain some issues about God&#39;s character and how he can be a loving, caring God while still letting us make our own choices.</p> <p>View or download our syllabus for this seminar by clicking <a href="https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a>.</p>', '2013-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:30', 12, 1, null, 'Of52ji-NfBk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Of52ji-NfBk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(613, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Marijuana / Weed / Cannabis / Pot?', '<p>Is it OK to use marijuana? It is becoming more and more popular in our culture, and with its increased prominence and possible legalization, it&#39;s something we get asked about quite a bit. This teaching explores what the Bible has to say about it.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:29; 3:17, 18; Eph. 5:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-04-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:38', 0, 0, null, 'IUy1ZumgjFo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IUy1ZumgjFo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(614, 1, 'What is true Joy? - More on Joy Blockers (Part 6)', '<p>When we draw near to the righteousness expressed in God&rsquo;s Word, we experience an inner wellbeing called joy. In contrast, when sin and foolish acts become our choice, they produce guilt and shame which steal our joy. We are encouraged to stay away from the joy blockers: idols, intentional sin, unwise choices, and isolation.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:19-22; Prov. 10:1, 28; 15:23; 3 John 1:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:07', 60, 6, 'obedience', 'EQ9kxbQdlT4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EQ9kxbQdlT4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(615, 1, 'What is true Joy? - Joy Blockers (Part 5)', '<p>Anything that takes the place of our relying on God is an idol. Since idols are inferior to God, they cannot provide for us as God does. It is our choice what to believe, but God calls us to shun idols and trust in Him for our strength, provision, and joy in life.</p> <p>Verses: Eze. 14:4, 7; Ps. 16:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:11', 60, 5, 'Idolatry, Astrology', '3wssKpccAWk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3wssKpccAWk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(616, 1, 'What is True Joy? - More on Developing Joy (Part 4)', '<p>Joy arises in us when we consider the love God pours into our daily life and the hope we have for everlasting life with God and Christ. Living among like-minded people in the Body of Christ also helps joy dwell in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:2-3; Rom. 12:9-12; 1 Pet. 1:8-9; Phil. 2:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:14', 60, 4, null, 'vFBwOICHMmk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vFBwOICHMmk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(617, 1, 'What is True Joy - Developing Joy (Part 3)', '<p>Joy comes when we are connected to God by reading and meditating on his Word, by giving praise and worshiping Him because He is worthy, and by prayer as we talk to him from our heart and then listen to Him as He responds to us. Having a God-focused life helps us live joyfully.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 9:23; Ps. 19:8; 21:6; 27:6; 47:5; 92:4-5; 126:2-3; 1 Thess. 3:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:14', 60, 3, 'Singing, Music', 'QkjM_cn4NlY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QkjM_cn4NlY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(618, 1, 'What is True Joy - Joy Defined (Part 2)', '<p>Happiness arises from external circumstances. Joy is a sense of wellbeing that bubbles up from within us. It provides peace and assurance whether we are in the midst of blessings or adversity. Joy is a spiritual experience that God provides and it sustains us through the ups and downs of life&rsquo;s journey.</p> <p>Verses: Neh. 8:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:22', 60, 2, null, 'GE4J9UAf1n4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GE4J9UAf1n4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(619, 1, 'What is True Joy? - Finding Our Joy (Part 1)', '<p>Life is difficult and comes with hardships, but persevering through those challenges is possible. God is able to sustain us in every situation as we focus on the blessings we have, not the negatives that we are enduring. Examples are given from the life of a church leader in China, Brother Yun, as written in his book <em>The Heavenly Man.</em></p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:32-34</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:55', 60, 1, 'Suffering, Persecution, Endurance, Joy, Strength', 'M1JbUhCGBIQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/M1JbUhCGBIQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 40, null),
(620, 1, 'Homosexuality - Pro-Gay Theology (Part 6)', '<p>Pro-gay theology is based on philosophy, sociology, and psychology that apply secular arguments to claim that homosexuality is normal behavior and morally neutral. Scripture states otherwise. Although some people claim that the scriptures that discuss homosexuality are mistranslated, misunderstood, or misapplied, we should understand the Bible as meaning what it says.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 18:22; 20:13; Rom. 1:27</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:40', 29, 6, 'Revisionist', 'prYFlp0LuUQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/prYFlp0LuUQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(621, 1, 'Homosexuality - How to Deal with Same Sex Attraction (Part 5)', '<p>God made us with sexual desires rooted in strong feelings that drive our behavior. Scripture contrasts Godly and ungodly behavior and commands us to control our feelings by disciplining our minds to live by God&rsquo;s principles.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 6:9-11, 19-20; 2 Cor. 5:15; Rom. 8:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:36', 29, 5, null, 'hzmmYw_H-_A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hzmmYw_H-_A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(622, 1, 'Homosexuality - Is There Scientific Evidence for Gay Behavior? (Part 4)', '<p>Everyone is born with a sin nature. As we grow up, many influences impact our life, including parenting style, family generational behavior, trauma, abuse, and our own decisions. All these influencers can impact what we become, including our sexual orientation.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 51:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:02', 29, 4, null, '-46Ki8pOygI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-46Ki8pOygI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(623, 1, 'Homosexuality - Why Did God Make Me This Way? (Part 3)', '<p>Mankind has a carnal nature and a spiritual nature. What our flesh desires pops up from within us out of our carnal nature. Sin has perverted the world God created in Genesis. Acting sinfully is contrary to God&rsquo;s original intent and fails to recognize the consequences of disobeying God.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:22-25; Col. 5:15-17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:00', 29, 3, 'Condemnation', 'KZPXvpS6L0U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KZPXvpS6L0U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(624, 1, 'Homosexuality - What does the Bible say? (Part 2)', '<p>Citing many parallels between the Old and New Testaments, this teaching illustrates that God&rsquo;s standard for sexual behavior involves a man and a woman in a covenant marriage relationship. Any other sexual activity is &ldquo;off the mark.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:21-24; 19:4-7; Lev. 18:22; Matt. 19:3; Rom. 1:20-31; 1 Cor. 6:9-10; 7:2-3; 1 Tim. 1:8-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '26:44', 29, 2, null, '8NQgyvecFHM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8NQgyvecFHM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(625, 1, 'Homosexuality - Introduction (Part 1)', '<p>Homosexuality is one of many sexual sins, and a topic that has brought a reaction by the Church of hard-heartedness and condemnation. We must approach these issues as Jesus did &ndash; with a perfect balance of grace and truth, not to affirm nor condemn. Culture does not dictate truth. God hates no one!</p> <p>Verses: John 1:17-18; 8:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:47', 29, 1, null, 'qm269_-74tM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qm269_-74tM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(626, 1, '(GMO) Genetically Modified Organisms', '<p>Adam&rsquo;s sin forfeited dominion and control of the earth, resulting in things such as thorns, thistles, biting insects, and poisonous plants. In this teaching we are reminded that one day, organisms will be &ldquo;Godly modified&rdquo; as described in Isaiah 11, where the wolf will lie down with the lamb, the leopard with the goat, and the lion with the calf. That&rsquo;s transformation!</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 11:6-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-03-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:48', 0, 0, null, 'oF4cCwRnF5E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oF4cCwRnF5E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(627, 1, 'The Purpose of God&rsquo;s Word', '<p>We are told In 2 Peter that the Bible gives us all things that pertain to life and godliness. Timothy tells us that the Bible is useful for teaching, rebuking, correcting, and training in righteousness. We are to read it to be wise, to believe it to be safe, and to practice it to be holy.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:1, 9, 28, 49, 52, 98, 130, 160, 162, 165; 2 Tim. 3:16; 2 Pet. 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:39', 0, 0, null, 'DlKRkRitcGk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DlKRkRitcGk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(628, 1, 'What is Faith? - Trust in God', '<p>The Book of Romans tells us that we are made righteous by our faith, not by our works. We trust in God&rsquo;s promises. Trust comes from hearing sound teaching and doctrine. Faith grows, and if not, something is wrong!</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:20-22; 10:1, 17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:43', 0, 0, null, 'cZGbSrvEQLo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cZGbSrvEQLo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(629, 1, 'How to assemble an REV Bible', '<p>The Revised English Version of the Bible is available for reading or download from the internet, free of charge. Many may prefer a &ldquo;paper&rdquo; Bible over a &ldquo;virtual&rdquo; Bible, however, as it can be easier to read and to add notes or pictures. This tutorial instructs the viewer on how to use a 3-ring binder and Bible index tabs or notebook dividers to assemble a printed REV Bible for ease of use in your studies.</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:00', 0, 0, null, 'OV7uyjaJUdI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OV7uyjaJUdI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'Not sure this has much value any more', 1, 1, null),
(630, 1, 'Sowing in Tears, Reaping in Joy - Make Good Decisions', '<p>Psalm 126:5 suggests that tough decisions can lead to great outcomes. This verse uses the image of farming, where tough decisions must be made, often by the hour. With decisions come trade-offs, risks, sacrifice, and perhaps even conflict. God encourages us to face life head-on and make the next decision a right one.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 126:5</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:45', 0, 0, null, 'enrYwKwqCw0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/enrYwKwqCw0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(631, 1, 'The Four Servant Songs of Isaiah (Part 5)', '<p>Isaiah 52 and 53 are key chapters where Jesus would have learned about what God was asking him to do. Written in the &ldquo;prophetic perfect,&rdquo; that is &ldquo;already, but not yet,&rdquo; Jesus learned that he would cleanse and make holy many nations through the shedding of his blood. This passage contains the promise that by his wounds, we are healed.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 52:13-53:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:39', 33, 5, null, 'smLJilnUpAw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/smLJilnUpAw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(632, 1, 'The Four Servant Songs of Isaiah (Part 4)', '<p>In the third of four &ldquo;Servant Songs,&rdquo; we see through the revelation of Isaiah that Yahweh is &ldquo;ramping up&rdquo; His instructions for Jesus, telling him what it will take for him to fulfill his ministry. He promises to help Jesus, encouraging him to build up others with his words, to not be rebellious, to not hide his face, and that he will not be put to shame.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 50:4-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:36', 33, 4, null, 'xSo4NXq0QEo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xSo4NXq0QEo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(633, 1, 'The Four Servant Songs of Isaiah (Part 3)', '<p>This teaching addresses the second &ldquo;servant song&rdquo; of Isaiah, where Jesus learns more of what God&lsquo;s will for his life is, and God&rsquo;s promises to him, building on the first servant song. This prophecy also reveals that Jesus would be tempted with discouragement because he would not see the fruits of his labor. God, however, promised Jesus that he would be rewarded.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 49:1-7; 1 Cor. 15:58</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:06', 33, 3, 'calling, recompense, light, salvation, strength, despised, redeemer, encouragement, exhortation', 'hwzjZBN3pAI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hwzjZBN3pAI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(634, 1, 'The Four Servant Songs of Isaiah (Part 2)', '<p>Four sections of Hebrew poetry written in Isaiah are called &ldquo;servant songs.&rdquo; As Jesus grew in knowledge and wisdom and read this first song, he understood that it talked about him. He learned how he should behave and what he would do. He also learned the promises God made to him for living his life&rsquo;s mission.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 42:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:03', 33, 2, 'hope, discipline, will, covenant, obedience, justice, light', 'Ow_bECfvGsw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ow_bECfvGsw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(635, 1, 'The Four Servant Songs of Isaiah (Part 1)', '<p>The more we know about Jesus Christ, the easier it is to follow him and to be like him. Isaiah reveals many things about Jesus and the future kingdom. Jesus understood that he should learn from Isaiah. In this first in a series of teachings, we find that the Bible says the Messiah is a servant of God.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 1:26; 4:2; 8:18-20; 42:1-4; Matt. 12:17; Acts 4:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:05', 33, 1, 'anointing, Hope, symbolism', 'ehIWQi6hASY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ehIWQi6hASY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(636, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Curses in the Age of Grace (Part 6)', '<p>Even though we are seated in the heavenly places because of our union with Christ, we still live in a physical world while we wait for his return. God has given us instruction about curses which is applicable for our lives today in the Age of Grace.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 11:12-19, 20-26; Rom. 12:14; 1 Cor. 4:12; 16:22; 2 Pet. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:27', 41, 6, 'sin, idolatry, consequences', 'T6_Qb3QV4pI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T6_Qb3QV4pI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(637, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Idolatry (Part 5)', '<p>Idolatry, which can result in curses to the third and fourth generation, is putting anything before God, and is an issue of the heart. According to Scripture, rejecting God&rsquo;s instruction and resorting to rebellion and stubbornness is a form of idolatry.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 20:4-6; 34:6-7; Num. 14:18; Deut. 28:15; 1 Sam. 15:23; Ezek. 14:4-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:04', 41, 5, 'sin, obedience', 'wNQ-X2nVDik', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wNQ-X2nVDik/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(638, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Generational Curses (Part 4)', '<p>Sin of all types can open doorways for curses to be passed on to us from our ancestors, and through us to our children and future generations. Learn how to break through these curses with the power of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 20:4-6; Matt. 27:24-25; Gal. 3:13; 2 Pet. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:18', 41, 4, 'demons, idolatry', 'cGDnCCF_eYI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cGDnCCF_eYI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(639, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Curses Resulting from Words (Part 3)', '<p>Words are used in prayer to appeal to God to intervene in our world. Similarly, some words can result in curses that can open doorways for evil influence. Life and death are in the power of words.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 5:12-22; Neh. 13:2, Pss. 57:4; 109:6-12; Prov. 18:21; 26:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:19', 41, 3, 'demons, blessing, tongue', 'DCNANX6LKTo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DCNANX6LKTo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(640, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Curses Resulting from Actions (Part 2)', '<p>The action of the original sin resulted in curses for Adam, Eve, and the Serpent. Sinful actions on our part open the door for demonic influences to come into our lives. Like the blood sprinkled over the doorposts at the Passover, the covering of the blood of Jesus Christ along with repentance and rebuking the curse will result in Satan passing us by.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:14-19; 4:10-11; Deut. 27:15-26; Gal. 3:10; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:37', 41, 2, 'devil, spiritual, idolatry', '3QdOsbU8jMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3QdOsbU8jMY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(641, 1, 'Understanding Curses | Introduction to Curses (Part 1)', '<p>Satan&rsquo;s power and authority over us was broken by Jesus Christ. However, Satan still tries to, and does, influence our lives. Curses are words or actions that allow demonic influence to affect us. Curses can be results of words, actions, or generational sin.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 11:12-25; Gal. 3:10-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:34', 41, 1, 'Devil, evil, spiritual', 'UnPQ9SJ2JdI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UnPQ9SJ2JdI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null);
