(642, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Armageddon?', '<p>The future kingdom ruled by Jesus Christ is not in heaven but on earth. The Battle of Armageddon occurs when Christ returns on his white horse along with his armies to conquer all those who are against him. This bloody battle occurs north of Jerusalem and start off the events that set up the Messianic Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Isaiah 63:2-3; Rev. 14:19-20; 16:6; 19:14-21; 20:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:37', 0, 0, 'kings, war', 'TiigfKWeQLM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TiigfKWeQLM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 35, null),
(643, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Heaven? (Part 2)', '<p>As born-again Christians, we look forward to our future inheritance, which includes eternal life on earth in the Millennial Kingdom, followed by life in the New Jerusalem, the Eternal City. This is promised throughout the Bible. It is our Hope and the anchor of our soul.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 37:9-11; Isa. 57:13; Ezek. 37:12; Dan. 2:34-35; 1 Thess. 4:16-17; Matt. 5:5; Rev. 1:7; 5:10; 19:11-15; 21:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:51', 0, 0, 'promise, death, rapture, resurrection', '4n7QE6fQaC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4n7QE6fQaC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(644, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Heaven? (Part 1)', '<p>When the Bible speaks of heaven, the Hebrew actually means &ldquo;the heavens,&rdquo; and can refer to anything above the earth including the spiritual realm where God is. Some things in that spiritual realm are described in the Bible, such as the throne, and God standing on a paved work of sapphire stone.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 24:9-10; 25:40; 2 Sam. 21:10; 2 Chron. 20:16; Ezek. 1:26-28; Heb. 8:5; Rev. 4:2-3; 11:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:03', 0, 0, null, 'I3bbtd12U54', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I3bbtd12U54/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(645, 1, 'What does the Bible say about God?', '<p>The Bible tells us that God is the Creator, that He is one God, not many, and that He has a personal name&ndash;Yahweh. God is love, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. He is righteous, just, the giver of every good gift, and is often misrepresented. This teaching sheds light on what the Bible truly says about God.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:15; 1 John 4:8, 16; John 3:16; James 1:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-01-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:56', 0, 0, null, 'b7kUXbs_tCg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b7kUXbs_tCg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 39, null),
(646, 1, 'Will Having Faith Prevent Me From Suffering?', '<p>Although faith is strength, it is not a vaccination to prevent suffering or an antidote to cure suffering. Many places in Scripture state that hard trials, tribulations, and persecution will come to godly people. The &ldquo;Heroes of Faith&rdquo; in Hebrews 11, and Jesus himself, all encountered suffering. Not accepting this fact can lead to disillusionment with Scripture and occasionally even being judgmental of others who are suffering.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Pet. 4:12; Acts 14:22; Rom. 8:22; 2 Tim. 3:12; Heb 11:1-13, 32-38</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:22', 0, 0, 'Groaning, Endurance', '35sCAtx6e2I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/35sCAtx6e2I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(647, 1, 'Who Do You Say Jesus Is?', '<p>Some people relate to Jesus by their life-style or behavior or things currently happening in their lives. This includes touchdown Jesus, therapist Jesus, political Jesus, hippy Jesus, new age Jesus, guru Jesus, boyfriend Jesus, and others. All of these are valid to a point, but he is so much more. We should not forget that Jesus Christ is Lord of lords, judge of the world, savior to mankind, redeemer, and mediator between man and God.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-12-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:10', 0, 0, null, 'TlFuazL9ynA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TlFuazL9ynA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(648, 1, 'Our Freewill Choice: Everlasting Life or Everlasting Death', '<p>God has given mankind free will to make decisions. One of those decisions is to obey God or not. Based on their decision, people determine if they will have everlasting life or everlasting death. God is just to allow us to make this choice. God is love and wants people to choose everlasting life.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:16-17; 3:5, 22; Isa. 32:4; Rom. 2:14-15; 6:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:10', 0, 0, 'Everlasting', 'uFoAQ-kyEkY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uFoAQ-kyEkY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(649, 1, 'Samaria - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 22)', '<p>This video is an onsite teaching in Samaria about the history of this area, from how it became capital of Israel after Solomon died to when it was destroyed by Assyria.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 14:17-37; 2 Kings 17:1-33</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-12-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '34:40', 27, 22, 'Solomon, Ahab, Jezebel, Ahaz', 'c8Q3KbTF-cw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/c8Q3KbTF-cw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(650, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues (Part 5)', '<p>Speaking in tongues is prayer and praise to God, and the interpretation of tongues will reflect that. It is a sign of the power of God to unbelievers. The manifestation of prophecy is different in that it is a sign to those who believe. Both manifestations will edify and bless the people in the meeting.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 28:1-2, 9, 11; Hosea 1:4b; 4:8-10; Amos 2:6; 1 Cor 14:4-5, 21-22, 26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:59', 37, 5, null, '5Qa63JzAKj0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5Qa63JzAKj0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(651, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues (Part 4)', '<p>The Bible makes it clear that the person who speaks in tongues is the one who must interpret. God and the Lord Jesus Christ are very personal and will work with you in your unique individual manner as you learn to walk with them and manifest the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 14:13; Heb. 5:12-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:06', 37, 4, null, '3wvOvwTYq-o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3wvOvwTYq-o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(652, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues (Part 3)', '<p>When someone speaks in tongues in the congregation, that same person should interpret. As speaking in tongues is prayer and praise to God, the interpretation will be likewise. The people hearing the interpretation in a language they understand will be edified, built up, and blessed, and God will be glorified.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 14:4-5, 14a, 16-17, 27-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:55', 37, 3, null, 'kT4cSkrfB8Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kT4cSkrfB8Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(653, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues (Part 2)', '<p>When a Christian speaks in tongues, he or she is speaking to God, not to people. When interpreted, that message is spoken in a language those present will understand, but it is not a word-for-word translation.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:4, 11; 10:44-46; 11:28; 1 Cor. 11:17; 12:5, 7-10, 14-15, 20-21; 14:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:47', 37, 2, null, 'DXQNCEUrynQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DXQNCEUrynQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(654, 1, 'The Interpretation of Tongues (Part 1)', '<p>When a person confesses Jesus Christ as Lord and believes God raised him from the dead, they become born again. Something is born within them, which is the gift of holy spirit. When the gift is given, all of its manifestations come with it. Speaking in tongues and interpretation of tongues are two ways to manifest the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:4; 10:44-46; 1 Cor. 12:1, 7; 14:1, 12, 37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:22', 37, 1, null, '__pMnHvufsc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/__pMnHvufsc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(655, 1, 'Valley of Elah - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 21)', '<p>There are many lessons to be learned from this detailed teaching of the record of David and Goliath from 1 Samuel, which is taught in the area where the event occurred. Included in the teaching is a demonstration of the type of sling used by David to slay Goliath.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 8:19, 20; 17:1-11, 32-52</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '25:58', 27, 21, null, 'yOYVkSsmaxk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yOYVkSsmaxk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(656, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Alcohol?', '<p>Scripture is very graphic in its description of drunkenness and teaches that we should not get drunk. However, it does not teach that we should not drink alcohol at all. There are many records that instruct when it is appropriate to drink alcohol and when it is not.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 23:29-35; John 2:10; Rom. 14:15, 17; Eph. 5:18; 1 Tim. 5:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:00', 0, 0, 'Ferment, Beer', 'Aa3D-n_0cBE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Aa3D-n_0cBE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(657, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Lying? Half Truths?', '<p>The Bible is clear that we should not lie. The Devil is the father of lies. Lying is part of our sinful nature, but when we lie we should confess our sin, receive forgiveness, and rectify any wrong we have caused. Rare exceptions are seen in Scripture where it is appropriate to lie in order to protect life.</p> <p>Verses: Ex. 20:16; John 8:44; Eph. 4:25; Col. 3:9; 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 0, 0, null, 'F-HB1oSwMwg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F-HB1oSwMwg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(658, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Angels?', '<p>The Bible says a great deal about angels, so there is no reason to be confused about who they are and what they do. Just as God created different kinds of physical beings, He also created different kinds of spiritual beings, and angels are one kind. They are powerful beings that deliver God&rsquo;s messages, serve God, and fight for Him.</p> <p>Verses: Job 1:6; Ps. 89:5; Zech. 5:9; Luke 2:13; Col. 2:18-19; Heb. 13:2; 2 Pet. 2:11; Jude 1:14; Rev. 22:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:50', 0, 0, null, 'DTNOGpINvEY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DTNOGpINvEY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 64, null),
(659, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Foul Language?', '<p>God is concerned about language because words have power. Obscene language comes from a place that attacks God and His creation. When we take the Lord&rsquo;s name in vain, we corrupt a spiritually-empowered name intended for blessing. Our words are meant to build people up, not tear them down.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:1-4; 4:29; Exod. 20:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:13', 0, 0, 'corruption', 'y0628qp6nc4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y0628qp6nc4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(660, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Soul?', '<p>God gave animation to the body through the soul. Biblically, the soul is identified as a person, the life of the body, and emotions or thoughts. Erroneous teachings say that animals do not have souls, that souls are immortal and that souls live on after death. Scripture clarifies these misunderstandings.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:10; 27:37; John 12:27; Gen. 1:20, 24, 29-30; Lev. 24:17-18; Ezek. 18:4; Matt. 10:28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:07', 0, 0, null, 'RsNzkt3tYZs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RsNzkt3tYZs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 133, null),
(661, 1, 'Lachish - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 20)', '<p>The Bible Lands Tour in 2000 visited the city of Lachish. A powerfully fortified city of the scriptures, Lachish has a remarkable history extending from Joshua to Hezekiah, to its defeat by the Assyrian General Sennacherib and ultimately its fall to the Babylonians. Excavations at Lachish have produced letters that record events and timely words from prophets.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 10:1-3; 2 Chron. 11:5-10; 32:1; Mic. 1:8-9, 13; 2 Kings 19:35; Jer. 34:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '30:55', 27, 20, null, 'R4IxUzvkMnk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/R4IxUzvkMnk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(662, 1, 'What does the Bible say about Ghosts?', '<p>The traditional view of what ghosts are is false. In truth, demons impersonate people and appear as ghosts so people become terrified. God&rsquo;s way is to give you hope in Jesus Christ and to deliver you from fear.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 9:5; Gen. 3:4; Job 4:12-18; 1 Sam. 28:19-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:41', 0, 0, null, 'osbiqugC1vk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/osbiqugC1vk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 59, null),
(663, 1, 'Being a Christian is like being a Pumpkin', '<p>This teaching, originally done around Halloween time, draws an analogy between a pumpkin and God&rsquo;s chosen believers. Just as we clean up the pumpkin, God cleans us up as well. Once the pumpkin is finished, the light glowing out from within reminds us of the light of God radiating out from within us for the world to see.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:08', 0, 0, null, 'BFEriIUr6go', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BFEriIUr6go/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(664, 1, 'The Revised English Version® (REV®) & Commentary', '<p>The Revised English Version (REV) was inspired by a need to have an easily-readable translation with accurate theology for young people. The REV is accessible on any device that connects to the internet and is complimented by a Commentary that explains difficult verses.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:32', 0, 0, null, 'Uvfb7p-O-TM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Uvfb7p-O-TM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(665, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Death Penalty? (Part 2)', '<p>God affirms the value of life by commanding the death penalty in Mosaic Law. Evil needs to be purged out of society in order to keep godly people safe. Some scriptures have clear instruction about crime and consequences, while others require understanding the context. Ultimately, it is God&rsquo;s perfect love and our obedience to His commandments that promote a healthy and safe society.</p> <p>Verses: Deut.19:18-19; Eccles. 8:11; Matt 7:1, 5, 24; 26:52; Luke 6:29; 22:36; Lam. 3:30; John 16:10; 14:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:44', 0, 0, null, '0AAK8uHm8KQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0AAK8uHm8KQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(666, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Death Penalty? (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching invites the listener to consider what the Bible says about national &ldquo;self-defense,&rdquo; personal self-defense, and social self-defense as it explores God&rsquo;s perspective regarding the death penalty.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 9:6; Exod. 20:13; 21:12, 14; Lev. 24:17; Num. 35:16; Deut. 19:11-13; 1 Tim. 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:24', 0, 0, null, 'rWPqWBU2WoM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rWPqWBU2WoM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 35, null),
(667, 1, 'Why is the Bible called The Bible?', '<p>The etymology of the word &ldquo;bible&rdquo; developed from some early writing materials, trade routes, and cultures. Enjoy this short but information-packed video to hear about the origins of the book we refer to today as the Bible.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:20', 0, 0, null, 'QCMjK0_VpY8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QCMjK0_VpY8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(668, 1, 'Good and Bad: Instruments of Righteousness', '<p>Being a Christian does not make our problems go away, but being a Christian gives us a different perspective for better understanding the world around us and our part in it. This teaching offers a perspective from the Apostle Paul&rsquo;s life about the many circumstances he endured as God revealed His perspective to him.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 6:3-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:53', 0, 0, null, 'tlQrkjqC3MI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tlQrkjqC3MI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(669, 1, 'Is Everything That Happens God&rsquo;s Will?', '<p>Good and bad things happen in our lives. Does it make sense that no matter what happens in this world, good or bad, only good will result? This teaching addresses what the Scripture has to say about this common misconception.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 10:22; Rom. 8:28; 1 Cor. 13:6-7; 2 Cor. 12:8-9; Eph. 5:1; James 1:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-10-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:52', 0, 0, null, '4bsfNpzBuWI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4bsfNpzBuWI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 79, null),
(670, 1, 'Beth-shemesh - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 19)', '<p>This on-location teaching describes the record of the Ark of God as it was moved from Shiloh to Beth-shemesh, captured by the Philistines, then returned by God to Beth-shemesh.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 15:10; 21:13; 1 Sam. 4:1-3, 5-11; 5:1-11; 6:1-16, 19-21; 7:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:33', 27, 19, 'religion', 'LGr2C7DE5V8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LGr2C7DE5V8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(671, 1, 'Pool of Bethesda - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 18)', '<p>Many disabled people were in and around the pool area of Bethesda on a Sabbath, yet Christ found just one man, spoke with him, and healed him. This on-location teaching describes the record of Jesus healing one certain disabled man at the pool of Bethesda.</p> <p>Verses: John 5:1-3, 5-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:10', 27, 18, null, '1Wb-aaU8xc4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1Wb-aaU8xc4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(672, 1, 'The Wall Peg of Love', '<p>This teaching emphasizes the importance of a wall peg in the ancient world to illustrate how the security of what was hanging from it depended on the sturdiness of the wall peg. The sturdiness of love gives meaning to all the things of God that hang from it.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:83; Isa. 22:20-25; Ezek. 15:1-3; Zech. 10:4; Matt. 22:35-39, 40</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:30', 0, 0, null, '96vc1s5PGl4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/96vc1s5PGl4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(673, 1, 'Mount of Olives  - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 17)', '<p>This on-location teaching is from the Mount of Olives, with a view of the area of the ancient Temple of Solomon. While capturing several practical differences between wisdom and godliness, this teaching gives extensive biblical detail concerning many significant historical and future events on the Mount of Olives.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 15:30; 1 Kings 11:1-8; 2 Kings 23:12-14; Zech. 14:1-9; Ezek. 47:1-11; Matt. 27:39-41; Lev. 4:1-12; Num. 19:1-9; Heb. 13:8-10; Ezek. 43:21; Neh. 3:31; John 19:19-20; 11:45-48; 19:17-18; Num. 1:2; Luke 19:37-38; 23:44-47</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:01:37', 27, 17, 'Crucifixion, Jerusalem, Sacrifice', '7IwGJbcOtdM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7IwGJbcOtdM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(674, 1, 'Wilderness of Judea - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 16)', '<p>With a view of the desert wilderness area of Judea, this on-location teaching highlights many practical lessons learned from the temptations of Christ. The annual weather and farming patterns in this area provide added understanding of the culture of biblical times. Astronomical events add depth to the scriptures concerning the birth of Jesus Christ in nearby Bethlehem.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 4:1-13; Ruth 1:1; Luke 2:1-18; Matt. 2:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '43:20', 27, 16, null, '5EiGpk56V9U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5EiGpk56V9U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(675, 1, 'The Obedience Model of Pleasing God', '<p>Which pleases God more: to know His will, or, to know and <em>do</em> His will? The knowledge model of pleasing God states that knowing what the Bible says pleases God. The obedience model states that it is the knowing and doing that pleases Him. The Creator of the universe wants us to be doers of the Word, not listeners only.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:47-50; 21:28-31; 28:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:47', 0, 0, 'Disciples', 'xLQ-KX4LQ48', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xLQ-KX4LQ48/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(676, 1, 'We Should Obey God', '<p>God wants everyone to obey His will because it results in blessings. Yet often we do not do what we know we should do. Jesus said, &ldquo;Why do you call me Lord, but don&rsquo;t do what I say?&rdquo; This video addresses this common human predicament and offers suggestions for overcoming our resistance to obeying God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 15:22; Luke 6:46; 1 Cor. 9:25-27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-09-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:08', 0, 0, 'Obedience, Sacrifice, Training', 'H-p4NDG7Aw0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H-p4NDG7Aw0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(677, 1, 'Christian Living - 5 Steps to Getting Back on Track', '<p>Sometimes we do not do something we know we should do. As an alternative to &ldquo;beating ourselves up&rdquo; about the missed opportunity, this teaching offers five steps to do better the next time: reproof, remorse, repentance, renouncing, and reordering our steps.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 7:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-08-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:00', 0, 0, 'sorrow', 'tVc7okb-zkk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tVc7okb-zkk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(678, 1, 'Mount Gilboa - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 15)', '<p>This is an on-site teaching about how God used Gideon, seemingly a nobody from a poor family, to defeat a large enemy army that was oppressing Israel. So that Israel would not boast in the victory being theirs alone, God orchestrated a strategy for Gideon to lead a mere 300 soldiers to attack in the middle of the night and bring about a great victory.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 6:1-40; 7:1-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '33:38', 27, 15, 'Baal, Asherah, Midianites, Amalekites, Jezreel, Fleece', 'TVgeT92o2Lo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TVgeT92o2Lo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(679, 1, 'Tel Jezreel - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 14)', '<p>This is an on-site teaching at the winter home of King Ahab and his wife Jezebel. Ahab and Jezebel conspired to murder Naboth and take his vineyard. After they did so, God spoke to Elijah who prophesied of their deaths. His successor Elisha then set in motion God&rsquo;s plan resulting in Jezebel&rsquo;s death and Jehu&rsquo;s becoming the next king.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 21:1-29; 2 Kings 9:1-27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '28:11', 27, 14, null, 'ZeXx2ax22T4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZeXx2ax22T4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(680, 1, 'Sermon on the Mount - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 8)', '<p>This is an on-site teaching about Jesus&rsquo; Sermon on the Mount. Although this sermon fills three chapters in Matthew, only Matthew 5:1-10 are covered here. Each of God&rsquo;s promises in that section is linked to Old Testament scriptures which document that these promises were not new, but prophesized, and will be fulfilled in the age to come.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:1-10; Isa. 1:21-31; 2:1-4; Ps. 37:1-3, 9, 11, 13, 16-19, 27, 37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '40:24', 27, 8, 'Beatitudes', 'swlL1HHLQgc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/swlL1HHLQgc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 32, null),
(681, 1, 'Scythopolis/Beth-shan - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 13)', '<p>This is an on-site teaching about the city of Beth-shan. Saul, the first King of Israel, fought with the Philistines, who killed him and his sons. Saul&rsquo;s beheaded body was staked to the hill side of Beth-shan, with the bodies of his sons. In honor of what Saul did earlier for the people of Jabesh-Gilead, soldiers of that city recovered the bodies and properly buried them.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 10:23, 24; 11:1-11; 31:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '27:25', 27, 13, 'Jonathan, Gilboa', 'hDYgpvTaC7M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hDYgpvTaC7M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(682, 1, 'City of Dan (2) - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 12)', '<p>The scriptures tell us that as a result of Solomon&rsquo;s abandoning God in his heart, the Kingdom of Israel was divided in two: the Northern Kingdom, Israel, and the Southern Kingdom, Judah. Though God would bless obedience, both kingdoms fell to sin. The Northern Kingdom under Jeroboam fell to idolatry, while the Southern Kingdom under Rehoboam fell to cruelty and unwise advice.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 11:9-11, 26-28; 12:16, 25-32</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:45', 27, 12, null, 'XIxc0Hx56MM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XIxc0Hx56MM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(683, 1, 'City of Dan (1) - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 11)', '<p>This is the historical record of the Danites&rsquo; lack of trust in the Lord. Though Joshua had allotted them the land west of Jerusalem, they chose idolatry, corruption, and disobedience; therefore, they forfeited the land which was their God-given inheritance. The lesson of the Danites is that if you do not walk in trust, but choose an ungodly life, you will find it hard to fulfill God&rsquo;s tasks.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 18:1-30; 1:34; Josh. 19:40, 49</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '25:46', 27, 11, null, 'jx9z1NGP6Vs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jx9z1NGP6Vs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(684, 1, 'Caesarea - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 10)', '<p>Caesarea Philippi was a lush geographical location caused by a spring coming from the nearby mountainous area. In this lovely location Peter identified Jesus as the Christ. A short time later, on Mt. Hermon, Jesus, Peter, James, and John experienced the event known as the &ldquo;transfiguration.&rdquo; This event prepared Jesus for his sacrificial crucifixion.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:13-20; 17:1, 2; Mal. 4:5, 6; Isa. 38:10; Ezek. 37:12; Luke 9:28, 29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:36', 27, 10, null, 'J1UzLa3cHCA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J1UzLa3cHCA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(685, 1, 'Capernaum - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 9)', '<p>Jesus began His ministry in Capernaum, a thriving city by the Sea of Galilee. From the beginning, Jesus taught about the kingdom of God with authority and power. As miracles followed him, his reputation spread. Central to Christ&rsquo;s message were commitment and faith. The &ldquo;faith in action&rdquo; of Christ&rsquo;s day is still applicable today.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 4:12-17; Mark 11:21-28; John 6:53-66; Luke 7:1-10; 10:13-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '28:47', 27, 9, null, '2nz6ZUYTmFU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2nz6ZUYTmFU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(687, 1, 'Our Sin & God&rsquo;s Mercy', '<p>From creation, God&rsquo;s mercy has been on display. Adam and Eve could have died after their disobedience, but God chose to lovingly cover their sin. Though Adam and Eve&rsquo;s covering for sin was temporary, we have been provided with a permanent covering from sin through the sacrifice of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:17; 3:17; Rom. 5:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-06-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:05', 0, 0, 'grace', '7iQNLvUbe-U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7iQNLvUbe-U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(688, 1, 'Are You On God''s Train?', '<p>Disappointment in our Christian walk may be due to our expectation that God is not doing things our way. Guess what? God is not our servant! When we choose to accept Him, obey Him, know Him and share Him, then we will find the Christian life exciting. Join in with what God is doing.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 5:13, 14; Gen. 1:28; 2 Cor. 5:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:05', 0, 0, 'servant, paradise', 'wZNpl_AgrAE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wZNpl_AgrAE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(689, 1, 'Tel Megiddo - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 7)', '<p>Tel Megiddo is where the Battle of Armageddon will occur. This on-site teaching examines various scriptures that give details of this extended campaign. Megiddo was also a significant place in the Old Testament. One important lesson in this teaching is that faithfulness to God now can profoundly affect us in the next life.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 63:1-3; Ezek. 39:1-16; Rev. 14:14-20; 16:12-16; 19:11-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:37', 27, 7, 'judgments, seals, trumpets, thunders, bowls, beast, prophet, army, anti-Christ, winepress', 't2j8MqFiktk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/t2j8MqFiktk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(690, 1, 'Mount Tabor - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 6)', '<p>The &ldquo;Fifth Gospel&rdquo;&mdash;the land&mdash;plays a big part in biblical history and understanding the Bible. This on-site teaching illustrates that by expounding the record of Judges 4 and 5. The Israelites were oppressed by the Canaanites and finally they cried out to Yahweh. Israel was victorious in an unanticipated way. The declaration near the end of this account is applicable in a Christian&rsquo;s life today.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 4-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '29:06', 27, 6, 'Jezreel, prophetess, Sisera, Canaanites', 'sw6cAKRcD4w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sw6cAKRcD4w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(691, 1, 'Nazareth - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 5)', '<p>Jesus first proclaimed that he is the Messiah in Nazareth. This on-site teaching examines two Gospel accounts separated by time and illustrates that the crowds&rsquo; responses did not change in spite of the many healings and miracles Jesus performed in other places. A lesson we learn is that God moves in ways the world does not expect.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 6:1-6; Luke 4:14-30; John 1:43-46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:49', 27, 5, 'Galilee, honor', 'GEGkApIAVzo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GEGkApIAVzo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(692, 1, 'Mount Carmel - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 4)', '<p>On-site at Mt. Carmel, this teaching gives historical information and background about the area. It demonstrates why understanding the &ldquo;Fifth Gospel&rdquo; &ndash; the land &ndash; unlocks the meaning of some scriptures. The primary focus of the teaching is examining the record of Elijah and the prophets of Baal, which holds an important lesson for believers today.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 17:1; 18:16-46; Song of Sol. 7:1, 5; Jer. 50:19; Amos 9:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '31:15', 27, 4, 'Jezreel, idols, sacrifice', 'FVA-fcuN6kU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FVA-fcuN6kU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(693, 1, 'Aqueducts at Caesarea Maritima - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 3)', '<p>This on-site teaching takes place at the aqueducts at Caesarea Maritima. Caesarea Maritima is where Cornelius, a Roman centurion and Gentile, and his family received the gift of holy spirit. We see how the Lord worked in both Cornelius and Peter&rsquo;s lives to bring about Peter&rsquo;s visit to Cornelius&rsquo; house. Peter realized there that the Church was forever changed.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 10:1-8, 23-46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:49', 27, 3, 'Gentiles, speaking, tongues, salvation, visions', 'yklT2ypIVss', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yklT2ypIVss/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(694, 1, 'Royal Palace at Caesarea Maritima - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 2)', '<p>This on-site teaching explains the background of this important New Testament city. The prison where the Apostle Paul was held for more than two years was near this royal palace. Paul went to Jerusalem in spite of guidance not to go and was captured and brought to Caesarea. There is a significant lesson for us in this account of Paul&rsquo;s life.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:22-24; 21:3-4, 7-15; 23:23-35; 24:1-27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '23:36', 27, 2, 'humility, prophecy, disobedience', '4ahiF36ldLI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4ahiF36ldLI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(695, 1, 'Amphitheater at Caesarea Maritima - Israel Tour 2000 (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching at the amphitheater in Caesarea Maritima explains the importance of the land of Israel as the &ldquo;Fifth Gospel.&rdquo; When we experience the land and culture, we gain deeper understanding of the biblical accounts and can better reflect on how to apply the lessons to our lives. This teaching focuses on the life of Philip the Evangelist.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 8:36-40; Acts 21:7-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:49', 27, 1, 'witness, rewards, kingdom', 'uSkPKrHfduc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uSkPKrHfduc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(697, 1, 'The Great Commission: Go, Make Disciples, and Teach', '<p>Jesus&rsquo; final instruction to his disciples was to go, make disciples of all nations, and teach them to obey all that he had commanded. This teaching explains what it means to be a disciple of Jesus and what to teach to others.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:37-40; 28:18-20; Luke 14:26, 33; John 8:31-32; 14:21</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p> <p>Suggested Keywords: followers, commandment</p>', '2012-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:20', 0, 0, null, 'sL0IgJBdEeA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sL0IgJBdEeA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(698, 1, 'How to Become a Christian', '<p>No matter what efforts people make to live longer on earth, they will inevitably die. However, God does not want anyone to die forever and offers the free gift of everlasting life. This teaching explains how anyone can accept this free gift and why accepting it works to produce life that lasts forever.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 1:3-4; John 3:16; Rom. 6:23; 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:47', 0, 0, 'atonement, sacrifice, confess, sin, death', 'DMzblR8YDQ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DMzblR8YDQ0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(699, 1, 'Summer Fest 2012: Fun in The Son', '<p>The event will be held at Camp Vision, Bloomington, Indiana and it officially starts on Thursday, July 12 and concludes on Saturday evening, July 14th. Registration will be open on Wednesday July 11 after 4:00pm.</p>', '2012-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '0:56', 0, 0, null, '-aYvcvjYx9A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-aYvcvjYx9A/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'announcement, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(700, 1, 'Live Video Teachings - Livestream.com/stfonline', '<p>To watch our free live video teachings go to Livestream.com/stfonline.</p>', '2012-03-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '0:24', 0, 0, null, 'MJg4-Pr5ZlI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MJg4-Pr5ZlI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'announcement, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(701, 1, 'Don''t Attack My Body!', '<p>As Christians, we don&rsquo;t want to be antagonistic toward other believers who may think or act differently. This teaching stresses the importance of loving each other in the Body of Christ and keeping the &ldquo;unity of the spirit in the bond of peace.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:3; Acts 9:4; Gal. 5:14-15; Eph. 4:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-03-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:58', 0, 0, 'Saul, Damascus, persecution', 'cmhu3t0HVl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cmhu3t0HVl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(702, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible (Metonymy)', '<p>Metonymy is a figure of speech employing the use of the name of one thing instead of the name of another. Examples from Scripture as well as from modern vernacular are explained. By studying the context and subject matter, we can recognize this figure of speech and more clearly understand the Word of God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 25:23; 2 Kings 6:5; Ps. 5:9; Lam. 3:7; Amos 4:6; Nah. 2:3; Matt. 10:34; Luke 24:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:06', 0, 0, null, 'WKyZ2rkHYFw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WKyZ2rkHYFw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(703, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible (Asyndeton)', '<p>The figure of speech Asyndeton is explained here. This figure is used when there is no word &ldquo;and&rdquo; between items in a list. Figures of speech in the Bible do not happen by mistake. They point to something important and place emphasis on what is being said.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 7:21, 22; 1 Cor. 3:10-13; Gal 5:22-23; 2 Tim 3:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:24', 0, 0, 'immorality, evil, pride, love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, meekness, self-control', '3CM09A9CZAw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3CM09A9CZAw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(704, 1, 'Figures of Speech Used in the Bible (Polysyndeton)', '<p>The figure of speech Polysyndeton is explained here. This figure is used when the word &ldquo;and&rdquo; occurs between each item in a list. A figure of speech is a legitimate grammatical device that God uses to bring special emphasis to points in His Word.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 22:9-10; Hag. 1:11; Luke 10:27; Eph. 4:31; 2 Pet. 1:5-7; Rev. 18:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:55', 0, 0, 'Abraham, Isaac', 'KCutNFhOd_Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KCutNFhOd_Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(705, 1, 'Figures of Speech used in the Bible (Antonomasia)', '<p>Antonomasia is a figure of speech involving a name change, which imports characteristics from one name or subject into another name or subject. We must pay careful attention to what is literal and what is figurative in Scripture and study the context in order to recognize figures of speech and what they convey.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 9:31; Ezek. 34:22-23; Mal. 4:5; Matt. 17:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, 'Elijah, David', '06KU6Hu8WK0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/06KU6Hu8WK0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(706, 1, 'Figures of Speech used in the Bible (Synecdoche)', '<p>Synecdoche is used when a part is put for the whole of something, or a whole is put for the part of something. By understanding the language of the Biblical world, we can more properly understand the Word of God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:19; 2 Kings 8:9; Pss. 1:1; 44:6; Isa. 20:2; Jer. 26:9; Matt. 3:5; John 21:7; James 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:35', 0, 0, null, 'DdjdvscbMJI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DdjdvscbMJI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(707, 1, 'It&rsquo;s Time to Grow Up (Part 2)', '<p>There are four distinct stages of Christian maturity: exploring Christ, growing in Christ, getting close to Christ, and Christ-centered living. Essential to each stage are the practices of being immersed in Scripture, developing spiritual relationships, and developing personal spiritual practices. This teaching explores how these practices relate to each stage of Christian growth.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, null, 'g-MT5UTQvDw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/g-MT5UTQvDw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(708, 1, 'It&rsquo;s Time to Grow Up (Part 1)', '<p>We are not to remain spiritual babies. God has designed us to grow physically, intellectually, emotionally, and spiritually. This teaching begins an exploration of the stages of Christian growth so that we can know how to become spiritually mature men and women.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:11-15; Col. 4:12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:13', 0, 0, null, '1_sAZJ6KHnw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1_sAZJ6KHnw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(709, 1, 'No Ordinary Child (Part 5)', '<p>You were not born to be ordinary, and God desires you to live as the extraordinary child He designed you to be. When we depend on ourselves and our own ability, there does not seem to be anything exceptional about us, but that changes as we grow in intimacy with God.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 6:15; 1 Sam. 15:11; 17:37; John 5:30; 14:10; Rom. 8:17; 2 Cor. 5:17; 1 John 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:01', 0, 0, null, '_U4ncYe_UFs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_U4ncYe_UFs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(710, 1, 'No Ordinary Child (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching discusses seven desires of the heart, ways that we perceive we are loved. Satan seeks to manipulate us into trying to have these desires met in ungodly, harmful ways; but there are also good and godly ways to manage these desires. This teaching clearly reveals how God instructs us to have our deepest needs met.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:17', 0, 0, null, 'Te1c1W5ta08', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Te1c1W5ta08/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(711, 1, 'No Ordinary Child (Part 3)', '<p>How does Satan manipulate us and cause us to see ourselves as mundane, and not uniquely special? Every human being is born with a desire for unfailing love, which God alone is able to provide. Satan would deny us this love, but we can recognize and effectively deal with his lies, so that each of us can be the extraordinary person God has made us to be.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 19:22; John 8:44</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:41', 0, 0, null, 'QNOetS1Guh8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QNOetS1Guh8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(712, 1, 'No Ordinary Child (Part 2)', '<p>God sees us as extraordinary and having great potential. What happens to us that makes us seem ordinary? There is a diabolical agenda against every human being, which is revealed in God&rsquo;s Word. Learn to recognize the devil&rsquo;s craftiness and how to deal with it in a way that will enable you to shine.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:25; 3:1, 7-13; Rom. 8:5, 7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:02', 0, 0, 'Crafty, Sin', 'X9A7d1H7sXk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X9A7d1H7sXk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(713, 1, 'No Ordinary Child (Part 1)', '<p>Moses&rsquo; mother saw that he was a goodly, fine child, and not ordinary. But is any child ordinary in the eyes of God? What happens that causes us to see ourselves as plain, rather than the extraordinary individual that God designed and made us to be?</p> <p>Verses: Acts 7:20; John 3:16; 1 Tim. 2:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:42', 0, 0, null, 't_Fdxoi2fW0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/t_Fdxoi2fW0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(714, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 14 - Appendix 2) - Baptism & Receiving the Holy Spirit', '<p>When you become saved, you are born again, and at that time you receive holy spirit. You are then able to manifest that spirit at any time. Sometimes, however, a born-again Christian may not manifest holy spirit immediately. Learn what prevents a believer from manifesting that spirit, and what to do about it.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 8:12-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:35', 28, 14, null, 'nW7bSnSfOGc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nW7bSnSfOGc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(715, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 13 - Appendix 1) - Baptism & Salvation: Mark 16:16', '<p>Water baptism was a symbol that pointed to the greater reality of the baptism in holy spirit. When a person believes in Christ, he is saved, and at that time he is baptized in holy spirit. Scripture does not support the idea that one must be water baptized in order to be saved.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 16:13-16; Luke 24:33-36; John 20:19-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:20', 28, 13, null, 'ZT3lVpc8DyI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZT3lVpc8DyI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(716, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 12) - The One Baptism for the Church', '<p>This teaching on Christian Baptism dispels the argument that the one baptism for the church today is water baptism. Our baptism today is baptism in holy spirit, which is receiving the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:5-6; 1 Cor. 14:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:44', 28, 12, null, 'dBRY-ytfqmA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dBRY-ytfqmA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(717, 1, 'Presenting Your Life to God as a Masterpiece', '<p>When a person accepts Jesus Christ as Lord, their life becomes as a blank canvas on which they present their life to God and Jesus Christ as a masterpiece. We are all to do our best to live a life worthy of our calling.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1; 2 Cor. 5:10; Eph. 4:1; Phil. 1:27; 2 Tim. 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:49', 0, 0, null, 'nvTZiOJf3EA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nvTZiOJf3EA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(718, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 11) - Ignoring Pentecost & Paul&rsquo;s Revelation', '<p>This teaching explains why, after receiving revelation regarding baptism in holy spirit, the Apostle Paul was unable to change the course of the tradition of water baptism already established in the church.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:5; 1 Cor. 1:17; Gal. 1:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:40', 28, 11, null, '4PWv-HZanqg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4PWv-HZanqg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(719, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 10) - Water Baptism in the Early Church', '<p>This teaching explains that in the early years of the Church, the apostles continued with ceremony of water baptism as Jesus Christ taught them. They had not yet received the revelation given to the Apostle Paul regarding baptism of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:19; Acts 1:5; 2:38; 8:12, 26; 21:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:38', 28, 10, null, '40bWpEJJY94', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/40bWpEJJY94/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(720, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 9) - Baptism, Holy Spirit, & Salvation', '<p>This teaching explains that the moment you are saved, you are baptized with holy spirit without the need for water baptism. This is illustrated by looking at the record of Cornelius and his family in the Book of Acts.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:38; 10:36, 39-40, 44-48; 11:14; Eph. 1:13; 1 Cor. 12:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:41', 28, 9, null, 'AN3zThr-I0k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AN3zThr-I0k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(721, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 8) - Baptism from Symbol to Reality on the Day of Pentecost', '<p>J</p> <p>This teaching explains that after the Day of Pentecost, water baptism, which is symbolic and administered by people, changed to a greater and real baptism given by God, the baptism of the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Isa. 44:3; John 7:37-39; Acts 1:8; 2:1-4, 33; 1 Cor. 12:7; 2 Cor. 5:17</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:51', 28, 8, 'trinity, saved, born-again', 'N7hQyAcJ6v8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N7hQyAcJ6v8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(722, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 7) - The Baptisms of John the Baptist & Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching explains that John the Baptist baptized by immersion in a public location, which is unlike the quiet cleansing ceremony of the Old Testament. His baptism ceremony represented repentance and the resurrection to new life.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 7:29-30; John 3:22; 4:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:29', 28, 7, 'Pharisees', 'JDEFOPjW--w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JDEFOPjW--w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(723, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 6) - The Historic Roots of Water Baptism', '<p>This teaching takes a look into the Old Testament ceremony of physical cleansing, which many cultures used to establish cleansing in the sight of God. This cleansing became an important ceremony for the Jews who were scattered after King Nebuchadnezzar burned the temple in Jerusalem.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 15:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:23', 28, 6, 'ceremony', 'sKSKoIgqNrA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sKSKoIgqNrA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(724, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 5) - The Parallel Between Sacrifice & Water Baptism', '<p>This teaching shows through Scripture that the importance of biblical rituals such as sacrifice and water baptism was not in the ritual itself, but in the revealing of the heart of the people who were being obedient to God.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Ps. 51:16-17; Hosea 6:6; Amos 5:21-24</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:03', 28, 5, 'rituals', 'YRs_ZiUPGU0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YRs_ZiUPGU0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(725, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 4) - Water Baptism, Symbolic of the Greater Baptism', '<p>This teaching explains that just as the Old Testament ritual of animal sacrifice points to the greater reality of Jesus Christ&rsquo;s sacrifice for our sins, water baptism is symbolic of the greater reality of receiving the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Heb 9:1, 9, 10</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:31', 28, 4, 'rituals', 'u3hrl9AZc9w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/u3hrl9AZc9w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(726, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 3) - Is There a Right Way to Baptize?', '<p>Various denominations differ in how they water baptize. Some immerse; some sprinkle. Scripture doesn&rsquo;t say how John or Jesus&rsquo; disciples baptized. Considering the &ldquo;mikvehs&rdquo; or &ldquo;ritual baths&rdquo; of biblical times, immersion was likely, but affusion, meaning pouring on one&rsquo;s head, is a possibility. Neither can be proven from Scripture.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 28, 3, null, '8HJ9sz6WNKU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8HJ9sz6WNKU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(727, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 2) - The Meaning of the word Baptism', '<p>The words &ldquo;baptism&rdquo; and &ldquo;baptize&rdquo; are common in Greek literature and are used in the Old Testament, the Gospels, and the New Testament. Baptism applies to contact with a substance like water, oil, blood, or even honey. In Scripture, it is either by water, as done by John the Baptist, or by holy spirit, as occurred on the Day of Pentecost and after.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 32:15; Mark 1:8; 44:3; Acts 2:17, 18, 33; Titus 3:5, 6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:00', 28, 2, null, 'xX6tF2hpzck', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xX6tF2hpzck/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(728, 1, 'Christian Baptism (Part 1) - The History & Doctrine of Christian Baptism', '<p>Two types of baptisms are mentioned in the Bible: baptism in water and baptism in holy spirit. When it comes to water baptism, some denominations baptize by immersion, some by pouring, and some by sprinkling. This introductory video gives some history of church baptismal practices.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:24', 28, 1, null, 'rWzAwA58jV8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rWzAwA58jV8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(729, 1, 'Introduction to Figures of Speech in the Bible', '<p>One legitimate writing technique authors use to emphasize a point is to employ a figure of speech. There are many different figures of speech, but some are quite common in the Bible. For example, metonymy&mdash;using one noun for another&mdash;is frequently used in Scripture. An example is when &ldquo;Jacob&rdquo; is used to refer to all the people of Israel.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:34', 0, 0, 'Simile, Metaphor, Hyperbole', 'WhuGQQRldEI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WhuGQQRldEI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(730, 1, 'Seeing the Qualities of God in the Physical World', '<p>If we see lipstick on the rim of a water glass, we know that someone&rsquo;s lips have been there. In the same way, seeing beauty in a flower, the design of a leaf, the function of photosynthesis, or the strength of a tree trunk reflects God&rsquo;s attributes in His creation. Therefore, upon looking around your environment, remember that nature reflects aspects of its Creator.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:02', 0, 0, 'light, darkness, life, death, serving', 'Vig4-V9X_fo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vig4-V9X_fo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(731, 1, 'Taking Time to Get Dressed - Putting on the Armor of God', '<p>In the morning, we put on clothes in preparation for the day. In a similar way, we should dress our minds with spiritual thoughts including being clothed with humility, with prayer, with thanksgiving, and with praise to God for His blessings and daily provisions.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 50:14; 100:4; Rom. 13:14; Col. 3:10; 1 Pet. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:05', 0, 0, 'holiness, righteousness, thanks', '0HhxdvrlHio', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0HhxdvrlHio/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(732, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 6)', '<p>People are capable of being wise, foolish, and wicked. This teaching examines one of the five types of fools in Scripture, the &ldquo;nabal.&rdquo; This person is the extreme form of wickedness and works against God. He has gone past the mere words of a mocker and takes intentional harmful actions that no amount of warning, reproof, or intellectual reasoning can dissuade.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 14:1; 53:1; 74:18; Isa. 32:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:11', 35, 6, 'ungodliness, self-centered, cunning, discernment', 'ZsFOpiewZSs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZsFOpiewZSs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(733, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 5)', '<p>From God&rsquo;s perspective, when a person chooses to act wickedly, he is wicked. This teaching examines a type of wicked person, the mocker or scorner. This person has intentional hurt and destruction in his heart. This teaching elaborates on this kind of wicked behavior and how to respond to it.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 9:7-8; 11:9; 13:1; 14:9; 15:12; 18:3; 21:24; 28:24.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:12', 35, 5, 'mouth, arrogance, boasting, contempt, deceit', 'eJL_Eq3TWGM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eJL_Eq3TWGM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(734, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 4)', '<p>People are capable of being wise, foolish, and wicked. One of the five types of fools in Proverbs, and the most frequently described, is the &ldquo;stubborn fool.&rdquo; This person easily slides into wickedness and evil behavior. He knows what he should do and regularly chooses not to do it. This teaching elaborates on this kind of foolish behavior and how to respond to it.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 10:23; 14:7, 16; 17:10; 18:2, 5; 26:3-5, 11; 29:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:09', 35, 4, 'foolish, willful, arrogance, pride, rebellion, punishment, reproof, consequences, anger, temper', '65uUkya6pLU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/65uUkya6pLU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(735, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 3)', '<p>People are capable of being wise, foolish, and wicked. One of the five types of fools in Proverbs is the &ldquo;unreasonable fool.&rdquo; This person knows the proper thing to do but he does not want to do it. This teaching elaborates on this kind of foolish behavior and how to respond to it.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 10:13; 12:15; 14:3; 15:5, 14; 20:3; 22:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:52', 35, 3, 'foolishness, pride, discernment, judgment, discipline, rod', 'Vpemk4KmN08', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vpemk4KmN08/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(736, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 2)', '<p>People are capable of being wise, foolish, and wicked. God instructs us to have discernment about people we interact with and how we respond to them, and to have this same awareness about ourselves. There are five Hebrew words translated &ldquo;fool&rdquo; in Proverbs. This teaching focuses on the characteristics of one of them, the &ldquo;simple fool.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 19:7; Prov. 7:7; 14:15; 19:25; 22:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:10', 35, 2, 'instruction, discipline, deception', 'yNzGY-dTHxY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yNzGY-dTHxY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(737, 1, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked (Part 1)', '<p>A proverb can be defined as &ldquo;words to rule life.&rdquo; This teaching begins a series from Proverbs of three groups of people and addresses God&rsquo;s view of a wise person. To be wise is to live a disciplined, prudent life and do what is right. The mark of maturity is discernment and being able to recognize good and evil.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:1-3; 3:21; 10:13; Isa. 5:20; Heb. 5:14</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:31', 35, 1, 'personification, judgment, humility, meekness, truth', 'GxLlR_x-6TY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GxLlR_x-6TY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(738, 1, 'Context in Scripture - Understanding the Word of God', '<p>By extracting verses from the Bible without considering their scriptural scope, context, and vocabulary, people can and do make the Bible say just about anything they want, sometimes intentionally, sometimes unintentionally. When reading the Bible, God deserves our heart, time, and effort to make sense of its meaning, with a view toward helping others come to trust in it.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 31:49; Ps. 14:1; Jer. 18:11; 29:11; Rom. 5:16, 18; 8:1; 2 Tim. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-10-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:34', 0, 0, 'God-breathed, inspired', 'jCRTHUV2uH8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jCRTHUV2uH8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(739, 1, 'Standing on the Firm Foundation', '<p>The Bible tells us that Jesus Christ is the foundation on which we should build our lives. It is our responsibility to stand on that firm &ldquo;rock.&rdquo; This teaching examines three things that prevent us from continuing to stand, and Satan&rsquo;s role in them. If we want to accomplish what God has planned for us, we must keep standing.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 3:10-11; 2 Cor. 1:8-9; Eph. 6:13; James 1:2, 12-15; Rev. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:04', 0, 0, 'pressure, temptation, endurance, perseverance, trials, slander, anxiety, accountability', 'rOopzT56n8s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rOopzT56n8s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(741, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 6) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>God reveals the nature of the enemy with a variety of appellations or the terms which He applies to him. As the accuser, the enemy is relentless in accusation. As the slanderer, he uses inflammatory language to undermine, hurt, and tear down. As the destroyer, he afflicts. Our best defense is knowledge that gives us strength and the ability to stand on God&rsquo;s high ground.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 4:1; John 8:44, 10:10; Rev. 12:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:44', 36, 6, 'Slanderer, Destroyer, Accuser', 'slMfTePq684', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/slMfTePq684/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(742, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 5) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>God reveals the nature of the enemy with a variety of appellations or the terms which He applies to him. As the deceiver, the enemy uses lies and manipulation to sow deception in an attempt to convince us not to stand on the promises of God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:4; Isa. 5:20; John 8:44; 2 John 1:7, Rev. 20:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:11', 36, 5, 'Temptation, Deception', 'V3KFjlayPco', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V3KFjlayPco/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(743, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 4) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>God reveals the nature of the enemy with a variety of appellations or the terms which He applies to him. As the tempter, the enemy is always working to manipulate the environment to influence us through the world. We need to have a plan to resist steadfastly.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Luke 4:1-2</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:22', 36, 4, null, 'dfPtyIjTB7s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dfPtyIjTB7s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(744, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 3) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>God reveals the nature of the enemy with a variety of appellations or the terms which He applies to him. &ldquo;Satan&rdquo; comes from the Greek word <em>santana</em> which means &ldquo;adversary&rdquo; or &ldquo;one who works in opposition.&rdquo; The devil is constantly trying to thwart and oppose the plans and promises of God.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 2:3-4; 2 Tim. 3:8a</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:05', 36, 3, null, 'URnECVEE44w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/URnECVEE44w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(745, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 2) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>God reveals the nature of the enemy with a variety of appellations or terms which He applies to him. This teaching discusses the appellation &ldquo;god of this age&rdquo; or &ldquo;god of this world&rdquo;. The use of these terms emphasizes the devil&rsquo;s sphere of influence and how he works in the world to develop systems by which he seeks power and worship.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Isa. 14:12-14; Matt. 4:8-9</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:19', 36, 2, 'lucifer', 'OtshIN97ADY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OtshIN97ADY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(746, 1, 'The Nature of the Enemy (Part 1) - Spiritual Battle', '<p>The New Testament Epistles reveal that we are in a spiritual battle and our adversary is Satan. Much about this enemy and his methods is revealed to us. We are assured that through Jesus Christ we have power and authority over this enemy and when spiritual adversity comes, we can be overcomers.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 2:11; Gal. 5:1; 1 John 4:4; Rom. 8:37; Col. 1:13; Luke 10:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:23', 36, 1, 'Slavery, Darkness, Kingdom', 'v_7X4fRneX4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/v_7X4fRneX4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(747, 1, 'Free Will - What does the Bible say? - Part 2', '<p>God created mankind with free will to make decisions, including choosing salvation. However, some verses in John 6 seem to say that only those God draws to Him can be saved. Studying the context of these verses shows that God is actually calling us constantly to accept Jesus as the Messiah and Lord in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: John 6:25-45</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:56', 0, 0, 'choice', '4WUG27lIq9M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4WUG27lIq9M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(748, 1, 'Free Will - What does the Bible say? - Part 1', '<p>Many verses state that God gives people free will to make decisions, and He always encourages them to make choices that lead to life now and in the future. Those who believe in predestination hold that God predetermines our eternal destiny and translate verses in support of that belief. This teaching offers alternatives on what the Bible really says about free will and salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:19; Ezek. 33:11; Acts 13:44-48</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:32', 0, 0, 'choice', 'zC13itBJ_dM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zC13itBJ_dM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(749, 1, 'What Does It Mean to Be a Son of God?', '<p>Upon confessing Christ as Lord and believing that God raised him from the dead, we become sons of God with the gift of holy spirit. As we adopt our new nature, it affects how we act, what we do, and how we think about life. We no longer need to worry about earning God&rsquo;s love. We are empowered to speak and act as ambassadors for Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 3:26, 27; 1 John 3:2; 2 Cor. 5:20; John 14:13; Rom. 8:37</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:34', 0, 0, 'Salvation, Wholeness, Righteousness', 'JSZuzxi9I_Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JSZuzxi9I_Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(750, 1, 'Dealing With Evil - Standing firm in righteousness', '<p>The sword that will separate what is truly good from what is truly evil is the Word of God. The account of Jesus healing a man with a withered hand and the reaction of the religious leaders, as well as other Gospel records, are lessons that encourage us to take a stand against evil.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 9:7; 17:23; 25:26; Matt. 28:13; Luke 6:6, 7, 11; John 8:27, 41-44</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:44', 0, 0, 'Sabbath, Pharisees, Devil', 'k2zm_kTA1rs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k2zm_kTA1rs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(751, 1, 'How to Love God - An action, not just a feeling', '<p>How do we show God that we love Him? Loving God is more than just a feeling, it is demonstrated through action. When we obey God&rsquo;s commands and serve His people, helping one another, we are loving God.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 22:5; Matt. 22:37-39; Heb. 6:10; 1 John 5:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-07-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:31', 0, 0, 'commandment', 'RnRFNgPy5v4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RnRFNgPy5v4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(752, 1, 'Keep Praying - The Power of Prayer - What does the Bible say about Prayer?', '<p>Prayer is an essential part of the Christian&rsquo;s relationship with his heavenly Father. The word &ldquo;pray&rdquo; means &ldquo;ask.&rdquo; Many verses are cited in this teaching, showing us the power of prayer along with numerous things that God instructs us to pray for.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 4:6; 1 Thess. 5:17-19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:36', 0, 0, null, 'lSR_B9ta6PQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lSR_B9ta6PQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(753, 1, 'Are you living a life of Good Fruit? Living a Godly life', '<p>God has called us to produce righteous fruit such as love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, meekness, and self-control. It takes conscious effort and making deliberate choices to bear good fruit. Our good fruit demonstrates that we are disciples of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: John 15:8, 16, 17; Rom. 7:4; Gal. 5:19-23</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-06-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:38', 0, 0, 'appointed, spirit, Kingdom', 'vujijS0WdGU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vujijS0WdGU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(754, 1, 'Submission In Christ - Obeying the Lord', '<p>When we are instructed to obey other people, it is always in light of the fact that our primary obedience is to God. This teaching explains the governing phrase &ldquo;in the Lord&rdquo; where the Bible instructs wives, husbands, children, and servants to submit to one another in the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 5:29; 1 Cor. 15:22; Eph. 5:8; Col. 3:18-22; 4:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-06-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:45', 0, 0, 'light, walk, master', '3WQN1C2-EFE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3WQN1C2-EFE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(755, 1, 'Ambassadors for Jesus Christ', '<p>This exegesis of Colossians 4:5 and 6 teaches us how to walk with wisdom toward those outside the community of faith and what it means for our speech to be &ldquo;with grace&rdquo; and &ldquo;seasoned with salt.&rdquo; As ambassadors for Jesus Christ, we want to make the most of every opportunity to reach people for the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 4:5, 6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-05-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, 'witnessing', 'BAKTFlmf0ZM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BAKTFlmf0ZM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(756, 1, 'God is Trying to Raise Up Heroes', '<p>A hero is someone who puts aside his self-interest and comes to the aid of another. God is in the business of training heroes. When our concerns involve the things of God and the Body of Christ, and therefore others, we become heroes.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 7:32; 12:24, 25; Phil. 4:6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-04-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:41', 0, 0, 'prayer', 'vYC8TLajwOQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vYC8TLajwOQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(757, 1, 'Sin is Crouching at the Door', '<p>This sharing discusses ways we can master sin in our lives. By having confidence in God, being honest, confessing our sin, and staying connected with godly people, we will become stronger and learn to rule over sin.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 4:7; Luke 22:28-32; James 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-04-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:07', 0, 0, 'temptation', 'pfogZ0ZFHfA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pfogZ0ZFHfA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(758, 1, 'Blind Spots', '<p>Because of our human condition, we are susceptible to becoming desensitized to the darkness surrounding us. Often we develop blind spots and give a &ldquo;pass&rdquo; to wayward behavior, world systems, bad habits, or pride and hate. But with the Lord and the light of God&rsquo;s Word, we can stand against the darkness in the world.</p> <p>Verses: John 12:36, 37, 40; 2 Cor. 4:4; Obad. 1:3; 1 John 2:11; Ps. 146:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:39', 0, 0, null, 'qx_etecTffo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qx_etecTffo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(759, 1, 'When the Christian Life gets Tough: Stand', '<p>Making a commitment to honor God in our daily lives can be a joy or it can be a challenge. When your way grows weary and lonely, do not blame God, but instead recommit yourself to faithfulness, love, and service to our Lord and you will find life&rsquo;s blessings in the end.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 15:16-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-03-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 0, 0, 'troubles', 'gjW1B6rnrFk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gjW1B6rnrFk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(760, 1, 'Good Grief (Part 2)', '<p>When an individual goes through a traumatic event, the pain can be beneficial if you learn from it. Turn to God in these difficult times and invite Him into the grieving process. Ask Him to teach you something from the experience.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 34:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-03-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:18', 0, 0, 'submission', 'KSbJqtlwvq8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KSbJqtlwvq8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(761, 1, 'Good Grief (Part 1)', '<p>There is nothing good about traumatic events, but God can work in that event to bring about something good. The grieving process is what God has designed to get us past the trauma and pain. Rather than suppressing or denying grief, allow God&rsquo;s deep inner healing to help you through the pain.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 6:67; 1 Sam. 15:35; Esther 4:1, 3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-03-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:56', 0, 0, 'sorrow', 'AF4R8wEwOzE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AF4R8wEwOzE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(762, 1, 'Deal With Things As They Are', '<p>God told us from the beginning that life would be difficult. When life goes wrong, often our response is emotional and negative. That negativity hurts us and those around us. God&rsquo;s Word gives us keys to happiness: practice self-control, focus on the blessings, and be thankful.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 11:3; Gen. 3:17; 2 Cor. 10:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:23', 0, 0, null, 'q77xR-qjVjc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q77xR-qjVjc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 75, null),
(763, 1, 'Fight Through Discouragement - Trust in God', '<p>Every human experiences discouragement. Though discouragement can be debilitating, if we stay faithful to prayer and reading the Bible, God will encourage us. The biblical record of Moses provides us a colorful picture of overcoming discouragement.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:10-13, 18; 4:1, 10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-02-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, 'trust, persevere', 'EJITfHn9FT0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EJITfHn9FT0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(764, 1, 'Communion: Sharing a Meal', '<p>Mealtime is becoming a lost tradition in our culture. This is unfortunate since it was meant to be a social event for connecting and sharing our lives while enjoying the fruits of God&rsquo;s creation. Scripturally, meals have great significance. The Passover meal foreshadowed the coming Messiah, while the Communion meal celebrates the sacrifice of Jesus Christ for us all.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 19:25; 1 Cor. 11:36</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:45', 0, 0, null, 'O9EZokAtxkE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/O9EZokAtxkE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(765, 1, 'Everyone Needs a Father', '<p>Every human being needs a father, not only in the physical world, but also in the spiritual realm. Our Heavenly Father seeks to care for the fatherless. We were all &ldquo;orphans&rdquo; in need of a spiritual father. God has made a way for all of us to be a part of His family through His son, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 10:17, 18; 24:17, 19-21; Ps. 10:14; 68:4, 5; John 14:15, 17, 18; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-02-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:52', 0, 0, 'love', 'ZNEIZ2bbmds', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZNEIZ2bbmds/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(766, 1, 'Let Your Light Shine - Part 3 - Live for God, Be an example', '<p>Jesus told us to &ldquo;let your light shine&rdquo;; therefore, we need to rid ourselves of light-blockers. Sin, isolation, doctrinal error, and lack of prayer prevent God&rsquo;s light from shining in the world. When the moon faces the sun, it reflects its light fully; when we face the Son, we reflect his light fully to a dark world.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:6, 7; Heb. 10:24, 35; Eph. 5:9; John 3:21; Rom. 13:11, 12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-02-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 0, 0, null, 'W0GkVt15PRk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/W0GkVt15PRk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(767, 1, 'Let Your Light Shine - Part 2 - Seven Deadly Sins - Is There Anything Blocking Your Light?', '<p>Sin is the big &ldquo;blocker&rdquo; of not allowing our spiritual light to shine. This teaching talks about sins that we can control but often choose not to, such as when we are exhorted to speak words of encouragement to others but speak belittling words instead, and how to address what blocks our light.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> John 3:19-20</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 0, 0, null, '9yOovNKFzNA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9yOovNKFzNA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(768, 1, 'Let Your Light Shine - Part 1 - You Are the Light of the World', '<p>Light is significant to the wellbeing of mankind. This is true in the physical world but is perhaps even more important in the spiritual realm. God is light and when we have Christ, we are light. In this dark world, how bright is your light?</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:14-16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:37', 0, 0, null, 'wPET-k34KuA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wPET-k34KuA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(769, 1, 'Is There a Place of Eternal Torment?', '<p>The parable in Luke 16 concerning Lazarus and the rich man is often misunderstood as literal rather than a story. This teaching is an explanation of the parable as a teaching tool and illustrates that every parable has a main point. In this case, the point is not that people burn in hell forever.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Rev. 20:14</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> Joshua Anderson</p>', '2011-01-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:39', 0, 0, null, 'WqH898UYyKs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WqH898UYyKs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(770, 1, 'How Christian Holidays Should Be Celebrated', '<p>Many Christian holidays have pagan origins and influences. Since separating truth from tradition is an important concern, this teaching discusses how Christians should celebrate various holidays, guided by the dictates of their hearts.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 14:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:53', 0, 0, 'Christmas, Halloween, Easter, Holidays', 'OnotvnFe4rM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OnotvnFe4rM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(771, 1, 'Keeping God First in Our Lives', '<p>God wants to be first in our lives. For example, many times we don&rsquo;t thank Him for the day until we go to bed at night, instead of thanking Him for the day He has given us first thing in the morning.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 150:1-6; Mal. 1:6-10; 2:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:05', 0, 0, null, 'PHXxUukI21A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PHXxUukI21A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(772, 1, 'Help Each Other', '<p>As children of God, we are born into a family, and families help each other. Culturally, we are less inclined to help each other and get involved in each other&rsquo;s lives than in biblical times, but scriptures give us guidance to overcome that and help each other overcome problems.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 15:22; 27:6, 9; Eccles. 4:9-13; 8:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-12-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, 'Friendship', '7phjNynKHMg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7phjNynKHMg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 18, null),
(773, 1, 'If You Pray - Obey!', '<p>This teaching uses the life of Paul on his third missionary journey as an example of how, if we pray for and receive specific guidance, we must obey it. God told Paul not to go to Jerusalem, but he went anyway to the great hindrance of his prayers and his ministry.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:23; 21:4,12,14; Rom. 15:30-31; 1 Cor. 16:3-4; 2 Cor. 8:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:47', 0, 0, null, 'F1s0gxkdZwE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F1s0gxkdZwE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(775, 1, 'Work Hard to be Holy', '<p>&ldquo;A little folly outweighs wisdom and honor.&rdquo; We should strive to have a balance between wanting to better ourselves for God and recognizing that God says we are already loved and acceptable in His sight.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 10:1; Matt. 5:48; 2 Cor. 13:5; 2 Tim. 2:15; 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-12-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:54', 0, 0, null, 'RYXuopft17s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RYXuopft17s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(776, 1, 'The &ldquo;Good Old Days&rdquo; – Being Thankful', '<p>The Bible instructs us that it is not wise to ask &ldquo;why are former days better?&rdquo; It is built into the nature of life that we grow in wisdom and in our ability to cope with challenges. We take on more responsibility, making the former days seem easier. The Bible gives us ways to manage our increased responsibility wisely.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 5:13; 7:10; Matt. 6:33; 13:22; Phil. 4:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-12-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:22', 0, 0, null, 'Bc1QvFmMR0Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Bc1QvFmMR0Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(777, 1, 'Looking for Happiness? Seek God', '<p>This teaching discusses the source of true happiness. Happiness does not come from our possessions or fun, but rather comes from our relationship with God. Life with God is full of meaning; life without God is meaningless.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 1:2, 3, 13,18; 2:1-4, 8, 10, 11, 14, 16, 17, 25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:29', 0, 0, null, 'n3CwHRPozKY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/n3CwHRPozKY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(778, 1, 'Focused vs. Distracted - Keeping God first', '<p>Godliness does not happen by accident. It requires concerted effort. Distractions often hold Christians back from attaining godliness. This teaching discusses two parables that Jesus taught to illustrate the importance of focusing on the things of God and the result of doing so.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:44-46; 19:23-24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:14', 0, 0, null, 'mLbYlF-9cl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mLbYlF-9cl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(779, 1, 'How Much is Owed? Forgiveness, Grace, Mercy', '<p>Unforgiveness often short-circuits the life of a believer. It leads to anger, which makes peace hard to find. This teaching uses a parable that Jesus told to illustrate how much God has forgiven us of and how much we owe others in forgiveness, grace, and mercy.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:15, 21-31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-10-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:46', 0, 0, 'love, debt, sin, talent', 'zVLu37mwHU4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zVLu37mwHU4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(780, 1, 'Is Jesus Crying Over You?', '<p>Jesus Christ burst into tears when he saw Jerusalem before him when he was about to enter the city. The record in Luke tells us why. It is easy to see Jesus&lsquo; heart for people. He has not changed. Does he have reason to cry over you? You can find out here and if so, choose to do something about it.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 19:28-29, 35-41</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-09-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:42', 0, 0, 'bitterness, sin, fear, doubt, Messiah, discouragement, victorious', 'xwJpiyOc2XM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xwJpiyOc2XM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(781, 1, 'Will We be Rewarded or Suffer Loss?', '<p>You may have confessed Jesus as Lord, but have you really made him Lord of your life? When Christians stand before him at the judgment seat, we want to be holy and blameless. This sharing looks at how we can position ourselves to be rewarded by our Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:28-29; 14:19-12; Eph. 1:4; Heb. 11:25-26; 1 John 4:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:50', 0, 0, 'devotion, submission, trials, testing, love', '0afxyTjoRT0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0afxyTjoRT0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(782, 1, 'The Judgment Seat of Christ', '<p>The heart of this teaching is to motivate Christians to be the best they can be for Jesus Christ, to conform themselves to his image, and get rid of habitual sin. Scripture indicates that we will stand fully exposed before the judgment seat of Christ and we will give an account for everything we did in this life.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:18; Rom. 5:1-2; 2 Cor. 5:9-10; 1 John 2:28</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:03', 0, 0, 'confidence, shame, punishment, sanctification, holiness, perseverance', 'zZ6C1aRzMkU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zZ6C1aRzMkU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(783, 1, 'Hope Fuels Our Passion', '<p>In order to accomplish what Jesus Christ wants for our lives, we must have hope to fuel our passion. Many things that happen in the world can bring discouragement. We must read the Bible and find the promises there for us. Hope is the anchor of our souls.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 13:12; Rom. 15:4, 13; 1 Thess. 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:00', 0, 0, 'encouragement, endurance, evangelism', 'jbVSPl03Z-Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jbVSPl03Z-Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(784, 1, 'Understanding the Bible in its Cultural Context (Part 3)', '<p>This teaching discusses various ways that honor and shame were important in the Eastern culture in biblical times. By understanding eastern culture we can begin to grasp the richness of what the Bible is saying, especially in the example of Jesus Christ&rsquo;s being called the Head of the Body.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; Exod. 3:5; Esther 8:15; Job 19:9; Rom. 16:20; 1 Cor. 15:25; Eph. 1:22.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:25', 40, 3, 'crown, honor', 'gR12LXrx12M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gR12LXrx12M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(785, 1, 'Understanding the Bible in its Cultural Context (Part 2)', '<p>When we read the Bible, we need to understand the social implications of the culture to get the richness of the meaning. This teaching focuses on honor and shame as examples of prevalent dynamics of Eastern culture.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 18:7-8; Matt. 19:16; 22:16; Luke 3:23; 4:22; John 1:45-46</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:33', 40, 2, 'Jesus, Nazareth, David, Goliath', 'QhlmrjeqPtc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QhlmrjeqPtc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(786, 1, 'Understanding the Bible in its Cultural Context (Part 1)', '<p>When a reader and a writer have different social systems, there can be misunderstanding about the meaning of what is written. The Bible is an Eastern book with social values, culture, and customs that are very different from Western thinking, and must not be interpreted through a Western mindset.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:31', 40, 1, null, '3EHkoowC1jk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3EHkoowC1jk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(787, 1, 'What does the Bible say about the Devil and the Spiritual Battle?', '<p>As Christians, we need to know the Devil&rsquo;s ways and not be ignorant of his devices. This teaching briefly looks at some of the Devil&rsquo;s devices. Jesus Christ has given us power and authority to fight in the spiritual battle. We need not be intimidated, but need to be prepared.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 4:5-8; John 8:44; 10:10; 2 Thess. 2:4; Jam. 4:7; 1 Pet. 5:8; Rev. 20:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:56', 0, 0, 'worship, accuser, deceiver', 'D3EgY01sGWU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/D3EgY01sGWU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(788, 1, 'Various Names and Titles of the Devil', '<p>God does not want us to be ignorant of who the devil is and how he behaves. This teaching discusses the many titles and names given to the devil, which give us clues to his identity and characteristics.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 4:3; 10:25; 12:24-27, 31; Mark 3:28-29; Luke 12:10; John 12:31; 2 Cor. 4:4</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:29', 0, 0, null, 'MWKheu3Mkb4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MWKheu3Mkb4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(789, 1, 'Forgiven: But what about habitual sin?', '<p>Our sins are forgiven when we believe in Jesus Christ and confess our sins. The way to avoid habitual sin is to fix our minds on God&rsquo;s word daily and resist committing the same sin over and over again. Can we be forgiven over and over? Yes, we can each time, but our goal should be to change our habits.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 8:46-50; Rom. 10:9-10; 2 Cor. 7:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:18', 0, 0, null, 'rezDc5Q39Ts', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rezDc5Q39Ts/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(790, 1, 'Can a Christian be Possessed? (Part 3)', '<p>This video discusses symptoms of demonization. We learn how calling on the name of Jesus Christ will cause the adversary to flee. We have the full authority, as Jesus Christ did, to stand up to the devil. We must &ldquo;put on the whole armor of God,&rdquo; so that we can &ldquo;stand against the wiles of the devil.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:11; 1 Pet. 5:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:40', 59, 3, null, 'sxzA_89luhc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sxzA_89luhc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(791, 1, 'Can a Christian be Possessed? (Part 2)', '<p>Signs of demonization in Christians are discussed in this video. The devil tells us lies to influence our behaviors. He constantly badgers us to do wrong, and to feel wrongly about ourselves and others. It is very important that we &ldquo;put on the whole armor of God,&rdquo; so that we can &ldquo;stand against the wiles of the devil.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Job 1:6; Ezek. 8:5-6; Eph. 6:12; James 4:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:25', 59, 2, null, '8KiBlG9qb6Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8KiBlG9qb6Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(792, 1, 'Can a Christian be Possessed? (Part 1)', '<p>We need to have a healthy perspective of the spiritual truths regarding whether or not a Christian can be possessed by a demon. This video is an in-depth discussion of the words &ldquo;possession&rdquo; and &ldquo;demonization.&rdquo; It also discusses the ministry of discerning of spirits and how to help those who may be demonized or possessed.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 9:32; Luke 4:18-19; 10:19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:48', 59, 1, null, '5V471obb27c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5V471obb27c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(793, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Rejoices In The Truth (Part 13)', '<p>When there is peace between people, love is part of the equation. We are encouraged to walk in obedience to our Lord and to love one another as we love ourselves. God rejoices when we love one another as he commands.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:14; Prov. 23:15-16; 24:17; 3 John 1:3.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:15', 39, 13, null, 'Ijg1NFLDvC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ijg1NFLDvC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(794, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Does Not Delight in Evil (Part 12)', '<p>Love does not delight in evil. God is love, light and goodness, among other things, and has no part in evil. We must not rejoice in the suffering of those who persecute us. Instead we are encouraged to walk in love and forgiveness.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 24:5-7; Prov. 6:16-19; Ps. 119:163; 1 Thess. 5:21-22</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:27', 39, 12, null, 'uuCLclNgFTA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uuCLclNgFTA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(795, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Does Not Keep a Record of  Wrongs (Part 11)', '<p>If we live in the love of God, we will not keep a record of how others have hurt or wronged us. God commands us to walk in love. We can learn to forgive every time someone&rsquo;s offenses against us come to mind. This frees us from pain and bitterness that burden our lives, enabling us to live in peace and love.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:10-18; 1 Cor. 13:4-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:12', 39, 11, null, 'eVd80e7Guo0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eVd80e7Guo0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(796, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love is Not Easily Angered (Part 10)', '<p>Love is always about others. If we work to serve others and not focus on ourselves, we will walk in love. We must be slow to anger and always focus on God. If God is the center of our lives, we are less likely to be provoked, and we will be focused on service.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 4:28-30; 1 Cor. 13:4-5; Eph. 6:4; James 1:19-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-08-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:20', 39, 10, null, 'jafBxTEyL9E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jafBxTEyL9E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(797, 1, 'Come to Jesus; He has Paid the Price', '<p>The wages of sin is death, but we are called to Jesus who paid the ultimate price that we may be saved and have life in the kingdom with Jesus and God. Each of us has a choice - life or a second death. We can have life in the kingdom or be separated from God.</p> <p>Verses: Job 26:7-8; 36:27-28; Eccles. 1:7; Matt. 7:24; 10:9-10; 11:28; 14:11; 27:3-4; Rom.10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-08-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:54', 0, 0, null, 'waeQgs1havE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/waeQgs1havE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(798, 1, 'Having a Temptation Plan', '<p>Why not treat temptation like an emergency or disaster and be prepared with a plan when it strikes? In this teaching, nine keys against temptation are discussed. You can beat temptation and obey God!</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 39:12; Ps. 119:13, 59, 115, 146, 173; Prov. 3:5-7; 4:19; 14:12; 16:2; Jer. 17:9-10; Matt. 4:1-11; 16:23; 1 Cor. 6:18; 2 Cor. 10:5; Heb. 4:15-16; James 1:14; 4:7; 2 Pet. 2:8; 1 John 1:9-10.</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2010-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:04', 0, 0, 'sin, evil, self-awareness, adversary, pray', 'EF1Dg_6eP8g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EF1Dg_6eP8g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(799, 1, 'Developing a Heart of Service', '<p>Because of the great love God has for us, we are obligated to love one another. This teaching defines two perspectives of God&rsquo;s love and gives examples of Jesus perfectly mirroring God&rsquo;s love. We, too, can love the way Jesus did by developing a heart of compassion rather than indifference, which is key to developing a heart of service.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 103:13; Isa. 49:15; Jer. 31:20; Matt. 14:14; 20:34; Luke 7:12; 2 Cor. 1:3-4; 1 Pet. 4:10; 1 John 4:11-12, 20</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:54', 0, 0, 'comfort, miracles, healing, heart', 'UZ6o-fQB5W0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UZ6o-fQB5W0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(800, 1, 'The KJV Only Controversy: Understanding The Vocabulary (cont&rsquo;d.) (Part 4)', '<p>In the more than 400 years since the King James Version of the Bible was written, the English vocabulary has changed. In order to understand and enjoy what this version says, we need to understand the meaning of the words at the time. A number of verses and words are reviewed, giving past and current vocabulary meanings.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:29; 13:1; Lev. 2:1; Num. 13:17; Judg. 12:14; 1 Sam. 27:10; 1 Kings 11:1; Prov. 22:29; Jer. 4:22; 24:2; Matt. 6:31; 19:14; Luke 19:13; 1 Thess. 4:15; 2 Tim. 3:6; Titus 2:14; Heb. 4:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:11', 26, 4, null, 'pTmSAIvccDI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pTmSAIvccDI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(801, 1, 'The KJV Only Controversy: Understanding The Vocabulary (Part 3)', '<p>In the more than 400 years since the King James Version of the Bible was written, the English vocabulary has changed. In order to understand and enjoy what this version says, we need to understand the meaning of the words at the time. A number of verses and words are reviewed, giving past and current vocabulary meanings.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 41:5; Josh. 9:5; Judg. 3:29; 1 Sam. 8:12; 20:40; Isa. 1:13; Matt. 9:17; Acts 1:8; 21:15; 28:13; Rom. 1:13; 12:16; 1 Cor. 1:29; 2 Cor. 5:17; Phil. 1:27; 4:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:08', 26, 3, null, 'NCiFtG0tvu8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NCiFtG0tvu8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(802, 1, 'The KJV Only Controversy: Versions and Revisions (Part 2)', '<p>This segment of a 4-part series discusses the various Bibles from which the King James Version comes and the multiplicity of revisions of the version itself. It is also demonstrated that in the 1638 revision of the King James Version, the translators themselves indicated they were unsure of some of the meanings of the words.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 19:2; Matt. 14:30; Acts 5:7; Rom. 11:8; Eph. 4:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:33', 26, 2, null, 'Nszjqu7mDFo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Nszjqu7mDFo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(803, 1, 'The KJV Only Controversy: Greek Manuscripts (Part 1)', '<p>Some people teach that the King James Version of the Bible is the only translation that should be read. This first segment of the 4-part series discusses the various redacted Greek manuscripts on which the King James Version is based. Support is given for reading new translations of the Bible based on the more numerous, better, and sounder Greek manuscripts available today.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:10', 26, 1, null, 'ftdYhrqum8s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ftdYhrqum8s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(804, 1, 'You Are Absolutely Forgiven', '<p>The scriptures incorporated in this teaching are an encouraging reminder of God&lsquo;s forgiveness and His great love toward us. Anyone who has confessed Jesus Christ as Lord is completely forgiven by his sacrificial blood. This teaching also addresses sins committed after a person is born-again and how to accept forgiveness.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 103:1-4, 11-12; 130:2-5; Matt. 26:28; Eph. 1:7-8; Col. 1:14; 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:04', 0, 0, 'sin, redemption, mercy, grace', 'KIKz_p0MmfQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KIKz_p0MmfQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(805, 1, 'Things to Consider Before You Buy a Bible', '<p>The Bible is God-breathed and life-giving. We should want to read it. A number of factors should be considered when selecting a Bible to buy. The suggestions touch on different types of Bible translations as well as including a tip regarding the King James Version.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 27:3; 41:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 0, 0, null, 'ySDVuToDQ6g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ySDVuToDQ6g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(806, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: The Biblical Trumpet', '<p>The better we can mentally picture what life was like during the times of the Bible, the more we will enjoy reading it. Learning the customs of biblical cultures helps. Often, the English word translated &ldquo;trumpet&rdquo; is the Hebrew word &ldquo;<em>shofar</em>&rdquo;. In this series segment, two types of shofars are shown and explained. At the conclusion, we are able to see God&rsquo;s heart regarding our praise to him.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 6:6; Judg. 6:34; Ps. 150:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:14', 40, 21, 'horn, music', 'Srgrc-GdNfE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Srgrc-GdNfE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(807, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Is Not Rude (Part 9)', '<p>In 1 Corinthians, Paul addressed the improper behavior of the Corinthian believers in their meetings. They did not act with the love of God but were instead rude to each other. In this sharing, behaviors that demonstrate impropriety are compared with godly, loving behaviors.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:20; 13:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:00', 39, 9, 'honesty, decency, character', '28xnJYd5TR0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/28xnJYd5TR0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(808, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Is Not Proud (Part 8)', '<p>We all have a tendency to act pridefully, caring more for ourselves than others - sometimes even when we think we&rsquo;re being loving. The love of God is never prideful but is always devoted to others. When we live in God&rsquo;s <em>agape</em> love, we live seeing ourselves and others as God sees us.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 16:5; Obad. 1:3; Mark 12:30-31; Rom. 12:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:01', 39, 8, null, 'KFu9298Ryso', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KFu9298Ryso/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(809, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Does Not Boast (Part 7)', '<p>What does your personal &ldquo;thermometer&rdquo; register when you feel a tendency to embellish an accomplishment? This teaching shares some great tips on recognizing personal and cultural tendencies to boast or exaggerate. When we live in God&rsquo;s <em>agape</em> love, we do not seek attention for ourselves but rather we work toward helping others.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:4; 2 Cor. 10:17; 1 Pet. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:46', 39, 7, null, 'zw3RrXODFWs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zw3RrXODFWs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(810, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love Does Not Envy (Part 6)', '<p>In Paul&rsquo;s letter to the followers of Jesus in the wealthy port city of first century Corinth, God lets us know eight truths about what love does <em>not</em> do. One of those truths is the absolute absence of envy. When we live in God&rsquo;s <em>agape</em> love, we are thankful for what God has blessed others with.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:4-6; 1 Sam. 17:28-29; 18:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:47', 39, 6, null, 'kKV9tycpEfQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kKV9tycpEfQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(811, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | What Is Love? (Part 3)', '<p>Four separate Greek words for the one English word <em>love</em> are discussed for a clearer understanding of what love means from God&rsquo;s perspective. What motivates you to turn toward God? What motivates God to care for you? Discover in this teaching a particular category of love greater than feelings or emotions that motivates both God and man.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 10:37; John 5:20; 1 Cor. 13:4-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-07-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:33', 39, 3, null, 'hUNBjcTmj8Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hUNBjcTmj8Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(812, 1, 'How to Read the Bible', '<p>Libraries are full of books but God only wrote one book. Here are some helpful hints for reading the Bible in order to understand what God wants for our lives. Take a few minutes to hear how you can better enjoy reading the Bible.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:07', 0, 0, null, 'UfMv4xzR2sI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UfMv4xzR2sI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(813, 1, 'Overview of The New Testament', '<p>Jesus spent a lot of time reading and studying all the Scripture available to him. He highly encourages us to do the same, and we have more written Scripture today than he did during his life. Take a few minutes to hear about the unique perspective of each of the four Gospel accounts of the life of Jesus, the many records of the first Christians, and a glimpse of our future with Christ.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Hebrews 7:19, 22; 8:6; 9:23; 10:34</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:51', 0, 0, null, 'Xav-S6sHhMI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Xav-S6sHhMI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(814, 1, 'The New Testament is the New Covenant', '<p>What is the difference between a testament and a covenant? Why is the page separating the Old Testament from the New Testament located between Malachi and Matthew in our Bibles? What is a covenant, and what is our part in the New Covenant? As Christians we should know the answers to these questions, and this teaching is a great start.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 24:4-8; Luke 22:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:57', 0, 0, 'blood', 'si5RyDI0-P4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/si5RyDI0-P4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 23, null),
(815, 1, 'Speaking In Tongues: How to Do It (Part 4)', '<p>Continue your quest to learn how to speak in tongues with this teaching. As you speak, trust God to give you the words. God is such a loving Heavenly Father; He will always help you in just the way you need. You can speak in tongues; this teaching will help you, and God will provide the words.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 14:2,5; Acts 2:4; James 4:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:01', 43, 4, null, 'hKqyiVuDMeE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hKqyiVuDMeE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(816, 1, 'Speaking in Tongues: What It Is For (Part 3)', '<p>Are you looking for scriptures that address the purpose of speaking in tongues? Listen to this teaching to deepen your understanding of this intimate communication with God and the many benefits of speaking in tongues.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:11; 1 Cor. 12:3; 14:2, 5, 14, 15, 17, 22; 1 Thess. 5:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:17', 43, 3, null, 'nptK7vYy0yA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nptK7vYy0yA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(817, 1, 'Speaking In Tongues: What It Is (Part 2)', '<p>This video looks at what speaking in tongues is, where the language comes from, who can do it, how it is manifested, and why it is important for the Christian believer to speak in tongues.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:33, 38; 1 Cor. 12:3, 7; 13:1; 14:5, 18; 1 Thess. 5:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:14', 43, 2, null, '-3N3hmaHLTE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-3N3hmaHLTE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'not in doc', 1, 24, null),
(818, 1, 'Speaking in Tongues: What it is not (Part 1)', '<p>There are many misconceptions about what speaking in tongues really is. This confusion is a result of looking to the physical world in an attempt to understand and explain something that is spiritual. Speaking in tongues is spiritual and must be understood by studying God&rsquo;s spiritual book, the Bible.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:8-12; 14:2; 1 Thess. 5:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:04', 43, 1, null, 'lEJCpOEuw-g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lEJCpOEuw-g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(819, 1, 'The Wisdom Model of Living Life: A Key to Being Successful', '<p>Making wise choices is essential to living a successful life. God tells us over and over in the Bible not only to be wise, but how to be wise. Unfortunately, while many Christians have been taught to have faith, few have been taught how to be wise.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:2; 4:7; 6:6; 24:27; Luke 1:17; 2:40; Gal. 6:7; Eph. 1:17; 5:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:13', 0, 0, 'Fool', 'PaRsBSLC7Js', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PaRsBSLC7Js/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(820, 1, 'Watch What You Are Thinking', '<p>It is possible to live a holy life, and the Bible teaches us how. We must be vigilant about what we allow into our minds. In His Word, God teaches us what to avoid and what to do and think about instead. This is what enables us to keep our hearts pure.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:23; Rom. 1:21; 1 Cor. 15:33; 2 Cor. 10:5; Phil. 4:8; James 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:08', 0, 0, null, '1exP1bQE1TI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1exP1bQE1TI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(821, 1, 'How to Guard Your Heart', '<p>If we want to rid ourselves of problem behaviors and attitudes in order to live a godly life that is a blessing to ourselves and others, we must purify our hearts. In this video, we learn that God not only expects us to do so, He teaches us how we can.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:23; Mark 7:20-23; 2 Cor. 10:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:02', 0, 0, null, 't76MGI2J6BM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/t76MGI2J6BM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(822, 1, 'How to Read the Bible: Easy tips', '<p>The pointers taught in this video will help you learn how to read and become familiar with the Bible. You will be surprised at how simple it is! With these tips, the Bible becomes very readable, uncomplicated, and exciting. You will find that, indeed, there is life in the Word of God.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 0, 0, null, 'cQhHDYkgECM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cQhHDYkgECM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(823, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love is Kind (Part 5)', '<p>The Greek word &ldquo;chresteuomai&rdquo; means &ldquo;lifting burdens,&rdquo; and is translated into English as &ldquo;kind.&rdquo; A detailed study of what this looks like in application reveals specific actions we can take as Christians to be genuinely loving.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 5:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-06-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:30', 39, 5, null, 'VO3QkkLqNZw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VO3QkkLqNZw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(824, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | Love is Patient (Part 4)', '<p>The word &ldquo;patient&rdquo; in 1 Corinthians13:4 is the Greek word &ldquo;makrothumeo&rdquo; and means &ldquo;long suffering,&rdquo; or &ldquo;long to get hot,&rdquo; in other words, putting up with people for a long time. The love of God is a &ldquo;doing&rdquo; love, not a sentimental love. Learn more about godly patience in this video.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:34-35; 1 Cor. 13:4; 2 Cor. 6:5-6; 1 Thess. 5:14; 2 Tim. 4:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-06-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:25', 39, 4, null, 'DmEaQ9QLap0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DmEaQ9QLap0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(825, 1, 'Evangelism Lessons from Acts 17', '<p>This teaching covers a couple lessons in evangelism, including: when the spirit of God is stirred within you, do not quench it by sitting idly, and how to use the wisdom God gives you to take action. In this record from Acts we learn that, while conflict is sometimes unavoidable, the Apostle Paul worked hard to present the gospel in a way that was not offensive.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 17:16-34</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:05', 0, 0, null, 'SnZoIqscf0s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SnZoIqscf0s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(826, 1, 'Dedicated to God, Not to a Denomination', '<p>Most people are content to go to their church and accept what they are told to believe. We have an obligation to honor God by diligently seeking the truth, which is in the book He wrote, the Bible. If we seek, we will find, and can believe with confidence. This builds true unity in the Church.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:24, 33; Luke 10:27; John 4:23; 1 Cor. 1:10-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 0, 0, null, '0yxHjhowo9E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0yxHjhowo9E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(827, 1, 'Kindness - Let''s stop the insults & unkind words', '<p>We live in a very unkind culture where harsh words and insults are often rewarded rather than condemned. Yet kindness is a command of God, and we will be held accountable by Him for the words we speak. We bring honor to God as we clothe ourselves with kindness.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:29; 5:1-4; Col. 3:12; 4:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:00', 0, 0, null, 'aEtpPNfg1OE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aEtpPNfg1OE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(828, 1, 'What Does the Bible Say About Cremation?', '<p>While the Bible describes what was done with dead bodies in various cultures, it provides no specific guidance for what to do with dead bodies. General principles apply, including being respectful and proceeding with love for the deceased and survivors. We are exhorted to make the most of our time when we are alive, for when death comes, life ceases in every way until we are resurrected.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 31:12; Gen. 2:19; Eccles. 9:10; John 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:35', 0, 0, 'Burial', 'MLzOVtd7y6o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MLzOVtd7y6o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(829, 1, 'Joy Comes from the Lord', '<p>Everyone desires joy in his life. Some seek it through external means, but when circumstances change, joy leaves. Lasting joy comes from within and is anchored in the hope of what God does for us &mdash; past, present, and future.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 4:6, 7; 16:8-11; Prov. 14:12, 13; Phil. 4:4; James 1:2; Gen. 39:20; Heb. 12:2; 1 Thes. 4:13-14; John 13:16, 17</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Tench</p>', '2010-05-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:40', 0, 0, 'Folly', '12sXEg-LzOI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/12sXEg-LzOI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(830, 1, 'Why Study the Bible?', '<p>The Bible is a priceless book given by God to mankind so they may know how to live life and be eternally blessed. It&rsquo;s a big book and will take time to read. Learn the principles and keys that will make your Bible-reading time satisfying.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, null, '7WWDrda2-Vw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7WWDrda2-Vw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(831, 1, 'Our Identification with Christ: What happened to Jesus, happened to us!', '<p>The Book of Romans states that God declares righteous the person who has faith in Jesus. How does that work? Since the wages of sin is death and all have sinned, then we should be &ldquo;toast!&rdquo; However if we, by faith, accept Jesus&rsquo; death and resurrection as atonement for our sins, then we have been cleansed of sin and made righteous in God&rsquo;s eyes.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 6:1-9, 23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 0, 0, 'Baptized, Grace, Buried, Raised, Crucified', 'c10B74vYaH8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/c10B74vYaH8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(832, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Muddied Spring', '<p>The Bible is a book about an eastern culture. Readers from a western culture may not understand some eastern terminology or figures of speech. Proverbs 25:26 is one such case where a muddied spring is used as a simile for a righteous person who compromises his values. When that happens, his character is tarnished and others are disappointed.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:26; 2 Chron. 12:14; 2 Tim. 3:12; 1 Cor. 9:26, 27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:10', 40, 20, 'Fountain, Well, Discipline, Disappointment', 'CqMtJW0X1HQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CqMtJW0X1HQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(833, 1, 'God is Not an Angry God, He is Not Mad at Mankind', '<p>God is loving and righteous. Mercy, grace, forgiveness, patience, and compassion reflect His core nature. However, He is also righteous, which means there are times when people&rsquo;s bad behaviors bring God&rsquo;s judgement upon them. We are exhorted to imitate God&rsquo;s love in word and deed toward others, but we don&rsquo;t have to tolerate bad behavior.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:8; Rom. 3:25; Deut. 31:16, 17; 1 Kings 11:9; Mark 3:5; Eph. 4:31, 31; 5:1; Rom. 5:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, 'Atonement, Covenant, Imitator', '1qAGzJ43S8Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1qAGzJ43S8Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(834, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | The Manifestations Require Love (Part 2)', '<p>In the Body of Christ, people have different ministries and giftings given by God. As important as these are, if they are not practiced in love for others, their impact is diminished. The actions or words still may be a blessing to others, but since God looks at the heart of the giver, if the actions are not done with selfless intentions, God gives no personal rewards for that action.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-05-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:40', 39, 2, null, 'bLs0hS99Ngs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bLs0hS99Ngs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(835, 1, 'Love: The More Excellent Way | The Greatest of These is Love (Part 1)', '<p>In the Body of Christ, people have different ministries and giftings given by God. As important as these are, if they are not practiced in love for others, their impact is diminished. God&rsquo;s <em>agape</em> love toward us, as demonstrated by Christ, is our model for how to live and interact with others.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:27-30; 13:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:00', 39, 1, null, 'b09FJk6PW24', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b09FJk6PW24/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(836, 1, 'Compassion Brings Comfort', '<p>God is the father of compassion and comfort. Jesus, being the image of God, acted out of compassion when feeding the hungry, healing the sick, and casting out evil spirits. When compassion stirs within us, we should act to comfort people from the pressures and pain present in their lives. Jesus is our model to act compassionately.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 1:3, 4; 4:4; Ps. 103:8; Heb. 1:3; Matt. 14:12-14; 15:30-32; 20:30-34; Mark 1:40-42</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-05-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 0, 0, 'Grace', '3NCS0JyJceU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3NCS0JyJceU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(837, 1, 'No Room for Idols', '<p>Whatever we place ahead of what God wants of us is an idol, be it behaviors, objects, or positions that demand our focus. Power, titles, money, pride, emotions, and beauty can all be idols. An idol reveals itself when, if threatened, it provokes anger, or if lost, causes despair. God loves us unconditionally and He wants us to love Him above all.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 18:18-22; Deut. 6:5; Ps.51:10; 86:11, 12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-05-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:03', 0, 0, 'Idolatry, Serve, Heart', 'q7HelKSo8e4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q7HelKSo8e4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(838, 1, 'Emotional Heart Disease', '<p>People in the world and in the Christian Church are suffering from emotional heart disease, a condition caused by a cold, hard-hearted attitude towards others. In contrast, God&rsquo;s love protects, is kind, is hopeful, is truthful, and is unconditional. When people truly grasp how much God loves them, then they will demonstrate His love to others.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4,5; John 3:16,17; Rom 5:8; 8:38,39; 1 Cor. 13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-05-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:21', 0, 0, null, 'AJi7nofC0JA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AJi7nofC0JA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(840, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Godly Wisdom', '<p>Wisdom is overlooked in today&rsquo;s culture as a virtue; however, in the biblical world, it was priceless. Godly wisdom is &ldquo;the application of knowledge through discipline.&rdquo; Modern translators compare wisdom with rubies, but a true Hebrew translation would compare wisdom with coral: a reddish-orange stone that was rare and highly valued in biblical culture.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 3:13-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:34', 40, 19, null, '3pJqt-hDP2A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3pJqt-hDP2A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(841, 1, 'Jesus Christ, Our Atoning Sacrifice', '<p>Scripture tells us that God is love, but along with His love, He is just. Knowing &ldquo;God&rsquo;s nature,&rdquo; we discover that He found a way to deal with our sinful nature in a just manner. Through atonement brought by the blood of His son, Jesus Christ, God lovingly reconciled us to Himself.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:9; Rom. 3:23-25; 1 John 4:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, 'forgiveness', '5gmixcVfJho', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5gmixcVfJho/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(842, 1, 'Is God a bloody God?', '<p>This teaching refutes the claim that the Christian God is a &ldquo;God of blood&rdquo; and explores why God required sacrifice. His Word tells us that &ldquo;the wages of sin is death,&rdquo; but God set up a plan for His people to be able to live eternally in harmony, enjoying the richness of His creation.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 14:12-14; Rom. 6:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:49', 0, 0, 'scapegoat, substitute, blood', 'RXsE0RcukrY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RXsE0RcukrY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(843, 1, 'Tips for Teaching the Bible', '<p>Teaching God&rsquo;s Word is a privilege and should encourage discussion. It is best if the teaching is robust with an accurate presentation of the Word of God and prepared with a focused purpose. The goal is for the hearers to be blessed, to enjoy, to participate, to learn, and to live God&rsquo;s Word.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:07', 0, 0, null, 'IvYL-nwBIcc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IvYL-nwBIcc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(845, 1, 'Making Time For God', '<p>Often worldly activities get in the way of spending time with God or living in ways that please Him. Jesus said, &ldquo;Where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.&rdquo; God is only interested in where your heart is. We need to simplify our lives so that things that have eternal value take precedence in our daily choices.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 5:13; Matt. 6:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-04-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:11', 0, 0, 'treasure', 'i3-bjrL7gWI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/i3-bjrL7gWI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(846, 1, 'You Can Never Go Back', '<p>The Bible tells us multiple times to be thankful in every situation. What makes us unthankful? The culprit is our thinking habits. When we think about the past, we tend to see things out of perspective. When we focus on the future, we miss living in the present. Controlled, healthy thinking lives in the &ldquo;now.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 16:1-3; 1:11; 3:7; Col. 3:15-17;</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:25', 0, 0, 'self-control', 'fJt78NfS69E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fJt78NfS69E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(847, 1, 'The Spiritual Battle: Don&rsquo;t Be Ignorant of Satan&rsquo;s Devices', '<p>As Christians, we are warned not to be ignorant of Satan&rsquo;s schemes. Satan uses deception, manipulation, and control against Christians who are not alert. Though his schemes are many, be prepared for these two contrasting devices: 1) believing Satan does not exist, and 2) assigning him too much credit.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 2:8-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:08', 0, 0, 'deceive', '5IIKqwDuq8U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5IIKqwDuq8U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(848, 1, 'God works with us in four areas: Pride, Fear, Unforgiveness, Ungodly habits', '<p>This teaching identifies four areas that prevent us from living out the promises of God. God is always trying to work with us so that we can learn to replace ungodly habits with godly habits.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:14-15; Rom. 8:5; Eph 4:22; Col. 3:13; Heb. 11:6; 1 Pet. 5:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-04-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, null, 'r_Rx4z3y0GA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/r_Rx4z3y0GA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(849, 1, 'Developing a Community Commitment Statement', '<p>A commitment statement is a tool to help you organize and give boundaries and direction to your small church group. This sharing includes tips on how to find the purpose of your group and determine what you would like to accomplish for the Lord.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-04-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:47', 0, 0, null, 'awrxunvKQg4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/awrxunvKQg4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(850, 1, 'Characteristics of a Godly Community', '<p>Forming a small group creates community and fosters a sense of belonging. In this sharing, aspects of Christian practice from the Bible demonstrate how to form a godly community in which people are blessed.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; Acts 1:8; Rom. 15:7; Eph. 4:15, 32; Col. 3:9, 13; 1 Thess. 5:14-15; 1 Tim. 2:4; James 4:11; 5:9, 16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-04-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:32', 0, 0, 'mercy, humility, confidence, honesty', '7-faJQnrnto', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7-faJQnrnto/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(851, 1, 'Jesus Christ - A Sin Offering', '<p>Some Bible versions say that Jesus became sin. This study of the Greek word &ldquo;<em>hamartia</em>&rdquo; shows that there is a more accurate translation that gives a much better understanding of 2 Corinthians 5:21. Jesus Christ died in our place as a substitute and offering for our sin so that we could stand righteous before God.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 29:14; Lev. 4:24; 2 Cor. 5:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 0, 0, null, 'gN6krtlLn2o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gN6krtlLn2o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(852, 1, 'The Last Week of Jesus Christ&rsquo;s Life: A look at Jesus&rsquo; attitude during the last 7 days of his life', '<p>Jesus Christ, even knowing that he was going to be tortured and die, focused on others. During his final days, he healed people and taught them so they could know he was the Messiah and they could be saved. What a wonderful example for us to live for other people like Jesus did.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 18:35-43; 19:9-10, 41, 45, 47</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:33', 0, 0, null, 'm0UP-mTdWbg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m0UP-mTdWbg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(853, 1, 'Jesus Christ - Our Approach Offering', '<p>In the Old Testament there were many rules involving altars and sacrifices that had to be observed before anyone could approach God. In the New Testament, Jesus Christ was the sin offering that brought us near to God. Now we can approach God and come into His presence at all times.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 1:1-2; Num. 1:51; 3:10; Rom. 6:23; 2 Cor. 5:21; Heb. 10:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-04-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, null, 'U-nuf40KuEQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U-nuf40KuEQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(854, 1, 'Easter: Some history behind our Christian Holiday', '<p>This teaching looks at the history of the Passover and Feast of Unleavened Bread. Early Christians celebrated the Passover until the Apostle Paul received revelation that Christians did not have to keep the Feasts. Some of the history behind the Easter Holiday is reviewed, including a declaration at the Council of Nicaea in 325 A.D.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 12:1-2; Acts 12:4; Col. 2:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-04-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, null, '0erEuRr7l1M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0erEuRr7l1M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(855, 1, 'Keys to Trusting in God', '<p>This sharing gives three keys that help us trust in God. (1) Learn and understand God&rsquo;s character. (2) It is God&rsquo;s will for us to trust in Him. (3) Be open to God&rsquo;s suggestions.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 34:6; 2 Kings 5:9-14; Ps. 22:5; 11:17; Prov. 11:28; John 15:13; Rom. 8:35; Heb. 11:6; 1 Pet. 5:7</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Preston</p>', '2010-03-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:06', 0, 0, null, 'ofscete-Mq8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ofscete-Mq8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(856, 1, 'Let''s Persevere! Let''s Endure!', '<p>This encouraging message gives keys to inspire us to run the race with perseverance and endurance, sharing examples of the greatness of God and how those who have gone before us lived their lives in faith, love, and hope.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 66:1-2; 1 Thess. 1:3; Heb. 10:35-36; 11:22; 12:1</p> <p>Teacher: Charlie Preston</p>', '2010-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:50', 0, 0, 'humility', '35St_sBA6vU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/35St_sBA6vU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(857, 1, 'Be Great in the Kingdom of Heaven!', '<p>This message encourages us to come to the Lord with meek and humble hearts, hearing and doing what he says, so that we will be able to effectively teach others. By practicing humility and mercy, we will become great in the Kingdom of Heaven.</p> <p>Verses: Hosea 6:6; Matt. 5:19; 9:9-13; 12:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: Charlie Preston</p>', '2010-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:50', 0, 0, 'Beatitudes', 'cemIcEj8qjQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cemIcEj8qjQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(858, 1, 'How Best to Build a Closer Relationship with God', '<p>We are to be honest and open before God, and in so doing find His grace and mercy. The Book of James tells us that we are to draw near to Him, and He will draw near to us. This idea is repeated in the Book of Hebrews. In both of these examples we are to go to Him first. God desires connection with us.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:27-28; 2:19, 25; Pss. 32:5; 34:8; Heb. 4:16; 10:22; 12:1; James 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Preston</p>', '2010-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:47', 0, 0, null, '7D6azRyGbTo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7D6azRyGbTo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(859, 1, 'The Four Men Crucified with Jesus Christ', '<p>The traditional teaching that Jesus was crucified with two others is challenged via careful study of the Four Gospels. E.W. Bullinger&#39;s &ldquo;Companion Bible, Appendix 164&rdquo; points out that as Matthew and Mark describe two as &lsquo;robbers&rsquo;, Luke describes two as &lsquo;criminals.&rsquo; Further study shows that timing differed between the first two and the second two. Translators also inserted &lsquo;one&rsquo; that is absent from the original Greek manuscript.<br /> &nbsp;</p> <p>Verses: Matt 27:35-38, 44; Mark 15:27; Luke 23:33, 39-40; John 19:17-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:32', 0, 0, null, 'uxvE8zKZJk4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uxvE8zKZJk4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 28, null),
(860, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Sow in Tears; Reap in Joy', '<p>Making good decisions is certainly a challenging process that all of us face regularly in this world. Psalm 126 encourages us to make better choices as we consider that the future reward of a difficult decision is weightier than a great sacrifice or cost borne today. Having less today can mean having much more tomorrow.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 126:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:18', 40, 18, null, 'oFVHXTTwk2Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oFVHXTTwk2Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(861, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Cast Your Bread Upon The Waters', '<p>This teaching shows us a godly way of making decisions. Scripture tells us that when gratification is delayed, often we will benefit in greater ways in the future than if we opt for the quick gratification now. Share your resources with others and see what God gives back to you.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 11:1; Gal. 6:9</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:31', 40, 17, null, 'V-nbzZxq9sI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V-nbzZxq9sI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 17, null),
(862, 1, 'Finding Balance in Your Life', '<p>Solomon teaches us that we are not to be overly righteous or wise, nor overly wicked or foolish. We are to maintain a balance in our lives, keeping Christ at the center as our fulcrum.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:1-6, 9; Eccles. 7:15-19; Col. 3:15-16</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Anderson</p>', '2010-03-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:48', 0, 0, 'trespass', 'p4Fc9tbA9SA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/p4Fc9tbA9SA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(863, 1, 'He is Risen! &ldquo;This Jesus God has Raised!&rdquo;', '<p>&lsquo;He is Risen&rsquo; are the three most important words ever spoken! The prophecy from Genesis 3:15 is illustrated throughout this teaching. Jesus was indeed the Lamb of God and has been raised from the dead.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; 22:1-13; Matt. 22:28; Mark 16:6-7; Luke 24:32; Acts 2:29-32; Rom. 6:23; Heb. 11:17</p> <p>Teacher: Michael Patten</p>', '2010-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:47', 0, 0, null, 'li0JSMfAKDU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/li0JSMfAKDU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(864, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: The Roman Triumph / The Triumph Parade', '<p>This teaching describes the Roman custom of celebrating war victories. A triumphal parade was thrown in honor of the victory, featuring war heroes, political leaders, captives in chains, carts of spoils, the conquered king dressed in black, and oxen for the feast to follow. Incense burned throughout the parade route. Alluding to the victory parade, 2 Corinthians describes that Christians are the fragrance of incense, the &ldquo;aroma of Christ.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 2:14-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:30', 40, 16, 'triumphal procession manners customs', '_O4XjxM4iJw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_O4XjxM4iJw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 26, null),
(865, 1, 'Into Your Hands I Commit My Spirit', '<p>Jesus&rsquo; final words, spoken on the cross, repeated David&rsquo;s prayer to Yahweh in Psalm 31:5, at which time David was in deep trouble. In each case, the speaker exhibited great trust in God. To commit your &lsquo;spirit&rsquo; is to commit your life. Jesus was described as &lsquo;an innocent sufferer trusting God.&rsquo; We are to trust God to the ultimate, knowing He is good on His Word.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 31:5; Luke 23:46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:04', 0, 0, null, '_B0eU8C5A4o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_B0eU8C5A4o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(866, 1, 'Three Days and Three Nights', '<p>It has been traditionally taught that Jesus died on a Friday and arose Sunday morning. Building the Biblical chronology of events shows that Jesus Christ was crucified on a Wednesday and was raised the following Saturday afternoon.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:40; Mark 15:16, 20, 25, 32; Luke 22:66; 23:1, 7, 11; John 19:14, 31; 20:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:21', 0, 0, 'good friday tradition', 'dxCldp0v8cQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dxCldp0v8cQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'not in doc', 1, 30, null),
(867, 1, 'Reasons Why the Resurrection is Believable', '<p>To be saved and have everlasting life, one must confess Jesus as Lord and believe God raised him from the dead. This teaching presents logical, historical, and Biblical evidence of the resurrection of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 6:23; 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:44', 0, 0, null, 'KbidMrajphs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KbidMrajphs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'not in doc', 1, 12, null),
(868, 1, 'My God, My God, Why Have You Forsaken Me?', '<p>This video addresses the statements Jesus spoke from the cross. Jesus knew that all he needed to do was ask and God would send angels to help, but he accepted the path to his death. Jesus and the Jewish people knew the Old Testament and its teachings and they would have recognized the verses he cried out on the cross.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 22:1-31; Matt. 27:26-53; John 16:32; 19:36</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:13', 0, 0, null, 'hncQ9BIzT2g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hncQ9BIzT2g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(869, 1, 'Faith, Hope, and Love', '<p>Faith, hope and love are key elements for life. By faith we claim the promises of God. By hope we anticipate our living in the kingdom to come with our Heavenly Father God and His Son Jesus. The greatest of the three is love. Jesus showed us exceedingly great love by dying for us on the cross so that we would be reconciled to our God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:8-12; 13:13; Eph. 4:22-25; 1 Thess. 4:13-18; Heb. 11:1; 12:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-03-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:57', 0, 0, null, 'ib9WAyn1js8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ib9WAyn1js8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(870, 1, 'Encourage Each Other in the Love of Jesus Christ', '<p>We find encouragement in our faith in Jesus Christ, knowing that we have redemption through him and are co-heirs of the salvation earned for us by his death and resurrection. We have life with him in the kingdom to come. Because of this, we work to be worthy of this gift and to share this sacred secret with others.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:1-40; Phil. 1:1-29; 4:15; Heb. 2:1-5; 2:1-5; 12:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-03-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 0, 0, null, 'I-xE3qbYFSo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I-xE3qbYFSo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(871, 1, 'Whiter Than Snow', '<p>This video discusses examples of God cleansing us, making us whiter than snow. He cleanses us of our sins when believe in all Jesus Christ did for us. God cleanses our scarlet sins to be cleaner and whiter than snow.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 12:9-10; 2 Kings 5:26; Isa. 1:18; Matt. 28:3; Rom. 10:9-10; Rev. 3:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:07', 0, 0, null, 'Ie3PPU2ZpCI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ie3PPU2ZpCI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(872, 1, 'The Daughters of Zelophehad', '<p>Five women, daughters of Zelophehad, descendants of Joseph through Manasseh, influenced the changing of inheritance laws in the time of Moses. Their father died leaving no sons, so there would be no inheritance for the women and the family name would cease. With courage and humility, the daughters asked Moses that their father&rsquo;s inheritance be given to them. God instructed Moses to change the laws of inheritance.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 27:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 0, 0, null, 'HK9RHqzUOMc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HK9RHqzUOMc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(873, 1, 'Should Women be Silent in the Church?', '<p>Should women be quiet in the Church? The Adversary has tried to stop women&rsquo;s voices in the Church. God has given us all holy spirit to be used fully in ministry. This teaching specifically addresses 1 Corinthians 14:34-35 and gives examples in other verses of women praying and prophesying in the Church.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> Acts 2:17; 1 Cor. 7:8; 11:5; 14:5, 33-36; Gal. 3:28</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:23', 0, 0, null, 'iUmqlsxkSQE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iUmqlsxkSQE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(874, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Prepare the Way of the Lord', '<p>This teaching discusses examples of roads, paths, and ways. God has provided in His Word a direct path for us to travel to Him. That path is Jesus Christ - the way, the truth, and the life. Just as roads/paths must be maintained, we must work to maintain our relationship with God and our Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 40:3; Matt. 3:3; John 14:6; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:49', 40, 15, 'manners customs', 'IcjSE3steRc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IcjSE3steRc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(875, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Oriental Greetings', '<p>When we understand biblical customs through an eastern perspective, we see that traditional greetings could take a great deal of time. Jesus Christ was kind and gracious, yet in this time of urgency he instructed his disciples to move quickly. For us, the example is not to waste time on useless, meaningless things, but to get moving and live life being obedient to the will of the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 4:29; Luke 10:4; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:15', 40, 14, null, 'ugnp-yNtam4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ugnp-yNtam4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(876, 1, 'Nehemiah: Let''s Build the Wall (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching looks at the opposition Nehemiah faced while rebuilding the wall around Jerusalem. Life is a spiritual battle; evil will try to set us up for disaster, as Nehemiah experienced, but he held fast to his mission. When we do the work of God and of Jesus, we have to hold fast to their promises.</p> <p>Verses: Neh. 2:19; 4:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:36', 0, 0, null, 'WWbZCTQ7D9Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WWbZCTQ7D9Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(877, 1, 'Nehemiah: A Man of Vision (Part 1)', '<p>Nehemiah was a man of vision, prayer, and fasting. He prepared his heart to do what God put in his heart to do. The adversary came against him to stop him from rebuilding the wall around Jerusalem, but Nehemiah held to God&rsquo;s promise, power and faithfulness.</p> <p>Verses: Neh. 2:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:15', 0, 0, null, '1I7XWx828MM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1I7XWx828MM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(878, 1, 'The Faithfulness of God: Look at His Creation', '<p>The order and regularity of the physical world reflects the faithfulness of God. To those who love Him and keep His commandments He is just, blameless, pure, and righteous, but to those who are ungodly, He is shrewd. God&rsquo;s word is loaded with promises to His people; many have already been fulfilled and more are yet to come true.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 7:9; 32:4; 2 Sam. 22:25-27; Ps. 33:4; 145:13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:50', 0, 0, 'Creation, Covenants', 'V3up6JQSW8E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V3up6JQSW8E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(879, 1, 'What is Faith?', '<p>Faith is essential to pleasing God and to accomplishing good works. Faith is simply trust in God and trusting that what He has said is true. We can increase our faith by dwelling on God&rsquo;s word in the Bible, by walking in holy spirit, and by living as God would have us to live.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11:1; Rom. 10:17; John 12:10; 14:12; Mark 5:33, 34</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, 'Magic, Healing', 'JSAmmKX9lWA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JSAmmKX9lWA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(880, 1, 'The Battlefield is in our Mind', '<p>Sin comes from our fleshly nature. We can prevent sin in our lives by how we think and act. Jesus suffered in the flesh, but, through a renewed mind, lived the will of God. A stronghold is a form of sin which hinders us from living in mental freedom and fullness of life.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 10:2-5; 1 Sam. 2:1-4; Luke 4:18</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-03-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:45', 0, 0, 'Weapons, Arguments, Deception, Oppression', 'xCxdxRs5Ibg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xCxdxRs5Ibg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(881, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Like a Bottle in the Smoke', '<p>Scripture draws an analogy between a person and a &ldquo;bottle (wineskin) in smoke.&rdquo; In Biblical times, liquids were often stored in animal skins. When not in use in a home, they were hung up to be out of the way. Since a typical living area had a fire but no chimney, liquid containers hung in the smoky upper area of a home which was considered a harsh environment. We should take care that we do not become &ldquo;a bottle in the smoke.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:83; Judg. 4:19; Matt. 9:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 40, 13, 'Wine, Vinegar', 'pE1dwxh8sv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pE1dwxh8sv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(882, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Biblical Water Wells', '<p>Water was scarce in Biblical times and was often accessed by hand-dug wells. This teaching surveys the various verses that mention wells so we understand their cultural and practical significance. Narrow wells, as mentioned in Proverbs 20:5, are used as a simile to describe the snare of prostitutes and adulteresses.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 20:5; John 4:7-11; Gen. 21:30; 26:18; 29:8; Num. 20:17; 2 Sam. 23:15; Prov. 23:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 40, 12, null, 'mqvgIqZPO7o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mqvgIqZPO7o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(883, 1, 'Get in the Yoke: Matthew 11:28 Come to me all you who are weary & burdened, and I will give you rest', '<p>Mike Patten of Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship International shares on &quot;Get in the Yoke.&quot;</p>', '2010-02-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:30', 0, 0, null, '9Xqum2p8tfw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9Xqum2p8tfw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated due to suggestion of Calvinism', 1, 1, null),
(884, 1, 'Our Vision: Building an Enduring Work of Truth - Learn more about us at STFonline.org', '<p>Dan Gallagher of Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship International teaches on &quot;Our Vision: Building an Enduring Work of Truth.&quot;</p>', '2010-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:19', 0, 0, null, 'P_ETlYR296A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/P_ETlYR296A/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated per JJW', 1, 0, null),
(885, 1, 'Running a Small Christian Fellowship', '<p>This video gives practical tips on running a home fellowship. These include: praying to seek God&rsquo;s direction; having a core vision so all attenders are on the same page; when best to meet and where; who is your target demographic; and the meeting format. All these should be thought through before starting with the flexibility that they will need adjustments as the group develops.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:50', 0, 0, null, 'inTznHK64g8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/inTznHK64g8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(886, 1, 'The Phases of Home Church Development', '<p><em>How to Lead Small Groups</em> is a book by Neal McBride that describes six phases of home church development, from initiation to maturity. This presentation follows the book and briefly discusses the issues and benefits that come with each phase.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:01', 0, 0, 'Fellowship, Leadership', '67Zx5X6R2GU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/67Zx5X6R2GU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(887, 1, 'Psalm 23 (Part 2)', '<p>The last three verses of this Psalm compare the relationship between the shepherd and his sheep with the relationship of Lord to his people. There are things that the Lord provides for us and there are things we need to do for ourselves. The partnership results in &ldquo;goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 23:4-6</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2010-02-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:40', 0, 0, 'Fear, Comfort', 'Qw4tZaJdHEg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Qw4tZaJdHEg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(888, 1, 'Keys to Starting a Christian Fellowship', '<p>This teaching discusses several practical keys to consider when deciding to start a Christian fellowship. Some of these elements are prayer, a nucleus of at least two people, consistency, commitment, flexibility, and sound biblical teaching.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 4:12; Matt. 18:20</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:56', 0, 0, 'witnessing', 'Gm3Jm7iP5Kg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gm3Jm7iP5Kg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(889, 1, 'Psalm 23 - The Lord is My Shepherd (Part 1)', '<p>This psalm focuses on the relationship between the Lord and the one who wants to follow him. This relationship is illustrated with a shepherd and his sheep. As the psalm unfolds we learn the characteristics of a good shepherd and we begin to understand what a trustworthy leader will do for his followers.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 23:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2010-02-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:25', 0, 0, 'faithfulness', 'Sl2Y4u7j23s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Sl2Y4u7j23s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(890, 1, 'Tattoos – So You Want a Tattoo? (Part 5)', '<p>In this final part of the 5-part series on tattoos, the teacher discusses several points to consider before getting a tattoo. These include the purpose, the image, your motive, health considerations, your finances, the location on your body of the image, who will be applying the tattoo, and how the image will change over time. Tattoos should not be gotten impulsively.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:04', 55, 5, null, 'OGM4nGN3XZg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OGM4nGN3XZg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(891, 1, 'Tattoos - What to Do about Ungodly Tattoos (Part 4)', '<p>In this part of the 5-part series on tattoos, we are reminded that we are not made ungodly by outward things but by the inward motives of the heart. The teacher offers three solutions for Christians who have recognized that their tattoos are ungodly. Seeking repentance and forgiveness is key.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:37-39; 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:50', 55, 4, null, 'ERyE84gOatQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ERyE84gOatQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(892, 1, 'Tattoos - Bible Verse Commonly Used to Say that Getting a Tattoo is Wrong (Part 3)', '<p>In this part of the 5-part series on tattoos, Leviticus 19:28 is examined using various translations of the Bible and offering a cultural context for the verse. The teacher illustrates that gashing, slashing, or incising the flesh was a pagan practice of mourning for the dead, worship of the dead, or to represent a false deity.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 19:28; Isa. 49:16; Jer. 16:6; 44:4-5; 48:36-37</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:26', 55, 3, null, 'v0xkuP2E-jM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/v0xkuP2E-jM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(893, 1, 'Tattoos- Examining the Motives of your Heart (Part 2)', '<p>This part of the 5-part series on tattoos addresses the motives that might influence one&rsquo;s choice to get a tattoo. If Christians are considering getting a tattoo, they need to carefully examine the motives of their hearts, and make sure that the message of a tattoo promotes godliness rather than ungodliness.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 14:22</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:35', 55, 2, null, 'bfLwdYOVigk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bfLwdYOVigk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(894, 1, 'Tattoos - What Does the Bible Say? (Part 1)', '<p>Tattooing is currently very popular and it behooves Christians to understand what the Bible says about it. This first part of a 5-part series on tattoos introduces the Bible verses that address tattoos, pointing out that the Levitical Law forbade cutting or marking the body, but that Jesus fulfilled the Law and set us free from it.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 19:28; Isa. 49:15-16; Rom. 10:4; Eph. 2:13-15; Col. 3:23; 1 Tim. 1:5; 2 Tim. 2:22</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:36', 55, 1, null, 'c0O6t8wEoM0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/c0O6t8wEoM0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(895, 1, 'Get Connected: Fellowshipping Together', '<p><strong>:</strong> As the Body of Christ, it takes a team effort to do what God has called us to do. It is important to find ways to connect with other Christians even when there are differences in doctrine. This teaching examines some differences between the primary model that many churches use and the &ldquo;organic, simple church&rdquo; model that Spirit and Truth Fellowship promotes.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 0, 0, null, '2y6_DPK5arI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2y6_DPK5arI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(896, 1, 'The Gospel of Peace: What Is It? (Part 3)', '<p>If we want to minister successfully for God, it is essential to put on the &ldquo;shoes&rdquo; of the gospel of peace. Jesus told his disciples that he gives them peace, but not a peace like the world gives. His peace prepares us to build on the &ldquo;foundation of the apostles and prophets&rdquo; with Jesus as the cornerstone.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:27; Eph. 2:15, 19-22</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2010-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:37', 0, 0, null, 'T2_5oF5UiBs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T2_5oF5UiBs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(897, 1, 'The Gospel of Peace: We Have Peace with God (Part 2)', '<p>The Bible presents its own perspective of peace, which is different than the world&rsquo;s perspective. The gospel of peace is what God has accomplished and made available. This teaching examines a section in the Book of Ephesians that indicates believers who were once separated from God have been brought near by the blood of Christ who is our peace.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:13-18</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2010-02-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:44', 0, 0, null, 'hOw3I7D8cUI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hOw3I7D8cUI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(898, 1, 'The Gospel of Peace: Fit Your Feet with the Gospel of Peace (Part 1)', '<p>Part of our spiritual equipment is having our feet shod with the gospel of peace. Well-fitted shoes help one to move confidently. Having our feet &ldquo;fitted with the gospel of peace&rdquo; means that by knowing that we are forgiven and justified by Christ, we are freed from unnecessary strivings and have continual access to the Father.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:15; Rom. 10:15; 5:1, 2; Isa. 52:7</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2010-02-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:39', 0, 0, null, 'rDtn__5latg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rDtn__5latg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(899, 1, 'Highlights from our annual Teens & Twenties Bible study camp', '<p>Camp Vision was the site of the celebration of healthy, eager, bright-eyed youth seeking Godliness. Through fellowship, praise/worship, music, teachings, discussions, research and fun, the goal was achieved.</p>', '2010-02-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '3:54', 0, 0, null, '0A5UwL0TKwM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0A5UwL0TKwM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'outdated, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(900, 1, 'Forgiveness / Participating in Redemption', '<p>Although Jesus Christ died to pay for our salvation and the forgiveness of our personal sins, he did not take sin out of the world. Since Christ&rsquo;s death, our part as Christians is to receive the injustices of today&rsquo;s world and not repay evil for evil. Rather, we are asked to forgive as we participate in the redemption process.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:4, 5, 22; Col. 1:24; Phil. 3:10; 2 Cor. 1:5; 1 Pet. 4:13; Luke 23:34; Matt. 19:29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:54', 0, 0, 'endure, suffering', 'J11bkCfmthI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J11bkCfmthI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 21, null),
(901, 1, 'Understanding What &ldquo;Faith&rdquo; Is', '<p>Through the centuries, the meaning of &ldquo;faith&rdquo; has been obscured by man&rsquo;s teachings. The &ldquo;faith&rdquo; God speaks of in Scripture is &ldquo;trust, assurance and confidence&rdquo; in God. True faith is not following sacraments, but is built on a relationship with the Father that comes by spending time with God, studying and knowing His Word, praying, and being transformed by His truth.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11:6; Eph. 1:9; 6:19; 2 Cor. 5:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:53', 0, 0, null, 'FfjpBN2mLe4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FfjpBN2mLe4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 21, null),
(902, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Biblical Signet Rings & Wax Seals', '<p>In Biblical days, seals were an important part of the culture and were used to certify official acts. Seals were used in business as a type of signature or used in an act of finalizing something. Remarkably, when we accepted Jesus as Savior, God sealed us permanently with the holy spirit of promise. Our salvation is officially determined, guaranteed, or &ldquo;sealed&rdquo;.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 38:18; 41:42; Esth. 3:10: Jer. 32:10; Dan. 6:17; Matt. 27:66; Eph. 1:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 40, 11, null, 'y4_slrzeobs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y4_slrzeobs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(903, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Name Changes In the Bible - Jacob to Israel, Solomon to Jedidiah', '<p>There are many biblical examples of name changes in Scripture. God changed names for good purposes, while evil kings changed names to assert their authority over others. The ultimate &ldquo;name change&rdquo; came through Jesus, who changes our names from &ldquo;sons of disobedience&rdquo; to &ldquo;children of God.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 17:5, 15; 35:10; 41:45; Num. 13:16; 1 Sam. 12:24; 2 Kings 24:17; 2 Chron. 36:4; Dan. 1:7; John 1:42; Acts 4:36; Eph. 2:1; 1 John 3:1; Rev. 19:12, 13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:30', 40, 10, 'antonomasia, authority', 'JMzSqGljF-4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JMzSqGljF-4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(904, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Manners & Customs series: Biblical Names and Appellations', '<p>Biblical names can be complicated. A child born in biblical times was given one proper name, with his father&rsquo;s name attached at the end for identity clarification. Beyond designating how a person was known, biblical names could describe a person or reflect one&rsquo;s circumstances. Names could be changed later in life to describe life experiences, like Job. The greatest of all names is Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 25:25; John 6:42</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:11', 40, 9, null, 'oKZOiatiD5I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oKZOiatiD5I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(905, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Pointed Pottery', '<p>Understanding biblical customs helps the Bible come to life. For example, pottery in biblical days was formed to have a point on the bottom side of the vessel. This is peculiar until you realize that the floors of their homes or tents were dirt. By loosening the dirt, the pointed vessel could be inserted into the ground for stability.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 10:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:21', 40, 8, null, 'Q4-ZttV3R_c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Q4-ZttV3R_c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(906, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: What is an Ox Goad? Let Wisdom be our Goad', '<p>A goad is a 6-to-8-foot-long stick with a pointed end. This instrument was used by farmers to train their oxen to move in a straight line. The goad poked the shoulder, not hurting the animal, but showing them the way. When Scripture says &ldquo;The words of the Lord are like goads,&rdquo; it means they make us wise by guiding us and keeping us moving in the right direction.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 3:31; 1 Sam. 13:2; Eccles. 12:11; Acts 26:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:03', 40, 7, 'training', 'NJXy2uqq6s4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NJXy2uqq6s4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(907, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Oil Lamps in the Biblical World - Let Your Light Shine!', '<p>Light is essential to life. For thousands of years, light at night was made possible by bowls, wicks and olive oil. Jesus used the &ldquo;lamp&rdquo; as an illustration for how we are to be well-oiled and illuminated with godliness, to be positioned to shine to the dark world around us.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:14-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:02', 40, 6, 'shine', 'YbGetwNTHfc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YbGetwNTHfc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 16, null),
(908, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: Gird Up the Loins of Your Mind, Be Prepared for Action', '<p>The biblical custom of wearing a long robe made it necessary, when a person needed greater mobility, to gather up the material and secure it with a belt around the waist. This shortening of the robe for quick movement is described by the word &ldquo;gird.&rdquo; Using this illustration, the Bible is telling us that we are to always be ready to act for God.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 12:11; 1 Kings 8:46; Luke 12:37; 1 Pet. 1:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:51', 40, 5, 'manners customs', 'LQ5bY7G41XY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LQ5bY7G41XY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 24, null),
(909, 1, 'Manners & Customs series: An Overview of Manners & Customs in the Bible', '<p>This teaching gives many examples of differences between modern western culture and the biblical eastern cultures. To really enjoy and appreciate the depth of what the Bible says, we need to understand the customs of the times and the people.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 14:15; Judg. 14:5; Song of Sol. 1:5; Luke 13:32</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:37', 40, 4, null, '0roDJsy4x68', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0roDJsy4x68/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(910, 1, 'Welcome to Spirit & Truth Fellowship International', '<p>This introduction to Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship International highlights the greatness of God&rsquo;s Word and benefits of studying its blessings and accuracy. The message is followed by information about the organization and an invitation to get involved.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 19:7, 10; 138:2; John 17:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:19', 0, 0, null, 'FI9VEpHPRe4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FI9VEpHPRe4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(912, 1, 'Highlights from our Teens & 20s Live Out Loud 2009 Conference', '<p>Highlights from our (Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship International&#39;s STFonline.org) annual youth conference, Live Out Loud 2009. It was held the end of December in central Indiana.</p>', '2010-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:50', 0, 0, null, 'h5RUg522b2o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/h5RUg522b2o/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'outdated, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(913, 1, 'Ways of the World vs. God&rsquo;s way.', '<p>This sharing offers keys to living God&rsquo;s way, such as: Become born-again, care for the cause, have faith, know that every day is precious time to live for God. As we keep God&rsquo;s Word in our hearts, we can learn to become like Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1-2, 14; 1 Cor. 15:33; 2 Cor. 4:4; Col. 1:27; 2 Tim. 3:12</p> <p>Teacher: Grace Theisen</p>', '2010-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:38', 0, 0, null, 'ccz5tqE-nT8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ccz5tqE-nT8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(914, 1, 'Pls join us...Appalachian Mission Trip 2010 is now open for registration! See more info link', '<p>Registration is now open for our June 6 - 11, 2010 Appalachian Mission Trip at http://www.stfonline.org/register</p>', '2010-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:46', 0, 0, null, '1RDfmeivTyQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1RDfmeivTyQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'outdated, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(915, 1, 'Jesus Christ: Prophet, Priest, & King', '<p>Prophets, priests and kings in the Old Testament were anointed. This teaching expounds on three offices of Jesus Christ, the Anointed One: as prophet, as high priest, and as the king who will reign forever and ever.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 30:30; Deut. 18:15; 1 Sam. 15:1; 1 Kings 19:15-16; Matt. 16:13-16, 21-23; 1 Cor. 15:3; 1 John 1:7, 9; Heb. 7:17, 24-26; Rev. 11:15</p> <p>Teacher: Michael Patten</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:32', 0, 0, null, 'L7y2X7QfF2U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/L7y2X7QfF2U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(916, 1, 'Let&rsquo;s Get Together! Let&rsquo;s not Give up Meeting Together', '<p>The early Christians were devoted to fellowshipping together, sharing their lives, meals, and possessions, and praying and studying the Scriptures together. A fundamental aspect of the Christian Church is meeting together with other members of our spiritual family.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:41-44; Rom. 12:10, 16; 13:8; 14:13; 15:7, 14; Heb. 10:24-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:43', 0, 0, null, 'PGXVRFrqjXs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PGXVRFrqjXs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(917, 1, 'What is the Biblical Model for Getting Together as a Church?', '<p>Records in the Book of Acts and the Church Epistles show believers meeting together for fellowship in their homes. This teaching points out benefits of the simple, small group model of fellowship as well as detriments and benefits of meeting in larger groups.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:28; Acts 2:42; 8:1; Rom. 16:3-5; 1 Cor. 16:19; Phil. 1:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:40', 0, 0, null, 'i4Ml_M7b2g8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/i4Ml_M7b2g8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(918, 1, 'The Simple Church', '<p>The word &ldquo;church&rdquo; in the Bible does not mean a building, but is the Greek word &ldquo;ecclesia&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;the called out&rdquo; or &ldquo;the assembly.&rdquo; Jesus said that where two or more gathered in his name, he was in the midst. The &ldquo;Simple Church Movement&rdquo; of home fellowships has helped spread the good news of Jesus Christ around the world.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:20; Acts 12:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, 'outreach', 'Uht4o_fJKUo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Uht4o_fJKUo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(919, 1, 'Why Should We Meet?', '<p>When first century believers got together, they focused on outreach, spreading the good news of Jesus Christ. This resulted in many new believers who needed to be discipled in the ways of Jesus Christ. Their meetings were reflections of fully sharing their lives as they developed deep relationships in the family of God.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:19-20; Acts 5:41-42</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:43', 0, 0, 'fellowship, witnessing', '3DXwq1ANO3k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3DXwq1ANO3k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(920, 1, 'Let''s Spread the Good News', '<p>Some of the most rapid spreading of the message of Jesus Christ has come by using what some call the &ldquo;Oikos Principle&rdquo;, or &ldquo;Household Principle.&rdquo; We can share what Christ has done for us with family, fellow-workers, friends, neighbors, and anyone with whom we associate.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 8:39</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:19', 0, 0, 'witnessing, fellowship, outreach', '7I-XjlKQWNo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7I-XjlKQWNo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(921, 1, 'Am I Qualified?', '<p>We are not all called to be preachers or teachers, but we are all called to be witnesses about what Jesus has done for us. He has given each of us the full measure of the gift of holy spirit which empowers us to fulfill our own ministries.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:18', 0, 0, 'testimony, outreach', 'gr5zzs2tREw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gr5zzs2tREw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(922, 1, 'Giving Versus Tithing', '<p>The sharing of our finances without obligation, but freely given to individuals or organizations that minister to our spiritual needs, is pleasing to God. He will supply our every need according to His riches in glory in Christ Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 3:1-10; Phil. 4:15-19</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 0, 0, 'tithing, money, giving', 'EEfUwo5M_-4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EEfUwo5M_-4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(923, 1, 'Was Jesus really born on December 25th?', '<p>Although Scripture is not specific about the date of Christ&rsquo;s birth, it does leave helpful clues. God revealed specific dates for other events. What is His silence about the exact date of Jesus&rsquo; birth telling us? This teaching also addresses the historical reasons for the tradition of December 25 as the Lord&rsquo;s birthday.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 8:1; Luke 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:19', 0, 0, null, 'Vetl5s4B0_o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vetl5s4B0_o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(924, 1, 'A Biblical Overview of the True Christmas Story', '<p>This teaching presents a review from Scripture of the people and circumstances surrounding Jesus&rsquo; birth. The details are notably different from traditional views. We learn, among other truths, who the Magi were, when they arrived, and why they brought the gifts that they brought.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:7-34; Matt. 2:11-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:12', 0, 0, 'myth tradition', '4ej95zQmfss', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4ej95zQmfss/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'is there a better place to reference this?', 1, 23, null),
(925, 1, 'Retelling the True Christmas story (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching continues to address the contrast between the traditional picture of Jesus&rsquo; birth and the scriptural truths of this important event, with emphasis on understanding the cultural practices of the time and place of Jesus&rsquo; birth.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, null, 'bE4IH8PHCl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bE4IH8PHCl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(926, 1, 'Retelling the True Christmas story (Part 1)', '<p>The Bible actually reveals few details about the birth of Christ. This teaching addresses the reasons for that and dispels the traditional picture of Jesus&rsquo; birth by discussing what Scripture does reveal along with cultural understanding of the time and place.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:6-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:59', 0, 0, 'manger', 'tewch66jmgU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tewch66jmgU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(927, 1, 'Glory to God in the Highest (Luke 2:14)', '<p>The shepherds in the fields surrounding Bethlehem when Jesus was born experienced a magnificent supernatural event when suddenly appearing before them was an angel of the Lord and they were surrounded by the brightness of God&rsquo;s glory. This teaching addresses this wonderful, one-of-a-kind moment in detail.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 3:12; Luke 2:13-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, null, 'XZMlqWqbIxY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XZMlqWqbIxY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(928, 1, 'What Does the Bible say about the Magi (wise men)?', '<p>Tradition, folklore, and song lyrics have contributed to many different stories about the magi (or wise men) associated with the birth of Jesus. This teaching explains the biblical record of the Magi who travelled to see him &ldquo;who has been born king of the Jews,&rdquo; Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 5:11; Mic. 5:2; Matt. 2:1-4, 8-9, 11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:26', 0, 0, 'Christmas', 'BVIOrDx49a0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BVIOrDx49a0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(929, 1, 'Mary, the Mother of our Lord Jesus', '<p>This teaching explores the biblical records regarding Mary, the mother of our Lord Jesus. Her character, faith, courage, and humility are reflected in her decision to accept the angel&rsquo;s message of her pregnancy. Her praise and prayer express her gratitude to God. So much can be learned from this young woman&rsquo;s life.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:25; Luke 1:31-34, 42-47</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 0, 0, 'Christmas', 'S2S6DFONQ-E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S2S6DFONQ-E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(930, 1, 'How old was Mary when she Became Pregnant?', '<p>Mary received the angel Gabriel&rsquo;s message of her pregnancy from God as a young woman. The culture of the time in which Mary lived was much different than our current-day western culture. Consider these biblical records and the culture of the day to learn more about the young Mary and her family.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:55-56; Luke 1:26-29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:43', 0, 0, 'Christmas', '62kfJ3NywuA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/62kfJ3NywuA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(931, 1, 'To Hear God&rsquo;s Voice, Avoid a Hard Heart', '<p>Do you want to be more connected to the living God and hear His voice? This exhortation from Hebrews encourages us not to become hardened by sin but to help each other recognize areas in our lives that could use some improvement.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 14:23; Heb. 3:7-8, 12-13, 15; 4:7</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-12-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 0, 0, null, 'iNQH-SOsXLs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iNQH-SOsXLs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(932, 1, 'Drawing Near to God (Part 2)', '<p>It cost God the life of His Son, Jesus Christ, to provide us the way to draw near to Him. This pathway between humanity and God was opened by the resurrection of Jesus. Our access to the sanctuary of God is continually overseen by Jesus, our High Priest, and provides us the opportunity to draw near in honest, genuine relationship with our Creator.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:19-22</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-12-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:16', 0, 0, null, 'C5-IllrzJC4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/C5-IllrzJC4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(933, 1, 'Drawing Near to God (Part 1)', '<p>The opportunity to draw near to God was greatly improved with the ratification of the New Covenant brought about by Christ&rsquo;s sacrifice. Now we can have confidence in our access to God, to approach Him to receive mercy, grace, and help any time we have need.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 4:15-16; 12:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-12-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:38', 0, 0, 'Messiah', 'eq38S7EEVnM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eq38S7EEVnM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(934, 1, 'Loving Above the World: The heart of love (Part 7)', '<p>Jesus loved by teaching, serving, healing, rebuking, praying&hellip; whatever was needed. His thoughts, actions, and words were all in perfect harmony to fully exhibit the love of His Father. Love is the heart of caring behind the action, not just the action alone. We can have the same heart of love to both care and do whatever is needed.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:43-48; 8:3; Mark 10:17-22; Luke 7:14-15; John 3:16; 1 Cor. 13:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-12-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:22', 42, 7, null, 'zi62KH5JLIs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zi62KH5JLIs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(935, 1, 'Loving Above the World: Get Over Yourself (Part 6)', '<p>We all care for our own needs, even everyday things like eating and sleeping. With the same care we have for ourselves, we can care for others. To love like Jesus loved means that we care and do for others like we care and do for ourselves, setting aside our personal feelings.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:35-39; Mark 4:16-19; Rom. 13:8-10; 1 Cor. 13:5; 1 Tim. 6:9-10, 17-18; 1 John 4:18</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:37', 42, 6, null, '_3sWIwtEbTw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_3sWIwtEbTw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(936, 1, 'The Book of Romans: Our Righteousness (Part 2)', '<p>God is completely righteous. No person can earn his own righteousness. We depend on God to provide His righteousness to us by means of the sacrifice of His Son Jesus Christ. The sacrifice of Jesus Christ allowed God to extinguish the guilt of sin and to cancel His obligation to punish sin for those who believe.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23-25</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, null, '4OYkxZAzKLY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4OYkxZAzKLY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(937, 1, 'The Book of Romans: Our Righteousness (Part 1)', '<p>The righteousness that comes from God had always been veiled and not clearly understood. Paul wrote in Romans that a righteousness from God is now revealed or unveiled in the Gospel. It is exciting to think that as we understand the good news of Jesus Christ, we understand the righteousness of God, a gift freely given.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:16-17; 3:19-24</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-11-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:05', 0, 0, null, 'rFo-Su6dJ5U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rFo-Su6dJ5U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(938, 1, 'Grace and Peace from God', '<p>Most of the New Testament Epistles begin with a salutation to the local church which includes &ldquo;grace and peace&rdquo; from God and the Lord Jesus Christ. This is consistently God&rsquo;s will for the church: to accept His grace&mdash;His unmerited and undeserved divine favor&mdash;and to be at peace. When grace and peace are mentioned over and over again, we should take notice and learn what they mean.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:7; 1 Cor. 1:3; 2 Cor. 1:2; Gal. 1:3; Eph. 1:2; Phil. 1:2; Col. 1:2; 1 Thess. 1:1; 2 Thess. 1:2; 1 Tim. 1:2; 2 Tim. 1:2; Titus 1:4; Philem. 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2009-11-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:50', 0, 0, null, 'mNXwiC2mvBc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mNXwiC2mvBc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(939, 1, 'Friends of Jesus: Mary and Martha', '<p>This teaching reviews three Gospel passages that include Mary and Martha, with attention to the reaction of each woman to Jesus&rsquo; words and deeds. Jesus addressed each of them individually according to their personal needs. Though their behaviors and reactions in the same situation were different, both were cared for and honored by Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 10:38-42; John 11:17-32; 12:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2009-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:06', 0, 0, 'Hospitality, Service', 'lhWsUJhmn8w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lhWsUJhmn8w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(940, 1, 'Loving Above the World: Follow the Leader (Part 5)', '<p>Jesus&rsquo; entire life was a demonstration of the Father&rsquo;s love. Even when on the cross, he answered a malefactor&rsquo;s plea for salvation. Since we have decided to make him Lord in our life, we should obey him as Master. Now it&rsquo;s our turn to love others in words, truth, and action.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9; Luke 6:46; 23:39-43; John 15:9-14; 1 John 3:16, 18, 23</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:15', 42, 5, null, 'CGAKE5pRNC8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CGAKE5pRNC8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(941, 1, 'Loving Above the World: Jesus'' decision to love (Part 4)', '<p>Whether Jesus was grieving the death of John the Baptist, or feeding a hungry crowd, or talking to the Samaritan woman at the well, he responded to other&rsquo;s needs above his own. His priority was to proclaim the Good News by word and deed regardless of his own personal circumstances. This is our example of showing the love of God to others.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 119:59, 60; Matt. 14:12-14; Mark 6:34-37, 45, 46; John 4:3-7, 28, 29, 39-43</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 42, 4, null, 'PZBnK_CN99U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PZBnK_CN99U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(943, 1, 'Psalm 42: God&rsquo;s Provision in Times of Need', '<p>Psalm 42 describes the human state of trusting in God while going through hard times. The psalmist laments his distress and anguish and wonders where God&rsquo;s help is. Then he recalls the little streams of blessings God has bestowed upon him over the years and how these have merged into a waterfall flowing over him.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 42:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: Elaine Landmark</p>', '2009-11-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, 'Faithfulness', 'cdkeM1b5Bak', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cdkeM1b5Bak/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(944, 1, 'Thankfulness: Always be Thankful', '<p>God wants us to be peaceful and thankful. Earthly things bring happiness for a short time, but heavenly rewards are forever. Don&rsquo;t be unhappy now because of what you don&rsquo;t have, rather be thankful for what you have now and what God and Jesus have waiting for you in the future.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:15; Heb. 10:32-34; 11:24; Matt. 6:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-11-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:25', 0, 0, 'Treasures, Heart, Rewards', 'temk12LpshE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/temk12LpshE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(945, 1, 'Loving Above the World: It''s our turn (Part 3)', '<p>Since we have and understand God&rsquo;s commands to us and Jesus&rsquo; example of how to fulfill them, it is time for the church to put love into action so that others may be comforted and saved. As an illustration, the local people on Malta in the Book of Acts demonstrated love toward Paul and the others shipwrecked with him, not for their own benefit, but so these visitors&rsquo; needs were met.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:5-7; 1 Cor. 10:32, 33; Acts 16:19-31; 28:1, 2</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:33', 42, 3, null, 'luHS5r4VHCA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/luHS5r4VHCA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(946, 1, 'Loving Above the World: Be Imitators of God (Part 2)', '<p>The Church is called to imitate God. Jesus did this by living as the Father directed him. This included being good to strangers, loving others, and even loving his enemies. We are not to live selfishly but to care about others as we care for ourselves. Although sometimes not easy to do, God enables us to do what is difficult, just as Jesus did.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:28, 29; 13:34, 35; Matt. 5:43, 44; Luke 7:12-15; 1 Cor. 13:5; Eph. 5:1, 2</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:14', 42, 2, 'Kindness', 'DW1FrbpRMsA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DW1FrbpRMsA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(947, 1, 'Loving Above the World: What is our motivation to love? (Part 1)', '<p>God loved us by sending His son Jesus to be a reflection of Him and to take away our sins so that we might have everlasting life. Since God did this for us when we were alienated from Him as sinners, in return we should love Him by loving our friends and our enemies.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:43-47; Eph. 5:1; 1 John 3:1; 4:8-11; 16; Ps. 16:11; 34:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2009-11-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:34', 42, 1, 'Joy, Atonement', 'thm0QA8u8nE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/thm0QA8u8nE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(948, 1, 'Love | What Does Love Act and Look Like?  (Part 5)', '<p>This teaching addresses the difference between &ldquo;love&rdquo; and &ldquo;like&rdquo; in American culture and the misunderstanding caused by misusing the word &ldquo;love.&rdquo; Using 1 Corinthians as a basis, it further illustrates that godly love is clearly described as godly behaviors or actions.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 13:4-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:10', 52, 5, null, 'Q_o59XsboLQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Q_o59XsboLQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(949, 1, 'Love | What&rsquo;s the Difference between Phileo and Agapao? (Part 4)', '<p>The teaching explores the biblical account of a dialogue between Jesus and Peter in the Gospel of John to show the difference in the meanings of the Greek words <em>phileo</em> and <em>agapao</em>, which are both translated &ldquo;love.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: John 21:14-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:41', 52, 4, null, 'G48KeZQyTOI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/G48KeZQyTOI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(950, 1, 'Love | Love Is Giving (Part 3)', '<p>The word &ldquo;love&rdquo; is used broadly and often wrongly in many cultures today. Scripture teaches us that godly love is not a feeing but is action and involves obedience and giving.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:15, 21, 23-24; 1 Cor. 13:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:47', 52, 3, null, '2Q2ngQiyvmQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2Q2ngQiyvmQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(951, 1, 'Love | The Four Kinds of Love (Part 2)', '<p>In the Greek language there are four different words translated &ldquo;love,&rdquo; Three appear in the New Testament scriptures. This teaching explains the definition, nuances, and usages of each of these different words.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 23:4-5; John 3:16, 5:20, 11:3; Rom. 12:10; 1 John 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:33', 52, 2, null, 'm8z4rJaC3Zo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m8z4rJaC3Zo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(953, 1, 'Love | Love is tough (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching demonstrates that in so many situations in life, choosing to be loving is a tough thing to do, especially to act lovingly regardless of what anyone may do or say against us.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 24:12; Acts 17:31; Rom. 2:4, 12:17, 19; 1 Cor. 15:58; James 1:19-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:30', 52, 1, null, 'maoQpWJt9VQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/maoQpWJt9VQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(954, 1, 'Keys to Walking with Spiritual Power', '<p>This teaching expounds a specific key to walking with spiritual power: the believer&rsquo;s &ldquo;power of attorney.&rdquo; It is given to believers by Jesus Christ and involves the believer&rsquo;s authority to use his name to accomplish the work he would have us to do.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 16:17-19; John 15:16; Acts 3:6-16; 19:13-16; Phil. 2:8-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-10-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:53', 0, 0, null, 'cuQtoiHGzrk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cuQtoiHGzrk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(955, 1, 'The Measure of a Man', '<p>We all measure ourselves. To measure is simply to make a comparison between the thing being measured and a fixed standard. As Christians we are encouraged to be sure we are measuring ourselves against the best standard, which is God&rsquo;s standard.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 6:41-42; Acts 13:36; 1 Cor. 4:3-4; 2 Cor. 5:10; 10:12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:55', 0, 0, null, 'FNBXWwWSJAw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FNBXWwWSJAw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(956, 1, 'God''s purpose through the ages', '<p>God&rsquo;s purposes through the ages have been consistent and faithful. This teaching addresses God&rsquo;s purposes in light of two concepts: reconciliation, and destroying the works of His enemy the Devil.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15, 21; Judg. 2:18; 1 Sam. 5:1-4; Luke 19:10; Acts 2:23; Rom. 8:28; 1 Cor. 16:26; Eph. 3:10-11; 1 Tim. 2:3-5; 2 Tim. 1:19; 1 John 3:8</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 0, 0, null, '8gsbv-mXMhA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8gsbv-mXMhA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(957, 1, 'Be Generous!', '<p>This teaching illustrates the Bible&rsquo;s perspective of generosity and the benefits of being generous. Giving joyfully and generously may bring rewards in this life, but certainly will bring rewards in the future kingdom of God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 29:12-14; Prov. 11:25; Ps. 37:25-26; 112:1-5; 2 Cor. 9:6-8; 1 Tim. 6:17-19; 1 John 3:17</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:29', 0, 0, null, 'soK1bDhE-RA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/soK1bDhE-RA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(958, 1, 'Why Praise?', '<p>Why should we praise God? This teaching shows us not only the reasons why we should praise, but also what praise is, and gives examples of praise from Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 16:1-2, 4, 7-12; 2 Chron. 2:7-8, 10; Pss. 79:13; 139:14; Matt. 11:25; Eph. 11:6; 1 Pet. 11:6</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-10-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:31', 0, 0, null, 'WiFU5ZtPrPU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WiFU5ZtPrPU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(959, 1, 'What is the &lsquo;Mystery&rsquo; or &lsquo;Sacred Secret&rsquo;', '<p>The Greek word <em>musterion</em> is often transliterated into the word &ldquo;mystery&rdquo; in Scripture and is used as an excuse for not understanding the things of God. This teaching explains why this translation is inaccurate and that a better translation is &ldquo;sacred secret.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:11; Rom. 16:25-26; 1 Cor. 2:7-8, 10; Eph. 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:37', 0, 0, 'interpretation', 'yqhuQOo1aU4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yqhuQOo1aU4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 37, null),
(960, 1, 'Ambassadors for Christ', '<p>God has given all Christians the ministry of reconciliation, and we are His ambassadors. This teaching shows the importance of this ministry and how to become better ambassadors for God.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 14:15-23; 2 Cor. 5:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:25', 0, 0, null, 'TGfxX-mbQ44', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TGfxX-mbQ44/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(961, 1, 'Godliness', '<p>Scripture says that Christians should train themselves to be godly. This Bible study reviews the Greek word <em>gumnazo</em> which means &ldquo;to exercise vigorously,&rdquo; and gives examples of how Christians can spiritually train themselves.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 9:24-26; 1 Tim. 4:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 0, 0, 'fellowship', '9Y4rhUhcD6s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9Y4rhUhcD6s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 13, null),
(962, 1, 'What does the Word &ldquo;Lord&rdquo; Mean?', '<p>This Bible study brings clarification to the translation of the Greek word <em>kurios</em> in scripture. It is a cultural term used to show respect when addressing an official who has authority and can be translated as &ldquo;sir&rdquo;, &ldquo;master&rdquo;, or &ldquo;lord.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 31:35; Matt. 13:27; 20:8; 27:63; John 4:9-11; 12:20; 13:16; Acts 10:4; 25:26; 1 Pet. 3:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:50', 0, 0, null, 'UO4bLkAGwMM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UO4bLkAGwMM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(963, 1, 'What Does the Name &ldquo;Jesus Christ&rdquo; Mean?', '<p>This teaching explains that the Hebrew name for Jesus is <em>Yeshua</em>, a common name given to children prior to the birth of Jesus Christ. The Greek word <em>christos</em> and Hebrew word <em>masah</em> mean &ldquo;anoint.&rdquo; The teaching reveals how &ldquo;Christ&rdquo; became added to Jesus&rsquo; name.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 4:3; 1 Sam. 10:1; Isa. 61:1; Matt. 1:17; 3:16</p> <p>Teacher<strong>:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 0, 0, null, 'hYDEFEOZV78', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hYDEFEOZV78/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 38, null),
(964, 1, 'What Does the Bible Say About Hell? (Part 2 of 2)', '<p>Do people really burn in hell? Part two of this two-part teaching continues to dispel the doctrinal argument that sinners burn in forever in hell by clearing up difficult scriptures that have been erroneously translated to support that belief.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:46, 42-43; Mark 9:45, 48; 2 Pet. 2:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:41', 0, 0, 'everlasting', 'C7cplP-g2v8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/C7cplP-g2v8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(965, 1, 'What Does the Bible Say About Hell? (Part 1 of 2)', '<p>Do people really burn in hell? Part one of this two-part teaching reminds the listener that God is love and explains the choices of life or death. The Hebrew word <em>gehenna</em> is erroneously translated as &ldquo;hell&rdquo; in Scripture. The teaching dispels the theology that sinners burn forever in hell.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 15:8; Ps. 37:10; Jer. 7:20; Mal. 4:1; Matt. 5:29; 10:28; John 3:16; Rom. 6:23; Rev. 20:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 0, 0, 'everlasting', '72eJeryrQeI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/72eJeryrQeI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(966, 1, 'What is the Soul? (Part 2 of 2)', '<p>Where does your soul go when you die? This teaching continues to explain that soul, our life force, is not as believed in mythology - living on after a person&rsquo;s death - but that it is in every part of our living body, and the concept of soul and life are one and the same.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:47', 0, 0, 'Resurrection', 'lbSBMZZt-QE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lbSBMZZt-QE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 45, null),
(967, 1, 'What is the Soul? (Part 1 of 2)', '<p>Where does your soul go when you die? This teaching explains that soul is the life force of humans and animals alike and that it is important to go to Scripture to learn about it. The Hebrew word <em>nephesh</em> and Greek word <em>psuche</em> are both translated &ldquo;soul,&rdquo; and have many meanings that help us understand what happens to the soul after death.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:20-21, 24, 30; Exod. 1:5; Lev. 24:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:50', 0, 0, 'Resurrection', '8ZoE74k2TcI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8ZoE74k2TcI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 89, null),
(968, 1, 'Why Isn&rsquo;t It Good Enough to Believe in God and Just Love Each Other?', '<p>The Bible is indeed believable and is not the work of man. Written over a period of 1500 years by about 40 writers, the Bible is God-breathed through revelation and contains specific instructions on how we are to serve, thank, and worship Him. Further, the Bible is filled with historically verifiable prophecies. We can believe it!</p> <p>Verses: Job 26:7; Gal. 1:11-12; 2 Tim. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:11', 0, 0, null, '3pF4pgeMYOA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3pF4pgeMYOA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(969, 1, 'Exercising Our Faith', '<p>Exercise builds strength and endurance. Being a Christian is not a spectator sport. The real growth for a Christian is with small groups that encourage participation and prayer. Pentecost redefined the life of a believer into a royal and holy priesthood. We now have to do the work, and God has equipped us to do so.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 1:51; 3:10; Rom. 12:1; 2 Cor. 5:18; Eph. 4:12; James 5:16; 1 Pet. 2:5, 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:46', 0, 0, null, '1LMYN3EtMpI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1LMYN3EtMpI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(970, 1, 'Multiculturalism and the Pattern of this World', '<p>The adversary is at work in every culture to make it ungodly. This teaching explores why we are not to be conformed to our cultural patterns, many of which are sinful. We must be willing to stand for God.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:29; 12:2; Eph. 5:4, 18; 1 Tim. 2:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:22', 0, 0, null, 'AqQSIW04NM8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AqQSIW04NM8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(971, 1, 'The Canon of Scripture: How the Bible came to be', '<p>This teaching describes how the Bible has &ldquo;evolved&rdquo; through the ages into its present form. The &ldquo;Codex&rdquo; was the original book form, made by binding and gluing parchment scrolls together. The Christian community accepted the books based upon how they were received, collected, read, used, and passed down.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 12:12; 2 Tim. 4:6-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:00', 0, 0, null, '12o9XImLqWE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/12o9XImLqWE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(972, 1, 'The Integrity of Scripture: The Bible - You Can Believe It!', '<p>The Bible is the most reliable of all ancient documents. The fact that it has been copied so many times adds to, rather than takes away from, its integrity. Multiple copies of the original texts, in many different languages, can be pieced together into manuscript families which enables researchers to see their consistency. The Bible is accurate and we can believe it!</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:31', 0, 0, 'translation', 'E78cKkWmo3Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E78cKkWmo3Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(973, 1, 'Our Power in the Spiritual Battle', '<p>Lack of spiritual maturity and biblical illiteracy work hand-in-hand to rob Christians of their ability to use the power God has given them through the work of Christ. Satan uses two main ploys to hinder Christians&rsquo; authority and ability: 1) convince people he does not exist, and 2) convince people that he has more power than he really does.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 24:49; Acts 4:33; Rom. 10:17; Eph. 1:19-20; 1 John 5:2-4, 19-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-09-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:44', 0, 0, null, 'e_-aMMrJcUA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/e_-aMMrJcUA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(974, 1, 'Cleansing the Temple', '<p>This teaching explains that evil spirits may be embedded in physical objects. We may unknowingly bring items into our homes that have demons in them or associated with them, like artifacts, collectibles, and so on. A wise Christian carefully examines his home to ensure its contents are spiritually clean.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 7:26; Acts 19:18-19</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:11', 0, 0, 'Idols', 'fVJI9YAlH3A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fVJI9YAlH3A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(975, 1, 'We Will All Give an Account', '<p>Repentance and confession affect our eternal inheritance. God&rsquo;s Word declares that we will all give an account for everything we do and say, for every idle or empty word, and for our behavior. This teaching encourages us to rid ourselves of anything that separates us from God.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 7:9; Acts 17:30; Rom. 14:11; 2 Cor. 5:10; 10:3-5; Eph. 1:13; 5:1; 1 Thess. 4:4; Heb. 12:1; Rev. 20:11-13</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:35', 0, 0, null, 'wdDzKlbFf_Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wdDzKlbFf_Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(976, 1, 'Teaching, Preaching, and Testimony', '<p>This teaching is a reminder to all Christians that we are &ldquo;Ambassadors for Christ&rdquo; and it is our responsibility to share the Good News. Not all of us have the gifts of teaching or preaching, however our testimony is the best way for us to be the ministers of reconciliation that we are called to be.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 11:1; Acts 4:13-20; 10:30-34; Rom. 12:4-8; 2 Cor. 5:17-20; 1 Tim. 2:7; 1 Pet. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-09-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:46', 0, 0, null, 'xed_1mFfvw8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xed_1mFfvw8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(977, 1, 'Use Your Power Tools', '<p>This teaching draws intriguing parallels between the power that we have via holy spirit and the power tools that we regularly use in our homes or at work. A power tool has rules for use, as does our spiritual power. We need to use the right tool for the job.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 9:1; Acts 4:33; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-09-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:57', 0, 0, null, 'iplYfubgvf4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iplYfubgvf4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(978, 1, 'Should we question the Bible?', '<p>Many Christians think that having questions about the Bible is offensive to God, but God tells us in His Word to ask questions. He wants us to know all about Him, about life, about all spiritual matters. He wants us to be wise, and it is only natural to ask questions to gain wisdom.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 10:11; Luke 10:25-26; Acts 8:28-31; James 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:33', 0, 0, null, '9SWeOFJdI6g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9SWeOFJdI6g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(979, 1, 'Does God Speak to Men?', '<p>All Scripture is God-breathed, given to men to record, and is profitable for teaching, reproof, correction and instruction in righteousness. This teaching confirms through the Word that, yes, God has spoken to men and women throughout the ages.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 12:12; Job 38:1; Gal. 1:11-12; 2 Pet. 1:20-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:00', 0, 0, null, 'iXoyeJYYGF8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iXoyeJYYGF8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(980, 1, 'Can we really know God?', '<p>Our God really wants us to know Him. The teaching that we really cannot know God is debilitating to believers. This teaching clarifies the meaning of Isaiah 55:8, a verse commonly cited to demonstrate that we cannot understand God. Knowing and understanding are critical to any relationship and are certainly critical to our relationship with God.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 14:1; 103:7; Isa. 55:6-9; Jer. 4:22; John 1:18; 1 John 1:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:35', 0, 0, null, 'vXrG-JKsw38', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vXrG-JKsw38/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(981, 1, 'Righteousness - Every Christian''s Gift from God', '<p>If we want to understand the New Testament, we need to understand what righteousness means. Righteousness refers both to something spiritual that we have been given and to how we live. It is important to understand both aspects and to discern the difference between them.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:20-22; 5:17; 6:23; 2 Tim. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:57', 0, 0, null, '4AXWPKFNTKw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4AXWPKFNTKw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(982, 1, 'Thanks: The Benefits of Thanks Living (Part 2)', '<p>There is a physical benefit derived from giving thanks. Thankfulness is an antidote for mental, physical, emotional and spiritual illness. The Bible is full of examples of the benefits of giving thanks and thankfulness.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 28:7; Prov. 14:30; 15:13, 30; 16:24; 17:22; 1 Thess. 5:16-18; Heb. 12:15.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-09-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:00', 0, 0, null, 'XRJVZ3wN2FU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XRJVZ3wN2FU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(983, 1, 'Thanks: The Joy of Thanksgiving (Part 1)', '<p>Throughout the scriptures we are told to give thanks. God even instituted a feast of thanksgiving in the Old Testament. We receive joy when we are thankful for all His many blessing in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 7:13; 1 Cor. 14:16; Phil. 4:6; Col. 3:17; 1 Thess. 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-09-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:36', 0, 0, null, 'lifogbJpowo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lifogbJpowo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(984, 1, 'The Life of Moses: His Example to us and How God Worked with Him (Part 3)', '<p>God works with us as we are. He is fully capable of providing us with the tools we need to complete His work. Moses was fearful and felt he was not up to what God needed him to do. Yet God was with him and provided what he needed to do the work.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:10; 4:11-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:21', 47, 3, null, '1JHyzjPC3x8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1JHyzjPC3x8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(985, 1, 'The Life of Moses: His Example to us and How God Worked with Him (Part 2)', '<p>God told Moses, &ldquo;I am sending you to bring my people out of Egypt.&rdquo; Moses was not excited about this and responded &ldquo;Who am I?&rdquo; meaning he didn&rsquo;t feel capable. God replied &ldquo;I will be with you.&rdquo; As with Moses, God knows what we can do and He will be with us.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:11-15, 4:2-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:16', 47, 2, null, 'DElodELtueg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DElodELtueg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(986, 1, 'The Life of Moses: His Example to us and How God Worked with Him (Part 1)', '<p>Moses was afraid, worried, and anxious. He did not believe that he measured up to the task God was asking of him. But God worked with him, and he completed God&rsquo;s task. God is as concerned about us now as He was with Moses then. He will send us to do His work and be right there with us to complete the task.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-08-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:11', 47, 1, null, 'nvjbhfTDlMQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nvjbhfTDlMQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(987, 1, 'Letting God&rsquo;s Love Flow Through Us', '<p>We need to know God&rsquo;s love for us personally in order for that love to overflow from us toward others. Our capacity to love others stems from God&rsquo;s love for us.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:16-19; 5:1-2; 1 John 4:7-11, 15-17; Luke 6:31-36</p> <p>Teacher: Jackson Trigg</p>', '2009-08-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 0, 0, null, 'SbYT3wRhpVA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SbYT3wRhpVA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(988, 1, 'Bible Translation Project: Revised English Version® (REV®) & Commentary', '<p>John W. Schoenheit of Spirit &amp; Truth Fellowship International shares on why we are working on a New Testament translation of the Bible. You can view the REV and Commentary online at http://www.stfonline.org/rev</p>', '2009-08-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:09', 0, 0, null, 'edIa6oy_FXk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/edIa6oy_FXk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'old blurb on the REV', 1, 0, null),
(989, 1, 'The Discipline of Forgiveness (Part 4)', '<p>Forgiveness can take time. This teaching talks about the various emotions and stages we experience during the process of forgiving, and how to recognize the difference between a feeling and a choice pertaining to forgiveness.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:21-35</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:37', 48, 4, null, 'I0DRtZt3Wkw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I0DRtZt3Wkw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(990, 1, 'The Discipline of Forgiveness (Part 3)', '<p>Why is forgiveness necessary and how can we effectively bring ourselves to do it? This teaching offers five practical keys, things we can actually do that will help us genuinely forgive others.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:9-15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:20', 48, 3, null, '-HxM0As8gm4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-HxM0As8gm4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(991, 1, 'The Discipline of Forgiveness (Part 2)', '<p>Why is forgiveness so important? What kinds of things can hinder us from forgiving? This teaching offers three helpful keys to walking in the freedom of forgiveness that God wants us to have.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:21-35; Heb. 12:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:07', 48, 2, null, 'xMNs59GuSLE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xMNs59GuSLE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(992, 1, 'The Discipline of Forgiveness (Part 1)', '<p>In this introduction to the topic of forgiveness, we see how central a concept it is to Christianity and why learning to forgive is an essential discipline for walking in a powerful and victorious Christian life.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 86:5; 99:8; Matt. 6:9-15; 18:35; Eph. 4:32; Col. 3:1</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:30', 48, 1, null, 'C_DFsTNk7b0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/C_DFsTNk7b0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(993, 1, 'God is our Refuge, not Defense Mechanisms', '<p>This teaching discusses defense mechanisms, which are walls that we build up around ourselves to protect ourselves from hurt, but which only multiply our sorrows. We are to look to God as our shield and refuge. Only He has the strength to protect us.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 11:1; 16:1-11; 62:5-10; 118:7-14</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2009-07-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:44', 0, 0, null, 'e66iR6Iu9Lg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/e66iR6Iu9Lg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(994, 1, 'Don''t Follow Your Heart, Follow God!', '<p>This teaching warns against worldly advice to follow our own hearts and our own feelings, which can lead us astray. Biblically, we are to direct our hearts toward God, and to trust in the Lord and in his ways.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 15:38-40; Ps. 42:11; Prov. 3:1-8; 23:17-19; Jer. 17:7-10; Mark 7:21-23</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2009-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:54', 0, 0, null, 'N-A3yF--vS0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N-A3yF--vS0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(995, 1, 'Truth Matters: Walking in the Truth (Part 6)', '<p>Truth does exist. However, men have always tried to suppress and distort truth, and exchange truth for a lie. As truth seekers, we can acknowledge, rejoice in, and walk with truth. We can also speak the truth in love.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:6; Acts 20:30-32; Rom. 1:18, 25; 10:9,10; 1 Cor. 13:6; Eph. 4:14,15; 2 Thess. 2:9,10; 1 Tim. 6:3-5; 2 Tim. 3:6-7; 4:2-4; Titus 1:13; James 5:19; 2 John 1:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:50', 49, 6, null, 'Mdqu3CUq52I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Mdqu3CUq52I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(996, 1, 'Truth Matters: The Characteristics of Truth (cont) (Part 5)', '<p>The universal, exclusive, and objective nature of truth is explained in this segment. Truth is not superficial or trendy. Nothing can be both true and untrue at the same time. Truth is not subject to the opinions or interpretations of men.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:9, 10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallaher</p>', '2009-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:16', 49, 5, null, 'pYcEhcTkQgc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pYcEhcTkQgc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(997, 1, 'Truth Matters: The Characteristics of Truth (cont) (Part 4)', '<p>The video explains the &ldquo;correspondent&rdquo; nature of truth and the &ldquo;coherent&rdquo; nature of truth. When we take the time to research the Bible, we find that it always corresponds to that which is true and it will not contradict itself.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:53', 49, 4, null, 'DLjmoxNC4pM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DLjmoxNC4pM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(998, 1, 'Truth Matters: The Characteristics of Truth (Part 3)', '<p>Truth is not relative; it is absolute, meaning it does not change based on circumstances; it is fundamental and perfect. Learn more in this short video about other characteristics of truth.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:53', 49, 3, null, 'JcIPoBmHISs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JcIPoBmHISs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(999, 1, 'Truth Matters: Truth Seekers (Part 2)', '<p>Truth-seekers are motivated by the promise that truth is available and can be discovered. A truth-seeker must be humble and courageous enough to accept truth when it presents itself. Truth exposes error and separates light from darkness and good from evil. For those willing to seek, they will find, and the truth will set them free.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:7, 10:34-37; John 8:32</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:10', 49, 2, null, 'ObXmrPtPjp4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ObXmrPtPjp4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1000, 1, 'Truth Matters: Introduction (Part 1)', '<p>Opinions and perspectives are relative, but truth is timeless, unchanging, and not dependent on circumstances. Science is based on the reality that in the physical realm, truth exists and the laws governing the physical realm can be discovered. Spiritual truth also exists, and if one seeks and searches, it too can be discovered.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:22', 49, 1, null, 'YBePVRWwTIk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YBePVRWwTIk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1001, 1, 'Figures of Speech in the Bible: An Overview', '<p>Figures of speech are used with precision by God in His Word; they add emphasis to what is being stated. There are over 200 varieties of figures of speech, each of which has a name and fits into a specific category. Some examples of figures of speech explained in this video are ellipsis, anaphora, polysyndeton, and asyndeton.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:3-8, 11:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-06-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:48', 0, 0, null, 'y6GfSXNAMys', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y6GfSXNAMys/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1002, 1, 'Are There Lost Books of the Bible?', '<p>This teaching provides sound reasoning for why we should not be deceived or discouraged by those who claim that there are lost books of the Bible. Often that is only any excuse for not reading the Bible or believing it. God is the author of the Bible. Reading and living by the written Word of God that we have will pay wonderful dividends.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 12:12; 2 Tim. 3:16; 4:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-06-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:31', 0, 0, 'canon', '7npzmGFeeng', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7npzmGFeeng/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1003, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost: The gift of holy spirit is poured out (Part 3)', '<p>When the Day of Pentecost arrived, faithful Jews from all over the Mediterranean and Middle Eastern world were in the Temple in Jerusalem. This video explains the significance of the fire that appeared that day and the importance of what was given by God.</p> <p>Verses: John 20:21-22; Acts 1:7-8, 2:1-6, 33</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:44', 51, 3, 'tongues', 'k_LiY6rCzjM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k_LiY6rCzjM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1004, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost: Where Did it Occur (Part 2)', '<p>Christian tradition teaches that on the Day of Pentecost the apostles spoke in tongues in &ldquo;the upper room,&rdquo; which is where they slept. But a closer look at Acts 2 reveals that the Christian church began in the House of God, which was the Temple in Jerusalem.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 24:51-53; Acts 1:12-13, 2:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:26', 51, 2, null, 'ghtjzUliLHw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ghtjzUliLHw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1005, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost: The history of The Feast of Weeks (Part 1)', '<p>In the Old Testament, God commanded all the men of Israel to appear in the Temple three times each year: Passover, Pentecost, and the Feast of Tabernacles. Passover and the Feast of Tabernacles lasted seven days, but Pentecost, also called the Feast of Weeks, occurred on only one day. God chose that day to pour out His gift of holy spirit!</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 23:15-16; Deut. 16:16; 1 Cor. 15:23; James 1:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:21', 51, 1, null, '1jJUwL6ntnY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1jJUwL6ntnY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1006, 1, 'Salvation is Permanent for Christians (Part 5)', '<p>On the Day of Pentecost, God did something He had never done before. He had not even spoken of it; it was a sacred secret. He gave spiritual birth to His children, making us partakers of His very nature, by putting incorruptible seed within us.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 3:7-10, 5:17; Eph. 1:22-23; Phil. 3:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:08', 44, 5, null, 'M2u31swwPtY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/M2u31swwPtY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1007, 1, 'Salvation is Permanent for Christians (Part 4)', '<p>Our relationship with God is different from that of believers in the Old Testament and the Gospels. Unlike them, we are born of God, with incorruptible seed, and are partakers in the divine nature. We have holy spirit sealed in us, which is the guarantee of our salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:37,39; 1 Cor. 14:5; 2 Cor. 1:22; Eph. 1:13-14; Phil. 3:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:50', 44, 4, null, 'ik_vWlOIwjg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ik_vWlOIwjg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1008, 1, 'Salvation is Permanent for Christians (Part 3)', '<p>In order to learn more about God&rsquo;s magnificent grace in this administration, one should look for vocabulary that is used uniquely from the Book of Acts to the Book of Jude. This teaching examines a number of words and phrases, including &ldquo;born-again,&rdquo; &ldquo;adopted,&rdquo; &ldquo;seed,&rdquo; &ldquo;divine nature,&rdquo; &ldquo;holy ones,&rdquo; and &ldquo;sealed with the promised holy spirit.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:7; 1 Cor. 1:2; Eph. 1:3; 3:9-10; 1 Pet. 1:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 44, 3, null, 'Kf4IPijwQxY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Kf4IPijwQxY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1009, 1, 'Salvation is Permanent for Christians (Part 2)', '<p>In the New Testament books from Acts 2 through the Book of Jude, God develops a father/child relationship with those who are saved, reflected in the vocabulary. In these books there are three different Greek words used to show we are born of God, painting the picture that the Christian new birth is permanent.</p> <p>Verses: Hosea 1:8-9, 23; Titus 3:5; James 1:18; 1 Pet. 1:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:06', 44, 2, 'incorruptible', 'wbJfww3L_Dc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wbJfww3L_Dc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1010, 1, 'Salvation is Permanent for Christians (Part 1)', '<p>This teaching addresses the question &ldquo;What is the &lsquo;grace&rsquo; in the grace administration?&rdquo; and discusses the debate over the question of the permanence of our salvation. It examines reasons for the debate and builds a case for understanding God&rsquo;s rules during different time periods. The rule for salvation changed on the Day of Pentecost.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:25; Ps. 1:1-6; Ezek. 33:11, 13; Hab. 2:4; Matt. 10:22; Eph. 3:2,9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:02', 44, 1, 'law', 'RYbGmhNu6F4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RYbGmhNu6F4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1011, 1, 'The eight Administrations in Scripture (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching takes a detailed look at the Administration of Grace, which is also called the Administration of the Sacred Secret. In many Bible translations, the Greek word <em>musterion</em> is mistranslated as &ldquo;mystery,&rdquo; but should more accurately be &ldquo;secret&rdquo; or &ldquo;sacred secret.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 2:7; Eph. 3:2, 9-10; Col. 1:26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:05', 0, 0, null, 'vS01tMGppBE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vS01tMGppBE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1012, 1, 'The eight Administrations in Scripture (Part 1)', '<p>God changes the rules with which He deals with people in different time periods throughout history. To better understand the Bible, we need to be aware of this and know what rules apply to us. This teaching identifies eight different &ldquo;administrations&rdquo; in the Bible. The only one that is specifically named in the Bible is the Administration of Grace, in which we live now.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:29; 9:3; Rom. 14:5; Eph. 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, 'Pentecost, rapture, tribulation', 'CgFEMjgfxF8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CgFEMjgfxF8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1013, 1, 'What God Says About the Death Penalty', '<p>Many Christians believe that God does not support the death penalty. This idea originated from one of the &ldquo;Ten Commandments,&rdquo; in which older translations of the Bible mistranslated the Hebrew word as &ldquo;kill.&rdquo; Most modern translations recognize the correct translation as &ldquo;murder.&rdquo; While it may sound harsh, God gave man the death penalty to keep society safe.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 9:6; Exod. 20:13; 21:12; Lev. 24:17; Num. 35:16-18, 31; Eccles. 8:1; 1 Tim. 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:48', 0, 0, null, 'x-IL80qn348', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/x-IL80qn348/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1014, 1, 'Communion: What Jesus intended', '<p>Jesus Christ introduced what we now call &ldquo;communion&rdquo; during the Last Supper when he was eating with his disciples. The intention of his teaching was that whenever believers ate together, they should remember his sacrifice. The early church did this, but communion fairly quickly changed into something quite different, even hurtful and devaluing of Christ&rsquo;s accomplishments for us.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 26:20, 26-28; Acts 2:42; 1 Cor. 11:17-25; 1 Tim. 4:4-5; Jude 12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:37', 0, 0, 'wine, blood', 'fIKB8Y8TOgg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fIKB8Y8TOgg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1015, 1, 'How to Get Saved and Why', '<p>The best news ever is that God has made an offer to everyone to live forever in perfect bodies in paradise. This is called salvation (from death into life) and it is easy and free to receive. This teaching presents scriptures that explain how and why this is possible and exactly what we must do to accept this wonderful gift.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 1:3-5; John 1:29; 3:16; Rom. 6:23; 10:9-10; Eph. 2:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-05-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:35', 0, 0, null, 'ChUCWNbDSbg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ChUCWNbDSbg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1016, 1, 'Call Jesus teacher and be his disciple', '<p>Jesus is our Lord and teacher. He will teach us his ways. He loves us far too much to watch us receive salvation but then leave us continuing in our own ways. Jesus taught by example. As we gain experience imitating him, we set examples for others to follow.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:13-15; Phil. 3:17; 1 Thess. 1:4-7; Heb. 13:7</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2009-05-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:06', 0, 0, null, 'gGFYJHBM2Bk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gGFYJHBM2Bk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1017, 1, 'Some Keys That Bring Rest For Your Soul', '<p>Citing scriptural references, this teaching presents five keys to bringing spiritual refreshment and rest to our souls. We are encouraged also to reach out to refresh others and are shown a way to do that.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 19:7; 23:1-3; 32:1-5; Prov. 11:25; Jer. 15:16; Matt. 11:28-30; Acts 3:19-20; Rom. 1:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2009-05-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:56', 0, 0, null, 'vIXyIQs8J9E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vIXyIQs8J9E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1018, 1, 'Standing in the Gap (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching provides a powerful example of a believer standing in the gap with the record of Nabal and his wife, Abigail, in the Old Testament. Abigail wisely intervened, or stood in the gap, between Nabal&rsquo;s foolish behavior and David&rsquo;s rash reaction to it, changing the entire outcome of the situation.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 25:1-3, 13, 18, 20, 21, 28, 31, 32</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-05-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:43', 0, 0, null, 'gF0LVIZ5bFE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gF0LVIZ5bFE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1019, 1, 'Standing in the Gap (Part 1)', '<p>After Adam&rsquo;s disobedience, a gap or separation occurred between God and mankind. God used prophets and godly men and women to stand in that gap and draw men back to God. Today, we have Jesus Christ who permanently bridged the gap between God and man. As believers, having Christ in us, we can now participate in standing in the gap, drawing people to God through Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 22:23-26, 30; Matt. 10:7,8; 1 Cor. 2:8; Col. 1:25-27; 1 Tim. 2:5; 1 Pet. 1:8;</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:51', 0, 0, 'reconciliation', 'KImrd8onoFc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KImrd8onoFc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(1020, 1, 'Jesus - The Door to an Enlightened Heart', '<p>God&rsquo;s desire is for His children to know Jesus and have their hearts enlightened by truth. To mentally assent God&rsquo;s Word is to have knowledge, but to know God&rsquo;s Word in your heart is to ignite His truth into action. Look at God&rsquo;s Word with your eyes, listen with your ears, then understand with your heart.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:1-6; Matt. 13:13-18; John 3:2; Acts 2:37; Eph. 1:16-18; 2 Cor. 3:12-18; James 1:22-25; 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: Josh Anderson</p>', '2009-05-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:52', 0, 0, null, 'KXtj6uMpIPc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KXtj6uMpIPc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1021, 1, 'The Godly Response to Offense', '<p>People frequently offend each other, so God gives wise counsel on this topic in His Word. This teaching discusses ways to manage being offended, such as: be quick to forgive, handle the offense in the moment, and practice self-control, be quick to listen, hold back wrath, respond softly, and more.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 12:16; 15:1; 19:11; 29:11; Matt. 5:23,24; 18:15; Luke 17:3-4; Eph. 4:26, 27; Phil. 1:1-5; Col. 3:12-14</p> <p>Teacher: Josh Anderson</p>', '2009-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:59', 0, 0, null, 'vZbUeCuGMNc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vZbUeCuGMNc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1022, 1, 'Psalm 141: An encouraging example of a prayer we could all pray', '<p><strong>Suggested Description:</strong> -- This brief teaching encourages us to pause, to think, to digest and to absorb the powerful prayers in Scripture, particularly the prayer in Psalm 141. We are exhorted to be active participants with God&rsquo;s Word&mdash;not passive readers.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 141:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Josh Anderson</p>', '2009-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:36', 0, 0, 'meditate', 'YUz9t6ciOeA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YUz9t6ciOeA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1023, 1, 'Failing Forward: Expectations  (Part 4)', '<p>God wants us to &ldquo;fail forward.&rdquo; Failing forward is about our attitudes and experiences. Our expectations affect our attitudes and outcomes, and realistic expectations help us weather through difficult circumstances. When we place our expectations on God, we will not be disappointed.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 11:34; Ps. 22:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-04-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:42', 46, 4, null, 'otZX3NVtv_0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/otZX3NVtv_0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(1024, 1, 'Failing Forward: Friends (Part 3)', '<p>Our perspective on life affects our attitudes. Oftentimes our perspective is affected by the people we associate with. Are your friends miserable comforters? Are they positive or negative? Are they encouraging or discouraging? Changes in our attitude may require evaluating and changing our friendships.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 11:14; 1 Cor. 15:33, 34</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-04-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:35', 46, 3, null, 'Rp7ercpphnk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Rp7ercpphnk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(1025, 1, 'Failing Forward: Reality Thinking (Part 2)', '<p>Our attitudes result from our thinking and therefore affect our choices. We are to train our minds to focus on &ldquo;now&rdquo; thinking. We learn from the past, but we do not live in the past. Choose to learn from your past choices, and then &ldquo;fail forward.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 3:13-14</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-04-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:59', 46, 2, null, 'CD4bjXBnXV0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CD4bjXBnXV0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 14, null),
(1026, 1, 'Don''t Blame God | Difficult Verses Explained: The Hardening of Pharaoh''s Heart (Part 4)', '<p>God&rsquo;s nature is consistent from Genesis 1:1 to Revelation 22:21. Though there are difficult verses that can create confusion, understanding the languages of the Bible helps clarify these. An example is the hardening of Pharaoh&rsquo;s heart in Exodus. This teaching explains the Hebrew idiom embedded in that record.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 4:21; Ezek. 20:25; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:17', 25, 4, null, 'eSPzrbi9fPk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eSPzrbi9fPk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 33, null),
(1027, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Blame God | The Spiritual Battle: Daniel 10 (Part 3)', '<p>Do not be fooled into thinking that God is behind death, disease, and destruction. Though we live in a five-senses world, our daily battles are spiritual. Like Daniel, when we are in times of trouble, we need to first seek the Lord in prayer for understanding, guidance, and help.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 10:1-14; Heb. 2:14; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:33', 25, 3, null, 'aLPr782e0fw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aLPr782e0fw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 37, null),
(1028, 1, 'Don''t Blame God | God is at War: The Spiritual Battle (Part 2)', '<p>It is important not to blame God for all the pain, death, and sickness going on in the world around us. There is an actual war going on and sometimes people get hurt, but that is not God&rsquo;s doing. Take a few minutes to hear about our valiant God who fights for us.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 15:3; Ps. 18:4-9, 14, 17; Eph. 6:12; Luke 13:15-16; Acts 10:38</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-04-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:03', 25, 2, 'Control, Battle', '34I9p_dM5Wo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/34I9p_dM5Wo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 93, null),
(1029, 1, 'Do your best: A study of the Greek word Spoudazo', '<p>The Greek word <em>spoudazo</em> reveals the kind of effort that demonstrates our love for God and for each other. This teaching explores new insights with a deeper look at the Greek word <em>spoudazo</em>.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 22:37-39; Gal. 2:10; Eph. 4:3; 2 Tim. 2:15; Titus 3: 12; 2 Pet. 1:1-2, 4-5, 10, 12-16, 20-21</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-04-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:53', 0, 0, 'Study, Tools', 'XbNb4rEqlYM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XbNb4rEqlYM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1030, 1, 'Isolation Vs One Anothering', '<p>God designed people to live in relationship with each other. Two human tendencies usually hinder relationships: fear and offense. God provides remedies for both of these tendencies in people. This teaching explores these remedies.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:18; Deut. 31:6-8; Acts 2:42-47; Rom. 12:16; 14:13; Eph. 4:2; Heb. 3:13; 10:25; 2 John 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-04-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:18', 0, 0, 'Community', '6que9FHRqj8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6que9FHRqj8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1031, 1, 'Don''t Blame God | Is God in Control of Everything That Happens? (Part 1)', '<p>Does God cause sickness, disease and death? That is a good question and it deserves a good answer - not from traditional sources, but rather from God&rsquo;s Word. Let&rsquo;s find out what God has to say about this very important question.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:28; Luke 4:5-7; 1 Cor. 15:24-25; 2 Cor. 4:4; Heb. 2:14; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-04-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:38', 25, 1, 'Satan', 'RDgIRWYzPBc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RDgIRWYzPBc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1032, 1, 'To the Praise of God&rsquo;s Glory', '<p>Throughout all time, God has exhibited His glory in many ways. He sent His Son to rescue mankind knowing that many people would come to trust Jesus Christ as their Savior and Lord. This act of love demonstrated God&rsquo;s glory. Enjoy hearing about this exceptional phrase, &ldquo;To the praise of God&rsquo;s glory.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:3-6, 11-13; 1 Pet. 1:1-2, 4-7</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-03-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:45', 0, 0, null, 'vqs8_ZL4I4Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vqs8_ZL4I4Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1033, 1, 'Good versus Evil and Pride versus Humility', '<p>Followers of Jesus Christ all want to do what is good before God, but oftentimes fall short of truly living like our Lord did. This is the struggle of human existence. Enjoy the encouragement of this teaching to choose to trust, acknowledge, and fear God.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 3:5-7; Luke 18:19; Rom. 7:18-21; Gal. 5:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-03-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:52', 0, 0, null, 'WCKyLmHV1J8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WCKyLmHV1J8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1034, 1, 'Discover God&rsquo;s Individual Gifts of Grace', '<p>God has provided you with giftings that enable you to serve Him in ways only you can do. Whether God tells you, or others let you know, or life experiences show you, God has built something special within you to ensure that you are best suited to help with the Lord&rsquo;s work on earth.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:3-6; 1 Cor. 12:4-6; Eph. 2:8; 4:3-8, 11-12; 1 Pet. 4:10</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-03-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:44', 0, 0, 'Ministry', 'xIFAsU0N_ZY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xIFAsU0N_ZY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1035, 1, 'Historically Verifiable Prophecies (Part 4)', '<p>Our confidence in the many words of God increases as we observe historically-verifiable prophesies. This teaching takes a look at several prophecies about the Lord Jesus Christ identified as the Messiah. God has gone to great lengths to prove His trustworthiness as we continue to read and study Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 12:3; 49:10; 2 Sam. 7:16; Isa. 11:1; Mic. 5:2; Zech. 9:9; Isa. 53:5-8, 11-12; Ps 22:16, 18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:41', 45, 4, null, 'quvBRtSfKHI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/quvBRtSfKHI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1036, 1, 'Historically Verifiable Prophecies (Part 3)', '<p>Frequently God has spoken of events before they happened that can then be recognized after they&rsquo;ve occurred. This provides us evidence that God&rsquo;s prophecies and promises are indeed trustworthy. He has also spoken of events yet to happen and we can trust that they will happen because God has proven Himself trustworthy.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 48:18-20; Isa. 44:26-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:55', 45, 3, null, 'pxOsGZTZMg4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pxOsGZTZMg4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1037, 1, 'Historically Verifiable Prophecies (Part 2)', '<p>God invites us to read His book, find His prophecies, and look for evidence of their fulfillment. Prophecy is one method God uses to prove to mankind that His book is full of His trustworthy words. Enjoy this segment in your quest to establish your trust in the Bible.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 12:1-2; 16:8-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:48', 45, 2, null, '9M4i9dgwcis', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9M4i9dgwcis/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1038, 1, 'Historically Verifiable Prophecies: Introduction (Part 1)', '<p>The Bible is God&rsquo;s Word and is reliable and trustworthy. As a demonstration of that, God had written into His Word historically verifiable prophecies that were future when they were declared but have since come to pass. Looking at various verses from the Book of Isaiah, this teaching illustrates that God is true to His Word and gave us Scripture to verify that.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 41:21-23; 42:8-9; 43:8-10; 46:8-10; 48:3-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:33', 45, 1, null, 'PdUAtcRTHA4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PdUAtcRTHA4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1039, 1, 'Failing Forward: Turning Mistakes into Stepping Stones to Success (Part 1)', '<p>We all experience failure. How we approach our failures determines what we learn from them. Our attitude and perspective help us have better outcomes from unfavorable or even terrible circumstances. Joseph, David, and Jesus are examples of this.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-03-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:00', 46, 1, null, '3_yO7ELg1z8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3_yO7ELg1z8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1040, 1, 'Spiritual Warfare and Prayer', '<p>Many Christians believe that whatever happens in this world is God&rsquo;s will. They do not pray because they do not understand why they should. This teaching shows in Scripture that we are in a spiritual warfare with the adversary and that not everything that happens is God&rsquo;s will. This is why the heart of God is for us to pray and to pray diligently.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 10:1-4; 1 Tim. 2:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:58', 0, 0, 'salvation', 'BITn-mjm8vI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BITn-mjm8vI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1041, 1, 'Who sinned that this man was born blind?', '<p>John 9:1-3 is an important event in Jesus&rsquo; ministry, and mistranslations have clouded its true meaning. We know that God does not inflict illness on someone for the purpose of healing them later. This teaching reveals the accurate translation and meaning of John 9:3, exposing the beauty of this important event.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 19:3; Mark 5:12, 23; John 9:1-3; Acts 10:38; Eph. 5:33; 1 John 3:8</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2009-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:18', 0, 0, null, 'yyDbuRKHdCU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yyDbuRKHdCU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1042, 1, 'TruthOrTradition.com promo', '<p>Visit http://www.TruthOrTradition.com for answers to your tough theological questions. You have questions, we have answers! Visit TruthOrTradition.com</p>', '2009-03-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '0:55', 0, 0, null, 'AYB2Opzm3QU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AYB2Opzm3QU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'old promo, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1043, 1, 'What does the Bible say about...?', '<p>What does the Bible say about subjects like...</p>', '2009-03-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '1:50', 0, 0, null, 'DREL-XiNC7Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DREL-XiNC7Q/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'old promo, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1044, 1, 'Pray, pray, pray! Why is Prayer Important?', '<p>God repeats many times and in many ways in His Word that we should pray, and pray often. Yet many Christians seldom pray. One reason is that the belief that God is in control undermines the importance of prayer. We are in a spiritual battle and our prayers are a powerful weapon against the spiritual forces of evil.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:19; Acts 10:38; Rom. 12:12; Eph. 6:18; Col. 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:17; 1 John 5:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:25', 0, 0, null, 'UMpWdtdLDfo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UMpWdtdLDfo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1045, 1, 'TruthOrTradition.com on iPhone', '<p>TruthOrTradition.com is now mobile! Check out our new iPhone optimized site at http://www.TruthOrTradition.com/iphone</p>', '2008-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:41', 0, 0, null, '4sQERxeid6g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4sQERxeid6g/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'promo for old app, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1049, 3, '8 Watts of Willingness', '<p>There is great value in having a heart to do God&rsquo;s will and to serve Him as a faithful vessel, even if we feel unequipped or underprepared to do so. If we are willing to remove the distractions from our lives and seek to do what God and Jesus Christ have called us to do, great things can be accomplished even if we only have a small amount of willingness on our part.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 2:20-21, 14-19; 4:1-2; Ps. 90:12; 39:4</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-01-14', 'Castos', 0, '26:21', 0, 0, 'readiness, desire, service', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/8_Watts_of_Willingness.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/8-watts-of-willingness', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1050, 3, 'The Real Christmas Story', '<p>The Christmas story is important because the birth of Christ is important. The traditional story of His birth contains many errors, and presents a cold, hard, and lonely picture about the circumstances of his birth. This expository teaching explores and reveals a deeper, more accurate understanding of the customs, time and place, and other details that truly make the birth of Christ an inspiring account of love, obedience, giving, and sacrifice.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:24-40, 56-57; 2:1-24; Matt. 1:18-25; Lev. 12:6-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-12-12', 'Castos', 0, '1:10:45', 0, 0, 'virgin, betrothed, manger', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/The_Real_Christmas_Story.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-real-christmas-story', null, 1, 1, 'Is there a better place to reference this?', 1, 75, null),
(1051, 3, 'It''s Okay To Enjoy Your Life', '<p>There is a belief among many Christians that we don&rsquo;t deserve and should not pursue enjoyment in this life--that life should only be taken seriously and sober-mindedly at all times. But is that really God&rsquo;s intention for us? Scripture illustrates God&rsquo;s viewpoint that we can and should enjoy our work and the fruit of it, and even to approach life with humor.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 6:45-48; Titus 2:6; Phil. 3:1, 4:4; Isa. 22:12-13; 1 Cor. 15:32; Eccles. 2:24-25; 3:4,12-13, 22; 5:18; 8:15; 9:7; 11:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-11-06', 'Castos', 0, '23:17', 0, 0, 'contentment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/It_s_Okay_To_Enjoy_Your_Life_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/its-okay-to-enjoy-your-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1052, 3, 'No Retirement', '<p>This teaching explores the importance of our individual calling and how each of us has been redeemed to a life of service to Jesus. We were not preordained, but we were invited into service and relationship with our Lord&mdash;and we, by our free will, answered that call. It&rsquo;s a commitment from which we don&rsquo;t get to retire, just like Jesus did not retire when he ascended to the Father&rsquo;s right hand!</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:28-30; 11:29; Matt. 22:1-14; 2 Thess. 2:13-14; 1 Cor. 1:26-29; Eph. 1:15-18; 4:1; Phil. 3:10-14; 2 Thess. 1:3-12; 2 Pet. 1:10-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2019-10-07', 'Castos', 0, '28:26', 0, 0, 'chosen, purpose', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/No_Retirement.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/no-retirement', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1053, 3, 'The Shema of Deuteronomy 6:4', '<p>The Shema is not only a declaration to Israel &ndash; it is a statement about relationship. This teaching presents three aspects of the Shema: what it is not saying, what it is saying, and how it applies to our lives. The teacher explores its meaning through a Biblical Unitarian perspective, highlighting what it reveals about God and our relationship with Him. We are encouraged to love God with all our heart, soul, mind, and strength.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4-5; 4:35, 39; Mark 12:28-34; John 17:3; 1 Cor. 8:6; Exod. 20:2-3; Song of Sol. 6:8-9; Zech. 14:9; 13:2; Isa. 2:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:20', 0, 0, 'monotheism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/The_Shema_of_Deut_6_4.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-shema-of-deuteronomy-64', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 91, null),
(1054, 3, 'Live Joyfully in Every Circumstance', '<p>Philippians is a wonderful book in the Church Epistles, a letter penned by Paul with an abundance of encouragement and instruction for believers. One of the greatest aspects of Philippians is the depth of exploration into joy and endurance and how, through our reliance on Jesus and our unity with him, we can all have a godly mindset and approach to life no matter what situations we face.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:9-25; Phil. 1:1-4:23</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-08-21', 'Castos', 0, '57:12', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Live_Joyfully_In_Every_Circumstance.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/live-joyfully-in-every-circumstance', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1055, 3, 'God&rsquo;s Unique Day', '<p>Zechariah 14:6-7 speak of a &ldquo;unique&rdquo; day in the future known only to Yahweh. Our God has quite a challenge to take on: restore our fallen world with its many flaws, to the state of &ldquo;Paradise&rdquo; as it was in the Garden of Eden. But God is up to the challenge and it will only take Him one &ldquo;unique&rdquo; day to do it.</p> <p>To view the chart referenced in this teaching, <a href="https://www.stfonline.org/simple-chart-of-the-future" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 1:1-2; Dan. 9:24-27; Rev. 19:11, 14-15, 17, 19-21; 20:7-9; Ezek. 37:11-14; Matt. 25:31-33; Zech. 14:1-7; Luke 21:7-12, 20-22; 23:43; Gen. 1:30; 2 Cor. 12:4; Isa. 11:1-2, 5, 9; 35:1-2, 6, 7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-07-19', 'Castos', 0, '56:35', 0, 0, 'restoration', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/God_s_Unique_Day.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/gods-unique-day', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 71, null),
(1056, 3, 'Righteousness: Doing Right by God and People', '<p>It is important to every Christian that we understand the meaning of righteousness, especially as it is used in the New Testament. While the uses of &ldquo;righteousness&rdquo; were often blended in the Old Testament and Gospels, the word has two distinct meanings in the New Testament Epistles: 1.) having a right standing in the sight of God, and 2.) doing right by God and others.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23, 24; 5:1; 10:4; 2 Tim. 3:12, 16; 2:22; Phil. 4:8; 2 Chron. 12:5, 6; Ezra 9:13-15; Ps. 11:7; 116:5; 145:17; 37:21,32; 1 Sam. 12:7; Deut. 24:12, 13; 2 Sam. 22:2; Eccl. 7:16; Matt. 5:6, 10, 20; 6:33; Jer. 23:1-5; Luke 11:46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-06-19', 'Castos', 0, '48:09', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Righteousness_Doing_Right_by_God_and_People_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/righteousness-doing-right-by-god-and-people', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1057, 3, 'The Day of Pentecost', '<p>This teaching examines several aspects of the Day of Pentecost including the names of Pentecost in the Old Testament and the offerings and what they signified. Also presented is clear evidence that on the Day of Pentecost the Apostles were not in an upper room, but in the Temple itself, and shows the significance of Pentecost in the life of believers today, especially in light of the manifestations of the gift of holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 23:14; 34:23; Deut. 16:16; Lev. 23:9-11, 15-17, 21; Acts 1:8; 2:1-18,33; John 7:27-39; Ezek. 11:19; 36:26,27; Eph. 1:13,14; Matt. 12:44; 1 Pet. 2:5; Exod. 19:9-25; 20:1-2; Luke 24:50-53</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-05-14', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:46', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/The_Day_of_Pentecost.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-day-of-pentecost', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1058, 3, 'Stir Up the Gift', '<p>Every believer has a service to perform &mdash;something God has equipped and enabled them to do, a &ldquo;gift&rdquo; ministry. The subject of our gift ministries is approached in four parts: the background of Paul&rsquo;s phrase, &ldquo;stir up the gift;&rdquo; the meaning of &ldquo;stir up the gift;&rdquo; keys to recognizing our individual gifts, callings, and service; and ways our gifts can be fitted together to build up the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:3-7; Rom. 12:1-8; Eph. 4:1,7-8, 11-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:30', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Stir_Up_the_Gift.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/stir-up-the-gift', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1059, 3, 'What About the Rapture?', '<p>This teaching takes a thorough look into the biblical evidence for the Rapture, including its purpose, meaning, places where it is referenced in Scripture, and more. The Rapture is a great part of every Christian&rsquo;s hope. A scriptural understanding of what it is and the intricacies surrounding it are laid out simply in this teaching.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 9:7; 61:1-3; 63:1, 4; 65:17, 19-23, 25; Jer. 32:37; Dan. 7:13; Zech. 9:9-10; Matt. 16:13-16, 21-22; 23:34-35; 24:3, 9; John 12:32-34; 1 Cor. 15:51-54; Eph. 3:2-3, 5; 1 Thess. 1:10; 4:15-18; 5:2, 9; 2 Thess. 2:1-2, 7; Rev. 1:4, 9-10; 2:1, 4, 7, 9-10, 14, 16, 20, 23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:18:10', 0, 0, 'heaven, appearing, gathering', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/March_2019.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-about-the-rapture', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 170, null),
(1060, 3, 'Experiencing Ephesians in Love', '<p>This teaching explores the theme of love that is woven throughout the Book of Ephesians. Taking a look into many passages surrounding the story of God&rsquo;s purpose through the ages, this teaching unfurls a powerful love story between God and mankind through paths of redemption, promise, calling, restoration, commission and more.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:4; 2:4; 3:16-19; 4:1, 15-16; 5:1-2, 25-33; 6:23-24</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '48:07', 0, 0, 'eternal, heart, understanding', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/February_2019.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/experiencing-ephesians-in-love', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1061, 3, 'Trust God and Let Go', '<p>The teacher takes us into Hebrews and points out how the Old Testament believers trusted in the promises of God. In the New Testament, the Apostle Paul also is a great example of trusting God and letting go of his credentials and past. By following these examples in the Old and New Testaments, we also can trust God, &ldquo;let go,&rdquo; and grow into an intimate relationship with Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11; 12:1-3; Phil. 3</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:14', 0, 0, 'Assurance, confidence', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/January_2019.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/trust-god-and-let-go', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1062, 3, 'Evangelism - Giving the Greatest Gift', '<p>How can you help someone receive the greatest gift&mdash;everlasting life? This teaching explores the topic of evangelism from many angles, including why evangelism is so important, why it&rsquo;s risky, and why it&rsquo;s ultimately worth it. Included are helpful, practical tips on how to be an ambassador for Christ in a way that engages people and helps show them the love, power, and reality of God.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:7; Mark 8:36-37; Luke 15:4-7; Acts 1:8; Rom. 10:14-15; 1 Cor. 2:14-16; 3:9; 14:5, 6, 22; 2 Cor. 2:14-16; 3:4-6; 5:10, 17-20; Eph. 6:19; Phil. 2:25-28; Col. 4:2-4; 1 Thess. 2:19-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:48', 0, 0, 'Witness, Outreach', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/December_2018.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/evangelism-giving-the-greatest-gift', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1063, 3, 'God''s Seal of Ownership', '<p>The Book of Ephesians is the apex of all communication regarding the Body of Christ with Jesus as the head, and the blessings we have as believers who are part of the Body of Christ. Chapters 1-3 of Ephesians present our position in Christ, and Chapter 1 in particular presents our place in God&rsquo;s plan and in His family in that we are sealed with the promised holy spirit.</p> <p>Visit <a href="https://stfonline.org/pdf/Ephesians-Diagram.pdf" target="_blank">this link</a> for a Greek Diagram of Ephesians 1:1-14.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:3-14; 4:30; 2 Cor. 1:21-22; Est. 8:8; Rom. 15:28; Heb. 6:13-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:37', 0, 0, 'Covenant, Guarantee', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/November_2018.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/gods-seal-of-ownership', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(1064, 3, 'Family Unity', '<p>This three-part teaching explores the topic of unity in our Christian walk. The first segment brings insight regarding care, respect, and submission between husbands and wives. The next addresses the parent/child relationship, how our earthly parental relationships reflect our relationship with God. The final segment explores the master/servant relationship, and the necessity for love, care, honor and respect for others.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 5:21-6:4; 1:4; Col. 3:18; Heb. 12:12; Mark 14:32-36</p> <p>Teacher: Gary, Karen, Grace and Caitlyn Theisen</p>', '2018-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '49:14', 0, 0, 'marriage, humility', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/October_2018_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/family-unity', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1065, 3, 'A Look into Ezekiel', '<p>This teaching introduces us to the prophet Ezekiel, focusing on the first 3 chapters of the Book of Ezekiel, which, although difficult to understand, contain many lessons we can learn from Ezekiel&rsquo;s life and visions. The teaching includes a vivid description of God&rsquo;s chariot throne, His glory, and His commands to speak His words whether others listen or not.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 1-3; Gen. 1:7; 18:1; 1 Tim. 6:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:31', 0, 0, 'Cherubim; Firmament', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Sept_2018_-_A_Look_into_Ezekiel.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/a-look-into-ezekiel', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1066, 3, 'Free Will', '<p>This teaching covers the concept of free will in the Bible and Christian life, exploring God&rsquo;s interplay with us as we choose day-to-day whether to honor God and do His will, or to simply accomplish our own agenda. All decisions, good or bad, have consequences. Godly choices lead to Godly results. His desire for us is to voluntarily choose to love Him and be a part of His family.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:3-4; Phil. 2:13; Rom. 7:15-25; 8:1-4; 10:9-13; 2 Tim. 4:8; Gal. 6:7; Matt. 6:9-10; 26:30-34</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2018-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:13', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/August_2018_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/free-will', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1067, 3, 'Blessing One Another', '<p>Many Christians do not realize that the biblical phrase &ldquo;one another&rdquo; refers specifically to Christians. God commands us to act for the benefits of &ldquo;one another&rdquo; in specific ways. This teaching explores how &ldquo;one another&rdquo; is used in the New Testament, offering practical advice for how we can best support and uplift one another in genuine love as we strive to obey God and strengthen the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 4:31; 5:13; 6:10; John 1:12; 13:34-35; 1 John 3:2, 9-11; Rom. 1:13; 12:10, 16; 14:13, 19; 15:5, 7, 14, 17; Matt. 22:34; Mark 12:29-30; Deut. 6:4; Lev. 19:18; 1 Thess. 4:9,18; 5:15; 1 Tim. 1:22; Col. 1:28; 3:9,13,15; 1 Cor. 11:33; Eph. 4:2,32; 5:21; 1 Pet. 4:10, 19; 5:5; Heb. 10:24; James 4:11; 5:9, 16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:07', 0, 0, 'Relationships', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/July_2018_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/blessing-one-another', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1068, 3, 'Rewards in the Future Kingdom', '<p>The subject of rewards in the coming Kingdom of Christ on earth is not very well understood. However, rewards are addressed in dozens of verses, which explain the kinds of rewards we can earn, how our inheritance can be a reward, and whether or not we can lose our rewards. When Christ sets up his kingdom, he will reward each person based on what they have done in this life.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 19; Heb. 2:14; 11:24; 12:1-2; Acts 3:20-21; 27:20; Isa. 35:1-7; Ps. 62:12; Prov. 24:12; Eccles. 12:13-14; Matt. 5:5, 12; 16:27; 19:27; Jer. 17:10; Ezek. 33:20; 37:9-14; Rom. 2:6; 6:5; 10:9; 1 Cor. 6:9-10, 24-37; 15:58; 2 Cor. 5:10; Gal. 5:19-21; 6:9; Phil. 4:17; 2 Tim. 2:5-13; 4:7; 1 Thess. 4:6; Col. 3:23; Eph. 1:14; 5:5; Mal. 3:16; 2 John 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:41', 0, 0, 'Motivation; Obedience', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/June_2018_-_Rewards_in_the_Future_Kingdom.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/rewards-in-the-future-kingdom', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 29, null),
(1069, 3, 'Can Anything Separate Us From the Love of God?', '<p>One of the believer&rsquo;s privileges set forth in the book of Romans is &ldquo;eternal life.&rdquo; This teaching explores what it means to be &ldquo;more than a conqueror &ldquo;in Christ by illustrating that the theme of Romans is the &ldquo;good news&rdquo; of Jesus Christ. An overview of chapters 1-8 of Romans reveals the scope of the epistle, clearly portraying the way to salvation and eternal life.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:15-18; 2:1, 9-12, 28-29; 3:1-2, 20-24, 30; 4:1, 3, 9-10, 24; 5:1, 6, 8-12, 15-19; 6:1-6, 8; 7:7, 13, 24-25; 8:1-2, 30-39; Eph. 2:5-6; Col. 2:20; 3:1, 3-4; 2 Tim. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:06', 0, 0, 'security', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/May_2018_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/can-anything-separate-us-from-the-love-of-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1070, 3, 'Fulfilling Your Function in the Body of Christ', '<p>Understand the work that God has called each of us to is vital as our effectiveness for Christ depends on our understanding of our calling. The road to discovering our individual function in the Body of Christ is explored through key sections from the Book of Acts.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 5:27-39; 9:1-6, 10-16, 19-22, 26-30; 10:1-5, 9-16; 11:1-4, 18-26; 13:1-3; 2 Cor. 10:12-18; Rom. 12:1-8; Eph. 4:7, 11-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2018-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:08', 0, 0, 'growth', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/April_2018_Fulfilling_Your_Function_in_the_Body_of_Christ_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/fulfilling-your-function-in-the-body-of-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1071, 3, 'Living Wholeheartedly', '<p>Going through life our hearts can become numb and unable to fully experience the depths of joy and love. We may become afraid to feel the pain and sadness that come from the same place as joy and love. This teaching explores the steps we can take to heal and acquire strength for the journey to live life with our whole heart.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 22:14, 15; 27:7-8, 13, 14; 34:18; 36:7-10; 87:7; 133:1; 139:23-24; 147:3; Prov. 4:23; 14:10; 16:22; 27:19; Rom. 10:9-10; 12:15-16, 18; Matt. 22:37-39; 25:14-30; Jer. 17:9; 29:13; Luke 1:37; 6:45; Exod. 25:8; 1 Cor. 3:16; Gal. 4:6; Heb. 3:6-8; 10:19-22; Mark 14:34; Zech. 7:12; John 4:14; 13:35; 14:2; 17:20-24; Eph. 3:16-20; 4:3; Col. 3:13-14; 1 Sam. 61:1</p> <p>Teacher: Caitlyn Theisen</p>', '2018-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '49:29', 0, 0, 'Courage, honesty, peace', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/March_2018_Living_Wholeheartedly_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/living-wholeheartedly', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1072, 3, 'When It Hurts to Bend the Knee', '<p>There is more to worshipping God than attending church or singing praises. Worship involves sacrifice. Becoming a disciple is an act of worship. It is about obeying God even when we don&rsquo;t feel like it. Being a follower of Christ means we must forsake ourselves and follow him, no matter the cost.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:24-25; 10:37-40; Col. 3:23-24; Rom. 12:1-2; Mark 12:30; Isa. 29:13; John 4:23-24; 1 Pet. 2:4-5; 1 Cor. 3:16; 2 Cor. 3:18; Eph. 4:20-24</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2018-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:58', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/February_2018_When_It_Hurts_to_Bend_the_Knee_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/when-it-hurts-to-bend-the-knee', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1073, 3, 'Thinking Like God Thinks', '<p>Examples from the Torah and Christ&rsquo;s life, show that not only is it possible to think like God does, but it is also a vital part of living a godly life. If we want to conduct ourselves in a way that serves and honors God, we must immerse ourselves in His way of thinking so we can be imitators of Christ and, therefore, imitators of God.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 1:2-4; 55:3, 6-8; 56:1; Eph. 5:1; John 7:24; 14:9; 1 Cor. 11:1; Acts 13:22; Rom. 12:1-2; Phil. 2:5; Matt. 7:1-2; Mark 1:35; Luke 22:42; 24:44; Josh. 1:7; Ps. 1:1-2; Exod. 21:1-4, 23-25, 28-29, 33-34; 22:14-15; 23:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2018-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:44', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/January_2018_Thinking_Like_God_Thinks_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/thinking-like-god-thinks', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 61, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1074, 3, 'Crisis in Colossae', '<p>The Book of Philemon contains amazing insights into personal relationships among believers. Paul&rsquo;s letter reveals much about how the Body of Christ is to work together in unity and forgiveness. This deep look into Paul&rsquo;s demonstrated love for Onesimus and Philemon explores how the blend of grace and truth can translate into our lives and encourage us to walk in love even through difficult situations.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 4:7-9; Philem. 1-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2017-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:34', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/December_2017_Crisis_in_Colossae_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/crisis-in-colossae', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1075, 3, 'Jesus - The Red Thread', '<p>Throughout Scripture, we are presented with many accounts of people who walked bravely down the path of God&rsquo;s will that was laid out before them. Each one points toward a bigger picture, Jesus Christ, and together they form the &ldquo;red thread&rdquo; of scripture. This teaching explores the source of bravery in several people of the Bible, illustrating how these accounts parallel and point toward the coming Savior.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 18:15-16; Num. 13:30-33; 14:1-16; 1 Sam. 17:1-37; Eph. 1:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: Janet Speakes</p>', '2017-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '42:04', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/November_2017_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/jesus-the-red-thread', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1076, 3, 'Making the Most of Your Time / Invest in Your God-Given Talent', '<p>This pair of teachings addresses making the most of the time and talent God has given us. First, explore the importance of doing our best now, because our time in this life is limited. How we spend our time will echo in eternity. Next, the Parable of the Talents shows that each person is talented in his unique way. We are to use our talents, however great or small, to invest in the future kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: (First Teaching) Luke 9:23; 1 Cor. 13:5; Heb. 10:24; (Second teaching) Matt. 25:14-30; 1 Pet. 4:10-11; Rom. 12:3-8; 1 Cor. 12:4-6, 14-31</p> <p>Teacher: Ryan Maher, Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2017-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:07', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/October_2017_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/making-the-most-of-your-time-invest-in-your-god-given-talent', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1077, 3, 'What is Faith?', '<p>The Greek word <em>pistis</em> is often translated &ldquo;faith,&rdquo; but what does it mean? The concept of &ldquo;faith&rdquo; in the Bible is commonly misunderstood. Learn the history of &ldquo;the Word of Faith Movement&rdquo; and how trying to make things happen by &ldquo;just having faith&rdquo; puts an immense amount of pressure on Christians. This teaching helps us understand that while our trust in God and Christ does not force things to happen, there are wonderful effects of trusting God and living wisely.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 23:23; Acts 17:31; Heb. 11:1, 6; 13:5; 2 Cor. 5:1-7; Prov. 23:4; 28:20; Luke 12:15; 1 Tim. 6:8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:13', 0, 0, 'Believing, Receiving', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/September_2017_-_What_is_Faith__.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-is-faith', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 244, null),
(1078, 3, 'Prepare to Win', '<p>Competing in a grueling athletic event requires proper training and preparation. Each Christian has a race course laid out ahead of him and to win our race we must prepare ourselves. We prepare for good works, prepare to give an answer, prepare to resist, prepare to fight, and prepare to endure. Then, after a life of doing our best, we will be warmly welcomed by Jesus Christ at his return.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 3:11-15; 9:25; 2 Tim. 2:19, 21-22; 4:5; Rom. 13:12-14; Prov. 23:26, 17; Eph. 6:10-18; Heb. 10:32-37</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '51:57', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/August_2017_-_Prepare_to_Win.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/prepare-to-win', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1079, 3, 'What in the World Are We Doing?', '<p>As Christians, we are often warned about the perils of getting too involved in the world. We&rsquo;re told not to love the things of the world; not to conform to the world; and to keep the commandment unstained while living in this world. With all these instructions, it can be difficult to know how we should conduct ourselves in the world&mdash;to know what, in the world, we are doing!</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 145:6; 1 Tim. 5:7; 6:11-14; James 1:27; 4:4; 1 John 2:15-17; 5:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2017-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '34:48', 0, 0, 'reproach, identity', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/July_2017_-_What_in_the_World_Are_We_Doing_.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-in-the-world-are-we-doing', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1080, 3, 'Forged in Fire', '<p>Despite the fact that adversity is a part of everyone&rsquo;s life, people exert a lot of effort trying to avoid it. This mindset of seeking ease and comfort can limit us in seeing how God can and does use adversity to work powerfully with us. Having a proper attitude during difficult times helps us develop the character of Christ, increase in godliness, and grow more into the image of our Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:1-2, 12; 45:5; Prov. 17:3; Isa. 48:10; 2 Cor. 11:23-33; Gal. 5:15, 25; Phil. 2:13-14; 1 Thess. 5:6-8; Heb. 4:6; 12:4-8; James 1:2-4, 12; 5:10-11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:01', 0, 0, 'Blame, Comfort, Grief', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/June2017-ForgedinFire.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/forged-in-fire', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1081, 3, 'Understanding Wisdom Literature in the Bible', '<p>The Bible employs many figures of speech; it also contains poetry and wisdom literature that are written in a non-literal way. In biblical cultures &ldquo;wisdom statements&rdquo; were well-understood, but in our much more straightforward and factual writing of today, those statements can be confusing. This teaching shows how wisdom statements can be clarified in light of the scope of Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 25:21-23; 1 Kings 22:15; Ps. 1:6; Prov. 11:31; 13:5; 15:6; 16:3, 7; 18:3; 22:6; Isa. 55:12; Matt. 5:13, Rom. 13:3; 1 Pet. 3:13; 1 John 1:8; 3:1-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:25', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/May-2017-Understanding-Wisdom-Literature-in-the-Bible.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-wisdom-literature-in-the-bible', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1082, 3, 'Focus on the Mission Possible', '<p>The mission of every born-again Christian is to love God with all his heart, soul, mind, and strength, and his neighbor as himself, and to honor and serve Christ. This teaching delves into the Book of Hebrews, exploring the theme of Jesus as the Christ and the reasons why we should spend our energy serving, worshipping, and obeying him, while turning our eyes constantly to follow him.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 1:1-4; 2:1, 5-9, 17-18; 3:1-3, 7-13; 4:1-2, 11-16; 5:11-14; 6:9-12, 19-20; 10:19-25, 35-36; 11:6; 12:1-3, 14-16; 13:1-2, 15-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2017-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:13', 0, 0, 'hope', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/April2017-Focus-on-the-Mission-Possible.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/focus-on-the-mission-possible', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1083, 3, '7 Spiritual Battlefields', '<p>There is an ongoing war raging between good and evil. This three-part teaching looks at seven different spiritual battlefields: arts &amp; entertainment, media, education, government, business/science, religion, and family, explaining how both God and the Devil are fighting to capture our hearts and our loyalty through these media.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 52:7; Ezek. 28:12-15; 1 Cor. 15:33; Eph. 6:12; 1 Tim. 2:1-3; 6:10-11; Heb. 13:5; James 3:12-17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2017-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:53', 0, 0, 'wisdom, worldliness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/March2017-SevenSpiritualBattlefields.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/7-spiritual-battlefields', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1084, 3, 'Persistent Prayer', '<p>Persistent prayer enables us to endure the difficulties we experience in this life. Jesus set the example for us as he, through fervent prayer, endured intense suffering. Through prayer, endurance, and focusing on Jesus, we can truly experience the joy that God wants for us.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:1-3; James 4:1-3; 5:16-20; Isa. 5:14-15; John 9:31; 15:9-17; Ps. 34:15-16; 66:18; 145:19; 1 Cor. 12:1-2; 1 John 3:1-23; Gal. 5:14; Rom. 13:8-10; Matt. 22:37-40</p> <p>Teacher: John Truitt</p>', '2017-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:19', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/February2017-Persistent-Prayer.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/persistent-prayer', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1085, 3, 'Joy and Forgiveness', '<p>Suffering is a universal problem, and almost as universal is the hurt, anger, resentment, and bitterness that can accompany or follow suffering. The Apostle Paul suffered as a prisoner in Rome, yet he wrote, &ldquo;Now I rejoice in my sufferings for you.&rdquo; If we are going to have joy in life we must let go of unforgiveness and resentment.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:4; 2 Cor. 1:5; 5:10; Phil. 3:10; 1 Peter 4:13; Rom. 8:22-27, 32; Matt. 5:11-12; Col. 1:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2017-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '55:43', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/January2017-JoyandForgiveness.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/joy-and-forgiveness', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 86, null),
(1086, 3, '3 Weeks in Thessalonica', '<p>During the Apostle Paul&rsquo;s time in Thessalonica he encouraged believers to build one another up, bless each other, and assist each other in creating and growing a lasting work in the Lord. Scripture provides this wonderful example of serving the Lord and our fellow believers.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:9, 25, 34-40; 17:1-10; Eph. 4:6; 1 Thess. 1:2-6; 2:1-11, 17; 3:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: David Hanson</p>', '2016-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '45:13', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Dec2016-3-Weeks-in-Thessalonica.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/3-weeks-in-thessalonica', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1087, 3, 'Begin with the End in Mind', '<p>Many successful people have accomplished great things by beginning their efforts with the end goal in mind. This idea applies to our Christian walk, and the Bible provides examples of it in both the Old and New Testaments. Scripture exhorts us to hold our end goal in mind.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 51:11-12; 1 Cor. 1:4-9; 9:1-19; John 8:45-58</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2016-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:55', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Nov2016-Begin-with-the-End-in-Mind.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/begin-with-the-end-in-mind', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1088, 3, 'Unity', '<p>Deep in every person&rsquo;s heart is a desire to be connected with others, to be known and accepted, to be united with family and friends. As Christians, we often feel the tug for unity but lack an understanding of how to achieve it. This teaching explores the subject of unity from the three perspectives in Scripture: Unity of the Spirit, Unity of the Faith, and Unity of Fellowship.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:9-10; 4:1-3; John 13:35; 17:11; 1 John 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:25', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/October2016-Unity.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/unity', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1089, 3, 'Father Figures', '<p>One of the most fundamentally important relationships is the one that exists between a father and a child. It is no coincidence that one of the primary ways God relates to people &ndash;specifically to the Body of Christ&mdash;is as a Father figure. This teaching gives greater insight into the relationship between God and His children, and how this bond enriches and empowers us to serve God and others.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 3:1; 5:3; Ps. 68:4-5; James 1:27; Jer. 49:8-11; Luke 15:11-32; Matt. 5:43-48; Eph. 5:1; 2 Tim. 2:2; 1 Thess. 2:10-11; Col. 1:27</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2016-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:22', 0, 0, 'parenting', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/September-2016-Father-Figures.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/father-figures', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1090, 3, 'Living Behind Enemy Lines', '<p>The cry of God&rsquo;s heart through the ages, &ldquo;Let my people go!&rdquo; finally became a spiritual reality when Christ escaped the hold of the grave, rising forever from the dead. But until the day comes when we are gathered to Christ, we must continue to live behind enemy lines. This teaching presents strategies we can employ in order to live and thrive until the final victory.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16-17; Heb. 10:24; 11:9-10, 13-14, 16; Phil. 3:18-21; Rom. 8:24; Eph. 2:5; 6:12; 1 Cor. 1:18; Phil 2:12; 2 Cor. 2:11; John 10:10; 1 Pet. 1:13; 4:7; 5:8; Col. 2:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:02', 0, 0, 'Encouragement, Endurance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/August2016-LivingBehindEnemyLines.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/living-behind-enemy-lines', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1091, 3, 'Love Your Neighbor As Yourself', '<p>Jesus taught us that the second most important commandment in the whole Bible is to love our neighbors as we love ourselves. Despite this, there is often a surprising lack of love in the Christian community. This teaching focuses on why we should love our neighbor, how we already love ourselves, and practical ways to demonstrate loving behavior towards others.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:14-18; 12:1-2; 14:1-3, 10-15; Gal. 5:16-17, 19-23; Ps. 73:1-4, 12-17, 24; Matt. 5:16, 22, 29-30, 43-44, 46; 22:39; 2 Pet. 1:5-7, 10-12; 1 John 2:28; 1 Cor. 3:16-17; 15:33; 2 John 1:8; Eph. 4:29; 5:25-29; Phil. 2:3; Isa. 5:20; 2 Cor. 3:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:48', 0, 0, 'judgment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/July2016-LoveYourNeighborAsYourself.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/love-your-neighbor-as-yourself', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1092, 3, 'The Bible: Told Through Story', '<p>Our minds are specifically designed for stories, and story is a powerful force in our daily lives. The Bible is a fascinating narrative, a not-yet finished story of God&rsquo;s ongoing dealings with people throughout history. We are all invited to be a part of this story.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:21', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/June-2016-The-Bible-Told-Through-Story.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-bible-told-through-story', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1093, 3, 'The Wedding Banquet of the Lamb', '<p>The &ldquo;wedding banquet of the Lamb&rdquo; is spoken of in Revelation 19 and Isaiah 25, and is a topic of much misinterpretation. This teaching demonstrates that this banquet is part of the celebration of the inauguration of Jesus Christ as king over the earth at the start of the Millennial Kingdom. All saved people will enjoy this banquet with the King of Kings.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 19:6-8; Isa. 2:1-4; 25:6-7; 30:6, 23-24; 51:3; Amos 9:13; Gen. 12:3; Zech. 8:22; Matt. 8:11-12; 21:45-46; 22:1, 3-9; 25:1, 10; 26:29; Luke 13:28-30; 14:1-2, 7-8, 10, 12-18, 21; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:15', 0, 0, 'wedding', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/May-2016-The-Wedding-Banquet-of-the-Lamb.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-wedding-banquet-of-the-lamb', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 147, null),
(1094, 3, 'The Covenants of God', '<p>God is the ruler of His Creation, and He will bring to pass the things He has promised. To truly understand the richness of God&rsquo;s plan as given to man in His sacred word, it is essential to understand covenants. This teaching shows how God has worked with mankind throughout history and continues to work through covenants to bring to pass His plans and purposes.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 16:9; 2 Chron. 20:6; Lev. 2:13; Heb. 8:8; 9:15, 19-21; Hosea 6:7; Gen. 3:15, 21; 9:4-5, 9; 22:17-18; Exod. 19:5-6; Jer. 31:31-34; Matt. 26:28; John 3:16; 2 Cor. 3:3; Isa. 59:21; Ezek. 11:19-20; 1 Cor. 15:24-28</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:51', 0, 0, 'sovereignty, dispensation, administration', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/April-2016-TheCovenantsofGod.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-covenants-of-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(1095, 3, 'The Revelation Manifestations', '<p>Understanding the receiving of revelation from God and the Lord Jesus Christ includes ascertaining it as a message of knowledge or wisdom to the gift of holy spirit born inside the believer. That message is then given to the mind or body in any of seven ways: seeing, hearing, smelling, tasting, touching, just knowing or through strong emotion.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:7-8; Exod. 19:25; 20:1,18-19; Deut. 5:4; Eph. 3:16; 4:24; Col. 3:10; 2 Cor. 4:16; 2 Kings 4:38-40; 6:13-17; 1 Sam. 3:4-10; 11:4-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2016-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:35', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/March-2016-The-Revelation-Manifestations.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-revelation-manifestations', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1096, 3, 'Pride', '<p>Jesus taught that the greatest commandment of all is to love God with all your heart, soul, mind, and strength. Conversely the greatest sin would be loving something or someone more than God. This teaching demonstrates that everyone struggles with pride in life and explores practical ways to lessen pride&rsquo;s grip, enabling believers to better love and serve God.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> 1 Cor. 1:31; 2 Cor. 9:2; Pro. 8:13; 13:10; 14:3; 16:5, 18; Ps. 10:4; 40:4; 73:6-9; 2 Chron. 26:16-21; 1 John 2:16; Ezek. 28:2, 12-19; Isa. 14:12-17; James 4:1-3, 6, 10.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:55', 0, 0, 'humility', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/february-2016-pride.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/pride', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(1097, 3, 'Offended', '<p>Today more and more people are feeling offended by the thoughts and actions of others. The spirit of offense is behind much of this tension as it engenders frustration, resentment, anger, and bitterness between people. The result is an increasing loss of compassion, coldness, and even hatred. This teaching helps the believer to explore godly solutions to free themselves from the enemy&rsquo;s trap of being &ldquo;offended.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:19; 2 Cor. 4:3-4; Eph 4:26-27, 31; Prov. 19:11; 22:24; 29:22; 30:33; Col. 3:8; 2 Tim. 2:23-26; Matt. 15:12-14</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2016-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:10', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/january2016-Offended.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/offended', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1098, 3, 'God&rsquo;s Divine Council', '<p>Little known by the Christian Church is the fact that God has an inner divine council of spirit beings with whom He works to administer the universe. This makes sense when one considers the way God works with mankind and with Jesus Christ. This teaching scripturally shows that this divine council has actively helped God in the past and will continue in that role in the future.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26, 28; 2:15; Deut. 16:18; Eph. 1:22-23; 3:14-15; 4:11-12; Rev. 3:14; 4:1-4; Matt. 19:28; Isa. 1:26; 6:8; 14:12-14; Jer. 23:3-4, 16-18, 21-22; 1 Cor. 6:2; 8:5; Heb. 7:1; Ps. 82:1; 89:5-8; Job 1:6; 15:8; Dan. 4:13-14,16-17, 23-24; 7:8-10, 25-26; 1 Kings 22:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:39', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Dec2015-GodsDivineCouncil.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/gods-divine-council', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 274, null),
(1099, 3, 'That&rsquo;s Ironic', '<p>God is a master in His use of irony. Whether verbal or situational, the outcome is often the complete opposite of what was said or seemingly intended. Sometimes the irony is very subtle, but at times it is like a neon sign flashing the words, &ldquo;God is at work here!&rdquo; The scriptures reviewed here show God&rsquo;s use of irony for emphasis in the Bible.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 18:27, 38-39; Esther 6:3-12; 7:9-10; Gen. 3:15; 37:10; 43:26; 1 Sam. 5:1-12; 17:33, 49; Josh. 6:17, 25; 2 Sam. 11:2-11; Dan. 1:12-16; 6:1-24; Rev. 16:21; Matt. 16:18; 26:69-75; Mark 1:40-45; 7:9; 1 Cor. 1:27</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:56', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/November2015-Thats-Ironic.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/thats-ironic', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1100, 3, 'Mature in Christ', '<p>It should be the goal of every Christian to become mature in Christ. But if we have the wrong idea about what that means, we can set goals for ourselves that are unattainable and that leave us feeling defeated. Believers may have problems in this world, but mature believers seek to do God&rsquo;s will even in the midst of trouble and are centered on serving others.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:3-4; 5:23; 1 Cor. 8:1; 13:1-4; James 1:19-27; Rom. 7:15-18; 15:25-26; Gal. 4:12-14; John 4:34; 5:30; 6:38; 8:29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '46:05', 0, 0, 'Discouragement, Endurance, Health', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/October2015-Mature-in-Christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/mature-in-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1101, 3, 'We Ought to Obey God Rather Than Men', '<p>In Acts 5 the Apostles declared &ldquo;We ought to obey God rather than men.&rdquo; In many cultures and societies around the world, we are seeing increasing attacks on Christian values and the passage of laws that contradict the ways of God. This teaching explores the concept of obedience to God as it relates to the realms of our personal, family, church, civil, and corporate lives.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 1:15-21; 1 Sam. 15:1-3, 22; Dan. 6:6-10; Matt. 12:50; 14:4; 22:17-22; 28:19-20; Luke 11:27-28; Acts 5:27; Rom. 13:1-2, 5; Eph. 4:11-12; 6:5-7; Heb. 12:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:49', 0, 0, 'Witnessing, government, influence', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/September-2015-We-Ought-to-Obey-God-Rather-Than-Men.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/we-ought-to-obey-god-rather-than-men', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1102, 3, 'Rough Weather Ahead', '<p>Many parts of the world are experiencing weather patterns that are unprecedented in recent history. This should not be surprising as the Bible clearly ties weather patterns to the behavior of the people in a country. This three-segment teaching covers the nature of the earth as a war zone between Good and Evil, that people have an effect on what happens on earth, including the weather, and what Christians can do about it.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 5:19; 2 Cor. 4:4; Exod. 15:3; Ps. 68:21; 107:33-34; Matt. 6:10, 33; Deut. 11:13-17; 28:1-8, 11-12, 14-25, 38-40; Lev. 18:24-25; Jer. 3:2-3; 7:12-18; 12:4; 23:10; Amos 4:6-7, 9-10; 2 Tim. 4:1-5; Luke 22:35-36; Isa. 61:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:54', 0, 0, 'Consequences, blessings, curses', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/august2015-rough-weather-ahead.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/rough-weather-ahead', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1103, 3, 'Effective Witnessing for Christ', '<p>Jesus directed his followers to be witnesses for him. Yet so many in the Body of Christ are not actively spreading the Good News. This teaching examines the problems that keep Christians from witnessing and provides practical solutions that will help many become more comfortable and effective in witnessing to others so that we all can become effective ambassadors for Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:16-20; John 3:16; Acts 1:8; 5:18-20; 7:1-3; 17:16-24; Rom. 1:21-23; 2 Cor. 5:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:45', 0, 0, 'Evangelism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/July-2015-Effective-Witnessing-for-Christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/effective-witnessing-for-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1104, 3, 'Be Strong in the Lord', '<p>Life is too difficult for Christians to be mentally, physically, and spiritually successful without help from the Lord. The Bible encourages us to be strong in the Lord, and that is a must if we are going to succeed as God&rsquo;s workers, athletes, warriors, and ambassadors. This teaching examines 5 simple points for staying positive, being engaged in life, and being effective ambassadors for God.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 5:30-31, 14:14; Gen. 42:36; 1 Cor. 10:13; Eccles. 9:11-12; Gen. 3:17-19; Eph. 6:10-13, 4:26; Ps. 4:4; Prov. 3:24; Eccles. 7:21-22; 2 Cor. 10:5; Jer. 12:1-5; Isa. 50:7; Ps. 73:1-5, 8-9, 11-19, 21, 23-25; Heb. 10:32-37; 1 Cor. 15:58</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:22', 0, 0, 'attitude', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/June-2015-Be-Strong-in-the-Lord.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/be-strong-in-the-lord', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1105, 3, 'Faith Lessons from Everyday Life', '<p>Most Christians understand that God is our spiritual Father, but don&rsquo;t realize that, like any loving father, He wants to be intimately involved in our lives, providing instruction, education, and training on a daily basis. All of creation is designed to teach us about God, and God has always taught His people through the natural world. This teaching demonstrates how He does that, citing many biblical and personal examples.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:5-11; Deut. 8:5; Prov. 3:11-12; Rom. 8:28; Gen. 45:4-5; John 15:1-2; Rom. 8:5-6; Col. 1:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:46', 0, 0, 'maturity', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2015_faith_lessons_from_everyday_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/faith-lessons-from-everyday-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1106, 3, 'Take Control of Your Life', '<p>It can be very unsettling to feel like we are out of control of our lives. Yet we all face unwanted circumstances that we may not be able to change. The Bible says that Satan enslaves people through fear. While we may not be able to change our circumstances, we can still be in control of ourselves. Jesus showed us how to do that, even in the face of experiencing horrific torture and death.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 2:14-15; 11:24-26, 35; 12:2; 1 John 5:16-19; 1 Cor 10:13; Eph. 5:1-2; Ps. 77:12; Mark 8:31; John 13:11, 27, 18:1-8; Matt. 26:47-54; John 18:19, 33-38; 19:8-12; 1 Tim. 6:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:36', 0, 0, 'perseverance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/april2015_take_control_of_your_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/take-control-of-your-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 72, null),
(1107, 3, 'Children of the Light', '<p>The number of descriptions in God&rsquo;s Word comparing God and light indicate a deeper reality than many have realized. This teaching examines properties of light, including some recent discoveries, as well as many vivid descriptions of God, other spiritual beings, and light in the Bible. This illuminates why one day, when our bodies are transformed, we will live with God and Jesus in a place that needs no sun or moon.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 18:28; 37:4; 2 Cor. 6:14; 11:13; Gen. 1:1-2; 1 John 1:5; Dan. 2:19; 7:9; 12:2-3; Ex. 3:2; 13:21; 24:17; 34:29-33; Ezek. 1:28; 2 Sam. 22:13, 15; Num. 16:35; Isa. 14:12; 60:2, 5, 19; John 8:12; 9:5; 12:35-36; Matt. 17:1, 3; Rev. 1:12, 13; 22:5; 21:22; Eph. 5:7-8; 1 Thess. 5:5; Judges 5:31; Phil. 2:14; Prov. 13:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:22', 0, 0, 'science, dna', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2015_children_of_the_light.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/children-of-the-light', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1108, 3, 'The Book of Esther', '<p>The Book of Esther is packed with powerful, practical lessons and wisdom for life. Expository teaching is contrasted with topical teaching, demonstrating how we can learn the valuable lessons that God placed in the text of the Bible. Buried deep in the pages of Esther, we learn the value of boldness, sacrifice, graciousness, thankfulness, and looking for ways to let our light shine on this earth.</p> <p>Verses: Esther 1:1-5, 10-11, 14-15, 19; 2:1-2, 5-8, 10-17, 21-23; 3:1-2, 6, 7-11, 13; 4:8-17; 5:1-10, 14; 6:1-14; 7:1-10; 8:1-5, 17; Eccles. 11:3; John 8:44</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2015-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:50', 0, 0, 'Boldness, Purim', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2015_the_book_of_esther.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-book-of-esther', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1109, 3, 'Love is…', '<p>The desire for love and the capacity to love have been hardwired into every human being. Most people do not recognize when they love in a worldly way or in a godly way. Knowing the difference between the two is essential if Christians are truly going to love as God loves. This teaching gives perspective on what it means to love God&rsquo;s way.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:16; 2:13; 3:16; Luke 11:43; John 3:16, 19; 12:42-43; 21:14-19; 2 Tim. 4:10; 2 Pet. 2:15; Eph. 5:1; 1 Cor. 13:3-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2015-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '53:34', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2015_love_is.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/love-is', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 50, null),
(1110, 3, 'Battling Discouragement and Shame', '<p>Two natures, sin nature and the nature of God, reside within an individual who is born again of God&rsquo;s spirit, and those natures war against each other. So we sin. Often worse than the sin itself is the shame and condemnation we feel because of our sin. Scripture teaches us what we can do to mitigate our feelings of failure and shame that often derail our walk with God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:9; Ps. 103:11-14; 2 Cor. 7:8-11; 1 Cor. 15:54-56; Rom. 4:14-15; 5:20; 6:9-11; 7:1-25; Gal. 5:16-17.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:43', 0, 0, 'guilt', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2014_battling_discouragement_and_shame.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/battling-discouragement-and-shame', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1111, 3, 'Maturing in Love', '<p>Learning that God loves you is an amazing and necessary first step for a relationship with God. Maturing in that relationship and love includes discovering how real Jesus is, how Jesus and God have equipped all believers for discipleship, and how the gifts and ministries given help Christians grow. Altogether, this helps Christians become imitators of Jesus, strengthening unity in the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; 1 John 4:9-11; Matt. 28:18-19; 5:43-48; Acts 9:3-6; Eph. 4:1-4, 11-13; 6:18; 1 Cor. 10:33-11:1; 2 Thess. 2:16; 1 Thess. 2:11-12; Rom. 14:19; Col. 1:27-29; John 14:12; 18:4</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2014-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '40:33', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2014_maturing_in_love.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/maturing-in-love', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1112, 3, 'Sons of God – Led by the Spirit', '<p>God&rsquo;s desire has always been to have a relationship with mankind. For much of man&rsquo;s existence, God has been limited in the type of relationship He can have. The &ldquo;Old Covenant thinking&rdquo; of mankind creates the limitation. &ldquo;New Covenant thinking&rdquo; embraces our relationship to God as His children and helps us mature into being led by the spirit of God within us.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 26:1-5; Rom. 2:14-16; 5:20; 8:1-4, 14-15; Exod. 19:56; Deut. 14:2; Gal. 3:24; Jer. 31:31-33; Luke 22:20; Matt. 26:28; Heb. 8:13; 9:15; Eph. 2:14-16, 18; 2 Cor. 3:6; John 16:12; Phil. 1:29-30; Prov. 1:3; 2:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:20', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct_2014_sons_of_god_led_by_the_spirit.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/sons-of-god-led-by-the-spirit', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1113, 3, 'The First and Greatest Commandment', '<p>What is the first and greatest commandment? Jesus was asked this and quoted from Deuteronomy. Having a full understanding of the Gospel record and the Old Testament commandment helps us understand that God &ldquo;alone&rdquo; is to be our God. Also, understanding some secondary meanings of the commandment help us to love Him with &ldquo;all&rdquo; our heart, soul, and might.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 12:28-34; Deut. 6:4-5; 4:35, 39; Zech. 14:19; 13:2; Isa. 2:20; Luke 2:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:59', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sept_2014_first_greatest_commandment.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-first-and-greatest-commandment', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1114, 3, 'Don&rsquo;t Be Defeated By Sin', '<p>Christians are God&rsquo;s children, and He loves us with an undying love. This simple truth is most profound, yet how often we forget it! We disobey; we make mistakes. We feel badly about our sins. Sometimes we get so caught up in our feelings of failure that we forget God loves us. Worse, we can begin to believe that He does not love us, is angry with us, or is marshaling His spiritual forces against us. We need to get past these feelings, and we can!</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:8-9; 3:1-2; Rom. 3:10-18, 23-24; 5:1, 8, 20; 6:11; 7:14-25; 8:3, 18, 31-39; Rev. 12:10; Ps. 103:2-17; 1 Sam. 1:6-8; 17:28-29; 1 Pet. 3:14, 17; 2 Tim. 3:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:24', 0, 0, 'forgiveness, faithfulness, discouragement', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/august_2014_dont_be_defeated_by_sin.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/dont-be-defeated-by-sin', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 70, null),
(1115, 3, 'Forgive and Forget', '<p>One of the biggest psychological burdens we face is unresolved anger and bitterness toward someone who has hurt us. God instructs us to forgive offense just as He, because of His great love for us, has forgiven us. When we ask God for forgiveness, He not only forgives us but forgets our sin. When we have forgiven someone else, the process of repairing the damaged trust can begin.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:12; 4:30-32; Matt. 5:25; 18:21; Luke 17:4; Col. 3:13; 2 John 1:5-8; Ps. 103:8-14; Isa. 43:24-25; Rom. 14:10-12; Heb. 4:15-16; 14:13; 2 Cor. 5:10; Rev. 20:12; 1 John 1:9; Phil. 3:13-15;</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '51:04', 0, 0, 'confession, repentance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july_2014_forgive_and_forget.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/forgive-and-forget', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1116, 3, 'Problem or Possibility?', '<p>The world is becoming a darker and darker place; wickedness is on the increase. If we are not careful, our joy and peace can be replaced by a gloomy outlook, anger, or feelings of hopelessness. By keeping in mind that God foretold of this darkness, we can focus on the opportunities we have all around us. A darker world means more chances to be a light in someone&rsquo;s life.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:1-5; 1 Cor. 13:13; Heb. 10:37; 11:6; Phil. 3:20-21; 4:6-9; Col. 3:12-17; Lev. 18:24-25; Ps. 37:10-11; 107:33-34; Jer. 12:4; Hosea 10:4; Matt. 24:6-12; Isa. 11:1-10; Zech. 3:1-2; Jude 1:21-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:54', 0, 0, 'discouragement, fear, endurance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2014_problem_or_possibility.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/problem-or-possibility', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 68, null),
(1117, 3, 'Is the End Really Near? Signs of the End Times', '<p>&ldquo;Is the end really near?&rdquo; Are the various social, political, financial, and even geological upheavals that seem to be taking place throughout the world signs of the &ldquo;end times?&rdquo; Should Christians even be observing &ldquo;signs of the seasons&rdquo; in the first place? Being aware of &ldquo;end-time signs&rdquo; like &ldquo;birth pains&rdquo; can heighten our awareness of the coming events and show the urgency of spreading the message about Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 29:29; Acts 1:6-7; 8:1; 13:50; Matt. 24:2-15, 29; Luke 11:29; 21:5-26; Mark 8:11-12; 13:24-27; Heb. 10:33-34; 11:35-38; 2 Thess. 2:3-4; 2 Tim. 3:1-5; Dan. 9:26-27; 12:4; Isa. 11:1; 43:5-6; Num. 19:2-7; Rev. 6:1-2; 12:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:22', 0, 0, 'wrath, antichrist, tribulation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2014_is_the_end_near.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/is-the-end-really-near-signs-of-the-end-times', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 31, null),
(1118, 3, 'Understanding the Last Supper', '<p>The Last Supper was a pivotal event for the Apostles and for us. Jesus said that he would send a &ldquo;Helper;&rdquo; that he would reveal himself to us and not leave us as orphans; that our status in his eyes changed from servants to friends, and much more. If we are going to understand our relationship with Jesus Christ, we need to understand the points Jesus made during the Last Supper.</p> <p>Verses: John 7:39; 13:1-38; 14:1-31; 15:1-27; 16:1-33; 17:1-26, 18:1; Ezek. 36:26-27; Joel 2:28; Matt. 12:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:30', 0, 0, 'comforter', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/april2014_understanding_the_last_supper.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-the-last-supper', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1119, 3, 'Let&rsquo;s Be Wise', '<p>Life is difficult but living life with wisdom prevents us from making it more difficult. When people live life foolishly making unwise choices, they open the door to spiritual attacks from the Devil. Keeping the end in mind, following the commandments of God, and living with discipline, planning, and self-control leads to blessings in this life and in the life to come.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 1:1-6; Prov. 1:7; 4:7,13; 17:17; 21:17; 24:27; 27:6-9; Eccles. 7:12; 11:4; Matt. 6:19; 7:16; John 10:10; 1 Cor. 3:9; Gal. 5:16-17, 22-23; Eph. 5:15-16; Phil. 1:20; 4:12-14; Titus 1:15; 2 Tim. 3:1-4, 16.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:36', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2014_lets_be_wise.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/lets-be-wise-1', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 81, null),
(1120, 3, 'The Feasts of Israel', '<p>Through the feasts of Israel, God has revealed many details concerning his plan of redemption and the timeline in which events will occur. By gaining an understanding of the feasts, not only will key sections of the Word of God be understood in a new and meaningful way, but also we will gain a greater understanding of Jesus Christ as both a suffering servant and the returning conquering King.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:14; Exod. 13:7; 19:17-19; 23:16; Lev. 23:4-24, 34-43; Deut. 16:4; Ps. 41:9; Isa. 27:13; Ezek. 3:4; Matt. 16:6; 24:31; John 20:17; Rom. 6:1-18; Acts 2:1; 20:6; 1 Cor. 15:20-23, 51; 1 John 1:9; Rev. 11:15.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2014-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:23:10', 0, 0, 'Messiah, Types', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2014_feasts_of_israel.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-feasts-of-israel', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1121, 3, 'Thankfulness and Happiness', '<p>A primary basis of being happy and satisfied in life is being thankful. Rather than presenting thankfulness as an option , the Bible actually commands us to be thankful. Rather than waiting for an event to be thankful for, our thankfulness should come first. The Bible gives us keys and examples to help us be thankful in every situation, good, bad, in plenty or in need.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:8; Ps. 48:9; 71:12; 77:12; Eccles. 11:3; Matt. 6:25-34; Rom. 7:24-25; 12:1-2; 1 Cor. 15:57; Eph. 2:10; 5:20; Phil. 4:6, 8, 11; Col. 2:7; 3:15; 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:18; Heb. 10:25; 13:15; 1 John 1:3.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2014-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:23', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2014_thankfulness_and_happiness.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/thankfulness-and-happiness', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1122, 3, 'Prophetic Foreshadows', '<p>No one will ever properly understand the New Testament without understanding the Old Testament. One of the greatest principles for connecting the two involves understanding the concept of prophetic foreshadowing. God uses prophetic foreshadowing involving people, places, things, events and time to cast a shadow forward, from one event or concept to a later event or concept, which draws our attention to the things God wants to emphasize and communicate.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 22:2; 37:4; Exod. 25:9; 2 Chron. 3:1; Ps. 9:3-4; Jer. 30:9; Ezek. 34:23; Hosea 11:1; Matt. 2:15; 12:39; John 3:14-15; Gal. 4:22-25; Acts 7:9; Heb. 4:4-11; 8:5.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:55', 0, 0, 'Messiah', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2013_prophetic_foreshadowing.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/prophetic-foreshadows', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1123, 3, 'Major in the Majors', '<p>People in business know that if they are going to stay in business, they must &ldquo;major in the majors.&rdquo; They must figure out what is profitable and focus on that. What is profitable for Christians? This teaching presents a study of the Greek word for &ldquo;profit,&rdquo; and shows seven things that God says are profitable for those who follow Him.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:26; Luke 9:25; 16:1-9; John 6:62-63; 1 Cor. 13:3, 8; Gal. 8:18; 1 Tim. 4:7-8; 2 Tim. 3:16-17; Titus 3:1-14; Heb. 1:1-2; 13:9; Jude 1:14.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:36', 0, 0, 'success', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2013_major_in_the_majors.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/major-in-the-majors', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1124, 3, 'The Helper', '<p>Jesus knew intimately how difficult the spiritual battle is and that when he left, his followers were going to need spiritual help. He promised that he would not leave them alone and was sending them a helper. This teaching provides insight into specific ways we can rely on the helper, holy spirit, to assist us as we endeavor to do the good works we were created to do.</p> <p>Verses: John 7:39; 14:1, 12-18, 21, 23, 26; 15:26-27; 16:13-14, 21; Luke 24:46-49; Acts 1:4-5; 2:6-11; 23:6; Joel 2:28; Isa. 44:3-5; Matt. 10:26-27, 19-20.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:11', 0, 0, 'Revelation, Manifestations', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2013_the_helper.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-helper', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 69, null),
(1125, 3, 'Jesus and Nicodemus', '<p>In John 3, Jesus talks with Nicodemus, the Pharisee. Unfortunately, many of the things that can be learned from their conversation, which primarily concerned the resurrection from the dead, are buried in mistranslation and tradition. This expository teaching provides many valuable insights on how to read and understand the Bible, as it clarifies some of the mistranslation that has led to erroneous tradition and confusing doctrines in the Church.</p> <p>Verses: John 2:23-25; 3:1-14, 31; 5:28-29; Ps. 115:17; Eccles. 9:5; Ps. 6:5; Isa. 26:19; 33:24; Col. 1:18; Ezek. 37:12-14; Dan. 2:44; Matt. 4:17; 5:5; Ezek. 2:44; Luke 22:18-23; 23:51; Mark 11:10; Luke 21:31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:14', 0, 0, 'Kingdom, Born', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2013_jesus_and_nicodemus.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/jesus-and-nicodemus', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 140, null),
(1126, 3, 'Prudence: Learning to do the Next Right Thing', '<p>Life is filled with uncertainty, risk, and the ever-present need to make choices, many of which are insignificant, but others can be critical points of decision. This teaching explores the concept of prudence, and how to develop it in our lives. As we discipline ourselves to be prudent, we learn the art of doing the next right thing.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:1-4; 2:6-9; 3:13-18; 12:16, 23; 14:8; 22:3; Rom. 1:20; John 8:44; Gen 37:3; 9:6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:04', 0, 0, 'Foolishness, Habits, Wisdom', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/aug2013_prudence.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/prudence-learning-to-do-the-next-right-thing', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1127, 3, 'Understanding the Story of Lazarus', '<p>The record in John 11 of the death of Jesus&rsquo; friend Lazarus has been an obstacle for many students of the Bible. Why would Jesus wait two days before going to help Lazarus? This teaching shows why he waited. It also reveals a wonderful side of Martha not widely recognized. It showcases the spectrum of emotions Jesus experienced related to this event.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:30-31, 40; 1:28; 11:1-53</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:47', 0, 0, 'Emotions, Friendship', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2013_understanding_the_story_of_lazarus.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-the-story-of-lazarus', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 63, null),
(1128, 3, 'The Sense of Entitlement', '<p>Many people are out of touch with the sense of entitlement they have and the problems it produces for them. This mentality causes people to live with a false sense of reality, with unmerited and inappropriate expectations. When we realize that the only thing that matters is what we are entitled to through the redemptive work of Christ, we can begin to live in the joy of God&rsquo;s amazing grace.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 20:1-15; Isa. 14:13-14; Gen. 3:2-5; 4:3-7, 19, 23-24; 2 Chron. 26:16-21; Num. 12:1-2; 2 Sam. 13:12-17; Rom. 3:22-23; 6:23; 12:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '45:38', 0, 0, 'Bitterness, Emotions', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2013_the_sense_of_entitlement.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-sense-of-entitlement', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1129, 3, 'Living Like Jesus Did in Grace and Truth', '<p>While Jesus Christ was full of both grace and truth, most people tend to lean toward one or the other. To walk like Jesus did, we have to know when to call people back to the truth and when to extend grace, and we must do that in the manner that God does: with tolerance, often called &ldquo;forbearance.&rdquo; Our lives should demonstrate a balance of truth, grace and tolerance.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 23:37; 26:36-44; John 1:14; Acts 6:8; 14:26; 17:31; Rom. 4:2; 7:15-25; 12:6, 19; 1 Cor. 2:14; 8:6, 9; 13:4; 2 Cor. 6:1; Gal. 2:21; 5:16, 25; Eph. 1:7; 2:8; Phil. 3:10; Col. 4:6; 1 Tim. 4:2; Heb. 4:6; 13:9; 1 Pet. 5:5; 2 Pet. 3:9, 18; Jude 1:4.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:42', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2013_living_like_jesus_did.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/living-like-jesus-did-in-grace-and-truth', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1130, 3, 'Full of Grace and Truth', '<p>Jesus modeled both grace and truth in his life, and we can do the same. People tend to put more focus on one or the other but walking in doing both at the same time is extremely challenging. Looking at examples of Jesus living in a balance of grace and truth helps us to find balance between the two in our own lives.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 15:23-27; Mark 2:23-27; John 1:14-17; 8:2-8, 31; 2 Cor. 12:8-9; Col. 1:15.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '50:04', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/april2013_full_of_grace_and_truth.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/full-of-grace-and-truth', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1131, 3, 'Jesus the Servant of Yahweh', '<p>The more we know about Jesus Christ, the more personal inspiration we can draw from his example. A series of prophecies about our Lord which are not commonly known are the four &ldquo;Servant Songs&rdquo; in Isaiah. These songs encapsulate much of the attitude and mission of our Messiah, including bringing salvation not only to Israel, but to all people.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 42:1-7; 49:1-7; 50:4-11; 52:13-15; 53:1-5.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2013-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:13', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2012_jesus_servant_of_yahweh.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/jesus-the-servant-of-yahweh', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 213, null),
(1132, 3, 'Finding Our Joy', '<p>Our ability to experience joy affects almost every area of our lives. Not only does it impact our relationships with our spouses, family, co-workers and friends, it also has much to do with our ability to endure harsh life events like suffering or persecution. This teaching helps us understand how to access greater joy in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 9:7-14, 23-24; Deut. 6:4; Neh. 8:10; Ps. 16:11; 19:8; 21:6; 27:6; 30:10-12; 47:5-9; 92:4-5; 126:2-3; Prov. 10:1; 17:21; 21:15; Ezek. 14:4, 7; Matt. 10:32-34; Rom. 12:9-12; Phil. 2:1-5; Col. 3:13; 1 Thess. 3:9; Heb. 10:19-22; 12:2-4; 1 Pet. 1:8-9; 3 John 1:3-4.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:49', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2013_finding_our_joy.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/finding-our-joy', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1133, 3, 'Who Do You Say I Am?', '<p>Jesus asked his disciples, &ldquo;Who do you say I am?&rdquo; This most important question echoes through the world today. This two-part teaching explains the confusion about the Messianic identity of Jesus among those he interacted with and discusses how Christians today can better align their actions with their knowledge of &ldquo;who he is.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 17:6; Lev. 5:1-5; Num. 24:17; 2 Kings 4:22-44; 5:1-14; Job 19:25; Ps. 16:10; Isa. 9:6; Zech. 10:4; Matt. 11:2, 27; 16:13-16; 21:9-11; 26:64; Luke 24:25-27; John 1:18-34; 10:24; Rev. 1:12-16.</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2013-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:27', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2013_who_do_you_say_that_i_am.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/who-do-you-say-i-am', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1134, 3, 'The Wages of Sin is Death', '<p>How could God allow people to have genuine free will, and yet have a way to righteously exclude them from His everlasting Kingdom if they decided to be evil? By establishing a decree long before He ever created mankind, God provided for humble and loving people to have a wonderful everlasting future. This teaching also shows that those who are not saved will be annihilated in the Lake of Fire, not tormented forever.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 2:9-16; 6:23; 9:22; 10:9; Isa. 14:12-15; 32:4; 66:22-24; Gen. 2:16-17; 3:1-5, 22; John 3:16; Rev. 20:10, 14; Ps. 9:17; 37:10, 20; 92:7; Prov. 10:25; Job 20:9; Mal. 4:1; Matt. 3:12; 7:19; 10:28; 13:40-43; 25:46; 2 Pet. 2:6, 12; 3:7; Phil. 3:19; Heb. 10:27; Acts 3:23; 2 Thess. 1:9; Mark 9:43, 45, 47, 48</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:31', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2012_wages_of_sin_is_death.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-wages-of-sin-is-death', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 143, null),
(1135, 3, 'Standing in Difficult Times – An Exposition of 2 Timothy', '<p>One of the books that can help us navigate through tough times is 2 Timothy. Paul was in jail and about to lose his life and the Church was being heavily persecuted. In the midst of all that, Paul wrote to Timothy giving godly advice on what to do personally and how to move the Church forward. That advice is as valuable today as it was 2000 years ago.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:1-8, 14; 2:1, 2, 4, 8, 14, 15, 20, 28; 3:1, 12, 14; 4:2, 4-6, 8, 18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '49:18', 0, 0, 'faith, leadership', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/november2012_standing_in_difficult_times.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/standing-in-difficult-times-an-exposition-of-2-timothy', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 79, null),
(1136, 3, 'Endurance Inspired by Hope', '<p>Any worthy goal is only achieved through endurance, and the key to endurance is how much we are inspired by the goal. Christians have no greater goal than everlasting life and the rewards we will receive from the Lord when we appear before his throne. The letters to the seven congregations in the Book of Revelation show how Jesus seeks to inspire believers in their faithfulness and endurance with some wonderful promises.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 1:3; Rev. 1:3, 10, 19, 20; 2:1-20, 25-29; 3:1-22; Exod. 20:3; Matt. 22:37; John 14:12; Heb. 11:6; Rom. 13:13; 1 Cor. 6:18</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:32', 0, 0, 'prize', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/october2012_endurance_inspired_by_hope.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/endurance-inspired-by-hope', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1137, 3, 'Knowledge and Obedience', '<p>Knowing the truth is important, but God wants us to couple our knowledge with obedience. It is more important to know a little and obey what we know, than it is to know a lot and obey only a little. Jesus consistently spoke of &ldquo;pleasing God,&rdquo; not in terms of knowing Him, but of obeying Him. God desires an obedience-based relationship with mankind.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 4:13; 11:6; Matt. 21:28-31, 46-50; 28:9-20; Luke 6:46; 12:37, 41, 47-48; 1 Sam. 15:22-23; James 1:22; 1 Cor. 9:24-27; Gen. 3:4-6; John 14:15, 23-24; Col. 1:9-10; 2 Cor. 5:10; Rom. 14:12; Rev. 20:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit and Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '50:08', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/september2012_knowledge_and_obedience.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/knowledge-and-obedience', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1138, 3, 'The Lord Cometh!', '<p>Life is difficult, and in order to live day by day in a godly manner it is important to have a clear vision of our Hope. This teaching points out various aspects of the Hope of Israel as it is portrayed in the Old Testament and Gospels. As the time got closer to Christ&rsquo;s coming, information about him and the deliverance he would bring became clearer and more specific.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; 9:26; 12:3; 49:10; 2 Sam. 7:16, 18; Isa. 9:2, 6, 7; 11:1, 2, 6-9; 25:6-8; 26:19; 32:15; 35:5-7; 63:1-4; 65:17, 20; Mic. 5:2; Ezek. 37:11-14; Dan. 2:31-35; 7:13; 12:1-2; Mal. 4:1-5; Matt. 2:1-15, 26, 30-31, 36-47; 25:1-33, 41, 46; Rev. 14:16; Mark 13:27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:10:50', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/august2012_the_lord_cometh.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-lord-cometh', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1139, 3, 'Provider, Protector, Prophet, and Priest', '<p>Anyone who oversees others is taking care of God&rsquo;s most valuable possession, His people. The role of leader has four major responsibilities: to be a provider, protector, prophet, and priest. Scripture provides examples of each of these four roles, and shows how Jesus Christ gave us clear examples of them in his life and ministry.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 5:8; Exod. 21:10-11; Eph. 5:25-28; 6:4; Prov. 23:13; 29:17; 30:21-23; Col. 3:21; Deut. 4:8-10; 11:18-21; Gen. 3:6-7; 8:18-20; 14:12-16; 30:19-20; Neh. 4:13-14; Heb. 4:14-15; 7:25-26; 12:9-10; 1 Sam. 2:11-12, 17, 22; Ezra 10:10-12; John 7:5-6; 12:7; 18:9; 19:27; Acts 1:14; Luke 22:32; 24:39; Mark 14:6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:32', 0, 0, 'Character, family, intercede, personality', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2012_provider_protector_prophet_and_priest.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/provider-protector-prophet-and-priest', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1140, 3, 'Revisiting Administrations: Understanding Dispensationalism', '<p>Understanding the dispensations, or administrations, in the Bible is essential to understanding the Bible itself. God has always related to the world as His household, and just as in any household, from time to time the rules change. If we understand the administrations, we can better understand God&rsquo;s changing of the rules, which ones to obey and which have been made obsolete by newer rules.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:2, 9; Rev. 19:11; 20:4; Heb. 10:4; Rom. 10:9; 15:4; 1 Cor. 1:2; 7:2; 2 Tim. 3:16; Gen. 1:26; 9:3; 17:12, 14; Gal. 5:2; 2 Cor. 9:7; Mark 7:18-19; 1 Tim. 4:3; Matt. 6:5-7; Exod. 21:33-34; 22:1-5; Deut. 19:16-20;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:34', 0, 0, 'Requirements; Laws', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2012_revisiting_administrations_understanding_dispensationalism.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/revisiting-administrations-understanding-dispensationalism', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 55, null),
(1141, 3, 'Iron Sharpening Iron', '<p>Conflict is an ever-present relational reality, and godly confrontation is the mechanism we can employ to resolve it. When done properly, confrontation is a very effective tool for promoting peace and helping us grow in pure-heartedness. This teaching provides the biblical basis for godly confrontation as well as valuable insights on how to be more effective in developing this necessary relational tool.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 10:19; 12:18; 14:15; 15:4, 23, 31; 18:19; 22:3; 25:11-12; 27:17; Matt. 5:9; Ps. 51:10; 2 Tim. 4:2; Acts 6:1; 15:1; Gal. 2:11-12; 6:1; James 1:19-20; 3:17-18</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:55', 0, 0, 'Disagreements, Honesty, Resolution', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2012_iron_sharpening_iron.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/iron-sharpening-iron', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1142, 3, 'Life is Not a Game - Being Effective for God', '<p>Many people do not make good use of their time or abilities; they fail to plan and act wisely. In this teaching, the Spiritual Warfare and Wisdom models of life are examined and compared with popular alternatives. To think and act according to God&#39;s wisdom, we need to have a vision for our life, work with good teachers, leaders and encouragers, and get rid of those things that drag us down.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 15:19; Prov. 4:5, 7; 8:8-9, 11; 19:8; 28:5; Josh. 5:13-14; Exod. 15:3; 1 John 5:19; Acts 10:38; Luke 11:18, 23; Eph. 2:10; 5:15-17; Rom. 12:2; Heb. 10:24-25; 11:24-26; 12:15-16; John 14:21, 23-24; Luke 3:10-14; 2 Cor. 5:9-11, 17-20; 6:14-15; Eccles. 5:13; 9:18, 10:1; 1 Cor. 15:33; Titus 3:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:13', 0, 0, 'Contradiction, Beliefs', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/april2012_life_is_not_a_game.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/life-is-not-a-game-being-effective-for-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 163, null),
(1143, 3, 'A Basic Understanding of Curses', '<p>Many people do not realize the spiritual impact of their actions or words. This teaching addresses the subject of curses in the Bible and how they can open a door for demons to influence a person&rsquo;s life, the lives of their family and even future generations. Three categories of curses are examined: curses resulting from a person&rsquo;s actions, from their words, and also curses that come from previous generations.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 3:10-13; Gen. 3:14-17; 4:10-12; Deut. 22:22-29; 27:15-26; Exod. 12:12-13; 20:4-6; 21:17; Mal. 2:2; 3:9; Hag. 1:6-9; Jer. 48:10; Rev. 22:18-19; Prov. 18:21; 26:2; Num. 5:12-22; Neh. 13:1-2; Ps. 64:2-8; 109:1-7, 9-14; Luke 6:26-28; 9:53-55; Rom. 12:14; 1 Cor. 4:11-12; Obad. 1:3; Matt. 27:24-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:10', 0, 0, 'Ancestral, defraud, cruelty', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2012_a_basic_understanding_of_curses.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/a-basic-understanding-of-curses', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1144, 3, 'The Parable of the Sower', '<p>Growing deep roots in the Word is a matter of time and personal commitment. The Parable of the Sower teaches us how to be fruitful for the Lord, and the key to understanding it is realizing that <em>we</em> are in control of what kind of soil we are.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:19-21; 7:7; 13:1-9, 18-23; Deut. 6:4; Job 23:12; Ps. 1:1-2; Prov. 11:4; 1 Tim. 6:9-10; Mark 4:18-19; Eccles. 5:13; 1 Pet. 3:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2012-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:08', 0, 0, 'fruit', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2012_the_parable_of_the_sower.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-parable-of-the-sower', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1145, 3, 'Knowing Jesus Christ', '<p>Jesus Christ made it clear in his teachings that in order to really know God and have a relationship with Him we must develop a true and intimate relationship with His Son. We get to know Jesus through God&rsquo;s word, through the Church, the Body of Christ, and through our spiritual practices.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:37; Luke 24:27-32; John 14:6-7; 17:3, 6, 25-26; Acts 2:41-42; 9:4; Rom. 12:4-5, 10; Phil. 3:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2012-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:14', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2012_knowing_jesus_christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/knowing-jesus-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1146, 3, 'No Ordinary Child', '<p>From God&rsquo;s perspective, no one ever born is to be considered &ldquo;ordinary.&rdquo; Sadly, despite such potential for being &ldquo;extraordinary&rdquo; through God, far too many people do not believe they are. When we are aware of our sinful nature and the methods Satan uses to attack us, we can turn our dependency to God and be who He wants us to be, extraordinary.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:22; 7:20; John 3:16; 5:30; 8:44; 14:10; 1Tim. 2:3-4; Gen. 2:25; 3:1, 6; Rom. 8:5, 7-8, 17; Prov. 19:22; 1 John 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:59', 0, 0, 'Dysfunction, Love', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2011_no_ordinary_child.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/no-ordinary-child', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1147, 3, 'The History & Practice of Water Baptism', '<p>Water baptism has been a subject of debate ever since the Day of Pentecost. In this teaching you will learn about the history of water baptism from ceremonies that started when the law was given to Moses, through the baptism that John the Baptist and Jesus&rsquo; disciples performed, to the greater reality of baptism in the holy spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:2-6; Mark 1:8; Acts 1:5; 2:33; 10:44; Heb. 9:1, 9-10; Lev. 15:13-15; Deut. 12:13-14; John 4:1; Matt. 28:19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:22', 0, 0, 'humility', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2011_the_history_and_practice_of_water_baptism.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-history-practice-of-water-baptism', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 70, null),
(1148, 3, 'The Wise, The Fool, & The Wicked', '<p>God&rsquo;s desire for Christians is to gain wisdom. The Book of Proverbs is rich in teaching how to discern foolish and wicked behavior and how to obtain wisdom. This teaching will help the listener identify foolish behavior in themselves and others and the corresponding antidote to get back on the path of the wise.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:3, 5, 7, 9; 2:6; 3:21; 7:7, 22; 9:7-8; 10:13,18, 23; 11:9; 12:15; 13:1, 19; 14:1, 3, 7, 9, 15; 15:5,12; 17:10; 18:2, 6, 15; 19:7, 25; 20:3; 21:11, 24; 22:10, 15; 26:3-5, 11; 28:24; 29:9, 11, 28; Isa. 5:20; 32:6; Heb. 5:14; Phil. 1:9-10; Ps. 5:31</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:20', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2011_the_wise_the_fool_and_the_wicked.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-wise-the-fool-the-wicked', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1149, 3, 'Romans 9', '<p>Romans 9 is a difficult section of scripture, seeming to indicate that God chooses some people to bless, and others to destroy. Most people find this idea incongruous with a loving God. By delving into the broad scope of scripture, Semitic idioms, and the nuances of the Greek text, this teaching brings to light the truths in this chapter. God is indeed, loving, merciful, and patient.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 9:1-33; 10:9; Gen. 25:21-23; Matt. 2:18; Mal. 1:1-3; Exod. 4:13; 8:19; 9:13-16, 20; 11:3; 12:37; Jer. 18:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:34:54', 0, 0, 'Calvinism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/september2011_romans_9.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/romans-9', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 262, null),
(1150, 3, 'The Nature of the Enemy', '<p>Whether they know it or not, everyone on earth is in the middle of a raging spiritual battle. In His Word, God has given us intelligence about our enemy. Some of the enemy&rsquo;s titles, include &ldquo;god of this age,&rdquo; &ldquo;Accuser,&rdquo; &ldquo;Adversary,&rdquo; &ldquo;Deceiver,&rdquo; &ldquo;Destroyer,&rdquo; &ldquo;Slanderer,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Tempter.&rdquo; These titles reveal a great deal of information about our adversary and provide practical insight that will enable us to stand strong in the fight.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:1; 1 John 4:4; Rom. 8:37; Col. 1:13; 2:15; Luke 4:1-3; 10:19; 2 Cor. 4:4; Matt. 4:3-10; Ezek. 14:4; Isa. 14:12-14; Gen. 3:4; 4:9; 1 Sam. 5:20; 17:42; Prov. 13:10; 16:18; 2 Tim 3:8; 2 Thess. 2:3-4; 1 Tim. 5:14; Hag. 2:12-13; John 8:44; 10:10; Rev. 9:11; 12:10; 20:7-8; 2 John 1:7; 1 Pet. 5:8</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:28', 0, 0, 'lucipher, satan', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/august2011_the_nature_of_the_enemy.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-nature-of-the-enemy', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1151, 3, 'Idiom of Permission', '<p>God is love. However, in the Bible there are things God is said to do that seem to be clearly unloving. This teaching explains simply and thoroughly the &ldquo;idiom of permission,&rdquo; a commonly occurring idiom of Semitic languages which attributes to God responses of people. Understanding this idiom reveals that God is indeed the righteous and loving God we know Him to be.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 9:12; Num. 21:4; Ezek. 20:25; Acts 1:8; 10:28; John 1:17-18; Luke 10:1-20, 23; Heb. 2:14; Deut. 8:15; Prov. 3:11-12; 2 Sam. 24:1; 1 Chron. 21:1; Job 1:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '51:42', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2011_idiom_of_permission.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/idiom-of-permission', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1152, 3, 'Powerful and Effective Prayer', '<p>Most Christians know that they should pray, and many do pray frequently. Yet many times we are frustrated because we don&rsquo;t seem to get answers to our prayers. This encouraging teaching identifies our responsibilities in prayer, some common &ldquo;prayer blockers,&rdquo; and practical keys to make our prayers more effective.</p> <p>Verses: James 1:5-6; 4:1-3; 5:16,17; Matt. 6:5-6; John 14:13-14; 15:7,16, 23, 26; 16:23; Phil. 3:12; 4:6; Ps. 17:6; 57:2; 66:18-19; 84:11; Gen. 1:1; Isa. 55:11; Prov. 12:2; 1 John 3:21-22; 5:14; Isa. 50:7; Ezek. 3:9; Luke 8:12; Ezra 8:23</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:04', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2011_powerful_and_effective_prayer.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/powerful-and-effective-prayer', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1153, 3, 'In Christ - Our Union with Christ', '<p>The Bible is the source of Christian doctrine and practice. Therefore, it is vital that Christians are able to read and understand what it is saying. Yet it contains language that can be confusing to modern readers. This teaching explains some of the language, customs, and idioms understood by first century Greeks, focusing on the small but important word &ldquo;in,&rdquo; and bringing a clearer understanding of our relationship with Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 3:1; 2 Cor. 1:18, 22; 5:21-22; 13:2-4; Rom. 6:1-6; 8:1-2, 38-39; 10:9; 16:7; 1 Pet. 1:23; 2 Pet. 1:4; Eph. 1:3, 6-7, 13-14; 2:6; 1 Cor. 12:27; 14:5; 15:21; Acts 17:27-28; Col. 2:6-7, 11; 2 Thess. 1:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2011-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:09:13', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2011_in_christ_our_union_with_christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/in-christ-our-union-with-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1154, 3, 'Commit Yourself to God', '<p>Scripture helps us understand what it means to &ldquo;commit our way to the Lord.&rdquo; Being committed to God, in the Hebraic mindset, is like being &ldquo;rolled up&rdquo; with the Father. When we love God, we become committed to Him by having our words and actions demonstrate obedience to Him.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 17:10; 37:4; John 14:9, 26; 17:10; Gen. 6:22; 22:17; Exod. 7:6; 19:5; 39:43; Prov. 23:17; 1 Cor. 15:33; 1 John 2:3-4; 5:3; 2 Cor. 5:10; Rom. 6:10-14; Phil. 2:12-13; Gal. 5:17; Eph. 4:17; Eccles. 12:13</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:34', 0, 0, 'faithfulness, morality', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/april2011_commit_yourself_to_god.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/commit-yourself-to-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1155, 3, 'The Exchanged Life', '<p>At the time of the new birth a person&rsquo;s sins are charged to Christ, and in return Christ&rsquo;s righteousness is credited to the believer. This is often referred to as the &ldquo;Great Exchange.&rdquo; The believer can now live the &ldquo;Exchanged Life.&rdquo; This is really the power base of Christian living, allowing Christ to live through us. &ldquo;His life for mine, now my life for his.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23; 5:12; 8:5-8, 11; Lev. 17:11; Heb. 9:22; 2 Cor. 5:14-17, 20-21; 12:10; Col. 1:25-27; 2:11-14; 1 Cor. 2:8; 3:1-3; Gal. 5:1; John 16:13; Matt. 26:26-28</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '48:23', 0, 0, 'sacrifice, atonement, ambassador', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2011_the_exchanged_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-exchanged-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1156, 3, 'Make Room in Your Heart for God', '<p>God is a loving Father and He wants us to spend time with Him. We tend to make time in our daily lives for people and other things, but often neglect to make room in our lives for God. Here are eight important steps to remove the clutter from our hearts so that we can focus more on God and make more room in our hearts for Him.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 1:1; 10:4; 26:2; 119:78, 105; 139:1; 141:3; Matt. 9:4; 2 Pet. 3:1; John 6:18; Luke 8:24; Gen. 18:12; Heb. 3:1; 4:12; Phil. 4:6-8; 2 Cor. 10:5; 1 Pet. 2:21-23; 4:1, 7-10; 1 Cor. 14:20; Prov. 14:8; Isa. 55:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: Cara Hanson</p>', '2011-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:24', 0, 0, 'thoughts, mind', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2011_make_room_in_your_heart_for_god.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/make-room-in-your-heart-for-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1157, 3, 'Let Your Light Shine', '<p>God is light and in Him is no darkness. Jesus was a light to the world, and he taught that his followers were lights. Our sin nature and the systemization of error caused by Satan are constantly trying to block our light. Scripture helps us become aware of common ways we block our light, and encourages us to be clearly seen as the radiant light we are called to be.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 104:1-2; 119:105; Gen. 1:3; 3:24; 1 John 1:5-7; 2:10; Exod. 33:18-23; 34:29-35; John 3:19-21; 9:4-5; 12:44-46; Matt. 5:14-16; 6:22-23; 17:1-2; 22:29; Rev. 1:12; Heb. 10:24-25; Eph. 5:8-9; 2 Cor. 4:4-6; Rom. 13:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2011-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:50', 0, 0, 'blindness, truth, reflection', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2011_let_your_light_shine.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/let-your-light-shine', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1158, 3, 'Understanding The Magi', '<p>The Magi were wonderful men who traveled from the Parthian Empire to see the young Messiah. Despite clear information about them in the Bible, traditions about the Magi, who were astronomers, have clouded who they were and when they came to Bethlehem. Knowing the truth about these men helps us to understand why God would spend a whole chapter telling us about them.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:1-23; 28:19; 2 Tim. 2:2; Dan. 2:48; 4:9; 5:11; Mic. 5:2-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:58', 0, 0, 'christmas, gifts, Herod, star', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2010_understanding_the_magi.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-the-magi', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 43, null),
(1159, 3, 'Our Obligation to God', '<p>God has freely poured grace out upon us. We are both saved and forgiven by it. Once we receive God&lsquo;s grace and become His children, we have an obligation to Him, which He clearly states in His Word. The Bible spells out examples of our moral obligations to God and shows us how to fulfill them in our lives. Doing so is part of our obedience to God.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 7:10; 19:28-41; Acts 17:29; Rom. 15:1, 26-27; 2 Cor. 12:11; 13:5; Eph. 5:28; 2 Thess. 1:3; 2:13; Heb. 5:11-12; 1 John 2:6; 3:16; 4:11; 3 John 1:8; John 13:14; 12:42; Amos 5:18-24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:04', 0, 0, 'examine', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2010_our_obligation_to_god.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/our-obligation-to-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1160, 3, 'First the Promise, Then the Challenge', '<p>Throughout history, God has called and inspired many people with wonderful promises. So often, however, those people have had to journey through a &ldquo;land of challenge.&rdquo; In this teaching, the lives of several servants of God who were given great promises are examined with the hope of helping us to properly prepare for facing difficult times.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; 12:1-7, 10; 37:3-11; 1 Cor. 10:13; 2 Sam. 3:14; Exod. 3:16-18; Heb. 12:3-4; Col. 3:15-16; Ps. 126:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:11', 0, 0, 'patience, discouragement', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2010_first_the_promise_then_the_challenge.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/first-the-promise-then-the-challenge', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1161, 3, 'Spiritual Heart Disease', '<p>From the time Adam rejected God and rebelled against him, the effects of that sin have been painfully felt in the hearts of every human. The state of mankind&rsquo;s heart causes many to turn to a variety of ungodly solutions to find relief and solace. God instructed us with the remedy for this &ldquo;illness.&rdquo; When we follow it, we begin to heal and become able to help and heal others.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:16; 3:6-18; Mark 7:3-27; Rom. 1:28-31; 5:8; Deut. 6:4-9; Luke 18:18-23; Ps. 86:11; John 3:16; 1 Cor. 13:1-7; John 13:35; 1 John 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:42', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2010_spiritual_heart_disease.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/spiritual-heart-disease', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1162, 3, 'Living Wisely', '<p>In some Christian circles, &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; has been supplanted by a focus on &ldquo;faith&rdquo; with the assumption being that if we can get what we want by &ldquo;faith&ldquo;, then wisdom is not needed. Both faith and wisdom are important, and we need to understand both and how they work together. Living wisely is not easy to do but we must take the time and be disciplined to think through our decisions.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 6:7; 2 Cor. 5:7; Prov. 1:2, 7; 3:5, 13; 4:5, 7; 6:1-7; 14:8; 28:19; 23:29-30; 29:11; James 2:5; 1 Cor. 12:9; John 12:49; 14:31; 1 Kings 18:36; Luke 1:17; 2:40; 14:28; Col. 3:16; Eccles. 7:18; Eph. 4:29, 32; Heb. 12:15; 2 Cor. 6:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:53', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/aug2010_living_wisely.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/living-wisely', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 42, null),
(1163, 3, 'Understanding the Book of Romans: Righteousness by Faith in Christ', '<p>The book of Romans is the great doctrinal treatise that forms the foundation of the Christian faith. It clearly sets forth that salvation comes by faith in Jesus Christ, and that the saved are righteous in the eyes of God. This teaching answers often-asked questions such as, What exactly does &ldquo;righteous&rdquo; mean? Was it different in Old Testament times? Why do so many Christians seek salvation through good works?</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 3:7-10; Rom. 1:16-17; 3:19-31; 4:3-7, 16; 5:1; 10:9; Deut. 6:25; Dan. 12:1-7; Ps. 1:1-6; 37:10-11, 29; Ezek. 33:12-14; Luke 18:9-11; Hab. 2:4; Gal. 2:16-17; Matt. 3:8; Mark 10:17-21; Acts 21:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:08:52', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2010_understanding_the_book_of_romans.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-the-book-of-romans-righteousness-by-faith-in-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 168, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1164, 3, 'Get in the Right Line', '<p>This teaching uses a very clear analogy of standing in the &ldquo;wrong line&rdquo; of worldly perspective and sin that prevents Jesus from revealing the Father to us. When we acknowledge our sin and repent, then we move into the &ldquo;right line&rdquo; so that Christ can reveal the Father to us. That change on our part enables us to understand and do what Christ our Lord wants us to do.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 10:5-7; 11:1-29; 14:3-5; John 1:29-34; 17:25-26; Luke 5:27-32; 7:18-19; 10:17-21; Isa. 35:5-6; Josh. 24:1-7, 13-15, 20, 23; Mal. 3:1; Ezek. 14:1-6; 2 Pet. 3:8-9; Heb. 9:11-14; 1 John 1:5-7</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2010-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:58', 0, 0, 'renounce, yoke', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2010_get_in_the_right_line.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/get-in-the-right-line', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1165, 3, 'Should Women Be Silent in the Church?', '<p>For centuries the voices of women have been stifled in the Church due primarily to two New Testament scripture references that have been mistranslated and mishandled. That misinterpretation stands in contradiction to the larger context of the New Testament concerning women. On the Day of Pentecost, women also received holy spirit, and spoke and taught in the early Church.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:11; 7:2; 11:5-6; 14:5, 23-24, 26, 29-37; 16:19; Acts 2:17-18; 21:9; 1 Tim. 2:11-13; Rev. 2:20-21; Phil. 1:2; 4:2; Col. 4:15; 2 Tim. 4:21; Job 29:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:59', 0, 0, 'scribes, manuscripts', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2010_should_women_be_silent_in_the_church.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/should-women-be-silent-in-the-church', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1166, 3, 'As Each Part Does Its Work', '<p>The Body of Christ needs to be built up until we all reach maturity. With so much work still to be done, each believer&rsquo;s effort is vital. This teaching explores some of the obstacles that hinder us in building up the Body of Christ and helps believers to understand that the Lord&#39;s work will only get done as each one does their work.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:13, 16, 29, 31-32; 5:23; Matt. 9:37-38; 13:22; Heb. 6:10-12; 12:3-4, 14-15; Prov. 18:19; 1 John 1:9; 1 Tim. 1:15-16; Phil. 3:13-15; 1 Cor. 12:14-16, 18-22, 27; 13:3; 15:9-10; 2 Cor. 2:7-11; Rom. 6:2; 16:2-3, 6-7, 12, 23; Luke 14:16-20; Col. 4:7-8, 12; Neh. 3:3, 14-15; 4:6, 12, 14-21; John 4:34; 19:28-30; Ps. 22:14-15; Heb. 13:3</p> <p>Teacher: Cara Hanson</p>', '2010-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:15', 0, 0, 'calling', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/apr2010_as_each_does_part_does_its_work.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/as-each-part-does-its-work', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1167, 3, 'Who is Jesus Christ?', '<p>Records in the Four Gospels show that Jesus Christ is our Lord and Savior and also our hero and role model. Scripture reveals that Jesus got hungry, tired, and had family problems just as we do, yet he focused on God, lived and loved like no other person before or since. Knowing Jesus this way inspires us to live a more focused and holy life.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; Deut. 18:15; Jer. 30:21; John 4:34; 7:12-13; 12:1-7; 14:12, 31; 21:25; Rom. 5:14; 1 Tim. 2:5; 1 Cor. 15:45; Mark 1:35, 40-42; 3:20-21, 31-35; 4:35-40; 6:30-32; Eph. 2:10; Matt. 10:24-25; 16:13-16; 26:6-9, 39; Ps. 41:7-9; Heb. 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2010-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:31', 0, 0, 'commitment, humility', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2010_who_is_jesus.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/who-is-jesus-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 93, null),
(1168, 3, 'What does the Bible say about Tattoos?', '<p>This teaching explores three questions about tattoos: What does the Bible say? Is it okay for a Christian to get one? What should one do with an ungodly tattoo? In the Old Testament God condemned the idea of marking or cutting oneself as that practice was associated with pagan worship. The New Testament encourages us to love one another by not causing others to stumble by our actions, which could include tattoos.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 19:28; 1 Kings 18:26-28; Jer. 16:6; 41:4-5; 48:36-37; Isa. 49:15-16; Eph. 2:13-14; Rom. 8:37-39; 10:4; 13:8, 10; 14:22-23; 1 Cor. 8:9, 37-39; 10:23; Gal. 5:14; Col. 3:23; 1 Tim. 1:5; 1 Sam. 15:23; Matt. 15:17; 1 John 1:9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:36', 0, 0, 'motive, repentance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/what_does_the_bible_say_about_tattoos.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-does-the-bible-say-about-tattoos', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1169, 3, 'Perfecting the Saints', '<p>One of Jesus&rsquo; last commands before his ascension was &ldquo;make disciples of all nations.&rdquo; The vision of God and Jesus for each Christian is to become a mature believer. Exploring the Greek words <em>telios</em> and <em>katartizo</em> to helps us better understand how to achieve this goal of walking in love towards others and helping &ldquo;equip&rdquo; them so that we all become unified and mature in Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:43-48; 28:19; Eph. 2:22; 4:11-16; Heb. 13:20-21; 2 Thess. 2:16; Gal. 6:1; 1 Thess. 1:1-10; 2:7-8, 11-12, 17; 3:1, 9</p> <p>Teacher: Dave Hanson</p>', '2010-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '40:54', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2010_perfecting_the_saints.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/perfecting-the-saints', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1170, 3, 'Let&rsquo;s Get Together!', '<p>God tells us in Hebrews 10:25 &ldquo;Let us not give up meeting together, as some are in the habit of doing.&hellip;&rdquo; Here we consider three aspects of why we should meet together: to reach the lost of the world for Christ, to raise up to maturity those who come to him, and to develop greater relationships and connections with others in the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:23-25; Acts 5:41-42; Matt. 26:18; 28:18-19; Luke 5:27; 8:39; Acts 2:41-42; 8:1-3; 28:30-31; Philem. 1:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2010-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:44', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2010_lets_get_together.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/lets-get-together', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1171, 3, 'Giving & Tithing', '<p>Much confusion exists among Christians regarding giving and tithing. Many believe God commands them to tithe and some believe that if a person does not tithe, he will be cursed by God. This can cause guilt, shame, and even fear among Christians who do not tithe. Explore the full scope of the Word of God for a scriptural understanding of these two important concepts.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:19-21; Heb. 10:32-34; 11:8-10; Gen. 4:3; 14:17-20; 28:20-22; Lev. 27:30-32; Num 18:21-24; Mal. 3:8-10; Gal. 3:13; Rom. 12:1; 2 Cor. 8:1-9; 9:6-8; Luke 6:38; 1 Cor. 9:3-12; Gal. 2:10; Rom. 12:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:10:40', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2009_giving_and_tithing.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/giving-tithing', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 74, null),
(1172, 3, 'The Giver and The Gift: A Study of the Holy Spirit', '<p>Within the Bible there are many names for God that describe His varied characteristics. The holiness of God is expressed in His name as well as His personal gift to humankind. This teaching surveys the many usages of the terms &ldquo;Holy Spirit&rdquo; and &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; in the Bible, and takes a look at God, His character and His gift to all those who choose His Son as Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:18; 6:34; 12:18; Luke 1:35; Gen. 1:2; 1 Kings 18:12; Num. 11:17, 25; John 3:6, 8, 34; 7:37-39; 14:17; Acts 2:38; 10:38; 2 Kings 2:9; Eph. 1:13; Rom. 8:23; Ezek. 36:26-27; Isa. 59:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:17', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2009_giver_and_the_gift.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-giver-and-the-gift-a-study-of-the-holy-spirit', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1173, 3, 'What is going on in Heaven?', '<p>We all have thoughts about heaven, but are they in line with what the Bible says about it? Scriptures show that the &ldquo;whole creation&rdquo;, not just the earth, is groaning in pain. Furthermore, the Devil is often in the presence of God, accusing Jesus&rsquo; followers. This teaching explores the spiritual battle in heaven and what Jesus Christ is doing for us now.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 1:10-19; 2:1, 7, 11, 17, 29; 4:1-4; 11:19; 12:1-14; 15:5; 16:1, 17; 20:2; Isa. 6:1; Exod. 24:9-11; Luke 10:1, 17-18; 22:31; 24:36-39; Rom. 8:22-27, 34; 1 Cor. 15:45; 2 Cor. 3:17; Heb. 7:25; Job 1:6; 2 Pet. 3:9; Gen. 3:14; Mic. 6:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:52', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2009_whats_going_on_in_heaven.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-is-going-on-in-heaven', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 70, null),
(1174, 3, 'Is God in Control of Everything That Happens?', '<p>Many people believe that &ldquo;God is in control&rdquo; of all things on the earth today, that everything that happens is His will. This is not what the Bible teaches; what God wants often does not happen. The Devil has a lot of control and people can and do defy and disobey God&rsquo;s will.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:28; Josh. 24:15; 2 Chron. 33:10; Luke 4:5; 7:28-30; 10:17-23; 11:14; John 1:17-18; 10:10; Acts 10:38; 1 Cor. 9:22; 1 Tim. 2:4; James 1:13; 1 Pet. 5:8; 2 Pet. 3:9; 1 John 3:8; 5:3, 19; Rev. 12:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:09:20', 0, 0, 'confidence', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2009_is_god_in_control_of_everything_that_happens.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/is-god-in-control-of-everything-that-happens', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 57, null),
(1175, 3, 'The Interpretation of Tongues', '<p>One of the nine manifestations of the gift of holy spirit is the interpretation of tongues, and as speaking in tongues is praise, worship and thanksgiving directed to God, so is the interpretation of tongues.</p> <p>Verses: Job 6:4; 7:11; Ps. 34:18; 51:17; 77:6; Isa. 28:7-15; 1 Cor. 12:7; 14:1-32; Gal. 1:11; Heb. 5:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-08-28', 'Castos', 0, '1:25:33', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr1993_interpretation_of_tongues.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-interpretation-of-tongues', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 53, null),
(1176, 3, 'Gifts of Grace (Romans 12)', '<p>God tells us that each of us should use whatever gift we have received to serve others, faithfully administering God&rsquo;s grace. Gaining a greater understanding of our personal gifts helps us to be more effective in administering God&rsquo;s grace to the rest of the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 139:13-16; Rom. 12:3-8, 16; Acts 13:36; 1 Cor. 12:12-31; Eph. 4:11; Phil. 4:8; 1 Pet. 4:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:03', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/aug2009_gifts_of_grace.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/gifts-of-grace-romans-12', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 180, null),
(1177, 3, 'The Condition of Our Heart', '<p>The Parable of the Sower relates to the hearts of mankind. This parable includes a stern warning to &ldquo;consider carefully how you listen,&rdquo; as Jesus reveals four conditions of the heart: the hard-hearted, half-hearted, shallow-hearted and the good-hearted. The noble and good-hearted hear the Word, retain it, and by persevering, produce abundant, good fruit.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:19; 13:9; Luke 8:5-18; Rom. 1:20; 1 Tim. 2-4; 6:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Mike Patten</p>', '2009-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '50:38', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2009_condition_of_our_hearts.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-condition-of-our-heart', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1178, 4, 'Walking in the Truth', '<p>This fourth and final segment of the series &ldquo;Truth Matters&rdquo; focuses on a lifestyle of truth in a post-modern world, where the concept of a singular truth is unpopular. Truth comes from God and Jesus&rsquo; purpose was to testify to God&rsquo;s Truth with his whole life. To follow him accordingly is urgent, both currently and for our future.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:6; 17:17; 18:37; 1 Tim. 2:4; Gen. 2:16; 3:1, 4; 1 John 3:18; 1 Cor. 13:6; Eph. 4:13, 15; 6:13-14; 3 John 1:3</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '36:31', 13, 3, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/truth_matters_part4_walking_in_the_truth.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/truth-matters-part-4-walking-in-the-truth', '/i/seminars/TM.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1179, 3, 'Character Counts', '<p>The Bible has many references showing that our character is built upon what we say, think, and do. God is so concerned about our character that He tells us we will be judged accordingly. Everyone&rsquo;s character is under their own control, and it is up to each of us to work at having good character. Four steps are given for us to evaluate and change our character.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:1-4; 12:9-11; 1 Cor. 9:24-27; 15:33; Phil. 4:8-9; Mark 4:35-39; Gal. 5:22; 2 Cor. 5:10; Col. 3:23-25; Acts 13:22; 1 Kings 11:4, 9; Prov. 4:23; Matt. 5:27-28; Acts 24:24-26</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher, John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:25', 0, 0, 'honesty', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2009_character_counts.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/character-counts', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1180, 3, 'Convicted, but not Condemned', '<p>Life is filled with choices. Wrong choices can range from a simple misstep to serious sin. No matter what type of error we make, God has laid out a path that leads us from darkness back to His light. This teaching explores the roles of reproof, remorse (godly sorrow or worldly sorrow), and repentance, and their relationship to the redemptive reality that God has called us to.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Rom. 3:9-12; 4:25; 5:1, 9, 11-12, 18; 6:23; 8:1; Gal. 5:1, 13; Eph. 4:31-32; 1 Cor. 6:18; Heb. 4:16; 12:14; 1 Pet. 1:14-15; 2 Cor. 7:8-10; 2 Thess. 3:14-15; 2 Tim. 2:15; 1 John 2:28; Gen. 4:4-6; Matt. 26:69-70, 72, 74-75; 27:3-5; 2 Sam. 12:13-16; 1 John 3:21</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:36', 0, 0, 'guilt', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2009_convicted_not_condemned.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/convicted-but-not-condemned', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(1181, 3, 'Prayer Matters', '<p>The doctrines that &ldquo;God is in control&rdquo; and &ldquo;everything that happens is God&rsquo;s will&rdquo; have undermined the prayer habits of the Church. The earth is a war zone, and when we pray we participate in the spiritual battle. Our prayers speak into existence the legal permission for God to act in our lives. Prayer takes time and energy, but it makes a difference and is vital if we are going to live God-pleasing lives.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 5:17; Mark 1:35; 3:24; Gen. 1:28; Luke 4:5-6; 18:1; 1 John 5:19; Ps. 18:1, 4-10, 13-14, 17; 24:10; Exod. 15:3; Eph. 6:12, 18; Dan. 10:1-14; 1 Cor. 14:15,18; James 4:2-3; 5:16; Rom. 12:12; Phil. 4:6; Col. 4:2; Matt. 6:8; 7:7; Heb. 4:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:32', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/apr2009_prayer_matters.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/prayer-matters', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 76, null),
(1182, 3, 'Living from the Heart of God', '<p>Even though salvation is not obtained by keeping the Law, Scripture declares the Law &ldquo;holy, just, and good.&rdquo; The Law contains God&#39;s wisdom and heart for mankind, and many of the Old Testament commandments are reflected in the New Testament imperatives, helping us to live lives that are pleasing to God and free from the bondage of sin.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:15; 4:3; 2 Pet. 3:15-16; 2 Cor. 5:10; 2 John 1:8; 1 Thess. 4:3-7; 1 John 1:9; 2:28; 1 Cor. 9:9; Rom. 3:20-22; 6:8, 11-16; 7:12; 10:4; Gal. 3:2, 5, 10; Deut. 22:8; Exod. 22:6; Matt. 5:21-22, 27-28, 33</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2009-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:04', 0, 0, 'Dispensationalism, Torah', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar2009_living_from_the_heart_of_god.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/living-from-the-heart-of-god', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1183, 3, 'Walking in Wisdom', '<p>We learn from the example of King Solomon that we need godly character in order to walk in godly wisdom year after year. Wisdom will show us the right path to choose, but it is by godly character that we are able to carry out wise choices.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:6-10; 4:7; 11:2; Lev. 26:18-19; 1 Kings 3:5-12, 27-28; 8:60; 9:1-4; 10:7, 14-15, 18-21, 23-24, 26-28; 11:1-3; 4:3; Rom. 14:12; Eph. 5:3; Deut. 17:15-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:12', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2009_walking_with_wisdom.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/walking-in-wisdom', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1184, 3, 'Building an Enduring Work of Truth', '<p>This two-part presentation clarifies the purpose, values and strategies of Spirit and Truth Fellowship International as of 2009 and looks at supporting scripture of each word in the phrase &ldquo;building an enduring work of truth,&rdquo; which expresses the vision of Spirit and Truth for 2009 and beyond.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:24-27; 16:18; Ps. 127:1; Eph. 2:18-21; 1 Cor. 3:9-15; John 6:27; Rom. 12:6-8; 1 Peter 4:10</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2009-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:01', 0, 0, 'vision', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2009_building_an_enduring_work_of_truth.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/building-an-enduring-work-of-truth', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1185, 3, 'Fundamentals of Being a Disciple', '<p>The key to excellence is focusing on fundamentals. As Christians, we too must focus on doing what it takes to live a life pleasing to God. This teaching highlights 5 fundamentals that will lead us to be the ambassadors for Christ that God has equipped us to be.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:24-25; Deut. 6:1-9; Rom. 12:1,12; Eph. 6:18; Col. 4:2-4; 1 Thess. 5:17; Matt. 6:5-8; 1 Cor. 11:17; 2 Cor. 5:17-20; 9:6; Prov. 4:7; Rev. 20:13-21:5; 1 Pet. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:36', 0, 0, 'witnessing', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2008_fundamentals_of_being_a_disciple.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/fundamentals-of-being-a-disciple', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1186, 3, 'Tactics of the Enemy', '<p>In Proverbs 7, God reveals Satan&rsquo;s methods through the imagery of an ignorant and naive youth and a cunning adulterous woman. God lays out the Adversary&rsquo;s tactics including his use of words and his appeals to our senses. Evil is never far from us. God then provides the solution as to how we can defend ourselves in the final two verses of the chapter.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 7:1-27; 2 Cor. 2:11; Eph. 6:16; John 10:10; Ps. 119:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2008-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:30', 0, 0, 'witchcraft, disease', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2008_tactics_of_the_enemy.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/tactics-of-the-enemy', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1187, 3, 'Death and Resurrection to Life', '<p>This teaching consists of Parts I and II of the &quot;Death and Resurrection to Life&quot; seminar shows that God designed man as body, soul and spirit. The body cannot live without a soul, nor can the soul live without a body. Most cultures of the world believe, however, that the dead are alive in some form or another. The devil promotes and reinforces this lie.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:16-22, 26; Gen. 1:20, 30; 2:7, 16-17; 3:4; 9:10; Heb. 2:14; Luke 4:41; Deut. 18:9-12; Eph. 2:1; 1 John 4:13; Acts 2:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:16:13', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2008_death_and_resurrection_to_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/death-and-resurrection-to-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1188, 3, 'The Fruit of the Spirit', '<p>Jesus Christ exemplified godly character and every Christian should aspire to be like him. If we set a target or goal of being like Christ, our behavior will exhibit the fruit of the spirit as listed in Galatians 5:22-23. This fruit is the essential character of Christ, his nature. This teaching briefly examines the characteristics of the 9 listed fruits, also pointing out that the list is not exhaustive.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:16-26; 2 Pet. 1:4; Phil. 2:13; 3:1; Col. 1:27; Matt. 5:44; Exod. 23:4; 1 Thess. 5:16; Ps. 23:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: John W Schoenheit</p>', '2008-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:20', 0, 0, 'meekness, peace', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/aug2008_fruit_of_the_spirit.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-fruit-of-the-spirit', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 461, null),
(1189, 3, 'Nehemiah - A Man of Vision', '<p>The book of Nehemiah is filled with leadership principles. This teaching, using the record of Nehemiah&rsquo;s rebuilding the wall of Jerusalem as an example, demonstrates the power of holding a clear, godly vision, and explores six steps involved in accomplishing that vision.</p> <p>Verses: Neh. 1:3-6, 11; 2:4-11, 16-20; 4:1, 4-10, 14-15; 6:1-8, 11-16; Luke 4:1-8, 15-30; 14:28-30</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2008-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:09', 0, 0, 'strength', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2008_nehemiah_man_of_vision.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/nehemiah-a-man-of-vision', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1190, 3, 'The Example of Elisha', '<p>Having a long and successful ministry requires great compassion for God&rsquo;s people. Elisha was a powerful man of God who had such a ministry. His example instructed Jesus Christ, and challenges us to fulfill our ministries, too.</p> <p>Verses: Mal. 4:5; Matt. 14:23; 15:22-28; 17:10-13; Mark 1:40; 8:22-25; 2 Kings 2:9-10, 13-25; 3:1-3, 13-20; 4:1-44; 5:1,12; 6:18; 13:20-21; John 3:34; 6:53-60; 8:6-7; 9:6-7; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:11', 0, 0, 'Manifestation, Revelation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2008_example_of_elisha.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-example-of-elisha', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1191, 3, 'Mature in Christ', '<p>This teaching identifies two primary reasons we do not see more maturity in the Church today. It will not only challenge the listener, but also will encourage and exhort in the pursuit of spiritual maturity.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Pet. 2:1-2; Rom. 12:2, 17; Eph. 4:11-14; Gen. 1:28; Matt. 5:46-48; 19:16-22; 25:14-15; 1 Cor. 13:6; 14:20; Col. 1:28; 3:13; 4:12; Mark 4:3-8; John 15:1-6; Heb. 4:12; 5:12-14; Phil. 1:9; James 4:4, 7; 2 Tim. 2:15</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2008-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:44', 0, 0, 'Discipline, Weakness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2008_mature_in_christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/mature-in-christ-2', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1192, 3, 'The Transformed Life', '<p>The process of transforming our hearts occurs as we are faithful to renew our minds, which is to bring our thoughts to a new level of godliness. This teaching discusses the importance of having a transformed heart, and how interconnected our mind and body really are.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 8:3; 12:2; Eph. 2:2; 4:17-19; 5:3-4; Matt. 12:34-35; 13:15; Mark 7:21; Rev. 2:23; Ps. 26:2; 16:7; 51:10; Philem. 1:7; 1 Tim. 4:1-2; Phil. 4:8; Col. 3:2; Prov. 4:23; 2 Pet. 2:14; 1 Cor. 6:18; 9:24; James 4:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:27', 0, 0, 'Habits', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/apr2008_the_transformed_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-transformed-life', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 57, null),
(1193, 3, 'Stand, even when you do not understand', '<p>God doesn&rsquo;t promise us an effortless, carefree life, but He does promise to remain with us throughout our lives. This teaching takes us into the lives of some of the great people in the Bible who lived through difficult times. Through them we learn that, despite great trials, we can stand for God, even when we don&rsquo;t understand everything about the situation.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Pet. 3:13-18; 2 Cor. 1:2-10, 13; 13:5; Job 10:1-3; Lam. 3:1-7; Jer. 17:7-10; Exod. 16:4; Deut. 8:15-16; Ps. 7:8-9; 119:71; 1 Pet. 1:6; 4:12; James 1:2; Rom. 5:3-8; 1 Cor. 10:13; 13:2-13; 1 Pet. 5:9; Lam. 3:40; Acts 14:22; 2 Tim. 3:11-14; Prov. 25:2; Matt. 9:11-13; 11:2-6; 13:13-17; 22:41-43</p> <p>Teacher: Joshua Anderson</p>', '2008-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '55:43', 0, 0, 'Disciple, Discipline, Growth', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar2008_stand_even_when_you_dont_understand.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/stand-even-when-you-do-not-understand', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null);
