(1194, 3, 'Our Guarantee of Salvation', '<p>Unlike in the Old Testament, in this present Grace Administration, the guarantee of salvation for Christians is permanent - it cannot be lost. This truth is stated repeatedly in the Church Epistles and is expressed in terms of both birth and adoption to emphasize its irreversible nature.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 14:30; 19:16-17; Mark 5:23, 28; John 11:11-12; 1 John 1:10; Rom. 8:17, 23, 35-39; 10:9-10; 13:11; 14:5; 1 Thess. 4:15-17; 5:8; Eph. 1:13-14; 2:6, 8; 3:2; 5:23; Gen. 1:29; 9:3; Exod. 31:13; Num. 15:32-36; Col. 2:16; 3:1; Deut. 6:25; Ps. 1:1-5; 51:11; Ezek. 33:13-16; 37:12; Acts 16:30-31; 1 Peter 1:23; Titus 3:5; James 1:18; 2 Cor. 1:21-22; 3:7-8, 10; 5:5, 17; 2 Peter 2:4; Gal. 5:17; 1 Cor. 12:27; 13:8; 14:5; Phil. 3:20; Hosea 1:6, 9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:01', 0, 0, 'Saved', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2008_our_guarantee_of_salvation.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/our-guarantee-of-salvation', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(1195, 3, 'The Birth of Christ', '<p>The story of the birth of Jesus Christ as described in the Bible differs significantly from the traditional view. Consideration of the Scripture as well as biblical custom sheds light on when it occurred, where it occurred, and who was present on that night to support the young family.</p> <p>Verses: Luke: 1:57; 2:1-11, 16; 4:17; 10:34; 19:5-7; 22:10-11; Matt. 1:24-25; 5:13-15; 12:43; Ezek. 16:4<strong>;</strong> Phil. 3:5; Rom. 12:19; Eph. 4:27; Gen 21:2; 29:32; Judg. 13:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2008-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:25', 0, 0, 'Manger, Bethlehem', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2008_the_birth_of_christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-birth-of-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 27, null),
(1196, 4, 'The Characteristics of Truth and How Truth is Revealed', '<p>This teaching explores why truth matters and that many people hold contradictory ideas in their minds without ever realizing it. It discusses the characteristics of truth, how to discern truth from error, and identifies several ways that truth is revealed to mankind. It shows that the primary way God reveals truth to us is through His Word.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1,14; Ps. 12:6; 19:1-4; 25:4; 119:43, 89, 159-160; 138:2; John 17:17; 2 Tim. 3:16; Prov. 4:7; 6:6-8; James 3:13-18; Rom. 1:20; 15:14; Eph. 4:11-13; Col. 4:12; Heb. 5:13-14; Matt. 12:33; Mark 7:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2008-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:13:30', 13, 2, 'Tradition', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2008_truth_matters_part_2_3.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/truth-matters-parts-2-and-3', '/i/seminars/TM.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1197, 3, 'What is the Church?', '<p>Every Sunday around the world, and most especially in the western world, millions of Christians &ldquo;go to church&rdquo;. This conversational presentation explores the traditional definition of a &ldquo;church&rdquo; and turns to the Bible to show how the early believers met in ordinary homes and ministered to each other in simple settings.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:2; 12:12-18; 14:12, 26, 34; 16:19; Acts 2:42; 7:37-38; 18:1-8; 19:8-10, 32; 20:20; Rev. 2:1; Matt. 18:19-20; Eph. 4:11-12; Rom. 16:5; Col. 4:15; Philem. 1:2; 2 Tim. 3:12</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher, John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:21', 0, 0, 'Fellowship', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2007_what_is_the_church.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-is-the-church', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1198, 3, 'Mary, the Mother of Jesus: Defining True Greatness', '<p>Mary&#39;s life and character demonstrates that she was a great woman of God. As a young woman, she declared that she was &ldquo;a servant of the Lord&rdquo; and went on to become a wife, mother, and a disciple of her son, the Lord Jesus Christ. Her life exemplifies courage, humility and love for God.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:1, 16, 18-25; 2:11; 12:46-49; 13:55-56; Luke 1:26-56; 2:7, 16-19, 21-35, 51; Dan. 9:25; Isa. 7:11; Lev. 12:8; John 2:1-4; 19:25-27; Mark 3:21; Acts 1:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-11-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:05', 0, 0, 'Angel, Genealogy', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2007_mary_the_mother_of_jesus.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/mary-the-mother-of-jesus-defining-true-greatness', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1199, 3, 'Take Up the Armor of God', '<p>As Christians living for the Lord, each of us should recognize that we are in a spiritual battle and do what it takes to stand in the fight throughout our lifetime. Understanding each piece of the armor of God, enables us to take up the whole armor that God has placed before us.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:10-17; Luke 4:12-13, 18-19; 1 Pet. 5:18; Rom. 5:17; 8:18-23; 1 Tim. 6:11; 2 Tim. 3:16; Phil. 4:7; Ps. 107:20; 119:165; 1 Thess. 5:8; Acts 16:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-10-01', 'Castos', 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2007_take_up_the_armor_of_god.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/take-up-the-armor-of-god', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(1200, 4, 'What it Means to be a Truth Seeker', '<p>This first part of the series &ldquo;Truth Matters&rdquo; explores in detail what it means to be a truth seeker, the value of truth, the price one must be willing to pay for truth, and the qualities that are common to all truth seekers.</p> <p>Verses: John 18:37-38; Matt. 7:7-9; 10:34-36; 12:46-50; Prov. 1:20; 2:9-11; 4:7; 7:7-9; 8:7-11; 23:23; 25:2; Phil. 1:9-10; 1 Kings 3:16-28; 4:29-30; Acts 17:24-27; Isa. 45:15, 19; Ps. 19:1-4; Jer. 29:11-14; 1 Tim. 2:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2007-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:28', 13, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2007_truthmatters_pt1_truth_seekers.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/truth-matters-part-1-truth-seekers', '/i/seminars/TM.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1201, 3, 'Hezekiah - A Man of Action', '<p>This teaching focuses on Hezekiah&rsquo;s godly character and highlights principles he exemplified that made him one of the greatest kings Judah ever had. We too can learn and practice those principles in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 28:1-3, 24; 29:1-31:1; 2 Kings 16:10-12; 1 Tim. 3:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-08-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:58', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/aug2007_hezekiah.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/hezekiah-a-man-of-action', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(1202, 3, 'Forgive One Another', '<p>This teaching explores some of the consequences of unforgiveness and examines some biblical records of forgiveness. The listener is asked to consider what genuine forgiveness is, what it is not, and what is the process of forgiveness.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:30-32; Col. 3:13; 1 John 2:9-11; 3:21-23; Matt. 5:38-41; 6:22-24; 18:21-22; John 12:15; Gen. 4:23-24; 50:12-21; Exod. 33:20-34:8; Num. 14:1-20; Luke 17:3-5; 24:13-32</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2007-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:02', 0, 0, 'Vengeance', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jul2007_forgive_one_another.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/forgive-one-another', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1203, 3, 'The Heart of Evangelism', '<p>This teaching focuses on telling others about Jesus Christ. It shows from Scripture that God commands Christians to evangelize, shares some ways to do so, and emphasizes that evangelism is an act of love.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; Rev. 20:12-15; 21:1-4; Mark 16:15; 2 Cor. 5:18-21; Acts 1:8; 2:40-47; 13:1-52; 1 Cor. 3:4-8; Matt. 10:5-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:03:06', 0, 0, 'Witnessing, Ambassadors, Salvation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2007heart_of_evangelism.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-heart-of-evangelism', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1204, 3, 'My God, My God, why have you forsaken me?', '<p>Jesus&#39; words from the cross, &ldquo;Eli, Eli, lama sabachthani,&rdquo; have confused Bible students for years. Many think that Jesus either was, or thought he was, forsaken by God. In this teaching we learn that Jesus Christ was reciting part of Psalm 22, trying to jar people into understanding that prophecy was being fulfilled before their eyes.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 26:1-5, 50-54; 27:41-43, 45-50; Mark 10:32-34; John 13:25-27; 16:32; 19:28-30, 36; Isa. 52:14, 53:3-5; Ps. 22:1-31; Exod. 25:4; Heb. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:33', 0, 0, 'devotion, commitment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2007_eli_eli_lama.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/my-god-my-god-why-have-you-forsaken-me', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 275, null),
(1205, 3, 'A Community of Grace: Five Steps on the Path of Grace', '<p>What a blessing it would be to live in a community where there is favor, kindness and goodwill towards one another. The community of grace is a concept that is explored by presenting five steps that Christians can take to promote that concept and bring it to pass.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 57:4; Prov. 4:24; 11:9; 13:3; 14:9; 15:1-2, 4; 17:14; 18:21; 23:9; 26:4-5, 18-28; Matt. 5:23-24; 12:34; 15:11; 18:21-22; Rom. 14:12-13; 1 Cor. 13:4-6, 11-13; 2 Cor. 6:1-2; 10:5-6; Gal. 5:13; 6:1, 9-10; Eph. 4:29-32; Phil. 2:3-5; Col. 4:6; James 1:19, 26; 4:6; 1 Pet. 2:15-17; 3:8-10; 4:8-10; 5:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2007-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:44', 0, 0, 'harmony', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/apr2007_communityofgrace.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/a-community-of-grace-five-steps-on-the-path-of-grace', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(1206, 3, 'The Passover: A Sacrifice of Grace', '<p>In the book of Exodus we learn that the Passover Lamb was God&rsquo;s provision and protection in the Israelites&rsquo; escape from Egyptian slavery. In the New Testament we learn that Jesus Christ is our Passover Lamb, what that should mean to us as Christians today and how we can make it applicable in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 8:22-23; 9:4, 25-26; 10:22-23; 12:1-14; Rom. 12:1, 14-21; 1 Cor. 4:12-13; 5:7; 2 Cor. 1:12; Eph. 2:1,10; 4:29; Phil. 1:29; Col. 4:6; 1 Pet. 4:10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:46', 0, 0, 'Passover, Grace', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar2007_passover_sacrifice.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-passover-a-sacrifice-of-grace', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 16, null),
(1207, 3, 'Jesus Christ Our Approach Offering', '<p>It is important for Christians to understand all that Jesus Christ accomplished for us. One of his great works was to remove all the distance between God and humankind, giving each believer welcome access into the very presence of God.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 19:10-13; Lev. 1:1-9; 10:1; 16:13; Num. 1:51; 3:10; Deut. 12:13-14; Ps. 100:4; Matt. 27:50-51; 2 Cor. 5:21; Eph. 5:1-2; Heb. 9:6-8; 10:19-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2007-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:38', 0, 0, 'Tabernacle, Sacrifice, Offering', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2007_jc_ourapproach_offering.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/jesus-christ-our-approach-offering', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(1208, 3, 'Keys to Godly Communication', '<p>Effective communication can be difficult, especially in times of conflict. When in conflict we always need to ask ourselves if we are really obeying God&#39;s Word.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 33:11; Prov. 18:2-6, 13, 15, 17, 19, 21; Zech. 7:10; Matt. 7:3-5; 18:15-17; 22:35-40; 1 Cor. 1:10; Eph. 4:25-27</p> <p>Teacher: Ryan Maher</p>', '2007-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:31', 0, 0, 'Apologize, Offend', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2007_keysto_godlycommunication.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/keys-to-godly-communication', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(1209, 3, 'The Conditional Nature of Prophecy', '<p>One aspect of prophecy that has not been well understood by Christians is that it is almost always conditional in nature. God is often calling us to greater things, but because He also gave us free will, our behavior can effect whether or not a prophecy comes to pass. Examples of prophecy in the Bible reveal the often unspoken &ldquo;if&rdquo; in personal prophecy.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> 1 Cor. 14:1; Jer. 4:5-6; 18:1-12; 1 Sam. 13:13-14; 2 Sam. 7:11; 12:7-14, 18; 1 Kings 11:7-11; 21:21-29; 2 Chron. 12:1-7; Jonah 3:1-10; 2 Kings 20:1-6; Mark 14:35-36</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2006-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:06:45', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sept2006_conditionalnatureof_prophecy.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-conditional-nature-of-prophecy', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(1210, 3, 'A New Perspective on the Manifestations of the Holy Spirit', '<p>1 Corinthians 12 contains wording that can be confusing, making it seem like each Christian can manifest only one of the nine manifestations listed. This teaching explains the manifestations of holy spirit and confirms from the Bible that every Christian is equipped to operate all nine of them.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Acts 1:8; 2:17-18; Eph. 1:13; Heb. 11:11, 20-23, 30; 1 Cor. 1:10-13, 26-29; 2:1-3; 3:1-4; 6:1-2, 6-8; 11:17-18; 12:1-11; 14:1, 5, 24, 26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2006-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:04', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2006_newperspectiveon_manifestations.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/a-new-perspective-on-the-manifestations-of-the-holy-spirit', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(1211, 3, 'Understanding Healing in its Biblical Context', '<p>God loves us and wants us to be in good health. However, healing is a gift that is received by trust; it is not a right that we can demand. In light of that fact, this teaching explains the patron-client relationship of trust, the figure of speech called the prophetic perfect, and the practice we call Communion.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 10:4; Heb. 4:16; 11:6; Matt. 7:7; Num. 24:17; Jude 1:12, 14-15; Eph. 2:6-7; 1 Pet. 2:24; 1 Cor. 11:17-31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2006-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:09:42', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jun2006_understandinghealing.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/understanding-healing-in-its-biblical-context', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 71, null),
(1212, 3, 'Healing - God''s Gift of Mercy and Grace', '<p>Factors that can affect healing include humility, faith, sowing and reaping, and stewardship. These are discussed in this teaching, as well as the levels on which healing can occur: physical, emotional, spiritual, and moral.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 3:6; 5:12,15; 10:34-38; 14:9-10; 28:8-9; Ps. 41:3-4; 107:20; Luke 4:18-19; 8:48; Matt. 4:23-24; 9:22; 10:1; 12:22; 13:54-57; 15:22; 1 Cor. 3:16-17; 12:9, 28, 30; Phil. 2:26-27; 4:8; Heb. 4:6; 1 Pet. 2:24; Mark 9:21-24; 10:51-52; 11:23; Prov. 4:6; 14:30; 15:13, 30; 16:24; 17:22</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2006-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:14:24', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/HealingMay2006DG.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/healing-gods-gift-of-mercy-and-grace', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 103, null),
(1213, 3, 'The Balance of Truth and Love: Valuing Right Doctrine and Right Relationships', '<p>Jesus had both truth and a deep love for others&mdash;and the sinners, prostitutes, and tax collectors felt his love and wanted to be around him. This teaching explores keys to building loving relationships through self-awareness, social awareness, self-management and relational management.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:43-48; 9:9; 11:16-19; Heb. 4:12; Luke 18:9-14; 2 Tim. 2:15; John 13:35; Col. 3:12-13; Rom. 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2006-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:22', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar2006_balanceoftruthlove.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-balance-of-truth-and-love-valuing-right-doctrine-and-right-relationships', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 34, null),
(1214, 3, 'Failure of Idols, Lilies in a World of Thorns, and Spiritual Success vs. Worldly Success - LOL 06, Part 2', '<p>These teachings feature the youth of our fellowship community, and were recorded live at the 2006 Live Out Loud Teens and Twenties Conference. They explore how the Idols and values of this world fail us, and how God alone is worthy of our worship.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 10:14; Ps. 115:1-8; Song of Sol. 2:2; Ps. 139:13-14; Col. 2:20-22; 1 Pet. 1:13-16, 18-19; 2:11; 3:3-4; 1 John 2:15-17; Eph. 4:17-19; 1 Cor. 6:15-20; 1 Tim. 2:9-10; Rom. 13:14; James 4:4-5; Rom. 11:36; 12:12</p> <p>Teacher: Shawn Mercer, Natalie Lawrence, and Kristen Burk.</p>', '2006-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:51', 14, 4, 'Purity', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/LOLhighlights2-FEB2006.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/failure-of-idols-lilies-in-a-world-of-thorns-and-spiritual-success-vs-worldly-success-lol-06-part-2', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 15, null),
(1215, 3, 'Gossip, Whom or What do You Worship, and Courage - LOL 06, Part 1', '<p>These teachings feature the youth of our fellowship community, and were recorded live at the 2006 Live Out Loud Teens and Twenties Conference. They challenge us to consider the power of our words, worship the One True God and courageously live to serve others rather than just look out for ourselves.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 16:28; 18:21; Ps. 64:3; Matt. 4:8-9; 6:28-34; 2 Cor. 12:9; Phil. 2:9-11; Eccles. 2:10-11; 2 Tim. 1:7; Phil. 4:13</p> <p>Teacher: Ryan Maher, Matthew Johnson, Colin Stark</p>', '2006-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:04:47', 14, 3, 'Relationships, Culture', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/LOLhighlightsJAN2006.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/gossip-whom-or-what-do-you-worship-and-courage-lol-06-part-1', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1216, 3, 'Job - The Righteous Sufferer', '<p>This overview of the Book of Job emphasizes some great lessons such as worshipping God whether we are in good or bad situations, people speaking a mixture of truth and error, and the flesh&rsquo;s inability to discern truth in the spiritual world.</p> <p>Verses: Job 1:1-22; 2:1-13; 3:1-5, 25-26; 4:1-3, 7-9, 12-21; 6:1-3, 10, 29; 8:3-4, 6; 10:7; 11:13-15; 14:11-14; 21:7-17, 34; 34:10-12; 38:1-6, 31, 33, 39; 40:1-8; 42:7-17; 1 John 5:19; Matt. 4:8-9; Luke 4:5-7; Rom. 8:28; Eccles. 7:21-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2005-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:10:23', 0, 0, 'Discernment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/nov2005_job_righteous_sufferer.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/job-the-righteous-sufferer', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 28, null),
(1217, 3, 'The Benefits of Thanks - Living', '<p>This teaching provides a new perspective of the subject of thankfulness, encouraging us to consider the benefits flowing from an attitude of gratitude. Obeying God by being thankful can improve our mental and physical health and enable us to have peace in difficult situations.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 7:17; 28:7; Col. 3:15; James 1:2; Heb. 10:32-34; Prov. 14:30; 15:13, 30; 16:24; 17:22; 1 Thess. 5:16-18; Matt. 5:22-24; Gen. 3:17-19; Luke 17:11-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Dan Gallagher</p>', '2005-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '52:09', 0, 0, 'Rejoice', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2005_thanks_living.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-benefits-of-thanks-living', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1218, 3, 'An Overview of the Sacred Secret', '<p>For ages and generations God kept a sacred secret so huge and so wonderful that had Satan known it he would not have crucified Jesus Christ. Today, in the Age of Grace, God has made known that secret to anyone who reads the Church Epistles.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 2:6-10; 2 Cor. 3:7-10; 5:17; Hosea 1:2, 6; Eph. 1:9; 2:6; 3:1-10; Rom. 6:4, 6, 8; 8:15, 23, 38-39; 16:25-26; Col. 1:26-27; 1 John 3:1; Lev. 25:55; 1 Pet. 1:23; 2 Pet. 1:4; 1 Thess. 4:13-18; Phil. 3:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2005-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:13:14', 0, 0, 'Salvation, Born Again, Administration', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/july2005_overview_sacred_secret.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/an-overview-of-the-sacred-secret', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 13, null),
(1219, 3, 'Failing Forward', '<p>Success often follows many failures. Learning how to deal with the mistakes and defeats, persecutions and adversities can develop a pathway to truth. The Bible has many examples of people making terrible mistakes and recovering to be great heroes of faith.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:15; 37:19-24; 39:19-20; 40:23; 45:3-7; Prov. 24:15-18; Josh. 2:1; Matt. 1:5-6; 5:11; James 2:25; Exod. 2:13-15; 33:11; 1 Sam. 9:1-2; 18:8-12; 19:1; Luke 24:25-26; 2 Cor. 6:4-10; 11:23-30; 12:7-10; John 15:1-2, 20; Rom. 8:34-39</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2005-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:36', 0, 0, 'growth, loss, blessing', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/june2005_failing_forward.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/failing-forward', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(1220, 3, 'Slave to Sin - No more!', '<p>We all have sin in our lives. However, we can choose freedom over bondage and admit we are weak and need help and reach out to God and to others for help as we progress on our road to wholeness. This will require genuinely opening our hearts to God and others.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:6; 6:5; Ps. 62:7; 139:23-24; Mark 2:17; John 8:33-36; 10:14; Gal. 5:1; James 5:16</p> <p>Teachers: Kathy Lunardini, Travis Williams</p>', '2005-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:50', 0, 0, 'deliverance, healing, strongholds', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2005_slave_to_sin.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/slave-to-sin-no-more', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1221, 3, 'Highlights of Live Out Loud - Part 2', '<p>By resolving to do the will of God and fulfilling the purpose for which He placed us in the Body, we can have a future worth having. This requires great love, and love is an action word. You can give without loving but you cannot love without giving.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1; Eph. 2:10; John 10:10; 15:13; 1 Cor 12:18; Gal. 1:15; Eccles. 1:12-18; 2:1-17; 8:8; Matt. 10:41-42; 16:27; Prov. 1:20-30; 1 John 3:18; Eph. 5:1-2; John 15:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Ryan Maher</p>', '2005-04-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:22', 14, 2, 'wisdom, purpose, love', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/apr2005_lol_hightlights_p2.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/highlights-of-live-out-loud-part-2', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1222, 3, 'Highlights from Live Out Loud - Part 1', '<p>Understanding what God has given us is a key to being a cheerful giver. Each person&rsquo;s ministry is a unique gift and God will help each person fulfill his ministry. The Bible provides keys to defending against the Adversary&rsquo;s lie that we may be &ldquo;missing out.&rdquo;</p> <p>A 4-Part Highlight from Live Out Loud Conference, 2005, including &ldquo;Knowing What God has Given Us and Giving from that Abundance, Staying Fired up in the Spiritual Battle, Will You Answer the Call? And 4 Keys for Success in this Life.</p> <p>Verses:[BD] 2 Cor. 1:3-5; 5:17-21; 9:6-11; Rom. 5:5; 8:37; [KL] John 8:31-34; 10:10; James 1:2-3, 12; Gal. 6:9-10; Heb. 11:31-38; Eph. 6:10-20; Jer. 29:11; 1 John 2:25, 28; Matt. 6:33; 1 Cor. 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: Billy Darr, Kathy Lunardini, Ryan Maher, Dallas Estes</p>', '2005-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:01:50', 14, 1, 'purpose', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/march2005_lol_hightlights_p1.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/highlights-from-live-out-loud-part-1', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1223, 3, 'Discipling As a Body Working Together', '<p>We are urged to walk in a manner worthy of our calling and to fulfill our ministry, as it is our responsibility in the Body of Christ. By pursuing this path of fulfilling our ministry we grow up to be more like Christ and help others do the same. We are to pursue this until we all attain unity, knowledge, and maturity.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 11:22-29; Acts 20:22-38; 21:1-26; Eph. 4:1-16; Col. 3:12-17; Matt. 4:21</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen, Mark Graeser</p>', '2005-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:16', 0, 0, 'purpose, gift, bond', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2005_discipling_as_a_body.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/discipling-as-a-body-working-together', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1224, 3, 'What is True Discipleship?', '<p>This teaching identifies a six-step biblical pattern that gives structure to the process of moving from being a new follower of Christ to becoming a mature and empowered disciple who acts in Christ&rsquo;s stead, having been delegated that authority by Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matt 5:10; 6:24; 10:37-38; 2 Tim. 3:16-17; Acts 5:33-38; 14:23; 22:3; Eph. 5:1; Phil 3:7; John 9:34; 2 Cor. 7:1; Rom 12:1-2; Heb. 11:1-27; 12:2</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Theisen</p>', '2005-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:50', 0, 0, 'endurance, sacrifice', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2005_true_discipleship.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-is-true-discipleship', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 9, null),
(1225, 3, 'Love is Giving', '<p>This teaching shows what true love is and how it is expressed. It looks at some Greek words showing the various aspects of love: <em>agape, phileo, eros</em>, and <em>storge</em>, and examines the difference between &quot;love&quot; and &quot;like.&quot; Love is best shown by actions and obedience. Our actions define our love.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 23:5, 24; John 3:16; 4:19-20, 34; 15:9-10; Luke 11:11; Matt. 5:43; 6:1-6; Eph. 5:1; 1 Cor. 13:1-4; 2 Cor. 3:17; James 2:23.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2004-12-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:02:27', 0, 0, 'friendship', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dec2004_loving_is_giving.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/love-is-giving', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1226, 3, 'Trust: The Foundation of All Godly Relationship', '<p>This teaching will prompt you to examine yourself and consider the following questions: Are you generally a trusting or a distrusting person? Have you ever trusted when you shouldn&#39;t have or not trusted when you should have?</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:28; 2:15; 3:6; 22:1; Exod. 19:9; Num. 20:9; 1 Sam. 17:32-37; Ps. 9:7; 18:2; 19:2; 52:8; 54:4; 55:16; 56:3, 10; 57:1; Gal. 5:19-22; Luke 16:19; Rom. 5:3; 12:2; Eph. 3:16; James 1:3 Heb. 11:17</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2004-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '58:42', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2004_trust_the_foundation.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/trust-the-foundation-of-all-godly-relationship', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1227, 3, 'The Importance of Speaking in Tongues', '<p>This teaching is primarily for people who already speak in tongues and is an exhortation to do so as much as possible. It does not teach how to speak in tongues but goes into detail as to why we should.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 11:17, 25; 1 Chr. 12:18; 24:20; Isa. 28:7-11; Matt. 6:3-4; Acts 2:3-4, 11, 32-33; 10:44, 46; 19:61; Rom. 2:16; 1 Cor. 2:6-11; 12:3, 7; 13:4-5, 24-25; 14:1-21, 39; 2 Cor. 3:17; Eph. 3:2; 1 John 3:23-24; Jude 1:20; Rev. 1:12-20; 2:1-11, 17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2004-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:25', 0, 0, 'praise', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2004_importance_of_sit.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-importance-of-speaking-in-tongues', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 71, null),
(1228, 3, 'What Jesus Christ is Doing For Us Today', '<p>This inspiring and informative teaching will enhance your relationship with the Lord Jesus Christ, in that it will help you understand that Scripture reveals what Jesus is currently actively doing for each member of his Body, the Church.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:16-17; John 5:21-22; Acts 1:21; 2:29-36, 47; 7:54; 9:10, 32-35; 16:7, 18-19; Rom. 8:34; 1Cor. 16:7; 2 Cor. 12:8; Gal. 1:11, 16-17; 2:19; Phil. 3:21; Col. 1:16-17; 2:19; Eph. 1:19-20; 4:9-11, 15-16; 1 John 1:3; Rev. 1:1, 9-20; 2:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2004-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:55', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may2004_what_is_jc_doing_today.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/what-jesus-christ-is-doing-for-us-today', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(1229, 3, 'Healthy Submission', '<p>This teaching is not only a step toward greater understanding of God&lsquo;s heart for marriage, but also an exhortation to all in the Body of Christ to show their submission to the Lord Jesus by demonstrating appropriate submission to others.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:1-4, 15; 5:13, 21-32; 6:13; Phil. 2:5-14; Acts 5:1-10; 18:10-21, 24-28; Prov. 27:6; Col. 1:24, 27-29</p> <p>Teacher: Gary and Karen Theisen</p>', '2004-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:23', 0, 0, 'marriage', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/feb2004_healthy_submission.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/healthy-submission', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 13, null),
(1230, 3, 'Self Talk', '<p>This teaching examines the scriptural basis for carefully considering what we are thinking about and &ldquo;talking to ourselves&rdquo; about, especially when what we are dwelling on in our minds is contradictory to God&rsquo;s Word.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 10:17; Prov. 23:7; Phil. 4:4-9; 2 Cor. 10:5; 1 Sam. 27:1; 30:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2003-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:21', 0, 0, 'habits, attitude', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep2003_selftalk.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/self-talk', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(1231, 3, 'Financial Stewardship: God''s Heart Concerning Money and Possessions', '<p>This teaching develops the concept of &ldquo;stewardship&rdquo; as the Biblical balance between the poverty and prosperity extremes taught by some Christians. It summarizes five principles of stewardship and examines the Biblical concept of ownership and property rights.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:24; 17:20; 21:21; 25:21-45; Luke 6:20-24; 12:22, 32; Mark 3:28; 4:18; 10:17-31; Ps. 50:12; 109:1-20; John 10:10; James 1:6-7; Gen. 2:15; 24:24-35; 26:12-14; Eccles. 2:18; 8:14; Prov. 10:15; 14:31; 30:8-9; Exod. 19:5; 21:20; 22:25; 23:10-11; Lev. 19:9; 25:8, 23, 25, 28; Job 41:11; Deut. 10:18; 14:26, 28; 15:1-18; 19:14; 20:17; 23:19; Hosea 5:10; Ruth 2:3, 7; Acts 2:44</p> <p>Teacher: Dan Gallagher</p>', '2003-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:13', 0, 0, 'money, wealth, debt', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan2003_financial_stewardship.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/financial-stewardship-gods-heart-concerning-money-and-possessions', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1232, 3, 'TRANSFORMATION: Becoming like Christ', '<p>The Bible says that Christians are to be &ldquo;imitators of God&rdquo; and are to live a life of love as Jesus Christ did. Doing so requires that we get rid of anger, bitterness, and evil communication, and to purify our hearts. Scripture provides steps we can take to accomplish this.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:8; 4:17, 29, 31; 5:1-4; James 4:8; Rom. 8:3; 12:2; Deut. 6:25; Matt. 5:27, 29-30; 12:33-34; 13:15; Luke 6:45; 2 Cor. 1:3-5; 13:7; 1 Tim. 4:7; Rom. 6:13; Titus 2:11-12; Phil. 3:10; 4:8; Col. 1:24; Acts 9:4; 1 Cor. 15:58</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2002-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:13:19', 0, 0, 'obedience', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/oct2002_transformation_beinglikechrist.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/transformation-becoming-like-christ', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 107, null),
(1233, 3, 'Women: Man''s View or God''s View?', '<p>This sequel to &ldquo;The Role of Women in the Church&rdquo; (Mar/Apr 1996) is a powerful encouragement to women who have doubted God&rsquo;s calling because of false interpretations of difficult scriptures. The teaching concludes with a biblical example of one woman&rsquo;s powerful calling.</p> <p>Note: In the years since this excellent teaching, the conclusion was reached that 1 Cor. 14:34-35 are probably not authentic. The teaching is still well worth listening to.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:11-15; 1 Cor. 10:32; 11:1-16; 14:33-35; Eph. 5:22-23; Esther 1:10-12; 2:1, 5-7, 17-18; 4:12-16; 5:8</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2002-06-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:52', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jun2002_women_gods_view_mens_view.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/women-mans-view-or-gods-view', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(1234, 3, 'Healthily Processing Anger', '<p>Anger can be justifiable or unjustifiable. This teaching looks at the physiological, psychological, and spiritual prices we pay when we deal with our anger inappropriately. It also provides strategies for properly dealing with anger, both our own and someone else&rsquo;s when it is directed at us.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 4:26-27, 29-32; Ps. 2:2-3; 78:12-16, 38; 103:8; Jer. 44:1-8; Rom. 1:18; 7:15-23; 12:17-21; Mark 3:1-6; John 2:13-19; Matt. 5:33-37; 16:21-23; Luke 9:51-56; 13:10-17; 15:1-32; 2 Cor. 12:20-21; Prov. 15:1-2; 16:32</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2002-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:12:02', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar2002_healthily_processing_anger.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/healthily-processing-anger', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 58, null),
(1235, 3, 'Overcoming Evil with Good: A Response to the Tragedy of September 11, 2001', '<p>God is not responsible in any way for terror, death or any other evil. This teaching examines what our proper biblical response to evil should be, so that we can have a safe and free society.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Luke 4:5; 6:29; 10:17-23; 11:14-19, 29, 35; 22:36; 1 John 3:8; 4:7; 5:19; Gen. 1:28; 9:6; 2 Cor. 4:4; Heb. 2:14; Rev. 12:7; 1 Cor. 15:26; Acts 1:8; 2:38; 10:38; Job 1:6; 16:10; John 1:17-18; Eph. 6:12; 1 Kings 17:17-20; Rom. 12:21; 13:3-4; Exod. 21:12; Lam. 3:30; Isa. 50:6; Matt. 26:52</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2001-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:17:19', 0, 0, 'Enemies, Self-Defense', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep_oct2001_overcoming_evil_with_good.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/overcoming-evil-with-good-a-response-to-the-tragedy-of-september-11-2001', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(1236, 3, 'The Role of Women in the Church - Part 2', '<p>Women have been excluded from teaching and leading in the Christian Church, historically and currently. 1 Timothy 2:11-15 has been used to support this stance. This teaching clarifies the meaning of these verses.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 20:14-22; Rom. 12:3-8; 16:1-7, 12, 15; 1 Tim. 2:11-15; Prov. 31:1</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2001-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '57:46', 15, 2, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/may_jun_2001_role_of_women.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-role-of-women-in-the-church-part-2', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1237, 3, 'Reaching out with the love of God; Christianity - The come as you are party', '<p>Jesus Christ showed us how to reach out with the love of God. He loved both the sinners and the Pharisees who were around him. In so doing, he left us a model to follow and showed that the language of love is universal.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:19; Rom. 2:4; 5:6, 43-44; 12:16; Eph. 4:15, 29, 32; 5:1-2; Luke 15:1-32; Matt. 5:43-44; Gal. 6:1; James 1:19; 3:17; Jer. 10:24; Eccles. 7:20, 21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2001-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:05:23', 0, 0, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr_2001_come_as_you_are_party.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/reaching-out-with-the-love-of-god-christianity-the-come-as-you-are-party', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1238, 3, 'Proverbs: Wisdom for All Ages', '<p>This teaching examines some of the structure of Proverbs and shows that the famous section of Proverbs 31:1-31 is not speaking about a &quot;virtuous woman,&quot; but rather is figurative language personifying &quot;Wisdom&rdquo; and &quot;Folly&quot; as two women.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:1-33; 2:1-5, 12-19; 3:13-17; 4:5-9; 5:1-6; 7:4-23; 8:1-17; 9:1-6,13; 10:1, 12, 19, 23, 30; 11:1; 12:18; 15:10; 16:18, 28; 18:13; 22:6; 23:13-14; 25:2; 26:14; 28:26; 29:15-17; 31:10-20; Matt. 13:10-13; Eccles. 8:8; 2 Tim. 2:24-26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1999-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:25:05', 0, 0, 'Foolishness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/julaug1999_proverbs_wisdom_for_all_ages.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/proverbs-wisdom-for-all-ages', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1239, 3, 'Running for the Prize', '<p>This teaching clearly sets forth the difference between salvation and the rewards that Christ will give to those believers who have earned them. It presents compelling evidence that it is not wrong to strive to get rewards in the Kingdom. The Apostle Paul states that we are to labor, even agonize, as we run in such a way as to receive the prize.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 3:9-17; 9:24-25; 13:1-13; Heb. 12:1-2; Eph. 3:2, 9; John 14:21-24; Exod. 23:4; Col. 1:28-30; 3:23; Matt. 5:1-12; 6:1-5; 10:40-42; 16:13-27; 18:1; 20:20; 1 John 1:9; 2:28; 2 John 1:8; 2 Cor. 5:9; Rom. 14:9; 1 Thess. 2:19; 4:8; 2 Tim. 2:11; 4:6; James 1:12; 1 Pet. 5:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1997-07-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:19', 0, 0, 'inheritance, confess, persevere', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jul_aug1997_running_for_the_prize.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/running-for-the-prize', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 39, null),
(1240, 3, 'The Ten Commandments', '<p>This teaching explains how the Christian can separate the laws that were &quot;done away&quot; in Christ from the ones still applicable. It gives special attention to the Ten Commandments and how they are to be applied today.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 6:14; Deut. 6:25; 19:11; 22:1-4; Heb. 10:1; Lev. 19:32; 24:17-22; Exod. 20; 21:12; Eph. 6:2; Gen. 9:6; Num. 45:16; Eccles. 4:9-12; Titus 2:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1997-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:25:35', 0, 0, 'law, laws', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr_1997_ten_commandment.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-ten-commandments', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1241, 3, 'The Role of Women in the Church - Part 1', '<p>This teaching addresses many translation errors and biases in 1 Timothy 2:11-15. Women have often been excluded from teaching and leadership roles in the Church because of misunderstanding and/or mistranslation of this section of scripture. Along with providing a more accurate translation of these verses, dominant cultural influences at the time of Paul&rsquo;s writing are explained.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 1:3; 2:11-15; 4:7; 5:14; 6:20-21; 2 Thess. 2:7; Rom. 6:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1996-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:13:25', 15, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr_1996_role_of_women_pt1.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-role-of-women-in-the-church-part-1', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 13, null),
(1242, 3, 'Justification by Faith', '<p>Martin Luther proclaimed over 500 years ago justification by faith alone as the basic tenet of true Christianity. Any person who confesses Jesus Christ as Lord and believes in his heart that God raised him from the dead is justified by that faith, independent of any good works on his part. Good works should be the fruit of a Christian understanding his salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:1-17; 3:10, 19-31; 4:1-25; 5:1; 7:7, 12; 9:30-33; 10:1-11; Matt. 3:1; 4:17, 23; 16:21-22; Mark 9:9-13; 11:22; Luke 9:1; 18:31; 24:11, 36-37, 45; Heb. 11:1-10; Hab. 2:4; Ps. 40:6; 51:16; 1 Sam. 15:22; Jer. 7:22; Hosea 6:6; Amos 5:21; Gal. 2:15; 3:1-29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1995-09-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:20:42', 0, 0, 'Reformation, Gospel', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/sep95_justification_by_faith.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/justification-by-faith', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1243, 3, 'The Last Week of Christ''s Life', '<p>Tradition has greatly distorted much of the beautiful truth about the events leading up to and including our Savior&#39;s death and resurrection. This teaching weaves the details from the four Gospels into a chronological timeline of these events, highlighting the similarities and differences of specific details as they have been recorded in the Gospels.</p> <p><strong>Verses:</strong> 1 Cor. 5:7; 15:4; Gen. 3:15; Exod. 12:1-15; Mark 11:1-12, 20; 13:1; 14:1, 12, 21; 15:16, 21-25, 42; John 12:1-19; 13:1; 18:12-27; 19:14, 31; 20:1; Matt. 12:38; 15:25; 21:1-11, 14-18, 23; 24:1; 26:1, 17, 57; Prov. 25:2; Luke 22:40-43; 23:1-7; Isa. 52:13; Ps. 22:31</p> <p><strong>Teacher:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '1995-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:25:11', 0, 0, 'sacrifice', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr_1995_last_week_of_christs_life.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-last-week-of-christs-life', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(1244, 3, 'The Sons of God Of Genesis Six', '<p>This teaching explains who the &ldquo;sons of God&rdquo; were in Genesis 6, and that they orchestrated one of the first Satanic attacks on mankind to try to stop the promised &ldquo;seed&rdquo; of Genesis 3:15 from being born.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:11-12, 21, 24-25; 3:17-18; 6:1-5; Lev. 19:19; Num. 13:1-2, 23, 26-33; Deut. 2:9-11, 19-22; 3:10-11; 7:1-2; 9:1-3; 20:10-18; Josh. 11:21-23; 1 Chron. 20:4-8; Job 1:6; 2:1; 26:1-5; 38:4-7; Ps. 88:3-10; Prov. 2:16-18; 21:16; Isa. 14:3-9; 26:14, 19; Dan. 3:25, 28; 2 Cor. 5:1-2; 1 Pet. 3:18-20; 2 Pet. 2:4; Jude 1:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:27:45', 0, 0, 'nephilim, angels', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/jan_feb_1993_sons_of_god_gen6.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-sons-of-god-of-genesis-six', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 517, null),
(1245, 3, 'The Kingdom of God: Paradise Regained', '<p>The Hope is the anchor that keeps Christians from drifting away from God. For many, this hope is vague because of the lack of understanding of what happens after the gathering together (or &ldquo;Rapture&rdquo;) of the Church. This teaching will bring clarification of the Christian&rsquo;s future in the Kingdom of God following the Rapture.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:15; 3:15, 26; 12:7; 13:15; 49:10; Job 19:25-27; Ps. 103:19; Isa. 2:4; 11:2-9; 26:19; Jer. 31:34; 9:7; Ezek. 37:11-13; 47:13-14; Dan. 12:1-2, 13; Amos 9:13; Mic. 4:3; Matt. 4:7; 5:3-10, 20; 10:5-7; Mark 1:14-15; 11:9-10; Luke 17:21; 23:40-43; Rom. 5:1-2; 2 Cor. 12:3-4; Eph. 1:18; 5:5; Col. 1:12-14, 21-23; 1 Thess. 2:12; 2 Tim. 2:12; 4:18; Heb. 6:17-19; 2 Pet. 1:10-11; Rev. 20:1-3, 5-6, 7-10; 21:1-4, 15-18, 22-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1992-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:26:54', 0, 0, 'Inheritance, Immortality', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr1992_kingdom_of_god_paradise_regained.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-kingdom-of-god-paradise-regained', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 55, null),
(1246, 3, 'The Bible And Civil Law', '<p>Scripture states in 1 Timothy 1:8 that the law is good if one uses it lawfully. This teaching explains how God intended government to function to protect the rights of law-abiding citizens while fairly punishing criminals in accordance with the seriousness of their crimes.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 21:1-7, 12-21, 28-36; 22:1-31; 23:1-9; Num. 15:32-36; 5:1-4; Deut. 15:12-14; 22:8; 1 Kings 2:28-31; Neh. 5:3, 12; Amos 3:11-12; Acts 5:29, 40; Rom. 13:1-7; 1 Tim. 1:8-11; 1 Pet. 2:13-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1990-03-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:23:21', 0, 0, 'Justice, Fairness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/mar_apr_1990_bible_civil_law.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-bible-and-civil-law', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1252, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 1 | Introduction; Unitarianism Explained', '<p>This session discusses what Unitarianism is and how it elevates Yahweh, God, as having no equals, as the one true God, and as God alone. It explains that this in no way detracts from the significance of His Son Jesus nor the powerful role of God&rsquo;s gift of holy spirit. Understanding their harmony and distinctly different roles shows God as supreme, Jesus as His faithful Son, and the holy spirit as God&rsquo;s power and influence in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4; 32:39; Exod. 20:3; Isa. 40:25; 46:9; Ps. 83:18; 86:10; John 14:1; 1 Cor. 8:6; 1 Tim. 2:5</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:16:27', 22, 1, 'Tradition, Shema', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-1-On-The-Errors-of-The-Trinity.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-1', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 241, null),
(1253, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 2 | Trinitarianism Explained', '<p>This session defines Trinitarianism as &ldquo;father, son, and holy spirit are three persons with one essence that are co-equal and co-eternal,&rdquo; and three different forms of Trinitarianism are explained. Established about 1700 years ago, this new doctrine requires new vocabulary and new meanings not mentioned in Scripture. The doctrine of the Trinity is not taught in the Bible by Moses, Jesus, Peter, or Paul because it didn&rsquo;t exist then.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 12:30; John 10:30; 20:31; 1 Cor. 8:6; Heb. 1:5</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:11:43', 22, 2, 'Polytheism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-2-On-The-Errors-of-The-Trinity.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-2', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 143, null),
(1254, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 3 | Trinitarianism – A Doctrine of Inference', '<p>Most Christian doctrines are clearly stated in the Bible, but the Trinity is one that is not. Instead, it is formulated from various verses and woven into a concept that is contradicted by many clear verses. Many Trinitarian biblical scholars cannot explain this doctrine and profess that it just must be taken by faith. Some go so far as stating that salvation is dependent on believing the Trinity even when no scripture supports this conclusion.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; 10:30; 2 Cor 13:14; Rom. 10:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:18:15', 22, 3, 'Polytheism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-3.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-3', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 146, null),
(1255, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 4 | The Doctrine of the Double Nature of Christ', '<p>The cornerstone of Trinitarian doctrine is that Christ is 100% man and 100% God, that is, Christ has two natures in one person. However, Jesus himself stated that he only does what God shows or tells him, and that God is greater than he. The Scriptures describe Jesus as divine, meaning God-like, but that doesn&rsquo;t mean he is equal to God.The Trinitarian doctrine is neither defined nor supported by scripture.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:13; Mark 13:32; John 1:18; 14:27</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:07:15', 22, 4, 'idolatry', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-4.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-4', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 131, null),
(1256, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 5 | Arguments Outside of Scripture Used to Defend the Trinitarian Doctrine', '<p>The first three centuries of Christian doctrine embraced the Apostle&rsquo;s Creed and made no mention of a Trinitarian doctrine. However, numerous church councils in the fourth century introduced human philosophy, largely based on Plato&rsquo;s writings, and created a new view that God, Jesus, and the Holy Spirit are three persons with one essence, co-equal and co-eternal. In this way, Scripture was corrupted to mean something that was never intended.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:32; 1 John 5:7; 1 Tim. 3:16; 1 Thess. 5:21; Col. 2:8</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:13', 22, 5, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-5.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-5', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 103, null),
(1257, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 6 | Trinity: Mystery or Contradiction', '<p>The Bible is God&rsquo;s revelation to humankind to reveal truth and bring understanding. Using mysterious explanations is incompatible with God&rsquo;s purpose. God and Jesus are not fully knowable by humankind, but what is written about them can be known and understood. Scripture exhorts people to use reason and search for truth. Literary guidelines for Scripture interpretation include understanding figures of speech, biblical customs and culture, and word meanings.</p> <p>Verses: John 4:20-23; 5:36-39; Rom. 10:17; Acts 17:22-23; 1 Thess. 5:21; Eph 1:16-18; 2 Tim. 3:14-17</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:36', 22, 6, 'hermeneutics', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-6.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-6', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 102, null),
(1258, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 7 | The God of the Old Testament and New Testament is the Same.', '<p>The Old Testament reveals God as being supreme, above all other gods. His position of supremacy is repeated in the New Testament. Jesus frequently referred to God as his father and taught that he did the will of the Father. Jesus gave God the glory in all that he did. They were a team of a loving Father and His obedient Son. No Trinitarian alliance between God and Jesus is explicitly referred to in the Old or New Testament.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 6:4; Mark 12:29-30; 1 Cor. 8:6</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:31', 22, 7, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-7.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-7', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 51, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1259, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 8 | Jesus&rsquo; Denial of Being God', '<p>The differences between God and Jesus are so numerous in Scripture that it is impossible for them to be co-equal. God is eternal, omniscient, omnipotent, self-existent, and infinitely good. Jesus not only never claimed these attributes, but also denied he had them. The word <em>logos</em> in John 1:1 is shown not be a person, but the manifold aspects of God.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 9:22; Matt. 19:17; 28:18; Mark 10:18; John 1:1, 14; 14:28; 7:16; 2 Cor. 13:4; Isa. 40:13; 1 Tim 2:5</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:36', 22, 8, 'incarnation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-8.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-8', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(1260, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 9 | Jesus Did Not Exist Before His Birth', '<p>The past tense, when describing a future action as being accomplished in the present, is often used to state that Jesus was alive before his birth. However, this is a figure of speech that emphasizes the certainty now that a future event will indeed happen. Further, the holy spirit is called a gift from God, not a third person of the Trinity, and is often omitted in epistolary salutations when God and Jesus are mentioned.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:30-35; John 6:62; 8:58; 17:5; Rev. 13:8; Luke 24:49</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:40', 22, 9, 'preexistence', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-9.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-9', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1261, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 10 | Names and Titles of God and Jesus', '<p>There are many names for God in Scripture including Lord, Yahweh/Jehovah, Elohim, and more. Jesus also has many names including Lord, Son of God, Messiah/Christ, and Savior. The holy spirit is called &ldquo;the Comforter&rdquo; and &ldquo;the gift of God.&rdquo; If God, Jesus, and the holy spirit are co-equal, then the names of each would apply to all the three. This session addresses that this is not the case. Each one is uniquely different but has similarities to the others.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 2:6-11; Isa. 7:14; 9:6; Matt. 1:23; 16:22-23; John 1:1-3; 20:28, 31; Exo. 7:1; 20:1-3; Gen. 1:26; 3:22; 11:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:10', 22, 10, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-10.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-10', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1262, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 11 | Similarities Do Not Imply Equality', '<p>The concept of the Trinity entails that attributes of God are shared by Jesus and the holy spirit, implying that those similar attributes make them co-equal. However, a great many verses also apply those same attributes to other individuals in Scripture. Thus, upon considering a given attribute, if it applies to God and to other people, that doesn&rsquo;t make those other people equal to God.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 43:11; Acts 5:31; Ezra 7:12; 1 Tim 6:15; 1 Chron. 29:20; Col. 2:9; 3:13; 1 John 1:9; Eph. 3:19; 1 Cor. 11:7; 2 Cor. 4:4; John 17:14</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:19:41', 22, 11, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-11.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-11', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 61, null),
(1263, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 12 | Difficult and/or Misunderstood Verses Incorrectly Used to Confirm the Trinity', '<p>Studying the biblical verses cited to confirm the Trinity reveals problems such as corruption from the ancient texts, misinterpretation in light of context, or misunderstanding Eastern culture through a Western mindset. Such verses are addressed in detail one at the time to show how the typical interpretations contradict the preponderance of verses that state that Yahweh God is supreme, has no equals, and is God alone.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:7-10; 17:5; Acts 7:44-45; 1 Cor. 10:4; 2 Cor. 5:19; 13:14; Phil. 2:5-6; Col. 1:16-19; 1 Tim. 3:16; Heb. 1:1-2; 11:24-26; Rev. 1:8</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:17:38', 22, 12, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Disk-12.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-12', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 35, null),
(1264, 4, 'On the Errors of the Trinity | Session 13 | Study of &ldquo;Logos&rdquo;', '<p>Trinitarians state that the &ldquo;logos&rdquo; in John 1:1 is Jesus, who was with and was God from the beginning. However, when Jesus is substituted for God, many verses of Scripture make no sense. However, if the &ldquo;logos&rdquo; is understood to encompass the power, wisdom, reason, and discourse of God, of which Jesus was the human expression, then the verses make sense. John 20:31 states that Jesus is the son of God, not God the son.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:1, 14, 18; 20:31; Rev. 19:13</p> <p>Teacher: Don Snedeker</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '54:56', 22, 13, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/5fbac378-5998-4528-b265-2ddb079082b9-Logos.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26205/episodes/session-13-study-of-logos', '/i/seminars/TE.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 45, null),
(1265, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 1 | Introduction', '<p>Session 1 focuses on the basics of the Bible: the integrity of the Word of God, how the Word of God came to us, the characteristics of God&rsquo;s Word, and the blessings of His Word.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:17; Rom. 7:12; 10:17; 15:4; Ps. 12:6; 19:7; 138:2; 119:97-100, 160; Num. 23:19; 2 Tim. 3:15-16; 2 Pet. 1:20-21; Gal. 1:11; John 8:32; 17:17; Luke 24:32; Jer. 15:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '36:40', 18, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-1-New-Life-In-Christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-1-new-life-in-christ', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 121, null),
(1266, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 2 | &ldquo;Take My Word for It&rdquo; – God', '<p>Session 2 focuses on the historically-verifiable prophecies that are recorded in God&rsquo;s Word, citing five prophecies that did in fact predict the future accurately. This sets a track record for the reliability of the truths that are contained throughout God&rsquo;s Word.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 12:2; 16:10; Num. 24:5; Deut. 17:14; 1 Sam. 8:4; Isa. 44:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:29', 18, 2, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-2-Take-My-Word-for-It-God.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-2-take-my-word-for-it-god', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1267, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 3 | &ldquo;Take My Word for It&rdquo; – God (continued)', '<p>Session 3 highlights the fact that God&rsquo;s Word is verifiable through scientific, archaeological, and historical records. Scriptures cited include accurate descriptions of weather patterns and winds. Archaeological dig sites confirm the existence of historical nations and locations and reveal timelines consistent with their biblical references.</p> <p>Verses: Job 26:7; 36:27-28; Eccles. 1:6, 7; Rev. 16:16; Dan. 1:1; 5:1; Jer. 25:1; John 7:17; 14:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '26:08', 18, 3, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-3-Take-My-Word-for-It-God-continued-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-3-take-my-word-for-it-god-continued', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1268, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 4 | The Text We Have Is Reliable', '<p>Session 4 continues with the theme of the verifiability of God&rsquo;s Word, highlighting the fact that multiple copies of manuscripts build the tenacity and reliability of the text. The Dead Sea Scrolls and &ldquo;lost&rdquo; books are addressed in this teaching, as well as &ldquo;information overlap,&rdquo; the idea that the same incidents are described in multiple places in the Bible and agree in detail. These topics all reinforce the accuracy of God&rsquo;s Word.</p> <p>Verses: Phil 3:3; 1 Cor. 14:1; Matt. 6:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:46', 18, 4, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-4-The-Text-We-Have-Is-Reliable.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-4-the-text-we-have-is-reliable', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1269, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 5 | The Workman and the Perfect Word', '<p>Session 5 continues with the theme of the accuracy of God&rsquo;s word with emphasis on the reader&rsquo;s working to examine the scriptures carefully. This includes understanding the context, culture, and circumstance of the verses. The concept of &ldquo;apparent contradictions&rdquo; is discussed as well.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:20; Hos. 4:6; 2 Tim. 2:15; Matt. 13:10; 15:1-3; 22:29; John 7:17; 1 Cor. 2:14; Prov. 2:25; 25:2; Mark 4:33-34; Gen. 6:19-21; 7:1-3; 8:18-20; 31:19, 29, 48-50; Exod. 2:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:10', 18, 5, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-5-The-Workman-and-the-Perfect-Word.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-5-the-workman-and-the-perfect-word', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 46, null),
(1270, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 6 | Uncovering the Perfect Word', '<p>Session 6 identifies 5 key elements necessary for us to understand and watch for in Scripture that enable us to properly interpret God&rsquo;s Word. These are context, scope, customs, figures of speech, and errors in translation or transmission. The teachers illustrate each of these keys through the scriptures in a most intriguing fashion.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 12:38-40; 17:10-13; 24:3-14; Rev. 14:6-7; Mark 15:25, 33-34, 42; Lev. 23:4-7; Num. 28:16-18; John 19:31; 1 Pet. 1:13; Luke 6:29; Lam. 3:30; Isa. 50:6; Mal. 4:5; 2 Kings 9:30-31; Exod. 20:13; 21:12,15-16, 20; Eph. 3:2-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:34', 18, 6, 'mystery', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-6-Uncovering-the-Perfect-Word.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-6-uncovering-the-perfect-word', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(1271, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 7 | Uncovering the Perfect Word (continued)', '<p>Session 7 introduces the topic of Administrations, also known as Dispensations, whereby God changes the rules of how He relates to His people over time. The eight administrations are enumerated and described, along with corroborating scriptures. When an administration changes, the rules frequently change as well. Examples of rules that changed include marriage, worship practices, food, and the Sabbath.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 3:2, 9; Gen. 1:29; 2:24; 9:1-6; 12:8; 17:12-14; 20:11-12; Gal. 5:2; Exod. 20:8-10; 24:3-8; Lev. 11:3-7; 18:9; Deut. 12:1-3; Jer. 30:7; Matt. 19:4-6; Mark 1:40-45; Col. 1:25-26; Rev. 20:7-9; Rom. 1:4-5; 15:4; 1 Cor. 1:1-2; 7:2; 10:25; Col. 2:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:25', 18, 7, 'dispensationalism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-7-Uncovering-the-Perfect-Word-continued-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-7-uncovering-the-perfect-word-continued', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 55, null),
(1272, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 8 | The Fall', '<p>Session 8 begins with the statement &ldquo;The whole Bible is about two men,&rdquo; the first Adam who ruined everything by bringing on the moment that mankind took on sin nature, and the last Adam who is in the process of fixing everything&ndash;Jesus Christ, the &ldquo;Savior to Come,&rdquo; as prophesied in Genesis. The teaching also describes some of the many figures of speech used in the Bible as the event of the fall is explained.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:45; Gen. 2:7, 16-17, 25; 3:1, 8-22; Luke 11:35; Rom. 5:12, 18-19; 8:18-22; Rev. 22:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:02', 18, 8, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-8-The-Fall.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-8-the-fall', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 44, null),
(1273, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 9 | Who Is In Control?', '<p>Session 9 specifically addresses the often-used statement &ldquo;God is in control of this world.&rdquo; Here we learn that in the Garden, God gave dominion of the earth to Adam. When Adam sinned, he (Adam) relinquished that control to the Devil. Numerous scriptures demonstrate that God is love. In contrast, our world today is under the Devil&rsquo;s control and reflects his character&ndash;sickness, war, lying, adultery, murder, and worse.</p> <p>Verses: James 1:17; Gen. 1:26-28; 1 John 3:8; 5:19-20; John 1:17-18; 10:10; 1 Cor. 15:26; 2 Cor. 4:4; Luke 4:5-7; 10:17-24; 13:10-17; Heb. 2:14; Acts 10:38; Matt. 12:22-26; Exod. 4:21; Job 1:6; Eph. 6:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit, Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:46', 18, 9, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-9-Who-Is-In-Control-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-9-who-is-in-control', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 43, null),
(1274, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 10 | Where Are the Dead?', '<p>In Session 10, the teachers continue their quest to challenge tradition vs. Biblical truth by addressing where the dead are now, and where they are not. Death is an enemy, not an immediate transition to the afterlife. Concepts covered in Scripture include Hell, the grave, the Lake of Fire, heaven, and the devil. We learn that there is no everlasting torment for the unsaved, and that the only way to have everlasting life is through Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:21; 2:19; 3:4; Deut. 18:9-13; 1 Cor. 15:26; 2 Cor. 5:1-8; Ps. 6:5; 49:12-14; 115:17; 146:4; Eccles. 3:19-21; 9:4-6, 10; 12:7; Job 14:12; John 3:13, 16; Acts 2:34; 1 Thess. 4:13, 15-18; Rev. 20:4-5, 11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:47', 18, 10, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-10-Where-Are-the-Dead-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-10-where-are-the-dead', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 94, null),
(1275, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 11 | Salvation and the Savior', '<p>Session 11 highlights the fact that the entire Bible, from Genesis 3:15 to Revelation 22:21, points to Jesus Christ as our Lord and Savior. Every one of the 39 books in the Old Testament makes a specific reference to the coming Messiah. The teaching demonstrates in detail exactly how Jesus was qualified to be THE Messiah.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:3-4; 15:20-23; Gen. 22:1-2; Heb. 2:17-18; 5:7-9; 11:17-19; John 1:29; 17:1-3; Rom. 6:23; 2 Cor. 5:21; Isa. 52:13; 53:12; 1 Tim. 2:5; Luke 1:26-35; 24:1-8; Matt. 27:45-50; Acts 1:9-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '37:45', 18, 11, 'salvation, wholeness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-11-Salvation-and-the-Savior.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-11-salvation-and-the-savior', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 105, null),
(1276, 4, 'New Life in Christ  | Session 12 | Salvation By Faith', '<p>Session 12 covers the fundamentals of being saved, that is, being &ldquo;born again.&rdquo; Faith is at the root of pleasing God. It is essential for the new birth, the gift of salvation, which we learn is easy and free to obtain. The teaching continues with discussion about the concepts of grace and works, crucial elements which differentiate how the Old and New Testaments address salvation and righteousness.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11:1, 6-7; 11:22; 2 Cor. 5:7; 10:15; Luke 17:5; Rom. 3:19-24; 10:9-10,17; 1 Tim. 2:3-4; Acts 16:22-32; 21:17-21; Eph. 2:8-9; Deut. 6:25; John 3:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:14', 18, 12, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-12-Salvation-By-Faith.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-12-salvation-by-faith', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 103, null),
(1277, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 13 | The Christian Church', '<p>Session 13 describes the origin of the Church, which is not a building but rather an assembly of people with a specific purpose. The focus is on the 7 Epistles to the Church and how they address the doctrine, reproof, and correction aspects of what God revealed to Paul. The apex of the teaching presents God&rsquo;s &lsquo;sacred secret&rsquo; not revealed in the Old Testament or the Gospels, that is, the glorious riches of Christ in you, the hope of glory!</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:2; 2:6-10; 3:7-11; Matt. 13:11; 18:17; 25:31-34; Acts 2:1-4; 19:32,39; 1 Thess. 4:13-18; Rev. 19:11-16; Eph. 1:9; 3:1-10; Col. 1:25-27</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:30', 18, 13, 'mystery', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-13-The-Christian-Church.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-13-the-christian-church', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 66, null),
(1278, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 14 | The New Birth', '<p>This session compares and contrasts salvation in the Old Testament with salvation in the New Testament. In the New Testament, you will find the terms &ldquo;adoption,&rdquo; &ldquo;fullness,&rdquo; &ldquo;guarantee,&rdquo; &ldquo;gift,&rdquo; and &ldquo;nothing will separate us,&rdquo; among others. God makes these promises to us, His children, due to the greatness of His love for us and for His glory through the saving work of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 3:1; 1 Pet. 1:3, 23; Titus 3:5; James 1:8; Eph. 1:5,13-14, 23; 2:10; Rom. 8:15, 35-39; Gal. 4:5; 1 Cor 3:10-17; 2 Cor. 1:21-22; 5:4-5; Hosea 1:2-8; Deut. 6:25; Ps. 1:4-5; Ezek. 33:11-16; Matt. 10:22; 19:16-18; 24:13; Rev. 2:10-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:51', 18, 14, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-14-The-New-Birth.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-14-the-new-birth', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(1279, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 15 | The Gift of Holy Spirit', '<p>We learned in the previous session that salvation in the Old Testament was vastly different in the New Testament. Session 15 continues that comparison, differentiating between Holy Spirit (the Giver) and holy spirit (the gift). In the Old Testament, holy spirit was given to few people, given by measure, and was conditional. After Pentecost, holy spirit was given to <em>all</em> who believe, in fullness, and is permanent.</p> <p>Verses: John 2:17; 4:24; 14:12; 15:26; 20:22; Acts 1:8; 2:1-5, 8, 38; 20:28; Luke 11:13; 24:49, 53; 1 Thess. 4:8; 1 Pet. 1:23; 2 Pet. 1:4; Col. 1:2; Lev. 23:15; Matt. 3:11; Ps. 51:11; 69:9; Num. 11:16-17, 25; 2 Kings 2:9; Judg. 16:20; 1 Sam. 16:14; Eph. 1:13; 4:5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '37:41', 18, 15, 'Counselor', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-15-The-Gift-of-Holy-Spirit.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-15-the-gift-of-holy-spirit', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 31, null),
(1280, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 16 | The Manifestations of Holy Spirit', '<p>This session continues to unfold the many facets of the gift of holy spirit. This one gift has many functions, and we as Christians can use them all &ndash; all nine of them &ndash; when we are born again. This teaching explains that we are to manifest them, that is, we are to bring them to light. The focus of this session is speaking in tongues&mdash;what it is, what it isn&rsquo;t, and 11 reasons why should we do it.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:1-11; 13:1, 8-12; 14:2-6, 15-22; John 14:16, 26; 20:21-22; Acts 1:8; 2:11; 10:46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:38', 18, 16, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-16-The-Manifestations-of-Holy-Spirit.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-16-the-manifestations-of-holy-spirit', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 132, null),
(1281, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 17 | Speaking In Tongues', '<p>This session further illuminates the manifestation of speaking in tongues, discussing why, how often, and how we should or should not pray in this manner. The details are important, or else the Apostle Paul wouldn&rsquo;t have devoted an entire chapter (1 Corinthians 14) to them. When speaking in tongues, what you speak is God&rsquo;s business; that you speak is your business. We are to pray without ceasing.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:6, 10; 14:1, 5, 12, 18, 23; 2 Cor. 1:21; Acts 2:1-4; 10:27-29, 44, 46; 11:1-3,15,18; 1 Thess. 5:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:00', 18, 17, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-17-Speaking-In-Tongues.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-17-speaking-in-tongues', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 52, null),
(1282, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 18 | Hope – the Anchor of the Soul', '<p>This session addresses the error of the traditional Christian belief that when we die, we go immediately to heaven. God&rsquo;s word provides an abundance of evidence that paradise will not be in heaven, but rather will be on this earth. For example, Jesus stated, &ldquo;The meek will inherit the earth.&rdquo; Multiple scripture references show clearly what Christians will inherit and exactly how glorious it will be.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 2:14; 6:19; Matt. 5:5; 26:29; Ps. 37:9-11, 28-29; Ezek. 37:1-14; Gen. 1:30; 13:14-17; Acts 7:5; Rev. 19:11-15; 21:4: Luke 23:43; 1 Thess. 4:17; 1 Cor. 6:2; 13:11-12; Jer. 23:5-6; 31:33-34; Mic. 4:3-4; Isa. 11:6-9; 25:6; 32:15-18; 33:24; 35:1-7, 10; Phil. 3:20-21; Amos 9:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:43', 18, 18, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-18-Hope-the-Anchor-of-the-Soul.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-18-hope-the-anchor-of-the-soul', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1283, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 19 | Hope – Jobs and Judgments', '<p>This session provides descriptions of what paradise will look like and explains how we will spend eternity. God designed us to work, and various Old Testament scriptures detail our future jobs. The session explains that we will be judged for how we have lived our lives, and that judgment involves rewards. God has provided us an avenue for asking for and receiving forgiveness of our sins so that we have the best possible outcome at the judgment.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:15; Isa. 32:1; Amos 9:13-14; Ezek. 39:14-15; 44:10-16; 47:10; Jer. 17:10; 31:12; Eph. 2:10; Matt. 16:27; 25:14-18, 26; 2 Cor. 5:9-11; Col. 3:23-25; 1 Thess. 4:3-6; 2 Tim. 2:11-13; 1 John 1:9; 2:28; Luke 9:26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:26', 18, 19, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-19-Hope-Jobs-and-Judgments.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-19-hope-jobs-and-judgments', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 74, null),
(1284, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 20 | Sonship – Blessings and Responsibilities', '<p>As children of God, we receive countless blessings. This session enumerates the key blessings we have as Christians, among which are righteousness, justification, and sanctification. It addresses the question, &ldquo;Since we know we can&rsquo;t lose our salvation, why not continue sinning?&rdquo; We learn that obedience amplifies our blessings, and that our behavior speaks volumes to those around us, either drawing others toward God or away from Him.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 1:1; 5:21; 10:3-5; Rom. 2:24; 3:20-26; 7:15-17; 12:1-2; 1 Cor. 1:2; Col. 1:2; Phil. 2:12; Heb. 11:24-25; Ps. 119:165; Eph. 2:1-3; 5:1-5: Gal. 5:16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:26', 18, 20, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-20-Sonship-Blessings-and-Responsibilities.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-20-sonship-blessings-and-responsibilities', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(1285, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 21 | Developing the Character of Christ', '<p>Continuing the theme of responsibilities of being God&rsquo;s sons, this session focuses on being like Christ in our behaviors. Known as &ldquo;fruit of the spirit,&rdquo; the Epistle to the Galatians contains a list of nine qualities that we will exhibit as we become more Christlike. We cannot erase our sin nature; however, we can choose to behave in a manner that displays our Christlike nature.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Gal. 5:19-24; 6:1; Matt. 7:21; 11:29-30; Exod. 23:4-5; Luke 6:35, 45; 10:27; 1 Cor. 9:24-27; 13:4-8; Acts 5:41; 1 Thess. 5:16; Heb. 12:2; Ps. 23:5; Phil. 4:7; 2 Cor. 3:11; Isa. 9:6; Col. 1:11; 2 Tim. 3:10; Rom. 2:4; 15:14; Eph. 4:31-32; Num. 12:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '39:37', 18, 21, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-21-Developing-the-Character-of-Christ.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-21-developing-the-character-of-christ', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(1286, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 22 | The Power of Prayer', '<p>Continuing the theme of the responsibilities that come with sonship, this session focuses on prayer and its incredible power. Several related concepts mentioned in this teaching include God&rsquo;s command to pray continually, to be faithful, watchful, thankful, and to pray without ceasing. Most importantly, prayer opens the pathways for God to enter into our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:2; Eph. 6:18; Phil. 4:6; Col. 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:17; Matt. 6:7; Luke 11:1-8; 18:1; Mark 11:20-24; Dan. 10:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit: Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '37:10', 18, 22, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-22-The-Power-of-Prayer.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-22-the-power-of-prayer', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 157, null),
(1287, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 23 | Giving, Witnessing, and Fellowship', '<p>This session concludes the topic of the responsibilities of sonship by addressing God&rsquo;s will for us to give, witness and fellowship with other believers. God has always desired that men give, and He looks at the heart of the giver. Witnessing simply involves telling others about Christ, and He has commanded us to preach to &ldquo;all creation.&rdquo; Fellowship is critical to the church. We are to encourage our brothers and sisters, spurring one another to do good deeds.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 4:3-5; 14:17-20; Heb. 7:4; 10:22-25; Lev. 27:30-33; Mal. 3:8-12; 1 Cor. 9:7-14; 12:12-27; 2 Cor. 5:17-20; 9:6; Mark 12:41-44; 16:15; Rom. 10:9-15; Acts 1:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '38:46', 18, 23, 'ambassador, tithing', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-23-Giving-Witnessing-and-Fellowship.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-23-giving-witnessing-and-fellowship', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(1288, 4, 'New Life in Christ | Session 24 | Praise and Worship', '<p>This closing session summarizes the entire seminar, touching on the many topics that were presented. It concludes with a discussion of worship and praise. Our Heavenly Father, Yahweh, and His Son, our Savior and Lord, Jesus Christ, are indeed worthy of our praise! We are encouraged to maintain our connection to our Masters through fervent prayers, praise, and worship.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 15:1-2; Acts 16:22-25; 1 Tim. 2:8; Neh. 12:27-28, 43; Ps. 150; Phil. 1:9-11; Eph. 1:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit; Sue Carlson</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:26', 18, 24, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-24-Praise-and-Worship.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26146/episodes/session-24-praise-and-worship', '/i/seminars/NLIC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 54, null);
