(1289, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 1 | Introduction', '<p>Many people believe that when Christians die, they immediately go to heaven to be with Jesus, and they take great comfort in that. This seminar is not designed to cause people discomfort, but rather to provide great freedom in knowing what truly happens to people when they die. To find this freedom and to understand the true nature of death, we must look to Scripture, not to religious traditions or worldly cultures.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:16-22; Gen. 2:15-17; 3:4; 7:21; Eccles. 9:4-6; Rom. 5:12; Luke 4:41; Deut. 18:9-12.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '56:19', 19, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-1-Introduction.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-1-introduction', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 67, null),
(1290, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 2 | What Happens to the Body, the Soul, and the Spirit when a Person Dies?', '<p>To accurately understand death, we must look to God&rsquo;s Word and not human traditions. God designed the body, soul, and spirit to live together, not apart from each other. Soul is the life force of the body and all its cells. God gives us a portion of His spirit when we are born again. So, when a person dies, their soul ceases to exist and their spirit &ldquo;returns&rdquo; to God.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:20, 24, 30; 2:7; 9:10; Lev. 24:18; Acts 2:18; Eccles. 12:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '32:44', 19, 2, 'life, ghost', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-2-What-Happens-to-the-Body-the-Soul-and-the-Spirit-when-a-Person-Dies-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-2-what-happens-to-the-body-the-soul-and-the-spirit-when-a-person-dies', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 50, null),
(1291, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 3 | The Dead are in the Grave, Not in Heaven or &ldquo;Hell&rdquo;', '<p>In this session, we learn from the Bible that the dead are dead, &ldquo;sleeping&rdquo; in the ground and turned back to dust. They are not alive in Heaven, Hell, or Paradise, as is commonly taught. God never comforts anyone by telling them they will immediately go to heaven when they die. The Bible clearly states that Jesus is the only person who has died and ascended into Heaven after His death.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 31:16; 3:25-27; Ps. 6:5; 13:3; 16:10; 30:2, 8-9; 49:12, 14-15; 89:48; 115:17; Job 7:21; 14:10-13; 17:13-16; Eccles. 9:4-6, 10; Isa. 26:19; 38:9-12, 18-19; Matt. 16:18; Dan. 12:1-2, 13; Hosea 13:14; John 3:1, 13, 16; Acts 2:29-32.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '59:36', 19, 3, 'sheol', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-3-The-Dead-are-in-the-Grave-not-in-Heaven-or-Hell-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-3-the-dead-are-in-the-grave-not-in-heaven-or-hell', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 50, null),
(1292, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 4 | The Dead Will Get Up at the Rapture, or One of the Resurrections', '<p>This session illustrates that people in the Bible, such as Job, did not look to go to Heaven immediately upon death, but rather they looked to the resurrection where they would receive life again in a spiritual body. It also discusses the difference between the phrases &ldquo;raised from the dead,&rdquo; and &ldquo;raised out from among the dead,&rdquo; as well as the type of resurrected body Jesus had and that we Christians will have.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 19:11; 20:3-7, 11-15; Job 19:25-27; Phil. 3:20-21; Luke 14:12-14; 24:36-39; 1 Cor. 15:35-44, 51-55; Isa. 26:19; Ezek. 37:1-14; Ps. 37:9-11, 22; Dan. 12:12; Matt. 13:19; 17:9; 22:23-30; John 11:21-24; 14:1-3; Acts 3:15; 4:1-2; 1 Thess. 4:13-18; Col. 2:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:12:10', 19, 4, 'imperishable', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-4-The-Dead-will-get-up-at-the-Rapture-or-one-of-the-Resurrections.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-4-the-dead-will-get-up-at-the-rapture-or-one-of-the-resurrections', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 78, null),
(1293, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 5 | The Judgment Follows the Resurrection', '<p>The Bible clearly states that when people die, they are in the grave and are not immediately judged to go to Heaven or Hell. Rather, they will be judged at one of the four future judgments after they are raised from the dead. Those who have rejected God will be totally consumed in the Lake of Fire. We as Christians will be raptured, then judged and rewarded for how we have served God here on earth.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 2:19; 4:16-18; 2 Cor. 5:10; Matt. 3:7-8, 11-12; 10:15; 12:41-42; 13:47-50; 16:27; 25:31-46; Rev. 20:4-6, 11-14; Ps. 1:5; Eccles. 12:14; John 5:22, 28-29; 12:48; Acts 17:31; 2 Tim. 4:1; 1 Pet. 1:7, 13; 2 Pet. 3:7; 1 John 3:2; Jude 6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '47:05', 19, 5, 'wrath, punishment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-5-The-Judgment-Follows-the-Resurrection.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-5-the-judgment-follows-the-resurrection', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1294, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 6 | An Examination of Scriptures Commonly Used to Show the Dead are Alive', '<p>Several scriptures seem to be unclear concerning the death of men such as Elijah, and have been misconstrued to indicate that the dead are alive in heaven or hell. However, none of these scriptures actually say that. We need to consider the greater context of Scripture, as well as Hebrew grammar, to properly understand that those who have died are in the grave awaiting one of the resurrections.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 5:18-24; Heb. 11:4, 5, 7-8, 11, 13; John 3:13; Jude 14-15; 1 Sam. 28:3-20; Deut. 18:9-15; 2 Kings 2:11, 15-17; Matt. 10:16-17, 24-28; 17:1-3, 9; Acts 4:32; 1 Pet. 2:11; Luke 9:30-31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '1:00:13', 19, 6, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-6-An-Examination-of-Scriptures-Commonly-Used-to-Show-the-Dead-are-Alive.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-6-an-examination-of-scriptures-commonly-used-to-show-the-dead-are-alive', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1295, 4, 'Death and Resurrection to Life | Session 7 | How Christians Have Come to Believe that the Soul Lived on after Death', '<p>Scripture verses taken out of context over the years have led to doctrinal errors which conclude that the soul lives on after death. As we read these various verses, it is important for us to consider both the immediate and the greater context. Doing so will help us accurately understand what is written concerning death and resurrection.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 16:1, 19-31; 23:42-43; Joshua 23:14; 2 Cor. 5:1-10; Phil. 1:12-15, 18-24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2000-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '51:00', 19, 7, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-7-How-the-Pharisees-came-to-Believe-that-the-Soul-Lived-on-after-Death.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24984/episodes/session-7-how-the-pharisees-came-to-believe-that-the-soul-lived-on-after-death', '/i/seminars/DRTL.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(1296, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 1 | Introduction, Why Study the Old Testament?, Overview of the Old Testament', '<p>This introductory session of the seminar covers two foundational topics. It explains the reasons why we should study the Old Testament, and it presents a detailed overview of the Old Testament. Beginning with Genesis 1:1 and ending with Malachi, the final book of the Old Testament, the overview highlights turning points in humankind&rsquo;s relationship with God, how the kingdom of Israel came to be, and the condition of Israel at the close of the Old Testament.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 15:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '42:26', 17, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-1-Introduction-Why-Study-the-Old-Testament-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-1-introduction-why-study-the-old-testament-overview-of-the-old-testament', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 334, null),
(1297, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 2 | Suggested Order for Reading the Old Testament', '<p>Session 2 provides a suggested reading order of the Old Testament, which follows the historical chronology. It explains that the devil was hidden to people in Old Testament times and details the &ldquo;idiom of permission,&rdquo; which is key to understanding how God related to His people. Finally, there is a close look at the account of the creation, through the point of the creation of animals.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '41:57', 17, 2, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-2-Suggested-Order-of-Reading-the-Old-Testament.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-2-suggested-order-of-reading-the-old-testament-genesis-11-25', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 206, null),
(1298, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 3 | Man Enters the Picture (Woman too)', '<p>Session 3 discusses the gap in time between Genesis 1:1 and 1:2, and the creation of Adam and Eve. It describes what Adam and Eve&rsquo;s original relationship was to the rest of creation, to each other, and to their Creator. The session also brings to light details of the serpent&rsquo;s temptation of Eve, and the results of Adam&rsquo;s sin.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Pet. 3:1-7; Isa. 45:18; Gen. 1:26-31; 2:5-25; 3:1-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:04', 17, 3, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-3-Man-Enters-the-Picture-Woman-too-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-3-man-enters-the-picture-woman-too', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 62, null),
(1299, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 4 | Jesus Christ – The Coming King', '<p>Session 4 covers Adam and Eve being driven from Eden, God&rsquo;s initiation of the blood sacrifice, and the promise of a Redeemer who would purchase back what was lost. It also demonstrates how God has, at times, taken on human form to communicate with humans, to reveal wonderful details about the promised future and His plan of redemption.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:16-24; 18:1-16; Daniel 7:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:54', 17, 4, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-4-Jesus-Christ-The-Coming-King.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-4-jesus-christ-the-coming-king', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 64, null),
(1300, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 5 | Noah and the Flood', '<p>Session 5 follows the events in Genesis from the record of Cain and Able through Noah and the Flood. It discusses why Cain&rsquo;s sacrifice was not accepted, and that he would have known it. The reason for the Flood is explained, along with a description of the ark, a discussion of its contents and occupants, and the duration of Noah&rsquo;s living in the ark.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 4:1-25; 5:1-3; 6:1-22; 7:1-24; 8:13-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:55', 17, 5, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-5-Noah-and-the-Flood.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-5-noah-and-the-flood', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 52, null),
(1301, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 6 | After the Flood, How to Use the Oxford Bible Atlas', '<p>Session 6 covers God&rsquo;s instructions to Noah as he exits the ark to a changed world. Noah&rsquo;s son Shem is designated as the one through whom the Redeemer would come. People multiply on the face of the earth, rebel against God, and build the Tower of Babel. Abraham&rsquo;s ancestry is traced back through Shem. The session ends by demonstrating how helpful the Oxford Bible Atlas is when studying the Bible.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 8:13-22; 9:1-20; 11:1-9, 24-32</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '21:57', 17, 6, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-6-After-the-Flood-How-to-Use-the-Oxford-Bible-Atlas.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-6-after-the-flood-how-to-use-the-oxford-bible-atlas', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 72, null),
(1302, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 7 | Abraham, the Father of All Them that Believe', '<p>Session 7 follows the life of Abram (later renamed Abraham) travelling from Ur to the land that God promised to give to him and his descendants. The geography of the land is described as Abram moves through it, travels to Egypt and back, gives a portion to his nephew Lot, and meets the priest Melchizedek. The session concludes with an explanation of the blood covenant and God&rsquo;s unbreakable promise to Abram.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 11:27-32; 12:1-20; 13:1-18; 14:8-20; 15:1-19; Heb. 7:1-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '42:01', 17, 7, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-7-Abraham-the-Father-of-all-them-that-Believe.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-7-abraham-the-father-of-all-them-that-believe', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 51, null),
(1303, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 8 | Isaac, A Type of the Coming Redeemer', '<p>Session 8 continues to follow Abraham&rsquo;s life. His son Ishmael is born to the slave girl Hagar; the covenant of circumcision is instituted; and Sodom and Gomorrah are destroyed. Abraham&rsquo;s wife Sarah gives birth to Isaac, the son God had promised. The session reveals how Isaac is a type, or foreshadowing, of the coming Redeemer.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 16:1-16; 17:1-27; 18:16-33; 19:1-38; 21:1-7; 22:1-19; Heb. 11:17-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:25', 17, 8, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-8-Isaac-A-Type-of-the-Coming-Redeemer.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-8-isaac-a-type-of-the-coming-redeemer', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 73, null),
(1304, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 9 | Jacob and Esau', '<p>In Session 9, God continues to work as Abraham finds a suitable wife for Isaac. Isaac&rsquo;s wife Rebekah gives birth to twins, Jacob and Esau. The birthright is explained, and that Jacob stole it from Esau. Jacob then flees from Esau to Padam-aram. On the way there, God confirms to Jacob that the promised redeemer will come through his descendants.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 23:1-5; 24:1-4; 25:1-11, 21-34; 27:1-46; 28:10-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:47', 17, 9, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-9-Jacob-and-Esau.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-9-jacob-and-esau', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1305, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 10 | The Origin of the Twelve Tribes of Israel; Judah–The Christ Line', '<p>In Session 10, Jacob has 12 sons and is renamed &ldquo;Israel.&rdquo; He identifies his son Judah as the one through whom the promised seed will come. Israel&rsquo;s son Joseph is sold into slavery in Egypt, where he rises to great power and saves his father&rsquo;s family from famine. Israel and all his descendants move to Egypt, where they eventually become enslaved to the Egyptians.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 29:1-35; 30:1-11; 32:28; 35:8,16-20, 27-29; 49:1-33; 50:22-26; Ex. 1:1-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:51', 17, 10, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-10.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-10-the-origin-of-the-twelve-tribes-of-israel-judahthe-christ-line', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 72, null),
(1306, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 11 | Moses: A Humble Beginning', '<p>Session 11 opens with the birth of Moses to a mother and father who were great believers. The session elaborates on the details of Moses&rsquo; early life and how he came to the place where he met God in the desert of Sinai.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Ex. 2:1-25; 3:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:47', 17, 11, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-11.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-11-moses-a-humble-beginning', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 66, null),
(1307, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 12 | Moses: You Too Can Do God&rsquo;s Will', '<p>Session 12 details Moses&rsquo; return to Egypt to deliver the children of Israel from slavery. Over a period of months, ten plagues ensue. The children of Israel choke down the Passover meal and are protected from the tenth devastating plague. They plunder the Egyptians, leaving Egypt in order to worship and serve God.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Rom. 15:4; Ex. 3:12-22; 4:1-17; 11:1-10; 12:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:24', 17, 12, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Session-12.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-12-moses-you-too-can-do-gods-will', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 50, null),
(1308, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 13 | Egypt is History', '<p>Session 13 describes the children of Israel crossing the Red Sea, in which Pharoah and the Egyptian army drown. Egypt is destroyed politically, socially, militarily, agriculturally, economically, and religiously. Rules for an annual Passover commemoration are instituted. God continues to provide whatever the children of Israel need, and they continually forget what He has done for them.</p> <p>Verses: Ex. 12:29-36, 43-51; 14:1-31; 15:22-27; 16:1-13; John 6:22-35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:09', 17, 13, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-13.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-13-egypt-is-history', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 55, null),
(1309, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 14 | The Ten Commandments', '<p>Session 14 teaches of the Lord&rsquo;s covenant with Israel and His giving of the Ten Commandments at Mt. Sinai. The children of Israel were terrified by the fire, smoke, thunder, and lightning that accompanied Yahweh&rsquo;s voice and asked that the Lord speak directly to Moses only. Yahweh gave other commandments to Moses and promised that in the future, He would speak to Israel through a prophet, a promise which foreshadowed Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ex. 16:13-36; 17:1-7; 19:1-25; 20:1-2; 24:1-8; Deut. 4:10-14; 5:1-5, 22-27; 18:14-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:53', 17, 14, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-14.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-14-the-ten-commandments', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 47, null),
(1310, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 15 | Moses Intercedes for Israel', '<p>Session 15 describes Moses, Aaron, and 70 elders travelling up Mt. Sinai, seeing God, and hearing His voice. Moses made subsequent trips and received more detailed commandments. In Moses&rsquo; absence, the children of Israel turned their backs on God and enticed Aaron make a golden calf. Moses interceded in prayer and saved Israel from destruction. The Levites and Moses executed the instigators of the idolatry.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 12:18-29; Ex.24:8-18; 32:1-5, 7-35; 34:1-4, 28-35; 1 John 5:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:11', 17, 15, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-15.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-15-moses-intercedes-for-israel', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 45, null),
(1311, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 16 | Back to Bondage, or Into the Promised Land?', '<p>Session 16 begins with Moses coming down from Mt. Sinai for the seventh time and guiding the construction of the Tabernacle. He organized an army and assigned the Levites&rsquo; duties. He sent men to spy out the Promised Land, and their weak report resulted in decades more of wandering in the desert. The session concludes with Moses&rsquo; commissioning of Joshua to assume leadership of Israel, in anticipation of Moses&rsquo; death.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 40:17; Num. 1:1-3; 3:5-9; 10:11; 13:1-3, 17-33; 14:1-38; 27:12-23; Deut. 1:1-2, 22-23; 1 Cor. 10:1-13</p> <p>Teacher<strong>:</strong> John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:38', 17, 16, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-16.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-16-back-to-bondage-or-into-the-promised-land', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 58, null),
(1312, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 17 | Joshua: Be Strong and Courageous', '<p>Session 17 demonstrates that it takes courage to follow God&rsquo;s will, but it is always possible. God instructed Joshua to keep all the commandments Moses had given as he led the children of Israel into the Promised Land. God worked for Joshua just as He had worked for Moses, and continually works for His people. Joshua learned the primary importance of teaching the next generation, and how to do so effectively.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Josh. 1:1-18; 2:1-24; 3:1-17; 4:19-24; Num. 32:1-40; Deut. 6:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:55', 17, 17, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-17.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-17-joshua-be-strong-and-courageous', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 37, null),
(1313, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 18 | Putting God First: Trust and Obey', '<p>God wants a loving relationship with His people; therefore, worship must come first, and after that, the work. This is clearly seen in Session 18, with the children of Israel stopping to worship after crossing the Jordan River. The Lord then instructed Joshua to attack Jericho in a unique way, and the city was taken. One man secretly stole some things devoted to the Lord, and disaster ensued.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 5:1-15; 6:1-27; 7:1-9; Gen. 34:1-26; 1 Kings 16:29-34</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:18', 17, 18, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-18.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-18-putting-god-first-trust-and-obey', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 72, null),
(1314, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 19 | Adventures of Joshua and Israel', '<p>Session 19 opens with Israel&rsquo;s defeat at Ai and the discovery of the sin of Achan. The problem was remedied, and Israel destroyed Ai. Joshua built an altar to Yahweh and read all the words of the Law to the people. The inhabitants of Gibeah deceived Joshua, who permitted them to live, thus allowing pagan idolators to live within Israel&rsquo;s borders. Caleb received Hebron for his inheritance.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 7:10-26; 8:30-31; 9:1-27; 14:15-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:10', 17, 19, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-19.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-19-adventures-of-joshua-and-israel', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 52, null),
(1315, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 20 | Choose This Day Whom You Will Serve', '<p>Session 20 describes the division of the Promised Land between the 11 tribes, excluding Levites. Joshua reminded the Israelites of their rich spiritual heritage and all God had done for them. They vowed to serve the Lord and erected a witness stone. Following the death of Joshua and Eleazer the high priest, the children of Israel entered the period of the Judges.</p> <p>Verses: Josh. 19:49-51; 24:1-33; Judg. 2:10-19; 21:25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:34', 17, 20, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-20.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-20-choose-this-day-whom-you-will-serve', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1316, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 21 | Judges: The No-Excuse Book', '<p>Session 21 gives an overview of the Book of Judges, looking closely at Othniel, Ehud, and Deborah. The exciting Book of Judges clearly shows that no matter what the circumstances are, if someone is strong, courageous, and willing to obey God to get rid of sin, they can do great things with Him.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 1:1-3, 9-13, 19-36; 3:12-30; 4:1-24; 5:20, 28-30; 2 Sam. 18:8; Josh. 22:24-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '42:51', 17, 21, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-21.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-21-judges-the-no-excuse-book', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 32, null),
(1317, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 22 | Gideon: Just Do What God Says', '<p>In Session 22, God&rsquo;s grace and mercy is once again demonstrated as He works in unexpected ways to deliver Israel from their oppressors. Despite being fearful and hesitant, Gideon had a wonderful heart, displaying incredible generosity to a visiting stranger who turns out to be an angel. Gideon learns to trust the Lord, defeating a formidable foe with an army of very few men and very unusual weapons.</p> <p>Verses<strong>:</strong> Judg. 6:1-40; 7:1-25; 8:22-35; 9:1-5; Gen. 4:25-26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '41:13', 17, 22, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-22.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-22-gideon-just-do-what-god-says', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 47, null),
(1318, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament  | Session 23 | Samson: A Man Alone', '<p>Session 23 briefly discusses Jephthah and the daughter he sacrificed to the Lord. Then it begins an in-depth look at Samson and his early life as a judge in Israel. Samson&rsquo;s birth was foretold to his parents by an angel of the Lord, who instructed them to raise him as a Nazirite. Samson shocked his parents with his request to marry a Philistine woman.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 13:1-24; 14:1-20; 15:1-5; Amos 4:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:37', 17, 23, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-23.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-23-samson-a-man-alone', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1319, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 24 | Samson: It&rsquo;s No Joke', '<p>Session 24 continues with Samson&rsquo;s exploits. His wonderful sense of humor becomes evident, but lack of support from God&rsquo;s people wears on him. Eventually his relationship with Delilah brings about his downfall.</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 15:6-20; 16:1-31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:02', 17, 24, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-24.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-24-samson-its-no-joke', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1320, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 25 | Samuel: Trained by God', '<p>Session 25 begins with comments on the Book of Ruth, which is rich in detail and easy to read and understand. The session then moves to an introduction to the great judge and prophet Samuel. His mother prayed for a child, and made and kept a promise to God, presenting her young son to the high priest Eli to be trained for a lifetime of service to the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 1:1-28; 1 Sam. 2:11-21, 27-36; 3:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:22', 17, 25, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-25.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-25-samuel-trained-by-god', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 48, null),
(1321, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 26 | The Power of God vs. Religion', '<p>In this session, we see how Samuel grew and served under the high priest Eli. But Eli was weak, his sons were corrupt, and the people were not taught how to obey God. Still, the Lord worked with Samuel, who became well-respected for his godliness. Although Samuel did teach Israel how to live by God&rsquo;s Law, they rejected God and requested a king to rule over them.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 3:8-21; 4:1-22; 5:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:50', 17, 26, 'Ark of the Covenant, Tabernacle', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-26.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-26-the-power-of-god-vs-religion', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(1322, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 27 | Whether by Many or by Few', '<p>In this session, we see Israel get their king when Samuel anoints Saul. Although he was impressive to look at, Saul&rsquo;s moral and spiritual stature did not match his physical height. He was hesitant before his enemies and arrogant before God. His son Jonathan was confident in God&rsquo;s ability to save and beat back the Philistines with a bold move.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 8:18; 9:1-27; 10:1-9, 17-26; 13:1-22; 14:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:07', 17, 27, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-27.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-27-whether-by-many-or-by-few', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 49, null),
(1323, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 28 | Saul, a Study in Human Nature', '<p>The effects of one&rsquo;s surroundings on their spiritual life are clearly demonstrated in Session 28. Saul continued to be full of pride and would not admit his mistakes. Samuel confronted Saul and told him that his kingdom would not continue. The Lord then sent Samuel to anoint David, who became Saul&rsquo;s harp player and armor bearer. When David slayed Goliath, Jonathan was heartened by David&rsquo;s audacious trust in God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 15:1-36; 16:1-23; 17:11, 47; 18:1-4; 1 Cor. 15:33-34</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:38', 17, 28, 'obedience, rebellion', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-28.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-28-saul-a-study-in-human-nature', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 29, null),
(1324, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 29 | Saul and David: A Difference in Heart', '<p>Session 29 vividly contrasts the heart of Saul with the heart of David. Saul went from bad to worse and did not repent from sin. David also made mistakes and sinned, but admitted his error, sought God&rsquo;s forgiveness, and did what he could to make amends. Many Israelites who were in distress joined David and looked to him for leadership.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 18:1-30; 19:1; 20:30-34; 21:1-5; 22:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:43', 17, 29, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-29.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-29-saul-and-david-a-difference-in-heart', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 33, null),
(1325, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 30 | The End of Saul', '<p>Session 30 explores how David strengthened himself to be successful in the many challenges he faced. In the midst of that, Saul continued on the road down and consulted a medium rather than God on the eve of battle. He and three of his sons died the following day. A two-year civil war erupted between David and Saul&rsquo;s remaining son, Ish-bosheth. When Ish-bosheth was murdered, David became the undisputed king of Israel.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:22-31; Heb. 12:2-3; 1 Sam. 28:1-19; 30:1-6; 31:1-13; 1 Chron. 10:13; 2 Sam. 2:1-4, 8-10; 3:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:10', 17, 30, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-30.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-30-the-end-of-saul', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(1326, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 31 | David: Coming to Grips with Sin', '<p>Session 31 studies the record of David expanding his kingdom and making Jerusalem his capital city. He is humbled and deeply moved when God reveals that the Messiah will come through him. Despite his strengths, David succumbed to weakness, committing adultery and murder. When confronted, David made no excuses but admitted his sin. He received God&rsquo;s forgiveness, but Nathan the prophet told David there would be consequences to his household.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 5:1-7; 7:1-29; 10:1-7; 11:1-27; 12:1-14; Exod. 22:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:35', 17, 31, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-31.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-31-david-coming-to-grips-with-sin', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1327, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 32 | David: The Faithfulness of God', '<p>Although David sinned, he always repented and then got on with living for God. In disobedience to the Law, he numbered the fighting men of Israel, and 70,000 people died as a result. David repented and offered a sacrifice, which was accepted with fire from heaven. Following God&rsquo;s instructions, he began acquiring materials for the Temple and writing down detailed plans for his successor, Solomon, to follow.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 12:15-25; Ps. 51:1-19; 1 Chron. 21:1-30; 22:5; 23:1, 24-32; 28:11-19; 29:14-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:55', 17, 32, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-32.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-32-david-the-faithfulness-of-god', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 32, null),
(1328, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 33 | Solomon: A Sad Story', '<p>Session 33 describes a promising start for Solomon as he ruled with the wisdom God had blessed him with. He built the Temple and dedicated it with a magnificent festival. The glory of the Lord filled the house. But subsequently, Solomon ignored Scripture, leaning instead on his personal strengths. He married foreign wives who turned his heart from Yahweh, even to the end that he built altars to pagan gods on the mountain overlooking Jerusalem.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 2:10-12, 46; 3:1-28; 4:1, 7, 20-34; 5:13-18; 6:1, 7, 37-38; 2 Chron. 5:1-14; 7:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:03', 17, 33, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-33.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-33-solomon-a-sad-story', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1329, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 34 | Solomon: Turning His Back on God', '<p>Session 34 details specific instructions from the Law of Moses that Solomon ignored. Solomon spent 7 years building the Temple, then 13 years building his own palace. While accumulating huge wealth for himself, he heavily taxed the people, forced them to provide unpaid labor, and gave away part of the Promised Land. Finally, he built temples to pagan gods on the mountain overlooking Jerusalem and the Temple of Yahweh.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 7:1, 7-8; 9:1-15; 10:1-29; 11:1-13, 41, 43; 2 Chron. 9:12; Deut. 17:16-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:16', 17, 34, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-34.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-34-solomon-turning-his-back-on-god', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1330, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 35 | The Split of the Kingdom', '<p>Session 35 describes the Lord&rsquo;s telling Solomon He would rip the kingdom from him. After Solomon&rsquo;s death, Jeroboam established his own kingdom in the 10 northern tribes, referred to in scripture as Israel. He established his own dynasty, calendar, and pagan religion. Jeroboam&rsquo;s sin becomes a byword in Israel. The Levites left the northern kingdom and joined with Jerusalem in Judah, the southern kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 11:26-40; 12:1-33; 13:1-6; 14:1-20; 22:51-53; Judg. 18:29-30; 2 Chron. 11:13-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '41:15', 17, 35, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-35.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-35-the-split-of-the-kingdom', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 35, null),
(1331, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 36 | The Highlights of the Kings Period, Chronology of the Kings of Judah and Israel', '<p>Session 36 spotlights the overlapping records in Kings and Chronicles, showing the importance of reading multiple records to get a complete view of each king&rsquo;s reign. With this type of study, the attitudes and beliefs common to that part of the ancient world become more apparent to modern western readers.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 13:2; 14:19-20; 20:23; Eccles. 12:11-12; 2 Kings 5:1-19; 21:1-18; 22:8-20; 23:1-28; 2 Chron. 33:1-20; 34:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '41:22', 17, 36, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-36.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-36-the-highlights-of-the-kings-period-chronology-of-the-kings-of-judah-and-israel', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1332, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 37 | Jonah: A Type of Christ', '<p>The Book of Jonah, although short, contains many important lessons. Session 37 showcases the use of research materials to pinpoint when Jonah lived, the extent of his travels, and why he ran away from God. The record of Jonah also illustrates the difference between obedience from a pure heart and ineffective religious rituals.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 14:23-25; Jonah 1:1-17; 1 Kings 14:14-16; Matt. 12:38-41; Luke 11:29-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:33', 17, 37, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-37.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-37-jonah-a-type-of-christ', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1333, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 38 | Jonah Gets the Job Done', '<p>Continuing with the study of Jonah, Session 38 demonstrates the fulfillment of Ahijah&rsquo;s 200-year-old prophecy, how that led to the origins of the Samaritans, and why they were detested by the Jews. Jonah beautifully expresses the hope of Old Testament believers as he realizes he is about to die. He then learns not to fight against God but to obey.</p> <p>Verses: Jonah 2:1-10; 3:1-10; 4:1-11; 2 Kings 17:1-7, 21-34; John 4:9</p> <p>John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:28', 17, 38, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-38.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-38-jonah-gets-the-job-done', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1334, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 39 | Profiting from the Prophets', '<p>Session 39 transitions from the historical records to the prophetic books of the Old Testament. Although not appearing chronologically in the Bible, these books add much information referencing kings, historical events, and other prophets. They also contain many prophecies of future events, revealing that some prophecies have multiple fulfillments, and many prophecies have yet to be fulfilled.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 1:1; 7:1-17; Hosea 1:1; 11:1-5; Amos 1:1; Mic. 1:1; 2 Kings 16:1-9; 23:31-37; 24:1; Matt. 1:22; 2:14-15; Jer. 25:1, 11-13; Dan. 1:1-2</p> <p>John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:39', 17, 39, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-39.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-39-profiting-from-the-prophets', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1335, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 40 | Some Prophets and Some Kings', '<p>Session 40 examines the vivid imagery employed by God to warn His people of the coming destruction of Jerusalem, and the death or captivity of its inhabitants. A series of kings, their councilors, and most of the people refuse to believe and repent. The result that follows is wave after wave of conquest, with talented and capable people being carried off to Babylon, until eventually only the poorest in the land remain.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:11-12; Jer. 22:18-19; 36:1-32; 39:11-18; 2 Kings 24:1-20; 25:1-10, 27-30; Ezek. 4:1-17; 5:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '27:57', 17, 40, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-40.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-40-some-prophets-and-some-kings', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1336, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 41 | Daniel: From Captivity to Command', '<p>Session 41 begins with the account of Nebuchadnezzar carrying some of the children of Jerusalem&rsquo;s nobility away to Babylon so he can train them to serve in his court. Among them is Daniel, who is determined not to eat food offered to idols. He persists in asking for a simple alternative for himself and his companions. Over time, they earn recognition as standouts in the king&rsquo;s court.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 1:1-27; 2:1-49</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '30:07', 17, 41, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-41.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-41-daniel-from-captivity-to-command', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1337, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 42 | The God We Serve is Able to Save Us', '<p>When Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego refused to worship the golden image created by Nebuchadnezzar, officials reported them to the king. The penalty was death. But they were miraculously rescued, which brought glory to God, and they continued to serve the king alongside Daniel. King Nebuchadnezzar later became insane and lost his kingdom, but regained both when he humbled himself before God, giving honor and praise to the King of heaven.</p> <p>Verses: Matt.2:1-12; Dan. 3:1-30; 4:1-37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '25:59', 17, 42, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-42.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-42-the-god-we-serve-is-able-to-save-us', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1338, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 43 | Daniel: A Faithful Man', '<p>When King Belshazzar, son of Nebuchadnezzar, hosted a drunken party, a hand appeared writing a message on the wall. Daniel, by this time old and nearly forgotten, was summoned to interpret the writing. He did so, and was promoted to third rank in the kingdom, where he remained when the kingdom was conquered by Cyrus of Persia. Cyrus had been prophesied about in detail and by name 200 years prior.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 5:1-31; Isa. 44:24-28; 45:1-6, 13-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:16', 17, 43, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-43.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-43-daniel-a-faithful-man', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1339, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 44 | Because He Trusted His God', '<p>As the top ranking official in Babylon when Cyrus entered the city, Daniel would have told him of the prophecy in scripture concerning his reign. Cyrus decreed that the Jews be allowed to return to Jerusalem and provided for the rebuilding of the Temple. After its completion, Ezra arrived, followed by Nehemiah, who led the rebuilding of the wall of the city. Daniel remained in Babylon serving Cyrus.</p> <p>Verses: Ezra 1:1-8; 6:15; 7:1-10; Neh. 1:1-11; 2:1-5; Dan. 6:1-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:28', 17, 44, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-44.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-44-because-he-trusted-his-god', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 37, null),
(1340, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 45 | Esther: A True Woman of God', '<p>The beloved Book of Esther is the record of an orphaned girl among the Jewish captives in the Persian capital Susa who became the emperor&rsquo;s queen. Esther, who had been raised by her cousin Mordecai, was beautiful, intelligent, and wise. Esther and Mordecai together faced the king&rsquo;s decree, which was prompted by Haman, to destroy all the Jews in the kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Esther 1:1-22; 2:1-23; 3:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:12', 17, 45, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-45.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-45-esther-a-true-woman-of-god', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1341, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 46 | The Christ Line Preserved', '<p>Continuing in the Book of Esther, Haman, second in command of the kingdom, persuaded the king to decree that all Jews should be destroyed, which would have eliminated the Christline. But Esther&rsquo;s cousin, Mordecai, convinced her to petition the king, risking her life on behalf of her people. Because of her brave and wise action, the Jews were spared from destruction. The Christline was preserved.</p> <p>Verses: Esther 3:3-15; 4:1-17; 5:1-14; 6:1-14; 7:1-10; 8:1-17; 9:1-32; 10:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:36', 17, 46, 'feasts, Purim', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-46.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-46-the-christ-line-preserved', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1342, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 47 | Malachi: The Last Prophecy of the Promised Christ', '<p>Session 47 opens with a brief explanation of the Christian group responsible for the production of this seminar, and why it is vitally important for everyone to engage in personal study and application of Scripture. Then, there is a look at the last prophet in the Old Testament. Malachi answered questions that were being asked about God and assured his audience that the promised Messiah would indeed come.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 10:1-4; Mal. 1:1-14; 2:1-17; 3:1-17; 4:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '29:09', 17, 47, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-47.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-47-malachi-the-last-prophecy-of-christ', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1343, 4, 'A Journey Through the Old Testament | Session 48 | The Kingdom of God: Paradise Regained, The Future Kingdom, Conclusion', '<p>Jesus Christ is the redeemer promised to Eve in the Book of Genesis, who would buy back all that was lost in the Garden of Eden. This final session recaps how the promised Messiah was spoken of throughout the Old Testament, and also provides a glimpse of the details of the future kingdom spoken of in the scriptures, over which Christ will reign.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:7-8; 3:23-24; 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '28:28', 17, 48, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/session-48.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26191/episodes/session-48-the-kingdom-of-god-paradise-regained-the-future-kingdom-conclusion', '/i/seminars/JTOT.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(1344, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 1 | Overview of Millennial Positions, Overview of Rapture Positions, Reasons to Believe in a Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>This is the introductory session to the seminar, The Book of Revelation. It covers an overview of millennial positions, rapture positions, and reasons to believe in a pre-tribulation rapture. It also presents differences between the Church of the Body of Christ and Israel regarding the Millennial Kingdom.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:36', 21, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/01-Session-1.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-one-overview-of-millennial-positions-overview-of-rapture-positions-reasons-to-believe-in-a-pre-tribulation-rapture', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 276, null),
(1345, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 2 | More Reasons to Believe in a Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>Continuing from Session 1, this session gives more clarification to the differences between Israel and the Church of the Body. Topics discussed include salvation, holy spirit, sacrifices, the wrath, and tribulation. Israel is encouraged to look for signs during the tribulation for encouragement while in Paul&rsquo;s epistles the Church is instructed to wait for the appearing of the Lord Jesus Christ. The session also details the &ldquo;when,&rdquo; &ldquo;where&rdquo; and &ldquo;purpose&rdquo; of the Rapture.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 1:10; 4:16-17; 5:9; Rom. 5:9; Rev. 1:7; 12:6, 14; 13:7, 9-10; 14:13; Matt. 24:3-4, 9, 13, 15, 19-22, 29-31, 34, 36-42; 25:31-42, 46; 1 Cor. 1:7; Titus 2:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:53', 21, 2, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/02-Session-2.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-2-more-reasons-to-believe-in-a-pre-tribulation-rapture', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 160, null),
(1346, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 3 | Chronological Overview, The Old Testament Character of the Book of Revelation', '<p>Session 3 of this seminar demonstrates how the Book of Revelation is a fulfillment of the prophecies and promises made to Israel in the Old Testament. It presents a rationale as to why the book should not be viewed as a &ldquo;figure of speech,&rdquo; which demeans its literal meaning, but rather as the fulfillment of prophecy to Israel.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 1:1-5; 2:1, 4-5, 8-9, 12, 14, 18, 26-27; 3:1, 7, 14, 20-22; Hag. 2:6-7; Rom. 16:20; Matt. 10:21-23; 16:27-28; 24:22, 30, 34; Acts 7:37-38; 19:24-27, 32, 39, 41; 1 Cor. 8:4-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:43', 21, 3, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/03-Session-3.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-three-chronological-overview-the-old-testament-character-of-the-book-of-revelation-revelation-13-4-revelation-2181218-31714', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 271, null),
(1347, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 4 | More Evidence that Revelation is Specifically Referring to Israel in the Future, Explanation of &ldquo;The Lord&rsquo;s Day&rdquo;', '<p>This session further examines the parallels between the Old Testament and the Book of Revelation. It compares and contrasts the letters to the Churches in the Age of Grace to the Book of Revelation, emphasizing the need for people living in each biblical timeframe to have words that are specific and relevant to the age in which they live. The session closes with an explanation of the Lord&rsquo;s Day.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 1:4-20; 2:1-11; 3:5, 14; 4:1-11; 5:1-5; Matt. 24:4-5, 9-16; 2 Cor. 5:10; 12:1-4; Col. 3:23-25; Dan. 7:9-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:24', 21, 4, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/04-Session-4.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-4-more-evidence-that-revelation-is-specifically-referring-to-israel-in-the-future-explanation-of-the-lords-day', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 165, null),
(1348, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 5 | Literal or Figurative?', '<p>This session compares end times prophecies in the books of Revelation and Matthew. It explores reasons to accept the Book of Revelation literally and not figuratively. Further, it discusses the scriptural reasons for the location of the future, eternal home of all believers.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 5:6-14; 6:1-17; 7:1-9; 14:1; Gen. 8:20-21; Matt. 24:3-9, 24; Deut. 13:1-5; 18:21-22; Prov. 3:1-5; 25:2; Jer. 1:1-3; 21:1; 25:1; 27:1; 35:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:29', 21, 5, 'seals', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/05-Session-5.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-5-revelation-56-14-matthew-243-9-revelation-61-17-revelation-71-8', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 194, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1349, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 6 | Tribulation in the Book of Revelation', '<p>This session expounds on the Seal, Trumpet, Thunder, and Bowl Judgements during the period of the Tribulation and examines the devastation that will occur on the earth and its population. The listener is encouraged to accept the literal truth of the details and not be swayed by placing human understanding or speculative interpretations on the book.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 24:22; 25:31-33; Rev. 7:9-17; 8:1-13; 9:1-21; 10:1-4; Isa. 13:9, 12; 24:1-3, 5-6; 49:8, 10; Gen. 4:11-12; Lev. 18:8-9, 21-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:26', 21, 6, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/06-Session-6.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-6-revelation-79-17-revelation-81-13-revelation-91-21-revelation-101-4', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 62, null),
(1350, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 7 | Tribulation in the Book of Revelation (continued)', '<p>This session takes a close look at the seven years preceding the Day of the Lord and explains how this seven-year period was determined by looking at the prophecies in the books of Daniel, Matthew, and Revelation. It also explains the timetable for the division of the seven-year period into two segments of 3&frac12; year periods and clarifies who are the 144,000 preaching the gospel of the kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 10:5-11; 11:1-14; 12:4-6, 14; 13:5; Mark 4:10-12, 34; Matt. 13:10-15; 24:4-21; Dan. 7:23-25; 9:25-27; 1 John 2:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:03', 21, 7, 'beast', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/07-Session-7.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-7-revelation-105-11-revelation-111-2-revelation-124-6-14-135-revelation-113-14', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 49, null),
(1351, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 8 | Tribulation in the Book of Revelation (continued)', '<p>This session covers the pouring out of the bowls of God&rsquo;s wrath. Lucifer loses his position in the air and his anger is kindled knowing that his time is short. Believers are being killed off while remnants of Israel are protected. The antichrist is empowered against believers. The session explores the sign of the Woman in the heavens.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 5:6; 11:15-19; 12:1-17; 13:1-18; 14:1-13; 15:1-8; 16:1-11; 17:7-11, 15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:58', 21, 8, '666, dragon, beast', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/08-Session-8.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-8-revelation-1115-19-revelation-121-17-revelation-131-18-revelation-141-14-revelation-151-8-revelation-161-11', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 209, null),
(1352, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 9 | Tribulation in the Book of Revelation (continued)', '<p>This session explores the Babylonian religion&rsquo;s spread in its various forms all over the face of the earth as the earth&rsquo;s inhabitants adulterate themselves against God. Discussion begins on the one world government and one world religion. Details of the Battle of Armageddon and who comprises the armies of the Lord are introduced in this session.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 16:17-21; 17:1-18; 18:1-24; 19:1-16; Zech. 5:5-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '44:32', 21, 9, 'beast', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/09-Session-9.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-9-revelation-1617-21-revelation-171-18-revelation-181-24-revelation-191-10-revelation-1911-14', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 140, null),
(1353, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 10 | The Battle of Armageddon', '<p>This session describes the Lord Jesus descending from heaven with His armies, and the period of the Tribulation comes to an end. The kings of the earth gather to fight against the Lord and the historic boundaries of the battle are drawn. In the aftermath of the battle, the Sheep and Goat Judgement begins. Then the Lord begins establishing the Millennial Kingdom to fulfill the promises of God.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 14:14-20; 16:12-16; 19:17-21; 20:1; Isa. 63:1-6; Ezek. 39:1-21; Matt. 24:30-31, 25:31-34; Dan. 12:11-12; Zech. 12:7; 14:1, 6-8, 12-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:24', 21, 10, 'winepress, inheritance, abyss', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/10-Session-10.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-10-revelation-1915-21-revelation-201-6', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 69, null),
(1354, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 11 | Characteristics of the Millennial Kingdom', '<p>This session of the seminar looks at the future Kingdom of Christ on the earth. It clarifies who will live in the Millennial Kingdom and how it will fulfill the promises God made to Israel, Moses, Abraham, and others.</p> <p>Verses: Zech. 14:14-18; Isa. 49:22-23; 60:1, 5-7, 10-12; 61:4-6; 65:17-25; Eze. 43:4,13; 44:10-16; 47:1-5, 8-11, 13-14; 48:1-8, 25-27; Rev. 20:7-10; Josh. 15:5, 8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '43:16', 21, 11, 'sacrifice, Gehenna', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/11-Session-11.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-11-zechariah-1414-21-ezekiel-4042-isaiah-6517-25-ezekiel-434513ff-4410-16-ezekiel-45-48-ezekiel-471314-481-27-471-12-characteristics-of-the-millennial-kingdom-revelation-207-10', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 164, null),
(1355, 4, 'The Book of Revelation | Session 12 | The Final Judgment and the Everlasting Kingdom', '<p>The Millennial Kingdom ends with the final judgement. Every person who has ever lived has chosen life or death and those who have not been judged by this time will be judged. The city God has prepared for His people, New Jerusalem, will come down from heaven. God and the Lord Jesus Christ will dwell there with people forever in the Everlasting Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 7:30-31; 19:1-7; Ezek. 28:13-19; Rev 20:10-15; 21:1-27; 22:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '1993-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '37:18', 21, 12, 'gehenna', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/12-Session-12.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/26202/episodes/session-12-revelation-2010-15', '/i/seminars/REV.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 59, null),
(1356, 5, 'In the Book of Revelation, God is not the Lamb, and the Lamb is not God', '<p>[This article was originally published by Bill Schlegel on his website, <a href="https://landandbible.blogspot.com/2020/01/in-book-of-revelation-god-is-not-lamb.html" target="_blank">Land and Bible</a>.]</p> <p>The Book of Revelation is &ldquo;the revelation of Jesus Christ, which <strong>God gave him</strong>&rdquo; (1:1). From the very first verse we are told that Jesus is not God. God is differentiated from Jesus. The God <strong>of</strong> Jesus Christ <strong>gave</strong> Jesus Christ this revelation...</p>', '2020-02-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, 'Trinity', null, 'https://www.biblicalunitarian.com/articles/in-the-book-of-revelation-god-is-not-the-lamb-and-the-lamb-is-not-god', 'https://i0.wp.com/www.biblicalunitarian.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/In-the-Book-of-Revelation-God-is-not-the-Lamb-and-the-Lamb-is-not-God.jpg', 1, 0, null, 9, 26, null),
(1363, 1, 'Keys to Walking by the Spirit', '<p>Eighteen keys to walking by the spirit are shared with the understanding that God and the Lord Jesus Christ can, and do, also work outside of these parameters. Walking by the spirit is enhanced by our commitment to do whatever God and the Lord Jesus Christ ask, and by our desire to help others. We are encouraged to find where God and Christ have placed us in the Body of Christ to fulfill our ministry.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:41; Luke 10:20; Josh. 1:5; 3:7; Jer. 2:8; Mark 8:22-25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-05-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:55', 0, 0, 'manifestation, attitude, commitment, demons, humility, mind, revelation, servant, sin, wisdom', 'jONFLFgDuZU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jONFLFgDuZU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1364, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/03/2020) - Prayer: Ask, Thanks, and Praise', '<p>In this teaching Michelle Ruth shares on &ldquo;Prayer: Ask, Thanks, and Praise.&rdquo;</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:50', 0, 0, null, 'ekHnLkdoB2I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ekHnLkdoB2I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'upper case P in title Praise - JC', 1, 0, null),
(1365, 1, 'Speaking in Tongues and Common Questions that Come Up', '<p>Speaking in tongues is a manifestation of the gift of holy spirit. God&rsquo;s will for us regarding this manifestation is shown from Scripture. The benefits and purposes as well as fears and misconceptions of speaking in tongues are explained. The relationship between holy spirit and the mind is addressed.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 14:1-20; Luke 11:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:39', 0, 0, 'manifestation prophecy prayer worship', 'JBsv27vASiw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JBsv27vASiw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1366, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Let Focusing On Regrets Steal Your Joy', '<p>God wants us to have a good life. Today, as in the old covenant times, He places before us the choice of life and death and of good and evil. Jesus Christ paid the ultimate price for us to live life with great joy and without regret. This day, in your heart, what will you choose?</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:11-20; Rom. 10:5-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:19', 0, 0, 'blessing, commandments, difficulty, law, lord, love, Moses, obey, perish, righteousness, salvation', 'GRJWZg1Viy0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GRJWZg1Viy0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 57, null),
(1368, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/10/2020) - Revelation: Part 7', '<p>*DISCLAIMER: This teaching is not necessarily in alignment with other teachings regarding Revelation created by STF.</p>', '2020-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:32', 0, 0, null, 'WFX1klyXKV4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WFX1klyXKV4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Due to the disclaimer, should this be active?', 1, 0, null),
(1369, 1, 'Receiving Revelation from God', '<p>The teacher discusses the sources of revelation and cites examples of its operation through Old and New Testament records. In order to be a successful servant of the Lord, the Christian must know the ways in which God communicates with them. We are encouraged to &ldquo;get in the game&rdquo;. To do so we must recognize the multiple ways in which God and the Lord Jesus Christ work with and in us.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:11-12; 1 Cor. 12:4-8; Dan. 5:1-6; 2 Kings 6:8-17; 1 Sam. 9:12-17; 1 Chron. 14:13-16; 2 Kings 4:38-41; 1 Kings 18:46; John 6:5-6; 1 Sam. 11:4-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p><small>(Apologies for the technical issues causing the video portion to black out in some places.)</small></p>', '2020-05-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:09:37', 0, 0, 'Balaam, baptism, Belshazzar, discerning, Elijah, Elisha, emotion, manifestation, knowledge, message, senses, servant, walk, wisdom', 'KhCRKKmUiiM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KhCRKKmUiiM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1370, 1, 'The Making of the Apostle Paul', '<p>Saul, during the initial years of the Christian Church, was wreaking havoc, including executions, upon the believers of Jesus Christ. One day as he traveled to Damascus to further persecute the Church, he encountered the Lord Jesus. This encounter changed his life forever. He then went about the world speaking boldly in the name of Jesus Christ and demonstrating how the Body of Christ should work together.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:1-2; 8:1-3; 22:20, 59, 60; 7:51-53; 22:3-5; 26:9-11; 9:3-6; Rom. 8:31-39; Acts 9:12-19; Gal. 1:13-24; Acts 9:20-31</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-05-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:15', 0, 0, 'Ananias, Barnabas, Gamaliel, Pharisee, Sadducees, Sanhedrin', 'OgER3PFBR8M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OgER3PFBR8M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1371, 1, 'God Is the Source of True Comfort', '<p>When people are hurting, they often look to worldly sources for comfort and consolation. God is the source of true comfort. Why does the God of mercies provide such comfort to us in our afflictions? The Bible tells us that God has an even greater purpose for our comfort that involves others as well as ourselves.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor 1:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:30', 0, 0, 'overflow, pain, suffering', 'OTShI2l3X7o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OTShI2l3X7o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1452, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 15 | The Problem with Inheritance', '<p>If managed correctly, an inheritance can be a great blessing during hard times, help purchase a home, or be the means by which one starts their own business. But that requires the recipient to be prepared to wisely manage it, which takes self-discipline and time to learn. An inheritance can be wasted is a person is not prepared to wisely handle it so that they can enjoy the blessings that it can provide.</p> <p>Illustration: John Forsyth, a successful Canadian businessman, and the wasted inheritance of his children.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 20:21</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-15', 'Castos', 0, '13:29', 9, 15, 'wealth, money, wasteful, investment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-15-The-Problem-with-Inheritance-20.21-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-15-the-problem-with-inheritance-prov-2021', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1453, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 14 | Fools Can Appear Wise', '<p>Looks can be deceiving, and a fool can pass himself off as being wise. But a wise person is not deemed as wise because of their stature, demeanor, or appearance but according to their manner of life by living in obedience to Yahweh. This manner of life is demonstrated distinctly in what a wise person says and does, but a fool will not display this wisdom in their life.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Donkey and the Lion&rsquo;s Skin&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 17:28</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-06', 'Castos', 0, '08:57', 9, 14, 'foolishness, deception', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-14-Fools-Can-Appear-Wise.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-14-fools-can-appear-wise-prov-1728', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1454, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 13 | Holding Back Words', '<p>Wisdom tells us that we should be careful in how many words we use and when we use them, and that in response to being provoked, less words is often better and can keep us from saying things we would later regret. Moreover, keeping a cool spirit is essential so that we can think clearly about what we should say before we say it rather than responding out of heated emotions.</p> <p>Illustration: The lives and conduct of Calvin Coolidge &amp; George Whitefield</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 17:27; Matt. 12:36-37</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '14:16', 9, 13, 'patience, restraint, self-control', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-13-Holding-Back-Words-17.27-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-13-holding-back-words-prov-1727', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1455, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 12 | The Strength of Patience', '<p>Being aggressive and making demands from someone is likely not going to have a desirable outcome. Whether it is a person in a position of authority, someone at our place of employment, or even someone within our own family, if we make a request or plead our case with patience and gentleness of speech, we will more likely succeed in being persuasive and having them genuinely consider what we have to say.</p> <p>Illustration: The famous Jewish Rabbi named Rabbi Akiva.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:15</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-04-27', 'Castos', 0, '14:08', 9, 12, 'time, rush, immediately', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-12-The-Strength-of-Patience-25.15-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep12', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 38, null),
(1456, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 11 | Empty Boasting', '<p>All broken promises produce disappointment on the part of the recipient who never received what they eagerly looked forward to. Sometimes the disappointment is small and other times great. With wisdom, we can learn to be discerning about the individual who is making the promise and what exactly is being promised, knowing that not everyone is honest and intends to keep their promises.</p> <p>Illustration: The Seattle Art Museum and the Ebsworth Collection.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:14</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-04-17', 'Castos', 0, '12:39', 9, 11, 'boasting, bragging, pride', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-11-Empty-Boasting.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep11', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(1457, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 10 | A Gift Makes Room', '<p>It can be challenging to connect and break through a person&rsquo;s defenses. But when used properly with an honorable motive, a thoughtful gift that is given at the right time and in the right way can open doors, remove obstacles, and place you in a more favorable light in the eyes of others. A purposeful gift shows that you care and want to someone to know that they matter, and that can make all the difference in the world.</p> <p>Illustration: The incredible success of Cutco salesman John Ruhlin</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:16</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-04-10', 'Castos', 0, '16:15', 9, 10, 'opportunity, generosity, giving', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-10-A-Gift-Makes-Room.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep10', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 58, null),
(1458, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 9 | Strength on a Day of Trouble', '<p>Showing ourselves to not be lax when there is trouble can take as many different forms as the trouble that we encounter in life. When the occasion arises, what we do in response to the trouble will reveal whether or not our strength is small and limited. If we trust in God, knowing that he is the one that gives us true strength, we will not fail to show ourselves strong when it is needed the most.</p> <p>Illustration: Assistant Coach Ekkapol &ldquo;Ake&rdquo; Chantawong and the crisis of his team when they were trapped in a cave</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 24:10</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-04-03', 'Castos', 0, '13:30', 9, 9, 'leadership, endurance, difficultly', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Words-of-Wisdom-Ep-9-Strength-on-a-Day-of-Trouble-24.10-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep9', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1459, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 8 | Understand Your Road', '<p>The wisdom of the prudent person is that he understands the road that he walks and knows the end to which it leads. We must not allow foolishness to deceive us or lead us to use deceit in our course of life. Wisdom will help us ensure that our road follows the course of life that leads to living with the fear of Yahweh and not to trouble</p> <p>Illustration: Dutch Social psychologist Diederik Stapel&rsquo;s falsifying his research</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 14:8</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-03-27', 'Castos', 0, '11:23', 9, 8, 'prudence, foresight', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-8-Understand-Your-Road-14.8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep8', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1460, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 7 | Fear Brings A Snare', '<p>Living in fear of people and trusting in human power will always fail, but trusting in the strength of Yahweh our God, who is a sure rock beneath our feet, will never fail. No matter the circumstances, we are better off looking to God for help and trusting in him than putting our trust in other people or acting out of fear for what they might do to us.</p> <p>Illustration: King Hezekiah and the Assyrian Siege</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 29:25; 2 Kgs 18:5-14; Isa 30:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-03-20', 'Castos', 0, '15:15', 9, 7, 'fear, trust, snare', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-7-Fear-Brings-A-Snare-29.25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep7', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 211, null),
(1461, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 6 | Training A Child', '<p>The habits a child forms when they are young usually follow them into adulthood. If parents will train their children in the way of the Lord, they will likely continue on that road when they grow up. But even if they go astray, the instruction and guidance they received as a youth can resurface and they may remember what they were taught and turn back to the Lord.</p> <p>Illustration: John Newton and the effect of his childhood upon his faith as an adult.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 22:6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-03-12', 'Castos', 0, '15:02', 9, 6, 'children, teaching, discipline, parenting', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-6-Training-A-Child-22.6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep6', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 67, null),
(1462, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 5 | Rule Your Spirit', '<p>It doesn&rsquo;t matter how well you can outdo others; you will not be able to live without wisdom. Wisdom teaches that true strength is about internal mastery and ruling well within your own self so that as you live in a world filled with temptations to get angry and lash out, you are able to demonstrate true strength that few people ever really achieve.</p> <p>Illustration: American tennis player John McEnroe and the fatal flaw of his temper.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 16:32</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-03-04', 'Castos', 0, '13:23', 9, 5, 'patience, spirit, anger, self-control', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-5-Rule-Your-Spirit-16.32-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(1463, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 4 | Guard Your Mouth', '<p>If we&rsquo;re not careful to use wisdom to guard ourselves from falling into the traps and temptations of the flesh, we might utter foolish words that lead to our own destruction or those around us. We must learn the wisdom of silence, especially with regard to foolish words and unrestrained speech, and guard our mouth so that we can avoid the pain and harm that comes when we let our selfish desires drive the words we speak.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Tortoise and the Ducks.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 13:3; 18:21; James 3:6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-02-12', 'Castos', 0, '12:44', 9, 4, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-4-Guard-Your-Mouth-13.3-18.21-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-4-guard-your-mouth-prov-133-1821', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 32, null),
(1464, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 3 | The Blessings of Wisdom', '<p>There are such incredible blessings for those who walk with Wisdom on her road. We must recognize her priceless value and choose to orient our lives to her. This idea of holding fast to wisdom signifies the complete commitment and sincere devotion to keep oneself on the road walking alongside Wisdom and never departing from her onto a different road, knowing that her path is better than any path we could ever devise on our own.</p> <p>Illustration: Mastercard&rsquo;s &ldquo;Priceless&rdquo; ad campaign.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 3:13-18; 8:32-34</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-02-07', 'Castos', 0, '18:30', 9, 3, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-3-The-Blessings-of-Wisdom-3.13-18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-3-the-blessings-of-wisdom-prov-313-18', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(1465, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 2 | The Fear of Yahweh is the Foundation of Wisdom', '<p>The difference between a fear of Yahweh that is driven by selfish interests and the true fear of Yahweh is that the one who seeks to grow wise understands they cannot live with true wisdom apart from a genuine relationship with Yahweh. When we live with the true fear of Yahweh, our hearts will turn toward him and we will appreciate and value the disciplining and training that he gives so that we may become wise and discerning.</p> <p>Illustration: Sir Francis Bacon&rsquo;s humanistic (or human-oriented) philosophy and how it still permeates our entire society and world today.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:7, 9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-01-29', 'Castos', 0, '15:59', 9, 2, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-2-The-Fear-of-Yahweh-is-the-Foundation.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-2-the-fear-of-yahweh-is-the-foundation-prov-17-910', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 37, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1466, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 1 | The Purpose of Proverbs', '<p>The purpose of Proverbs is for the reader to grow and become wise and understanding, and if they are already wise, then they will become even wiser. If the meaning of a proverb is not readily apparent, we mustn&rsquo;t give up. We must be willing to be patient with ourselves and the proverb and diligently meditate upon it, taking into consideration all the aspects of the text until we are able to draw out the depth and richness of its meaning.</p> <p>Illustration: Charles M. Schwab, who was the president of Bethlehem Steel Corporation, sought out a simple and wise strategy for achieving higher productivity.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-01-24', 'Castos', 0, '16:56', 9, 1, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Words-of-Wisdom-Ep-1-The-Purpose-of-Proverbs.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-1-the-purpose-of-proverbs-prov-11-6', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 44, null),
(1467, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 0 | An Introduction to the Book of Proverbs', '<p>We call Proverbs a book in the Old Testament, but it is really not a book at all. It is actually a collection of several writings that have been brought together into a single volume and titled as &ldquo;The Book of Proverbs.&rdquo; While proverbs might seem brief, they hold deep meaning about how life is supposed to work and how to best live under the rulership of Yahweh God. Therefore, if we desire to grasp the wealth of knowledge and guidance that Proverbs has to offer, it will require of us an investment of time and effort to understand and reflect on them.</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-01-15', 'Castos', 0, '17:18', 9, 0, 'poetry, parallelism, couplet, imagery', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Words-of-Wisdom-Ep-0.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-0-introduction-to-the-book-of-proverbs', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 64, null),
(1468, 1, 'The Priestly Covenant', '<p>Doug Campbell shares on one of the lesser known covenants in the Bible.</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman.</p>', '2020-05-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:20', 0, 0, null, 'HqJO7-RMKz8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HqJO7-RMKz8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1469, 1, 'Job and Human Suffering: Don''t Blame God', '<p>The problem of evil and human suffering has been an issue that people have struggled with for generations. Is God the cause? Unfortunately, many people think He is. This teaching helps us understand that God is not the problem, in fact He provided the solution to the problem, Jesus Christ.</p> <p>View the Bible Project&rsquo;s video on &ldquo;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xQwnH8th_fs" target="_blank">the Book of Job</a>.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Luke 10:17-20, 23-24; 1 Pet. 5:6-11</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p> <p>Mentioned in the teaching: Lauren Daigle singing &ldquo;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vr0d51uFTMc" target="_blank">Still Rolling Stones &ndash; Social Distancing Version</a>.&rdquo;</p>', '2020-05-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '15:35', 0, 0, null, 'J2xm7Jany2g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J2xm7Jany2g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1470, 1, 'Living to the Praise of God''s Glory', '<p>We have been called to love God, to know Him, and be in service to each other. This teaching provides insight on how we can live to the praise of God&rsquo;s glory and take part in fulfilling His purpose for our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 11:20-23; Rom. 7:18-25; 8:18-19, 22-28; Eph. 1:3-12; 3:8-21; 4:1-4, 11-16; Col. 1:24-27</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:58', 0, 0, null, 'N575uEEmRTk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/N575uEEmRTk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1471, 1, 'Walking by the Spirit – What Are You Prepared to Do?', '<p>Walking by the spirit, for the Christian, includes many behavioral expectations. This teaching describes what it looks like to walk in the spirit as opposed to walking by one&rsquo;s own self-serving desires. The quality of the believer&rsquo;s life is greatly enhanced and pleasing to God as they make the active choice to live according to God&rsquo;s design.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:13; 1 Pet. 5:8; Gal. 5:1, 13-18; Rom. 8:1-11, Matt. 1:21; Gal. 5:17-23; 1 John 1:1-2:8; 1 John 5:3; Gal. 5:24; Eccles. 12:13</p> <p>Additional teaching referenced: <a href="https://spirittruth.podbean.com/e/rough-weather-ahead/" target="_blank">Rough Weather Ahead</a></p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:48', 0, 0, 'clear-headed, condemnation, death, devour, devil, fellowship, flesh fruit, joy, law, mind, peaceful, pray, saved, sin', 'KeljR4fKDwg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KeljR4fKDwg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1472, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 16 | It&rsquo;s Good to Leave an Inheritance', '<p>Setting aside a portion of the wealth we earn and planning to pass it on to our children is a demonstration of godly wisdom. But an inheritance should be more than just money, it is a way that we can share our knowledge of success and discipline to help our children live with wisdom and steward well the gift we give to them.</p> <p>Illustration: Scott Nash, owner of MOM&rsquo;s Organic Market, and his perspective on his children&rsquo;s inheritance.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 13:22</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-21', 'Castos', 0, '19:14', 9, 16, 'stewardship, investment', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-16-It-s-Good-to-Leave-an-Inheritance-13.22-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-16-its-good-to-leave-an-inheritance-prov-1322', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1473, 1, 'Who is the Thief in John 10:10?', '<p>Jesus Christ is the Good Shepherd and he laid down his life for his sheep. This teaching highlights sections of scripture from the Gospel of John in chapters 8 through 10. The reader is encouraged to look at the context of Scripture to determine who the thief that comes to steal, kill and destroy really is. It poses the question, based on biblical accuracy and self-reflection, &ldquo;Are you being led to or away from Christ&rdquo;?</p> <p>Verses: John 10:1-14; John 9:14, 28, 34, 39-41; John 8:37-59</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-05-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '22:00', 0, 0, 'blind, deny, devil, false, leader, liar, Moses, resurrection, salvation, truth', 'l-x9unPbMWo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/l-x9unPbMWo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 23, null),
(1474, 1, 'How are We Doing at Loving Ourselves?', '<p>God desires for His children to walk in maturity. Are the relational difficulties we encounter with others an extension of the difficulties we experience in our relationships with our Father, our Savior, and/or ourselves? We are encouraged to see ourselves the way our Father sees us and to build relationships with others based on what God and the Lord Jesus Christ gifted to us within the body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:37-40; Col. 1:25-28; Eph. 4:15-16; Rom. 7:14-25; Rom. 1:21-24; Gal. 5:14-18; Eph. 4:30-32; Rom. 5:1-12; Rom. 8:22-39</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-05-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:14', 0, 0, 'flesh, forgiveness, intercession, intimacy, love, purpose, relationship, tenderhearted, spirit, walk, war', 'dAWQU_iI1UQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dAWQU_iI1UQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1475, 1, 'We Have a Choice: There is no Fence to Sit on', '<p>Our faithfulness to share God&rsquo;s word gives people an opportunity to choose between life and death; good or evil; and doing things man&rsquo;s way or God&rsquo;s way. How does a person avoid being lulled to sleep when making the choice to be for or against Christ? Is it okay to just be a nice person? How do we truly follow Christ?</p> <p>Verses: Judg. 13:25; Deut. 30:11-20; Matt. 12:30; Mark 8:34-38; John 21:17-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-05-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:10', 0, 0, 'idols, pleasure, blessing, curse, rewards, ashamed, Peter, peace', 'safJ694l41s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/safJ694l41s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1476, 1, 'Pray for All People', '<p>We live in a world that, because of sin, is subject to attacks by the enemies of God. The great power of prayer throughout the Old and New Testament times is shared. As were our predecessors, Christians are exhorted to pray for all people, including those in authority so that we can lead quiet, peaceable, and tranquil lives.</p> <p>Verses: 1Tim. 2:1-3; Jer. 29:1-7; Neh. 1:1-11; Dan. 9:1-23; Rom. 8:26; Luke 11:1-10; Acts 4:21-31</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-05-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:43', 0, 0, 'ask, beg, captive, captivity, confession, curse, humility, intercede, intercession, mercy, persistence, petition, truth, salvation, saved', 'IowcxeS3ASU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IowcxeS3ASU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1477, 1, 'Praise God In Your Storm', '<p>Remembering to praise God when you are going through difficult times can be challenging. But when we praise God in the midsts of our trouble, God is most glorified.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 16:22-26; Neh. 8:10.</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille.</p>', '2020-05-29', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:07', 0, 0, null, 'LfdjY3f1hPA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LfdjY3f1hPA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1478, 1, 'No Christian is an Island: We Need Each Other', '<p>As Christians, members of the Body of Christ, we are not meant to stand alone. This sharing delves into how and why we are to help each other, support each other, be honest with each other, pray for each other, and more.</p> <p>Teachers: David Dougherty and John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:28', 0, 0, null, 'pvj3mxkAoEo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pvj3mxkAoEo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1479, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 17 | Good News From Far Away', '<p>When someone lives far away from friends and family, the desire to hear from them grows more intense as time goes on. To hear a good report, or good news, from them satisfies a fundamental craving in our soul&mdash;a craving for connection and relationship. There is wisdom in sending good news to our loved ones, for we know the beneficial effect it can have upon their soul.</p> <p>Illustration: Chong Bates and the search for her lost son.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:25; Gen. 37:23-28; 39:1-20; 43:27-28; 45:9, 25-28</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-05-29', 'Castos', 0, '18:24', 9, 17, 'friendship', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-17-Good-News-From-Far-Away-25.25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep17', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1480, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost', '<p>The Christian church began on the Day of Pentecost, the one day feast when Jews from around the known world were present in Jerusalem. It was the first time the gift of holy spirit that we have today was poured out by Jesus Christ. This teaching expounds on that Day and explains some of the differences between holy spirit in the Old Testament and the New Testament.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2; Luke 24:49; John 20:19-22; Joel 2:28ff.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:14', 0, 0, null, 'qn7rYOFU19s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qn7rYOFU19s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1481, 1, 'Jump In With Both Feet - We&rsquo;re Equipped', '<p>We all have an important role to play in the Body of Christ, and God has equipped every Christian to fulfill his or her role. Learn what God has done for us through Jesus Christ, figure out what your personal ministry is, and do not hesitate to get involved. God needs us to do our part!</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 1:2-3; 1 Cor. 3:9; 12:18, 28; Rom. 12:6-8; Eph 4:11-13.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-06-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:09', 0, 0, null, 'Y835ddouP4Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Y835ddouP4Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1482, 1, 'Should Christians Pay Attention To The Political Process?', '<p>Many Christians believe that God is in complete control of all aspects of the world, including politics. But in this teaching, we learn how Christians can play an important role by paying attention to the political process and voting.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:1-3; Gen. 1:26; Luke 4:5-7; 2 Cor. 4:4; Heb. 2:14; 1 John 5:19; Gal. 6:7; Prov. 4:7; Luke 4:9-12.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-06-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:05', 0, 0, 'sovereignty wisdom', 'EnbF5m1h1Ws', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EnbF5m1h1Ws/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1483, 1, 'Manifesting the Love of God in This World', '<p>All Christians have the very nature of God, and can manifest love like God and Jesus Christ do. We are not forced to love, it is something we must choose to do. God&rsquo;s Word tells us what that love looks like, and provides instruction on how to love like Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:7-14 ; 1 Pet. 2:3-8; 1 Cor. 13.</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings.</p>', '2020-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '21:30', 0, 0, null, 'IOPCzf8tINU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IOPCzf8tINU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1484, 5, 'YHWH: The Name of God', '<p>This article is from the BiblicalUnitarian.com website.</p> <p>&ldquo;The Sacred Name of God is a prominent feature in the Hebrew Scriptures (Old Testament) and appears nearly 7,000 times throughout its pages (6,828 times in Codex Leningradensis). In the actual Hebrew text, the Divine Name of God is written as four letters, YHWH (known as the <em>Tetragrammaton</em>). These four consonants representing the Divine Name have been referred to as the ineffable or incommunicable Name of God...&rdquo;</p>', '2016-11-16', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/yhwh-the-name-of-god', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/YHWH-the-name-of-god-1.png', 1, 0, null, 1, 20, null),
(1485, 5, 'Yahweh God', '<p>[This article was originally published by Greg Deuble on his website, <a href="https://thebiblejesus.com/articles" target="_blank">TheBibleJesus.com</a>, and is currently on <a href="https://www.biblicalunitarian.com/" target="_blank">BiblicalUnitarian.com</a>.]</p> <p>&ldquo;Everybody has a name. Every individual man, woman, boy and girl has a name. My personal name is Gregory. Gregory happens to mean &lsquo;watchful&rsquo;. I don&rsquo;t mind if you call me Greg &hellip; in fact, the only person who ever called me Gregory was my mother and then I knew I was in trouble because it was always said in a firm tone with an exclamation mark after it! Your name represents you, the real person, your &lsquo;self&rsquo;. I have known many people get quite upset when their rightful personal name is forgotten, altered, not spelled right, etc.</p> <p>&ldquo;In the Bible God has gone to a lot of trouble to reveal His Personal Name to us. Some 6,828 times the one and only God of the Bible is called Yahweh...&rdquo;</p>', '2020-06-08', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://www.biblicalunitarian.com/articles/yahweh-god', 'https://i1.wp.com/www.biblicalunitarian.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Untitled-design-5.jpg?resize=1071%2C603&ssl=1', 1, 0, null, 1, 38, null),
(1486, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 18 | Answer Or Don''t Answer', '<p>Wisdom tells us to be discerning and careful with what we say and how we say it. It is a best practice to pause and collect our thoughts before responding because once foolish words proceed out of our mouth, we can&rsquo;t take them back, even if we want to. We will have shot ourselves in the foot, and people will call us the fool instead.</p> <p>Illustration: Apple CEO Steve Jobs properly responding to a difficult Q&amp;A session where someone calls his personal life and technical skill into question</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 26:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-08', 'Castos', 0, '20:21', 9, 18, 'confrontation, foolishness, antagonism', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-18-Answer-Or-Don-t-Answer-26.4-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-18-answer-or-dont-answer-prov-264-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1487, 1, 'Being Peaceful, Positive, and Prayerful', '<p>In Matthew 14:22-33, both Jesus Christ and Peter walked on water. They were in the same storm, walking on the same waves, both listening to the howling wind. Why did Jesus not have a problem with it, but Peter did? It&rsquo;s how we look at things that counts. We need to be strong in our God and remember to pray.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 14:22-33; 1 Sam. 30:6; Col. 1:9ff.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-06-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:32', 0, 0, null, 'Z6D7mW8JlOE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Z6D7mW8JlOE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1488, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/07/2020) - Starting the Day with Identity', 'This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God''s love in your life, and pray.', '2020-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:44', 0, 0, null, 'O5F4k1FaZZk', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O5F4k1FaZZk&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/O5F4k1FaZZk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(1489, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/31/2020) - Revelation: Part 8', 'This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God''s love in your life, and pray.', '2020-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:14', 0, 0, null, 'X_fDpY8WSOI', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X_fDpY8WSOI&rel=0', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X_fDpY8WSOI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(1490, 1, 'Keep God''s Greatness at the Forefront of Your Mind', '<p>In troubled times, it can be easy to become dismayed. But when we recognize and focus on the greatness of God and how He is always with us, we can be peaceful and know that God is holding our hand through it all.</p> <p>Verses: Isaiah 41:2-13; Psalm 31:24</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '7:11', 0, 0, null, 'b43a5VAs4h0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b43a5VAs4h0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1491, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 19 | Listen to Counsel', '<p>Why should we listen to what others have to say? If we think we have all the right answers, then we shouldn&rsquo;t need to. But we must never perceive ourselves as having sufficient wisdom in all circumstances. That is why the wise person will ask other (especially God) for wisdom, because part of being wise is knowing that more wisdom is always helpful to make the best decision in any circumstance.</p> <p>Illustration: Jerry Wierwille and his prideful refusal to listen to his friend&rsquo;s advice when windsurfing</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 12:15</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-12', 'Castos', 0, '11:38', 9, 19, 'instruction, help', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-19-Listen-to-Counsel-12.15-.wav.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-19-listen-to-counsel-prov-1215', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 31, null),
(1492, 1, 'Maturing Into Christ Together To The Praise Of God&rsquo;s Glory', '<p>If we understand God&rsquo;s purpose for the universe and for us, we can then fulfill God&rsquo;s purpose for our lives. His purpose for us is to be in intimate relationship with Him, the Lord Jesus Christ, and each other. Everyone is welcome at the cross. God wants us to know and understand the Christ in us, along with all the holy ones. This teaching exhorts us to identify who we are in Christ and then provides keys on how to live out God&rsquo;s purpose in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: Eph 2:13-18; 3:9-19; 4:11-13; 4:1-3, 21-25; 5:21-33; Col 3:1-4.</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-06-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:30', 0, 0, null, 'H1WKsHyULGc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H1WKsHyULGc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1493, 1, 'Do Not Allow Yourselves to be Deceived', '<p>This teaching starts off in Luke 21:5, where Jesus Christ is speaking to his apostles about the end times. One of his admonishments to them (and to us) is to not allow themselves to be deceived. How is this accomplished? John then goes into the record of Judges 17-18, where Micah believed he was right in the things he was doing, yet he was very wrong.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 21:5ff; Judg. 17-18.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit.</p>', '2020-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:42', 0, 0, null, 'tc0xon0o7N4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tc0xon0o7N4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1494, 1, 'We Are Accepted By God', '<p>Christians need to make peace with the fact that if we are standing for God, the world will hate (or dislike) us. God loves us, He put us into a family. We should not expect the world to understand, because it won&rsquo;t. If we know that we are accepted by God, not being accepted by the world should not matter. This teaching helps us to have realistic expectations when we stand for God and the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: John 15:18-19; 1 John 3:13; Eph. 5:1; 1 John 3:1-3; 4:9-15, 19; Rom. 8:31-39.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-06-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:49', 0, 0, null, 'xtQHj-qQrrU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xtQHj-qQrrU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1495, 1, 'Understanding the Armor of God', '<p>The armor of God is a very important part of the Christian&rsquo;s life. This teaching offers a short overview of the armor of God described in Ephesians 6 and explains what it is and its importance to the Christian.</p> <p>Verses: Rom 3:19-24; Eph. 6:10-18; 1 Thess. 5:8-10; Titus 2:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-06-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:07', 0, 0, null, 'n_QeZM2qFnA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/n_QeZM2qFnA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1496, 1, 'Two Important Lessons From The Life Of Hezekiah', '<p>This teaching provides two important lessons we can learn from the life of Hezekiah. The first lesson discussed is that even when we do right in life, sometimes things can still go wrong for us. The second lesson is that prayer can have a dramatic effect on our lives.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 18:1-17; 2 Kings 19:1-4; 2 Kings 19:35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-06-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:42', 0, 0, null, 'VQjVXOIieIQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VQjVXOIieIQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1498, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 20 | Listen to Reproof', '<p>In general, reproof is meant to be a good thing that helps us become better. There will be plenty of criticism in life that does not qualify as being helpful, but part of growing in wisdom is to discern if the reproof is leading to life. It will require much humility to admit when we are wrong and to change our ways, but that is how we acquire good sense for making wise choices.</p> <p>Illustration: Famous American chef Thomas Keller receives harsh review from restaurant critic Peter Wells.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 15:31-32</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-20', 'Castos', 0, '19:41', 9, 20, 'correction, instruction, antagonism, negative', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-20-Listen-to-Reproof-15.31-32-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-20-listen-to-reproof-prov-1531-32', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1499, 1, 'Rest, Pray, Love', '<p>All of us face challenges and difficult times in our lives. How can we find peace amidst the storms of life? This teaching focuses on three things we can do: 1) rest in the Lord, 2) pray for all people, and 3) love one another.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 11:28-30; 1 Timothy 2:1-4; 1 Thessalonians 4:9-12</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-06-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:05', 0, 0, null, '9H3RMTIQ_kI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9H3RMTIQ_kI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1500, 1, 'Living in Grace', '<p>Song: &ldquo;<a href="https://youtu.be/pBNI41D21l0" target="_blank">A Friend Called Grace</a>&rdquo; by Phillips Craig Dean</p> <p>This teaching explores the grace of God that Christians live in now and how Jesus Christ died in place of people when they had done nothing to deserve such a blessing.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:7; 3:19-26; 5:1-11.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-06-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:57', 0, 0, null, 'CCPUi2BCDqo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CCPUi2BCDqo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1501, 1, 'Pour It Out to God', '<p>God wants us to come to him with all our cares and worries. Scripture tells us to &ldquo;pour out our heart&rdquo; to God. That means we can share with him every last one of our deep and personal concerns and feelings knowing that he listens to them and will help us. Nothing is too much for our God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 1:10-15; Ps. 62:5-8</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:20', 0, 0, 'prayer, comfort, anxiety', 'BuY5Xgbhg_c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BuY5Xgbhg_c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1502, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 21 | Listen Before Answering', '<p>How many times has it worked out well to answer someone impulsively before taking a moment to think? We must develop the habit of not answering or making decisions rashly, rather to always listen first and listen fully so that we can respond appropriately and effectively. Many heartaches and mistakes in life can be avoided if we will but take a step back for a moment before opening our mouths.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable &ldquo;The Mice in Council&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:13</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-06-26', 'Castos', 0, '14:11', 9, 21, 'patience, attention, consider', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-21-Listen-Before-Answering-18.13-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-21-listen-before-answering-prov-1813-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1503, 1, 'Getting Involved May Not Be Easy', '<p>This teaching follows the examples of King Saul&mdash;who made bad decisions&mdash;and Jonathan his son, a godly man who walked with God, made good decisions, and took the risks necessary for success with God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 13:16-14:23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-06-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:02', 0, 0, null, 'HerBcAnnUYo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HerBcAnnUYo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1504, 5, 'Examples of Figures of Speech Used in the Bible; What are they, their purpose, recognizing them…', '<p><strong>What is a Figure of Speech?</strong></p> <p>A departure from the normal rules of grammar or word usage. Examples:</p> <blockquote> <p>&ldquo;breadth and length and depth and height&rdquo;<br /> &ldquo;The mountains will sing.&rdquo;</p> </blockquote> <p><strong>What is the purpose of figures of speech?</strong></p> <p>To give special emphasis.</p> <p>To call attention to the point...</p>', '2013-08-07', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/examples-of-figure-of-speech-used-in-the-bible', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1505, 1, 'The Destruction of Benjamin – Evil on Both Sides', '<p>This teaching explores the last three chapters of Judges and shows how the destruction of the tribe of Benjamin was due to evil on both sides of the conflict, and that that still goes on today. Believers need to be aware of this and not be quick to pick sides in a conflict.</p> <p>Verses: Judges 19, 20, 21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:43', 0, 0, 'war, Belial', 'NTUjxrnWwLk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NTUjxrnWwLk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1506, 1, 'Bramble People', '<p>This teaching addresses the passage in Judges 9 where the evil leader Abimelech came to power and expounds the fable about the trees that Jotham spoke to the people of Shechem. &ldquo;Bramble people&rdquo; love to be noticed and praised, to be in charge and lord it over people, and although they talk big about doing things for others, in actuality they do things that feed their ego and build their reputation. These kinds of people still exist today, and wise Christians recognize them and pray they do not come to power.</p> <p>Verses: Judges 9:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '23:23', 0, 0, 'parable, trees', '8MSupzgeLJs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8MSupzgeLJs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 22, null),
(1507, 1, 'Trusting Relationships (Part 1 of 2)', '<p>When we were Born Again, we were called into a team called the Body of Christ. This teaching identifies some of the specifics of this team, along with a key component of the team: trust. 7 characteristics of trust are identified, and in Part 1 we dig deeper into the first 3.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Timothy 2:1-4, Colossians 3:5, Colossians 3:8-9, John 14:6, Matthew 5:27, Ezekiel 24:14, 1 John 1:8-10,Genesis 6:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2020-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:53', 0, 0, 'Mission, Culture', 'Ycgw8jhUp_c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ycgw8jhUp_c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1508, 1, 'Living Righteously Through the Hardships of Life', '<p>This teaching addresses 2 Corinthians 3-6, showing that the Bible predicts that there will be hardships in life and it is up to the believer to learn how to use them to grow in the Lord and continue to live righteously. </p> <p>Verses:  2 Corinthians 3-6 </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:13', 0, 0, 'righteousness', 'ZWUu27Gry0U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZWUu27Gry0U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1509, 1, 'The Parable of the Sower: Choose the Soil You Want to Be', '<p>This exposition of the Parable of the Sower, primarily from Matthew 13, describes that the different kinds of soil represent different kinds of people. The kind of person you are is not predetermined, but people choose by their thoughts and actions what kind of soil they will be. The kind of soil (person) you are can also change, so it is important to stay godly and guard your heart. </p> <p> Verses:  2 Cor. 6:11-13; Matthew 13</p> <p> Teacher: John  Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:00', 0, 0, null, '3uG1qm9MiqE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3uG1qm9MiqE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1510, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (7/5/2020) - Revelation: Part 9', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-07-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:41', 0, 0, null, 'Uw3fsKI8fW4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Uw3fsKI8fW4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe''s fellowship', 1, 0, null),
(1511, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 22 | The Generous Will Be Blessed', '<p>God blesses those who give freely and generously with the finances and belongings that they have and those who will use those blessings to serve his purposes&mdash;one of which is to provide and care for the poor and needy. And if we will gladly share a portion of our finances that God blesses us with, we will be blessed in return.</p> <p>Illustration: Yu Panglin, a very successful Hong Kong hotel and real-estate entrepreneur</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 22:9</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-09', 'Castos', 0, '12:32', 9, 22, 'generosity, giving, blessings, sharing', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-22-The-Generous-Will-Be-Blessed-22.9-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-22-the-generous-will-be-blessed-prov-229', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1512, 1, 'God Cares Most', '<p>Sometimes we may feel that no one cares about us. We may feel all alone at our job or at home. When David was on the run from Saul, he felt like he was all alone. He called out to God in his distress because he knew that even if no one cared for him, God did. We too can call out to God in our time of need and tell him all our troubles knowing he is the one who can help us.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 142:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-10', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:57', 0, 0, null, 'H24_Wln6nOM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H24_Wln6nOM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1513, 1, 'Trusting Relationships (Part 2 of 2)', '<p>When we were born again, we were called into a team called the Body of Christ. This teaching identifies some of the specifics of this team, along with a key component of the team: trust. 7 characteristics of trust are identified, and in part 2 we dig deeper into the last 4, continuing on from part 1.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 9:27-31; Eph. 3:8-9; 1 Cor. 2:7-8; Luke 22:41-42; 1 Thess. 2:9-10; Matt. 7:1-2; Luke 6:37; Matt. 8:2-3; John 4:7-9; John 4:39-41</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2020-07-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '21:38', 0, 0, 'mission, culture', '_mtOXcEXh4c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_mtOXcEXh4c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1514, 5, 'A Quick Reference to the Books of the Bible', '<p>This article is a very brief synopsis of each of the books of the Bible, and it&rsquo;s intended to give the novice reader a sense of each Book and how it fits with in the overall picture of the Bible.</p>', '2018-04-02', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/a-quick-reference-to-the-books-of-the', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/A-Quick-Reference-to-the-Books-of-the-Bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 15, null),
(1515, 1, 'Praise Jah!', '<p>This fellowship teaching centers around praising God for the accomplished work of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ. Our sacrifice in response to that accomplishment is the fruit of our lips&mdash;praise.</p> <p>Verses: Hebrews 13:10-16 and various Psalms</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-07-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:25', 0, 0, 'Atonement, Praise, Worship, Forgiveness, Psalms, Scapegoat, Altar, Sacrifice', 'bNFyg9pxAVM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bNFyg9pxAVM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1516, 5, 'Biblical definition (meaning) of the Greek word Musterion: The Administration of the Sacred Secret', '<p>Christians need to understand the wonderful gift of holy spirit that God has given to us and appreciate the grace we have. We also need to understand why God called the very time in which we live &ldquo;&hellip;the administration of the grace of God&hellip;&rdquo;</p>', '2013-02-11', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/biblical-definition-meaning-of-the-greek-word-musterion-the-administration-of-the-sacred-secret', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1517, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/12/2020) - The Bread of the Presence', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-07-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:55', 0, 0, null, 'zToTAirVKYI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zToTAirVKYI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe''s fellowship...', 1, 0, null),
(1518, 1, 'Jesus and Nicodemus (Understanding John 3)', '<p>The interaction between Jesus and Nicodemus described in John 3 is not well understood in the Christian world, but their conversation is very important in understanding the context of John 3 itself as well as other aspects of the future and the Kingdom of God.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:1-12; Ezekiel 37:1-14; Isa. 26:19;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:39', 0, 0, 'born above again', '30F2A_JVgi4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/30F2A_JVgi4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1519, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 23 | Glad Hearts and Fat Bones', '<p>Hearing bad news can have a dramatic effect on us. But the same is true with good news. Whether it is a smile or it is simply a bit of uplifting feedback or story of success that we can share with someone else, sharing positivity and joy with others has a profound life-giving impact. A wise person spreads the health and nourishing effect of good news knowing its positive effect in their lives.</p> <p>Illustration: Lathan Johnson and his fire team being trapped in Shoshone National Forest during the Little Venus Fire of 2006</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 15:30</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-14', 'Castos', 0, '14:32', 9, 23, 'gladness, wellbeing, report', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-23-Glad-Hearts-and-Fat-Bones-15.30-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-23-glad-hearts-and-fat-bones-prov-1530-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1520, 1, 'The Need for Evangelism - Gehenna (&ldquo;Hell&rdquo;) is Real', '<p>There are many people today, even Christians, who make fun of &ldquo;hellfire and damnation&rdquo; preaching but making fun of something does not make it go away or be only a myth. The Bible is very clear that unsaved people will be thrown into the Lake of Fire, where they will burn up and be annihilated. This teaching presents many verses from both the Old and New Testament about the Lake of Fire and Gehenna, which will show that it is no idle threat but the way that God will rid the earth of evil, rebellious people. This reality can serve as encouragement for Christians to be bold about their Christian Faith and speak to people so that they have a chance to live forever.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; Rom. 6:23; Rev. 20:11-15; Prov. 10:25; Ps. 37:20; 92:7; Mal. 4:1; Matt. 3:7, 12; Matt. 5:29; 10:28; 13:40-43</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '25:28', 0, 0, 'Annihilation', 'YmIPU9V4puc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YmIPU9V4puc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1521, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 24 | Watch What You Say', '<p>We should always weigh our words before we speak. As small and harmless as some might think words to be, caring little for whether they use them properly or not, they are more powerful and impacting than we often realize. We must become wise and handle our words with care, keeping watch over what we allow to pass through our lips. In this way, will watch over our life from trouble.</p> <p>Illustration: Mike Jeffries, CEO of Abercrombie &amp; Fitch, gives a disastrously offensive interview to Salon Magazine.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 21:23</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-17', 'Castos', 0, '15:29', 9, 24, 'wisdom, discernment, speech, offense', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-24-Watch-What-You-Say.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-24-watch-what-you-say-prov-2123', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1522, 1, 'Lessons from the Book of Jonah', '<p>Jonah was a very important prophet in Israel in the eighth century BC. Unfortunately, not much is known about him by the average Christian because the information is scattered around the Bible, and sometimes he is not mentioned by name. This teaching explores many places in the Bible and puts together some of the not well-recognized information about Jonah.</p> <p>Verses: Jonah 1:1-3; Matthew 12:40, Luke 11:29-30; 2 Kings 23-25; John 7:52; 1 Kings 14:15</p> <p>Teacher: JohnSchoenheit</p>', '2020-07-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:25', 0, 0, 'whale fish', '1v4Z1NMgAsQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1v4Z1NMgAsQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1523, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/19/2020) - Covenants & the Sacred Secret', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-07-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:20', 0, 0, null, 'XYRLJ_Jsuis', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XYRLJ_Jsuis/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'From Gabe, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1524, 5, 'Bible Study Guide', '<p>This Study Guide is for students of the Scripture who are serious about their faith. It assumes that the reader is familiar with the basics of Christianity such as how to get saved, the value of prayer, and importance of reading the Bible. It is for Christians who read their Bible and wonder what certain passages mean, but do not have a clear idea of how to gain more understanding, or for Christians who wonder how to learn more about what the Bible teaches. It is not a commentary, nor does it contain &ldquo;all the answers&rdquo; to questions about the Bible. Rather, it is a guide to learning, so the student of the Bible can learn how to answer many of the questions that may come up as he or she reads the Bible.</p>', '2009-04-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://www.truthortradition.com/pdf/BibleStudyGuide.pdf', 'https://www.truthortradition.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/What-does-the-Bible-say-about-%E2%80%9CSoul%E2%80%9D-1-300x142.png', 0, 0, 'inactive because it does not exist on the new site', 1, 13, null),
(1525, 1, 'Living Out God&rsquo;s &lsquo;Big Idea&rsquo;', '<p>God&rsquo;s purpose of the ages is for us to be His habitation. God lives in us, and our relationship with Him and with each other is through the accomplished work of Jesus Christ and our union with him. We should acknowledge that all Christians are saved sinners, and not look at each other according the differences we may have between us, but to be living sacrifices for each other.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:25-27; Eph. 3:1-12; 2:11-18; 4:1-6; 1 Cor. 15:20-28; Eph. 1:3; John 14:10-14, 17-20; 15:4; Rom. 12:1; Eph. 5:1ff</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-06-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:48', 0, 0, 'family, body', 'GseilYrmu0Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GseilYrmu0Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1526, 1, 'Called to Relationship', '<p>God has called us to be in relationship with Him and with each other. How do we carry that out? What does it look like? This thought-provoking teaching contains several practical keys on how to be in a fulfilling relationship with both God and the people in our lives. Two big ones are being honest with each other and listening from the heart.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:1-3, 10-15; Eph. 4:16, 24-32; 5:1ff; Matt. 18:15; 1 Cor. 15:20-28; James 1:19; Prov. 18:2, 13</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-06-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:20', 0, 0, 'communication, love', 'b5-lO3yXv7Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b5-lO3yXv7Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1527, 1, 'Jonah: Running from God', '<p>This teaching goes through Jonah chapters 1 and 2 verse by verse and expounds the text. We learn why Jonah ran from God, and why it can be concluded that Jonah was dead in the belly of the fish, not alive there as most Christians are taught.</p> <p>Verses: Jonah 1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:32', 0, 0, 'storm', 'xp0vWyVtgZA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xp0vWyVtgZA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1528, 1, '&ldquo;Even If God Doesn&rsquo;t&rdquo; Faith', '<p>We all encounter trials in life, but in the midst of trials and adversity, God works in us to grow and become stronger. God also promises that he will help us in every trial to endure through temptation and have a way to escape. But even if God doesn&rsquo;t deliver us from suffering in the way we think he should, our trust in God should not waver.</p> <p>Verses: Jas. 1:2-4; 1 Cor. 10:13; Dan. 3:14-18; Heb. 10:23</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:35', 0, 0, 'deliverance, testing', 'WdIGTM_GfLc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WdIGTM_GfLc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1529, 1, 'Preparing to Serve', '<p>Five people in the Bible took time away from the people they were destined to serve, and when they returned, did great things. Their example suggests devoting time to God and Jesus prepares us to serve in a greater capacity than if we do not.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 2:15; 4:19; 1 Kings 19:1-2, 8-9, 15-16; Luke 1:13-17, 80; 7:28; 4:1-2; Gal. 1:17-18; Eph. 3:1-3, 7</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2020-07-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '13:30', 0, 0, 'Desert, 40 days, Midian, Horeb, Arabia', 'RTPf3hdAk7U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RTPf3hdAk7U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1530, 5, 'The Bible as a Work of Literature', '<p>Everyone understands that the way we approach a book depends upon the kind of book it is. The Bible is no different. Learning to enjoy it requires that we understand it as a collection of many different genres, each serving a different purpose. Besides the many stories of people and events, it also contains poetry, prophetic warnings and sayings, proverbs, letters, and more. Since the Bible also served the Jewish nation as a historical and legal record, it includes genealogical lists, census records, and religious, sacrificial, and legal instructions. The Bible is a very diverse compilation of widely-ranging materials,...</p>', '2018-01-22', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-bible-as-a-work-of-literature', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/the-bible-as-a-work-of-literature.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1531, 1, 'What does the Bible Say about Repentance?', '<p>This teaching explores the biblical meaning of repentance from Old and New Testament perspectives. Embedded in the concept of repentance is humility, changing one&rsquo;s heart, turning back to God, prayer, and confession of sins. The believer&rsquo;s need to repent does not stop at the point of becoming saved.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 6:36-39; Dan. 9:1-10, 20-23; Matt. 3:11; 4:17; Acts 2:38; 2 Cor. 7:8-10</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2020-07-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:30', 0, 0, 'forgiveness', 'foT1u_MYJKs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/foT1u_MYJKs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1532, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 25 | Fast Money Doesn''t Last', '<p>If we are willing to work hard and be mindful of the money we receive, God can help us steward our finances well and receive the greatest value and blessing from them. The key principle is really not how much you earn, but it&rsquo;s what you do with it. Those who stumble across money or cheat others for it typically don&rsquo;t give much thought to how they should care for it and use it, and thus they almost always end up wasting it away on meaningless things.</p> <p>Illustration: 2017 fraudulent GoFundMe campaign by Katelyn McClure backfired on her</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 13:11</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-07-28', 'Castos', 0, '13:40', 9, 25, 'wealth, honesty, dishonesty, gain, loss', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-25-Fast-Money-Doesn-t-Last-Prov.-13.11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-25-fast-money-doesnt-last-prov-1311', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1533, 1, 'Jonah and Human Free Will', '<p>This teaching covers Jonah chapters 3 and 4 and shows that God gifted humans with free will, and the importance of making right choices. In this teaching, the illustration of the potter and the clay in Jeremiah 18 is also explained.</p> <p>Verses: Jon. 3-4; Amos 7:10-13; Jer. 18:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: JohnSchoenheit</p>', '2020-07-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:27', 0, 0, 'nineveh', 'pvHd2n5i6Yo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pvHd2n5i6Yo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1534, 1, 'How to Keep Evangelizing Even When You Don&rsquo;t See Results', '<p>It can be hard to be enthusiastic about sharing your Christian Faith with others when there does not seem to be any good results from all your efforts. This teaching talks about maintaining your energy and enthusiasm in those situations. Through various lessons in Scripture, we can see that obeying God always bears fruit even if we do not see it. For example, some of the &ldquo;seeds&rdquo; we plant take years to grow. Getting results is not our job, it&#39;s God&rsquo;s job. We will be more excited about our part in salvation history if we focus on our own job and what we can do, rather than looking at work that is God&rsquo;s or another person&rsquo;s responsibility.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 3:23-24; 1 Cor. 3:6-7; Acts 18:1-18; Rev. 3:15; 2 Chron. 33:9-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-07-31', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:52', 0, 0, 'rewards, Manasseh', 'Vui8tOyzDpk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vui8tOyzDpk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1535, 1, 'The Wise and Foolish Virgins', '<p>Jesus interrupted his teaching about the end times (Matt. 24-25) to tell two parables: the parable about the wise and foolish virgins, and the parable about the talents. This teaching focuses on the parable of the wise and foolish virgins, sets the background for the parable, then expounds it.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 24:1-2; 25:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:05', 0, 0, null, 'm8fLxSX0Bbk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m8fLxSX0Bbk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1536, 5, 'Things to Consider When Receiving a Prophecy', '<p><strong>1. Before receiving a prophecy, it is good to learn something about it and be prepared to receive it.</strong> Prophecy is a way that you can hear from the Lord himself about his love and concern for you and about his will for your life. Your personal prophecy will mean a lot more to you if you know what prophecy is and how it works, and if you prepare your heart to receive it, evaluate it, and act on it. If you have questions about prophecy,...</p>', '2013-08-05', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/things-to-consider-when-receiving-a-prophecy', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 11, null),
(1538, 5, 'The Conditional Nature of Prophecy', '<p><strong>Much Prophecy is Conditional</strong><br /> Prophecy is giving a message from God or the Lord Jesus to another person or persons, and that the main reason for prophecy is God&rsquo;s love for us. God wants a relationship with us, and He wants to show His love for us and desires us to love Him.</p>', '2013-01-15', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-conditional-nature-of-prophecy', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/conditional-nature-of-prophecy-truth-or-tradition.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 5, null),
(1539, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 26 | A Word at the Right Time', '<p>As we seek to walk with wisdom and to give a fitting answer at the right time, we need to realize and be confident in the fact that our words can shape the future of others and can help them overcome an obstacle, be comforted when hurting, or give them courage to do what they know is right. Our words are powerful, and we must learn to speak what is right, in the right way, and most importantly&hellip;at the right time.</p> <p>Illustration: The Civil Rights Era and the words of Martin Luther King Jr at defining moments</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 15:23</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-08-05', 'Castos', 0, '16:07', 9, 26, 'speech, fitting', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-26-A-Word-at-the-Right-Time-Prov.-15.23-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-26-a-word-at-the-right-time-prov-1523', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(1540, 5, 'God''s Divine Council', '<p>God is love. That simple statement explains why God created the universe as we know it, and populated it with both spirit beings and human beings. Furthermore, God gave those beings free will so He could interact with them and they could serve Him and interact with Him because they chose to out of love. God does not rule over His created beings as a tyrant, but works with them and allows them to help Him govern His created universe.</p>', '2018-07-02', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/gods-divine-council', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Gods-divine-council.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 54, null),
(1541, 1, 'Take It to the Lord', '<p>When we are suffering or struggling in life, our first response should be to inquire of the Lord and ask for his strength. The grace of the Lord is what will sustain us through hard times, and it is the times of adversity that will show the power of Christ to be at work in our lives. For when we are weak, then we are strong.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 12:7-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-08-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:31', 0, 0, 'thorn, conceit, prayer, endurance', 'YIvL3AEacqM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YIvL3AEacqM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1542, 5, 'What does the Bible Say About Fasting?', '<p>The purpose of this article is to give a better understanding of the topic of fasting. It is beyond the scope of this article to present an exhaustive study of the topic, but rather it will give the reader a better feel for the subject of fasting and why fasting might be helpful to believers today.</p>', '2013-09-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-fasting', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/bible_say_fasting.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 9, null),
(1543, 1, 'Jehoshaphat, A Man helped by God', '<p>Jehoshaphat was a godly king of Judah who was surprise-attacked by a large army from the east. This teaching provides some background on Jehoshaphat and covers the record of Judah&rsquo;s defeat of the large army that attacked them. God&#39;s miraculous intervention defeated the enemy then just as it takes God&#39;s intervention to defeat many enemies today.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 19:4-11; 20:1-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:01', 0, 0, null, 'mQ_RsWbmSl4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mQ_RsWbmSl4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1544, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/09/2020) - Holy Spirit', '<p>&hellip;...</p>', '2020-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:26', 0, 0, null, 'dl5ufAa4Imw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dl5ufAa4Imw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe''s fellowship', 1, 0, null),
(1545, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/02/2020) - The Good News', '<p>...</p>', '2020-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:47', 0, 0, null, '_ecpW9rwQfU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_ecpW9rwQfU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe''s fellowship', 1, 0, null),
(1546, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/26/2020) - Revelation: Part 10', '<p>Not active</p>', '2020-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:46', 0, 0, null, 'ANsaP1OzPnM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ANsaP1OzPnM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Gabe', 1, 1, null),
(1547, 1, 'The Message of Obadiah', '<p>This teaching takes a deeper look at the Book of Obadiah. Although there is a lot we do not know about the man Obadiah or the precise circumstances of the book, there are many lessons we can learn from it about consequences for sin, how God expects us to treat other people, and the eventual destruction of God&rsquo;s enemies and the vindication and restoration of His faithful people.</p> <p>Verses: Obadiah 1:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:43', 0, 0, 'Edom', 'llgc2TLMGSk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/llgc2TLMGSk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1548, 1, 'God&rsquo;s Love and Salvation by Trust in Jesus', '<p>One of the things that demonstrates God&rsquo;s love for humankind is the fact that He sent His only begotten Son to die for people, and the only thing a person needs to do to be saved is trust in Jesus. This teaching expounds on several verses and makes the point that salvation by trust in Jesus is a major theme in Romans.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 2:12-16; Rom. 3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:56', 0, 0, 'love', 'hDSejdG3ndA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hDSejdG3ndA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1549, 1, 'Pray to God with Boldness', '<p>There are lots of various kinds of prayers we can pray, including prayers of thanksgiving, petition, praise, and more. This teaching briefly covers the various different kinds of prayer and why they&rsquo;re important, and expounds on Jesus&rsquo; instruction on how we are to pray.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 11:1-10; 1 John 5:14-15</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '6:30', 0, 0, null, 'VO-IOn14bOM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VO-IOn14bOM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(1550, 5, 'Gospel Chronology of the Birth of Christ', '<p>This chronology will help you piece together the Gospel records of the Birth of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Read the records in the following order and enjoy letting the scriptures unfold this amazing event &ndash; the birth of our Lord!</p>', '2013-08-05', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/gospel-chronology-of-the-birth-of-christ', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 24, null),
(1551, 5, 'Beyond A Reasonable Doubt: 23 Arguments for the Historical Validity of the Resurrection of Jesus Christ', '<p>If true, the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead is the single most important event in the history of mankind, and therefore the one most crucial to establish as an authentic historical event. In fact, the resurrection is the very linchpin of the Christian faith, holding together every claim and every blessing. If the resurrection could be proven a fraud, Christianity would disintegrate as a total fabrication with little redeeming merit. Jesus would not even be an example of a &ldquo;good moral teacher,&rdquo; as some maintain, for his most important prediction&mdash;that he would be raised from the dead&mdash;would be found a lie.</p>', '2013-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/beyond-a-reasonable-doubt-23-arguments-for-the-historical-validity-of-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 27, null),
(1552, 1, 'The Book of Ruth | An Introduction (Part 1)', '<p>Ruth is a wonderful book with many themes and valuable lessons. In this Part One of a multi-part exposition of the Book of Ruth, the section 1:1-18 is covered verse by verse. This teaching is invaluable for anyone looking for a deeper understanding of this powerful and important record.</p> <p>Verses: Ruth 1:1-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:00:39', 53, 1, 'loyalty, family', 'I5f5wRrpoUc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I5f5wRrpoUc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1553, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/16/2020) - The Covenants & the Sacred Secret: Part 2', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:43', 0, 0, null, 'SwS_KpEcijc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SwS_KpEcijc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Noon fellowship, inactivated.', 1, 1, null),
(1554, 5, 'What is Hell?', '<p><strong>FAQ:</strong> I live in the USA, and it seems that our language is riddled with references to &ldquo;hell.&rdquo; I constantly hear that extremely versatile word used in conversations of all kinds. People say: &ldquo;What the hell?&rdquo; or &ldquo;The hell with it,&rdquo; or &ldquo;Hell, yes / no,&rdquo; etc. On occasion, some people, though not travel agents, have encouraged me to &ldquo;go to hell.&rdquo; I don&rsquo;t think I want to, because I&rsquo;ve heard that the Devil lives there, but if I did want to just drive by, where exactly is it located? Based on what people are saying, I assume that &ldquo;hell&rdquo; is a word used in the Bible, and if so, what is &ldquo;hell&rdquo;?</p>', '2013-01-15', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-hell', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/what-is-hell-truth-or-tradition.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 37, null),
(1555, 1, 'Walking in Your Function - Listening to Help', '<p>How often have you wanted to be heard, just listened to? This fellowship sharing explores the end of Job&rsquo;s story to get a sense of how to help others by really tuning in and listening.</p> <p>Verses:  Job 40, 41, 42:1-6; Eph. 4:29; 1 Pet. 4:10; James 1:19, 27; Gal. 5:13</p> <p>Teacher:  Ellen Cutler</p>', '2020-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '21:09', 0, 0, 'calling', 'vtohwym7h9o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vtohwym7h9o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1556, 5, 'Do Christians go to Heaven if they die?', '<p>A vital principle of Bible interpretation that must be upheld in handling any subject in God&rsquo;s Word is that any verses that are harder to understand must be analyzed in light of clear verses on the same subject. &ldquo;Clear&rdquo; verses are not just those that agree with one&rsquo;s theological position. They are those that seem to be straightforward and literal statements of fact. Figurative expressions that seem to be contradictory can best be handled after the literal, factual position is determined.</p>', '2013-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/do-christians-go-to-heaven-if-they-die', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 9, null),
(1557, 1, 'The Value of Truth', '<p>We live in a world in which personal opinion is considered more important than absolute truth, making room for &ldquo;my truth&rdquo; and &ldquo;your truth&rdquo;. But the biblical perspective is that truth exists outside of us and is not dependent on personal circumstances or feelings. Knowing the truth about truth is vital for a powerful and effective Christian life.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:4; John 8:31-32; Eph. 6:14; John 17:17; Hosea 4:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:27', 0, 0, null, 'zQo-dqekGP0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zQo-dqekGP0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 53, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1558, 5, 'Verses sometimes used to support the idea that our everlasting future is in Heaven', '<p>To a large degree, it is the failure to understand the cultural context of the Bible, as well as the scope of Scripture and the context of specific verses, that has resulted in some verses being misinterpreted and used to support the idea that heaven is the ultimate home of believers. The purpose of this article is to examine these &ldquo;difficult&rdquo; verses in the light of the scope of the entire Bible, the context of the verse in question, the translation of the Greek or Hebrew text, and the culture and customs of the time in order to bring their true meaning to light.</p>', '2016-12-01', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/verses-sometimes-used-to-support-the-idea-that-our-everlasting-future-is-in-heaven', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/everlasting_future_heaven.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 12, null),
(1559, 5, 'What was Jesus really saying to the malefactor in Luke 23:43?', '<p>Luke 23:42 and 43 is often used to teach that the penitent malefactor who believed in Jesus immediately went to &ldquo;heaven&rdquo; when he died (even though the verse in question reads &ldquo;paradise&rdquo;). However, the phrase in verse 43, &ldquo;I tell you the truth today,&rdquo; was a common Hebrew idiom used to emphasize the solemnity and importance of an occasion or moment</p>', '2015-07-01', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-was-jesus-really-saying-to-the-malefactor-in-luke-2343', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/malefactor-.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1561, 1, 'The Book of Ruth | Ruth and Boaz (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching continues a multi-part exposition of the Book of Ruth. There are some wonderful practical sessions in this section of Ruth as it reveals the bitterness of Naomi, the largess of Boaz, the diligence and sterling character of Ruth, and the invisible hand of God in blessing His people.</p> <p>Verses: Ruth 1:19-21; 2:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:36', 53, 2, 'generosity', 'EIHcU4o6EvI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EIHcU4o6EvI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1562, 1, 'Fasting Part 1 - An Introduction to Fasting', '<p>This teaching provides an introduction to fasting in the Bible. It explores why God commanded it in the Mosaic Law, why the prophets sometimes encouraged it, why the Jews added fast days to the calendar, and some of the benefits of fasting.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 16:29-31; Acts 27:9; Joel 1:13-14; Matt. 9:14-15; Luke 18:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-08-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:27', 0, 0, null, 'LYiZtabV9fc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LYiZtabV9fc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1563, 1, 'Uniquely Equipped', '<p>This teaching briefly explores the truth that God has uniquely equipped each of us with gifts, talents and abilities that empower us to glorify Him, honor our Lord Jesus, and serve the people around us.</p> <p>Verses:  Eph. 4:8; 1 Pet. 4:10; Rom. 12:1-8; Matt. 11:29-30</p> <p>Teacher:  Janet Speakes</p>', '2020-08-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '14:42', 0, 0, 'Body, renewed, humility, whole-hearted', 'EiZedanSbsg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EiZedanSbsg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1564, 5, 'The Bible: You Can Believe It!', '<p>The Bible is the best selling book of all time.</p> <p>It has been a source of strength and hope for countless numbers of people through the ages. While there have always been critics of the Bible, since the mid-1800s it has come under increasing attack, especially from scholars.</p>', '2013-08-05', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-bible-you-can-believe-it', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/the-bible-you-can-believe-it.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 13, null),
(1565, 5, 'What does the Bible say about &ldquo;Holy Communion&rdquo;?', '<p><strong>FAQ:</strong> I am confused about what many churches call &ldquo;Holy Communion.&rdquo; Why is there so much discrepancy in how different churches do it? Some use bread, others use wafers; some use wine, others use grape juice; some do it daily, others do it weekly, yearly, etc. What does the Bible say about taking Holy Communion and the Communion Service?</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-holy-communion', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 23, null),
(1566, 5, 'Defending Dispensationalism: Standing Fast in the Liberty', '<p>In recent years, a storm of controversy has arisen around a system of biblical interpretation called &ldquo;Dispensationalism,&rdquo; which the author believes is grounded in the biblical truth that there are only three distinct groups of human beings on earth today-Jew, Gentile and the Church of God, also known as &ldquo;the Body of Christ&rdquo; or &ldquo;Christians&rdquo; (1 Cor. 10:32).</p> <p>There is only one God, but He gave different rules at different times for people to live by. Dispensationalism is a way to understand these changes, and thus to better understand the purposes of God and how we are supposed to live today. Every Christian is aware that God no longer requires animal sacrifices, but few realize the radical extent of the changes that took place at Pentecost, the birthday of the Christian Church.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/defending-dispensationalism-standing-fast-in-the-liberty', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 13, null),
(1567, 5, 'Covenants and Dispensations', '<p>In addition to a topical or historical approach, it&rsquo;s also very helpful for us to understand that covenants are an important part of the Bible. A covenant is a legally binding agreement, and those found in the Bible are a big key to understanding God&rsquo;s actions throughout history. By understanding the various covenants in the Bible we can see how, since the time of Adam, God has progressively revealed aspects of His plans and purposes.</p>', '2018-03-26', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/covenants-and-dispensations', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/covenents-and-dispensations.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 13, null),
(1568, 5, 'How does one arrive at a Dispensational view of Scripture?', '<p>It is our opinion that dispensational understanding is the logical conclusion that is reached when viewing the biblical data through the &ldquo;lens&rdquo; of the following specific principles or ideals:...</p> <p>Upholding these ideals will help us navigate through the challenging waters ahead as we endeavor to discern God&rsquo;s purposes, plans and programs for the salvation, redemption and sanctification of all His people for all eternity. This is the domain of Dispensationalism.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/how-does-one-arrive-at-a-dispensational-view-of-scripture', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/dispensational_view_of_scripture.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1569, 1, 'All for His Glory!', '<p>This brief sharing is an encouragement to bring all that we are, our gifts, talents, and abilities, empowered by God&rsquo;s gift of holy spirit into all that we do in dedication to the glory of God.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:19-25; Col. 3:17-24; 1 Thes. 5:23 </p> <p>Teacher:  Janet Speakes</p>', '2020-08-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '10:21', 0, 0, 'consecration', 'NCJvlRrV2ic', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NCJvlRrV2ic/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1570, 1, 'Fasting Part 2 - Fasting, Prayer and Relationship', '<p>This teaching builds on Part 1, emphasizing from Isaiah 58 that fasting is about the heart behind it, not the activity itself. Fasting is to be done with a humble heart and true desire to be aligned with God. Where fasting occurs in the Bible, prayer is coupled with it, and the same heart of humility and godliness is required for our prayers to be effective.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 58:1-11; Job 35:12, 13; Matt. 6:1-13, 16-18; 1 Tim. 2:8</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2020-08-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:48', 0, 0, null, 'dODOIo8QKxQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dODOIo8QKxQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1571, 1, 'Do Not Fear What They Fear', '<p>We are all affected by what we see and hear. There is a multitude of influences coming at us every day from the news and media, and most of them are negative and tend to produce fear and worry. But instead of listening to the voices of the world, God encourages us to not look around at what everyone else is saying but to hearken to his words and to trust in him.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 8:11-13</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-08-27', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:04', 0, 0, 'anxiety', '7vEz1ToUZbM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7vEz1ToUZbM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1572, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 27 | Hard Work Will Be Rewarded', '<p>The reward of hard work is not more work (as the popular saying goes), but rather being able to enjoy the fruit of one&rsquo;s labor. Hard work might not seem pleasant in the moment; it requires exertion, dedication, and much time. But all that effort is not lost or sacrificed for nothing. There is an exchange that happens when we work hard, and wisdom tells us that the perseverance and steadfast commitment to see things through to the end is worth it.</p> <p>Illustration: Tim Cook, the successor of Steve Job&rsquo;s at Apple in 2011</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 27:18; Gen. 39:2-6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-08-26', 'Castos', 0, '14:34', 9, 27, 'prize, faithfulness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-27-Hard-Work-Will-Be-Rewarded-Prov.-27.18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-27-hard-work-will-be-rewarded-prov-2718', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1573, 5, 'The Sacred Secret: God&rsquo;s Gift to Us', '<p>For ages God kept a Sacred Secret. He did not tell anyone (or even give any hints) about His secret until after the death of His Son, Jesus (1 Cor. 2:9). Now, however, He has revealed it to mankind (1 Cor. 2:10; Eph. 3:5; etc.). Why did God keep His secret until after Jesus died? Because what God has given us today was so crucial to His overall plan for mankind that if Satan and his demons had known about it, <strong>they would not have crucified Jesus</strong>.</p>', '2013-01-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-sacred-secret-gods-gift-to-us', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 11, null),
(1574, 5, 'Why Does the Bible Have Two Genealogies of Jesus That Seem to Contradict?', '<p>The Bible calls Jesus Christ &ldquo;the son of David&rdquo; (Matt. 1:1). However, determining the genealogy from Jesus back to David has been a source of controversy (difficulty) for centuries. What we will see as we study this subject is that the gospel of Matthew contains the genealogy from David to Jesus via his mother Mary, while the gospel of Luke contains the genealogy from David to Jesus via his adopted father, Joseph.</p>', '2013-08-26', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/why-does-the-bible-have-two-genealogies-of-jesus-that-seem-to-contradict', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/two_genealogies.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 27, null),
(1575, 5, 'Agricultural Life—Peasants', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Two of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>When it is mentioned that French railway cars bringing wheat from the rich plain south of Damascus are now supplanting the camels that used to do it, that an American engineer is sinking Artesian wells at Sidon for irrigating the land, and that every summer English steamers lie off Gaza loading barley for Scotland, the suspicion naturally arises that the farmer of Palestine has left the shepherd behind,</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 5, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/agricultural-life-peasants', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/agricultural_life_peasants.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1576, 5, 'The Lord&rsquo;s Prayer (Matthew 6)', '<p>I have a manual grain mill. That means I buy my wheat and other grains in kernel form from a farmer in New York and grind them into flour by hand. What that further means is that I have between 30 and 45 minutes of round-and-round-and-round-and-round to do, left hand, right hand, both hands, any and every time I need flour for breads and biscuits. So what that ultimately means is that I have a lot of time early in the mornings when I am grinding that I have to figure out what to do with my thoughts. If you&rsquo;ve ever done a manual, repetitive job such as that, you know that the discipline it takes mentally to keep going can be quite a challenge.</p>', '2013-09-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-lords-prayer-matthew-6', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/lords_prayer.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1577, 1, 'Get Involved in Government', '<p>This teaching begins in Genesis and goes through several records in the Bible, including the New Testament, to show that God allows people to run their own governments, and thus we need to be involved in putting those governments in place to ensure they protect people&rsquo;s freedoms.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 9:1-6; Num. 11:14-17; Acts 6:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:18', 0, 0, 'voting, leaders', 'PBZwSoXkqfc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PBZwSoXkqfc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1578, 1, 'It&rsquo;s Your Government; Get Involved', '<p>Many people believe Christians should not get involved in politics. However, governments are composed of people, and those people make decisions that can have a huge impact on people&rsquo;s lives. This teaching covers the value of being involved with government, even if it is just prayer and voting, and gives examples from the Bible of God giving people the responsibility to govern themselves.</p> <p>Verses:  Gen. 9:6; Num. 11:16; Acts 6:1-4; 1 Sam. 8:10-17</p> <p>Teacher: John  Schoenheit </p>', '2020-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '17:45', 0, 0, 'elections leaders', 'SKXMpMKA6GY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SKXMpMKA6GY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1579, 1, 'Energize Giftings with the Hope', '<p>The future kingdom was a big motivator in Jesus&rsquo; life, enough so for him to go to the cross. As imitators of him, the same hope of the future kingdom can motivate us too. Let&rsquo;s use it to energize our spiritual walk!</p> <p>Verses:  Hebrews 12:1-3; Luke 8:1; Luke 9:1-2; Acts 1:3; Isaiah 65:17-23; Genesis 49:10; Psalm 110:1-2; 132:11; Matthew 16:28; 1 Corinthians 11:1; Jeremiah 3:15; 1 Thessalonians 4:15-17</p> <p>Teacher: Michelle Ruth</p>', '2020-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:01', 0, 0, 'joy, obedience', 's21cQe7-9qg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/s21cQe7-9qg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1580, 5, 'Religion in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Six of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>Religion is the great fact of Eastern life. &ldquo;&hellip;of him, and through him, and to him, are all things&hellip;&rdquo; (Rom. 11:36)&mdash;this is the acclamation of everything that lives in the East. Christianity, Judaism, and Islam have many deep distinctions, but they are all one with the regard to the existence and power of God. In the East, to be without religion is not an intellectual viewpoint, it is a moral void.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 12, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/religion-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/religion_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 4, null),
(1581, 5, 'Eastern Villages in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Six of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>Thick, high walls and fortified gates do not pose much of a deterrent to modern armies, but in the biblical era they were very effective, even against large, well equipped armies. For example, it took the Assyrians three years to break into the city of Samaria (2 Kings 17:5).</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 11, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/eastern-villages-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/eastern_villages_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1582, 5, 'Female Dress in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Four of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>The under dress and gown coat of women resembled those of men, and their upper robe corresponded to the suits of apparel or festival robes of men. These are referred to in 2 Samuel 13:18; Song of Solomon 5:3; Isaiah 3:22 and 23. There is still this resemblance in costume, the women&rsquo;s garments being, however, generally longer in proportion to the figure.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 8, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/female-dress-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/female_dress_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 4, null),
(1584, 5, 'Pottery in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Three of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>(A) <em>Its usefulness</em>. In the East the fragility of the pottery, the expensiveness of copper vessels, and the unsuitableness of leather bottles for many of the requirements of town and village life, creates a large and constant demand for the potter&rsquo;s goods. Earthenware jars are also preferred for holding drinking water, because the evaporation from the porous substance helps to keep the water cool. In the warm East it is a point of courtesy to give &ldquo;&hellip;a cup of cold water&hellip;&rdquo; (Matt. 10:42).</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 7, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/pottery-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/pottery_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 4, null),
(1585, 5, 'Day Laborers in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Three of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>Every Eastern town has a well-known place where men congregate at dawn and wait to be engaged in manual labor for the day. Such labor includes gardening, ditching, repairing walls, whitewashing, and lifting and carrying burdens.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 6, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/day-laborers-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/day_laborers_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1586, 5, 'Landscapes in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter One of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>When Palestine is seen for the first time, the eye is charmed with the bright distinctness of everything and with the beautiful blue of sea and sky. Then comes a feeling of disappointment as favorite features of beautiful scenery in other lands are looked for in vain. There are no farm houses dotting the landscape; no fields of grass, no horses or cattle grazing at liberty; no forests are visible; the lakes lie low in the Jordan Valley; the rivers are small, and the brooks are dry in summer. Where are the cedars, vines, fig trees, and the beauty of the olive? Is this the Promised Land? Was this the inheritance of the chosen people?</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 3, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/landscapes-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/landscapes_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 13, null),
(1587, 5, 'Why Read a Customs Book?', '<p>[This article was taken from Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>When you meet someone for the first time and therefore do not know much about him, there is a natural distance between the two of you. Friendships develop over time. In order for you to more intimately know the person, and eventually become a friend, it is important to know about him and his life. Where does he live? What does he do for work? Is he married? Does he have children? What does he do when he has time off? What are his attitudes about life?</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 1, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/why-read-a-customs-book', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/why_read_a_customs_book.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1588, 5, 'Home Life in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Five of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>If Jesus asked most Westerners to <strong>pick up your bed, and walk</strong>, they could not do it. Our beds are far too big and bulky. However, the beds of the biblical culture were usually thin mattresses stuffed with cotton or wool. Sometimes they were only layers of blankets. Therefore, they were easy to carry, as the record in John 5 indicates, and they were easy to roll up for storage, as the illustration at the top of the article shows.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 10, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/home-life-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/home_life_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1589, 5, 'Family Life in the Bible', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Five of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>In every land the home is the nursery of all that is best and most beautiful in human life. In Syria and Palestine there is no curse of alcohol and drunkenness to deaden and destroy natural feelings, and the parental devotion of the poorest is as happy and self-denying as that of the rich and refined. Nothing bewilders and shocks the Eastern mind more than the paragraphs of police news that are sometimes copied from English into Arabic and contain stories about the desertion and ill-treatment of children by their parents. Occasionally an infant is laid by night at the door of a convent or boarding school, but almost universally a child born into the poorest home is welcomed as a gift from God.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 9, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/family-life-in-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/family_life_in_the_bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1590, 5, 'Pastoral Life—Shepherds', '<p>[This article was taken from Chapter Two of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>In Matthew 13:3, Jesus began his parable with, &ldquo;&hellip;Behold, a sower went forth to sow.&rdquo; Unlike our farmers in the West who plow first then sow the seed, in the biblical culture the sower went before the plowman, who came after the sower and covered the seed that had been sown. The seed sown by the path was not covered, so the birds came and ate it (Matt. 13:4). If the sower had followed the plowman, the seed sown in the field would not have been covered and the birds would have eaten it just as they ate the seed by the path.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 4, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/pastoral-life-shepherds', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/pastoral_life_shepherds.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 4, null),
(1591, 5, 'Introduction: Bible Manners & Customs', '<p>[This article was taken from the introduction of Bible Manners &amp; Customs by Rev. G.M. Mackie, M.A, 1898 (which we have revised and reprinted)].</p> <p>The above illustration shows skin-bottles, and one large earthenware jar, in the corner of a house. Skin-bottles were made from animal skins and used to contain different liquids in biblical times, including water, wine, and milk (more on skin bottles in Chapter 4). They were often hung on hooks or nails on the wall of the houses, or on the posts of a tent. Over time, the smoke from the fire in the house would dry them out, turn them black, and cover them with soot.</p>', '2013-08-13', null, 0, null, 61, 2, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/introduction-bible-manners-and-customs', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/introduction_bible_manners_customs.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1592, 5, 'Misapplied Texts: 1 Samuel 26:8-11', '<p><strong>Touch not the Lord&rsquo;s anointed</strong></p> <p>People who support the idea that God should be the one to punish murderers often refer to the record of David and Saul, in which Abishai, one of David&rsquo;s men, wanted to kill King Saul, but David restrained him.</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/misapplied-texts-1-samuel-268-11', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1_samuel_26_8-11.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1593, 5, 'Misapplied Texts: Matthew 7:1', '<p><strong>Do not judge, or you too will be judged.</strong></p> <p>One of the basic keys to correctly understanding and interpreting Scripture is that no verse in the Bible can contradict any other verse. This is a basic rule of interpretation. God&rsquo;s Word, as He originally gave it, contains no errors or contradictions. The Bible is &ldquo;truth&rdquo; and truth is not inherently contradictory. There are many clear scriptures that tell Christians to make judgments. We have to judge both people and doctrine in order to live godly and safe lives.</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/misapplied-texts-matthew-71', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matthew_7_1.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1594, 5, 'Misapplied Texts: Luke 6:29', '<p><strong>If someone strikes you on one cheek, turn the other to him.</strong></p> <p>This verse is not talking about the death penalty or any other type of civil crime or punishment for crimes. Interestingly, people who quote this verse as saying there should not be a death penalty do not seem to grasp that the verse is saying there should not be any kind of retribution at all. If this verse were applied universally to the criminal justice system, it would mean no fines, no jails and not even any community service. Surely even the most liberal of people do not believe that we can have a safe society and enforce no laws at all!</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/misapplied-texts-luke-629/?tot=redirect', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/luke_6_29.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 4, null),
(1595, 5, 'Misapplied Texts: Matthew 26:52', '<p><strong>Put your sword back in its place,&rdquo; Jesus said to him, &ldquo;for all who draw the sword will die by the sword.</strong></p> <p>This verse is a condemnation of self-willed aggression. It has nothing to do with self-defense or the proper use of the criminal justice system. Earlier that same day, Jesus had told the disciples to buy a sword if they did not have one. &ldquo;He [Jesus] said to them, &lsquo;But now if you have a purse, take it, and also a bag; and if you don&rsquo;t have a sword, sell your cloak and buy one&rsquo;&rdquo; (Luke 22:36). Obviously, Jesus would not tell people in the afternoon to go buy a sword if they did not have one, and then late that night teach that if they used the sword they had bought they would die by it.</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/misapplied-texts-matthew-2652', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matthew_26_52.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 5, null),
(1596, 5, 'Misapplied Texts: John 8:1-11', '<p>The record of the woman caught in adultery is often quoted to show that Christ forgave criminals, and so that is what we should do in our society. However, there is reason to doubt that the woman was really deserving of death. It is easy to prove that the religious leaders who brought her to Jesus were not interested in justice. In the first place, Jesus was not a judge in that society, especially not of capital cases. That was left to the Sanhedrin, the ruling counsel of the Jews. Therefore Jesus had no authority to render judgment on the case.</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/misapplied-texts-john-81-11', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/john_8_1-11.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 2, null),
(1598, 1, 'Living by Trust', '<p>This teaching is an encouragement to live by trust in God&rsquo;s ability to bring His prophetic Word to pass. We grow in trust by developing an intimate relationship with Yahweh and Jesus Christ. Learning to understand the prophetic nature of God&rsquo;s written Word and developing an intimate prayer life with Him and His Son, the Living Word, helps us to stand fast during turbulent seasons of life.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:16-17; Gal. 3:11; Heb. 10:38; Hab. 1-3; James 5:16; 1Tim. 2:4</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2020-09-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:07', 0, 0, 'faith, prophecy, praise', 'X7uqZLGNS1A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X7uqZLGNS1A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1599, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 28 | Don''t Seek to Get Rich Quick', '<p>Yahweh designed us to work, and there is an inherent pleasure in honest, hard work. Those who understand this will find life more fulfilling and satisfying. If we are faithful as trustworthy and reliable workers, Yahweh will bless the work of our hands and will provide what we need. Honoring Yahweh with our integrity and character and being content with the blessings he bestows upon us is of greater value than all the money in the world.</p> <p>Illustration: Charles Ponzi, professional con artist and inventor of the &ldquo;Ponzi Scheme&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 28:20</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-09-08', 'Castos', 0, '14:23', 9, 28, 'riches, wealth', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-28-Don-t-Seek-to-Get-Rich-Quick-Prov.-28.20-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-28-dont-seek-to-get-rich-quick-prov-2820', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1600, 1, 'Nehemiah – A Portrait of Courage, Wisdom, Revelation and Perseverance', '<p>This teaching surveys the first 8 chapters of the Book of Nehemiah, including an overview of the historical context, with special emphasis on the character of Nehemiah, the quality of his leadership, and his keen focus on his godly mission. Threaded throughout these chapters are &ldquo;gem phrases&rdquo; that reveal Nehemiah&rsquo;s courage, wisdom, revelation, and perseverance.</p> <p>Verses: Nehemiah 1-8</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2020-09-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:35', 0, 0, null, 's6hOHfIdwFk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/s6hOHfIdwFk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1601, 1, 'God Calls Moses out of Midian', '<p>This teaching details how Yahweh pursued Moses and positioned him to bring deliverance to the captive children of Israel, which Moses tried to begin some 40 years prior but was rejected by his brothers. The example of Yahweh&rsquo;s willingness to work with Moses to the end he got back in the game and got the job done is an encouragement to us all to &ldquo;consider one another, to spur one another on to love and good works.&rdquo; </p> <p>Verses: Heb. 10:24; Exod. 3-4 </p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:49', 0, 0, 'redemption, calling', 'Nex8t64zEXY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Nex8t64zEXY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1602, 1, 'Vessels of Mercy', '<p>Performing our functions in the Body of Christ is directly related to our understanding and application of the mercy and blessings of God. How you see yourself as a vessel of mercy for others will determine your effectiveness in how you impact those around you. By embracing the benefits of our salvation, we acquire the spiritual strength needed to fulfill our individual functions in the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:15, 16; Rom. 9:22-24, 12:1-5; 1 Cor. 15:9-11; 2 Cor. 4:1-7; Eph. 3:7-10; Col. 3:12-15; 1 Tim. 1:12-16; 1 Pet. 1:3-7, 13; 1 Pet. 4:10; Jude 21</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Bolen</p>', '2020-09-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:57', 0, 0, 'Service, Love, Endurance', '7vZWoqCfx84', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7vZWoqCfx84/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1603, 1, 'God is Not the One Causing Your Suffering', '<p>Life can be tough, even bad at times, but God is not the one making life difficult for us; it is caused by God&rsquo;s enemy, the Devil. We have one of two choices to make: either abandon God and become bitter, or we can understand why life is the way it is and continue to trust in God through it all. In the Bible, Job and Naomi offer two different responses to going through tough times in life.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 5:19; John 12:31; Acts 10:38; Judg. 2:11-13; Acts 14:21-22; John 16:33; Heb. 11:36-38; Job 1:20-22; 2:7-10; Luke 10:17-18, 23-24; Ruth 1:13, 20; Rom. 8:28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-11', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '24:20', 0, 0, 'evil, warfare, demons, suffering, affliction, hardship', '2L-66Yy7gXQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2L-66Yy7gXQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1604, 1, 'The Importance of Praise', '<p>Throughout the Bible there are records of God&rsquo;s people giving praise to Him. This teaching covers some aspects of why God wants us to praise Him and why He is worthy of our praise. As Christians, in our prayers, we should not neglect giving praise to our Heavenly Father for all He has done and will do in the future.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 16:1-3, 23-30; 2 Chron. 20:1-30; Ps. 9:1-2, 11; 18:1-14; 33:1; 69:34; 79:13; 92:1-2; 139:14; Matt. 11:25; Eph. 1:3-14; Rev. 4:6ff; Acts 2:11; 10:46; 1 Cor. 14:16-17</p> <p>Teacher:  Rob Woods</p>', '2020-09-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:24', 0, 0, 'worship', 'Es-eC5rY5kE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Es-eC5rY5kE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1605, 1, 'Standing in Difficult Times', '<p>This teaching highlights events that occurred in the last days of the Kingdom of Judah. Jeremiah the prophet was caught up in the events of that time and had to stand fast against the ungodliness and hard-heartedness of that time.</p> <p>Verses: Jeremiah 29:1-14; 39:1-10; 41:16-19; 42:1-22; 43:1-7; 44:15-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:20', 0, 0, 'righteousness', 'f5IoG8QQG3U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f5IoG8QQG3U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1606, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/13/2020) - Division', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-09-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:05', 0, 0, null, 'wMFBh9TfQng', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wMFBh9TfQng/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 2, null),
(1607, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/30/2020) - Christian Leadership', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Gabe and Emily Hickman. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-09-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:53', 0, 0, null, 'M79ukXmiM9s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/M79ukXmiM9s/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 2, null),
(1608, 1, 'Knowing Who People Are by Their Fruit', '<p>In Matthew 7, Jesus tells us that we are to know who people are by the fruit that they produce. This teaching explains what Jesus meant when he said that we are to know people by their fruit and how it relates to our modern-day political process and choosing good leaders.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:15-20, Jer. 41:16-17; 42:1-7; 42:10; 42:19; 43:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:39', 0, 0, 'teachers prophets', 'h-oVCjzqs4M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/h-oVCjzqs4M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1609, 5, 'What is True Baptism?', '<p>When you read the title of this article and saw the word &ldquo;baptism,&rdquo; did you immediately think about water?</p> <p>If so, your response is like that of the vast majority of Christians. But the question we must ask is why the word &ldquo;baptize,&rdquo; which actually means &ldquo;to dip&rdquo; or &ldquo;to immerse,&rdquo; has become almost solely associated with water, when, biblically speaking, there are other &ldquo;liquid&rdquo; alternatives to be considered?</p>', '2013-12-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-true-baptism-book', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/true_baptism.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 46, null),
(1610, 5, 'The Last Week of Christ&rsquo;s Life', '<p>[The following article is an edited transcription of our audio teaching, <a href="https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-last-week-of-christs-life" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Audio Teaching">The Last Week of Christ&rsquo;s Life</a> by John Schoenheit.]</p> <p>Hello and God bless you!</p> <p>I am John Schoenheit, and I will be teaching on The Last Week of Christ&rsquo;s Life. Please turn with me in your Bible to 1 Corinthians chapter 5, verse 7.</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>1 Corinthians 5:7</strong><br /> Get rid of the old yeast, that you may be a new batch without yeast&mdash;as you really are. For Christ, our Passover lamb, has been sacrificed.</p> </blockquote>', '2013-08-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-last-week-of-christs-life', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/last_week_christs_life.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1611, 5, 'Eloi, Eloi, Lama Sabachthani – My God, My God, Why Have You Forsaken Me?', '<p>[The following article is an edited transcription of our audio teaching on Matthew 27:46 &ldquo;<a href="https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/my-god-my-god-why-have-you-forsaken-me" target="_blank">Eloi, Eloi, Lama Sabachthani &ndash; My God, My God, Why Have You Forsaken Me?</a>&rdquo; by John W. Schoenheit.]</p> <p>Q: Why Did God Forsake Jesus on the Cross? I have heard it taught it was because Jesus became sin for us and God cannot stand sin. Is this true?</p> <p>A: We do not believe that God forsook Jesus on the cross. The following transcription will cover this question in great detail.</p>', '2013-08-14', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/eloi-eloi-lama-sabachthani-my-god-my-god-why-have-you-forsaken-me', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jesus_forsaken.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1612, 5, 'Did God Really Forsake Jesus Christ on the Cross?', '<p><strong>Matthew 27:46</strong><br /> About the ninth hour Jesus cried out in a loud voice, &ldquo;Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani,&rdquo;&mdash;which means, &ldquo;My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?&rdquo;</p> <p>These words that Jesus cried out as he was hanging on the Cross have been a source of much confusion and debate among Christians through the years. Some teach that Jesus became sin, God cannot look on sin, and thus God forsook His Son. Others, citing the following verses, say that God did not forsake His Son when he needed Him the most:</p>', '2013-08-16', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/did-god-really-forsake-jesus-christ-on-the-cross', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/god_forsake_jesus_on_cross.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1613, 5, 'Developing a Proper Understanding of the Bible', '<p>Have you ever been so busy that instead of taking the time to call and speak directly to a coworker or friend, you sent off a short reply in an email or text message&mdash;but then your brief message was misunderstood and even caused the other person to be offended? The message may have been accurate, but your brevity came at a high price because the other person mistook it for anger or condescension and may have even misinterpreted your words.</p>', '2018-03-05', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/developing-a-proper-understanding', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/developing-a-proper-understanding.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1614, 5, 'Should we question the Bible?', '<p>Questioning is a normal and healthy part of learning. Every teacher I know loves students who ask questions, because it shows they are interested and learning. God certainly does not mind when we ask Him questions. Furthermore, God has answers to our questions. The Bible is full of answers on all kinds of subjects. God gave us a command to love Him with all our heart, soul, mind, and strength (Mark 12:30).</p>', '2013-08-08', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/should-we-question-the-bible', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Should-we-Question-The-Bible.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1615, 5, 'What does the Bible say about Lust?', '<p>[This article was taken from our book Sex and Scripture: A Biblical Study of Proper Sexual Behavior.]</p> <p>It is not always only outward behavior that is sin. Sexual lust is also sinful in the sight of God. God gives people the ability to think and to control their thoughts and desires. The option to think and desire either good or evil is very clear in the Greek text, because most words for &ldquo;desire&rdquo; can describe ei&shy;ther good or bad desires. It is the context that determines the nature of the desire. Thus, in most versions, <em>orexis</em> is translated &ldquo;lust&rdquo; in Romans 1:27: &ldquo;&hellip;men also abandoned natural relations with women and were inflamed with lust (<em>orexis</em>) for one another.&rdquo; Spiros Zodhiates defines <em>orexis</em> as: &ldquo;Appetite, lust or concupiscence. It is always the reaching out after an object with the purpose of drawing it to oneself and appropriating it.&rdquo;</p>', '2013-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-lust', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lust.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 49, null),
(1616, 5, 'A Christian&rsquo;s Response to Immodesty', '<p>Modesty is one of the most widely-discussed topics in Christianity&hellip;probably because no one can come down hard and fast on a sure biblical line where dress code is concerned. Some churches won&rsquo;t let people show up in less than a shirt and a tie, or a dress; others don&rsquo;t care if you come in a bikini top and Daisy Dukes, so long as you actually get there. But one thing that&rsquo;s pretty universally understood&mdash;by Christians and non-Christians alike&mdash; is that, outside of the confines of the house, where one is free to dress however one wants&hellip;apparel standards are changing.</p>', '2018-07-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/a-christians-response-to-immodesty', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/A-Christians-Response-to-Immodesty.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 10, null),
(1617, 5, 'What does the Bible say about Adultery?', '<p>[This article was taken from our book Sex and Scripture: A Biblical Study of Proper Sexual Behavior.]</p> <p>The Greek word used in the New Testament for an adulterer is <em>moichos</em> (adultery is <em>mocheia</em>) and it refers to someone who is married but having sexual intercourse with someone other than his or her spouse. In the Old Testament, and in both the secular Greek and Roman worlds, the definition of adultery was different.</p>', '2013-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-adultery', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/adultery.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 90, null),
(1618, 5, 'Does Divorce Disqualify Someone From Ministry?', '<p>There is an ongoing debate among Christians as to whether or not a Christian minister should be allowed to divorce&mdash;or if a divorced person can still minister in a corporate capacity. The Bible says ministers are to be &ldquo;the husband of one wife&rdquo; (1 Tim. 3:2), and some Christians believe that if you are divorced, whether you are remarried or not, you are no longer &ldquo;the husband of one wife.&rdquo; But does this phrase mean &ldquo;not divorced?&rdquo; No, it does not. Primarily it forbids polygamy, but perhaps as importantly it refers to being &ldquo;a one-woman man.&rdquo;</p>', '2019-03-25', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/does-divorce-disqualify-someone-from-ministry-2', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Does-Divorce-Disqualify-Someone-From-Ministry.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 33, null),
(1619, 5, '1 Corinthians 7 (Abstinence, Celibacy, Cohabitation, and Marriage)', '<p>[This article was taken from our book Sex and Scripture: A Biblical Study of Proper Sexual Behavior.]</p> <p>1 Corinthians 7 contains some of the clearest teaching in the Bible concern&shy;ing abstinence before marriage, celibacy, sexual intercourse inside and outside of marriage, and sexual obligations. The people of Corinth were interested in proper sexual behavior and had written to the Apostle Paul about it. By revelation, he answered their questions.</p>', '2013-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/1-corinthians-7-abstinence-celibacy-cohabitation-and-marriage', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/1_corinthians_7.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 54, null),
(1620, 5, 'Who is the Bride of Christ?', '<p>God has always been devoted to His people, and He wants His people to be devoted to Him. One of the ways God expresses the obligation His people have to Him, and the love and devotion they should show Him, is by referring to them as His &ldquo;daughter,&rdquo; &ldquo;wife,&rdquo; &ldquo;bride,&rdquo; or other similar terms. However, these terms have been the source of a lot of confusion. For example, there is a lot of misinformation in Christianity about the &ldquo;Bride of Christ.&rdquo; Some people believe the Church is the &ldquo;Bride of Christ.&rdquo; Others believe Israel is. Still others believe all the saved people of all time make up the Bride.</p>', '2014-09-03', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/who-is-the-bride-of-christ', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/who-is-the-bride-of-christ.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 21, null);
