(1621, 5, 'What about the other requirements of the Law? Sabbath worship, tithing, circumcision, water baptism (or ritual washing), kosher dietary laws, worship, high priests, special clothing, feast days, etc.', '<p><strong>Are any of these things required for the Church? Are we better Christians if we continue to practice some or all of these things?</strong></p> <p>These are important questions to answer, especially in light of the seemingly growing numbers of Christians participating in what is called &ldquo;Messianic Judaism.&rdquo; Our answer is &ldquo;No, these things are not required for the Church&rdquo; (Acts 15:10 and 11; Rom. 10:4; Gal. 2:14-16, 3:21-25, et al). Furthermore, the Church is neither &ldquo;better off&rdquo; nor &ldquo;more sacred&rdquo; when it adopts practices that God has not prescribed for it.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-about-the-other-requirements-of-the-law-sabbath-worship-tithing-circumcision-water-baptism-or-ritual-washing-kosher-dietary-laws-worship-high-priests-special-clot', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/what_about_the_other_requirements_of_the_law.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 17, null),
(1622, 5, 'Creation or Evolution, What&rsquo;s the Big Deal?', '<p>I was raised in a Christian home, and I do not really recall the topic of evolution or creationism ever being discussed. In the Christian school I attended, my classmates and I just assumed that because the Bible said God created the world, it was true. It was not until I attended high school, especially biology class, that the subject of evolution was presented to me as fact. I remember questioning some of the concepts, but I guess I reasoned that there was some way to reconcile the two approaches.</p>', '2013-08-05', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/creation-or-evolution-whats-the-big-deal', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/creation_evolution_big_deal.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1623, 5, 'The Creation – Evolution Controversy – Free Online Bible Study Seminar', '<p>A 6-hour seminar that exposes the fallacious Theory of Evolution for what it is &ndash; a religion, and not a science.</p> <p>The bottom line of the frontal assault on the integrity of God&rsquo;s Word is Satan&rsquo;s original lie: &ldquo;You shall be as gods.&rdquo;</p> <p>This seminar defines the classical Darwinian Theory of Evolution and shows that it is absolutely unscientific from every angle, being totally contradicted by mathematics, genetics, thermo-dynamics, anthropology, geology, biology, zoology and the fossil record.</p>', '2013-05-17', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/seminars/the-creation-evolution-controversy', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/seminar-the-creation.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1624, 1, 'Weathering the Storms of Life', '<p>How do we deal with unexpected events, trials and hardships in our lives? This teaching explores three things that we can do: 1) trust that God is always with us in every situation, 2) build our lives on a firm foundation, and 3) grow deep roots.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 23; Matthew 7:24-27; Matthew 13:1-9, 18-23; 1 Thessalonians 3:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2020-09-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:48', 0, 0, null, 'XZd5CQ1wXCM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XZd5CQ1wXCM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1625, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Paul&rsquo;s Visit to Thessalonica (Part 1)', '<p>When God told Paul in a vision to travel to Macedonia, one of the cities he visited was Thessalonica. The good news was received by many Jews and eventually many Gentiles as well. Unfortunately, due to antagonism from Jewish leaders, Paul was forced to leave the city prematurely. Not too long after he left, he wrote a letter to the believers in Thessalonica. This letter is 1 Thessalonians.</p> <p>Verses:  Acts 17:1-13</p> <p>Teachers:  Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-09-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:17', 54, 1, 'historical, background, chronology', 'g-jBSaKD_EA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/g-jBSaKD_EA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 10, null),
(1626, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/06/2020) - Communicating as an Ambassador', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p> <p>This teaching is by Tim Scholten</p>', '2020-09-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:59', 0, 0, null, 'My3BpEXTBf0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/My3BpEXTBf0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active, Gabe''s fellowship', 1, 1, null),
(1627, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 29 | The Future Can Be Fickle', '<p>The wise person doesn&rsquo;t boast about the future plans they have. Instead, they live day by day, trusting in Yahweh and the plans that he is bringing about in their life. While the future is unknown to us, Yahweh knows what is ahead and he will provide and take care of his people regardless of what happens tomorrow. Who else can we trust in concerning the uncertainty of the future except Yahweh our God?</p> <p>Illustration: Company Direct Forex Signals and its attempts to rope in investors with promises about the future and a return on investment.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 27:1; 1 Kgs 20:1-12; James 4:13-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-09-22', 'Castos', 0, '19:29', 9, 29, 'wisdom, patience, boast, plan, preparation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-29-The-Future-Can-Be-Fickle-Prov.-27.1-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-29-the-future-can-be-fickle-prov-271', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1628, 1, 'God Has Called Us to the Body of Christ', '<p>The Bible makes it clear that God created us to use our spiritual gifts and callings within the Body of Christ. This teaching discusses how when we each walk out our gifts and support others in using theirs, we strengthen the Body of Christ to the praise of God&rsquo;s glory.</p> <p>Verses: Col. 1:25-27; Eph. 3:7-12, 17-19; Eph. 4:15-16; 1 Cor. 12:4-11; Rom. 12:4-15; Eph. 2:6-10</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:05', 0, 0, 'relationship, purpose, secret', '_ZWVF4Z737A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_ZWVF4Z737A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1629, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/27/2020) - What are you investing in?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:54', 0, 0, null, 'm-MtWMM1l-Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m-MtWMM1l-Q/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'deactivated', 1, 1, null),
(1630, 1, 'Each of Us Have a Job to Do', '<p>We are called individually and collectively to fulfill our God-given function to the praise of His glory. This teaching discusses the Body of Christ, and how each of us has a job to do within it.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 1:4-7, 11; 2:10; 1 Cor. 12:4-27; Rom. 12:1-13; Eph. 4:1-7, 11-16</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:09', 0, 0, 'purpose, secret', 'bi9jwS5CCI0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bi9jwS5CCI0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1631, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Opening and Thanksgiving (Part 2)', '<p>First-century letter writing was not so different from letter writing today, but there were significant aspects to take note of. Paul opened his letter by thanking God for all the great qualities of faith, love, and hope that the Thessalonians exhibited. The Thessalonians were &ldquo;chosen&rdquo; by God, and Paul recounts their conversion to faith in Christ. He also prefaced other important themes that would develop more fully in subsequent sections.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess 1:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:14', 54, 2, 'epistles, background', 'J0pf803lhl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J0pf803lhl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(1632, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/20/2020) - The Covenants & the Sacred Secret: Part 3', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:37', 0, 0, null, 'XxRDQNNfodw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XxRDQNNfodw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Sunday noon VF - disabled', 1, 1, null),
(1633, 1, 'The Book of Ruth | Naomi and Ruth Plan and Act for Their Well-Being (Part 3)', '<p>This third teaching on the Book of Ruth covers the section in Ruth 2:20-3:12 where Naomi and Ruth make and execute a plan for their long-term well-being and Ruth&rsquo;s marriage to Boaz. Besides the wonderful story of Ruth itself, this teaching covers many of the practical life lessons in this powerful section of Scripture.</p> <p>Verses: Ruth 2:20-3:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:18', 53, 3, null, 'Ki5_NeBHD5M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ki5_NeBHD5M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1634, 1, 'Staying Positive in Distressing Times', '<p>The record of the travails and successes of Joseph is one of the longer records in the Old Testament focusing on the life of one person. Genesis 39 is about Joseph being sold as a slave in Egypt and how twice he started at the bottom and worked his way to the top due to his positive attitude, diligent effort, and the help of Yahweh.</p> <p>Verses: Genesis 39</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:55', 0, 0, 'challenges', '4hO4zo0jpcI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4hO4zo0jpcI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1635, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 30 | Don''t Boast About Yourself', '<p>Is it more meaningful if we brag about ourselves, or if someone else speaks highly of us? Faithfulness, kindness, generosity, good character, virtue, and other admirable qualities are often noticed by others. But even if people don&rsquo;t recognize us to the degree we would like or say enough good things about us, Yahweh sees everything and nothing escapes his notice.</p> <p>Illustration: Jack Hearp, Church of God pastor, and the endowment to Atlanta Bible College</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 27:2</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-10-01', 'Castos', 0, '15:39', 9, 30, 'boast, giving, generous, humble, humility', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-30-Don-t-Boast-About-Yourself-Prov.-27.2-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-30-dont-boast-about-yourself-prov-272', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1636, 5, 'The &ldquo;Sons of God&rdquo; of Genesis Six', '<p>[The following article is an edited transcription of our audio teaching, <a href="https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/24426/episodes/the-sons-of-god-of-genesis-six" target="_blank">The &ldquo;Sons of God&rdquo; of Genesis Six</a> by John W. Schoenheit.]</p> <p>What I want to do in this teaching is to show some of the reasons why God has had to do what He&rsquo;s done with mankind in the Flood and when the Israelites moved into Canaan.</p>', '2013-08-02', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-sons-of-god-of-genesis-six', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 12, null),
(1637, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/06/2020) - Conversing as an Ambassador', '<p>Note-this teaching was edited for improved quality and re-posted.</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-10-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:30', 0, 0, null, 'JnI9DzjUx94', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JnI9DzjUx94/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Inactive', 1, 1, null),
(1638, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/04/2020) - Why Prophecy?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:32', 0, 0, null, 'aeSkZEtvHbg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aeSkZEtvHbg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'inactive..', 1, 1, null),
(1639, 1, 'The Book of Ruth | Boaz Becomes the Kinsman-Redeemer (Part 4)', '<p>This fourth and final teaching in the four-part series on Ruth covers the verses from Ruth 3:13-4:22. In this section, the major player is Boaz. stepping into the role of Ruth&rsquo;s kinsman-redeemer. As well as the flow of history in Ruth, there are a lot of life lessons covered in this section.</p> <p>Verses: Ruth 3:13-4:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:06', 53, 4, null, 'xu2SwNTHSMk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xu2SwNTHSMk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1640, 1, 'Helping Each Other Fulfill Our Purposes', '<p>God gave each of us in the Body of Christ unique spiritual gifts and energizings to carry out for the common good. This teaching discusses how we are each called as members in particular to support each other in our spiritual enablements for the edification of the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:4-7; 12:21-27</p> <p>Teacher: David Dougherty</p>', '2020-10-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '14:27', 0, 0, 'function', 'lx7kPkwm1P8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lx7kPkwm1P8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1641, 1, 'Ambassadors for Christ', '<p>This teaching discusses being an ambassador for Christ and doing our best to reach unbelievers with the truth, as well as teaching truths to fellow Christians. In a dark, unbelieving world, knowledgeable Christians must learn how to reach out in love without seeming judgmental or pushing others away</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:18-20; 1 Cor. 9:19-27; Matthew 9:9-13; Hosea 6:4-7; 1 Cor. 2:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:01', 0, 0, 'evamgelism', 'SXE3GCbaGQI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SXE3GCbaGQI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1642, 5, 'Should Women be Silent in the Church? A Biblical Study of 1 Corinthians 14:34 and 35', '<p>For many centuries women have not been allowed to lead or to teach in churches based in part upon what God supposedly stated in 1 Corinthians 14:34 and 35.</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>1 Corinthians 14:34 and 35 (NASB)</strong><br /> <strong>(34)</strong> Let the women keep silent in the churches; for they are not permitted to speak, but let them subject themselves, just as the Law also says.<br /> <strong>(35)</strong> And if they desire to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands at home; for it is improper for a woman to speak in church.</p> </blockquote>', '2013-09-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/should-women-be-silent-in-the-church-a-biblical-study-of-1-corinthians-1434-and-35', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/women_silent.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 11, null),
(1643, 5, 'God&rsquo;s Plan of Cooperative Dominion', '<p>The book of Genesis gives God&rsquo;s plan in creating humankind and in it we discover that it was His goal to display His glory by creating two distinct genders that would cooperate together to display God&rsquo;s dominion on earth.</p>', '2013-09-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/gods-plan-of-cooperative-dominion', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cooperative_dominion.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 9, null),
(1644, 1, 'The Future Matters', '<p>The great people of the Bible knew that this life was short, followed by a Day of Judgment and a wonderful everlasting life for those who believed. This teaching focuses largely on Hebrews 11 and the verses that show people living in light of the future they could have.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11:1-2, 8-10, 13-16, 24-27. Rev. 22:12</p> <p>Teacher: JohnSchoenheit</p>', '2020-10-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:18', 0, 0, null, 'e7fq2llk-3Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/e7fq2llk-3Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 30, null),
(1645, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Paul&rsquo;s Ministry (Part 3)', '<p>At the beginning of the body of Paul&rsquo;s letter, he reminds the Thessalonians of his ministry and conduct among them, emphasizing how he and the apostles behaved and the desire to share their &ldquo;own souls.&rdquo; Also, Paul calls believers to holiness and purity as demonstrating a &ldquo;walk worthy of God.&rdquo; In the face of intense persecution, Paul affirms that the enemies of God are &ldquo;filling up the measure of their sins&rdquo; and they will experience His righteous judgment and wrath.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess 2:1-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:07', 54, 3, null, 'Fq70GEjI7YM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Fq70GEjI7YM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 2, null),
(1646, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/11/2020) - Lifestyle of Forgiveness', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:00', 0, 0, null, 'mi0j_xR-0Co', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mi0j_xR-0Co/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'from Sunday noon VF, inactive', 1, 0, null),
(1647, 1, 'Saul: Disobeying God', '<p>Saul had the potential to be a good king and spiritual man, but he allowed his stubbornness and worldliness to dictate his life and behavior. This teaching shows why Saul was a good choice for what the people wanted at the time and how his lack of dedication to making godly choices kept him from becoming the best king he could be.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 8:19-20; 9:5-6, 18-19; 1 Sam. 15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:38', 0, 0, null, 'hzbVY1etg9M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hzbVY1etg9M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1648, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Paul&rsquo;s Desire to Return to Thessalonica (Part 4)', '<p>Paul emphasizes his ongoing love and concern for the Thessalonian believers since his sudden separation from them and the subsequent persecution they had to endure. With deep concern over both his absence from the Thessalonians and the persecution they were experiencing, Paul sent Timothy in his place to minister to them because Paul did not want the believers to be shaken in their trust by the afflictions that they were enduring.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 2:17-3:5</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler and Ellen Fowler</p>', '2020-10-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:37', 54, 4, null, '_B0rFy8frBQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_B0rFy8frBQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1649, 1, 'Reading With A Purpose', '<p>When you read the Bible, you should be asking questions, looking for hidden gems and insights to answer the questions you are asking. This teaching is a small example of that. Reading the Bible is fun.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 20:1-38</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-10-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:26', 0, 0, 'fellowship, Paul, study', '2CsJGH6c0ZQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2CsJGH6c0ZQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1650, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Timothy&rsquo;s Report and Paul&rsquo;s Prayer (Part 5)', '<p>When Timothy returned to Paul with good news of the Thessalonians trust (faith), Paul expressed his overwhelming joy and excitement. His doubts had been assuaged and he was more desirous than ever to see them. Paul&rsquo;s transitionary prayer is that he would get to see them soon so that their hearts can be established and be blameless in holiness when Christ returns. A topic he will develop further in his letter.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess 3:6-13</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:44', 54, 5, 'epistles, report', 'uswSPz-7Kn8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uswSPz-7Kn8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1651, 1, 'What is Love?', '<p>Love is many-sided, and there is an emotional element to it. As it is expressed in the Bible, however, love shows itself by giving. This teaching provides verses and an example in the Bible of love being demonstrated by giving.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16; Eph. 5:1-2; Rom. 12:1; 1 Sam. 1:1-2, 10-11, 20-22, 24, 26-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:30', 0, 0, null, 'DB_f52izKac', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DB_f52izKac/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1652, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 31 | Arrogance is for the Fool (Prov. 14:16)', '<p>The wise person fears Yahweh and does not over-estimate themselves but is sensible and even-tempered, unlike the fool that is cocky and self-reliant, recklessly endangering themselves because they fail to see the need for any concern or restraint. The fool laughs in the face of evil thinking that it can&rsquo;t touch them. The pretensions of their own superiority have blinded them so that they cannot recognize evil for what it is. They trust wholly in themselves, feeling secure in their knowledge and understanding and thinking they don&rsquo;t need to listen to anybody else.</p> <p>Illustration: Major General John Sedgwick and the battle at Spotsylvania Courthouse</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 14:16; 13:13; 3:7</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille.</p>', '2020-10-16', 'Castos', 0, '13:54', 9, 31, 'wisdom, pride, tragedy', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-31-Arrogance-is-for-the-Fool-Prov.-14.16-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-31-arrogance-is-for-the-fool-prov-1416-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(1653, 1, 'Dead People are Dead (Part 1)', '<p>It is commonly believed that when a person dies, their soul (or spirit) goes to a good place (Heaven) or a bad place (&ldquo;Hell&rdquo;). This teaching shows from Scripture that when a person dies, they are dead, lifeless in every way, and will not have life again until the Rapture or a resurrection.</p> <p>Verses: Job 3:11-19; 30:23; 7:21; 14:12; Ps. 6:5; 49:12, 15; Ecc. 9:4-6; John 5:28-29; 1 Cor. 15:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:29', 0, 0, 'Death', 'TstgiIrY72s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TstgiIrY72s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1654, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/18/2020) - Revisiting Romans 9', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-10-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:37', 0, 0, 'Not active', '-Xur7RUgv8A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-Xur7RUgv8A/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1655, 1, 'The Wedding Feast of the Lamb', '<p>The Wedding Feast of the Lamb is not well known or well understood, but very soon after Jesus conquers the earth in the Battle of Armageddon there will be the Sheep and Goat Judgment and the Resurrection of the Righteous, and when all those people are together along with the Christians, then God will throw a huge feast. This teaching covers some background and details of the Wedding Feast.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 8:5-12; Rev. 19:6-9; Isa. 25:6; 2:1-4; 30:23-26; Zech. 8:22-23; Matt. 22:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:33', 0, 0, null, '9KqP7wIlcyA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9KqP7wIlcyA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1656, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | The Need to Pursue Holiness and Love (Part 6)', '<p>It is God&rsquo;s will for His people to live holy lives! On the basis of Paul&rsquo;s exhortations, it is clear that he wanted the Thessalonian church to continue growing in their walk of holiness by abstaining from all sexual immorality. In addition, Paul reiterates how much he has heard that they are showing love for one another. But he has a few instructions for the church so that they will more fully walk as Christ-followers and be good representatives of the faith in the eyes of unbelievers.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 4:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-10-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:15', 54, 6, 'discipleship, sanctification', 'DGV65ko34x8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DGV65ko34x8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1657, 5, 'Belonging to the Truth', '<p>&ldquo;What is truth?&rdquo; That is the question every human being will at one time or another have to face, and answer. Those who choose to face it in this lifetime, and who come to God for the answer, will be set free by the truth, and eventually gain everlasting life. Those who do not choose to come to grips with this question, and those who go to the wrong source for the answer, will remain in bondage. And one day they will stand face to face with The Answer, Jesus Christ, who will righteously judge them. How each of us relates to truth determines not only our everlasting destiny, but also the quality of our life now.</p>', '2013-09-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/belonging-to-the-truth', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/belonging_to_truth.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 12, null),
(1658, 5, 'Who is Our Firm Foundation? Names and Descriptions of the Messiah', '<p>Just over 2000 years ago the great Apostle Paul wrote by revelation that Jesus Christ was the foundation for every Christian life, and no one could lay any other foundation than him (1 Cor. 3:11). He also said that each of us &ldquo;should be careful how he builds&rdquo; (1 Cor. 3:10). Every builder knows how important the foundation of any project is. When it comes to our Christian life, however, our &ldquo;foundation&rdquo; is even more important than the foundation of a building because Jesus is not only our foundation, but our example. The more we know about Jesus, the clearer we will be about what and how to build our lives as Christians. One of the most important ways that God has chosen to reveal His Son is by the names and descriptions that are given of him in the Bible.</p>', '2013-09-26', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/who-is-our-firm-foundation-names-and-descriptions-of-the-messiah', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/messiah_firm_foundation.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1659, 5, 'Spiritual Battles: The Struggle Against Strongholds', '<p>The phrase &ldquo;spiritual battle&rdquo; has become almost a catchphrase in Christian circles nowadays. But what exactly is a spiritual battle? Do you feel like you are in a &ldquo;spiritual battle&rdquo;? For many Christians, the term &ldquo;spiritual battle&rdquo; is an expression encompassing the generality of the conflict between good and evil, so it often carries with it this vague idea of a war in heaven between angels and demons. Language like this might sound appealing to our ears, and we might nod in agreement when we hear it, but the reality and significance of the Christian&rsquo;s spiritual battle is really not often well-understood.</p>', '2019-05-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/spiritual-battles-the-struggle-against-strongholds', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Spiritual-Battles-The-Struggle-Against-Strongholds-.png', 1, 0, null, 1, 9, null),
(1660, 5, 'Tithing vs. Giving', '<p>Most churches I have been to teach rather emphatically that Christians should &ldquo;tithe,&rdquo; that is, give 10% of their income to their church. I have even heard some ministers say that if you don&rsquo;t tithe, God will not bless you. Must you give a tenth (10%) to the church? What does the Bible say about financial giving?</p>', '2018-08-06', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/tithing-vs-giving', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 33, null),
(1661, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/25/2020) – Covenants: Part 15 Covenants & the Sacred Secret Part 4', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-10-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:40', 0, 0, null, 'qapTAA5cmJw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qapTAA5cmJw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1662, 1, 'Dead People are Dead (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching continues the presentation of biblical evidence that when a person dies, they are dead in every way and not alive in any form or any place. They are awaiting their resurrection.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 38; Ps. 6:5; 49:12-15; 13:3; John 3:13; Gen. 25:8; Josh. 24:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:20', 0, 0, 'sleep; gates of Hell', '_dKqve3Y5yc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_dKqve3Y5yc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1663, 1, 'Divination, Sorcery and Demonic Forces', '<p>Many Christians are unaware of the spiritual battle between God and the Devil, and some get involved with things that God says are an abomination to Him because they give support and credit to the Devil. This teaching covers some of what God says about sorcery and divination and explains why they are an abomination to God.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 18:9-15; 1 Sam. 15:23; Zech. 10:2; 1 Sam. 28:3-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:28', 0, 0, 'witchcraft, necromancy, seances', '6DTMGhPRe5s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6DTMGhPRe5s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1664, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 32 | Take Care of Your Flocks (Prov. 27:23-24)', '<p>Everything in life requires attention in order to grow and prosper. We each have &ldquo;flocks&rdquo; in our lives that need diligent oversight and &ldquo;treasure&rdquo; that won&rsquo;t last forever. We can&rsquo;t think everything will work itself out on its own. Things don&rsquo;t just take care of themselves! Instead, we must strive to increase how we can better steward and take care of what Yahweh has blessed us with.</p> <p>Illustration: Tasmanian Institute of Agriculture development of drone surveillance technology &ldquo;Lambulance&rdquo; for remote monitoring of sheep biometrics.</p> <p>Verses: Prov 27:23-24; 12:10</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-10-27', 'Castos', 0, '17:19', 9, 32, 'caring, overseeing, faithfulness', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-32-Take-Care-of-Your-Flocks-27.23-24-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-32-take-care-of-your-flocks-prov-2723-24', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1665, 1, 'God and the Devil Are Both Sources of Information', '<p>Many Christians are unaware of the spiritual battle between God and the Devil and get involved with things that God says are an abomination to Him because they give support and credit to the Devil. This teaching covers some of what God says about sorcery and divination and why they are an abomination to Him, and what sources of information are godly and glorify God.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 18:9-15; Zech. 10:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-10-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:42', 0, 0, null, 'LsnlqLrRbG8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LsnlqLrRbG8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1666, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Grieving with Hope: the Return of the Lord (Part 7)', '<p>The way that Jesus&rsquo; followers grieve unlike the rest of humankind is with the hope of his return in their sight. The pain of losing beloved brothers and sisters in the Lord to the sting of death is not done away with because of the promise of resurrection, but it is endured with the comfort of knowing that they will be with the Lord when he returns. Both living and resurrected believers will be part of the glorious reception where we will celebrate the coming of the Lord Jesus as he descends from heaven in triumph.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 4:13-18</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Fowler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:42', 54, 7, null, '1vhr30YAvPw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1vhr30YAvPw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1667, 1, 'Saul: Setting A Bad Example', '<p>This teaching provides an overview of the life of Saul, the first king of Israel. Saul was a terrible king, and though he had many opportunities to change, he instead spiraled further and further down into sin and ungodliness, dragging many good people down with him. From his life we can learn what not to do if we want to be successful with God.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:13; 1 Samuel 8:20; 9:6-7; 16:1-2; 18:8-10, 25; 19:1, 9, 10; 20:24-33;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:43', 0, 0, null, 'TuFZaJkADcE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TuFZaJkADcE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 35, null),
(1668, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | The Coming Day of the Lord: Sons of Light and Sons of the Day (Part 8)', '<p>The world is unprepared for the day of the Lord when Jesus will return. They live in darkness, but those who trust in Jesus are sons and daughters of the light and of the day. We will explore what living as a child of the day means and how to be clear-minded, eagerly waiting with readiness since there is one unifying destiny for all God&rsquo;s people whether they are awake or asleep when Christ comes.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 5:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:57', 54, 8, null, '4eS33rJKTXQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4eS33rJKTXQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1669, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/01/2020) - Rooted and Grounded in Love', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-11-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:46', 0, 0, null, 'nU_5ves2Z7s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nU_5ves2Z7s/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'noon VF, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1670, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/08/2020) - Jehosheba –Choosing Trust Over Fear', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-11-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:20', 0, 0, null, 'rFDhZ4HeAC0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rFDhZ4HeAC0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'noon fellowship, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1671, 1, 'Consider Your Ways: Earning Rewards for the Future Kingdom', '<p>This teaching covers what &ldquo;crowns&rdquo; represent as they are used in the Bible and discusses rewards and how important they will be to Christians in the future when rewards are handed out. Christians need to consider their choices and make sure that they are living in a way that pleases God to maximize the rewards they receive in the future.</p> <p>Verses: Revelation 14:14; 4:4; Zech. 1:11; Haggai 1:1-15; 1 Cor. 9:23-27; 1 Thess. 2:19; 2 Tim. 4:8; James 1:12; 1 Pet. 5:4.</p> <p>Teacher: JohnSchoenheit</p>', '2020-11-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:59', 0, 0, null, 'iv1UyUSV_Z0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iv1UyUSV_Z0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1672, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 33 | Discern Your Steps (Prov. 14.15)', '<p>Being na&iuml;ve means having a general lack of understanding about people and the world, which leads to a person being gullible. When critical thinking is absent, we tend to not discern our circumstances and fall prey to unexpected consequences. Discernment requires time and effort to gain an awareness of what is real rather than presuming we know what is going on at first glance. Building wisdom in our lives takes time, but the outcome is that we can discern our steps and avoid making foolish decisions that we will later regret.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable &ldquo;The Fowler and the Blackbird&rdquo; and the keen senses of the catfish that enables it to thrive in very diverse environments.</p> <p>Verses: Prov 14:15; 15:22</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-10', 'Castos', 0, '18:55', 9, 33, 'prudent, wise, deliberation', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-33-Discern-Your-Steps-Prov.-14.15-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-33-discern-your-steps-prov-1415', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1673, 1, 'The Desire Of The Nations', '<p>Leadership was a controversial subject in Israel&rsquo;s history. This teaching takes a deeper look at Israel&rsquo;s desire for a King to rule them and lead them in war rather than having God as their King, and the impact this had on their nation.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Samuel 8, 9-10. Haggai 2:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2020-11-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:47', 0, 0, 'Saul, politics', '2CnNseb34Go', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2CnNseb34Go/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1674, 1, 'The Spiritual Battle: Prayer', '<p>This teaching shows why the spiritual battle between Good and Evil was so serious in the Old Testament and is still serious today, and why believers need to take prayer seriously and learn how to fight in the spiritual war using the power of prayer.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 22:18; Lev. 20:27; Eph. 6:10-20; Rom. 12:12; 1 Cor. 7:5; Phil. 1:3, 4, 9; Col. 4:1-3; 1 Thess. 5:17; Ezek. 25:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:38', 0, 0, 'sorceress', '1HFqa6rTbRE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1HFqa6rTbRE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1675, 1, 'Maintaining Peace Around Selfish People', '<p>Many people are selfish and knowingly or unknowingly can take advantage of other people, even those who have been very good to them, and this can by very challenging for the one who is mistreated to deal with. This teaching obviates that problem and shows from the Bible that it is a common one, and he reads and explains that from the life of David, which was almost 3,000 years ago.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 4:6-7; Rom. 12:18-19; 1 Samuel 23:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-13', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '17:16', 0, 0, null, 'BZubHzORVxs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BZubHzORVxs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(1676, 5, 'Working in the Future Kingdom: what will we be doing in heaven?', '<p>In the future Kingdom there will be different positions and responsibilities. At the Judgment, each person will &ldquo;receive what is due him for the things done while in the body, whether good or bad&rdquo; (2 Cor. 5:10). Therefore, every person will not receive the same reward or assume the same responsibilities. So, the question is not, &ldquo;What will we be doing in heaven,&rdquo; but, &ldquo;What will we be doing in our future life on earth?&rdquo; The answer to this question can be found in the Word of God.</p>', '2013-08-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/working-in-the-future-kingdom-what-will-we-be-doing-in-heaven', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/work_in_future_kingdom.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 24, null),
(1677, 5, 'Guaranteed Salvation', '<p>Through the centuries of the Christian era, there has been a huge debate about whether Christians can lose (forfeit) their salvation. In this article, we hope to show that once a person is born again of God&rsquo;s holy spirit, his salvation is guaranteed, that is, he is not in danger of the &ldquo;Second Death,&rdquo; which is when everyone who is not allowed into God&rsquo;s Eternal Kingdom will be thrown into the Lake of Fire and burned up (Rev. 20:12-15).</p>', '2013-08-28', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/guaranteed-salvation', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/guaranteed_salvation.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 13, null),
(1678, 5, 'God&rsquo;s Gift of holy spirit—a &ldquo;He&rdquo; or an &ldquo;It&rdquo;', '<p>[This article was taken from our book The Gift of Holy Spirit: The Power to be like Christ.]</p> <p>One of the major reasons that holy spirit has not been recognized by Christians to be a gift from God is that personal and masculine pronouns such as &ldquo;he&rdquo; or &ldquo;whom&rdquo; have been used with <em>pneuma hagion</em>. If we are to be confident that holy spirit is indeed a gift, and not a person, then the question about the pronouns associated with it has to be answered. The pronouns associated with the gift of holy spirit can, and should, be translated as pronouns such as &ldquo;it,&rdquo; &ldquo;which,&rdquo; and &ldquo;that.&rdquo;</p>', '2013-08-08', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/gods-gift-of-holy-spirit-a-he-or-an-it', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 10, null),
(1679, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Ministering to Fellow Believers and Being Spiritually Minded (Part 9)', '<p>Every church has leaders, and Paul gives important instructions on how to properly respect and think highly of these servants of the Lord. In addition, there are specific ways Paul says that everyone is to minister within the church. Paul further defines God&rsquo;s will for believers in a simple and memorable way. And in a final word of exhortation, we examine what it means to &ldquo;quench the spirit&rdquo; and why prophecy is not to be suppressed but rather tested.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 5:12-22</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler, Jerry Wierwille, Ellen Fowler</p>', '2020-11-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:20', 54, 9, null, 'b4usp7urQbo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b4usp7urQbo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1680, 5, 'The Origin of Orthodoxy', '<p>The basic teaching of orthodox Christianity concerning what happens after death is that the &ldquo;souls&rdquo; or &ldquo;spirits&rdquo; of righteous people go either to &ldquo;heaven&rdquo; or to some other blissful place. This teaching is in error. <strong>[1]</strong> It is impossible to understand such false doctrines without understanding their spiritual causes. From as early as the Garden of Eden, the Devil and his demons have been promoting the idea that people do not really die. After God plainly told Adam that he would &ldquo;surely die&rdquo; if he partook of the fruit of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, the Devil lied and said to Eve, &ldquo;You will not surely die&rdquo; (Gen. 3:4). Ever since that time, the Devil has been actively promoting this same lie wherever and whenever possible. Unfortunately, the idea that people continue living on after they die has found a fertile breeding ground in most religions, including orthodox Christianity.</p>', '2013-08-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-origin-of-orthodoxy', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/origin_of_orthodoxy.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 22, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1681, 5, 'The Millennial Kingdom will be populated by three &ldquo;categories&rdquo; or &ldquo;types&rdquo; of people', '<p>[This article was taken from chapter 4 of our book <a href="http://stfonlinestore.com/hope.aspx" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="The Christian''s Hope">The Christian&rsquo;s Hope: The Anchor of the Soul</a>]</p> <p>The Millennial Kingdom will be populated by three &ldquo;categories&rdquo; or &ldquo;types&rdquo; of people</p>', '2013-08-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-millennial-kingdom-will-be-populated-by-three-categories-or-types-of-people', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/millenial_kingdom.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 23, null),
(1682, 5, 'The Millennial (Messianic, 1000 year Reign of Christ) and Eternal Kingdoms', '<p>The Bible indicates that there will be two kingdoms on earth in the future, one following the other. The first kingdom will last 1,000 years and is therefore referred to as the &ldquo;Millennial (Messianic) Kingdom&rdquo; (from mil, one thousand, and annus, year). The second kingdom is referred to by the author as the &ldquo;Everlasting Kingdom.&rdquo;</p>', '2013-08-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-millennial-messianic-1000-year-reign-of-christ-and-eternal-kingdoms', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/millenial_eternal_kingdom.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 15, null),
(1683, 5, 'What is the purpose of the &ldquo;Millennial Kingdom&rdquo;?', '<p>One very important purpose of the Millennial Kingdom is to fulfill God&rsquo;s yet-unfulfilled promises to Israel. In fact, every unconditional covenant God made with Abraham and Israel will be fulfilled in the Millennial Kingdom.</p> <p>Another purpose of the Millennial Kingdom is to demonstrate for all time that even with Satan bound, Christ governing the earth and millions of believers in their new bodies living thereupon, unregenerate man&rsquo;s nature will always leave him susceptible to deception, unthankfulness and rebellion.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-purpose-of-the-millennial-kingdom', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/purpose_of_millennial_kingdom.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1684, 5, 'If the purpose of the Millennial Kingdom is to fulfill God&rsquo;s promises to Israel, what does that have to do with the Church?', '<p>The Church also will be a part of Christ&rsquo;s Millennial Reign. According to Ephesians 1:10, God is gathering together all things under one head, Christ. We believe that this verse is referring to the Millennial Kingdom, which means that the Church will be included. 2 Timothy 2:12 indicates that if we are faithful to serve him, &ldquo;we will also reign with him,&rdquo; which can only be referring to his Millennial Kingdom, when he reigns over the earth and all its people, both believers and unbelievers. Part of the faithful Christian&rsquo;s future reward is the privilege of reigning with Christ during this period.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/if-the-purpose-of-the-millennial-kingdom-is-to-fulfill-gods-promises-to-israel-what-does-that-have-to-do-with-the-church', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/millennial_kingdom_fulfill_gods_promises_to_israel.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 10, null),
(1685, 5, 'Is there a difference between the &ldquo;kingdom of God&rdquo; and the &ldquo;kingdom of heaven&rdquo;?', '<p>The ultra-dispensational view of E.W. Bullinger makes a distinction between the &ldquo;kingdom of God&rdquo; (heavenly) and the &ldquo;kingdom of heaven&rdquo; (on earth). However, we believe that as they are used in Scripture, these are synonymous terms that both refer to the Millennial Kingdom. It is not unusual in the Bible for something to have different names. For example, Jerusalem is called by many different names in the Bible. It is called &ldquo;the City of David&rdquo; (2 Sam. 5:7), <strong>[1]</strong> the City of God (Ps. 46:4), Salem (Ps. 76:2), Zion (Ps. 76:2), the Lord Our Righteousness (Jer. 33:16), Sodom (when its people were caught up in sin, Ezek. 16:46), the city of the Great King (Ps. 48:2; Matt. 5:35), Ariel (Isa. 29:1,2,7, either &ldquo;Lion of God&rdquo; or &ldquo;Hearth of God&rdquo;), etc. Cities, kingdoms and people often have more than one name in Scripture.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/is-there-a-difference-between-the-kingdom-of-god-and-the-kingdom-of-heaven', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kingdom_of_god_kingdom_of_heaven.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1686, 5, 'What is the &ldquo;Kingdom Now&rdquo; or &ldquo;Dominion&rdquo; theology movement in Christendom?', '<p><strong>Is there a sense in which we are in the Kingdom of God now?</strong></p> <p>&ldquo;Kingdom Now&rdquo; is the theological belief that the Church is presently subduing the enemies of Christ in order to pave the way for his appearing. Mishandling such verses as Acts 3:19ff and Ephesians 4:13 and 14 leads to the view that the Christian Church will remain on the earth and become a dominant force in the world by winning millions of people to the Lord in a great end-times revival. It is easy to understand why someone who believes that would be confused as he reads the Church Epistles, however, because they say that we are lights in the midst of a world that is growing ever darker.</p>', '2013-08-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-kingdom-now-or-dominion-theology-movement-in-christendom', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kingdom_now.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 18, null),
(1687, 1, 'Two Arguments for a Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>There are a lot of theories about when (and even if) the Rapture will occur. This teaching covers in some detail why the Rapture cannot be the same as the First Resurrection, and also why it has to be a Rapture before the Tribulation to fit with the Sheep and Goat Judgment of Matthew 25.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 11:26; Rom. 6:3, 5, 8; Eph. 4:30; Dan. 2:31-35; Zeph. 1:1-3, 12; Ezek. 20:33-38; Joel 3:14; Matt. 25:31-46</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:57', 0, 0, null, 'ey5b1QaDhJ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ey5b1QaDhJ0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(1688, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/15/2020) - A Blessing', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:23', 0, 0, null, 'PYL3_McWPwA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PYL3_McWPwA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Not active', 1, 0, null),
(1689, 5, 'Are we living in the Kingdom now?', '<p><strong>Q. I hear many Christians talk about how we as the Church are now living in and building the Kingdom of God, and I also hear many songs about Jesus now being the King. What about that? Are we now in the Kingdom of God, and are God and Jesus ruling over the world today?</strong></p>', '2013-08-03', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/are-we-living-in-the-kingdom-now', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1690, 5, 'Do miracles happen?', '<p>Some people say they cannot believe the Bible because they do not believe the miracles in the Bible are possible. It is true that there are some very notable miracles in the Bible, but they do not disprove the existence of God or the truth of Scripture. If anything, they prove God&rsquo;s existence and show His love and concern for His people. If you doubt the miracles in the Bible, the first question you should ask yourself is, &ldquo;Do I believe in God?&rdquo;</p>', '2013-08-07', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/do-miracles-happen', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/do_miracles_happen.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 7, null),
(1691, 5, 'What is the Manifestation of Working of Miracles?', '<p><strong>The manifestation of working of miracles is your exercising your God-given spiritual ability to do miracles by the power of God, according to what God or the Lord Jesus has revealed to you by a message of knowledge or a message of wisdom.</strong></p> <p>The manifestation of working of miracles (1 Cor. 12:10-KJV) is very similar to the manifestation of gifts of healings, except that the power of God results in a miracle. Like the other manifestations listed in 1 Corinthians 12:8-10, it is a &ldquo;manifestation&rdquo; (something made visible or obvious) of holy spirit, so it is done only by those who have the gift of holy spirit.</p>', '2013-09-03', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-manifestation-of-working-of-miracles', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/working_of_miracles.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 16, null),
(1692, 5, 'What is a Message of Knowledge?', '<p><strong>A message of knowledge is God or the Lord Jesus Christ providing to you information, insight, and understanding about something.</strong></p> <p>A message of knowledge is a manifestation of the gift of holy spirit (1 Cor. 12:7 and 8), so it is God or the Lord Jesus giving knowledge to us via the gift of holy spirit. We refer to &ldquo;a message of knowledge&rdquo; as a &ldquo;revelation manifestation,&rdquo; because God or the Lord Jesus Christ reveals the knowledge, or information, to us.</p>', '2013-08-29', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-a-message-of-knowledge', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/message_of_knowledge.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 15, null),
(1693, 5, 'What is a Message of Wisdom?', '<p><strong>A message of wisdom</strong> is God or the Lord Jesus Christ providing to you direction, or how to apply the knowledge you have about something.</p> <p>A message of wisdom (1 Cor. 12:8) is a manifestation of the gift of holy spirit. In contrast to knowledge, &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; is guidance or direction about what to do in any given situation. Webster&rsquo;s 1828 Dictionary captures the essence of wisdom: &ldquo;the right use or exercise of knowledge.&rdquo; <strong>[1]</strong> As a manifestation of the gift of holy spirit, a message of wisdom is God or the Lord Jesus Christ giving a Christian &ldquo;wisdom,&rdquo; direction as to what to do, via the gift of holy spirit that is sealed inside him.</p>', '2013-08-29', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-a-message-of-wisdom', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/message_of_wisdom.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 11, null),
(1694, 5, 'What is the manifestation of Faith?', '<p><strong>The manifestation of faith is your having the confidence or trust that what God or the Lord Jesus Christ has revealed to you by a message of knowledge or a message of wisdom will come to pass at your command.</strong></p> <p>Before we can understand the &ldquo;manifestation of faith&rdquo; (1 Cor. 12:9), we must understand what &ldquo;regular&rdquo; faith is. &ldquo;Faith&rdquo; is the translation of the Greek noun pistis, which means &ldquo;trust,&rdquo; &ldquo;confidence,&rdquo; or &ldquo;assurance.&rdquo; Our English word &ldquo;trust&rdquo; captures the sense very well. Sadly, most Christians do not know what &ldquo;faith&rdquo; is because the modern definition differs from the biblicalof &ldquo;faith,&rdquo; and the definition most Christians have in their mind, is a &ldquo;firm belief in something for which there is no proof &rdquo; (Merriam-Webster&rsquo;s Collegiate Dictionary).</p>', '2013-08-29', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-manifestation-of-faith', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/manifestation_of_faith.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1695, 5, 'What is the Manifestation of Gifts of Healing?', '<p><strong>The manifestation of gifts of healings is your exercising your God-given spiritual ability to heal by the power of God, according to what God or the Lord Jesus has revealed to you by a message of knowledge or a message of wisdom.</strong></p> <p>Gifts of healings is a manifestation of holy spirit (1 Cor. 12:9), and it occurs when a Christian, acting on revelation, and by faith, brings the power of God to bear on another person&rsquo;s physical, mental, or emotional need and heals him. God does multiple healings, and each of them is a gift, done out of His grace or mercy, but not every healing is the manifestation of gifts of healings.</p>', '2013-09-03', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-manifestation-of-gifts-of-healing', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/gifts_of_healing.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 30, null),
(1696, 1, 'Nabal, Abigail, David, and Christ', '<p>This teaching covers 1 Samuel 25 and the record of Nabal, Abigail, and David. It provides an explanation of the record itself and ties it into David being a type of Christ and in how in the big picture, on the Day of Judgement, there will only be two types of people: people like Nabal who reject God&rsquo;s Anointed and end up dead, and people like Abigail who humbly submit themselves to God&rsquo;s Anointed and end up living with him when he reigns as the King.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 19:18; 1 Samuel 25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:48', 0, 0, null, 'E609uMDQxDo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E609uMDQxDo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(1697, 5, 'What is the Spirit in the Fruit of the Spirit?', '<p>Galatians 5:22 and 23 list the fruit of the &ldquo;spirit,&rdquo; and different theologians and Bible teachers have stated their opinions about what &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; refers to. The word &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; is, after all, a very flexible word with at least three different meanings in Galatians alone. <strong>[1]</strong> Most theologians are Trinitarian, and simply say that &ldquo;spirit&rdquo; refers to &ldquo;the Holy Spirit,&rdquo; the &ldquo;Third Person of the Trinity.&rdquo; For those of us who are Biblical Unitarians, however, that explanation is hardly satisfactory. What we will show in this article is that the fruit of the spirit is the fruit of the new, spiritual nature that each Christian received at the time he or she was born again. Then we will see that it is up to each of us to know what godly, fruitful Christian character is and strive to develop it in our lives.</p>', '2013-09-04', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-spirit-in-the-fruit-of-the-spirit', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/spirit_in_fruit_of_spirit.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 18, null),
(1698, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 34 | Pride Can Be Deadly (Prov. 16.18)', '<p>Pride makes us think more highly of ourselves than we should, and it produces in us a sense of overconfidence and self-importance. When we are full of pride, we can lose sight of thinking things through clearly and sensibly. Thus, as a consequence, pride leads us to experience disaster in our lives. We are warned against succumbing to the temptation of pride because the consequence can be very high, even deadly.</p> <p>Illustration: Kami Rita Sherpa, the world record holder for the number of times summitting Mount Everest.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 16:18, 5; 8:3</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-18', 'Castos', 0, '16:33', 9, 34, 'destruction, negligence, conceit, puffed-up, arrogant, haughty', 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-34-Pride-Can-Be-Deadly-Prov.-16.18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-34-pride-can-be-deadly-prov-1618', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1699, 5, 'Discovering Your Individual Gifts of God&rsquo;s Grace', '<p>Regarding a person&rsquo;s gifts, I have been asked the question, &ldquo;How do I find out what my ministry is?&rdquo; In some ways that is like putting the cart before the horse. The gifts will define the ministry. In a similar way a horse will not be very effective in fulfilling its function of moving a cart along if it tries to push the cart from behind. However, if the horse is properly hooked up in front of the cart, it can pull a great load and fulfill its calling, so to speak. This analogy is helpful when it comes to the discussion of gifts, ministries, and the works of God.</p>', '2013-10-01', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/discovering-your-individual-gifts-of-gods-grace', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/individual_gifts.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1700, 5, 'What&rsquo;s in a Word? – Function', '<p>&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t care what your role in the ministry is. What is your function?&rdquo;</p> <p>The first time my friend ever asked me this, I blanked out. The mashup of &ldquo;receptionist, shipping department head, and editor&rdquo; &ndash; or &ldquo;reshipmeditor,&rdquo; if you will (though I would not) &ndash; died on my tongue. Suddenly I was in sixth grade again, frozen mute in my chair because I forgot to mentally practice saying &ldquo;here&rdquo; sixty-five times before the teacher called on me.</p>', '2020-06-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wiaw-function', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Whats-in-a-Word-Function.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 26, null),
(1701, 5, 'What is the Manifestation of Discerning of Spirits?', '<p><strong>The manifestation of discerning of spirits</strong> is God or the Lord Jesus Christ revealing to you information about the presence or non-presence of spirits (including both holy spirit or demons), and sometimes including the identity of demons present, whether or not you may cast them out, and providing the power to do it.</p>', '2013-09-03', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-is-the-manifestation-of-discerning-of-spirits', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/discerning_spirits.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 16, null),
(1703, 5, 'Angelic Warfare', '<p>Another biblical variable that affects our lives is the spiritual battle raging between the forces of good and evil in the realm beyond our five senses. Remembering from Ezekiel 28 and Isaiah 14 how much power and wisdom God originally gave &ldquo;Lucifer&rdquo; should help us to understand how formidable a foe we now have, and how diligent we must be in resisting him.</p>', '2013-08-20', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/angelic-warfare', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/angelic_warfare.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 22, null),
(1704, 5, 'The Patron-Client Relationship in the Ancient World', '<p>One of the most difficult aspects of Bible study is understanding the text in the way that a person living at the time the Bible was written would understand it. We can use the model of a stage play to teach us how to better interpret the Bible. Let&rsquo;s say we travel to England to see Romeo and Juliet by Shakespeare, played, not in American English with modern phrases and modern adaptations, but right in Stratford-on-Avon with the jargon used when Shakespeare wrote. When you are watching the play, there are three distinct aspects or concept areas to consider.</p>', '2013-08-07', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-patron-client-relationship-in-the-ancient-world', null, 1, 0, null, 1, 9, null),
(1705, 5, 'Do People Become Angels When They Die?', '<p>People do not become angels when they die. The Bible makes a very clear distinction between men and angels and it&rsquo;s never implied that we cross over into that other state of being when we die.</p> <p>However, if you walk into any Christian bookstore today, you&rsquo;re likely to find a trove of art, pillows, fridge magnets and cards all depicting the same thing: people ascending and becoming one with the angels when they die.</p>', '2019-11-04', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/do-people-become-angels-when-they-die', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Do-People-Become-Angels-When-They-Die.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 19, null),
(1706, 1, '1 Thessalonians Series | Prayer for Holiness and Paul&rsquo;s Final Instructions (Part 10)', '<p>Paul&rsquo;s prayer for the Thessalonians is for their complete holiness in their behavior and conduct&mdash;body, soul, and spirit. But the ability to live holy lives does not rest on our strength alone. The part God plays is indispensable and is encouraging to us in our aim to be holy. Finally, Paul&rsquo;s conclusion draws together the need for one another and the necessity for the church to follow his instructions.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 5:23-28</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler and Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:15', 54, 10, 'letters, kiss, faithful, blameless', 'aTxZVYgZQtY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aTxZVYgZQtY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1707, 1, 'More Evidence for a Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>This teaching covers further evidence for a pre-Tribulation Rapture, including how the revelation to Paul for the Christian Church is completely different from the revelation to Israel and how the Church is unique in being delivered from &ldquo;the wrath&rdquo;, which is scripturally the Tribulation, not the Lake of Fire.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 15:51-57; Isa. 65:17-22; 1 Thess. 1:10, 5:9; Rom. 5:9; Dan. 9:24, 26; Dan. 12:1; Zech. 14:1-2; Luke 19:41-43; 21:20-24; Matt. 24:9-10, 13; Rev. 6:16-17; Dan. 7:21, 25; Rev. 2:10; 13:7, 10, 14:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:22', 0, 0, null, 'f1jyB_Nz650', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f1jyB_Nz650/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 24, null),
(1708, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/22/2020) - Praise Yahweh', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-11-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '20:20', 0, 0, null, 'bWdgOPo76jU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bWdgOPo76jU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 1, null),
(1709, 1, 'Giving Thanks to God in Our Lives', '<p>Scripture instructs us to give thanks in everything. But what does that look like and why is it so important? Even though we celebrate the Day of Thanksgiving once a year, we are to build a thankful heart toward God and practice always giving thanks to him every day in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess 5:18</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-11-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '8:38', 0, 0, null, 'd4W7e3LhXGU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/d4W7e3LhXGU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1710, 5, 'A Christian Response to Depression', '<p>Over the course of my life, I&rsquo;ve gotten to know many people&mdash;some of whom are Christians of deep belief and passion for Jesus&mdash;who struggle with varying types of depression.</p> <p>The first time I ever befriended someone with depression, I was in my early teens. Up to that point, if anyone I knew was fighting that battle, it was not widespread knowledge. But then I befriended someone whose depression ran deep, to the point that they harbored suicidal thoughts. I remember at the time being honestly flabbergasted when I found out.</p>', '2019-09-16', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/a-christian-response-to-depression', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/A-Christian-Response-to-Depression.png', 1, 0, null, 1, 22, null),
(1711, 5, 'Treating the Symptoms Rather Than Curing the Problem', '<p>I had a friend who was recently in kidney failure. He was in need of a new kidney at the age of 29, and while he waited for this new kidney, he had to undergo dialysis to keep his blood filtered. He went to dialysis 3-4 times a week and although he could function this way for a while, he was not going to be cured of his ailment until he received a new kidney. Dialysis could treat the symptoms that were causing his body to not function properly, but it could not cure the problem.</p> <p>It got me thinking about how often we do this in life. You and your significant other aren&rsquo;t getting along, so you complain to a friend about them. This might cure the problem of your anger for a moment, but it won&rsquo;t fix your relationship. You&rsquo;re unhappy at your job, so you find a different one. This might cure the problems with your current boss, but what happens when problems with your new one arise? Your teenager is being disrespectful, so you take away their Internet privileges. This might help them see consequences of their actions, but what happens the next time they make a sarcastic remark?</p>', '2019-07-22', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/treating-the-symptoms-rather-than-curing-the-problem', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Treating-the-Symptoms-Rather-Than-Curing-the-Problem.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 10, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1712, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/29/2020) - Measured Portion', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-12-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:53', 0, 0, null, '25h-PJDokkw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/25h-PJDokkw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1713, 1, 'What Brings Us Endurance? The Encouragement of Hope', '<p>This teaching presents several verses from the Epistles that connect endurance, hope and encouragement, including Hebrews 6, which states that our hope is unchangeable and is the anchor of our souls. God also painted us very detailed pictures of our future throughout the Old Testament, making it easier for us to endure. This teaching presents several such pictures from the Book of Isaiah.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:1-5; 1 Thess. 1:3; 2 Thess. 2:16; Heb. 6:13-19; Isa. 11:1-9; 32:15-18; 33:24; 35:1-10; 65:17-25; Eph. 1:15-23</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2020-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:33', 0, 0, null, '7GQvN5576fw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7GQvN5576fw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1714, 1, 'Some How&rsquo;s and Why&rsquo;s to Approaching God', '<p>The Bible tells us that we can and should approach God with openness and frank speech due to Jesus being our &ldquo;approach offering.&rdquo; This teaching shows that Jesus was our offering for sin and how he opened the way for us to approach God as we do today.</p> <p>Verses: Job 6:13; Heb. 4:12-16; 2 Cor. 5:20-21; Lev. 1:1; Exod. 27:18; Lev. 10:1-3; Heb. 10:19-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:46', 0, 0, null, '-eynB68UjUg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-eynB68UjUg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1715, 1, 'The Messiah in Prophecy: What were the people expecting', '<p>We today have such a clear picture of the life and ministry of Jesus Christ that we have a hard time putting ourselves back into the shoes of the people who lived before him. This teaching looks at prophecies in Isaiah of the coming Messiah and discusses what someone who lived before the time of Christ would be expecting from the Messiah.</p> <p>Verses: Isaiah 7:1-17; 9:5-7; 11:1-5; 16:5; 42:1-4; 61:1-7; 2 Kings 16:1-9; Luke 1:34-35</p> <p>Teacher: JohnSchoenheit</p>', '2020-12-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:11', 0, 0, null, 'o1vKdO7cp2E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/o1vKdO7cp2E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 24, null),
(1716, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 35 | Humility Leads to Glory (Prov. 18:12; 15:33)', '<p>What Proverbs teaches us is that our attitude and way of thinking can send us down two drastically different roads. One ends in disaster, and the other in glory. Pride does not bring glory and honor; rather, humility is what does that. When we live with humility, willing to submit to Yahweh and live with the fear of Yahweh, then he will exalt us and give us glory and honor.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Tortoise and the Hare,&rdquo; 800-meter runner Taoufik Makhloufi, and financial guru Dave Ramsey</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:12; 15:33</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-12-02', 'Castos', 0, '19:22', 9, 35, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-35-Humility-Leads-to-Glory-Prov.-18.12-15.33-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-35-humility-leads-to-glory-prov-1812-1533-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 39, null),
(1717, 5, 'The Crowns: God&rsquo;s &ldquo;Extra Credit&rdquo; Program', '<p>While fear can be a strong motivator, God&rsquo;s primary method of motivation is love. Therefore, God describes ways in which He will reward Christians who go &ldquo;above and beyond.&rdquo; Every student is familiar with the concept of &ldquo;extra credit.&rdquo; It is usually a question at the end of an assignment or an exam that is not required but provides the student an opportunity to receive bonus points, usually to make up for other questions that the student might have gotten wrong. Teachers, as well as parents and employers, understand that the promise of reward can be a strong incentive to a better effort. In a sense, God has laid out an &ldquo;extra credit&rdquo; program for Christians.</p>', '2013-08-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-crowns-gods-extra-credit-program', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/crowns_gods_extra_credit_program.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 6, null),
(1718, 5, 'What Does the Bible Say About Tattoos?', '<p>Given the rise in popularity of people marking and modifying their bodies in all types of ways, it is only natural that Christians should pause and ask themselves, &ldquo;What does the Bible (God) say about Christians getting tattoos?&rdquo; And also, &ldquo;Is it okay for a Christian to modify (tattoo) the body this way?&rdquo;</p>', '2013-09-23', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-tattoos-can-a-christian-get-a-tattoo', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/tattoos.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 17, null),
(1719, 5, 'The Spiritual Battle Is Fought With sWORDS', '<p>Using words to communicate was God&rsquo;s idea. Read the first chapter of Genesis and you&rsquo;ll see the phrase &ldquo;God said&rdquo; ten times. Then two chapters later, not long after Adam and Eve were created and living in Paradise, they entered into the spiritual battle. It was a battle they weren&rsquo;t looking for, and in fact it&rsquo;s a battle they didn&rsquo;t even start. It was a battle of obedience expressed and fought through words. God said &ldquo;you will die, yes, die&rdquo; (Gen 2:17) and the serpent said &ldquo;No, you will not die&rdquo; (Gen 3:4).</p>', '2019-12-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-spiritual-battle-is-fought-with-swords', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/thats-ironic-3.png', 1, 0, null, 1, 18, null),
(1720, 5, 'We Cannot Follow Two Masters', '<p><strong>We cannot serve God and &ldquo;Wealth&rdquo;</strong><br /> It is a common complaint that people just &ldquo;cannot find the time&rdquo; to do the things with God that they want to do. Many people want to know the Bible better, or have more time to serve God&rsquo;s people, and just never seem to have the time to do it. Sometimes that turns out to be our own fault. Jesus taught that no one can serve two masters.</p>', '2014-03-14', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/we-cannot-follow-two-masters', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/we-cannot-follow-two-masters-truth-or-tradition.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 3, null),
(1721, 5, 'The Ten Commandments', '<p>I&rsquo;m going to be teaching on the Ten Commandments and talking about the relevance of the Ten Commandments in our lives today, and in order to do that, I want to set some of the heart from the New Testament because it&rsquo;s very important that we understand the relationship of the Old Testament Law to the New Testament.</p>', '2013-01-17', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-ten-commandments', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ten_commandments.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 12, null),
(1722, 5, 'Do Christians need to be married by a minister or can we just commit to each other privately in God&rsquo;s sight?', '<p><strong>Q:</strong> My girlfriend and I are totally in love and are committed to be together the rest of our lives. My family thinks that we should &ldquo;officially&rdquo; get married. Do we have to get married by a minister or a justice of the peace, or is it okay if two Christians just commit themselves privately to each other in God&rsquo;s sight?</p> <p><strong>A:</strong> The short answer to that question is that a person should get &ldquo;legally married,&rdquo; not just make a private commitment, and there are several reasons for that answer. Marriage is what is known as a &ldquo;creation ordinance,&rdquo; meaning a rule that God designed for every living person, in contrast to a &ldquo;Christian ordinance,&rdquo; or a rule applying only to Christians.</p>', '2013-08-08', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/do-christians-need-to-be-married-by-a-minister-or-can-we-just-commit-to-each-other-privately-in-gods-sight', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mairrage.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 41, null),
(1723, 5, 'What does the Bible Say About Divorce?', '<p>The institution of marriage between a man and a woman goes back to the beginning of Creation and has been recognized by every culture as the foundation of both family and civilization itself. God created two sexes, &ldquo;male and female&rdquo; (Gen. 1:27, 5:2), and He did so for the mutual benefit of both genders. The man and the woman bring different strengths into the relationship, and by doing so strengthen both the relationship and the family.</p>', '2013-09-16', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/what-does-the-bible-say-about-divorce', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/divorce.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 34, null),
(1724, 5, 'Seven Spiritual Battlefields', '<p>Most Christians are familiar with the phrase &ldquo;the spiritual battle,&rdquo; a term used to describe the war raging between the forces of good and evil. It is the ageless war between light and darkness, between God and His archenemy, the Devil. Unfortunately, all humankind&mdash;every man, woman, and child who has ever lived&mdash;is in the middle of the war, caught between the two great opposing armies. The war that started in the heavens above has spilled over the borders of the spirit realm into the Earth.</p>', '2019-06-17', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/seven-spiritual-battlefields', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/7-Spiritual-Battlefields.png', 1, 0, null, 1, 18, null),
(1725, 5, 'Articles in Korean', '<p>The following Korean articles are in PDF format. The articles could not be posted how we would normally post them because of font and formatting problems. We are sorry for the inconvenience. If you are unable to view these articles in PDF format, <a href="http://www.stfonline.org/contact/" target="_blank">please</a> <a href="http://www.stfonline.org/contact/" target="_blank">contact us</a> and we will be glad to mail you a copy of them.</p>', '2014-03-10', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://www.truthortradition.com/korean', 'https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/z/mini-i-love-you-hand-korean-heart-finger-sign-icon-vector-line-art-illustration-sticker-design-social-media-gesture-185130843.jpg', 0, 0, null, 9, 1, null),
(1726, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/06/2020) – Covenants: Part 16 Covenants & the Sacred Secret Part 5', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:29', 0, 0, null, 'CnX78gT8kgw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CnX78gT8kgw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1727, 1, 'Zechariah and Elizabeth', '<p>This teaching starts in Luke 1:5 and expounds on the beginning of the record of the birth of John the Baptist, the forerunner of Jesus Christ. It covers both the historical facts of the record and many lessons we can learn from the text as well.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:5-26; Luke 3:1; 2 Chron. 4:7-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:47', 0, 0, 'history', 'paZREqnRCto', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/paZREqnRCto/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1728, 1, 'Saul and the Medium at En-dor', '<p>The Bible warns people about getting involved with demons and people who deal with demons, such as mediums who contact the demonic world. This teaching covers 1 Samuel 28 and 31, where Saul goes to the woman medium at En-dor and explains that demons come into forms that fool people and allow the demons to feed them false or harmful information.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Samuel 28; 31:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:45', 0, 0, null, 'WVF4qQ8kzh4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WVF4qQ8kzh4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 26, null),
(1729, 5, 'When Will Believers Receive Their Rewards?', '<p>[This article was taken from our book <a href="http://stfonlinestore.com/hope.aspx" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="The Christian''s Hope">The Christian&rsquo;s Hope: The Anchor of the Soul</a>.]</p> <p>The Bible promises that those who obey God will be rewarded in the future. However, there is no verse of Scripture that specifically says specifically how or when the rewards will be given. It is very likely that an individual&rsquo;s reward will not be handed out all at once, as if it were a lump-sum cash gift, but rather that it will be given out over time. Since rewards can be positions and assignments in the Kingdom, it is logical that many of the rewards will be &ldquo;lived out&rdquo; year after year.</p>', '2013-08-19', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/when-will-believers-receive-their-rewards', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/when_will_christians_receive_rewards.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 8, null),
(1730, 5, 'Understanding Healing in its Biblical Context', '<p>We are going to be covering the following three aspects of healing:</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>1)</strong> the patron/client model of the New Testament<br /> <strong>2)</strong> an idiom used in the Bible called the prophetic perfect<br /> <strong>3)</strong> the communion service</p> </blockquote> <p>All three of these need to be understood in order to really understand the field of healing.</p>', '2013-08-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/understanding-healing-in-its-biblical-context', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/understanding_healing_biblical_context.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 31, null),
(1731, 5, 'The Synagogue', '<p>We get the English &ldquo;synagogue&rdquo; by transliterating the Greek sunagoge, which means, &ldquo;a bringing together&rdquo; (from sunago, to gather together). In its earliest usage, sunagoge did not refer to a building or place of gathering, but rather to the group of people who were gathered together. The Greek word &ldquo;synagogue&rdquo; is used more than 200 times in the Septuagint for gatherings of people, but never for a building where people gathered. Later, as the buildings for gathering developed, sunagoge became used of the &ldquo;gathering place&rdquo; as well as the people gathered. Thus, the word &ldquo;synagogue&rdquo; is similar to the English word &ldquo;church&rdquo; in that it can refer to the people who gather together or the place where the people gather together.</p>', '2013-09-28', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/the-synagogue', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/synagogue.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 5, null),
(1732, 5, 'Who is Jesus Christ?', '<p><strong>We believe that Jesus Christ is a completely unique (one of a kind) human being.</strong></p> <p>Why?</p> <p><strong>He is the only man ever born by way of God putting a seed in the womb of a virgin</strong> (Matt. 1:18; Luke 1:35). God put a perfect seed in the womb of Mary so that Jesus would be born without the sin nature that every other human being inherited from the First Adam. Therefore, Jesus is the only-begotten Son of God (John 3:16) and the Son of Man (John 5:27)&hellip;.</p>', '2013-01-13', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/who-is-jesus-christ', 'https://spiritandtruthonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/who-is-jesus-christ-truth-or-tradition.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 26, null),
(1733, 1, 'Mary and the Angel Gabriel', '<p>When Elizabeth was six months pregnant with John the Baptist, the angel Gabriel was sent to tell Mary that she would give birth to the Messiah. This teaching expounds on Luke 1:26-38 and the details of that section of Scripture, including where Mary was when Gabriel came to her, the meaning of what he said to her, and her responses.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:29-38</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:26', 0, 0, null, 'p3ZDuNfEb-g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/p3ZDuNfEb-g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 23, null),
(1734, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/13/2020) - Store Up Treasures in Heaven', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:00', 0, 0, null, 'MhS1YcQGKcY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MhS1YcQGKcY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1735, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 36 | Injustice is an Abomination (Prov. 17.15; 24.23-25)', '<p>Justice is something that Yahweh God cares deeply about. Judicial systems are set up to maintain justice, but they are flawed. Sometimes the innocent are convicted while the guilty go free. In Yahweh&rsquo;s eyes, any perversion of justice is an abomination. He is disgusted when wrong is called right, and right is called wrong. How can we strive to live with justice in our lives with the fear of Yahweh?</p> <p>Illustration: Horace Roberts, wrongfully convicted of a crime but exonerated 20 years later by DNA testing.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 17:15; 24:23-25</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2020-12-18', 'Castos', 0, '20:21', 9, 36, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-36-Injustice-is-an-Abomination-Prov.-17.15-24.23-25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-36-injustice-is-an-abomination-prov-1715-2423-25', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 28, null),
(1736, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/20/2020) - God Moving', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2020-12-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:13', 0, 0, null, 'mXBwmf1BNT4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mXBwmf1BNT4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 1, null),
(1737, 1, 'A Believer&rsquo;s Life Can Be Difficult', '<p>Many people believe that if someone lives righteously, their life will be free from troubles, but the scriptures show us that even a righteous person will go through difficulties in their life. This teaching shows several examples from the Bible of people who lived righteously but encountered major difficulties in their lives.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:5-7, Hebrews 11:32-38, Matthew 5:10-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:22', 0, 0, null, 'tXb2TQHJmmM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tXb2TQHJmmM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1738, 1, 'Who Were the Shepherds?', '<p>Tradition has depicted the shepherds to whom the angel appeared and announced the birth of the Messiah as poor, untrustworthy, and unrespectable. This teaching debunks that tradition by looking at shepherding from a biblical cultural perspective, illustrating how God&rsquo;s Word repeatedly draws an analogy between leadership of God&rsquo;s people and shepherding.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:7-18; Ezekiel 34:1-16</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2020-12-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:25', 0, 0, null, 'VBC4O_VMGHE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VBC4O_VMGHE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1739, 1, 'The Birth of John the Baptist', '<p>The birth of John the Baptist was a miracle. This teaching expounds Luke 1:57-80 and brings out many of the details of the events surrounding John&rsquo;s birth. The record has many details that make the record rich to read and practical to apply.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:57-80</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:16', 0, 0, null, 'fWEO1EBbXq0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fWEO1EBbXq0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(1740, 1, 'Gift-Giving, A Biblical Perspective', '<p>This teaching takes a fresh look at gift-giving by highlighting three types of exchanges in the Bible: God giving to man, man giving to God, and man giving to man. Often the best gifts create memories, ease someone&rsquo;s difficulties, and are imperfect.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 33:1-11; Matt. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Hickman</p>', '2020-12-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:11', 0, 0, null, 'j4i8W-FxUss', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/j4i8W-FxUss/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1741, 1, 'The Birth of Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching deals with historic misunderstandings and mistranslations of the seven verses surrounding Jesus&rsquo; birth and shows how it was a considerably different event than what is normally taught.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:13', 0, 0, null, 'TrZ_fNe8pjU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TrZ_fNe8pjU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 21, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1742, 1, 'Follow the Word of God, Not Your Heart', '<p>Throughout the Bible, we&rsquo;re given instructions on using wisdom, planning for the future, and setting proper priorities. This teaching discusses why it is important to follow the Word of God and not your heart or what you feel like doing.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew Proverbs 4:5-8; 24:27; 3:5-13; Jer. 2:14-20; 5:5-6; 17:9; Matt. 11:29-30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:13', 0, 0, null, 'sF5RgdlXlOM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sF5RgdlXlOM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(1743, 1, 'The Magi and the Birth of Christ', '<p>There are a lot of false traditions about the magi that obscure the importance of who they were and what they did. For example, they did not arrive the night Jesus was born, they did not follow a star from Parthia to Bethlehem, and there were not three of them, nor are they named in the Bible. This teaching expounds on Matthew 2:1-12 and explains some of what we know about the magi and why they were important to the story of the birth of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 2:1-12; Malachi 4:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:09', 0, 0, null, 'Gw464TLT7q4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gw464TLT7q4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 16, null),
(1744, 1, 'The Shepherds and the Birth of Christ', '<p>This teaching expounds Luke 2:8-20, covers the record of the shepherds at the birth of Christ, and explains why what the angels said to the shepherds was &ldquo;on earth peace among people with whom he is well pleased,&rdquo; rather than &ldquo;peace on earth, good will to people.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:8-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2020-12-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:38', 0, 0, null, 'x5mq6mbT1Kw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/x5mq6mbT1Kw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 12, null),
(1745, 1, 'Where did the Angel Meet Mary', '<p>Arguably one of the most important events in history was when the angel met with Mary and told her that she would be impregnated by God. This teaching expounds on Luke 1:26-38 and includes facts that are not well understood, such as where Mary almost certainly was when the angel appeared to her and spoke with her.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:26-38</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:33', 0, 0, null, 'jX1AtSSUqDQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jX1AtSSUqDQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 20, null),
(1746, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 37 | Don&rsquo;t Misplace Your Confidence (Prov. 25:19)', '<p>What sort of person would you call upon if you were in a pinch and needed help? Should what you know regarding a person&rsquo;s character affect your degree of confidence in them? Wisdom is about having discernment, and therefore, knowing someone&rsquo;s character and established pattern of behavior is important for knowing whether it is wise to put your confidence in them. If a person isn&rsquo;t a &ldquo;faithful&rdquo; individual, then your confidence is misplaced.</p> <p>Illustration: Rescue scene from the movie <em>Toy Story</em> featuring Woody and Buzz Lightyear.</p> <p>Verses: Proverbs 25:19</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-01-07', 'Castos', 0, '16:26', 9, 37, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-37-Don-t-Misplace-Your-Confidence-25.19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-37-dont-misplace-your-confidence-prov-2519-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1747, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/03/2021) – Dealing with Doubts – The Choice is Yours', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '17:59', 0, 0, null, '8fE_7la_2f4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8fE_7la_2f4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1748, 1, 'Take Heed to What You Believe and Do', '<p>This teaching addresses the two things that matter most in life&mdash;getting saved and living in a way that pleases God and will result in rewards in the coming Kingdom&mdash;and explores 2 Corinthians 5:10 and Matthew 24:1-8.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 24:1-28; 2 Cor. 5:9-10; Prov. 4:10-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:32', 0, 0, null, 'ZEabjMmv5Hc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZEabjMmv5Hc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1749, 1, 'Learn from the Torah', '<p>This teaching explores the need to know how God wants us to live and to think like He thinks. It addresses the &ldquo;Torah,&rdquo; the &ldquo;Instruction&rdquo; from God, and various laws and regulations from Exodus 20, 21, and 22 showing examples of how to think and live that are pertinent today.</p> <p>Verses: Exodus 20:1-17; 21:1-19; 22:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:05', 0, 0, null, 'Y3wRu97uRYg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Y3wRu97uRYg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(1750, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/10/2021) – God Loved us First – Part 1', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:17', 0, 0, null, 'S2q3ja-CQ0I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S2q3ja-CQ0I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Not active', 1, 0, null),
(1751, 1, 'The Lord&rsquo;s Prayer: A Model for How to Pray', '<p>In teaching his disciples and others how to pray, Jesus illustrated prayer to them by giving them a model prayer, which we commonly call the Lord&rsquo;s Prayer. This teaching examines that model phrase by phrase, emphasizing that each element should be an important part of our prayer lives.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:5-13; Luke 11:5-9; Matt. 4:8,9; 2 Cor. 4:3,4; Prov. 2:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:58', 0, 0, null, '3ryBWXPhR80', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3ryBWXPhR80/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(1752, 1, 'Do Not Fear Other gods', '<p>This teaching looks at 2 Kings 17 and the failure of King Hoshea. There are many parallels between the chaos, hatred, double crossings, political wrangling, and evilness we see in society/politics today and the time of Hoshea. Today&rsquo;s social and political climates cause much trepidation and fear, but we need not to be afraid; God makes that clear in this timely record fitting to today&rsquo;s situations.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 17:1-41</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2021-01-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, null, 0, 0, null, 'mpaowgUf4HA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mpaowgUf4HA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1753, 1, 'The Birth of John the Baptist', '<p>The birth of John the Baptist is an important part of the whole birth narrative involving the Lord Jesus Christ. This teaching expounds on Luke 1:57-66 verse by verse, shares many facts that are not well known, and makes valuable comments about the lessons we can learn from the record.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:57-66, 80</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-15', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:09', 0, 0, null, 'yxKDDOcPVfU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yxKDDOcPVfU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1754, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 38 | Don''t Mess With A Fool (Prov. 17:12)', '<p>We might think of foolishness as a relatively harmless characteristic of a person, but the Book of Proverbs thinks much differently about it. Foolishness is very harmful and destructive. We might not immediately perceive the wickedness in foolishness, but its consequences will come to bite everyone who is involved. Danger abounds when we encounter a fool in their foolishness, so we must be wise and cautious to avoid it.</p> <p>Illustration: Bear attack in Montana, and three friends killed on a fishing trip in Florida.</p> <p>Verses: Proverbs 17:12</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-01-15', 'Castos', 0, '13:38', 9, 38, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-38-Don-t-Mess-With-A-Fool-Prov.-17.12-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-38-dont-mess-with-a-fool-prov-1712', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 56, null),
(1755, 1, 'A Prayer for the New Year', '<p>This teaching looks at the opening prayer in Paul&rsquo;s letter to the Thessalonians to provide encouragement and comfort during persecution. The main points are: 1) Trust in God as the source for our energy to work and labor, 2) Persecution can be the catalyst for REVIVAL, and 3) The darker the night, the brighter the light.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 46; Proverbs 3:5-6; Isaiah 54:10; Matt. 5:14-16; Acts 8:1-8; 1 Thess. 1:2-10; 1 Peter 5:10</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2021-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:51', 0, 0, null, 'RFDrfxyFUo4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RFDrfxyFUo4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1756, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/17/2021) - Saved by Grace, Rewarded by Works', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:21', 0, 0, null, 'X4-nvtZtum8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X4-nvtZtum8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1757, 1, 'Control Your Thoughts and Change Your Life', '<p>God created man in His image. Part of that image is that we are autonomous beings with the ability to think, reason, experience emotion, and make decisions. We have the ability to &ldquo;program&rdquo; what we think about&mdash;and in many ways, what we think about is what we are. Our goal as Christians is to become Christlike, and as we put on the Word of God and think the thoughts of God, we will draw closer to reaching that goal.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26-27; 3:22; 6:6-7; Exod. 32:9-14; Prov. 3:25; 23:7; Deut. 30:19; Josh. 24:15; Ps. 18; Phil. 4:6, 8; Rom 12:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Rob Woods</p>', '2021-01-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:59', 0, 0, null, 'ZkDRXmDGZ5Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZkDRXmDGZ5Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1758, 1, 'Shaken: Learning to trust God and the things that Remain', '<p>When things fall apart in our lives, we are often shaken. This teaching explores 1 Thessalonians 2-3 and the Psalms. Paul had a great concern for the Thessalonian church being young in their Christian Faith and afflicted by the Adversary, shaking their world and his. The example of King David further shows how trusting God and leaning on your relationship with Him can help as you turn your troubles over to God and turn it to prayer and praise.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thessalonians 2:17-3:10, Hebrews 12:27-28, Psalms 121, Psalms 63, Psalms 62</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2021-01-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:55', 0, 0, null, 'b7Cz5NELnSc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b7Cz5NELnSc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1759, 1, 'Renewed Thankfulness', '<p>When someone does something for us, we show how much we appreciate them by saying &ldquo;Thank You.&rdquo; We are instructed to give thanks to God for all He has done, but like all things in life, we run the risk of becoming complacent and taking Him for granted. This teaching reminds us of the important of always living in gratitude toward God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 16:34; Col. 2:6-7</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:40', 0, 0, null, 'EG4d0w16168', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EG4d0w16168/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1760, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 39 | Lady Folly is a Fraud - Pt 1 (Prov. 9.13-18)', '<p>Lady Folly is a personification of the attribute of foolishness. She imitates wisdom as she tries to seduce people to listen to her, offering enticing and appealing things to lure na&iuml;ve people into her trap. But that is like any replica, it is designed to look like the authentic. If we know what to look for and if we examine where the road leads, we can easily spot that Lady Folly is a complete fraud.</p> <p>Illustration: Wolfgang Beltracchi, the most famous art forger of all time.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 9:13-18</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-01-22', 'Castos', 0, '17:08', 9, 39, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-39-Lady-Folly-is-a-Fraud-Pt-1-9.13-18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-39-lady-folly-is-a-fraud-pt-1-prov-913-18-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(1761, 1, 'Fear is the Enemy of Boldness', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:30', 0, 0, null, 'Skw0hr52UNE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Skw0hr52UNE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1762, 1, 'The Interpretation of Speaking in Tongues (Part 1)', '<p>The Manifestation of the Interpretation of Tongues is not well understood in the Church, but it is an important part of the manifestations of holy spirit. This teaching lays a foundation for better understanding the Interpretation of speaking in tongues by going over the gift of holy spirit that believers receive in the New Birth and the biblical records of the manifestation of speaking in tongues.</p> <p>Verses: John 7:37-39; Eph. 4:30; 2 Cor. 3:10; Acts 2:10-11; 10:46; 1 Cor. 14:1-5, 14-17, 39</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:35', 0, 0, null, 'F4edJY-neOI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F4edJY-neOI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 11, null),
(1763, 1, '1st Things 1st; (and 2nd Things 2nd)', '<p>In this teaching we take another look at the greatest and first commandment, and the second which is like it, from Matthew 22. From a place of loving Yahweh with all that we are, and with the gift of holy spirit empowering us, we are then able to love others well, do the Lord&rsquo;s work, and assist each other in building the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses:  Matthew 22:34-40; Deuteronomy 30:15-20; Galatians 2:20, 5:13-22, 6:1-10; Ephesians 4:29-32.</p> <p>Teacher:  Janet Speakes</p>', '2021-01-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:38', 0, 0, null, 'urgL4PmZdAo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/urgL4PmZdAo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 7, null),
(1764, 1, 'Fellow-workers with God: being witnesses', '<p>The Bible calls believers &ldquo;fellow-workers with God&rdquo;. An important part of that work is being witnesses of the things of God and what He has done. But many times, it seems that a Christian&rsquo;s efforts to witness to others fall on deaf ears. This teaching shows that there are times when it is very helpful to God that we witness, even if from a human perspective it does not seem to do any good.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 3:9; Acts 1:8; Jer. 7:27; Luke 21:12-19; Matt. 12:41-42; Matt. 10:5-13, Luke 9:21-26; Rev. 20:11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-01-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:40', 0, 0, null, 'qtz_2KIBolo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qtz_2KIBolo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(1765, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 40 | Lady Folly is a Fraud - Pt 2 (Prov. 9.17)', '<p>The voice of Lady Folly tempts people to see sweet and pleasant things in what is mischievous and rebellious. Her allure is in the excitement and thrill of getting away with what we want. But she doesn&rsquo;t tell you that her rewards are superficial and temporary, and they often come with drastic consequences. She calls out to people, inviting them to join her in secret pleasures, but little do they know that, in the end, it will always leave a bitter taste in their mouths.</p> <p>Illustration: Jordan Belfort, stockbroker busted for investment fraud, nicknamed &ldquo;The Wolf of Wall Street&rdquo;.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 9:17</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-01', 'Castos', 0, '15:22', 9, 40, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-40-Lady-Folly-is-a-Fraud-Pt-2-9.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-40-lady-folly-is-a-fraud-pt-2-prov-917', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(1766, 1, 'The Interpretation of Speaking in Tongues (Part 2)', '<p>This teaching is Part 2 of the series on the Manifestation of the Interpretation of Tongues. This teaching goes into topics such as how the human mind can get in the way of the message the Lord is trying to give, the value for people to try to interpret tongues and prophesy regularly, the importance of building a &ldquo;praise vocabulary,&rdquo; and more.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>Verses: Hebrews 5:14; 1 Cor. 14:1-22, 27; 1 Cor. 12:7-10; Isa. 28:1-13</p>', '2021-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:13', 0, 0, null, 'YiKi8S4LTTM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YiKi8S4LTTM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1767, 1, 'What is Intolerance and Who is Intolerant?', '<p>This teaching addresses the accusation levied at Christians in our culture today that we are intolerant; it explores the question &ldquo;Was Jesus intolerant?&rdquo; and contends that he was direct, specific, and inflexible about truth, but was all-welcoming, inviting all who hunger and thirst while holding an intolerant line with regard to sin. His stance was not &ldquo;popular&rdquo; in his time, and is still not today.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 11:20-30</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-01-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:38', 0, 0, null, '6zun_VdioK8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6zun_VdioK8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1768, 1, 'Lessons from the record of David and Bathsheba', '<p>This teaching covers 2 Samuel 11 and 12&mdash;the record of David and Bathsheba&mdash;diving into much of the chapters verse by verse and pulling lessons from the text on character and many other subjects. People have many crossroads in their life where they have to make choices as to how they will behave, and in these chapters we see people who made good choices and stood on morals, and people who made bad choices.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Samuel 11-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:57', 0, 0, null, '-qXsLM1vReo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-qXsLM1vReo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1793, null),
(1817, 1, 'Looking at Intolerance (continued)', '<p>This teaching addresses the accusation levied at Christians in our culture today that we are intolerant. By looking at the various &ldquo;I am the&hellip;&rdquo; statements in the Gospel of John (I am the bread of life; I am the light of the world; I am the good shepherd, etc), it illustrates that Jesus was inviting yet direct to all who hungered and thirsted, and confrontational when he needed to be.</p> <p>Verses: John 6:30-37; 8:12; 10:1-11; 11:25-26; 14:3-6; 15:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-02-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:16', 0, 0, null, 'lN8giwBLBYc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lN8giwBLBYc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1818, 1, 'Titus 1. The Need for Good Leaders and Good People', '<p>This teaching expounds on Titus 1:4-16, covering the chapter verse by verse. In it we see the need for, and qualifications of, good leaders. We also see that good leaders must be strong, because so many people, even some believers, are rebellious and in error. In Titus, Paul instructs his titular disciple in being the best leader possible.</p> <p>Verses: Titus 1:4-16; Eph. 4:7-12; Jer. 7:3-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:28', 0, 0, null, 'NcnhrL7D_fs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NcnhrL7D_fs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(1820, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/07/2021) – God&rsquo;s Heart for You - Life', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-02-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:01', 0, 0, null, 'pTiR8eiuhtM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pTiR8eiuhtM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null);
