(1821, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 41 | Finding Lady Wisdom - Pt 1 (Prov. 9.1-6)', '<p>Lady Wisdom is a personification of the attribute of wisdom. She invites people to come and dine with her as a metaphor for listening to her and learning from her. In her presence, her guests can experience many wonderful and satisfying things that show how gracious and beneficial she is to those who accept her invitation. If this is a picture of what life is like by having wisdom, then we should desire to find Lady Wisdom and enjoy the good life that only she can provide.</p> <p>Illustration: Preston Bailey, internationally acclaimed event designer, who has designed some of the most elaborate event decorations.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 9:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-09', 'Castos', 0, '18:14', 9, 41, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-41-Finding-Lady-Wisdom-Pt-1-Prov.-9.1-6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-41-finding-lady-wisdom-pt-1-prov-91-6-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1822, 7, 'Old Testament Chronology', '<p>One of the most challenging fields of biblical study is Old Testament chronology. The chronology of the Old Testament contains some of the most glaring apparent contradictions in the Scriptures. To properly reconcile these, a person needs to understand the difference between accession counting and non-accession counting, and understand that at times different calendars were used by the kingdoms of Judah and the northern tribes of Israel, frequently at the same time. This paper by John Schoenheit explains these counting systems and calendars, and addresses many of the more difficult sections of Old Testament chronology.</p>', '2021-02-10', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/Old_Testament_Chronology.docx', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQCxLjxziWf62jEXHBHErEXremBLKEYrxk7Cw&usqp=CAU', 1, 0, 'Do not change the file!  This is linked to several times in the chronology', 1, 36, null),
(1823, 1, 'Pray for Your Leaders', '<p>There&rsquo;s a lot of talk surrounding Christianity and politics, but what does the Bible have to say about government and politics? This teaching briefly explains what the Bible tells us about government and the importance of praying for our leaders.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: Gabe Hickman</p> <p>[This video was originally recorded in November 2020 during the U.S. presidential election season.]</p>', '2021-02-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '5:38', 0, 0, null, 'SrvhGYivJOc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SrvhGYivJOc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1825, 7, 'The Talmud', '<p>The Talmud (Hebrew for &ldquo;study&rdquo;) is one of the central works of the Jewish people. It is the record of rabbinic teachings that spans a period of about six hundred years, beginning in the first century C.E. and continuing through the sixth and seventh centuries C.E. The rabbinic teachings of the Talmud explain in great detail how the commandments of the Torah were to be carried out.</p>', '2021-02-12', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/Babylonian-Talmud.pdf', 'https://www.jewishbookcouncil.org/sites/default/files/styles/large_landscape/public/images/talmud-study.jpg', 1, 0, null, 1, 14, null),
(1827, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Spiritual Growth in the Face of Persecution (Part 1)', '<p>Not too long after Paul wrote a first letter, he wrote a second to the Thessalonians. With the historical and cultural background in mind, it is no surprise that Paul is commending this young church for their spiritual growth in the midst of suffering and persecution. Paul opens this letter with much enthusiasm and praise for the immense trust and love shown by the Thessalonian believers.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 1:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:35', 62, 1, null, 'HoxDvaWLYN4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HoxDvaWLYN4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1828, 1, 'Colossians 2: Standing Strong for Christ', '<p>This teaching expounds on Colossians 2, covering the chapter verse by verse. The believers at Colossae were bombarded with different belief systems, including such things as the worship of angels, so Paul encourages them to be rooted and grounded in the Christian Faith, that is, understand what they believe and why.</p> <p>Verses: Colossians 2:1-23; Romans 6:3-6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:30', 0, 0, null, '5iThT8bHuxo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5iThT8bHuxo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(1829, 1, 'Titus 2 and 3. Directives to God&rsquo;s People in the Church', '<p>This teaching expounds on Titus 2 and 3, mostly verse by verse. The church in Crete was young and needed direction on how to live in such a manner that they pleased God and made the Word of God attractive to others, so in Titus 2, the Bible speaks in turn to leaders, to older men, to older women, to younger women, to younger men, and to slaves, and gives direction in how to live. An important theme in Titus 3 is the permanence of salvation.</p> <p>Verses: Titus 2:1-15; 3:1-8; Gen. 4:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:12', 0, 0, null, 'Mmo9sV1dDec', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Mmo9sV1dDec/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(1830, 1, 'Hungry for God: Zacchaeus', '<p>The Bible is full of records of men and women who love God and rise above the social pressures around them to obey and follow Him. The Bible shows us that Zacchaeus, a chief tax collector, was such as man. This teaching expounds on the record of Zacchaeus, which has a lot of keys and principles we can learn from, including keys to standing up against social pressure.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 18:24-34; 19:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:47', 0, 0, null, 'oV_3FyIQnEI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oV_3FyIQnEI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(1831, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Comfort Concerning the Righteous Judgment of God (Part 2)', '<p>Paul reminds the Thessalonians of God&rsquo;s righteous judgment, and how even though they are currently suffering, God is going to do something about it when the Lord Jesus returns. Jesus is going to give them relief and punish those who are afflicting them. By pointing people toward the hope, we can comfort them with the coming judgment of God. He will execute justice and set things right in the world.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 1:5-8</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:14', 62, 2, null, 'dULTCn-NUTE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dULTCn-NUTE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1832, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 42 | Finding Lady Wisdom - Pt 2 (Prov. 9.6)', '<p>In a succinct and powerful statement, Lady Wisdom exhorts listeners to &ldquo;Leave their na&iuml;ve ways and live.&rdquo; We all have areas of foolishness in our lives, but sometimes changing our habits and ways of thinking is difficult and takes time and determination. But walking on the road of understanding will yield a life that cannot be achieved with foolishness. We must turn away from and leave it behind in order to experience the life that Yahweh intends for us to have.</p> <p>Illustration: The Parable of the Prodigal Son (Luke 15:11-24) &ndash; the younger son comes to his senses and leaves his foolish ways behind.</p> <p>Verses: Proverbs 9:6</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-22', 'Castos', 0, '20:08', 9, 42, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-42-Finding-Lady-Wisdom-Pt-2-Prov.-9.6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-42-finding-lady-wisdom-pt-2-prov-96', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1833, 1, 'Love One Another', '<p>This teaching looks closely at the span of time from Jesus&rsquo; Triumphal Entry in Jerusalem to Gethsemane, presenting a chart of the events, his audience, his location, and the topics he taught. One of those topics was &ldquo;love one another,&rdquo; also thought of as &ldquo;taking care of one another,&rdquo; which is the focus of this teaching.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:31-40; John 13:34-35; 15:9-17; Rom. 15:7</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-02-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:58', 0, 0, null, 'Z-a99_7r5Dg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Z-a99_7r5Dg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(1834, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/21/2021) - Accountability', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-02-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '19:26', 0, 0, null, '6uCepa35XsU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6uCepa35XsU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1835, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/14/2021) - Love Stories', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-02-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:08', 0, 0, null, 'mkv7KiU0B7k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mkv7KiU0B7k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1836, 1, 'Reigniting Your Gift', '<p>God has gifted each of us in unique ways to multiply for His kingdom, but if we&rsquo;re not careful, those gifts can lose their spark. This teaching uses anecdotal experiencing to explore the things that can impede, dim, or make us feel completely cut off from our spiritual gifts&mdash;and encourages us that it&rsquo;s not too late to reignite that spark!</p> <p>Teacher: Renee Dugan</p>', '2021-02-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:19', 0, 0, null, '0eRm75D1K40', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0eRm75D1K40/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1837, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | The penalty of everlasting destruction & being counted worthy of his calling (Part 3)', '<p>Paul finally reveals the specifics of God&rsquo;s righteous judgment toward the Thessalonian tormentors&mdash;they will pay the penalty of everlasting destruction when the Lord returns. And to both comfort and challenge the believers in Thessalonica, Paul prays that they will be counted worthy of God&rsquo;s calling, and that God would work powerfully in their lives to accomplish his will.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 1:9-12</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-02-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:20', 62, 3, null, '-riZkQPl6qE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-riZkQPl6qE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1838, 1, 'Christian Living - An Exposition of Romans 12', '<p>Romans 12 has powerful guidance about how to find your ministry and then how to live it in a way that pleases God. This teaching is a verse-by-verse exposition of Romans 12, with helpful explanations about living life as a Christian doing God&rsquo;s will.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 12:1-21; Jeremiah 16:16-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:24', 0, 0, null, 'NdYWs9ztXJk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NdYWs9ztXJk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1839, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/28/2021) – God is Love', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-02-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:51', 0, 0, null, '9gUIDLzqn2o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9gUIDLzqn2o/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1840, 1, 'What Christ Accomplished (Part 1)', '<p>The death of Jesus Christ was a watershed event and many things changed afterward. This teaching, in two parts, covers some of those things. This first is Jesus&rsquo; cry from the cross, &ldquo;It is finished,&rdquo;. The second is the difference between the New Testament epistles which open with &ldquo;Grace and peace,&rdquo; and the Old Testament epistles, which have no such greeting.</p> <p>Verses: John 19:30; Matt. 27:50-51; Num. 1:51; Heb. 4:16; 10:19-22; Eph. 2:13; Eph. 3:1-6; Num. 23:9; 1 Pet. 1:18-19; Titus 2:11-14; Eph. 1:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-02-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:09', 0, 0, null, 'uMjxdNKK38E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uMjxdNKK38E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 17, null),
(1841, 1, 'Grace Came Through Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching looks at one of the many accomplishments of Jesus Christ: the bringing of grace to believers. The grace that was brought by Jesus Christ is different from the conditional favor of God upon various people of the Old Testament. The grace ushered in by the work of Jesus Christ is free to all who trust in him.</p> <p>Verses: Titus 2:11; Rom. 3:19-26; 5:1-2, 15-16; Eph. 2:1-10; Psalm 84</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-03-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:22', 0, 0, null, 'gMWTWvgRwuM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gMWTWvgRwuM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1842, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 43 | The Greatest Treasure (Prov. 2.1-5)', '<p>We desire many things in life, and we often expend much energy striving to attain them. But sometimes we don&rsquo;t put forth the effort that is needed, or we don&rsquo;t stick with it long enough to see the results. We must not have that sort of short-sighted attitude or half-hearted effort in our search for wisdom. Wisdom is like a crown jewel or the finest silver&mdash;wisdom is the greatest treasure. The question is, &ldquo;Do we have the desire and determination to find her?&rdquo;</p> <p>Illustration: Howard Carter and the discovery of the tomb of King Tutankhamun.</p> <p>Verses: Prov 2:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-03-09', 'Castos', 0, '18:50', 9, 43, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-43-The-Greatest-Treasure-Prov.-2.1-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-43-the-greatest-treasure-prov-21-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1843, 1, 'What Christ Accomplished: The New Birth (Part 2)', '<p>The death of Jesus Christ was a watershed event and many things changed afterward. This teaching in several parts covers some of those things, including the New Birth from 1 Peter 1. 2 Corinthians 3:10 says that the glory that Christians have is so glorious that the &ldquo;glory&rdquo; of the Old Testament was no glory at all; it seems likely that the surpassing glory that Christians have is at least in part due to the permanence of salvation that Christians have in comparison with the Old Testament.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Corinthians 3:7-10; 1 Peter 1:1-5; Matt. 19:16-22; Acts 16:25-31; Ezek. 33:12-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:07', 0, 0, null, 'RrBcCEfhAdo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RrBcCEfhAdo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 8, null),
(1844, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Crisis and Correction Regarding the Day of the Lord (Part 4)', '<p>This teaching covers 2 Thessalonians 2:1-5, a passage which would have certainly provided comfort to the Thessalonians regarding their fears about misinformation about the Day of the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess 2:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler, Ellen Fowler</p>', '2021-03-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:59', 62, 4, null, 'HAzCt-ZvNm4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HAzCt-ZvNm4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1845, 1, 'The Christian is Declared Righteous', '<p>This teaching explores how every Christian is &ldquo;declared righteous&rdquo; and thus has right standing before God due to Christ&rsquo;s sacrifice. Then, from that position of righteousness, each believer should be thankful and want to do their best to live a godly life; but succeed or fail, they are still righteous in God&rsquo;s sight because of the death of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 1; Deut. 6:25; Romans 2:26-29; 3:1-2, 21-31; 4:1-3, 23-25; 5:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:30', 0, 0, null, 'cIRxKD3ZJxY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cIRxKD3ZJxY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1846, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | The Coming of the Lawless One (Part 5)', '<p>Before the Day of the Lord comes, the lawless one will be revealed because of the activity of the Adversary when the one restraining him is no longer holding him back; he will deceive many into believing a lie and perform counterfeit signs and wonders. Such disturbing prophecy is matched only by the assurance that when Jesus comes, he will utterly destroy the lawless one.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 2:6-12</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-03-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:22', 62, 5, null, 'ZBEwl8XdGyk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZBEwl8XdGyk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1847, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/14/2021) - Giants and Underdogs - Part 2', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:46', 0, 0, null, '6QnDkbdCPxI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6QnDkbdCPxI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'noon VF..', 1, 0, null),
(1848, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/07/2021) - Giants and Underdogs - Part 1', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-03-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:39', 0, 0, null, '4pAA5PqYOTM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4pAA5PqYOTM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'noon VF..', 1, 0, null),
(1849, 1, 'Christ&rsquo;s Last Supper Prayer (John 17)', '<p>At the close of the Last Supper, Jesus Christ prayed a wonderful and amazing prayer recorded in John 17. This teaching covers the three natural parts of that prayer&mdash;Jesus praying for himself, Jesus praying for his disciples, and Jesus praying for all believers&mdash;and how these are a model for how we should pray as his followers today.</p> <p>Verses: John 17:1-26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:09', 0, 0, null, 'bCC2aGDW5sM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bCC2aGDW5sM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1850, 1, 'Be decisive and make good choices', '<p>This teaching expounds 2 Kings 16:24-17:20 and draws life lessons from the record, not the least of which is the importance of being decisive and being able to make and act on good decisions even in times of great crisis when there is not a lot of time to plan and mull over the correct decision to make. It also shows how God can work in seemingly impossible situations to bring deliverance to His people, because God delivers Israel through a miracle.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 16:24-17:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:46', 0, 0, null, 'TuNjN1xTp4M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TuNjN1xTp4M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1851, 1, 'Do You Have What You Need?', '<p>The Book of Judges shares example after example of God working with people and bringing them great success in situations where they don&rsquo;t seem to have what they would need to get a job done. One lesson Christians need to learn is that, while it is nice to have everything we think we need to accomplish a task, often if we will just work with what we have and trust God to help, we can do what we need to do.</p> <p>Verses: Judges 3:31; 4:21; 15:15.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '10:28', 0, 0, null, 'vdppVyM0IQ8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vdppVyM0IQ8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1852, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/21/2021) – Peace from Trust', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-03-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:56', 0, 0, null, 'Pb8k8OtA9sY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Pb8k8OtA9sY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'from Sunday noon VF', 1, 0, null);
