(1853, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Stand Firm and Hold on to the Traditions (Part 6)', '<p>Life is filled with activities, perspectives, and values that are handed down from one generation to another. These become traditions in our countries, communities, and families. Some traditions are good, but some are not. Nevertheless, certain traditions (like the apostles&rsquo; teaching) need to be held on to firmly and not forgotten. God&rsquo;s truth revealed through the apostles is a tradition we should stand firm upon and not waver regardless of what we see or hear.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Thess. 2:13-17</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-03-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:07', 62, 6, null, 'qS364UpklqQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qS364UpklqQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1854, 1, 'A Simple Look at the Christian Life', '<p>This teaching looks at the Christian Life from the perspective of &ldquo;righteous requirements, divine discipline, and holy habits.&rdquo; We have the blessing and advantage of the written word of God to guide us in our day-to-day life, but we must be disciplined enough to do what the Bible says. Having holy habits such as prayer, Bible reading, giving of material blessings, and fellowship with other Christians takes some of the pressure off and a godly life becomes much easier.</p> <p>Verses: John 17:1-26 Rom. 7:12-16; 1 Tim. 1:8; Rom. 1:5; 16:25-27; Gal. 5:22-23; Prov. 25:28; 2 Tim. 1:7; 1 Pet. 1:6; 2 Tim. 3:3; Heb. 10:25; Ps. 106:3; Phil. 4:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:29', 0, 0, null, 'urzqAcmoL8M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/urzqAcmoL8M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1855, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/28/2021) - The Ultimate Hero', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-03-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:21', 0, 0, null, '2Z43x7ljPU4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2Z43x7ljPU4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1856, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 44 | Wisdom Comes From Yahweh (Prov. 2.6-8)', '<p>The Book of Proverbs is filled with wisdom, but where does that wisdom come from? Many of the proverbs are the words of Solomon, but their origin lies with Yahweh who is the source of all wisdom. If we desire to have true wisdom in life, then we must seek Yahweh with all our heart and ask him to give us wisdom so that we can live in righteousness, integrity, and humility.</p> <p>Illustration: King Solomon receiving wisdom from God to administer justice among the people of Israel</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:6-8</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-03-29', 'Castos', 0, '16:41', 9, 44, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-44-Wisdom-Comes-From-Yahweh-Prov.-2.6-8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep4-2', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 39, null),
(1857, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/04/2021) - The Resurrection - in Chronological order', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-04-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:12', 0, 0, null, 'fVlKuBVhmYQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fVlKuBVhmYQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'noon VF, not active', 1, 0, null),
(1858, 1, 'The Valley of the Shadow of Death', '<p>Jesus crossed the Kidron Valley four times during his last week before being crucified. This teaching gives some insight as to what Jesus Christ might have been thinking and what gave him hope during this time in his life.</p> <p>Verses: John 12:1-8, 27, 28: Psalm 23, Ezekiel 37</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2021-03-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:00', 0, 0, null, '-PW4IE_lR2A', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-PW4IE_lR2A/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1859, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | The Lord&rsquo;s Work in Paul&rsquo;s Ministry (Part 7)', '<p>As a minister for the Lord, Paul encountered much opposition in his ministry. As in our modern day, the message of Christ was met with criticism and unbelief. Prayer is vital to complete the work God has called His servants to accomplish. To this end, Paul conveyed his confidence that the Lord Jesus would enable the Thessalonians to follow his instructions and continue in faithful obedience.</p> <p>Verses:  2 Thess. 3:1-5</p> <p>Teacher:  Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-03-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:07', 62, 7, null, 'JfF_igWMWPE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/JfF_igWMWPE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1860, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/11/2021) – The Power of the Voice', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-04-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '16:47', 0, 0, null, '5u_Ai2ENaTI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5u_Ai2ENaTI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'not active', 1, 0, null),
(1861, 1, 'Psalm 22 and Jesus&rsquo; Cry from the Cross', '<p>When Jesus was hanging on the cross, he cried out, &ldquo;My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?&rdquo; Although it is commonly taught that God forsook Jesus because Jesus became sin, that is not what was happening. Jesus was not forsaken by God; Jesus was quoting the first verse of Psalm 22. By quoting that verse, Jesus was pointing people to Psalm 22, which is the clearest picture of the crucifixion in the entire Bible. This teaching covers Psalm 22 verse by verse and shows the parallels between it and the crucifixion.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 27:39, 43, 46, 47; Mark 15:34; John 8:28; 12:32-33; 19:23-24, 28; Ps. 129:3; 22:1-31.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '59:26', 0, 0, null, '7eXLcMdHis0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7eXLcMdHis0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1862, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 45 | Wisdom Will Guard You (Prov. 2.9-11)', '<p>Wisdom is a multi-faceted reality that can be described as consisting of understanding, insight, discretion, discernment, and many other important qualities. The practical value of wisdom is that it safeguards us against making bad choices and suffering the consequences of foolish mistakes. In this way, wisdom is our protector and guardian, watching over us and helping us, if we will let wisdom come into our heart and be willing to learn what it means to be wise.</p> <p>Illustration: Netflix CEO Reed Hastings&rsquo; vision for online movie streaming to avoid company failure and bankruptcy and to lead the entertainment industry into a new age.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:9-11</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-04-13', 'Castos', 0, '15:10', 9, 45, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-45-Wisdom-Will-Guard-You-Prov.-2.9-11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-45-wisdom-will-guard-you-prov-29-11', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(1863, 1, 'The Last Days of Christ&rsquo;s Life', '<p>This teaching covers the last days of Jesus Christ&rsquo;s life. That part of Christ&rsquo;s life is buried in tradition, and it is helpful to see what the Bible really says and what we can know. A large part of this teaching is showing a map of Jerusalem at the time of Christ; where he was taken from Monday afternoon when he ate the Last Supper to Wednesday morning when he was crucified. This teaching will be of interest to anyone who wants to know what happened to Christ in his last days on earth.</p> <p>Verses: John 18:13, 24; Luke 22:66; 23:1-12.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-03-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:20', 0, 0, null, 'AxRrXpyAhH0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AxRrXpyAhH0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1864, 1, 'How Jesus&rsquo; Death Could Pay for Our Sin', '<p>This teaching covers many of the &ldquo;whys&rdquo; about substitutionary sacrifice and much of its history from its inception in Genesis 3 and forward. It looks at the sacrifices of Cain and Abel, Noah&rsquo;s sacrifice of animals, Abraham&rsquo;s almost sacrifice of Isaac, and the sin offerings in the Tabernacle and Temple that pointed to the sacrifice of Christ for the sins of humankind.</p> <p>Verses:  Gen. 1:29-30; 3:21; 4:3-7; 8:20; 2 Cor. 5:21;</p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:49', 0, 0, null, 'DWMHhaYOITM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DWMHhaYOITM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 24, null),
(1866, 1, 'Substitutionary Sacrifice: How Jesus&rsquo; Death Could Pay for Our Sin', '<p>This teaching covers many of the &ldquo;whys&rdquo; about substitutionary sacrifice and much of its history from its inception in Genesis 3 and forward. It looks at the sacrifices of Cain and Abel, Noah&rsquo;s sacrifice of animals, Abraham&rsquo;s almost sacrifice of Isaac, and the sin offerings in the Tabernacle and Temple that pointed to the sacrifice of Christ for the sins of humankind.</p> <p>Verses:  John 18:13, 24; Luke 22:66; 23:1-12. Gen. 1:29; 2:16-17; 3:21; 4:3-4; 8:20; 12:7; 22:2, 4, 6, 8; Heb. 11:17-19; Lev. 4:4, 18-21; 2 Cor. 5:21; Matt. 20:28.</p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:37', 0, 0, null, '84LcSruKtZQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/84LcSruKtZQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 1, null),
(1867, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Discipline in the disorderly (Part 8)', '<p>As a minister of Jesus Christ, Paul dealt with a problem of some of the believers in the Thessalonian church who were conducting themselves with disorderly behavior. Specifically, some were freeloading and sponging off the generosity of other believers. Paul tackles the problem head-on and shows by both his example and his teaching how they were to correct the problem, insisting that believers are not to be lazy but instead be productive and provide for themselves. This section provides us with insight and guidance on how to deal with difficult issues in the church.</p> <p>Verses:  2 Thess. 3:6-12</p> <p>Teacher:  Jeff Tyler &amp; Ellen Fowler</p>', '2021-04-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:02', 62, 8, null, 'LL9ozRArE6U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LL9ozRArE6U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1868, 1, '2 Thessalonians Series | Disciplining the Rebellious Idlers (Part 9)', '<p>Sometimes people in the church decide they don&rsquo;t want to obey the Lord and forsake their sinful ways. Such people cannot be ignored, and for those in Thessalonica, the Apostle Paul suggests a particular course of disciplinary action. But he makes it clear that everything is to be done in love and with the goal of restoring the person to fellowship in the community.</p> <p>Verses:  2 Thess. 3:13-18</p> <p>Teacher:  Jeff Tyler &amp; Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-04-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:05', 62, 9, null, 'OQzVlonVZaM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OQzVlonVZaM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(1869, 1, 'The Red Heifer and Jesus Christ', '<p>One of the types of Christ in the Old Testament is the Red Heifer. Unlike other sin offerings, it was slaughtered outside the Tabernacle courtyard, as Jesus Christ was crucified outside the Temple, and kept until someone needed to be cleansed. The Bible is specific about the fact that if an unclean person refused the ash-water of the Red Heifer he or she was cut off from the congregation of Israel. Similarly, if a person refuses to be cleansed by the blood of Christ they are cut off from the congregation of the saved and select themselves for death.</p> <p>Verses: Numbers 19:1-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:34', 0, 0, null, 'm49fyWulOxc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m49fyWulOxc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1870, 1, 'The Resurrection Appearances of Jesus Christ', '<p>This teaching, accompanied by a detailed chart, goes through all Four Gospels tracking the events that happened between Saturday afternoon, (17 Nisan) when Joseph of Arimathea retrieved the body of Jesus Christ until Jesus appeared to the Apostles on the Sea of Galilee as recorded in John 21. The teaching is more of an overview of all the events rather than an in-depth exploration of any one event.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 27:57ff; Mark 15:42-16:8; Luke 23:50ff; John 19:38ff.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit &amp; Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-04-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:31', 0, 0, null, 'QT2mOLZlDTU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QT2mOLZlDTU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1871, 1, 'Overcoming Frustration and Discouragement', '<p>It can be easy to become discouraged and frustrated in life, especially if you are praying hard for things to happen but don&rsquo;t seem to get many answers. In Luke 18:1-8 Jesus taught his disciples about praying and not being discouraged. Also, presented from Luke 17 are some examples that can help us to stay encouraged as we follow our in Lord&rsquo;s footsteps, including staying focused on the goal, the Kingdom of God.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 17:1-37; 18:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:09', 0, 0, null, 'WsJsHm5J7B0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WsJsHm5J7B0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1872, 1, 'Rewards: How to be great in the Kingdom of God', '<p>In this teaching Jesus shows us how to secure a position of honor in the Kingdom, and the wisdom of striving in this life to have one. One day Jesus will conquer the earth and have a worldwide kingdom, and that kingdom will have differing positions and jobs in it; the honorable jobs will be given to those who deserve them.  </p> <p>Verses: Matt. 18:1-4; Mark 9:33-37; Matt. 20:20-28; Luke 22:24-29;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '22:56', 0, 0, null, 'nBjNdyN13Ow', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nBjNdyN13Ow/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(1873, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/18/2021) – Life in the Millennial Kingdom', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:12', 0, 0, 'Not active', 'pdKylHfc8Ls', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pdKylHfc8Ls/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1874, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/25/2021) – God - Keeper of our Heart', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:32', 0, 0, null, 'NDJ83oyYnN8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NDJ83oyYnN8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, 'Not active', 1, 0, null),
(1875, 1, 'How to Have a Strong Church', '<p>After his resurrection, Jesus met with Peter and confronted him three times about whether Peter loved him. This teaching examines those three confrontations and shows how each is different and important. Jesus gave Peter three different pieces of guidance about how to have a strong congregation: Feeding the lambs, shepherding the sheep, and feeding the sheep, and how each played out in Peter&rsquo;s first century ministry and in the Church today.  </p> <p> Verses:  Luke 22:31-44; John 21:15-19</p> <p> Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:24', 0, 0, null, 'DXrtyBFRbDU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DXrtyBFRbDU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 3, null),
(1876, 1, 'John 21 and Rewards in the Kingdom', '<p>This is a team-teaching that covers John 21 where Peter saw the disciple whom Jesus loved and asked, &ldquo;What about him?&rdquo; Jesus made it clear that each believer must be focused on their own ministry and do what that entails. Also covered are the three records in the Gospels where the disciples argue about who will be the greatest in the coming Kingdom of God. Jesus never said they were wrong to want to have positions of honor in the coming kingdom, but he did correct their perceptions of it and how to attain those positions -- by being humble to God and a servant to others.</p> <p> Verses:  John 21:20-22; Matt. 18:1; Mark 9:33-37; Matt. 20:20-28; Luke 22:24-29;</p> <p> Teacher:  Sue Carlson; John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:33', 0, 0, null, 'S-9ghVf7Wsk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S-9ghVf7Wsk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 10, null),
(1877, 1, 'What Trust Looks Like | ep 1 | What Trust DOES NOT Look Like', '<p>In this first of a three-part series on &ldquo;What Trust Looks Like&rdquo;, we explore the life of Hezekiah&rsquo;s father, King Ahaz. The state of the kingdom of Judah during his reign (@731 to 715 BC), before Hezekiah became king, was dire. Yahweh had offered Ahaz encouragement and opportunities to &ldquo;choose good&rdquo; through messages from His prophet, Isaiah, but Ahaz instead chose the evil of initiating rampant idolatry throughout the land of Judah in hopes of appeasing the false gods of the encroaching enemies. This is an example of &ldquo;What Trust [in Yahweh] DOES NOT Look like!&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses:  2 Kings 18:1-6, 19, 16:1-20; Isa. 7:1-18; 2 Chron. 28:16-25, 29:1, 32:10</p> <p>Teacher:  Ellen Cutler</p>', '2021-04-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:29', 63, 1, null, 'yXj94PIZML4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yXj94PIZML4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1878, 1, 'Asking the Right Question is Helpful', '<p>The Bible says life will be difficult. The examples in the Bible show that the most godly of people have difficult lives and we will too. It is important to realize this and think properly about life if one is to be peaceful and productive. Many people encounter difficulties in life and ask, &ldquo;Why me?&rdquo; assuming the position of &ldquo;victim.&rdquo; It is much more helpful to ask, &ldquo;What do I do now?&rdquo; and begin to move towards a godly solution to the problem.   </p> <p>Verses:  Acts 14:21-22; Phil. 4:10-13; 2 Cor. 4:16; 6:1-13; Rom. 7:22; Prov. 4:7</p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:44', 0, 0, null, 'zdZWi2gmC6I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zdZWi2gmC6I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 4, null),
(1879, 1, 'What Trust Looks Like | ep 2 | Hezekiah Trusts God', '<p>In this second of a three-part series on &ldquo;What Trust Looks Like&rdquo;, hear about the extensive preparations King Hezekiah made to restore proper worship of Yahweh in His Jerusalem temple. This true story about God&rsquo;s mercy for His people as King Hezekiah led them back to the God of Israel after years of deliberate rebellion invites us to consider how these lessons could influence our lives today.</p> <p>Verses:  2 Chron. 29:1-36, 30:1, 6-27, 31:1, 20-21, 32:1; 2 Kings 18:1-7; Isa. 20:1-5</p> <p>Teacher:  Ellen Cutler</p>', '2021-04-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:38', 63, 2, null, 'TLmDjC5JeNM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TLmDjC5JeNM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1880, 1, 'Being Godly in Spite of Evil People', '<p>God is the most powerful being in the universe, and He is good and righteous. Yet His creation&mdash;earth&mdash;has always seemed to be dominated by evil people. This teaching covers human history since the fall of Adam and Eve, showing how the god of this world and has helped people who align themselves with him to be wealthy and powerful while God&rsquo;s people are often persecuted and don&rsquo;t seem to have what they need to really succeed. The key to godly success in life is not having the right equipment but having the right attitude.   </p> <p>Verses:  Luke 4:5-8; 1 John 5:19; Gen. 4:3-9; 6:5-8; Job 21:7-21; Ps. 73:2-14; Jer. 12:1-2; John 8:37-44</p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-04-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:36', 0, 0, null, 'FRj1X8CqG1s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FRj1X8CqG1s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 14, null),
(1881, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 46 | Wisdom&rsquo;s Deliverance - Pt 1 (Prov. 2:12-15)', '<p>The world is filled with people who are seeking ways to take advantage of others. Wisdom will protect those who listen to her from all manner of evil perversions, twisted paths, and devious ways of the wicked. Wisdom is a guardian who will provide safety from the unrighteous schemes of evil people who would gladly exploit others for their own benefit.</p> <p>Illustration: Charles C. Parker, a New York con artist who sold the Brooklyn Bridge to wealthy immigrants for over 40 years.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:12-16</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-04-30', 'Castos', 0, '14:49', 9, 46, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-46-Wisdom-s-Deliverance-Pt-1.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep46', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(1882, 1, 'What Trust Looks Like | ep 3 | Finish Strong and Give God the Glory', '<p>Part 3 of &ldquo;What Trust Looks Like&rdquo; is the story of King Hezekiah and the people of Jerusalem facing dramatic opposition from a very dominant enemy. Despite being outmanned by the encroaching Assyrian army, King Hezekiah trusted God to prepare to battle King Sennacherib&rsquo;s much stronger force. God honored King Hezekiah&rsquo;s trust in quite a dramatic way! Truly Epic!</p> <p>Verses:  2 Kings 18:1-7, 13-37; 19:35-37; 2 Chron. 32:1-8; Isa. 37:1-35</p> <p>Teacher:  Ellen Cutler</p>', '2021-04-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:42', 63, 3, null, 'QAXYP_gyxaQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QAXYP_gyxaQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1883, 1, 'Keys to Understanding the Four Gospels', '<p>The Gospels are the definitive record of the life and activities of Jesus Christ but can be challenging to understand. Varying and contradictory records cause scholars to propose that because the writers were human, they simply saw things from a different point of view or got details wrong. But if the Bible is the inspired Word of God, that explanation is not satisfactory.</p> <p>Verses:  Matt. 20:29-34; 22:1-14; Luke 18:35-43; 19:37-44</p> <p> Teacher:  John  Schoenheit and Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-05-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:01', 0, 0, null, '_BHXp5MkTAY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_BHXp5MkTAY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 14, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1884, 1, 'A Key to Being Peaceful and Content', '<p>A great key to being peaceful and content is understanding both the final end of the wicked, who seem to do so well in this life, and the rewards that God will give to those who are godly and thankful. With evil people being in power in this world, understanding the hope and spiritual warfare can help Christians be peaceful, thankful, and content.   </p> <p>Verses:  2 Cor. 12:8-10; Luke 4:5-8; 1 John 5:19; Gen. 4:6-9; 6:5; Job 21:7-14; Ps. 73:3-13; Jer. 12:1-2; John 8:44</p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '22:30', 0, 0, null, '5Tr2wp4roXk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5Tr2wp4roXk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 24, null),
(1885, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/09/2021) - Three Sides to John the Baptist', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '21:35', 0, 0, null, '70qjZgMDNpY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/70qjZgMDNpY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1886, 1, 'Characteristics of Love', '<p>&ldquo;Walk in love.&rdquo; What, exactly, does that mean? There are characteristics to love that are important to understand. For example, love cannot be forced, it must be given freely, voluntarily. Also, love sets boundaries, it communicates clearly, and it does not control people, but releases them to make their own freewill decisions. The one who is released by love should love in return, which means taking responsibility for his actions, and that means obeying God&rsquo;s directions.</p> <p>Verses: John 4:8, 16; Eph. 5:2; Exod. 21:12; 1 Pet. 3:19; 2 Pet. 2:4-9; Rev. 12:5; Luke 22:42; John 14:15, 21-24; 1 Cor. 13:4-8.  </p> <p>Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:38', 0, 0, null, 'IBUaiNknG1E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IBUaiNknG1E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 5, null),
(1887, 1, 'Parables of the Kingdom of Heaven', '<p>The Kingdom of Heaven is not well understood, and that is in part because Christ spoke about it in parables. Matthew 13 has six parables that start with &ldquo;the Kingdom of Heaven is like,&rdquo; and by understanding these and the order in which they are taught we get a much better grasp of the Kingdom of Heaven, which is Christ&rsquo;s future kingdom on earth.  </p> <p> Verses:  Matt. 13:1-52</p> <p> Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, null, 0, 0, null, 'mN7s2qpL0Yk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mN7s2qpL0Yk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 17, null),
(1888, 1, 'The Times of Restitution of All Things | ep 1 | Introduction', '<p>In this introduction to the topic from Peter&rsquo;s sermon on the Day of Pentecost in Acts 3, we began to explore the various aspects of restoration and restitution that are coming: Rapture, Rewards, Resurrections, Judgements, and Glories that were &ldquo;spoken by all the prophets since the world began.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Acts 3:19-21; Ps. 1:1-6; 16:8-11; Matt. 12:9-10, 13; 13:39-43; 24:3-8; Mark 8:25; Acts 1:7; 2:22-28; 1 Cor. 15:22-26, 51-54; 1 Thess. 5:1; 4:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2021-05-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, null, 64, 1, null, '73qLgqDzBvw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/73qLgqDzBvw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1889, 1, 'Love and Responsibility', '<p>God is love, and so He does not control people but allows them the freedom to love Him or reject Him. Being loved comes with the responsibility for one&rsquo;s own actions. People who love God obey Him, and people who do not love Him do not.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:8, 16; Deut. 30:19; Luke 22:42; John 14:15, 21-24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-14', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:11', 0, 0, null, 'f76QLe62sr8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/f76QLe62sr8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1890, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/16/2021) - Teamwork', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-05-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:24', 0, 0, null, 'bDtHjxRXinE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bDtHjxRXinE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1891, 1, 'Cleansed by the Blood of Jesus', '<p>The blood of Jesus (representing his death) is spiritually powerful. We were bought with his blood, redeemed with his blood, made holy by his blood. Hebrews says that even our conscience was cleansed from dead works by his blood. However, to get the full blessing of Christ&rsquo;s blood in this life, we have to be mentally strong enough to believe it and live accordingly.   </p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:7; Isa. 64:1-6; Rom. 5:9, Heb. 9:14; 13:12; Rev. 1:5; 5:9;  1 Pet. 1:18-19; Rom. 3:25; Eph. 2:13  </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:32', 0, 0, null, 'rgqBp_IAeJo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rgqBp_IAeJo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(1892, 1, 'The Times of Restitution of All Things | ep 2 | Rewards', '<p>This brief overview of some of the rewards we have to look forward to in &ldquo;The Times of Restoration of All things&rdquo; focuses on the often-repeated promise that &ldquo;the meek will inherit the Earth,&rdquo; and what that might look like to those of us who are &ldquo;Joint-heirs with Christ.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 15:6-7; 26:3,4; Exod. 32:13; Ps. 24:1; 2:6-8; 25:12-13; 37:9,11, 22; 50:10-12; Prov. 2:21-22; Dan. 7:13-14, 18, 22, 27; Matt. 5:1-10; 6:1-6; 19:29; Luke 16:10-12, 15; 19:12-19; Acts 3:21-25; 7:5; Rom. 4:13; 8:16-17; 14:17-18; 1 Cor. 4:2-5; 6:2; 15:51-58; 2 Cor. 5:10-11; Gal. 3:29; Eph. 1:14, 18; 3:6, 5:8-10; Phil. 3:20-21; Col. 3:24; 1 Pet. 4:17; 2 Pet. 3:9; 1 John 2:28; 3:22; Rev. 5:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2021-05-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:24', 64, 2, null, '4YwDDQbrkpE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4YwDDQbrkpE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1893, 1, 'Have Courage', '<p>It takes courage to walk the Christian walk. But courage is not foolhardiness or a lack of wisdom. In fact, wisdom and courage go together. Having courage does not mean having no fear, but doing the right thing in spite of any fear. Courage and indecision are incompatible, as are courage and timidity. Things that build courage include knowing you are in the will of God, encouragement from others, and encouraging yourself. In contrast, bad news can be discouraging.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:7; Num. 13:20; Acts 28:15; Josh. 1:1-9; 2:11; 1 Sam. 30:6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:21', 0, 0, null, 'YEfAKYGzRkY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YEfAKYGzRkY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1894, 1, 'A Blind Man Healed', '<p>In John 9 Jesus healed a man who was born blind. He was likely very young, a teenager, yet he boldly stood against the religious establishment and their ungodly rules and beliefs and was excommunicated for it. But Jesus lovingly found him and revealed himself to him as the Messiah.   </p> <p>Verses: John 9:1-41; Rev. 14:13</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:28', 0, 0, null, 'YQGTZIgVHPo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YQGTZIgVHPo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1895, 1, 'Have Courage', '<p>It takes courage to walk the Christian walk. But courage is not foolhardiness or a lack of wisdom. In fact, wisdom and courage go together. Having courage does not mean having no fear but doing the right thing despite any fear. Courage and indecision are incompatible, as are courage and timidity. Things that build courage include knowing you are in the will of God, encouragement from others, and encouraging yourself. In contrast, bad news can be discouraging.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:7; Deut. 31:6-8; Acts 28:15; 1 Sam. 30:6; Josh. 2:10-11</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-21', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:59', 0, 0, null, 'smFi0Tn4Wz0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/smFi0Tn4Wz0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1896, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 47 | Wisdom&rsquo;s Deliverance - Pt 2 (Prov. 2.16-19)', '<p>We all desire to be spoken well of but we must be careful that we don&rsquo;t get caught in the trap of flattery from others where we might then make poor choices that we normally wouldn&rsquo;t. Sexual sin (like adultery) rarely happens suddenly. The seductiveness of flattery is that it works little by little over time until a person decides to make a foolish decision that they will regret the rest of their life.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:16-19</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-05-21', 'Castos', 0, '19:56', 9, 47, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-47-Wisdom-s-Deliverance-Pt2-Prov.-2.16-19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-47-wisdom39s-deliverance-pt-2-prov-216-19-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1897, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/23/2021) – Faith, Hope and Love – Part 2', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-05-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:35', 0, 0, null, 'mHmF9xUHY8E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mHmF9xUHY8E/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1898, 1, 'The Day of Pentecost', '<p>The Day of Pentecost in Acts 2 was the start of the Christian Church. In the Temple in Jerusalem that day, the gift of holy spirit was given to each person who believed in Christ. This gift empowers believers (Acts 1:8), and along with that power comes responsibility. God set the stage for empire-wide evangelism by timing the outpouring of the spirit with Pentecost, the one-day feast when Jews from all over the Roman empire would be in Jerusalem, and about 3,000 Jews got saved that day.  </p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:10; Acts 1:1-8; 2:1-13, 17-21, 41-42</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:15', 0, 0, null, 'lDIo_MmSVek', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lDIo_MmSVek/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1899, 1, 'The Times of Restitution of All Things | ep 3 | Judgments', '<p>An exploration of the various judgments in the Times of Restitution to come, including the resurrections of the Just and the Unjust, the Sheep &amp; Goat Judgment, and the Lake of Fire.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 32:4, 39-43; 1 Sam. 2:6-10; 23:1-7; Job 37:23; Ps. 1:5; 9:7-8, 16; 37:12-15, 28; 58:6-11; 103:6; 110:1-6; 149:5-9; Eccles. 12:13-14; Isa. 1:24-31; 24:21-23; Dan. 12:2-3; Mal. 4:1-3; 3:14-18; Matt. 12:36; 25:31-40; John 5:21-30; Rom. 14:10-12; 1 Cor. 4:4-5; 2 Cor. 5:10; 2 Thess. 1:7-10; 2 Thess. 2:8; 1 John 1:6-10; 2 Pet. 3:7-13; Rev. 17:14; 19:11-14, 19; 20:1-15</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2021-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:30', 64, 3, null, 'tZ7kF7wrL_s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tZ7kF7wrL_s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1900, 1, 'The Son of David', '<p>The phrase &ldquo;the son of David&rdquo; refers not only to being a lineal descendant of David (Matt. 1:20) but is also a messianic title. At the time of Christ there would likely have been thousands of people who were descended from David, so when people called Jesus &ldquo;the Son of David,&rdquo; they meant he was the Messiah. This indicates that God, in His love, revealed who Jesus was to people who needed to know.</p> <p> Verses: Matt. 1:1; 9:27; 12:23; 15:22; 20:30-31; 21:9; 22:42; John 12:13</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-05-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:45', 0, 0, null, 'cRxbPC4EPpc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cRxbPC4EPpc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1901, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/30/2021) – Who was Phoebe?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and prayer.</p>', '2021-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:31', 0, 0, null, 'QqlVjdvPjss', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QqlVjdvPjss/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1902, 1, 'The Times of Restitution of All Things | ep 4 | The Kingdom & the Glory', '<p>Wrapping up the series with glimpses of the future ages we find in the Old Testament, the Gospels and the Epistles: The Millennial Kingdom, the New Heavens &amp; New Earth, and the Ages to come.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:17-19; Exod. 15:18; Ps. 146:10; Isa. 2:3-4; 11:4-9; 13:13; 25:6-9; 32:1-3, 15-20; 34:4; 35:6-7, 10; 44:3-4; 54:8-17; 60:20; 65:17-23; 66:22-23; Ezek. 47:12; Hosea 13:14; Mic. 4:4, 7; Zech. 14:6-9; Matt. 19:28; 24:30, 32, 35; Luke 1:33; Acts 3:21; Rom. 5:2; 8:18-21; 1 Cor. 15:24-28, 58; 2 Cor. 4:17; Eph. 1:10, 18; 2:6-7; 3:17-21; Col. 3:4; 1 Thess. 2:12; 2 Tim. 2:10; 1 Pet. 1:11; 4:13; 5:1, 10; 2 Pet. 3:7-10; Heb. 11:10; 12:1-2, 22-23; Rev. 11:15; 17:14; 19:11-12, 16; 20:6; 21:1-11, 18-24; 22:1-6</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2021-05-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:19', 64, 4, null, 'PxKxIq8Oj98', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PxKxIq8Oj98/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1903, 1, 'The Son of David', '<p>The phrase &ldquo;the son of David&rdquo; refers not only to being a lineal descendant of David (Matt. 1:20) but is also a messianic title. At the time of Christ there would likely have been thousands of people who were descended from David, so when people called Jesus &ldquo;the Son of David,&rdquo; they meant he was the Messiah. This indicates that God, in His love, revealed who Jesus was to people who needed to know.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Sam. 7:16, 18, 25-29; Matt. 1:20; 9:27-28; 15:21-22; 20:29-34; 21:9; John 12:13; 1 Chron. 3:10-16</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '20:03', 0, 0, null, 'uxlTVQScMVs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uxlTVQScMVs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 46, null),
(1904, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/06/2021) - Help', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:47', 0, 0, null, 'gj7EebZrfKY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gj7EebZrfKY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1905, 1, 'What Did Jesus Say About Forgiveness?', '<p>Jesus spoke directly about forgiveness at least 6 times during his ministry. This teaching examines the meaning of Jesus&rsquo; statements about forgiveness and whether or not they apply to the Christian Church, which started on Pentecost and continues today.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 11:25; Matt. 6:12-15; 18:23-35; Luke 6:37; 11:4; 17:3-5; John 20:23; Rom. 15:4; Eph. 4:32; Col. 3:12-13</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-06-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:14', 0, 0, null, 'UIPwK3HH29o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UIPwK3HH29o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1906, 1, 'Getting to the Finish Line', '<p>How do we deal with the challenges we face? In this comparison of the Christian journey to long distance running, three essentials for running a successful race and getting to the finish line are explored: trust, love, and hope.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Thess. 1:2-10; 4:15-17; 2 Thess. 3:3-5,16</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2021-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:44', 0, 0, null, 'QnlL1PPZ9Ac', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QnlL1PPZ9Ac/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(1917, 1, 'Be Strong-willed in the Lord', '<p>Paul&rsquo;s letter to Timothy teaches us that in the last days things will be difficult, which is worsened by being &rdquo;weak-willed&rdquo; and not making good decisions and sticking with them . That was the case with some of the women in the Ephesian and Roman culture of Paul&rsquo;s time, who are described as &ldquo;weak-willed.&rdquo; Believers are to control their lives and thoughts and be strong in the Lord.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:1-7; Eph. 6:10; John 14:27; Exod. 5:1-9; Ruth 1:8, 11, 15, 16-18; Luke 9:23-26</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:57', 0, 0, null, 'q3SPbR1S7Fc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/q3SPbR1S7Fc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1918, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/13/2021) - What are you doing now Lord?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-06-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:51', 0, 0, null, '5YskCyrMQJ0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5YskCyrMQJ0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1919, 1, 'Christians Should Not Be Vengeful', '<p>We are not to pattern ourselves according to this age but rather change the way we think and act by thinking ahead of time. This becomes important especially in those times when we think we have been wronged&hellip;we are not to be vengeful but rather to allow God to sort out those things...because vengeance belongs to Him.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1-2, 20-21; Luke 18:1-8; Deut. 32:35; 2 Sam. 22:47-51</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2021-06-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:27', 0, 0, null, 'wBtJSP1L24Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wBtJSP1L24Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1920, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/20/2021) - Walking Through the Epistles', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-06-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:47', 0, 0, null, 'KSV_Kc_9XDQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KSV_Kc_9XDQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(1922, 1, 'Stop Being Offended', '<p>Offense is one of the enemy&rsquo;s most deadly and deceptive traps. It imprisons countless Christians, severs relationships, and widens existing social breaches. This teaching explores the how God&rsquo;s enemy seeks to cause frustration, resentment, anger, bitterness, and rage between people, with the goal of keeping Christians from sharing the good news of the gospel of Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:10-13; 1 Tim. 2:1-4; Eph. 5:15-16; 1 Pet. 5:1-9; Gen. 37:3-4; 1 Sam. 18:5-9; Luke 4:16-30; 2 Tim. 2:22-26; Eph. 4:26-32</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2021-06-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:53', 0, 0, null, 'm7dVy_STio4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m7dVy_STio4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 15, null),
(1923, 1, 'Korah&rsquo;s Rebellion', '<p>Numbers 16 is the record of a Levite named Korah who rebelled against Moses and God. Prideful, rebellious people are discontent when they have no need to be; they stir up others and get them to join with them; they falsely accuse leaders; they have hidden agendas and want leadership positions they don&rsquo;t deserve; they rewrite history; they misplace blame; and ultimately their rebellion will end in death.   </p> <p> Verses: Numbers 16:1-50</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:54', 0, 0, null, 'Jdmehas9dNg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Jdmehas9dNg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1924, 1, 'Making Good Decisions', '<p>Decision-making and walking in sound judgment can be a difficult but necessary and important part of life. Thankfully, the Word of God gives guidance such as seeking the Lord&rsquo;s will, asking yourself if Jesus would make the same choice, counting the cost, getting good, godly counsel, and realizing that emotional decisions can be bad decisions. No one knows the future, so make the best decision for right now with the best information you have.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:1; Luke 6:37; John 7:24; James 1:5; Mark 9:29; Luke 14:28-32; Prov. 4:7; Eccles. 8:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:13', 0, 0, null, 'Kk6jF_n2_2k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Kk6jF_n2_2k/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null);
