(1925, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 48 | The Wise Will Remain (Prov. 2.20-22)', '<p>Living wisely or foolishly has long-reaching effects. We experience many consequences of our choices in our present life. But some consequences will not become known until in the future. Wisdom provides health, success, and well-being, but more importantly, long life now, and everlasting life in God&rsquo;s future kingdom. While the wicked might seem to prosper now, there is a day coming where they will be &ldquo;cut off&rdquo; and will be no more.</p> <p>Illustration: Sheila Fields, who is a landlord in Buffalo, NY, suffered immense loss from the behavior of a deceptive and violent tenant.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:20-22</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-06-22', 'Castos', 0, '17:14', 9, 48, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-48-The-Wise-Will-Remain-Prov.-2.20-22-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-48-the-wise-will-remain-prov-220-22-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 24, null),
(1926, 1, 'Get Saved – It is Easy', '<p>Salvation is the most important thing in life because it means living forever instead of dying forever. The Bible makes it clear that Jesus Christ fully paid the price to save sinners and sin does not keep us from being saved.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 7:20; 1 Tim. 1:15; Rom. 5:6-8; Eph. 2:8-9; Rom. 10:9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:13', 0, 0, null, 'NffsW2SISuM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NffsW2SISuM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1927, 1, 'Lawlessness', '<p>The Bible characterizes the End Times as a time of increasing lawlessness, which will include random lawlessness as well as lawmakers putting in place laws and regulations that contradict and defy the laws of God. Biblical lawlessness includes man-made laws being &ldquo;lawless&rdquo; compared to godly justice.  </p> <p> Verses: Gen. 1:1; Isa. 33:22; James 4:12-17; Exod. 5:1-2; Matt. 15:1-9; 23:28; 24:11-12; 2 Thess. 2:3; Dan. 7:8</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:47', 0, 0, null, 'sFViktNOTuM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sFViktNOTuM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1928, 1, 'The Fruit of Walking in the Nature of Christ', '<p>Because of the saving work of Jesus Christ we are able to bear fruit to God. When we walk as children of godliness, in a manner worthy of the Lord, conducting ourselves according to the nature of Christ, we bring forth Godly fruit, that benefits us in this life and throughout eternity.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:4; Eph. 5:8-11; Col. 1:9-12; Gal. 5:16-25</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-06-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:53', 0, 0, null, 'cFHUofYXhA4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cFHUofYXhA4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1929, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/27/2021) - A Heart Tale of Two Kings', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-06-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:50', 0, 0, null, 'eqW6lRzmkzE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eqW6lRzmkzE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1930, 1, 'Making Good Decisions', '<p>Decision-making and walking in sound judgment are a difficult but necessary and important part of life. Thankfully, the Word of God gives guidance to make the best decision for right now with the best information you have.   </p> <p>Verses: John 14:27; 2 Tim. 3:6; Matt. 7:1; Luke 6:37; John 7:24; James 1:5; 1 Thess. 5:17; Luke 14:28-32; Prov. 4:7; Prov. 11:14; Eccles. 8:7 </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-02', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:28', 0, 0, null, 'trIFwrp2uBo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/trIFwrp2uBo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(1931, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/04/2021) - Triumphal Procession', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-07-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:46', 0, 0, null, 'HJ9_PPgLddw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HJ9_PPgLddw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1932, 1, 'What Trust Looks Like | ep 4 | Hezekiah&rsquo;s Illness And Recovery', '<p>Enjoy part 4 of &ldquo;What Trust Looks Like&rdquo; to hear how King Hezekiah chose to return to Yahweh after he initially succumbed to his pride by not giving Yahweh proper credit for healing him and saving Jerusalem from the Assyrians. Yahweh&rsquo;s faithful message via the prophet Isaiah influenced King Hezekiah to return to His God who powerfully restored his life.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 32:20-26, 32; 2 Kings 20:1-11, 12-19; 18:1-7; Isa. 7:14; 8:18; 9:6</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2021-06-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:29', 63, 4, null, 'QHtpDvha4Sw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/QHtpDvha4Sw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1933, 1, 'Daniel and Nebuchadnezzar', '<p>King Nebuchadnezzar ruled for 44 years during which God worked with him in amazing ways. There is great learning in the interactions between God, Nebuchadnezzar, and Daniel and his three companions, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego.</p> <p>Verses: Dan. 1:1-4, 17-21; Dan. 2:1-13, 27-28, 34-35, 44, 46-49; Dan. 3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:39', 0, 0, null, '9_Uy-upk_PU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9_Uy-upk_PU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1934, 1, 'Why Did Jesus Teach in Parables?', '<p>The parables Jesus taught revealed the heart of each listener. Those who were humble and hungry for God made the effort to find out what the parables meant, but those who did not care about God or the things of God would not make the effort to find the meaning. Thus, the parables, in an idiomatic sense, &ldquo;made&rdquo; the hearts of the people &ldquo;dull of hearing.&rdquo;  </p> <p> Verses: Mark 4:10-12, 21-23; Isa. 6:1-13; Exod. 4:21 </p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-06-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:36', 0, 0, null, 'Z39iRJIZ3EM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Z39iRJIZ3EM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1935, 1, 'Lawlessness', '<p>The Bible characterizes the End Times as a time of increasing lawlessness, which will include random lawlessness as well as lawmakers putting in place laws and regulations that contradict and defy the laws of God. Biblical lawlessness includes man-made laws being &ldquo;lawless&rdquo; compared to godly justice.  </p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1; Isa. 33:22; James 4:12; Matt. 23:27-28; 24:3, 4, 12; Mark 7:5-7; 2 Thess. 2:3; Dan. 7:25</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:00', 0, 0, null, 'Kmhks1l0n_I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Kmhks1l0n_I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1936, 1, 'Making Godly Choices', '<p>There are many choices to make over the course of life that have consequences large and small. But the most important choice anyone will ever make is to choose life &ndash; now and for all eternity &ndash; by accepting Jesus Christ as Lord and Savior. After salvation, Christians should continue to seek and choose the ways of God, knowing that He will richly reward us for all eternity.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:8-20; Heb. 11:24-26; 1 Cor. 2:9; Matt. 7:24-27; 16:18; 1 Cor. 3:11-15; Matt. 6:33; 7:7-8; Prov. 3:13-18; Heb. 11:6; Prov. 3:5-6; Rom. 7:14-25; Phil. 2:13; Eph. 6:10-18</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-06-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:14', 0, 0, null, 'fRhJIgJLpGc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fRhJIgJLpGc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1937, 1, 'Keeping a Cheerful Heart in Tough Times', '<p>The Bible encourages us to be cheerful, glad and joyful. It also provides guidance for keeping a cheerful heart in tough times. This teaching looks at several things we can seek out to maintain our joy, such as good words, good friends, encouraging others, prayer, hope and more.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 12:25; 15:13; 17:22; 27:9; Phil. 3:20; 4:4, 6-8, 10-13; Ps. 28:7; 119:74; Isa. 35:1-10; Heb. 12:1-13</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-07-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:21', 0, 0, null, 'xt--ot68x5Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xt--ot68x5Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1938, 1, 'God Appearing in Human Form', '<p>God created humans so He could love them and be loved by them. Though He is normally invisible and unseen, the Bible has many records of God coming into concretion and being with people, starting with Adam and Eve in the Garden of Eden and ending in Revelation with God Himself living with us. </p> <p>Verses:  John 1:17-18; Gen. 3:8; 12:7; 15:1; 17:1; 18:1-8; 28:13; Exod. 24:9-11; 1 Sam. 3:10; 1 Kings 3:5; 9:2; 11:9; Isa. 6:1-5; Ezek. 1:26-28; Dan. 7:9-14; Acts 7:55-56; Rev. 4:2-4; 5:7; 21:3-4</p> <p> Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:58', 0, 0, null, 'KvAXAPCvgJ8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KvAXAPCvgJ8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 6, null),
(1939, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/11/2021) - Being Imitators', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-07-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:31:38', 0, 0, null, 'SZpOv8bwGyo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SZpOv8bwGyo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1940, 1, 'Luke 15 –The Parable of the Forgiving Father', '<p>The Parable of the Forgiving Father is one of four parables in Luke 15 and 16 that Jesus taught consecutively to show that God was always trying to win people to Himself, but people need to do their part also. The sons in this parable exemplify two groups present at the time: sinners who were willingly listening to him, and religious leaders who were standing in opposition to him. </p> <p>Verses: Luke 15:1-2, 7, 10, 11-32; Deut. 21:17</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:15', 0, 0, null, 'EoMhKZyPLBc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EoMhKZyPLBc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1941, 1, 'Prayer: Easy and Important', '<p>Prayer is especially important, but many Christians are reluctant to pray for a number of reasons. The Bible has much to say about prayer, and there is no set formula, because it is mainly asking God for things and thanking Him. Prayer does not have to &ldquo;sound good&rdquo; or &ldquo;be fancy&rdquo; in any way, because God looks on the heart.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 4:6; Col. 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:17; Matt. 7:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-16', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '11:05', 0, 0, null, 'vmCyXEvINf0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vmCyXEvINf0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 33, null),
(1942, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/18/2021) - Rich Towards God', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-07-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:45', 0, 0, null, 'RvxYhuallnA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RvxYhuallnA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1943, 1, 'The Unsaved will be Annihilated in the Lake of Fire', '<p>In many different places, and in many different ways, the Bible makes it clear that the unsaved will be thrown into the Lake of Fire and burn until they are burned up, totally consumed, gone. Telic words in the Bible such as &ldquo;perish,&rdquo; and &ldquo;death&rdquo; are just some of the evidences that wicked people will burn up and be gone.  </p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:2; Ps. 21:9; 37:10-11, 20; 49:20; 92:7; Ezek. 33:13-16; Isa. 51:8; Nahum 1:10; Jer. 17:13; Job 20:9; Mal. 4:1; Matt. 3:12; 5:22; 7:19; 10:28; John 3:16; 2 Pet. 2:6; Rom. 6:23; Rev. 20:10; Josh. 15:8.   </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:54', 0, 0, null, 'zplW2mOer4M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zplW2mOer4M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1944, 1, 'Being Like Christ', '<p>Jesus told us that in the end times the love of many will grow cold. That being the case, we must work hard to be like Christ. Romans 12:10 tells us that when it comes to honorable living, we must not just lead but go above and beyond. It takes focus and vision to be like Christ in difficult times, but we can do it! </p> <p>Verses: Matt. 24:12; Rom. 12:10; Mark 13:12-13; Luke 21:16-17; Gal. 6:1-4; 5:1-17; Eph. 4:31-32;</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:32', 0, 0, null, 'UlpbfMA-4Zk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UlpbfMA-4Zk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1945, 1, 'Isaiah 53: The Suffering Servant', '<p>The prophecy of the Servant of Yahweh in Isaiah 52-53 is one of the four &ldquo;Servant Songs&rdquo; of Isaiah. In this Servant Song, the Messiah is portrayed as one who would grow up as a person with normal human troubles, carry the sins of humankind, die to redeem humankind, and be raised from the dead.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 52:1-13; Isa. 53:1-12; Isa. 54:1-2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:16', 0, 0, null, 'DtAJASLKSE8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DtAJASLKSE8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1946, 1, 'Being More Like Christ', '<p>Some 2,000 years ago, Jesus warned us that as we approach the End Times people will become more lawless and coldhearted, and that certainly does seem to be happening. If we are not careful and focused on being like Christ, we can get caught up in the way the world behaves and begin to lose the fire of godly love and behavior.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 24:12; Rom. 12:10; Luke 21:16; Mark 13:12-13; Isa. 50:7; Gal. 5:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:29', 0, 0, null, 'waE4z3G9goc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/waE4z3G9goc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(1947, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/25/2021) - Salvation and Rewards', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-07-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:39', 0, 0, null, 'oAQe2NZSXCc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oAQe2NZSXCc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1948, 1, 'Self Talk: The Blessing of a Positive Confession', '<p>Negative internal conversation, usually in the form of inner murmuring and complaining is a detriment to our Christian life and disposition. Three areas that are especially common avenues for unhealthy Self-Talk include our sin nature, living in a fallen world, and ungodly people. When we see ourselves the way God sees us, we can develop a positive internal dialogue and be more peaceful and blessed.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:14-20; Gal. 5:17; Jer. 5:1-2; 12:1-6; 15:16-17; 1 Kings 9:4; Eph. 1:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:02', 0, 0, null, 'hfuqAnDhxv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hfuqAnDhxv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1949, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 49 | Rest and Confidence in Yahweh (Prov. 19:23; 14:26-27)', '<p>People often strive for satisfaction in life through money, status family, or other life accomplishments so they can live at ease and not worry about life any longer. But there is only one thing can give us true life, rest, and contentment. If we seek to attain the fullness of life on our own, we will be left with only disappointment and heartache because we can&rsquo;t do it ourselves.</p> <p>Illustration: The Parable of the Businessman and the Fisherman</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 19:23; 14:26-27</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-07-27', 'Castos', 0, '15:52', 9, 49, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-49-Rest-and-Confidence-in-Yahweh-Prov.-19.23-14.26-27-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-49-rest-and-confidence-in-yahweh-prov-1923-1426-27', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 34, null),
(1950, 1, 'Self Talk: The Blessing of a Positive Confession', '<p>Negative internal conversation, usually in the form of inner murmuring and complaining is a detriment to our Christian life and disposition. Three areas that are especially common avenues for unhealthy Self-Talk include our sin nature, living in a fallen world, and ungodly people. When we see ourselves the way God sees us, we can develop a positive internal dialogue and be more peaceful and blessed.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 7:14-20; Jer. 12:1, 5-6.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:22', 0, 0, null, 'eKR8B7pYU8U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eKR8B7pYU8U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(1951, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/01/2021) - Living Joy', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-08-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '17:01', 0, 0, null, 'Ad03HeSiZVo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ad03HeSiZVo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(1952, 1, 'Understanding the Beatitudes', '<p>Jesus rephrased and retaught many promises made in the Old Testament in The Sermon on the Mount. The Beatitudes are generally misunderstood to be about this present time, but they are about the future. The meek will inherit the earth, those who desire justice on earth will see it, the pure in heart will see God, and mourners will be comforted, all in the future Millennial Kingdom.  </p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:1-12; Isa. 66:1-2; 61:3; Ps. 24:3-5; 37:9-11, 37; Matt. 24:37-44; 25:34-36.  </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-07-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:18', 0, 0, null, '8jp0hnDK404', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8jp0hnDK404/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(1953, 1, 'Samples from the Psalms', '<p>The Psalms offer us wonderful examples of how to pray; vivid pictures of our human condition in contrast to God&rsquo;s power to deliver; guidance for godly behavior; expressions of the reliability of God&rsquo;s words, and so much more. This teaching illustrates those offerings from select Psalms.</p> <p>Verses: Ps 5, 12, 15, 18; 19:7-14; Eph. 1:3-5, 18-21; 4:25-27, 31-32; 6:16; 2 Thess. 3:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-08-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:59', 0, 0, null, '2xuSCnKpAdM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2xuSCnKpAdM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(1954, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/08/2021) - Awake vs Woke', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:29', 0, 0, null, 'kbwGJdD4CRg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kbwGJdD4CRg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1955, 1, 'What a Friend we have in Jesus', '<p>Are you pursuing a relationship with the Lord? Jesus wants to build an intimate relationship with you. He will meet you right where you are and lead you to places that you might never go on your own.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 11:25-30; John 15:9-17; John 21:15-19; Acts 11:1-18</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2021-08-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:54', 0, 0, null, '7iAtUY9m6mw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7iAtUY9m6mw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1956, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/15/2021) – The Human Condition and God''s Power to Deliver', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:50', 0, 0, null, 'hrYxwFOKaM8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hrYxwFOKaM8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1957, 1, 'Making God Smile', '<p>The fifth commandment with promise is to honor our mother and father. God has given His children a unique way to honor Him. Every parent desires to be well thought and spoken of by their child or children. Speaking in tongues is one way we can speak well of God by declaring His mighty accomplishments, the great things He has done. And, it puts a smile on His face.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 2:1-11; Luke 1:46-55; Psalm 71:15-24; Acts 10:44-46; Psalm 148:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2021-08-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:12', 0, 0, null, 'ndr8m0sT1m0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ndr8m0sT1m0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1958, 1, 'Born for This Time', '<p>Many people are frustrated by the difficulty of the times we live in and they react in different ways. God did not make a mistake about who you are and when and where you were born. If you are alive now, you have the potential and ability to do well and be an effective minister for the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Amos 1:1; Jer. 1:5; 12:1, 5; Esther 4:8-16; 2 Cor. 5:20-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-08-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:39', 0, 0, null, 'tmf6Ej6geWk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tmf6Ej6geWk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 57, null),
(1959, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/22/2021) - Sowing Good Seeds', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-08-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '20:00', 0, 0, null, 'y3J8A9u7pgM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y3J8A9u7pgM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1960, 1, 'Born for This Time', '<p>Many people are frustrated by the difficulty of the times we live in and they react in different ways.. God did not make a mistake about who you are and when and where you were born. If you are alive now, you have the potential and ability to do well and be an effective minister for the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p> Verses:  Esther 2:5-8; 4:1-16; 2 Cor. 5:20-21; Luke 21:10-19; Acts 17:16-17.  </p> <p> Teacher:  John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-08-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:59', 0, 0, null, 'YOxkVH3H72M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YOxkVH3H72M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 23, null),
(1961, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 50 | Friends No Matter What! (Prov. 18:24; 17:17)', '<p>Everyone needs friends. Life is better being in relationship with people, and friendships are an important part of that. But not all friendships are equal. Some friends are better friends than others, and some friends are merely social. However, true friends and will stand by your side. What distinguishes one friend from the next and why does it matter? Wisdom reveals that knowing who your true friends are is important.</p> <p>Illustration: Frodo Baggins and Samwise Gamgee in the <em>The Lord of the Rings</em> on the slopes of Mount Doom in Mordor.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:24; 17:17</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-08-24', 'Castos', 0, '15:39', 9, 50, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-50-Friends-No-Matter-What-Prov.-18.24-17.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-50-friends-no-matter-what-prov-1824-1717', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 29, null),
(1962, 1, 'An Introduction to Hebrews', '<p>Who wrote the Book of Hebrews? When was it written? Who was the original audience? While we cannot affirmatively answer all these questions, the Epistle itself has enlightening internal evidence which helps the Bible student to understand this Epistle in new light.</p> <p>Verses: Hebrews 13:24, 13:3, 12:1-6, 9:11-27, 8:7-13</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2021-08-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:27', 0, 0, null, 'qWkoWgiOzvI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qWkoWgiOzvI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1963, 1, 'Prayer is an Act of Love', '<p>Jesus taught that if we love him, we will keep his words, which were not his own, but the Father&rsquo;s who sent him. One way we can demonstrate this love is by obedience to the command to pray. When we pray, we are expressing our love for God and for our Lord Jesus Christ as well as for those for whom we are praying.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 14:23, 25-31; 26:36-45; Mark 1:35; 9:14-29; Luke 5:16; 6:12; 11:1-4; 18:1-7; John 14:21-24; Acts 12:1-12; 4:23-31; Rom. 8:34; Eph. 6:18-19; Phil. 4:6-7; 1 Thess. 5:17; 1 Tim. 2:1-2; Heb. 4:16; 5:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-08-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:54', 0, 0, null, 'kSYwxcwzNZw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kSYwxcwzNZw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1964, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/29/2021) - Power in the Name', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-08-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:30', 0, 0, null, 'mar8Lgb2vvg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mar8Lgb2vvg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1965, 1, 'Living the Abundant Life', '<p>When Jesus spoke of the abundant life, he meant everlasting life and a fullness of life here with spiritual and mental abundance, not necessarily material abundance. We can avoid being sidetracked by material things when we look for the abundance that Jesus promised, such as love, joy, and peace.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:6, 9, 10; Gal. 5:22-24; 1 Peter 1:3-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-03', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '9:23', 0, 0, null, 'LKrknDPRc-o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LKrknDPRc-o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 33, null),
(1966, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/05/2021) – Labor Day Love', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-09-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:45', 0, 0, null, 'LxZzJLA9zSY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LxZzJLA9zSY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1967, 1, 'Plan for the End – It will come', '<p>Except for Christians who will be in the Rapture, death is inevitable. Hebrews 2:14-15 says that Jesus Christ freed us from fear of death, but we have to walk in that freedom. Christians who are not afraid of pain and death are in a better position to obey God in all things and thus do God&rsquo;s work here on earth and receive rewards in the future.  </p> <p>Verses: Heb. 2:14-15; 2 Tim. 4:6; 2 Pet. 1:13-14; Heb. 10:32-39; Matt. 19:23; Heb. 11:8-10, 21, 22, 24-26, 35, 39-40; 12:1-2; 2 Cor. 9:6; Luke 6:38; Col. 3:23-24; 1 Cor. 9:24-27; Phil. 4:15-17 </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-08-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:43', 0, 0, null, '2fanW2V2GDY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2fanW2V2GDY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1968, 1, 'The Christian in Spiritual War', '<p>Life is a battle. It is a spiritual battle but is played out on a physical battlefield. God helps us in that daily battle in many different ways, but we must also do our part to be prepared and to be willing to step into the battle.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 16:1-14; Ps. 144:1; Phil. 4:13; Eccles. 9:11; Ps. 33:16-19; Exod. 14:13-27; Gen. 34:24-35:7; Acts 9:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-08-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:47', 0, 0, null, 'AEWjjQid5qA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AEWjjQid5qA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(1969, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/12/2021) - See Yourself Through God''s Eyes', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-09-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:09', 0, 0, null, '27mPAuUBiXQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/27mPAuUBiXQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1970, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 51 | Get Back Up Again (Prov. 24:16)', '<p>When life knocks us down, it may seem impossible to stand back up and keep going. But we don&rsquo;t have to face our struggles in life in our own power. The person who submits to Yahweh will never walk through life alone, and when adversity knocks them down, they can rise again; disaster doesn&rsquo;t have to end in our defeat; we can get back up again!</p> <p>Illustration: Michael (&ldquo;Eddie the Eagle&rdquo;) Edwards and his struggle to qualify for ski jumping in the 1988 Winter Olympics in Calgary, Canada.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 24:16</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-09-14', 'Castos', 0, '15:17', 9, 51, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-51-Get-Back-Up-Again-Prov.-24.16-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-51-get-back-up-again-prov-2416', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 36, null),
(1972, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/19/2021) - Trusting Relationships', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-09-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:19', 0, 0, null, 'yRrUnrxGcdc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yRrUnrxGcdc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1973, 1, 'Wake Up', '<p>Listen to the song referenced in this teaching <a href="https://youtu.be/5KI_S4sa3I0" target="_blank">here.</a></p> <p>God&rsquo;s desire for mankind is that everyone be saved and come to a knowledge of the truth. This is in direct opposition to the desires of His enemy. As members of the Body of Christ, what are God&rsquo;s expectations for us as ambassadors for the Lord Jesus Christ in this Age of Grace?</p> <p>Verses: Pro. 21:2; Eph. 2:1-8; 6:11-12; 1 Tim. 2:4-5; 2 Cor. 2:10-11; 5:17-20; 10:3-6; 1 Cor. 12:1; 1 Thess. 4:13-18</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2021-09-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:23', 0, 0, null, 'lfxJ-aC0izI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lfxJ-aC0izI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1974, 1, 'What is the Destiny of the Unsaved?', '<p>The orthodox depiction of a hell ruled by the devil where people suffer eternally is not based on Scripture. This teaching explores what the Bible has to say about the destiny of the unsaved and explains the biblical depiction of &ldquo;hell.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 20:7-15; Gen. 3:4; Matt. 10:28; John 3:16; Rev. 14:9-11; Matt. 8:29; Mark 1:24; 2 Pet. 2:6; Matt. 16:27; Rom. 2:5-6; Matt. 11:20-22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '32:04', 0, 0, null, 'PS5buGnHVZw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PS5buGnHVZw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 40, null),
(1975, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/26/2021) – Transformational Prayer; Giving Glory to God', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-09-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:11', 0, 0, null, 'YykFuVgbHXk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YykFuVgbHXk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1976, 1, 'Lying and Civil Disobedience', '<p>Although some Christian philosophers say that lying is always wrong (cp. Immanuel Kant), other Christian philosophers see that telling an untruth to defend the life or wellbeing of oneself or others is allowed by God (cp. Dietrich Bonhoeffer). Decisions about how to behave when the government is evil are not easy, and they must be made individually, but the Bible does provide guidance on the matter.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 12:47-48; Ps. 119:69; Job 4:6-7; Prov. 28:12, 28; Exod. 1:15-20; 2:1-2; Gen. 38:11-19; Matt. 1:3; Josh. 2:1-6; Matt. 1:5; 1 Sam. 19:11-18; 2 Sam. 17:15-20; 1 Kings 18:1-4; Jer. 36:26; Acts 5:27-32 </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:35', 0, 0, null, 'tzrv5ZpDl5c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tzrv5ZpDl5c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1977, 1, 'Does Hell Exist?', '<p>The modern Christian concept of Hell has strayed far from biblical truth. There is no such thing as a &ldquo;Hell&rdquo; that is a fiery place, ruled by the Devil where people are &ldquo;tortured forever.&rdquo; God offers everyone the choice between living and dying (John 3:16; Rom. 6:23). The wicked will be thrown into the Lake of Fire where they&rsquo;ll suffer according to the extent of their sin and be annihilated.   </p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:10; Rev. 14:11; 20:7-15; John 3:16; Rom. 6:23; 12:19; Matt. 8:29; 11:20-24; 23:29; Mark 1:24; 2 Pet. 2:6; 2 Cor. 5:10; Rom. 2:5-6; </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:39', 0, 0, null, 'Dm_og_EPCzM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Dm_og_EPCzM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(1978, 1, 'The Gift of Holy Spirit and the Interpretation of Tongues', '<p>The interpretation of tongues is a not prophecy. It came with the new gift that God gave via Jesus Christ on the Day of Pentecost (Acts 2). Speaking in tongues is speaking to God, and it is the interpretation of that message. In contrast, prophecy is a message to people from God. Prophecy has been around since Genesis, whereas the interpretation of tongues has only been available since Pentecost.   </p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 12:10; Num. 11:16-17; 2 Kings 2:9; 1 Sam. 16:4; Ezek. 36:23-28; John 7:39; Eph. 1:13; Luke 24:49; John 14:16-17; 2 Pet. 1:4; 2 Cor. 5:17.</p> <p> Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '54:09', 0, 0, null, 'iRV4Bbq1fdc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iRV4Bbq1fdc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(1979, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/03/2021) – Pay Attention', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-10-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '21:53', 0, 0, null, 'qpqRRXH311o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qpqRRXH311o/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1980, 1, 'Growing in God&rsquo;s Grace (Part 1)', '<p>Approaching God at the throne of Grace daily to receive that which is needed in our individual walk with Him is essential to our growth as Christians. It also helps us to walk with the brethren in unity and service. Humility is key to emptying ourselves before God with open and honest communication.</p> <p>Verses: John 1:14, 16-17; Eph. 2:8; Rom. 3:21-26; 5:18-21; 5:1-2; Heb. 4:15-16; Deut. 8:3, 16-18; Eph. 4:7; 1 Pet. 4:10-11; 5:5-7; Jam. 4:4-6; 2 Pet. 3:18</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2021-09-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:03', 0, 0, null, 'LCi36lAu1tI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LCi36lAu1tI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1981, 1, 'Galatians 1-3', '<p>Written in 48 AD, Galatians was almost certainly the first Scripture penned since Malachi, hundreds of years before. The message of Galatians is important for understanding what Christians have in Christ today, and this overview points out some of the vast differences in how God relates to humankind as a result of Christ&rsquo;s sacrifice.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:1-8, 10-12, 23-24; 2:1-6, 9-13, 20-21; 3:1-11, 13-14, 26-29.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-09-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:53', 0, 0, null, 'NCc-Rgh7ldg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NCc-Rgh7ldg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(1982, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/10/2021) - Prayer and Praise from the Psalms', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:50', 0, 0, null, 'EW_TueCXZZI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EW_TueCXZZI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1983, 1, 'Growing in God&rsquo;s Grace (Part 2)', '<p>God has given us all things that pertain to life and godliness, so how do we proceed? 2 Peter presents a sevenfold ladder to grow in God&rsquo;s grace over a lifetime. The benefit in doing these things is that we will never fall and God promises an entrance to the Everlasting Kingdom with an abundant supply.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Pet. 3:18; 1:1-11; Matt. 8:5-10; 2 Tim. 3:14-17; 1 Thess. 4:4-5; Rom. 5:3-5; James 1:2-4; 1 Tim. 4:7-8; Rom. 12:5; Heb. 13:1; Col. 3:11</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2021-09-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:27', 0, 0, null, 'TunNrggl5fM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TunNrggl5fM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1984, 1, 'The Lord Building his Church', '<p>The Book of Acts presents the colorful record of the Lord&rsquo;s building his Church and introduces us to courageous ministers of the Gospel. This teaching follows the story in Acts with Stephen&rsquo;s execution, Saul&rsquo;s conversion and early travels and teachings, Barnabas&rsquo; support of Saul, and Saul&rsquo;s (Paul&rsquo;s) and Barnabas&rsquo; first missionary journey. It emphasizes the addition of Gentiles to the church, and the conflicts that resulted from that truth.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 6:5, 8, 10; 7:51, 56, 58; 8:1,3; 9:1-2, 15, 17, 19-29; 11:18-25; 12:25; 13:9, 46; 14:5, 19-20; Phil. 3:4-11</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-09-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:16', 0, 0, null, 'jRTR2L4vrGU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jRTR2L4vrGU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1985, 1, 'Walking in Love by God&rsquo;s Grace', '<p>To walk in God&rsquo;s love by His Grace is our reasonable service to the Lord. This expository teaching presents many practical verses on walking with our fellow brothers and sisters to bring harmony to the Body of Christ and honor and glory to our Heavenly Father and to our Lord Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1-21; Eph. 4:1-3; Rom. 13:8-14; 14:1-15:5</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2021-09-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:54', 0, 0, null, 'kdXiwslO-ZU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kdXiwslO-ZU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(1986, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/17/2021) – Is Our God Violent?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-10-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:33', 0, 0, null, 'MW_Ep96W8Ok', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MW_Ep96W8Ok/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(1987, 1, 'A Mighty Fortress is our God', '<p>God surely is our refuge and our fortress, our place of protection and projected strength. God asks us to seek His strength in our lives and commands us to be strong in Him. To effectively minister to others, we must walk in His power and that of our Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 91:2,9; Isa. 44:6-8; Jer. 32:17, 27; Ps. 59:16-17; 27:1-6; 18:1-19; Deut. 10:17; Josh. 1:9; Deut. 20:4; Ps. 27:7-8; 2 Kings 6:8-23; Isa. 40:29-31; 41:10-13; Eph. 3:14-19; 6:10-18; 1 Pet. 5:1-9; Phil. 4:12-13; 2 Cor. 12:1-10; Rev. 21:1; 1 Pet. 4:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-10-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:59', 0, 0, null, 'KwQMm2ghiIs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KwQMm2ghiIs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(1988, 1, 'Paul&rsquo;s Second Missionary Journey', '<p>This teaching opens with a re-cap of Paul&rsquo;s first missionary journey through Galatia and his early trips to Jerusalem. It then focuses on the details of Paul&rsquo;s second missionary journey, with emphasis on the people involved, such as Barnabas, John Mark, Silas, Timothy, Luke, Aquilla and Priscilla, and the key cities where Paul spent considerable time: Philippi, Thessalonica and Corinth.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 15:30-36, 40-41; 16:1-6, 9-10, 13-24, 35-40; 17:1, 5, 16; 18:1-17, 22</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-10-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:05', 0, 0, null, '2J9qLICGH8c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2J9qLICGH8c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1989, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 52 | Foolishness Destroys Wealth (Prov. 29.3)', '<p>Sometimes we only learn our lesson after the consequences of our actions catch up with us. Why is it so hard at times to see the pain down the road that our actions will cause? Foolishness causes a wide range of damage to our lives, and one of the areas it can drastically affect is our finances. Being enticed by sin and making poor choices, especially when it comes to sexual conduct, can have far reaching and harmful effects where we destroy our wealth in the process.</p> <p>Illustration: The Parable of the Lost Son (Luke 15:11-24)</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 29:3; 5:8-13</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-10-22', 'Castos', 0, '14:15', 9, 52, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/4f1538ec-3fc2-4012-893a-e9515118018e-Ep-52-Foolishness-Destroys-Wealth-Prov.-29.3-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-52-foolishness-destroys-wealth-prov-293', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 26, null),
(1990, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/24/2021) - Forget Not All His Benefits', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-10-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:13', 0, 0, null, 'jKVp7Q_3Glc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jKVp7Q_3Glc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(1991, 1, 'The Nature of Christ - Introduction: Background of the Epistle to the Galatians', '<p>This teaching explores the difficulties experienced by the churches in Galatia and Paul&rsquo;s concerns and purpose in writing this letter. Pivotal to understanding this letter is the truth that the &ldquo;fruit of the spirit&rdquo; listed in Galatians 5 is a picture of the nature of Christ, which lives in all those who have accepted Christ as their savior.</p> <p>Verses: Galatians 5:1, 13, 16-25</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-10-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:40', 0, 0, null, 'jIjdW_1_L40', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jIjdW_1_L40/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(1992, 1, 'Paul&rsquo;s Third Missionary Journey', '<p>This recap of Paul&rsquo;s first two missionary journeys highlights the key people, cities and struggles involved. His third journey focused on Ephesus, where we meet powerful leaders like Apollos and Priscilla and Aquila. The teaching fast-forwards to the final verses of Acts, which describe Paul&rsquo;s first imprisonment in Rome. It closes with a chart displaying where and when the writing of the epistles of Paul occurred throughout his journeys.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 18:23; 19:1-7, 10-12, 18-20; 20:5; 28:16-28</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-10-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:35', 0, 0, null, 'GH1wZS38oYE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GH1wZS38oYE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(1993, 1, 'The Nature of Christ - Cornerstone', '<p>Jesus Christ was prophesied in the Hebrew scriptures to be the &ldquo;cornerstone&rdquo;. To understand the significance of this concept we need to look to ancient construction methods, not modern-day methods. The ancient cornerstone was the first stone laid in a building, and it determined the physical orientation for the rest of the stones set in the building. In like manner, the nature and work of Christ has set the standard for how the church is to be organized and operated.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:19-22; 4:7-16; 5:1-2; 6:10-13; Job 38:1-7; Isa. 28:14-18; Matt. 3:13-17; 4:1-11; 7:24-27; 16:1-4; 21:42-44; Luke 22:39-42; John 5:19, 30; 15:4-5; Acts 4:1-12; Rom. 9:30-33; 12:12-13; 1 Cor. 3:1-12; 12:12-26; 1 Pet. 2:1-10; 5:8-11; James 4:7-10</p> <p>Teacher: Brian Bassindale</p>', '2021-10-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '54:05', 0, 0, null, 'knB3-ifpQ_w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/knB3-ifpQ_w/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(1994, 1, 'Seek Humility', '<p>God wants us to acknowledge that apart from Him we can do nothing of true value. He is the one who knows us, the one who created us. He has a plan for each one of us. This teaching looks at God&rsquo;s perspective of humility, the Lord Jesus as our example of it, and how we as God&rsquo;s children should seek it.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 66:1-2; Prov. 15:31-33; 22:4; Zeph. 2:3; Matt. 12:45-46; 2 Kings 5:1-14; Luke 4:1-13; 1 Pet. 5:1-11; Eph. 4:1-6</p> <p>Teacher:  Joyce Adams</p>', '2021-10-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:56', 0, 0, null, '0p7-ZNreaNo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0p7-ZNreaNo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1995, 1, 'The Epistles of Paul', '<p>This teaching explains the times and places of the writing of Paul&rsquo;s Epistles, illustrating from Acts and various Epistles when and from where the letters were written. It is important in studying the Bible to understand that we, now having the whole Bible, have a more complete perspective than did the writer or speaker of the time, and to consider, in contrast, what he understood and what his audience understood.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 1:1; 2:2; 1 Thess. 1:1; 2 Thess. 1:1; 1 Cor. 1:1; 2 Cor. 1:1; Rom 16:3, 21, 23; Gal. 1:4; Eph. 1:3, 9, 13, 19</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-10-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:14', 0, 0, null, 'DDyurU8sf3s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DDyurU8sf3s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(1996, 1, 'The Nature of Christ: Words as Warfare', '<p>This teaching explores the authority that our words have in forming the roots of either blessings or curses in our lives using illustrations from the parable of The Sower, as well as powerful personal examples from the teacher&rsquo;s life. Our words can produce fruit and affect quality of life and are an important aspect of how we conduct spiritual warfare, as we follow the example of Jesus&rsquo; powerful words.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 4:3-20; Eph. 3:14-20; Gal. 5:16-24</p> <p>Teacher: Len Cicio</p>', '2021-10-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:04', 0, 0, null, 'E7Kp0o9LZfQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/E7Kp0o9LZfQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(1997, 1, 'What is True Worship?', '<p>This teaching examines why and how we worship our Heavenly Father and Lord Jesus Christ. The first record of worship in the Bible reveals that attitude of heart is the most important aspect of worship. The epistles tell us that God asks us to present our bodies as living sacrifices to Him and that we can worship God in everything we do, i.e., &ldquo;do everything to the glory of God.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 4:2-11; Jer. 10:6; Ps. 86:10; 95:6-7; 1 Chron. 16:23-34; Gen. 4:3-7; Heb. 11:1-4, 6; Exod. 20:1-6; 1 Sam. 15:22; Deut. 29:18; Isa. 29:13-14; Matt. 15:7-9; Rom. 12:1-2; Col. 3:16-17; 1 Cor. 10:31; Heb. 10:1-14; Phil. 2:5-11; John 14:30-31; Rev. 5:1-14</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-10-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:28', 0, 0, null, 'r5Rdtg50KX8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/r5Rdtg50KX8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(1998, 1, 'Becoming Like Christ', '<p>Although the Bible says that Christians are to be lights in the world, too many Christians have not been transformed into the image of Christ and so do not really stand out as different from the unsaved people in the world. The big key to shining on the outside is being like Christ on the inside. Thankfully, the Bible gives keys to becoming transformed into the image of Christ.  </p> <p>Verses: Gal. 4:19; Eph. 4:17-24; Exod. 21:23-25; 1 Cor. 12:24-26; Prov. 27:17; Phil. 2:3-4. </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-10-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:39', 0, 0, null, 'GOrWYGvfabg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GOrWYGvfabg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(1999, 1, 'The Protestant Reformation Changed Everything', '<p>The Protestant Reformation brought about sweeping changes, not only in the Christian Church, but in the family and in society itself. From the end of the first century until October 31, 1517 the Church, which had become the Roman Catholic Church, put many unbiblical doctrines in place. The Protestant Reformation restored the centrality of the Bible in worship services and eventually even changed society and government itself.   </p> <p>Download the teaching notes <a href="https://media.spiritandtruthonline.org/Reformation-the-Reformation-Changed-Much.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:54', 0, 0, null, 'jmnMWhb1y_E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jmnMWhb1y_E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2000, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/31/2021) – Trust God - He Has Promised and Given Proof', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-10-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:08', 0, 0, null, '3T2dp7O0_TE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3T2dp7O0_TE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2001, 1, 'Ephesians 3', '<p>Ephesians 3 speaks powerfully of the Administration of Grace that began on the Day of Pentecost but was hidden in God before that time. It speaks of blessings to the Gentiles as part of the Body of Christ, our individual ministries because of God&rsquo;s grace, not because our lives are perfect, the manifold wisdom of God revealed through the Church, our access to God, and many other wonderful things.</p> <p>Verses: Ephesians 3:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:00', 0, 0, null, 'IAt2Bg4HCEw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IAt2Bg4HCEw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(2002, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/07/2021) -- Heap Praise On Him', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-11-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:38', 0, 0, null, 'WuJmue61LGI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WuJmue61LGI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2003, 1, 'Compassion', '<p>The very first word that God used to describe himself to Moses is compassionate. The words &ldquo;compassionate&rdquo; and &ldquo;compassion&rdquo; convey intense emotions of empathy, love, and pity that compel action. Jesus Christ is God&rsquo;s most compassionate gift to mankind. Jesus&rsquo;s words and actions vividly illustrated God&rsquo;s compassion. Christians are to follow his example by showing compassion to others.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 34:6; Ps. 103:13; Lam. 3:22; John 1:18; Matt. 14:13-14; Luke 7:12-15; Eph. 4:32; 1 Cor. 12:26; Col. 3:12-14</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-11-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:00', 0, 0, null, '5tu-Ip583vc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5tu-Ip583vc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2004, 1, 'Taking Care of One Another - Part 1', '<p>This two-part teaching addresses the concept that Christians are to have a special love for one another. It answers 3 questions: Where did the idea originate, what does it look like, and how we do it. This teaching explains the origin of &ldquo;loving one another&rdquo; gives a detailed background of the Corinthian church. Part 2 will address two illustrations of caring for one another from the Epistle of 1 Corinthians.</p> <p>Verses: Lev. 19:16-18; John 13:3-4, 12-14, 34-35; 1 Cor. 1:10-13</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-11-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:47', 0, 0, null, 'RhhCoRVCSbU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RhhCoRVCSbU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2005, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 53 | Out of Control (Prov. 25:28)', '<p>Emotions are a powerful part of who God created us to be. He did not intend for us to be controlled by our emotions&ndash; we must learn to master them. Without self-control, we become dangerous and unpredictable. We don&rsquo;t often make good decisions when emotionally embroiled, tending to hurt others by our words and actions because out of control emotions tend to result in foolish choices.</p> <p>Illustration: Russell Crowe assaulting a hotel desk clerk with a telephone in a fit of rage.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 25:28</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-11-09', 'Castos', 0, '15:41', 9, 53, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/ee3f6876-9910-405e-9986-db2f96b89683-Ep-53-Out-of-Control-Prov.-25.28-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-53-out-of-control-prov-2528', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2006, 1, 'Lessons from Deuteronomy', '<p>The Bible tells us to be imitators of God, but to do that we need His perspective. Thankfully, God has told us a lot about how we should be living, and many rules and examples that are not in the New Testament are in the Law of Moses. Deuteronomy 22 and 23 provide an example of very specific and practical laws to govern life.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 22:1-12; 23:1-25; Exod. 12:48; 23:4, 5; Lev. 15:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:19', 0, 0, null, '0aHqm16IfXA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0aHqm16IfXA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2012, 4, 'The Creation - Evolution Controversy | Session 5 | The Biblical Record of Creation (continued)', '<p>This session continues the explanation of the biblical record of creation, emphasizing the importance of understanding what the Bible does and does not say. The evidence around us concurs with the creation record. Creation declares the glory of God, while the &ldquo;mud-to-man&rdquo; theory is an affront to God and turns people away from Him. Christians need to be able to present the truth of creation in a meaningful way.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:17-31; 2:1-4, 15, 20-23; 3:1-5, 17-19; 7:11-20; 8:13; Isa. 11:6-9; 40:26; Ps. 19:1-4; 7:10; 147:1-4; Luke 4:5-7; Rev. 22:3; Rom. 1:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '42:40', 20, 5, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Creation-of-the-universe-continued.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/creation-of-the-universe-continued', '/i/seminars/CEC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(2013, 4, 'The Creation - Evolution Controversy | Session 4 | Darwin&rsquo;s Motivation, The Biblical Record of Creation', '<p>This session concludes the discussion on the &ldquo;evidence for early man,&rdquo; then summarizes the shortcomings of the evolution model from the various scientific perspectives. This is followed by a discussion of the evidence for a relatively young earth and moon, and the problems with the supposed timescale of billions of years. The focus then changes to the creation model and what the Bible says about creation.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1-17; Isa. 14:12-14; 45:18; Ezek. 28:11-17; 2 Chron. 9:29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '01:06:51', 20, 4, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Darwin-rejected-God-Creation-of-the-universe.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/darwin-rejected-god-creation-of-the-universe', '/i/seminars/CEC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(2014, 4, 'The Creation - Evolution Controversy | Session 3 | The Geologic Column and Fossils', '<p>This session opens with a discussion of the primordial earth: the chemicals, atmospheric conditions, and timeframe required for the emergence of life from non-life. It explains the origin of the geologic column and its revision over time. The critical lack of evidence in the fossil record for transitional life-forms required for evolution is discussed in detail. The session closes with a look at the various efforts made to find evidence for &ldquo;early man.&rdquo;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '01:12:40', 20, 3, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/The-geologic-column-Fossils.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/the-geologic-column-fossils', '/i/seminars/CEC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 27, null),
(2015, 4, 'The Creation - Evolution Controversy | Session 1 | Purpose, Definitions and The Two-Model System', '<p>The session begins by defining the terms &ldquo;evolution&rdquo; and &ldquo;creation.&rdquo; It examines the essential characteristics of a science, since evolution is widely believed to be &ldquo;scientific,&rdquo; in contrast to creation, which is classified as religion. An explanation of the &ldquo;two-model system&rdquo; then provides the basis for evaluating both creation and evolution against the available evidence. The evolution model is evaluated in terms of mathematical probability theory, physics, and biology.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '01:14:01', 20, 1, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Introduction-The-two-model-system.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/introduction-the-two-model-system', '/i/seminars/CEC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 54, null),
(2016, 4, 'The Creation - Evolution Controversy | Session 2 | Mechanism for Change', '<p>This session continues discussing evolution from the biological perspective. Evolution is believed to have occurred as a long sequence of undirected changes. However, no mechanism has yet been identified to explain the development of complex organisms based on this process. The mechanisms suggested&mdash;natural selection and mutations&mdash;are not supported by the fossil record or by studying living organisms. The popular phrase &ldquo;survival of the fittest&rdquo; is examined, then the focus shifts to biochemistry and patterns in species at the molecular level.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 1:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2019-01-01', 'Castos', 0, '01:12:36', 20, 2, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Mathematical-evidence-Evolution-is-a-cruel-process.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/mathematical-evidence-evolution-is-a-cruel-process', '/i/seminars/CEC.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 75, null),
(2017, 7, 'Open View Syllabus', '<p>This is the syllabus for The Open View of God Seminar.</p>', '2021-11-01', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/the-open-view-of-god-syllabus.pdf', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2033, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/14/2021) – Am I Building My Foundation on Sand?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-11-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:40', 0, 0, null, 'aKvQTMcUU6s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aKvQTMcUU6s/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2034, 1, 'Self-Control', '<p>It is essential that we control the content of our minds. Self-control is both the product and the fruit of living a life that aligns with the precepts and desires of God. It is God&rsquo;s desire to reward those believers who freely and diligently seek His face to serve the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:22; Prov. 12:15-20; Matt. 4:1-11; Titus 1:1-9; Deut. 12:28; 2 Pet. 1:1-11; 1Cor. 9:25-27; Eph. 4:11-32</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2021-11-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:20', 0, 0, null, 'lsv_cTTs1wc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lsv_cTTs1wc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2035, 1, 'Taking Care of One Another - Part 2', '<p>This two-part teaching addresses the concept that Christians are to have a special love for one another. This second part addresses the questions &ldquo;what does that look like?&rdquo; and &ldquo;how we do it?&rdquo; &ldquo;What does it look like?&rdquo; is answered with two illustrations from 1 Corinthians 8 and 10. A sample of &ldquo;how we do it?&rdquo; is presented in Philippians 2.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:34-35; 1 Cor. 8:1-13; 10:14, 18-24, 27-33; Phil. 2:3-4</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2021-11-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:23', 0, 0, null, '55rieg2_ZUU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/55rieg2_ZUU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2036, 1, 'The Privilege of Sharing Your Faith', '<p>People who lived during the Old Testament and the Four Gospels were not directed by God to share their Faith with others. Jesus gave a brand-new message to the Apostles in Acts 1:8: to be witnesses for Christ to the ends of the earth. Today, Christians have been given the ministry and the message to speak to reconcile people to God. For that reason, Christians are ambassadors for Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8; Exod. 19:5-6; 32:25-26; Num. 1:48-50; Deut. 28:1; Matt. 10:5-7; Luke 10:1; 1 Cor. 15:3-4; Rom. 10:9; 2 Cor. 5:18-20; 1 Cor. 3:9; 1 Pet. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:00', 0, 0, null, 'F8lM7y9eyYw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/F8lM7y9eyYw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2037, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/21/2021) – Faith, Hope and Love – Part 3', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:06', 0, 0, null, 'jLW4_n48qKc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jLW4_n48qKc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2038, 1, 'On Sharing Your Faith', '<p>Sharing belief in Christ is a wonderful privilege and something that God has directed us to do. The New Testament shows that Christian witnessing plays a large part in bringing people to Christ and everlasting life. From Adam and Eve through the ministry of Jesus Christ, disciples were not told to share their Faith with others, but we are invited to join God&rsquo;s efforts as fellow workers with Him.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 22:1-12; 23:1-25; Exod. 12:48; 23:4, 5; Lev. 15:16-18; Gen. 5:1-21; 11:10-26; Exod. 19:1-6; 32:25-28; Num. 1:47-51; Deut. 28:1; Matt. 10:5-7; Luke 10:1-9; Acts 1:8; 1 Cor. 3:9; 15:3-4; 2 Cor. 5:18-20; 1 Pet. 3:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:45', 0, 0, null, '7jSq60a3eaM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7jSq60a3eaM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2039, 7, 'REV Appendix 10: Jesus is the Son of God, not God the Son (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 10: <strong>&ldquo;Jes&uacute;s es el Hijo de Dios, no Dios el Hijo&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 10: <strong>&ldquo;Jesus is the Son of God, Not God the Son&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2021-11-24', null, 0, null, 67, 10, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_10_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 32, null),
(2040, 1, 'The Bible and Emotions', '<p>God expresses emotions and He created humankind in His image, so emotions are a fundamental part of every person&rsquo;s life. Emotional intelligence plays an important role in emotional wholeness ands helps us to navigate living in a broken world as fallen people. The Bible sometimes speaks of the emotions people are feeling, but most often we must bring our knowledge of emotions to the text to understand it more fully.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 16:1-5; 40:6; 45:25-28; 29:31-35; 30:1-8; 2 Sam. 3:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:23', 0, 0, null, '8egZ61I9dMw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8egZ61I9dMw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2041, 1, 'Job – The Righteous Sufferer', '<p>This teaching addresses many of the lessons in the Book of Job, including that innocent, righteous people suffer and we usually don&rsquo;t know why; there is always something to be thankful for; Satan is a liar and will never admit he is wrong; and people in very difficult situations can have emotional outbreaks that are uncharacteristic of them, and the person still needs to be shown love and compassion.</p> <p>Verses: Job 1:1-22; 2:1-13; 3:1-3; 4:1-2, 7, 12-19; 6:24-29</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '54:22', 0, 0, null, 'aw9ASWs1ym8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aw9ASWs1ym8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2043, 1, 'Use Your Time Wisely', '<p>The Bible exhorts us to use time wisely because God created us to do good works that He has prepared for us and we honor Him by doing His work. Also, God wants everyone to have great rewards on Judgment Day, and people will be rewarded according to what they have done.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 2:10; 5:15-16; Eccles. 12:13-14; 3:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-26', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '12:07', 0, 0, null, 'VoB2HY6fLHM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VoB2HY6fLHM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2044, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/28/2021) – Patterns', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-11-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '17:33', 0, 0, null, 'cOv1-tWznyk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cOv1-tWznyk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2045, 1, 'Godly Weeping and Mourning', '<p>Life in this fallen world is difficult, and you would think that with so much hardship in the world, people would be experts at handling it physically, mentally, and emotionally, but alas, that is not the case. Many people are not equipped to deal with things like death, pain and suffering, especially emotionally. Thankfully the Bible has advice and examples that help us through difficult emotional times.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 34:5-8; 1 Sam. 1:1-8; Eccles. 3:1, 4; Jer. 8:18; 9:1; Matt. 24:12; Luke 19:28-44; John 11:32-35; Rom. 12:15.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-11-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:39', 0, 0, null, 'zq4AsSXfi_0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zq4AsSXfi_0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2046, 1, 'We Have This Treasure', '<p>It is God&rsquo;s desire that all men be saved and come to the knowledge of the truth. The Lord Jesus Christ made everlasting life possible and has commissioned His Body to herald forth the good news of the gospel allowing others to receive the gift of everlasting life and heavenly rewards.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:1-9; 1 Cor. 2:1-7; 2 Cor. 5:17-20; 1 Thess. 2:19; Acts 10:34-46; 1 Tim. 2:1-7; 2 Tim. 1:6-12</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2021-11-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:38', 0, 0, null, '1OU2Gmf9vOI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1OU2Gmf9vOI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(2047, 1, 'Say &ldquo;No&rdquo; to Evil', '<p>It is noteworthy that the very first lesson in Proverbs is to say &ldquo;No&rdquo; to evil enticements. It is important for believers to think through who they are and how they want to live before they are in pressured situations so they can make the right decisions and act in ways that bring peace and joy, not agitation and regret.</p> <p>Verses: Proverbs 1:1-5, 8-19</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-04', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:27', 0, 0, null, 'U8Y2IPaWaQM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U8Y2IPaWaQM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2048, 7, 'Chronology of Israel from Alexander to Christ', '<p>This document contains the chronology of Israel from Alexander to Christ.</p>', '2021-12-07', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/CHRONOLOGY OF ISRAEL FROM ALEXANDER TO CHRIST.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 9, 16, null),
(2049, 1, 'Ruth - a story of love, hope, and redemption', '<p>This teaching explores the story of Naomi&rsquo;s transformation from despair to happiness through the loving actions of Ruth and Boaz. It is the story of God doing extraordinary things with ordinary people.</p> <p>Verses: Ruth 1:16,17; 2:8-12,19-20; 3:8-11; 4:13-17</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2021-12-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '58:22', 0, 0, null, 'msQOcVWzqCw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/msQOcVWzqCw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2050, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/12/2021) – Mark of a Healthy Christian - Our Conversation', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:45', 0, 0, null, 'cggjKcp6QzQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cggjKcp6QzQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2051, 1, 'Where does Joy Come From?', '<p>This is an overview of where joy comes from, how to have it and practical suggestions for how to hang on to it during times of hardship and affliction.</p> <p>Verses: Ecc. 2:26; Ps. 92:4-5; Prov. 10:28; Isa. 66:5; Hab. 3:17-19; Mark 4:13-20; Luke 6:20-31; Phil. 2:13; 2 Cor. 6:4-10; 7:4; 8:2</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2021-12-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:36', 0, 0, null, 'xR_-297Xqv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xR_-297Xqv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2052, 1, 'Zechariah and Elizabeth', '<p>Zechariah and Elizabeth are prominent figures in biblical history because they were the parents of John the Baptist. But like many painters or authors who only become famous after they die, Zechariah and Elizabeth were not prominent when they were alive. We know little about them from Bible itself, but what we do know gives us insight into their life and struggle.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 1:5-25, 39-45, 57-64, 80</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:13', 0, 0, null, 'W4afz2VsIGw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/W4afz2VsIGw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(2053, 1, 'Jesus in Old Testament Prophecies', '<p>The Book of Matthew seems to say that the Old Testament foretold that Jesus was to be born of a virgin, go to Egypt, and be the cause of great weeping in Judea. However, understood in their Old Testament contexts, they are not about Jesus. Nevertheless, they apply to Jesus in the sense that what happened in the Old Testament pointed to Jesus, applied to Jesus, and was typological of Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:23; 2:15, 18; Hos. 10:13-11:3; Jer. 31:1-17; Isa. 7:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:06', 0, 0, null, 'lO3yIZ29NS0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lO3yIZ29NS0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2054, 1, 'Transformation: The Story of Judah and Tamar', '<p>The story of Judah and Tamar is part of a larger narrative that illustrates God&rsquo;s grace in Judah&rsquo;s and describes his transformation from a wicked, selfish, dishonorable man to a man who is willing to substitute himself in the place of his brother Benjamin, as a bond servant in Egypt. The amazing transformation of Judah foreshadows the transformation available in the coming Messiah, the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 29:30-35; 37:2-11, 18-20, 26-27, 31-36; 38:1-26; 42:1-4; 43:1-9; 44:1-34; 49:8-10; Gal. 2:20; 2 Cor. 3:18</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2021-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:06', 0, 0, null, 'mdZCiC0C8hw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mdZCiC0C8hw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2055, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 55 | Keep My Commandments and Live (Prov. 4:1-4)', '<p>Children watch the behavior and life patterns of their parents and innately model their life after them. If the teaching of the parents is godly and their lives exhibit wisdom, their children will see that and learn how to live with wisdom in their life as well. But parents also must explicitly teach their children about wisdom in hopes that the children listen to and hold onto their words.</p> <p>Illustration: The example of the obedience of the Rechabites to the commandments of their ancestor Jonadab.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 4:1-4; 9:10; Jer. 35:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-12-15', 'Castos', 0, '19:19', 9, 55, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/693ebcf9-f69f-437f-89bf-63daae35a2b6-Ep-55-Keep-My-Commandments-and-Live-Prov.-4.1-4-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-55-keep-my-commandments-and-live-prov-41-4', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2056, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 54 | Wealth Flies Away (Prov. 23:4-5)', '<p>We all need money to live. With the ever-increasing cost of living and the invention of so many new things to make life better, getting rich can sound like a good plan to solve that problem and acquire everything we want. But wealth is deceptive in that it is inherently unstable. One day we can have it, and the next day it vanishes.</p> <p>Illustration: Sean Russell&rsquo;s disastrous 2017 investment in bitcoin.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 23:4-5</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-12-13', 'Castos', 0, '17:12', 9, 54, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/9c845cbe-ab39-45d2-9b8e-7aea3467e157-Ep-54-Wealth-Flies-Away-Prov.-23.4-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-54-wealth-flies-away-prov-234-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(2057, 1, 'Our God of Peace', '<p>Peace can seem to be elusive in today&rsquo;s world and many people have different ideas of what peace is. God has provided His idea of peace and has many sections of Scripture devoted to the subject. Explore some Scriptures to find out about what God&rsquo;s idea of peace is and why we need it.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:19-23, 16; John 14:27; Rom. 5:1, 16:20; 2 Cor. 13:11; Heb. 13:20</p> <p>Teacher: James Cutler</p>', '2021-12-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:56', 0, 0, null, 'WvrYKjqqBkQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WvrYKjqqBkQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2058, 1, 'Being a More Effective Christian', '<p>God has equipped His born-again Christian children with everything needed to be effective ministers for Him and do the work that Christ himself would do if he were here. Knowing that human weakness magnifies God&rsquo;s power and that every Christian is important equips us to do the Kingdom work that God has called us to.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 5:8; 10:14-17; 1 Cor. 1:26-31; 3:9.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:10', 0, 0, null, 'yNJkNeAXSXU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yNJkNeAXSXU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2059, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/19/2021) – Rahab - A Woman of Honor', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2021-12-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:02', 0, 0, null, 'CbB-RNO3CIk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CbB-RNO3CIk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2060, 1, 'The Nature of Christ - Service', '<p>This teaching explores an aspect of the nature of Christ not specifically listed in Galatians 5: service, opening with the question, &ldquo;How does freedom equate to servitude?&rdquo; The Levitical &ldquo;laws of holiness&rdquo; can be summed up as serving our neighbors. Jesus equated following him with serving one another. Service is in our nature to do, as we have been given the nature of Christ in us.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 5:13-14; Lev. 19:18; John 15:13; Psalm 22:31</p> <p>Teacher: John Hickman</p>', '2021-12-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:34', 0, 0, null, 'uQuZv-wNPDs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uQuZv-wNPDs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2061, 1, 'Be the Gift that You Are', '<p>God specifically says He chose the no-good things of the world, the weak and the low-born, to put to shame those who are wise, strong, and powerful, yet many Christians are held back by thoughts that they are not good enough, or smart enough, or influential enough to make a difference in the world. We can make a huge difference in the world if we will just move forward and do it.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 6:1-12; 1 Cor. 1:24-31; Eph. 4:7-13; Ps. 68:1, 4, 6, 7, 14-16, 18, 27, 29; Matt. 1:18-21, 24-25; 13:55</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:53', 0, 0, null, 'zkBRZnfwZZM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zkBRZnfwZZM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2062, 1, 'Be the Gift that You Are', '<p>Some Christians believe that they are not good enough, or wise or influential enough, to be effective for God. But God specifically says that not many wise or noble are called, but instead He has chosen the &ldquo;no good things of the world to put to shame those who are wise.&rdquo; As Christians move forward with the things that they do have, God magnifies those things and magnifies Himself to the world.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 6:1-12; 1 Cor. 1:24-31; Eph. 4:7-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-24', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:34', 0, 0, null, '4A5U63tjhOo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4A5U63tjhOo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2063, 7, 'REV Appendix 1: The Permanence of Christian Salvation (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 1: <strong>&ldquo;La permanencia de la salvaci&oacute;n cristiana&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 1: <strong>&ldquo;The Permanence of Christian Salvation&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2021-12-27', null, 0, null, 67, 1, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_1_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(2064, 1, 'Joseph, the Stepfather of Jesus', '<p>Not too much is written about Joseph in the Bible, but what is written gives us a good look into the man who was so influential in raising Jesus. The Gospel of Matthew tells us that Joseph was a righteous, good, and kind man, very disciplined and obedient to God. He was a &ldquo;builder,&rdquo; not specifically a &ldquo;carpenter,&rdquo; which was not a prestigious job.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 1:18-25; 13:54-57; Mark 6:3; Luke 2:24</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-30', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:15', 0, 0, null, 'UufbuR5X9jk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UufbuR5X9jk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2065, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/02/2022) – Hearts Can Change – Part 1', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-01-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:49', 0, 0, null, 'EGwlodf2MNA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EGwlodf2MNA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2066, 1, 'The Magi and Jesus&rsquo; Birth', '<p>The Magi came from the country of Parthia and traveled across the international border between Parthia and Rome to see the Messiah, arriving in Jerusalem more than a year after Jesus was born and inquiring of King Herod and the religious leaders the exact location. Understanding Micah&rsquo;s prophecy helps us understand how the religious leaders knew where Christ was born.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:1-13; Mic. 1:1-6; 4:1-13; 5:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2021-12-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:37', 0, 0, null, 'KYh4q4wdK-Y', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KYh4q4wdK-Y/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null);
