(2067, 7, 'Bible Study Guide', '<p>This Study Guide is for students of the Scripture who are serious about their faith. It assumes that the reader is familiar with the basics of Christianity such as how to get saved, the value of prayer, and importance of reading the Bible. It is for Christians who read their Bible and wonder what certain passages mean, but do not have a clear idea of how to gain more understanding, or for Christians who wonder how to learn more about what the Bible teaches. It is not a commentary, nor does it contain &ldquo;all the answers&rdquo; to questions about the Bible. Rather, it is a guide to learning, so the student of the Bible can learn how to answer many of the questions that may come up as he or she reads the Bible.<br /> &nbsp;</p>', '2010-11-01', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/BibleStudyGuide_201011.pdf', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(2068, 1, 'God and Nature', '<p>If people take a good look at nature and still choose to deny the existence of God, they are without excuse (Rom. 1:20). Even in the world&rsquo;s currently fallen state, the incredible diversity of life and beauty that surround us are sure evidence for a Creator. The Bible contains many references to the created world, and many lessons in life can be learned by observing what God created for us.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:1, 14-25; 2:8-9, 15-16; Ps. 115:16; Rom. 1:20; Isa. 55:12; Ps. 8:3-8; 104:10-24; Matt. 6:26ff; Luke 12:6; Prov. 6:6; Ps. 1:3; Jer. 17:5-8; John 15:4-5; Hab. 3:19</p> <p>Teacher: Rob Woods</p>', '2021-12-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:35', 0, 0, null, 'n3JtgfzhFxo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/n3JtgfzhFxo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2069, 1, 'Ecclesiastes: Slowing Down and Enjoying Life', '<p>A consistent message throughout Ecclesiastes is learning to enjoy life and making God part of daily life. It is good to have goals and get work done, but it takes great skill to enjoy the process of reaching the goal and enjoy doing the work. Most of life is doing, and learning to enjoy the doing, and enjoying God as you do the work makes life much richer and enjoyable.</p> <p>Verses: Eccles. 1:1, 12, 13, 17; 2:1, 2, 4-10, 15, 17, 24; 3:12-13, 16-17, 22; 4:6; 5:8, 18-20; 6:9; 7:2-4; 8:12-15; 9:7-9; 10:20; 11:8-9; 12:1, 13-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:15', 0, 0, null, 'Jd8Q8pBuIyk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Jd8Q8pBuIyk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2070, 1, 'Life of Trust', '<p>This teaching focuses on the life of George Muller. Among his many ministry endeavors, he established orphanages for the primary purpose of providing a living example of prayer and trust to strengthen the faith of all believers. He fully provided for the orphans only by prayer and faith, without asking anyone for money, as he wrote: &ldquo;that it may be seen that God is faithful still and hears prayers still.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:7-12; John 14:11-14; 15:7; 16:22-24; Heb. 4:16; Psalm 66:18-20</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-01-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:51', 0, 0, null, 'jTtDG0bj6Dg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jTtDG0bj6Dg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2071, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 56 | The Greedy Chew Gravel (Prov. 20:17)', '<p>A person might think that they can enjoy some benefit or personal gain through dishonest means as long as they don&rsquo;t get caught. The problem is what might seem good in the moment will eventually sting in the end. Wrongdoing can taste &ldquo;sweet&rdquo; at first because of the immediate gratification it offers, but the bitter pain of its consequences will eventually find you, either now or in the future.</p> <p>Illustration: Jeffrey Skilling, CEO of Enron, who implemented fraudulent accounting practices to deceive shareholders and investors.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 20:17; 24:12</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-01-06', 'Castos', 0, '15:49', 9, 56, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/4f491dcd-998e-47e5-90e0-989af62d69aa-Ep-56-The-Greedy-Chew-Gravel-Prov.-20.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-56-the-greedy-chew-gravel-prov-2017', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2072, 1, '10 Reasons the Bible is True', '<p>This video covers 10 pieces of evidence that point to the truth of Scripture. Many godly men and women have read the Bible and proven it true for themselves and God promises that if you are humble and obey Him that He will reveal Himself to you.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 3:16; 2 Pet. 1:20-21; Gal. 1:11; John 17:17; Prov. 25:2; Gen. 12:2; Job 36:27-28; John 14:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-07', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:54', 0, 0, null, 'Ee_0tyHFR-I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ee_0tyHFR-I/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2073, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/09/2022) – It&rsquo;s All in Perspective', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-01-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:54', 0, 0, null, '6NA_p94InBM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6NA_p94InBM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2074, 1, 'Life of Trust - Part 2', '<p>This teaching continues the story of the life of George Muller, recapping the standards of his prayer life and moving on to look at two qualities of his character that gave wings to his prayer life and ministry work: financial integrity and passion for the unsaved.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 12:22-34; 2 Cor. 9:6-8; Phil. 4:6-7; Rom. 1:11-12; Luke 16:10-13</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-01-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:53', 0, 0, null, 'On1QSXVdcts', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/On1QSXVdcts/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2075, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Prayer', '<p>&ldquo;Get Your Warrior On&rdquo; is the title of our current Thursday fellowship series, focused on gearing up our spiritual strength. This teaching is about doing that through prayer. The teaching looks at scriptures in the Church Epistles in which we are told to pray persistently, and scriptures in the Epistles that indicate what we should be praying for.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 15:30-32; Eph. 6:18-20; 1 Tim. 2:1; 3 John 1:2</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-01-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:02', 0, 0, null, 'in_dPJ1sbNY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/in_dPJ1sbNY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(2076, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/16/2022) – Never Stumble or Fall', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '19:41', 0, 0, null, 'Cb9bFf0rPO0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Cb9bFf0rPO0/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2077, 7, 'REV Appendix 11: What is the Holy Spirit? (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 11: <strong>&ldquo;&iquest;Qu&eacute; es el Esp&iacute;ritu Santo?&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 11: <strong>&ldquo;What is the Holy Spirit&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-01-17', null, 0, null, 67, 11, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_11_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2078, 1, 'The Good Shepherd', '<p>Jesus displayed his warrior nature as a best friend and fierce protector of his people. His mental, emotional, and physical ordeals on the cross give us victory in life as we accept his finished work and allow him to work through us as our Good Shepherd. Everything in his life leading up to this moment, turned what appeared to be his greatest defeat into his greatest victory for all humanity.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 22:1-31; 23:1-6; 24:1-10</p> <p>Teacher: Len Cicio</p>', '2022-01-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:55', 0, 0, null, 'ufYibjJii18', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ufYibjJii18/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2079, 1, 'Sharing Your Faith Like Jesus', '<p>Part 1 of a three-part series on the woman at the well. In this extended conversation with the Samaritan woman, Jesus demonstrates the principles of evangelism and helps recover the mission of the church. We are to help people in our day hear the words of Jesus for themselves.</p> <p>Verses: John 4:1-15</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-01-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:36', 65, 1, null, 'FPGX7yRNDbQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FPGX7yRNDbQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(2080, 1, 'Do Your Ministry!', '<p>Every person is born with a &ldquo;ministry,&rdquo; a way of serving God that involves the natural skills and abilities that they were born with. Then, when a person is born again, God augments those abilities with power and guidance via the gift of holy spirit. There is great joy and peace in walking out one&rsquo;s own ministry, and rewards in the future as well.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 13:5-14; 1 Cor. 9:16-27; 12:18; 1 Tim. 6:20; Exod. 3:1-10; 4:14; Num. 27:15-20; Judges 3:9-10; 6:11-16.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:03', 0, 0, null, 'lEl13IzGYmA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lEl13IzGYmA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2081, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 57 | Deceive or Be Deceived (Prov. 14:8)', '<p>Being &ldquo;shrewd&rdquo; or &ldquo;clever&rdquo; may not be a characteristic that many seek to grow in. But that is what it means to be &ldquo;prudent.&rdquo; We can develop our ability to look ahead and understand where things lead. Contrarily, a person could be content just following their own ideas and desires, and in the end, be misled and deceived. The great deception begins with our own&mdash;to be deceived is to deceive.</p> <p>Illustration: Sergei Anatolyevitch Torop (&ldquo;Vissarion&rdquo;), Russian cult leader of &ldquo;Church of the Last Testament,&rdquo; who professes to be the reincarnation of Jesus Christ and has a large following living with him on a commune in Siberia.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 14:8</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-01-21', 'Castos', 0, '17:26', 9, 57, null, 'https://episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/b759443a-fdd1-4765-bf1a-d9e3b7096fa8-Ep-57-Deceive-or-Be-Deceived-Prov.-14.8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-57-deceive-or-be-deceived-prov-148', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2082, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/23/2022) – Forgiveness Equals Freedom', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-01-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:04', 0, 0, null, '0NJ2deA9v70', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0NJ2deA9v70/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2083, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Find Your Strength in God&rsquo;s Grace', '<p>The Bible never teaches us that our lives as Christians will be without challenges or discouragements. Paul faced many challenges in his ministry. We live in a fallen world, but we have a tremendous source of strength for our minds and hearts through God&rsquo;s grace. However, we need to reach out to find that strength in God&rsquo;s grace as we carry out the work we have been called to do.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:7; 2:1; Phil 4:13; 1 Sam 30:1-6; Isa 40:28-31; Eph 6:10-18</p> <p>Teacher: Brian Bassindale</p>', '2022-01-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:57', 0, 0, null, 'eqSEqfaukxw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eqSEqfaukxw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(2084, 1, 'One Way Not to Be Discouraged—Pick the Right Target!', '<p>A great key to being joyful rather than discouraged in life is to pick the right target. The Bible says things will get worse, and the love of many will grow cold, so it is self-defeating to expect that to change. Christians should be praying and putting their energy into &ldquo;targets&rdquo; that can and do make a difference, such as being positive and encouraging and bringing the Gospel to unsaved people.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. 102:25-26; Isa. 41:1-16; 51:1-3; 60:1-5; Dan. 7:21-22; Hos. 4:3; Matt. 24:3-10; 2 Tim. 3:1-5; Rev. 13:1-9, 14:13</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:06', 0, 0, null, 'bZRU77qpQIM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bZRU77qpQIM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(2085, 1, 'Lessons from the Sermon on the Mount', '<p>The Sermon on the Mount was Christ&rsquo;s first major teaching to the multitudes, and in it, Jesus bridged Old and New Testament concepts. It introduced a spiritual side to the battle between Good and Evil, as well as an evangelical side to the believer&rsquo;s walk that was not part of the Old Testament revelation, along with many other topics.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 5:13-48; Prov. 19:11; 2 Chron. 18:1-3, 28-34; 19:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:57', 0, 0, null, 'aJg9KXMImv4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aJg9KXMImv4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2086, 1, 'God Expects You to Do the Ministry He Gave You', '<p>Each person is born with a unique set of talents and abilities. When a person is born again God energizes those abilities so that the individual can best serve God. We should not treat our God-given ministry lightly. God chose it for us, empowers us to do it, and expects us to do it with energy, godliness, and grace.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:1, 10; 4:13-14; 1 Sam. 13:13-14; Jer. 1:4-7; 1 Cor. 9:16-17; 12:12-18; 1 Tim. 6:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-01-28', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:22', 0, 0, null, 'uCrNggysmz8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uCrNggysmz8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2087, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/30/2022) – Hearts Can Change – Part 2', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-01-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:37', 0, 0, null, 'vzmhwdGS-qE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vzmhwdGS-qE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2088, 7, 'REV Appendix 2: Life in the Age to Come (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 2: <strong>&ldquo;La vida en la era venidera&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 2: <strong>&ldquo;Life in the Age to Come&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-01-30', null, 0, null, 67, 2, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_2_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(2089, 1, 'Get Your Warrior on – Overcoming the Fear of Death', '<p>Christians need to have such confidence in their being raised from the dead that they overcome their fear of death. Death is temporary for the Christian believer, and it helps to have strong mental images of the resurrection of ourselves and our loved ones to help us be bold and faithful until death.</p> <p>Verses: Job 19:25-27; Isa. 26:19-21; Ezek. 37:12-14; Dan. 12:2-3; Hos. 13:14; Matt. 16:13-18; 1 Cor. 15:35-38, 42-44, 49-55</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p>', '2022-01-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:14', 0, 0, null, 'xryrvkCIRM8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/xryrvkCIRM8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2090, 1, 'Meet the Board of Directors of Spirit & Truth', '<p>This fellowship was dedicated to introducing the Board of Directors of Spirit &amp; Truth, who are:</p> <p>Jeff Tyler, Chairman<br /> John Schoenheit, Research &amp; Teaching<br /> Shawnee Vickery, Education, Secretary<br /> Ellen Fowler, Governance<br /> Bob Mirabito, Treasurer<br /> Bob Evans, IT</p> <p>Also introduced was Spirit &amp; Truth&rsquo;s new Director, Gary Burnham, who oversees all ministry business and operations, and manages the staff.</p>', '2022-01-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:50', 0, 0, null, '8QkRUbwJrcc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8QkRUbwJrcc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2093, 3, 'Ep 57 - Deceive or Be Deceived (Prov. 14:8)', '<p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Being &ldquo;shrewd&rdquo; or &ldquo;clever&rdquo; may not be a characteristic that many seek to grow in. But that is what it means to be &ldquo;prudent.&rdquo; We can develop our ability to look ahead and understand where things lead. Contrarily, a person could be content just following their own ideas and desires, and in the end, be misled and deceived. The great deception begins with our own—to be deceived is to deceive.</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Sergei Anatolyevitch Torop (&ldquo;Vissarion&rdquo;), Russian cult leader of &ldquo;Church of the Last Testament,&rdquo; who professes to be the reincarnation of Jesus Christ and has a large following living with him on a commune in Siberia.</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Verses:</span> <span class="normaltextrun">Prov. 14:8</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Teacher:</span> <span class="apple-converted-space">Jerry Wierwille</span></p>', '2022-01-21', 'Castos', 0, '17:26', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/b759443a-fdd1-4765-bf1a-d9e3b7096fa8-Ep-57-Deceive-or-Be-Deceived-Prov.-14.8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-57-deceive-or-be-deceived-prov-148', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2094, 3, 'Ep 56 - The Greedy Chew Gravel (Prov. 20:17)', '<p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;">A person might think that they can enjoy some benefit or personal gain through dishonest means as long as they don&rsquo;t get caught. The problem is what might seem good in the moment will eventually sting in the end. Wrongdoing can taste &ldquo;sweet&rdquo; at first because of the immediate gratification it offers, but the bitter pain of its consequences will eventually find you, either now or in the future.</p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Jeffrey Skilling, CEO of Enron, who implemented fraudulent accounting practices to deceive shareholders and investors.</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Verses:</span> <span class="normaltextrun">Prov. 20:17; 24:12</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Teacher:</span> <span class="apple-converted-space">Jerry Wierwille</span></p>', '2022-01-06', 'Castos', 0, '15:49', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/4f491dcd-998e-47e5-90e0-989af62d69aa-Ep-56-The-Greedy-Chew-Gravel-Prov.-20.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-56-the-greedy-chew-gravel-prov-2017', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2095, 3, 'Ep 55 - Keep My Commandments and Live (Prov. 4:1-4)', '<p>Children watch the behavior and life patterns of their parents and innately model their life after them. If the teaching of the parents is godly and their lives exhibit wisdom, their children will see that and learn how to live with wisdom in their life as well. But parents also must explicitly teach their children about wisdom in hopes that the children listen to and hold onto their words.</p> <p>Illustration: The example of the obedience of the Rechabites to the commandments of their ancestor Jonadab.</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;Prov. 4:1-4; 9:10; Jer. 35:1-17</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-12-15', 'Castos', 0, '19:19', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/693ebcf9-f69f-437f-89bf-63daae35a2b6-Ep-55-Keep-My-Commandments-and-Live-Prov.-4.1-4-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-55-keep-my-commandments-and-live-prov-41-4', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2096, 3, 'Ep 54 - Wealth Flies Away (Prov. 23:4-5)', '<p>We all need money to live. With the ever-increasing cost of living and the invention of so many new things to make life better, getting rich can sound like a good plan to solve that problem and acquire everything we want. But wealth is deceptive in that it is inherently unstable. One day we can have it, and the next day it vanishes.</p> <p>Illustration: Sean Russell&rsquo;s disastrous 2017 investment in bitcoin.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 23:4-5</p> <p>Teacher:&nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2021-12-15', 'Castos', 0, '17:12', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/9c845cbe-ab39-45d2-9b8e-7aea3467e157-Ep-54-Wealth-Flies-Away-Prov.-23.4-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-54-wealth-flies-away-prov-234-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2097, 3, 'Ep 53 - Out of Control (Prov. 25:28)', '<p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Emotions are a powerful part of who God created us to be. He did not intend for us to be controlled by our emotions&#8211; we must learn to master them. Without self-control, we become dangerous and unpredictable. We don&rsquo;t often make good decisions when emotionally embroiled, tending to hurt others by our words and actions because out of control emotions tend to result in foolish choices.</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Russell Crowe assaulting a hotel desk clerk with a telephone in a fit of rage</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Verses:</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span class="normaltextrun">Prov. 25:28</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Teacher:</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</span></p>', '2021-11-09', 'Castos', 0, '15:41', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/ee3f6876-9910-405e-9986-db2f96b89683-Ep-53-Out-of-Control-Prov.-25.28-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-53-out-of-control-prov-2528', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2098, 3, 'Ep 52 - Foolishness Destroys Wealth (Prov. 29.3)', '<p>Sometimes we only learn our lesson after the consequences of our actions catch up with us. Why is it so hard at times to see the pain down the road that our actions will cause? Foolishness causes a wide range of damage to our lives, and one of the areas it can drastically affect is our finances. Being enticed by sin and making poor choices, especially when it comes to sexual conduct, can have far reaching and harmful effects where we destroy our wealth in the process.</p> <p>Illustration: The Parable of the Lost Son (Lk 15:11-24)</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;Prov. 29:3; 5:8-13</p> <p>Teacher:&nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '14:15', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/4f1538ec-3fc2-4012-893a-e9515118018e-Ep-52-Foolishness-Destroys-Wealth-Prov.-29.3-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-52-foolishness-destroys-wealth-prov-293', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null);
