(2099, 3, 'Ep 51 - Get Back Up Again (Prov. 24:16)', '<p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">When life knocks us down, it may seem impossible to stand back up and keep going. But we don&rsquo;t have to face our struggles in life in our own power. The person who submits to Yahweh will never walk through life alone, and when adversity knocks them down, they can rise again; disaster doesn&rsquo;t have to end in our defeat; we can get back up again!</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Michael (&ldquo;Eddie the Eagle&rdquo;) Edwards and his struggle to qualify for ski jumping in the 1988 Winter Olympics in Calgary, Canada.</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Verses:</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span class="normaltextrun">Prov. 24:16</span></p> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Teacher:</span><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:17', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-51-Get-Back-Up-Again-Prov.-24.16-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-51-get-back-up-again-prov-2416', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2100, 3, 'Ep 50 – Friends No Matter What! (Prov. 18:24; 17:17)', '<p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Everyone needs friends. Life is better being in relationship with people, and friendships are an important part of that. But not all friendships are equal. Some friends are better friends than others, and some friends are merely social. However, true friends and will stand by your side. What distinguishes one friend from the next and why does it matter? Wisdom reveals that knowing who your true friends are is important.</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Frodo Baggins and Samwise Gamgee in the <em>The Lord of the Rings</em> on the slopes of Mount Doom in Mordor.</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Verses:</span> <span class="normaltextrun">Prov. 18:24; 17:17</span></p> <p class="paragraph" style="margin: 0in; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="normaltextrun">Teacher:</span> <span class="apple-converted-space">Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:39', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-50-Friends-No-Matter-What-Prov.-18.24-17.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-50-friends-no-matter-what-prov-1824-1717', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2101, 3, 'Ep 49 - Rest and Confidence in Yahweh (Prov. 19:23; 14:26-27)', '<div> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">People often strive for satisfaction in life through money, status, family, or other life accomplishments so they can live at ease and not worry about life any longer. But there is only one thing that can give us true life, rest, and contentment. If we seek to attain the fullness of life on our own, we will be left with only disappointment and heartache because we can&rsquo;t do it ourselves.</span></p> </div> <div> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: The Parable of the Businessman and the Fisherman</span></p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="auto"> Prov. 19:23; 14:26-27</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="auto">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p> </div>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:52', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-49-Rest-and-Confidence-in-Yahweh-Prov.-19.23-14.26-27-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-49-rest-and-confidence-in-yahweh-prov-1923-1426-27', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2102, 3, 'Ep 48 - The Wise Will Remain (Prov. 2:20-22)', '<div> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Living wisely or foolishly has long-reaching effects. We experience many consequences of our choices in our present life. But some consequences will not become known until in the future. Wisdom provides health, success, and well-being, but more importantly, long life now, and everlasting life in God&rsquo;s future kingdom. While the wicked might seem to prosper now, there is a day coming where they will be &ldquo;cut off&rdquo; and will be no more.</span></p> </div> <div> <p class="paragraph"><span class="normaltextrun">Illustration: Sheila Fields, who is a landlord in Buffalo, NY, suffered immense loss from the behavior of a deceptive and violent tenant.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none">  Prov. 2:20-22</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p class="paragraph">If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p> </div>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '17:14', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-48-The-Wise-Will-Remain-Prov.-2.20-22-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-48-the-wise-will-remain-prov-220-22-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2103, 3, 'Ep 47 - Wisdom''s Deliverance - Pt 2 (Prov. 2:16-19)', '<p>We all desire&nbsp;to be spoken&nbsp;well of&nbsp;but we must be careful that we&nbsp;don&rsquo;t&nbsp;get caught in the trap of flattery&nbsp;from others&nbsp;where we&nbsp;might then&nbsp;make poor choices that we normally wouldn&rsquo;t.&nbsp;Sexual&nbsp;sin&nbsp;(like adultery)&nbsp;rarely happens suddenly. The seductiveness of flattery is that it works little by little over time until a person decides to make a foolish&nbsp;decision&nbsp;that they will regret the rest of their life.</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none">  Prov. 2:16-19</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '19:56', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-47-Wisdom-s-Deliverance-Pt2-Prov.-2.16-19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-47-wisdom39s-deliverance-pt-2-prov-216-19-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2104, 3, 'Ep 46 – Wisdom&rsquo;s Deliverance – Pt 1 (Prov. 2:12-15)', '<p>The world is filled with&nbsp;people who are&nbsp;seeking ways&nbsp;to take advantage of others.&nbsp;Wisdom will protect those who listen to her from all manner of evil perversions, twisted paths, and devious ways of the wicked.&nbsp;Wisdom&nbsp;is&nbsp;a guardian who will&nbsp;provide safety&nbsp;from the&nbsp;unrighteous&nbsp;schemes of&nbsp;evil&nbsp;people who would gladly&nbsp;exploit others&nbsp;for their own benefit.</p> <p>Illustration:&nbsp;Charles C. Parker, a New York&nbsp;con artist who sold the Brooklyn Bridge to wealthy immigrants for over 40 years.</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none">  Prov. 2:12-15</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '14:49', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-46-Wisdom-s-Deliverance-Pt-1.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep46', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2105, 3, 'Ep 45 – Wisdom Will Guard You (Prov. 2:9-11)', '<p>Wisdom is a multi-faceted reality that can be described as consisting of understanding, insight, discretion, discernment, and many other important qualities. The practical value of wisdom is that it safeguards us against making bad choices and suffering the consequences of foolish mistakes. In this way, wisdom is our protector and guardian, watching over us and helping us, if we will let wisdom come into our heart and be willing to learn what it means to be wise.</p> <p>Illustration: Netflix CEO Reed Hastings&rsquo; vision for online movie streaming to avoid company failure and bankruptcy and to lead the entertainment industry into a new age.</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 2:9-11; 4:6</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:10', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-45-Wisdom-Will-Guard-You-Prov.-2.9-11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-45-wisdom-will-guard-you-prov-29-11', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2106, 3, 'Ep 44 – Wisdom Comes From Yahweh (Prov. 2:6-8)', '<p>The Book of Proverbs is filled with wisdom, but where does that wisdom come from? Many of the proverbs are the words of Solomon, but their origin lies with Yahweh who is the source of all wisdom. If we desire to have true wisdom in life, then we must seek Yahweh with all our heart and ask him to give us wisdom so that we can live in righteousness, integrity, and humility.</p> <p>Illustration: King Solomon receiving wisdom from God to administer justice among the people of Israel</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none">  Prov. 2:6-8; Jas 1:5-8</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '16:41', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-44-Wisdom-Comes-From-Yahweh-Prov.-2.6-8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep4-2', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2107, 3, 'Ep 43 – The Greatest Treasure (Prov. 2:1-5)', '<p>We desire many things in life, and we often expend much energy striving to attain them. But sometimes we don&rsquo;t put forth the effort that is needed, or we don&rsquo;t stick with it long enough to see the results. We must not have that sort of short-sighted attitude or half-hearted effort in our search for wisdom. Wisdom is like a crown jewel or the finest silver—wisdom is the greatest treasure. The question is, &ldquo;Do we have the desire and determination to find her?&rdquo;</p> <p>Illustration: Howard Carter and the discovery of the tomb of King Tutankhamun.</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 2:1-5</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '18:50', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-43-The-Greatest-Treasure-Prov.-2.1-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-43-the-greatest-treasure-prov-21-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2108, 3, 'Ep 41 – Finding Lady Wisdom – Pt 1 (Prov. 9:1-6)', '<p>Lady Wisdom is a personification of the attribute of wisdom. She invites people to come and dine with her as a metaphor for listening to her and learning from her. In her presence, her guests can experience many wonderful and satisfying things that show how gracious and beneficial she is to those who accept her invitation. If this is a picture of what life is like by having wisdom, then we should desire to find Lady Wisdom and enjoy the good life that only she can provide.</p> <p>Illustration: Preston Bailey, internationally acclaimed event designer, who has designed some of the most elaborate event decorations</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 9:1-6</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '18:14', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-41-Finding-Lady-Wisdom-Pt-1-Prov.-9.1-6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-41-finding-lady-wisdom-pt-1-prov-91-6-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2109, 3, 'Ep 40 – Lady Folly is a Fraud – Pt 2 (Prov. 9:17)', '<p>The voice of Lady Folly tempts people to see sweet and pleasant things in what is mischievous and rebellious. Her allure is in the excitement and thrill of getting away with what we want. But she doesn&rsquo;t tell you that her rewards are superficial and temporary, and they often come with drastic consequences. She calls out to people, inviting them to join her in secret pleasures, but little do they know that, in the end, it will always leave a bitter taste in their mouths.</p> <p>Illustration: Jordan Belfort, stockbroker busted for investment fraud, nicknamed &ldquo;The Wolf of Wall Street&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Prov. 9:17</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:22', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-40-Lady-Folly-is-a-Fraud-Pt-2-9.17-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-40-lady-folly-is-a-fraud-pt-2-prov-917', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2110, 3, 'Ep 39 – Lady Folly is a Fraud – Pt 1 (Prov. 9:13-18)', '<p>Lady Folly is a personification of the attribute of foolishness. She imitates wisdom as she tries to seduce people to listen to her, offering enticing and appealing things to lure naïve people into her trap. But that is like any replica, it is designed to look like the authentic. If we know what to look for and if we examine where the road leads, we can easily spot that Lady Folly is a complete fraud.</p> <p>Illustration: Wolfgang Beltracchi, the most famous art forger of all time.</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Prov. 9:13-18</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '17:08', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-39-Lady-Folly-is-a-Fraud-Pt-1-9.13-18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-39-lady-folly-is-a-fraud-pt-1-prov-913-18-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2111, 3, 'Ep 38 – Don&rsquo;t Mess With A Fool (Prov. 17:12)', '<p>We might think of foolishness as a relatively harmless characteristic of a person, but the Book of Proverbs thinks much differently about it. Foolishness is very harmful and destructive. We might not immediately perceive the wickedness in foolishness, but its consequences will come to bite everyone who is involved. Danger abounds when encounter a fool in their foolishness, so we must be wise and cautious to avoid it.</p> <p>Illustration: Bear attack in Montana, and three friends killed on a fishing trip in Florida.</p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Prov. 17:12</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> &nbsp;Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '13:38', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-38-Don-t-Mess-With-A-Fool-Prov.-17.12-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-38-dont-mess-with-a-fool-prov-1712', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2112, 3, 'Ep 42 – Finding Lady Wisdom – Pt 2 (Prov. 9:6)', '<p>In a succinct and powerful statement, Lady Wisdom exhorts listeners to &ldquo;Leave their naïve ways and live.&rdquo; We all have areas of foolishness in our lives, but sometimes changing our habits and ways of thinking is difficult and takes time and determination. But walking on the road of understanding will yield a life that cannot be achieved with foolishness. We must turn away from and leave it behind in order to experience the life that Yahweh intends for us to have.</p> <p>Illustration: The Parable of the Prodigal Son (Luke 15:11-24) – the younger son comes to his senses and leaves his foolish ways behind.</p> <p>Verses:&nbsp;<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 9:6</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none">  Jerry Wierwille</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;335559740&quot;:360}">&nbsp;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at&nbsp;<a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '20:08', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-42-Finding-Lady-Wisdom-Pt-2-Prov.-9.6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-42-finding-lady-wisdom-pt-2-prov-96', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2113, 3, 'Ep 37 – Don&rsquo;t Misplace Your Confidence (Prov. 25:19)', '<p>What sort of person would you call upon if you were in a pinch and needed help? Should what you know regarding a person&rsquo;s character affect your degree of confidence in them? Wisdom is about having discernment, and therefore, knowing someone&rsquo;s character and established pattern of behavior is important for knowing whether it is wise to put your confidence in them. If a person isn&rsquo;t a &ldquo;faithful&rdquo; individual, then your confidence is misplaced.</p> <p>Illustration: Rescue scene from the movie <em>Toy Story</em> featuring Woody and Buzz Lightyear.</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2021-01-08', 'Castos', 0, '16:26', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-37-Don-t-Misplace-Your-Confidence-25.19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-37-dont-misplace-your-confidence-prov-2519-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2114, 3, 'Ep 36 – Injustice is an Abomination (Prov. 17.15; 24.23-25)', '<p>Justice is something that Yahweh God cares deeply about. Judicial systems are set up to maintain justice, but they are flawed. Sometimes the innocent are convicted while the guilty go free. In Yahweh&rsquo;s eyes, any perversion of justice is an abomination. He is disgusted when wrong is called right, and right is called wrong. How can we strive to live with justice in our lives with the fear of Yahweh?</p> <p>Illustration: Horace Roberts, wrongfully convicted of a crime but exonerated 20 years later by DNA testing.</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-12-19', 'Castos', 0, '20:21', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-36-Injustice-is-an-Abomination-Prov.-17.15-24.23-25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-36-injustice-is-an-abomination-prov-1715-2423-25', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2115, 3, 'Ep 35 – Humility Leads to Glory (Prov. 18:12; 15:33)', '<p>What Proverbs teaches us is that our attitude and way of thinking can send us down two drastically different roads. One ends in disaster, and the other in glory. Pride does bring glory and honor; rather, humility is what does that. When we live with humility, willing to submit to Yahweh and live with the fear of Yahweh, then he will exalt us and give us glory and honor.</p> <p>Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Tortoise and the Hare,&rdquo; 800-meter runner Taoufik Makhloufi, and financial guru Dave Ramsey</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-12-03', 'Castos', 0, '19:22', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-35-Humility-Leads-to-Glory-Prov.-18.12-15.33-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-35-humility-leads-to-glory-prov-1812-1533-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2116, 3, 'Ep 34 – Pride Can Be Deadly (Prov. 16.18)', '<p>Pride makes us think more highly of ourselves than we should, and it produces in us a sense of overconfidence and self-importance. When we are full of pride, we can lose sight of thinking things through clearly and sensibly. Thus, as a consequence, pride leads us to experience disaster in our lives. We are warned against succumbing to the temptation of pride because the consequence can be very high, even deadly.</p> <p>Illustration: Kami Rita Sherpa, the world record holder for the number of times summitting Mount Everest</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-11-19', 'Castos', 0, '16:33', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-34-Pride-Can-Be-Deadly-Prov.-16.18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-34-pride-can-be-deadly-prov-1618', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2117, 3, 'Ep 33 – Discern Your Steps (Prov. 14:15)', '<p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-11-11', 'Castos', 0, '18:55', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-33-Discern-Your-Steps-Prov.-14.15-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-33-discern-your-steps-prov-1415', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2118, 3, 'Ep 32 – Take Care of Your Flocks (Prov. 27:23-24)', '<p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-10-28', 'Castos', 0, '17:19', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-32-Take-Care-of-Your-Flocks-27.23-24-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-32-take-care-of-your-flocks-prov-2723-24', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2119, 3, 'Ep 31 – Arrogance is for the Fool (Prov. 14:16)', '<p>The wise person fears Yahweh and does not over-estimate themselves but is sensible and even-tempered, unlike the fool that is cocky and self-reliant, recklessly endangering themselves because they fail to see the need for any concern or restraint. The fool laughs in the face of evil thinking that it can&rsquo;t touch them. The pretensions of their own superiority have blinded them so that they cannot recognize evil for what it is. They trust wholly in themselves, feeling secure in their knowledge and understanding and thinking they don&rsquo;t need to listen to anybody else.</p> <p>Illustration: Major General John Sedgwick and the battle at Spotsylvania Courthouse</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 14:16; 13:13; 3:7</p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-10-17', 'Castos', 0, '13:54', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-31-Arrogance-is-for-the-Fool-Prov.-14.16-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-31-arrogance-is-for-the-fool-prov-1416-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2120, 3, 'Ep 30 – Don&rsquo;t Boast About Yourself (Prov. 27:2)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Is it more meaningful if we brag about ourselves, or if someone else speaks highly of us? Faithfulness, kindness, generosity, good character, virtue, and other admirable qualities are often noticed by others. But even if people don&rsquo;t recognize us to the degree we would like or say enough good things about us, Yahweh sees everything and nothing escapes his notice.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Jack Hearp, Church of God pastor, and the endowment to Atlanta Bible College</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-10-02', 'Castos', 0, '15:39', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-30-Don-t-Boast-About-Yourself-Prov.-27.2-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-30-dont-boast-about-yourself-prov-272', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2121, 3, 'Ep 29 – The Future Can Be Fickle (Prov. 27:1)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The wise person doesn&rsquo;t boast about the future plans they have. Instead, they live day by day, trusting in Yahweh and the plans that he is bringing about in their life. While the future is unknown to us, Yahweh knows what is ahead and he will provide and take care of his people regardless of what happens tomorrow. Who else can we trust in concerning the uncertainty of the future except Yahweh our God?</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Company Direct Forex Signals and its attempts to rope in investors with promises about the future and a return on investment.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-09-22', 'Castos', 0, '19:29', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-29-The-Future-Can-Be-Fickle-Prov.-27.1-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-29-the-future-can-be-fickle-prov-271', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2122, 3, 'Ep 28 – Don&rsquo;t Seek to Get Rich Quick (Prov. 28:20)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Yahweh designed us to work, and there is an inherent pleasure in honest, hard work. Those who understand this will find life more fulfilling and satisfying. If we are faithful as trustworthy and reliable workers, Yahweh will bless the work of our hands and will provide what we need. Honoring Yahweh with our integrity and character and being content with the blessings he bestows upon us is of greater value than all the money in the world.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Charles Ponzi, professional con artist and inventor of the &ldquo;Ponzi Scheme&rdquo;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-09-08', 'Castos', 0, '14:23', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-28-Don-t-Seek-to-Get-Rich-Quick-Prov.-28.20-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-28-dont-seek-to-get-rich-quick-prov-2820', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2123, 3, 'Ep 27 – Hard Work Will Be Rewarded (Prov. 27:18)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The reward of hard work is not more work (as the popular saying goes), but rather being able to enjoy the fruit of one&rsquo;s labor. Hard work might not seem pleasant in the moment; it requires exertion, dedication, and much time. But all that effort is not lost or sacrificed for nothing. There is an exchange that happens when we work hard, and wisdom tells us that the perseverance and steadfast commitment to see things through to the end is worth it.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Tim Cook, the successor of Steve Job&rsquo;s at Apple in 2011</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://truthortradition.com/donate"></a><a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-08-26', 'Castos', 0, '14:34', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-27-Hard-Work-Will-Be-Rewarded-Prov.-27.18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-27-hard-work-will-be-rewarded-prov-2718', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2124, 3, 'Ep 26 – A Word at the Right Time (Prov. 15:23)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">As we seek to walk with wisdom and to give a fitting answer at the right time, we need to realize and be confident in the fact that our words can shape the future of others and can help them overcome an obstacle, be comforted when hurting, or give them courage to do what they know is right. Our words are powerful, and we must learn to speak what is right, in the right way, and most importantly&hellip;at the right time.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: The Civil Rights Era and the words of Martin Luther King Jr at defining moments</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-08-05', 'Castos', 0, '16:07', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-26-A-Word-at-the-Right-Time-Prov.-15.23-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-26-a-word-at-the-right-time-prov-1523', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2125, 3, 'Ep 25 – Fast Money Doesn&rsquo;t Last (Prov. 13:11)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">If we are willing to work hard and be mindful of the money we receive, God can help us steward our finances well and receive the greatest value and blessing from them. The key principle is really not how much you earn, but it&rsquo;s what you do with it. Those who stumble across money or cheat others for it typically don&rsquo;t give much thought to how they should care for it and use it, and thus they almost always end up wasting it away on meaningless things.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: 2017 fraudulent GoFundMe campaign by Katelyn McClure backfired on her</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-07-29', 'Castos', 0, '13:40', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-25-Fast-Money-Doesn-t-Last-Prov.-13.11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-25-fast-money-doesnt-last-prov-1311', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2126, 3, 'Ep 24 – Watch What You Say (Prov. 21:23)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">We should always weigh our words before we speak. As small and harmless as some might think words to be, caring little for whether they use them properly or not, they are more powerful and impacting than we often realize. We must become wise and handle our words with care, keeping watch over what we allow to pass through our lips. In this way, will watch over our life from trouble.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Mike Jeffries, CEO of Abercrombie &amp; Fitch, gives a disastrously offensive interview to Salon Magazine.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-07-18', 'Castos', 0, '15:29', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-24-Watch-What-You-Say.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-24-watch-what-you-say-prov-2123', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2127, 3, 'Ep 23 – Glad Hearts and Fat Bones (Prov. 15:30)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Hearing bad news can have a dramatic effect on us. But the same is true with good news. Whether it is a smile or it is simply a bit of uplifting feedback or story of success that we can share with someone else, sharing positivity and joy with others has a profound life-giving impact. A wise person spreads the health and nourishing effect of good news knowing its positive effect in their lives.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Lathan Johnson and his fire team being trapped in Shoshone National Forest during the Little Venus Fire of 2006</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-07-14', 'Castos', 0, '14:32', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-23-Glad-Hearts-and-Fat-Bones-15.30-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-23-glad-hearts-and-fat-bones-prov-1530-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2128, 3, 'Ep 22 – The Generous Will Be Blessed (Prov. 22:9)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">God blesses those who give freely and generously with the finances and belongings that they have and those who will use those blessings to serve his purposes&mdash;one of which is to provide and care for the poor and needy. And if we will gladly share a portion of our finances that God blesses us with, we will be blessed in return.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Yu Panglin, a very successful Hong Kong hotel and real-estate entrepreneur</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-07-09', 'Castos', 0, '12:32', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-22-The-Generous-Will-Be-Blessed-22.9-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-22-the-generous-will-be-blessed-prov-229', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2129, 3, 'Ep 21 – Listen Before Answering (Prov. 18:13)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">How many times has it worked out well to answer someone impulsively before taking a moment to think? We must develop the habit of not answering or making decisions rashly, rather to always listen first and listen fully so that we can respond appropriately and effectively. Many heartaches and mistakes in life can be avoided if we will but take a step back for a moment before opening our mouths.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable &ldquo;The Mice in Council&rdquo;</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-06-27', 'Castos', 0, '14:11', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-21-Listen-Before-Answering-Prov.-18.13-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-21-listen-before-answering-prov-1813-1', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2130, 3, 'Ep 20 – Listen to Reproof (Prov. 15:31-32)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">In general, reproof is meant to be a good thing that helps us become better. There will be plenty of criticism in life that does not qualify as being helpful, but part of growing in wisdom is to discern if the reproof is leading to life. It will require much humility to admit when we are wrong and to change our ways, but that is how we acquire good sense for making wise choices.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Famous American chef Thomas Keller receives harsh review from restaurant critic Peter Wells.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-06-20', 'Castos', 0, '19:41', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-20-Listen-to-Reproof-Prov.-15.31-32-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-20-listen-to-reproof-prov-1531-32', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2131, 3, 'Ep 19 – Listen to Counsel (Prov. 12:15)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Why should we listen to what others have to say? If we think we have all the right answers, then we shouldn&rsquo;t need to. But we must never perceive ourselves as having sufficient wisdom in all circumstances. That is why the wise person will ask other (especially God) for wisdom, because part of being wise is knowing that more wisdom is always helpful to make the best decision in any circumstance.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Jerry Wierwille and his prideful refusal to listen to his friend&rsquo;s advice when windsurfing</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-06-12', 'Castos', 0, '11:38', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-19-Listen-to-Counsel-Prov.-12.15-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-19-listen-to-counsel-prov-1215', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2132, 3, 'Ep 18 – Answer Or Don&rsquo;t Answer (Prov. 26:4-5)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Wisdom tells us to be discerning and careful with what we say and how we say it. It is a best practice to pause and collect our thoughts before responding because once foolish words proceed out of our mouth, we can&rsquo;t take them back, even if we want to. We will have shot ourselves in the foot, and people will call us the fool instead.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Apple CEO Steve Jobs properly responding to a difficult Q&amp;A session where someone calls his personal life and technical skill into question</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-06-09', 'Castos', 0, '20:21', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-18-Answer-Or-Don-t-Answer-Prov.-26.4-5-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-18-answer-or-dont-answer-prov-264-5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2133, 3, 'Ep 17 – Good News From Far Away (Prov. 25:25)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">When someone lives far away from friends and family, the desire to hear from them grows more intense as time goes on. To hear a good report, or good news, from them satisfies a fundamental craving in our soul&mdash;a craving for connection and relationship. There is wisdom in sending good news to our loved ones, for we know the beneficial effect it can have upon their soul.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Chong Bates and the search for her lost son.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-05-30', 'Castos', 0, '18:24', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-17-Good-News-From-Far-Away-Prov.-25.25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep17', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2134, 3, 'Ep 16 – It&rsquo;s Good to Leave an Inheritance (Prov. 13:22)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Setting aside a portion of the wealth we earn and planning to pass it on to our children is a demonstration of godly wisdom. But an inheritance should be more than just money, it is a way that we can share our knowledge of success and discipline to help our children live with wisdom and steward well the gift we give to them.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Scott Nash, owner of MOM&rsquo;s Organic Market, and his perspective on his children&rsquo;s inheritance.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-05-21', 'Castos', 0, '19:14', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-16-It-s-Good-to-Leave-an-Inheritance-Prov.-13.22-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-16-its-good-to-leave-an-inheritance-prov-1322', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2135, 3, 'Ep 15 – The Problem with Inheritance (Prov. 20:21)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">If managed correctly, an inheritance can be a great blessing during hard times, help purchase a home, or be the means by which one starts their own business. But that requires the recipient to be prepared to wisely manage it, which takes self-discipline and time to learn. An inheritance can be wasted is a person is not prepared to wisely handle it so that they can enjoy the blessings that it can provide.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: John Forsyth, a successful Canadian businessman, and the wasted inheritance of his children.</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-05-16', 'Castos', 0, '13:29', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-15-The-Problem-with-Inheritance-Prov.-20.21-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-15-the-problem-with-inheritance-prov-2021', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2136, 3, 'Ep 14 – Fools Can Appear Wise (Prov. 17:28)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Looks can be deceiving, and a fool can pass himself off as being wise. But a wise person is not deemed as wise because of their stature, demeanor, or appearance but according to their manner of life by living in obedience to Yahweh. This manner of life is demonstrated distinctly in what a wise person says and does, but a fool will not display this wisdom in their life.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Donkey and the Lion&rsquo;s Skin&rdquo;</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 17:28</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-05-07', 'Castos', 0, '08:57', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-14-Fools-Can-Appear-Wise-Prov.-17.28-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-14-fools-can-appear-wise-prov-1728', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2137, 3, 'Ep 13 – Holding Back Words (Prov. 17:27)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Wisdom tells us that we should be careful in how many words we use and when we use them, and that in response to being provoked, less words is often better and can keep us from saying things we would later regret. Moreover, keeping a cool spirit is essential so that we can think clearly about what we should say before we say it rather than responding out of heated emotions.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: The lives and conduct of Calvin Coolidge &amp; George Whitefield</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 17:27; Matt. 12:36-37</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-05-01', 'Castos', 0, '14:16', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-13-Holding-Back-Words-Prov.-17.27-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-13-holding-back-words-prov-1727', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2138, 3, 'Ep 12 – The Strength of Patience (Prov. 25:15)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Being aggressive and making demands from someone is likely not going to have a desirable outcome. Whether it is a person in a position of authority, someone at our place of employment, or even someone within our own family, if we make a request or plead our case with patience and gentleness of speech, we will more likely succeed in being persuasive and having them genuinely consider what we have to say.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: The famous Jewish Rabbi named Rabbi Akiva.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 25:15</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-04-27', 'Castos', 0, '14:08', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-12-The-Strength-of-Patience-Prov.-25.15-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep12', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2139, 3, 'Ep 11 – Empty Boasting  (Prov. 25:14)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">All broken promises produce disappointment on the part of the recipient who never received what they eagerly looked forward to. Sometimes the disappointment is small and other times great. With wisdom, we can learn to be discerning about the individual who is making the promise and what exactly is being promised, knowing that not everyone is honest and intends to keep their promises.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: The Seattle Art Museum and the Ebsworth Collection.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 25:14</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-04-17', 'Castos', 0, '12:39', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-11-Empty-Boasting-Prov.-25.14-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep11', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2140, 3, 'Ep 10 – A Gift Makes Room  (Prov. 18:16)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">It can be challenging to connect and break through a person&rsquo;s defenses. But when used properly with an honorable motive, a thoughtful gift that is given at the right time and in the right way can open doors, remove obstacles, and place you in a more favorable light in the eyes of others. A purposeful gift shows that you care and want to someone to know that they matter, and that can make all the difference in the world.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: The incredible success of Cutco salesman John Ruhlin</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 18:16</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-04-11', 'Castos', 0, '16:15', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-10-A-Gift-Makes-Room-Prov.-18.16-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep10', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2141, 3, 'Ep 9 – Strength on a Day of Trouble (Prov. 24:10)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Showing ourselves to not be lax when there is trouble can take as many different forms as the trouble that we encounter in life. When the occasion arises, what we do in response to the trouble will reveal whether or not our strength is small and limited. If we trust in God, knowing that he is the one that gives us true strength, we will not fail to show ourselves strong when it is needed the most.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Assistant Coach Ekkapol &ldquo;Ake&rdquo; Chantawong and the crisis of his team when they were trapped in a cave</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 24:10</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-04-03', 'Castos', 0, '13:30', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-9-Strength-on-a-Day-of-Trouble-Prov.-24.10-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep9', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2142, 3, 'Ep 8 – Understand Your Road (Prov. 14:8)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The wisdom of the prudent person is that he understands the road that he walks and knows the end to which it leads. We must not allow foolishness to deceive us or lead us to use deceit in our course of life. Wisdom will help us ensure that our road follows the course of life that leads to living with the fear of Yahweh and not to trouble</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Dutch Social psychologist Diederik Stapel&rsquo;s falsifying his research</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 14:8</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-03-28', 'Castos', 0, '11:23', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-8-Understand-Your-Road-Prov.-14.8-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep8', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2143, 3, 'Ep 7 – Fear Brings A Snare (Prov. 29:25)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">Living in fear of people and trusting in human power will always fail, but trusting in the strength of Yahweh our God, who is a sure rock beneath our feet, will never fail. No matter the circumstances, we are better off looking to God for help and trusting in him than putting our trust in other people or acting out of fear for what they might do to us.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: King Hezekiah and the Assyrian Siege</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 29:25; 2 Kgs 18:5-14; Isa 30:1-5</span></p> <p>Teacher: <span data-contrast="none">Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-03-21', 'Castos', 0, '15:15', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-7-Fear-Brings-a-Snare-Prov.-29.25-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep7', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2144, 3, 'Ep 6 – Training A Child (Prov. 22:6)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The habits a child forms when they are young usually follow them into adulthood. If parents will train their children in the way of the Lord, they will likely continue on that road when they grow up. But even if they go astray, the instruction and guidance they received as a youth can resurface and they may remember what they were taught and turn back to the Lord.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: John Newton and the effect of his childhood upon his faith as an adult.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 22:6</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-03-12', 'Castos', 0, '15:02', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-6-Training-a-Child-Prov.-22.6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep6', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2145, 3, 'Ep 5 – Rule Your Spirit (Prov. 16:32)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">It doesn&rsquo;t matter how well you can outdo others; you will not be able to live without wisdom. Wisdom teaches that true strength is about internal mastery and ruling well within your own self so that as you live in a world filled with temptations to get angry and lash out, you are able to demonstrate true strength that few people ever really achieve.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: American tennis player John McEnroe and the fatal flaw of his temper.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 16:32</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-03-04', 'Castos', 0, '13:23', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-5-Rule-Your-Spirit-Prov.-16.32-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/wow-ep5', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2146, 3, 'Ep 4 – Guard Your Mouth (Prov. 13:3; 18:21)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">If we&rsquo;re not careful to use wisdom to guard ourselves from falling into the traps and temptations of the flesh, we might utter foolish words that lead to our own destruction or those around us. We must learn the wisdom of silence, especially with regard to foolish words and unrestrained speech, and guard our mouth so that we can avoid the pain and harm that comes when we let our selfish desires drive the words we speak.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration: Aesop&rsquo;s Fable, &ldquo;The Tortoise and the Ducks.&rdquo;</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 13:3; 18:21; James 3:6</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-02-13', 'Castos', 0, '12:44', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-4-Guard-Your-Mouth-Prov.-13.3-18.21-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-4-guard-your-mouth-prov-133-1821', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2147, 3, 'Ep 3 – The Blessings of Wisdom (Prov. 3:13-18)', '<p><span data-contrast="auto">There are such incredible blessings for those who walk with Wisdom on her road. We must recognize her priceless value and choose to orient our lives to her. This idea of holding fast to wisdom signifies the complete commitment and sincere devotion to keep oneself on the road walking alongside Wisdom and never departing from her onto a different road, knowing that her path is better than any path we could ever devise on our own.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="auto">Illustration: Mastercard&rsquo;s &ldquo;Priceless&rdquo; ad campaign.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="auto"> Prov. 3:13-18; 8:32-34</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="auto"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-02-07', 'Castos', 0, '18:30', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-3-The-Blessings-of-Wisdom-Prov.-3.13-18-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-3-the-blessings-of-wisdom-prov-313-18', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2148, 3, 'Ep 2 – The Fear of Yahweh is the Foundation (Prov. 1:7; 9:10)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The difference between a fear of Yahweh that is driven by selfish interests and the true fear of Yahweh is that the one who seeks to grow wise understands they cannot live with true wisdom apart from a genuine relationship with Yahweh. When we live with the true fear of Yahweh, our hearts will turn toward him and we will appreciate and value the disciplining and training that he gives so that we may become wise and discerning.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration:</span> <span data-contrast="none">Sir Francis Bacon&rsquo;s humanistic (or human-oriented) philosophy and how it still permeates our entire society and world today.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 1:7, 9:10</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="auto"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p>', '2020-01-28', 'Castos', 0, '15:59', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-2-The-Fear-of-Yahweh-is-the-Foundation-Prov.-1.7-9.10-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-2-the-fear-of-yahweh-is-the-foundation-prov-17-910', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2149, 3, 'Ep 1 – The Purpose of Proverbs (Prov. 1:1-6)', '<p><span data-contrast="none">The purpose of Proverbs is for the reader to grow and become wise and understanding, and if they are already wise, then they will become even wiser. If the meaning of a proverb is not readily apparent, we mustn&rsquo;t give up. We must be willing to be patient with ourselves and the proverb and diligently meditate upon it, taking into consideration all the aspects of the text until we are able to draw out the depth and richness of its meaning.</span></p> <p><span data-contrast="none">Illustration:</span> <span data-contrast="auto">Charles M. Schwab, who was the president of Bethlehem Steel Corporation, sought out</span> <span data-contrast="auto">a simple and wise strategy for achieving higher productivity.</span></p> <p>Verses:<span data-contrast="none"> Prov. 1:1-6</span></p> <p>Teacher:<span data-contrast="none"> Jerry Wierwille</span></p> <p>If you were blessed by this episode, please consider supporting this podcast by donating at <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/</a></p>', '2020-01-24', 'Castos', 0, '16:56', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-1-The-Purpose-of-Proverbs-Prov.-1.1-6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-1-the-purpose-of-proverbs-prov-11-6', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2150, 3, 'Ep 0 – Introduction to the Book of Proverbs', '<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 25px;" aria-hidden="true"><span class="TextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph" data-ccp-parastyle-defn="{">We call Proverbs a book in the Old Testament, but it is</span> <span class="NormalTextRun AdvancedProofingIssueV2 SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">really not</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">a book at all. It is</span> <span class="NormalTextRun AdvancedProofingIssueV2 SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">actually a</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">collection of several writings that have been brought together into a single volume and</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">titled</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">as &ldquo;The Book of Proverbs.&rdquo;</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">While proverbs might seem bri</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">ef, they hold</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">deep meaning about how life is supposed to work and how to best live under the rulership of Yahweh God</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">. Therefore, i</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">f we desire to grasp the wealth of</span> <span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph">knowledge</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW6119302 BCX4" data-ccp-parastyle="paragraph"> and guidance that Proverbs has to offer, it will require of us an invest</span></span></div>', '2020-01-15', 'Castos', 0, '17:18', 0, 0, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/Ep-0-Introduction-to-the-Book-of-Proverbs.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-0-introduction-to-the-book-of-proverbs', '/i/wow_logo.png', 0, 0, null, 0, 0, null),
(2151, 1, '2 Timothy; Paul&rsquo;s Last Epistle', '<p>Paul&rsquo;s second letter to Timothy was the last thing he wrote that is recorded in the Bible. Paul wrote about his death in the last chapter, making bold statements about what he had done and what he would be given in the future. These are an example to us of the certainty and value of the rewards we will receive in the future.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Tim. 1:1-3, 6, 13-18; 2:1-6, 10-17; 3:1, 12-17; 4:6-9, 13, 18; Rom. 6:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-02-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:59', 0, 0, null, 'pZDuLp0ur0o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pZDuLp0ur0o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2153, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 58 | Caution: Emotions! (Prov. 29:11)', '<p>Yahweh God created us to experience deep emotions. But not all emotions are created equal. Some are more difficult to deal with than others. Anger and other agitated emotions can quickly lead us into different ways of thinking and acting. And when that happens, we may say and do things that we later regret. We need to be cautious about our emotions and control them, or they will control us.</p> <p>Illustrations: 1) Kanye West interruption during Taylor Swift&rsquo;s best female video award at the 2009 MTV Video Music Awards ceremony. 2) Tom Brady&rsquo;s careful response to the press after Tampa Bay Buccaneers suffered a demoralizing defeat by the Los Angeles Rams at the end of the 2022 NFL playoffs.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 29:11; 25:28</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-02-02', 'Castos', 0, '18:54', 9, 58, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/6ce58954-b61b-4ed3-853e-cea0f35a07f9-Ep-58-Caution-Emotions-Prov.-29.11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-58-caution-emotions-prov-2911', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 132, null),
(2154, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/06/2022) – Parables of the Lost', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-02-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:39', 0, 0, null, '4aFBP-lcvFo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4aFBP-lcvFo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2155, 1, 'Facing the Pressures of Life', '<p>Life is filled with pressures, many of which distract the Christian from doing the work of the Lord. This teaching gives examples of how earlier believers withstood the pressures of life to complete the job that Yahweh set before them, encouraging us to do the same.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 6:5-8; 1 Sam. 17:34-37; Ps. 27; Isa. 53:3-8; Heb. 11:7, 24-27, 32-34; 12:1-3; 1 Pet. 5:6-11</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2022-02-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:02', 0, 0, null, 'ZRCWi_xJrBs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZRCWi_xJrBs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(2156, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Stand Fast', '<p>Those who trust God and stand for truth have always been harassed by those who do not. The early church had four key practices which enabled it to flourish, even in the face of persecution. By following these practices, Christians today can be prepared to continue bearing good fruit in an increasingly dark world.</p> <p>Verses: Heb. 11:3-4, 13, 32-39; Acts 2:6-8, 12-13, 42; Matt. 13:3-9, 18-23; Ps. 1:1-3;</p> <p>Teacher: Regina Dundon</p>', '2022-02-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:04', 0, 0, null, '6zkRy_90KCc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6zkRy_90KCc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2157, 1, '2 Kings 17 - The Fall of Israel', '<p>2 Kings 17 covers what God wanted written about the destruction of the Northern Kingdom of Israel. Romans 15:4 says that the Old Testament was written to instruct us, and this chapter has lots of lessons for us to learn. It is a powerful warning and teaching that ignoring and rejecting the commandments of God leads to disaster, so it&rsquo;s wise to learn the commandments of God and obey them.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 17:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-02-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:28', 0, 0, null, 'U8wOIs91iSs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U8wOIs91iSs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2158, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/13/2022) – Evaluating Truth', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-02-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:08', 0, 0, null, 'Uh0jIFC7q2k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Uh0jIFC7q2k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2159, 7, 'REV Appendix 3: Christ&rsquo;s Future Kingdom On Earth (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 3: <strong>&ldquo;El Reino Futuro de Cristo en la Tierra&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 3: <strong>&ldquo;Christ&rsquo;s Future Kingdom On Earth&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-02-14', null, 0, null, 67, 3, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_3_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2160, 1, 'Psalms of Trust', '<p>This teaching looks phrase-by-phrase at Psalm 23, from the perspective of both the Shepherd and the sheep. Written by David, who was a skilled and compassionate shepherd, the Psalm paints a picture of our God&rsquo;s caring for us in the same manner that a courageous and diligent shepherd would care for his sheep. The Psalm is a series of promises we can trust that God will fulfill toward his flock.</p> <p>Verses: Pss. 13:3-6; 23:1-6; 28:7-8; 32:7; 73:25-28; Prov. 3:25-26</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-02-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:21', 0, 0, null, '6OIzGkriqMY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6OIzGkriqMY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2161, 1, 'The Armor of God in Ephesians 6', '<p>In Ephesians 6:10-18, the Christian is told to be empowered by the Lord by putting on the whole armor of God, which enables the wearer to resist the opposition that originates from the evil spiritual forces directed by the Devil. The believer has to put on this armor/knowledge &ndash; it doesn&rsquo;t occur automatically.</p> <p>Verses: Eph. 6:10-18; 2 Tim. 4:7-8; 2 Cor. 11:25; Rom. 5:17; 2 Tim. 3:16; Phil. 4:6-7;</p> <p>Teacher: Pat Sweeney</p>', '2022-02-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:38', 0, 0, null, 'DvlbkSRJcMc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/DvlbkSRJcMc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 9, 0, null),
(2162, 1, 'What Did Jesus Say about Trust?', '<p>This teaching explores the meaning of several verses in which Jesus referred to having trust (faith) like a mustard seed or being able to move mountains. It addresses statements such as &lsquo;whatever you ask in prayer, believe&hellip;and you will receive.&rsquo;</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 17:19, 20; 21:18-20; Luke 17:3-6; Mark 11:12-14, 20-25</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-02-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:07', 0, 0, null, 'b3eDftHpSiQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/b3eDftHpSiQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2163, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 59 | If You Play With Fire, You Will Get Burned (Prov. 6:27-29, 32-35)', '<p>Few things are more deceptive than the promise of pleasure that lust brings. While there might be pleasure for a brief time, inevitably it ends with pain and suffering. Adultery is one of those deceptions. Few people who commit adultery truly understand the far-reaching implications and consequences of their actions. Only after they have sinned do they begin to realize just how destructive adultery can be to their life&mdash;and no one is immune to its effects.</p> <p>Illustrations: Jonathan Amerault, who had an affair with the wife of Armando Barron. In a fit of rage on account of Amerault committing adultery with his wife, Barron brutally assaulted and killed Amerault in vengeance.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 6:27-29, 32-35; Lev. 20:10; Deut. 22:22</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-02-16', 'Castos', 0, '15:59', 9, 59, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/ade323b6-5395-4b03-be75-9abdaf45c461-Ep-59-If-You-Play-With-Fire-You-Will-Get-Burned-Prov.-6.27-29-32-35-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-59-if-you-play-with-fire-you-will-get-burned-prov-627-29-32-35', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(2164, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Giving Under Pressure', '<p>We are in a war. But warriors do not always attack, sometimes they defend. They compassionately defend the helpless, the injured, the lost. Jesus and Paul taught us to give to others generously, to help the helpless, save the injured, find the lost.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 16:1-3; 2 Cor. 8:1-15; 9:1-15; Prov. 11:10-11, 24-25</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2022-02-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:38', 0, 0, null, 'AWfglyf37Ow', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AWfglyf37Ow/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2165, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (02/20/2022) – God&rsquo;s Seal', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-02-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:53', 0, 0, null, '7RPkTMJii88', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/7RPkTMJii88/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2166, 1, 'Paul&rsquo;s End of Life Pronouncement', '<p>Paul wrote 2 Timothy from a Roman dungeon under a death sentence. Sure enough, and soon after this writing he was executed by the Emperor Nero. Paul was an example of godliness during his life, and an example of confidence, even in his death. No wonder he could write to Christians, &ldquo;Be imitators of me, just as I also am of Christ&rdquo; (1 Cor. 11:1).</p> <p>Verses: 2 Timothy 4:6-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-02-25', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '16:50', 0, 0, null, 'V7i_FabwpuE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V7i_FabwpuE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2167, 1, 'Sharing Your Faith Like Jesus', '<p>Part 2 of a three-part series on the woman at the well. In this section the conversation takes an unexpected turn. We learn here from Jesus that people need to see their sin not simply as an offense to God but as the brokenness keeping them from what they most want and need in life.</p> <p>Verses: John 4:16-26</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-02-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:27', 65, 2, null, 'CEd4-NwSnKA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CEd4-NwSnKA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2168, 1, 'What Did Jesus Say about Trust and Prayer During the Last Supper?', '<p>This teaching opens with an overview of the themes of the Last Supper that occur in all 4 Gospels and those that are unique to the Gospel of John. Two of those unique themes in John pertain to the usage of the word &ldquo;in,&rdquo; or &ldquo;in union with&rdquo; and &ldquo;ask.&rdquo; Those words become the focus of the teaching.</p> <p>Verses: John 14:1, 10-15; 15:4-5, 7-8, 11; 16:1, 16, 19-20, 22</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-02-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:41', 0, 0, null, 'x2iho3VRrF4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/x2iho3VRrF4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2169, 1, 'Unanticipated Help', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-02-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '18:48', 0, 0, null, 'KWxh80AaO0s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KWxh80AaO0s/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2170, 1, 'Get Your Warrior on – The Christian as a Soldier', '<p>When a person becomes a Christian, he or she is enlisted in God&rsquo;s army in a great spiritual war that has raged for centuries &ndash; whether they recognize it or not. We see this truth highlighted in 2 Timothy 2 which depicts the Christian as a soldier. Various facets of what God is intending to convey by using this imagery are examined in view of three aspects of the spiritual battle Christians are engaged in: (1) the war against the flesh; (2) the war against spiritual forces of evil; and (3) the war against conformance to the schemes and patterns of this world.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 10:3-5; Eph. 6:10-13; 1 Pet. 2:11; Rom. 12:2; 2 Tim. 2:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-02-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:53', 0, 0, null, 'aXETTE5hWpU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/aXETTE5hWpU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2171, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 60 | Dangerous Women (Prov. 5:1-6)', '<p>You can never be too cautious so as to recognize when someone might be trying to seduce you. People can say all kinds of nice things about you and tell you how great they think you are, but if they are trying to manipulate you, watch out! The power of seduction is a deadly venom that if foolishly swallowed will lead to one&rsquo;s peril and demise. We must guard ourselves against &ldquo;dangerous&rdquo; people who would seduce us and have us join them on their journey toward destruction.</p> <p>Illustration: Joseph and the seductive attempts of Potiphar&rsquo;s wife in Egypt (Gen. 39:1-20)</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 5:1-6; 4:20; 2:2</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-03-02', 'Castos', 0, '19:28', 9, 60, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/dba24b74-4644-4257-934c-dd2d2e0729b2-Ep-60-Dangerous-Women-Prov.-5.1-6-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-60-dangerous-women-prov-51-6', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2172, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/06/2022) – How Did Jesus Not Sin Even Once?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:35', 0, 0, null, 'TYH3rBoNlUA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TYH3rBoNlUA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2173, 1, 'Sharing Your Faith Like Jesus', '<p>Part 3 of a three-part series on the woman at the well. Jesus&rsquo;s dialogue with his disciples can teach us something about his priorities and the purpose of the church in which we are called to serve. Then Jesus and the Samaritan woman model for us what it looks like to share our faith with the people in our lives.</p> <p>Verses: John 4:27-42</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-03-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:29', 65, 3, null, '0RF3v2twF1g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0RF3v2twF1g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2174, 1, 'Isaiah 40: Living for God', '<p>Isaiah 40 gives applicable guidance in walking with God and being a blessing to people: speaking comforting words, helping people adjust their life to make time for God, and reminding them of the Hope. God reminds us to speak up in support of Him, and to not be afraid of pressure or persecution. Those who wait for Yahweh and walk with Him will renew their strength, will be able to run with Him but not grow weary, and will one day be rewarded.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 40:1-3, 5-11, 28-31; Rev. 1:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:16', 0, 0, null, 'u5sUg8BqNMA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/u5sUg8BqNMA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2175, 1, 'Evidence for the Pre-Tribulation Rapture', '<p>Most evangelical Christians believe in the Rapture of the Church, but there are several theories as to when that Rapture will be. Is there a pre-Tribulation Rapture, a Mid-Tribulation Rapture, or a Post-Tribulation Rapture? This teaching discusses all three and gives some of the evidence for a Pre-Tribulation Rapture position.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 25:1-2; 1 Thess. 1:10; 4:13-18; 5:9; Rom. 5:9; 1 Cor. 15:51-52; Ezek. 37:11-15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:06', 0, 0, null, 'PtU9QeZ6KLs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PtU9QeZ6KLs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2176, 7, 'REV Appendix 4: The Dead are Dead (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 4: <strong>&ldquo;​Los muertos est&aacute;n muertos&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 4: <strong>&ldquo;The Dead are Dead&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-03-15', null, 0, null, 67, 4, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_4_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2177, 1, 'Parable of the Unrighteous Judge', '<p>The ongoing current events in the world can cause many to feel uneasy, worried, and discouraged. However, we have been given a way to deal with all of the noise outside. In Luke 18:1-8 Jesus teaches his disciples about the necessity to pray. He tells them a parable that is as timely today as it was when he first spoke it.</p> <p>Verses: Jer. 23:1-5; Luke 18:1-8; 2 Pet. 3:8-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2022-02-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:10', 0, 0, null, 'lgQ4OecLK3U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/lgQ4OecLK3U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2179, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/13/2022) – What Most Christians Don&rsquo;t Know', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-03-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:50', 0, 0, null, 'taAVjCxzdFY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/taAVjCxzdFY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2180, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Comfort', '<p>In the spiritual battle, the Lord never promised that we would not be hit by one or more of the enemy&rsquo;s flaming arrows. During those times we need to be comforted by the Body, enabling us to rejoin the battle. We should be cognizant that all members of the Body, including children, have a role to play. The children too, need to be protected from the fiery arrows of the wicked one.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:1-6; 1Cor. 12:4-7; 2 Cor. 1:3-7; Eph. 6:10-12, 16</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2022-03-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:58', 0, 0, null, 'wFyKi06WkCQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wFyKi06WkCQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2181, 1, 'Christian Unity and the Manifestations of the Holy Spirit', '<p>The manifestations of the gift of holy spirit have been very confusing in the Christian Church. A key to understanding them as listed in 1 Corinthians is their importance as a unifying factor in that Church. They were not living as if they needed, loved, or supported one another. When it comes to a Church Meeting, God works to produce unity by energizing different manifestations in different people to bring edification and build unity.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:10-12, 26-31; 3:5-6; 4:3, 7; 6:7; 8:9; 10:23-24; 11:17-22; 12:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:46', 0, 0, null, '00JYxlYS2bk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/00JYxlYS2bk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2182, 1, 'Guts: Christians Must be Risk-takers', '<p>People were offended at Jesus Christ, the &ldquo;rock of offense,&rdquo; and Christians today must take the risk of offending people in order to stand for him. There is no godly way to avoid persecution if we live godly lives. No one likes confrontation and persecution, but being persecuted for Christ is infinitely better than hiding one&rsquo;s faith and then receiving no rewards on the Day of Judgment.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 10:24-28; 16:24-28; 1 Cor. 3:10-17; Exod. 15:1-3; 1 Sam. 17:45; 2 Tim. 2:3-6; 2 Cor. 10:1-11; 1 John 5:19; Gal. 6:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:43', 0, 0, null, 'GOtjndYX7xY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GOtjndYX7xY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2183, 1, 'Living for God', '<p>Isaiah 40 contains much applicable guidance in how to walk with God and be a blessing to people: speak comforting words; help people make time for God in their life; remind people of the Hope. God reminds us to speak up in support of Him, and not fear persecution. Those who walk with Yahweh will renew their strength and will be able to run with Him but not grow weary.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 40:1-3, 5-11, 28-31; Rev. 1:7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:06', 0, 0, null, 'zBinvh72OBQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zBinvh72OBQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2184, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On - Live in the Moment: Bloom Where You&rsquo;re Planted', '<p>Throughout the days and seasons of our lives we can grow closer with Yahweh and our Lord Jesus Christ as we determine to keep our eyes upon them. With daily intentional preparation and forethought, we will reap the benefit of living with our spiritual eyes wide open: A moment by moment, day by day walk that aligns with our Father&rsquo;s heart! Let&rsquo;s look to the Bible for direction and encouragement.</p> <p>Verses: John 15:1-5; Eccl. 12:13; Mark 12:28-31; 14:32-36, 39; Eph. 2:10; Num. 11:10-17; Luke 5:15-16; 9:23; Acts 16:20-26; Ps. 5:1-3</p> <p>Teacher: Gayle Ackerman</p> <p>Songs:<br /> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jhnJXDGfPiE" target="_blank">Keep Me In The Moment - Jeremy Camp</a><br /> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zTZtKoAwf0U" target="_blank">Turn Your Eyes Upon Jesus - The Living Stones Quartet</a></p>', '2022-03-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:18', 0, 0, null, 'j7KaCWE2oy8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/j7KaCWE2oy8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(2185, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/20/2022) – Iron Sharpens Iron', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:44', 0, 0, null, '1d__PFeYo3w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1d__PFeYo3w/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 2, null),
(2186, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Seeking Understanding', '<p>This two-part teaching examines Jesus Christ in the gospel of Matthew through a series of incidents with his disciples and followers. Jesus desired for his followers to receive understanding from God and utilize that knowledge for their benefit. This teaching also explores &ldquo;Why the Parables?&rdquo; in the context of the things God desires us to understand: how one receives the word according to the condition of one&rsquo;s heart, the hope and rewards, and understanding that comes to us not by flesh and blood but by the spirit.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 13:1-13; 14:13; 15:10-15, 17-26; 16:1-20; Eph. 1:18-22, Pro. 2:1, 5</p> <p>Teacher: David Hutchings</p>', '2022-03-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:04', 0, 0, null, 'GNA4uRvRIPs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GNA4uRvRIPs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2187, 1, 'Understanding Philippians 3', '<p>The major lesson in Philippians 3 is about getting to know Christ and maturing to be like him. Paul wanted to, not just &ldquo;know about&rdquo; Christ, but to know Christ himself. Furthermore, he wanted to live in such a way that he experienced the power of Christ&rsquo;s resurrection, the sharing of his sufferings, and that Paul would conform himself to the way Christ lived and died. Paul knew he had not yet reached that goal, but he pressed forward to reach it and encouraged others to follow his example.</p> <p>Verses: Philippians 3:1-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:29', 0, 0, null, 'zsmPbvKILCM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zsmPbvKILCM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2188, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 61 | Stay Away Or Lose It All (Prov. 5:7-11)', '<p>Some choices in life will result in loss no matter which way you look at it. Certain things may appear to offer adventure, excitement, and discovery, but hidden beneath the surface is a world of destruction and suffering. Marriage brings many trials and challenges to life, and some might think that the grass is greener elsewhere. But that is a dangerous thought. The temptation to be unfaithful carries with it an untold amount of hurt and pain. And in the end, it will become a regret that you can never take back.</p> <p>Illustration: Francisco Huizar, who was sued by Keith King for $8.8 million for committing adultery with his wife and had to file for bankruptcy.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 5:7-11; 6:34-35</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-03-23', 'Castos', 0, '19:31', 9, 61, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/925f6978-2ea4-4818-89f1-7cd7f54654d8-Ep-61-Stay-Away-Or-Lose-It-All-Prov.-5.7-11-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-61-stay-away-or-lose-it-all-prov-57-11', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2191, 1, 'Our Spiritual Battle', '<p>When we accepted Jesus Christ as our Lord and Savior, we became contenders in a great spiritual war that has raged for centuries. God and His armies are pitted against the devil and his wicked spirits in a battle for the souls of men. For Christians, there are three key aspects of this battle: (1) our fight against the devil and his spiritual forces of evil; (2) our fight against temptation and sin; and (3) our fight against conformance to the pattern of this world.</p> <p>Testimony of Deliverance: Diego Hinojosa (Digital Diego)</p> <p>Link to Diego&rsquo;s song &ldquo;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L4lBfwWfvDY&amp;ab_channel=DigitalDiego" target="_blank">Take Me There</a>.&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: John 8:43-44; Acts 13:5-12; 26:18; Rom. 7:14-25; 12:2; 1 Cor. 10:13; 2 Cor. 6:14-18; 10:3-5; Eph. 6:10-13; Col. 1:13; 2 Tim. 2:3-4; Heb. 2:14-18; 1 Pet. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-03-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:30', 0, 0, null, 'VLCHY9SMKM4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VLCHY9SMKM4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2192, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (03/27/2022) – From Dust to Glorious', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-03-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:33', 0, 0, null, 'K52-MTTPS1w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/K52-MTTPS1w/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2193, 1, 'Fear Not', '<p>This teaching expounds four instances from the Old Testament of the phrase &ldquo;Fear Not&rdquo; as translated in the KJV. We are encouraged to &ldquo;fear not&rdquo; in the face of many circumstances, including change, unknown future, loss, and recovery from defeat. At the Last Supper, Jesus encouraged the apostles to have courage. Romans attests that nothing can separate us from God&rsquo;s love that is in Christ our Lord.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 46:1-5; Deut. 31:1-8; Josh. 7:6-12; 8:1-2; John 16:33; Rom. 8:31-39</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-03-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:56', 0, 0, null, 'PXJ9-q3Byr0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PXJ9-q3Byr0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2194, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On – Strengthening Our Sanctuary and Walls', '<p>Our God&rsquo;s incredible display of patience through the many journeys of His people is the longest running story in human existence. One such story is recorded in Ezra and Nehemiah. Through exploring this record, you will come closer to God as you take the opportunity to consider the condition of your inner quiet place and personal set of boundaries.</p> <p>Verses: Ezra 6:16, 22; Neh. 1:4-11</p> <p>Teacher: James Cutler</p>', '2022-03-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:25', 0, 0, null, '9anoxO89XEA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9anoxO89XEA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2195, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/03/2022) – Your Dynamic Ministry', '<p><a href="https://daringandboldlove.wixsite.com/blog/post/this-dynamic-ministry" target="_blank">Here is the link</a> to the blog sharing about Cash&rsquo;s ministry.</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-04-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:45', 0, 0, null, 'hIWFMam3eEY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hIWFMam3eEY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2196, 1, 'The Powerful Prophecy of Isaiah 8', '<p>Isaiah 8 is an important chapter that often gets overshadowed by Isaiah 7, though the two have many similarities and are closely tied together. Isaiah 8 also contains some wonderful lessons about why evil befell Judah and what godly people were to do in troubled times, and ends with evil people seeing doom and darkness&mdash;which sets the stage for Isaiah 9 in which the Messiah comes on the scene as a light in the darkness.</p> <p>Verses: Isaiah 8:1-22; 9:1-2, 6</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-03-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:32', 0, 0, null, 'ADidHHqT1YY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ADidHHqT1YY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2197, 1, 'Trouble in Corinth - The Need for Unity', '<p>Many people believe 1 Corinthians 12:8-10 refers to only receiving one manifestation of the spirit, when in fact the section is about how God brings about unity in the Body of Christ and a recognition of how we all need each other. When it comes to the manifestations of holy spirit, God works to bring about unity by energizing different manifestations in different people. To accomplish what God wants for us, we all need each other.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8; 2:38; 1 Cor. 1:10, 11; 3:1; 4:3; 6:1; 10:24; 11:17-18; 1 Cor. 12:4-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-08', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '19:03', 0, 0, null, 'dRIcJx7zj4M', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/dRIcJx7zj4M/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2198, 1, 'The Lord&rsquo;s Supper', '<p>The Lord&rsquo;s Supper was part of Jesus&rsquo; last supper with the apostles. This teaching examines the relationship between Passover and the Lord&rsquo;s supper; the origin of the Passover; how Passover was to be practiced; and the truth that Jesus was the Passover Lamb. It explains the importance of what Jesus meant in his statements about his body being given and his blood shed, and how we are to be celebrating that today.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 12:1-20; Luke 22:1, 7-8, 14-20; 1 Cor. 11:17-26</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-04-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:09', 0, 0, null, '96g8kBcd1Ng', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/96g8kBcd1Ng/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2199, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On…Our Main Message', '<p>Making sure the message of salvation is clear when we are witnessing is of utmost importance. Asking people to be &ldquo;saved&rdquo; is a common in Christianity today, but is that enough? People can agree with the teachings of Jesus and still not be saved. Everyone needs to know why they need a savior and what they are being saved from.</p> <p>Verses: Mat 16:13-20</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p> <p>Both of the clips Ellen played in her teaching are from <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cU4fkswSJhk" target="_blank">this video</a>.</p>', '2022-04-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '24:12', 0, 0, null, 'Vsv4WV8jqzo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vsv4WV8jqzo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 3, null),
(2200, 1, 'RSVP to Everlasting Life', '<p>This teaching looks at a parable in Matthew 22 regarding the wedding banquet of the King. There is a day coming when this banquet will be celebrated with the chosen of all time. Who are the called and chosen of the parable?</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:1-14; Acts 8:26-31, 17:22-31; 1 Tim. 2:1-4; Rev. 19:6-9</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p> <p>Link to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DXXxLwxfo0U" target="_blank">song at end</a>.</p>', '2022-04-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:52', 0, 0, null, 'IWIY2FScsnw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IWIY2FScsnw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 0, null),
(2201, 1, 'Get Your Warrior On - Voice Activated Power', '<p>The words that we speak to ourselves and to others, whether words of blessing or cursing, are powerful and they have an effect on us and on the people who hear us. This teaching covers several examples in the Bible where Jesus spoke and brought miracles to pass. The best thing we can speak to ourselves and others is God&rsquo;s Word, and it helps if we make the effort to memorize it. We need to be watchful of the words we are speaking.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 2:1-7; 18:21; Matt. 18:19; Mark 3:1-5; 4:37-39; 5:25-28; 7:32-35; 11:23; Luke 4:3-14, 33-36, 38-39; John 5:25, 28-29; 6:63; 11:41-44; Eph. 4:24-32; 1 Thess. 4:16; 1 Pet. 2:21-24</p> <p>Teacher: Rhett Major</p>', '2022-03-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:52', 0, 0, null, 'pAnBtTD-RCE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pAnBtTD-RCE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2202, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/10/2022) – Adam, Jesus and Me', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-04-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:05', 0, 0, null, 'ESpmrp0GVaU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ESpmrp0GVaU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2203, 1, 'Giving Grace', '<p>In any act of giving, we function as an extension of God&rsquo;s grace to the recipient. The evidence of this is all around us in our everyday lives. There is a connection between grace and giving, and this teaching is an endeavor to make that connection.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 14:17-24; Prov. 3:34; Luke 6:37-38; 21:1-4; John 3:16; 2 Cor. 8:1-6; 9:6-15; 1 Pet. 5:5</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2022-04-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:21', 0, 0, null, 'FiGh09ggIac', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/FiGh09ggIac/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2204, 1, 'Jesus Before Pilate', '<p>The titanic struggle in John 18 was over whether Pilate himself would believe in Jesus and thus gain everlasting life. The interaction was intimate and intense, and we see Jesus fighting for the soul of a person whose everlasting life hung in the balance, but in spite of Jesus&rsquo; efforts to reach Pilate, he chose his political position over his knowledge of what he had seen and heard.</p> <p>Verses: John 18:28-19:16; Luke 23:2, 5, 13-16; Matt. 27:15-26; Mark 15:25; Isaiah 53:11-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:02', 0, 0, null, 'PuGo7GHvnds', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PuGo7GHvnds/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2205, 1, 'The Last Supper to Jesus&rsquo; Resurrection', '<p>With the possible exception of the conception and birth of Jesus Christ, the events of the last week of Christ&rsquo;s life are the most important events in history, because it was the death of Jesus Christ that paid the price for human sin and made it available for people to be saved and have everlasting life. Sadly, the Church has not paid attention to Scripture, and has chosen to follow tradition rather than believe what the Bible actually says. For example, Jesus said he would be &ldquo;three days AND three nights in the heart of the earth&rdquo; (Matt. 12:40). Yet the Church historic has insisted that there are three days and nights between Friday at sunset until so early Sunday morning that it was still dark (John 20:1). Traditions like this have sometimes resulted in thinking individuals avoiding the Bible and Christianity, but the Bible does fit perfectly if we simply read what is written and fit it to a calendar. Jesus was arrested Monday night, crucified Wednesday morning, buried at sunset Wednesday night, rose Saturday night at sunset, and when people came to see the tomb early Sunday morning he had already risen and was gone.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 26:20; John 13:30; 16:32-33; 17:1; 18:1, 12-13, 24; Luke 22:66-67, 70-71; 23:1-2, 4-7, 11, 13, 20; Mark 15:9-10, 15, 11; John 19:9-11, 13-14; Mark 15:25, 33, 37, 42, 46-47; 16:1; Luke 23:55-56; John 20:1, 16-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:00:11', 0, 0, null, 'j4SAZBESfd0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/j4SAZBESfd0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2206, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/17/2022) – Feast of First Fruits', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-04-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:55', 0, 0, null, 'm1YgXwTl6mk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m1YgXwTl6mk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2207, 1, 'Paul in Philippi (Acts 16)', '<p>Paul traveled to Philippi on his second missionary journey with his companions, Silas, Luke, and Timothy. The visit was a tremendous success, but not without personal cost to both Paul and Silas. This teaching explores the consequences and triumphs of this journey, and how its outcomes led to growing the Body of Christ and to the eventual writing of the Epistle to the Philippians.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 15:35-41; 16:1-40</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:45', 0, 0, null, 'M17a18IxjW0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/M17a18IxjW0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2208, 1, 'God at War: God vs. the Devil', '<p>The world is a hard and dangerous place, and people rightly think that it should not be. This teaching explains that God is not the reason the world is hard and dangerous, and that He is doing the best He can to help, though there are limits in what He can do because He gave angels and people free will. The wise Christian believes God when He says that He is love, and looks for biblical reasons that the world is such an ungodly and dangerous place.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 4:8; 5:19; Deut. 30:19; James 4:4; Matt. 12:30; Luke 10:23-24; 11:14-18; John 1:18; Exod. 15:3; Exod. 9:12; 2 Cor. 4:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-22', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:24', 0, 0, null, 'ImGMs_dgkn8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ImGMs_dgkn8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2209, 1, 'Rooted Series #1: The Call to Follow', '<p>This teaching explores the great challenge facing the church today, which is discipleship. Jesus did not call us to make converts, but disciples&mdash;people who seek to embody the life of Jesus as their own. We can&rsquo;t do that unless we are truly disciples ourselves.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 3:13-19; Mark 4:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-04-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:38', 0, 0, null, '0_cwImav2uI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0_cwImav2uI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2210, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (04/24/2022) – Labor for the Reward that Lasts', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-04-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:27', 0, 0, null, 'tFOKNms73ks', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tFOKNms73ks/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2211, 1, 'Walking in Wisdom', '<p>Living wisely has many facets, and the Bible has a lot to say about it. As we might expect, the world has a vested interest in people not living wisely (Satan wants people sick, broke, and sad), so there is not much talk about it; yet the Bible says wisdom is the principal thing, and to be wise one must know where to find wisdom and be disciplined and self-controlled enough to actually do wise things and not give in to fleshly desires.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 1:7; 4:7; 5:22-23; 9:10; 10:4; 11:4; 21:5; 23:4-5; Ps. 111:10; Job 28:12-28; Ecc. 2:26; 1 Tim. 6:6-11; 2 Tim. 2:22; John 6:27; Matt. 6:33; 2 Cor. 5:9; Luke 12:16-21; 14:28; Gal. 5:22-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-04-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:29', 0, 0, null, 'CdK329gnEP4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CdK329gnEP4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2213, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 63 | Go Astray in Her Love (Prov. 5:15-19)', '<p>Yahweh intended man and woman to be united in marriage and to enjoy sexual intimacy within that union. Our world condones people seeking to satisfy their sexual cravings in various ways that do not honor Yahweh&rsquo;s design for the flourishing of humankind. Husbands and wives are to see their spouse as the sole avenue for sexual pleasure to protect and honor their marriage covenant. Faithful husbands and wives will be blessed as they enjoy many years of satisfying each other and being captivated by their love.</p> <p>Illustration: Bill Yaconis, a dear friend and wonderful example of a faithful husband for over five decades.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 5:15-19; Song 4:1-5; 5:1</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-04-27', 'Castos', 0, '22:20', 9, 63, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/78f7f46d-5690-4933-a53a-2ac112b2f601-Ep-63-Go-Astray-in-Her-Love-Prov.-5.15-19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-63-go-astray-in-her-love-prov-515-19', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2214, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 62 | It''s Too Late Now (Prov. 5:12-14)', '<p>Some say that experience is our greatest teacher. And its true that when we make mistakes, and they come with far-reaching effects, we realize very quickly how wrong the choice was that we made. But we can&rsquo;t go back and change what we did. All of the choices in our lives are one-way streets, and once we figure out that we have been heading down a particular road, it&rsquo;s too late to undo what has been done. We have to live with the consequences.</p> <p>Illustration: Two stories of men who share how their adultery cost them everything they hold dear.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 5:12-14; 12:15</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-04-07', 'Castos', 0, '22:20', 9, 62, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/59017914-bc66-4ac8-9bc7-143f0b822248-Ep-63-Go-Astray-in-Her-Love-Prov.-5.15-19-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-62-it39s-too-late-now-prov-512-14', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 1, null),
(2215, 7, 'REV Appendix 5: Annihilation in the Lake of Fire (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 5: <strong>&ldquo;Aniquilaci&oacute;n en el Lago de Fuego&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 5: <strong>&ldquo;Annihilation in the Lake of Fire&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-05-02', null, 0, null, 67, 5, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_5_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2216, 1, 'ROOTED Series #2: Spending Time with God', '<p>Christians are called to have an intimate relationship with our Heavenly Father and Lord Jesus Christ. Consider who you like to spend time with the most; isn&rsquo;t it the people that love you the most and who you love the most? God and Jesus have made it abundantly clear that they love us and want us to spend time with them. This teaching examines three ways in which we can spend time with God and Jesus, including: (1) conversing with them (prayer); (2) studying the holy Scriptures; and (3) meditating on the holy Scriptures.</p> <p>Verses: Rev. 3:20; Song 1:2, 9-16; Luke 5:15-16; Matt. 14:23; Luke 6:12; Luke 3:21-22; John 12:27-28; Ps. 62:8; John 16:13-15; Luke 4:16-21; Luke 24:13-27; Ps. 119:15-16; Josh. 1:8; Col. 3:16; John 15:7</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-05-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:48', 0, 0, null, 'CWKA3kVyk_c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CWKA3kVyk_c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2217, 1, 'The Unforgivable Sin', '<p>Christians are challenged to be joyful and hopeful in an evil world, and it helps to do that if we understand why it is such an evil place. Understanding that the Devil has &ldquo;children&rdquo; who are incredibly wicked and who will never repent or do what is right helps explain why the world is so evil, and sadly, why so many evil people seem to be at the top of society in almost every arena of life&mdash;religion, politics, music, and more. The Devil&rsquo;s children are at war with God and godliness, and they are one reason that Christians need to be diligent in prayer, to bring God&rsquo;s power and blessings into the world.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 13:13; Judges 19:22-28; 1 Kings 21:10-13; 1 Peter 4:12; Isaiah 11:1-4; 1 Sam. 2:12-17; 2 Sam. 20:1; John 8:44; Gen. 4:9; Matt. 12:31-32; 15:1-14; Acts 19:18-20; Acts 8:13; Luke 4:5-7;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:17', 0, 0, null, 'qwx0Vr45QBM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/qwx0Vr45QBM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2218, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/01/2022) – God Knows Your Name', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-05-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '16:25', 0, 0, null, '0-CSAS54-7o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0-CSAS54-7o/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2219, 1, 'Jesus Before Pilate: Who is in control?', '<p>The Four Gospels&mdash;especially the Gospel of John&mdash;describe some of Jesus&rsquo; interaction with Pontus Pilate. From a fleshly point of view, it seems Pilate had the power in the situation, since he represented the Roman government. But this teaching explains how it was really Jesus who was in control of the situation. He was the prisoner and the one being tortured, but he was fighting for the soul of Pilate, whose everlasting life hung in the balance.</p> <p>Verses: John 18:28-19:16; Luke 23:2, 5, 13-16; Matt. 27:17-19, 22-23; Mark 15:25; Romans 8:14-15.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-06', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:55', 0, 0, null, 'egcyaifFt70', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/egcyaifFt70/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2220, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/08/2022) – There is Another Option', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:47', 0, 0, null, 'eTc5xro90Nw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eTc5xro90Nw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2221, 1, 'ROOTED Series #3: Spending Time with Others', '<p>As children of God and ambassadors for the Lord Jesus Christ, we should seek their guidance on ways to profitably spend time with others. The Lord God gave us His son, Jesus, who laid down his life for us. What should we give in return? This teaching helps guide us in setting priorities in our lives for spending time with others.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 22:36-40; Gal. 6:1-2, 9-10; Eph. 5:1-10, 6:9; Col. 3:1-24; 1 Tim 2:1-4; 2 Tim. 2:1-2, 22-26; 1 Pet. 3:15; 1 John 3:16-18</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CkYQY8uHnsg" target="_blank">Opening song</a>.<br /> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lwXZZLwXvh4" target="_blank">Closing song</a>.</p>', '2022-05-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:25', 0, 0, null, 'L8amplKoEGo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/L8amplKoEGo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2222, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/15/2022) – Lessons from Jeremiah', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:19', 0, 0, null, 'gF9et_hlXJw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gF9et_hlXJw/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2223, 1, 'ROOTED Series #4: Knowing and using Your Spiritual Gifts for Service', '<p>As the third of four &ldquo;habits of discipleship&rdquo; presented in this series, this teaching explores the idea of using your spiritual gifts for service. The teaching presents three illustrations of &ldquo;using your gifts for service,&rdquo; along with three qualities of our spiritual gifts. It closes with a challenge: if you are uncertain of what your spiritual gifts are, try doing something for someone else. Your gifts will surface as you go.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 7:1-10; John 14:8-14; 1 Cor. 3:5; 4:6-7; 2 Cor. 3:3-8; Rom. 12:1-8</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KtKBkpbOLPE" target="_blank">Opening song</a>.<br /> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kdmgpMfnjdU" target="_blank">Closing song</a>.</p>', '2022-05-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:18', 0, 0, null, 'MjJ_aEwCwNc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MjJ_aEwCwNc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2224, 1, 'Study Your Bible', '<p>Millions of books have been written on earth, but only one of them is &ldquo;The Word of God,&rdquo; words that came from the Creator of the Universe. This teaching explores some different keys to becoming a faithful and knowledgeable Bible reader, how to plan and stick to regular Scripture reading, as well as covering some wonderful tools to help people learn the Bible.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-20', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:29', 0, 0, null, '1sJnT3N3wZI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1sJnT3N3wZI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2225, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 64 | Throwing It All Away (Prov. 5:20-23)', '<p>Some things in life it seems like we can escape from, or at least avoid the direct consequences of them. But when it comes to sin, the consequences always seem to find a way to come around and bite us in the end. That is because sin is destructive no matter which way you look at it. It will destroy you and likely also injure those around you. And if it is the sin of adultery, you can be sure the damage will be severe. It will bring great harm upon you, everyone involved, and countless others.</p> <p>Illustration: Carl Lentz, prominent and highly successful Hillsong Church pastor in New York City, and the adultery that destroyed his life and his career in Christian ministry.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 5:20-23; 14:12; 16:25; Rom 14:10-12; 1 Tim 5:24</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-05-18', 'Castos', 0, '19:10', 9, 64, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/96b851e9-42b0-49c5-ad34-25e6b47ace35-Ep-64-Throwing-It-All-Away-Prov.-5.20-23-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-64-throwing-it-all-away-prov-520-23', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2226, 1, 'The Man Born Blind in John 9', '<p>There are many wonderful lessons in the record of the man born blind in John 9. From the Pharisees&rsquo; point of view, Jesus&rsquo; healing of the blind man on the Sabbath was a sin. This teaching demonstrates how Jesus dealt with ungodly religious and cultural norms that kept people in bondage. We can learn from Jesus Christ&rsquo;s example and bring deliverance to people in our world today.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:58-59; 9:1-41</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:12', 0, 0, null, 'S3n5gHRHzUQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S3n5gHRHzUQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2227, 7, 'Appendix 6. Usages of &ldquo;Spirit&rdquo; (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 6: <strong>&ldquo;Usos de &lsquo;Esp&iacute;ritu&rsquo;&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 6: <strong>&ldquo;Usages of &lsquo;Spirit&rsquo;&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-05-22', null, 0, null, 67, 6, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_6_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2228, 1, 'Rooted Series #5: Sharing Your Faith', '<p>As the fourth of four &ldquo;habits of discipleship&rdquo; presented in this series, this teaching explores how and why we share our faith. It&rsquo;s all about Jesus: remember that he is with us always; listen for his guidance; ask him, &ldquo;Speak to me, Jesus.&rdquo; He is faithful to guide and coach us and he will not stop talking to us as we remember and listen.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 28:16-20; Acts 9:3-5, 10-19</p> <p>Teacher: Bob Mirabito</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4RjmtL7nmw0" target="_blank">Opening song</a>.</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=APATH3ea-D0" target="_blank">Closing song</a>.</p>', '2022-05-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:50', 0, 0, null, 'L0MwwGkxr2c', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/L0MwwGkxr2c/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2229, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/22/2022) – God is Our Refuge and the Source of Our Praise', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-05-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '11:53', 0, 0, null, 'ObuxV1B9VpE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ObuxV1B9VpE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2230, 1, 'Romans 9: God&rsquo;s Mercy to Israel and Gentiles', '<p>Romans 9 gives an explanation of how God had blessed the Jews, but they rejected Him anyway, and it also shows that God used that opportunity to bless the Gentiles. In order to understand this section, the reader must have a very good grasp of the Old Testament and the places that Paul drew his quotations from, because they were picked very carefully. A huge key to Romans 9 is in verse 14: &ldquo;There is no unrighteousness with God, is there? Absolutely not!&rdquo; God is righteous and merciful, and that is shown in Romans 9.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 21:8-13; 25:19-23; Exod. 9:13-18; 33:18-19; Jer. 18:1-4; Mal. 1:1-3; Rom. 9:1-33; 10:1-4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:17', 0, 0, null, 'ZmEu9T5wkIs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZmEu9T5wkIs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2231, 1, 'Every Life is Precious; and The Dead are Still Speaking Now', '<p>Sam Schoenheit opens up with a sharing on how every life is precious to God, using as an example the record of the death of Saul. Despite years of being hunted by him, David still mourned Saul&rsquo;s death.</p> <p>John follows with a Memorial Day teaching from Hebrews 11. Hebrews 11 is more than just &ldquo;we remember those who are dead,&rdquo; it points out that those who have died are still speaking (Heb. 11:4) in that their words and actions inspire us, guide us, and correct us. Hebrews 11 also tells us what &ldquo;trust&rdquo; (&ldquo;faith&rdquo;) is, and reminds us that we cannot please God if we do not trust God, and the people mentioned in Hebrews 11 had great trust in God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 31:1-6; 2 Sam. 1:23, 25-26; 2 Tim. 2:2-3; Heb. 11:1-16</p> <p>Teachers: Sam Schoenheit and John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '47:01', 0, 0, null, 'HCgM1-X_-P8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HCgM1-X_-P8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2232, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (05/29/2022) – Forgiveness – What Does it Look Like?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-05-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:36', 0, 0, null, 'X0rVV8zEq7Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/X0rVV8zEq7Q/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2233, 1, 'Overview: 1 Corinthians 12-14', '<p>Jesus taught that when the gift of holy spirit came, believers would have &ldquo;power.&rdquo; A lot of the explanation about that power is in 1 Corinthians 12-14, which explain the manifestations of the gift of holy spirit, especially speaking in tongues, interpretation of tongues, and prophecy, and 1 Corinthians 13 speaks of doing what we do in love.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. Acts 1:8; 1 Cor. 12, 13; 14:1-32.</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-05-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:43', 0, 0, null, 'Vkp1JzX2yKI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Vkp1JzX2yKI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2234, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/05/2022) – Don''t Be Discouraged - Have Hope', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-06-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:29', 0, 0, null, 'Oo0DLQP4s4w', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Oo0DLQP4s4w/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2235, 1, 'Pentecost Teaching: Things Christians Enjoy Today', '<p>On the Day of Pentecost (Acts 2), Jesus poured out the gift of holy spirit upon the people who believed in him. This was the start of the Administration of the Grace of God (Eph. 3:2) which has many blessings for the believers that believers who lived before Pentecost did not have. These include (but are not limited to) every believer having holy spirit; a new kind of spiritual power; operating the manifestation of holy spirit; clarity and ease in getting salvation; having permanent salvation; and being in union with Christ and being part of the Body of Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 1:8; 2:33, 38; John 15:26; 16:7; Gal. 2:20; Rom. 6:1-11; 10:9; 1 Cor. 2:6-10; 12:7, 13; 2 Cor. 3:5-10; Eph. 1:13-14; 2:6; 3:6; 4:30; Col. 2:11, 12; 2 Tim. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:49', 0, 0, null, 'nzGapQy1kGw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nzGapQy1kGw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2236, 1, 'Choose to Move Forward with God', '<p>Every Christian has a sin nature, so almost every Christian has a sense that they are not whole, they are not &ldquo;okay.&rdquo; Paul clearly expressed this in Romans 7:15-20 when he said that he did not do what he wanted to do, but he did things he did not want to do. The feelings of inadequacy, confusion, guilt, and shame can be so strong in some Christians that they give up on trying to do anything for God. But a huge key in being effective as a Christian is to realize that you can do wonderful things for God even if you are a broken person.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 3:11; 4:13; Deut. 30:19-20; Isa. 6:1-5; Jer. 1:4-6; Ezek. 1:28; 2:1-7; 3:15-17; Romans 7:7-25; 1 Cor. 15:9; Gal. 5:16-17; Eph. 3:8; 1 Tim. 1:15</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:48', 0, 0, null, 'k_vJmd4FlOE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k_vJmd4FlOE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2237, 7, 'Appendix 7. Usages of &ldquo;Soul&rdquo; (Spanish)', '<p>El Ap&eacute;ndice 7: <strong>&ldquo;Usos de &lsquo;Alma&rsquo;&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 7: <strong>&ldquo;Usages of &lsquo;Soul&rsquo;&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-06-11', null, 0, null, 67, 7, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_7_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2238, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/12/2022) – Another Jesus One Word at a Time', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:49', 0, 0, null, '4AnL6YdawLA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4AnL6YdawLA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2239, 1, 'The Image of God (imago dei)', '<p>Three aspects of the image of God &ndash; relational, substantive, and functional &ndash; show that the image of God is multi-faceted. While the fall of man did not keep people from being in the image of God, it &ldquo;blurred&rdquo; the image in that man&rsquo;s sin nature prevented him from fully living out what it means to be in God&rsquo;s image. Jesus Christ was the image of God par excellence because he lived it out perfectly in a way that other humans could not because of their sin nature. The redemptive work of Christ makes it possible for us to live out the image of God by imitating Christ&rsquo;s example: living in union with Him, showing forth His virtues, and proclaiming the Gospel.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26-27; 1 Cor. 11:7; James 3:9; Gen. 9:6; 5:1-3; Luke 3:38; Ps. 8:5; Gen. 2:25-3:10; Luke 4:5-8; Rom. 5:12-17; 2 Cor. 4:4; John 14:9; 1:18</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-06-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:39', 0, 0, 'disobedience', 't-M74dBmcl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/t-M74dBmcl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2240, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 65 | Raging Against Yahweh (Prov. 19:3)', '<p>When things go wrong in life, we tend to look for someone to blame. Rarely do we naturally like to assume responsibility for our poor choices. Instead of realizing that we made a stupid decision, and it is our fault for why things are the way they are, our sinful human inclination is to transfer the fault to something or someone else. In doing this, we forfeit the opportunity to recognize and learn from our mistakes.</p> <p>Illustration: Bruce Nolan suffering the consequences of his foolish choices and then blaming God for the misfortune in his life, from the movie Bruce Almighty.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 19:3</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-06-15', 'Castos', 0, '18:14', 9, 65, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/0cf57387-f51b-4a19-957c-5ca0ce5b1dae-Ep-65-Raging-Against-Yahweh-Prov.-19.3-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-65-raging-against-yahweh-prov-193', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2241, 1, 'Choose to Move Forward with God', '<p>Every Christian has a sin nature, so almost every Christian has a sense that they are not whole, they are not &ldquo;okay.&rdquo; Paul clearly expressed this in Romans 7:15-20 when he said that he did not do what he wanted to do, but he did things he did not want to do. The feelings of inadequacy, confusion, guilt, and shame can be so strong in some Christians that they give up on trying to do anything for God. But a huge key in being effective as a Christian is to realize that you can do wonderful things for God even if you are a broken person.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:19; Romans 7:5-25; Gal. 5:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-17', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '21:46', 0, 0, null, 'U4WWV1Bj6Cw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/U4WWV1Bj6Cw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2242, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/19/2022) – Stress - Less', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-06-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:28', 0, 0, null, 'CKB1DVWfiAk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CKB1DVWfiAk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2243, 1, 'Overview of the Book of Revelation', '<p>Revelation is considered to be one of the most difficult books in the Bible to understand. That is certainly true of parts of it, but the general scheme and flow of Revelation is not nearly as difficult to understand as most people think. Much of it becomes easier with a correct understanding of the scope of the Bible in general. That way, we can see how Revelation offers some specifics on what Christ described as a time of great tribulation and gives an overview flow of events until the New Jerusalem comes to earth and saved people live in it forever with God and Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Revelation 1:1-4, 9-11, 19; 4:1-5; 5:1; 6:8, 16-17; 8:6-12; 9:18; 10:1-4; 13:5; 14:13; 16:16; 19:11-15. Zech. 5:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:13', 0, 0, null, 'rOtq5hwH_R8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rOtq5hwH_R8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(2244, 1, 'Spend Time with your Heavenly Father', '<p>God&rsquo;s story is written in the sky (creation) and in the scriptures. The most important resource we have for spiritual growth in our lives is the Bible. It is the power of God to change your life. We not only need to read it, but allow it to challenge us into a deeper relationship with our heavenly Father.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 19</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-06-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:34', 0, 0, null, 'nI0zx4zF5U4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nI0zx4zF5U4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2245, 1, 'Philippians 4:13 and Romans 8:28', '<p>The Bible can be a difficult book to read for a number of reasons, but when verses are translated in a way that clashes with the context, it becomes even more difficult to understand. That is the case with Philippians 4:13 and Romans 8:28, which both have been important verses in the Christian Church, and translating them the way that best fits the context and culture makes a huge difference in how they can be understood and applied.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 8:18-31; Philippians 4:10-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:39', 0, 0, null, '8oU6N9p3KRk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8oU6N9p3KRk/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2246, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (06/26/2022) – Incorruptible Seed', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-06-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '20:32', 0, 0, null, 'nihJBaIVeGE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nihJBaIVeGE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2247, 1, 'Spending Time with God in Meditation', '<p>This teaching explores the biblical definition of meditation in contrast with the worldview of meditation. It highlights the priority God places on meditating on His law, His Word, and His wonderful acts. It also considers the questions &ldquo;Did Jesus specifically instruct his disciples to meditate?&rdquo; and &ldquo;Are Christians specifically instructed to meditate?&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 19:14; 104:12-16; 119:15, 23, 27, 78, 148; Joshua 1:1-9; Matthew 11:27-30; 1 Timothy 4:12-16</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-06-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:56', 0, 0, null, '-jPjpY1LPT8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-jPjpY1LPT8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2248, 1, 'Jesus on Hypocrisy', '<p>In Luke 11 and 12, Jesus confronted the Pharisees and Lawyers on their hypocrisy, and then taught about it to his disciples and the crowd of people listening. Hypocrisy is foolish because God sees the heart and knows the truth. People may be hypocritical to hide their greed or desire for control over others, and that was certainly the case with the religious leaders, but an important root of hypocrisy is fear, and Jesus addressed that also. No matter how people try to hide it, the truth will be revealed.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 11:37-54; 12:1-33</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-06-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:51', 0, 0, null, 'Etr2WUhpJ1Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Etr2WUhpJ1Q/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2249, 1, 'Understanding Philippians 4:13', '<p>The Bible can be a difficult book to read for a number of reasons, but when it is translated in a way that clashes with the context and our experiences in life it can be very difficult to understand. That is the case with Philippians 4:13, which has traditionally been translated &ldquo;I can do all things.&rdquo; The context is about having strength through Christ in all the different situations we are in, whether they are good or bad. Translating the verse properly engenders a humble attitude and fits with the context of Paul being in prison in less than ideal circumstances.</p> <p>Verses: Philippians 4:10-14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-07-01', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '14:26', 0, 0, null, 'wiiV3acCxAw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wiiV3acCxAw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2250, 1, 'Called by God', '<p>What does it mean for people to be &ldquo;called by God?&rdquo; Who is God calling? What are some of the things we are called to be? To do? What does it mean to be chosen by God? This teaching attempts to answer these questions and show some of the things we have as Christians.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 2:4; 2 Pet. 3:9; Gen. 12:1-3; Heb 11:8; Matt. 22:14; Acts 2:39; Rom. 1:6; 8:30; 9:26; 1 Cor. 1:9, 26; 2:2; Gal. 5:13; Eph. 1:18; 4:4; Col. 3:15; 2 Thes. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: Rob Woods</p>', '2022-07-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '32:37', 0, 0, null, 'XDc9ENOQEI0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XDc9ENOQEI0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2251, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/03/2022) – Rich Towards God', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-07-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '25:43', 0, 0, null, 'IzY5EVEH8Ms', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IzY5EVEH8Ms/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2252, 1, 'The Value of Prayer', '<p>There are countless numbers of things in life that we humans need God&rsquo;s help with, and one of the most effective ways to get that help is prayer. The Bible speaks about prayer many hundreds of times, and not just because it is a good thing to do, but because it is very important in the spiritual battle between Good and Evil. Jesus prayed regularly, and taught others how to pray, and that in and of itself should tell us that prayer is important and effective.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 6:5-7; Rom. 12:12; Col. 4:2; 1 Thess. 5:17; 2 Thess. 2:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-07-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:22', 0, 0, null, '6xWYnjSh42E', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6xWYnjSh42E/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 20, null),
(2253, 7, 'Appendix 8. On Calvinism and Predestination (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 8. <strong>&ldquo;Calvinismo y la predestinaci&oacute;n&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 8. <strong>&ldquo;On Calvinism and Predestination&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-07-08', null, 0, null, 67, 8, 'libre albedrío', null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_8_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null);
