(2254, 1, 'Raising Godly Children – Who is Your Josiah?', '<p>This teaching looks at the lineage of King Josiah and the people who may have mentored him&mdash;thereby leading him, against the odds, to become a tremendous man of God. With 32% of Christians being born again between the ages of 5 and 12 while living in the current cultural ideology, how can the Body of Christ mentor these little ones and help them live holy and godly lives?</p> <p>Verses: 2 Kings 18:2-7, 23:1-7, 25; 2 Chron. 33:1-6, 21-24; Matt. 18:1-6; Luke 18:15-17; Acts 8:30-31; 1 Cor. 12:1-2; 2 Cor. 2:11</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2022-07-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:24', 0, 0, null, 'jK7MmKU1lVI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jK7MmKU1lVI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2255, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/10/2022) – Fear of Allowing Yourself to Think', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-07-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:32', 0, 0, null, 'bI04M5uwNqo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/bI04M5uwNqo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2256, 1, 'Ambassadors for Christ', '<p>The Bible calls Christians &ldquo;ambassadors on behalf of Christ.&rdquo; As ambassadors, we have been entrusted with the ministry and the message of reconciliation. Now we appeal to the people in the world to be reconciled to God so that they can have everlasting life. We learn about how to be the best possible ambassador from chapters such as 2 Corinthians 5 and 6, and from places such as Matthew 10, when Christ sent out his 12 apostles to teach God&rsquo;s word and proclaim the kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 5:16-21; 6:1-13; Matt. 10:5-23, 34-37</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-07-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:16', 0, 0, null, 'G7j7hZTKF_U', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/G7j7hZTKF_U/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2257, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 66 | Worse Than A Fool: Wise In Your Own Eyes (Prov. 26:12)', '<p>Everyone has an innate desire to be right and to be knowledgeable about what they are doing. Sometimes this desire grows out of control, and we lose perception of reality by thinking that we are always right and have all the answers. We can deceive ourselves into thinking we are smarter and more understanding than we really are. Until our mindset changes, we are hopelessly lost in a fiction of our own making.</p> <p>Illustration: Alaskan bush pilot Mark Rose mocked God and was full of pride until near-death circumstances caused him to change his mind and believe in God.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 26:12, 16; 28:11, 26; 3:7</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-07-13', 'Castos', 0, '17:46', 9, 66, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/35c70685-06fd-4bcd-bd8f-7f017d76e8b6-Words-of-Wisdom-Ep-66-mixdown.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-66-worse-than-a-fool-wise-in-your-own-eyes-pxij', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 23, null),
(2258, 1, 'Crazy People part 1 - David', '<p>What do you do when trouble comes your way? This series is intended to help us trust Jesus more and learn to follow him wherever he leads us. In this teaching, we look at the example of David when he was on the run in the wilderness. Like David, we can learn to praise our way out of our difficulties, celebrate the small daily victories, and live in his shalom/peace.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 34</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-07-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:04', 0, 0, null, 'hpMPnH3iZ84', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hpMPnH3iZ84/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2259, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/17/2022) – Who is the Author of Death?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-07-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '29:51', 0, 0, null, 'Gk6ZaDDXL6I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Gk6ZaDDXL6I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2260, 1, 'How Can We Help?', '<p>As Christians we are called to do good works (Eph. 2:10). Those good works are primarily to help people in any way we can. This teaching contains examples from the Bible of some of the ways believers helped others and is an exhortation to us all to find our ministry in the Body of Christ and carry it out.</p> <p>Verses: Gen 14:11-16; 1 Kings 17:8ff; 2 Kings 2:7ff; Mark 1:40; Matt. 8:5; 20:29ff; Luke 10:29ff; Eph. 2:10; Rom. 1:8-12; Acts 3:1-10; Col. 1:24; 1 Cor. 9:19ff</p> <p>Teacher: Rob Woods</p>', '2022-07-19', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:07', 0, 0, null, '2w2Excy2dSs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/2w2Excy2dSs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2261, 1, 'John the Baptist', '<p>One of the very important characters in the Bible is John the Baptist. This teaching explores how, though John was born into the Levitical Priesthood&mdash;a very select group of people who could only attain the status of &ldquo;priest&rdquo; because their father was a priest, so they were born a priest&mdash;he chose not to live that lifestyle. He gave up almost certain wealth and stability for an ascetic life in the desert and a confrontational ministry that brought him persecution and eventually death.</p> <p>Verses: Isa. 39:1-7; 40:1-8; Mal. 3:1; 4:5-6; Matt. 3:1-3; 11:7-12; 17:9-13; Luke 1:5, 15-17; 3:1-17; John 1:19-23; 3:30</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:02:43', 0, 0, null, '__PBs0dy7D0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/__PBs0dy7D0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2262, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/24/2022) – Step Outside Your Comfort Zone', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-07-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:37', 0, 0, null, 'CGYjW5CyNX4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CGYjW5CyNX4/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2263, 1, 'The Qualifications of a Christian Leader', '<p>There is a great need for godly and knowledgeable leaders in the Body of Christ. In 1 Timothy 3, the Bible gives us a list of characteristics and one skill that leaders are to have. That list is helpful because it will reveal areas of strengths and weaknesses in the leader, and it is helpful to the congregation so that they know if the leader over them is qualified to lead or if he or she has areas that need support.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Tim. 3:1-7; Jam. 3:1; Rom. 2:24; 1 Cor. 7:1</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-07-26', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:35', 0, 0, null, 'GCWPZpEHLl8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GCWPZpEHLl8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2264, 7, 'Appendix 9. Fool and Foolish (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 9. <strong>&ldquo;Tonto y necio&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 9. <strong>&ldquo;Fool and Foolish&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-07-29', null, 0, null, 67, 9, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_9_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2265, 1, 'Crazy People part 3 - Jesus and Legion', '<p>The details of the record of Jesus&rsquo; healing the &ldquo;man from the tombs,&rdquo; possessed by Legion, bring to mind the following: Fear is evident from several angles, but Jesus was not afraid, and neither should we be. As ministers we must strive to replace pride and arrogance with mercy and compassion, as Jesus demonstrated. Finally, walking in loving relationship with Jesus involves asking him what he would like us to do.</p> <p>Verses: Mark 4:38-39; 5:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: Bob Mirabito</p>', '2022-07-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:55', 0, 0, null, 'EdoYrgVeZqA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/EdoYrgVeZqA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2266, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (07/31/2022) – Mature in Christ - It''s a Growth Process!', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-07-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:08', 0, 0, null, 'AgMnUQThcuM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AgMnUQThcuM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2267, 1, 'The Demon called &ldquo;Samuel&rdquo;', '<p>The Bible testifies that dead people are dead in every way and will only come to life when they are raised from the dead by God or Jesus Christ. Yet the Devil works hard to convince people that the soul is immortal, and one way he does that is by demons impersonating dead people. A good example of that is 1 Samuel 28, when a demon comes in the form of Samuel and convinced King Saul, the medium at En-dor, and even many modern Christians that Samuel was actually alive. But as this teaching shows, the &ldquo;Samuel&rdquo; Saul thought he was addressing was actually a demon, and the prophet Samuel was dead.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 24:23-24; 1 Samuel 28:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:17', 0, 0, null, 'nfrswD_f1BY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nfrswD_f1BY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(2268, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 67 | Strategy Trumps Strength (Prov. 21:22)', '<p>Our world tends to prize brawn over brains, thinking that the stronger you are, the better you are. But muscle can only get you so far. Wisdom and understanding in a situation can get you much farther than brute strength alone. A sharp mind with understanding will outdo strength any day because it is not just working hard physically that yields success, but working smart as well.</p> <p>Illustration: American wrestler Rulon Gardner&rsquo;s shocking victory over undefeated Russian champion Alexander Karelin to claim gold medal at the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 21:22; 16:32</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-08-03', 'Castos', 0, '16:29', 9, 67, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/1d94716e-470d-4575-b107-4b47bdb4965a-Ep-67-Strategy-Trumps-Strength-Prov.-21.22-.mp3', 'https://truthortradition.castos.com/podcasts/4122/episodes/ep-67-strategy-trumps-strength-prov-2122', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 19, null),
(2269, 1, 'Ambassadors for Christ', '<p>The sharing of one&rsquo;s faith with others to lead them to salvation is very important to God and Christ. Speaking to others about Jesus Christ and salvation can be challenging, but there is no better time to do it than now. This world is truly filled with danger, worry, and anxiety, but Christians can offer people the promise of a vastly better life than this one, and one that will last forever. The promises of God are so wonderful that they should be openly proclaimed to others.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Corinthians 5:16-21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-05', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '15:10', 0, 0, null, 'nVGXwSerqO0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nVGXwSerqO0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2270, 1, 'Crazy People part 4 - You Who Believe', '<p>Yahweh had a plan. His plan was to create a perfect environment to house mankind so he could fellowship with them, love them and be their God. He asked only one thing in return: &ldquo;believe me.&rdquo; Ever since He set his plan in motion and Adam walked away from Him, He has been asking the question, &ldquo;Where are you?&rdquo; Be a &ldquo;crazy person&rdquo; and answer Him.</p> <p>Verses: John 20:24-31; 1 Cor. 1:18-31; 2 Cor. 2:13-14; 1 Pet. 2:6-10</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2022-08-07', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:36', 0, 0, null, 'ptxIdiBTDsw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ptxIdiBTDsw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2271, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/07/2022) – Wisdom – I Need It', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-08-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:19', 0, 0, null, 'nbq-BLya_bY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nbq-BLya_bY/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2272, 1, 'What is the Glory of God?', '<p>Romans 3:23 says &ldquo;all men have sinned and fallen short of the glory of God.&rdquo; But what exactly is the glory of God? Historically, it has sometimes been taught that the glory of God is the divine presence itself, but the Bible describes this lustrous glory as being around God, not God Himself. This is illustrated by examples of some of the ways God has manifested His presence to His people: (1) where He is visible but not His glory, (2) where only His glory is visible, and (3) where both He and His glory are visible.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 3:23; Isa. 6:3; Gen. 18:1; Lev. 9:23; Isa. 58:8; Isa. 60:2; Ezek. 1:26-28; Rev. 4:3; Exod. 34:29-30; John 1:14; Exod. 40:34; Num. 14:14; 2 Cor. 3:7-18; Col. 1:27; Phil. 3:20-21</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-08-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:30', 0, 0, null, 'GUSZgY0wQsc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GUSZgY0wQsc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2273, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/14/2022) – One Foot in Each Kingdom', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '33:02', 0, 0, null, 'tcHUVE_VL7k', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tcHUVE_VL7k/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2274, 1, 'Crazy People part 5 - Abraham & Sarah', '<p>This teaching traces the unfolding of God&rsquo;s promise to Abram (Abraham) of land and many descendants, ending with Isaac&rsquo;s birth. Along the journey we observe Abraham&rsquo;s heart of worship, his honesty and openness in addressing his concerns to God, his generosity and care for others, and his and Sarah&rsquo;s growth in trust.</p> <p>Verses: Gal. 3:6-9; Heb. 11:8-12; Gen. 12:1-4, 6-10; 13:1-4, 14-18; 15:1-2, 4-8; 16:1-2; 17:1-8, 16-19; 18:10-12; Rom. 4:18-24</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-08-14', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:59', 0, 0, null, 'YbKggvJ5JmY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/YbKggvJ5JmY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'manually added', 1, 9, null),
(2275, 1, 'Romans 12: Up-newing the Mind', '<p>Romans 12 starts with an exhortation to live in a way that is pleasing to God, and that Christians are to be transformed by &ldquo;up-newing&rdquo; their mind, that is, bringing their mind up to spiritual thinking. Then it speaks of the different position that God has put each Christian into, and how we many make &ldquo;one Body in Christ,&rdquo; and how we must learn to function in our own God-given ministry. The next section is an exhortation and instruction about how to live a godly life, and the last section in the chapter continues that exhortation.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 12:1-21; Col. 3:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:24', 0, 0, null, 'c_ipuyA3gYw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/c_ipuyA3gYw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2276, 1, 'Crazy People part 6 - Better Together: Allies in God&rsquo;s Plan of Redemption', '<p>The Bible tells us that Yahweh is an &ldquo;ezer,&rdquo; a strong ally and rescuer. Eve, the prototype for all women, is called an ezer, exemplifying this aspect of God&rsquo;s nature in creation. God&rsquo;s plan of redemption is men and women allying with Him; this teaching explores how we are better together.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26-28; 2:18; 3:1, 15; Exod. 1:8-10,13-22; 15:1-3, 15, 20-22; Isa. 14:12-15; Micah 6:4; Matt. 1:18-25; Luke 8:1-3; John 4:13-14, 25-29, 39-42; Acts 16:6, 9-10, 12-15; 1 Cor. 14:34-35</p> <p>Teacher: Karen Theisen</p>', '2022-08-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:58', 0, 0, null, 'iYtzjJWBA_4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iYtzjJWBA_4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2277, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/21/2022) – One Foot in Each Kingdom Part 2 - Beyond Grace', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-08-21', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:59', 0, 0, null, 'oi2F-OU9z0I', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oi2F-OU9z0I/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2278, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (08/28/2022) – The Power of a Promise', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-08-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '28:48', 0, 0, null, 'ojuJ3VaPtjs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ojuJ3VaPtjs/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2279, 1, 'Jonathan: Godly Man and Warrior', '<p>Jonathan, son of King Saul, was a godly man and a great warrior, as well as a great role model. Sadly, his father was ungodly, and that caused difficulties for Jonathan; but it is in part due to the ungodly circumstances that Jonathan lived in that revealed his courage and godly character. We see in him many of the traits that godly people must have to really shine in the world.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 13:1-7, 16-23; 14:1-23; Luke 22:36</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-28', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:11', 0, 0, null, 'Suy_KyIg8fA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Suy_KyIg8fA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 21, null),
(2280, 1, 'Rehoboam, King of Judah', '<p>Rehoboam was the son of Solomon who became king of Judah after Solomon died. He was not a godly king, but did evil in the sight of Yahweh God, and it was his hard-hearted and selfish actions that led to the division of the United Kingdom David had established. A study of Rehoboam shows the great value of humility and obeying Yahweh, and the consequences, both in this life and in the future, of ignoring or defying God.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Kings 11:26-40; 2 Chron. 10:1-19; 11:1-23; 12:1-12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:04', 0, 0, null, 'LR6Jt5a8gHU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/LR6Jt5a8gHU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2281, 7, 'Appendix 12. The Role of Women in the Church (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 12. <strong>&ldquo;El papel de la mujer en la iglesia&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 12. <strong>&ldquo;The Role of Women in the Church&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-08-31', null, 0, null, 67, 12, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_12_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2282, 1, 'John 7: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles', '<p>John 7 is the opening of the record of Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles (the record continues in John 8). What Jesus did, and why he said what he said, are a great study in leadership principles, and the way that the leaders responded to him is a good study in evil leaders today because the same demons and demonic forces that were around in Jesus&rsquo; time are still around today. Believers need to be aware of these things in order to negotiate society in a godly way.</p> <p>Verses: John 7:1-52; Prov. 28:12</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-08-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:09', 0, 0, null, 'UFQW0eWeic0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/UFQW0eWeic0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2283, 1, 'Jesus Christ: The Last Adam', '<p>The Bible depicts sinless Adam (before the Fall) as a type of the Coming One, Jesus Christ. Adam and Christ are alike in that both were created in the image of God and both made a choice that had huge consequences for mankind. Adam chose to disobey God, resulting in condemnation and death for all mankind. Jesus Christ chose to obey God by dying as a sacrifice for sin, resulting in justification and life for those who believe. By freely choosing to embrace death, Jesus enabled God&rsquo;s plan for man to be fulfilled: glory, honor, dominion, and everlasting life with Him.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:7; Matt. 4:8-10; Rom. 3:23; Gen. 3:15; Rom. 5:12-14; 1 Pet. 1:18:21; Rom. 5:15-21; Gal. 3:24; 1 Cor. 15:20-23, 45; Gen. 2:7; Matt. 27:4; Phil. 2:5-11; Heb. 2:6-10; 1 Cor. 15:20-28, 45-49</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:23', 0, 0, null, '4DqjKaeLwRY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4DqjKaeLwRY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'updated desc', 1, 13, null);
