(2284, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/04/2022) – Trusting God in all Circumstances', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-09-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '20:40', 0, 0, null, 'MIBN_TE6Hdo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MIBN_TE6Hdo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2285, 1, 'John 8: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles', '<p>John 8 continues the record of Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles, which began in John 7. This teaching covers some of what Jesus did, why he said what he said, as well as some of the tactics used by evil people influenced by the devil. There are a great many leadership principles in the chapter. Believers need to be aware of these things in order to negotiate society in a godly way.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:1-50</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-09-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:01', 0, 0, null, '9N_21p48NJY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9N_21p48NJY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 2, null),
(2286, 1, 'The Demon called &ldquo;Samuel&rdquo;', '<p>The Bible testifies that dead people are dead in every way and will only come to life when they are raised from the dead by God or Jesus Christ. Yet the Devil works hard to convince people that the soul is immortal, and one way he does that is by demons impersonating dead people. A good example of that is 1 Samuel 28, when a demon comes in the form of Samuel and convinced King Saul, the medium at En-dor, and even many modern Christians that Samuel was actually alive. But as this teaching shows, the &ldquo;Samuel&rdquo; Saul thought he was addressing was actually a demon, and the prophet Samuel was dead.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Samuel 28:1-20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-09-09', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '27:32', 0, 0, null, 'wTzPotvQSZs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wTzPotvQSZs/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 79, null),
(2287, 1, 'The Old Testament Sabbaths and Feasts', '<p>At the time of Moses God instituted a number of Feasts and Sabbaths (days where no work could be done) that were interspersed through the year, and other feasts were added in time. The details of the feasts are not well understood, in part because there is no one place in the Five Books of Moses (Genesis through Deuteronomy) that a person can go and read about them. But when the information is presented in an ordered and understandable way, we can see why God speaks of &ldquo;serving&rdquo; the Lord; it is a lot of work, but God deserves it.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 12:3-11; 16:23-29; 20:8-11; 23:16; Lev. 23:6-8, 15-21; Num. 28:11-15; 29:1-38; Deut. 5:12-15; Esther 9:26-28; John 10:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-09-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:08:36', 0, 0, null, 'vz8yG4gQUxo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vz8yG4gQUxo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 25, null),
(2288, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/11/2022) – Jesus Loved Life', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-09-12', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:56', 0, 0, null, 'hCd7C1xco7Q', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hCd7C1xco7Q/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2289, 1, 'Hezekiah: A Leader with Confidence', '<p>Hezekiah was the son of Ahaz, one of the most ungodly kings in the history of Judah. Idolatry was rampant when Hezekiah took the throne at only 25 years old. How was he able to rapidly turn things around and turn Judah back to the worship of Yahweh? This teaching shows how Hezekiah was confident in his God and in his position as king, leading and inspiring the people to turn back to Yahweh. We as Christians can learn from his example, and stand boldly as representatives for God and the Lord Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Chron. 28:1-3, 5-6, 24-25; 2 Chron. 29:1-36; Eph 5:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-09-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '53:10', 0, 0, null, 'wwSWuhq8_U4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wwSWuhq8_U4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2290, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/18/2022) – Our Physical Reaction to God''s Power', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-09-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:04:52', 0, 0, null, 'hIwvq35hnWg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hIwvq35hnWg/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2291, 1, 'Let Your Light Shine', '<p>This teaching contrasts the light we have through our Lord Jesus Christ with the darkness of our enemy, Satan, in three points: 1) Don&rsquo;t be surprised by the darkness; 2) Pray to see the power of God rather than the pervasiveness of the enemy; and 3) Let the details of the Hope carry you.</p> <p>Verses: 2 Cor. 4:1-6; John 12:27-36; Prov. 3:25-26; Psalm 27:1, 14; 2 Kings 6:8-23; Isa. 11:6-10; 32:15-18; 35:1-10; 65:20-25; Eph. 5:8</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-09-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '35:27', 0, 0, null, '8XQSYOKrBDU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8XQSYOKrBDU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2292, 1, 'Who Is in Control?', '<p>Many Christians today believe that God is in control of everything that happens on the earth. This teaching explores what the scriptures reveal about the control and dominion of the earth from its beginning age in Genesis through its closing age in Revelation.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 1:26-28; 3:14-15; Deut. 30:19-20; Acts 13:16-23; 1 Cor. 2:6-9; 15:20-28; 1 Tim. 2:1-4; Rev. 21:1-5</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2022-09-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:44', 0, 0, null, 'mzMXkrmOAAI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mzMXkrmOAAI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2293, 1, 'Following Jesus Together, part 1 – Psalm 23', '<p>Scripture tells us that the Lord is our Shepherd. Various scriptures also use the analogy of a Good Shepherd and his sheep to show us how much God loves, guides, and protects us in all circumstances of life. This teaching explores this analogy and shows how it is also a great example of how we should care for one another.</p> <p>Verses: Psalm 23</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-09-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:24', 66, 1, null, 'IVt8HUYB_Yw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IVt8HUYB_Yw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2294, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (09/25/2022) – Discipleship', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-09-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '27:28', 0, 0, null, 'kEuH76zhRlA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/kEuH76zhRlA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2295, 1, 'Compassionate Leadership', '<p>One of the great metaphors given in the scriptures to describe the relationship between God and mankind is the Shepherd and His sheep. In the Bible a shepherd often refers to a king or ruler and a good shepherd provides strong leadership with tender care. As the good shepherd, Jesus demonstrated compassionate leadership. We are encouraged to follow his example to love and care for one another.</p> <p>Verses: Num. 27:12-23; Ps. 78:52-53, 70-72; Ezek. 34; Matt. 9:35-38</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-09-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:34', 0, 0, null, 'zLjJnBLDWI4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zLjJnBLDWI4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2296, 1, 'God is Not in Control YET!', '<p>This is a follow up to the teaching of Who Is in Control? It explores what life will look like when God&rsquo;s plans and purposes for mankind become a reality and the devil and his cohorts are locked away for 1,000 years. During this time the Lord Jesus Christ is given dominion and rulership of the earth. What happens when the 1,000 years ends? This is a glimpse into the promises of God for the Millennial Kingdom.</p> <p>Verses: Ps. Isa. 1:23-28; 2:4; 29:18-19; 30:23-24; 65:18-20; Jer. 31:33-34; 1 Cor. 15:20-28, 51-53; 2 Cor. 4:1-6; Eph. 3:1-6; 1 Tim. 6:12-16; 1 Pet. 5:8-11; Rev. 11:15, 20:1-3, 7-10</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2022-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:54', 0, 0, null, 'vmdXrLGXodg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vmdXrLGXodg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, 'had Ps 110-23-28 ref, not sure what she meant.', 1, 9, null),
(2297, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/02/2022) – Loving God', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-10-02', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '16:25', 0, 0, null, 'Y14vC7TAVTM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Y14vC7TAVTM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2298, 1, 'Your &ldquo;Inner Self&rdquo; and What to Feed It', '<p>For centuries, philosophers and theologians have discussed the issue of &ldquo;What is the real you?&rdquo; One of the ways the Bible describes the real you is as the &ldquo;inner self.&rdquo; The inner self gets &ldquo;fed&rdquo; and shaped by what we allow ourselves to think, the decisions we make, and the things we are exposed to. To live a peaceful and joyful life, we have to take charge of our inner self (control our thinking), and take charge of&mdash;to the best of our ability&mdash;what outside influences we are exposed to.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 10:34; 24:9; John 14:27; 16:33; Acts 14:22; Rom. 7:22; 2 Cor. 4:16; Eph. 3:16; Col. 3:15; 1 Thess. 5:18; 2 Tim. 3:12; Heb. 6:19; 1 Peter 1:5-8</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:47', 0, 0, null, 'ZxpETjET-sU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZxpETjET-sU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 15, null),
(2299, 1, 'David and Goliath', '<p>The basic story of David and Goliath is well known, but the record contains dozens of wonderful lessons that are well worth learning. This teaching covers the geography, and some of those lessons such as that life is full of &ldquo;evil giants,&rdquo; that satanic and ungodly people will lie if it is to their advantage, that the enemy will say things that are not true to try to get people upset so that they think and act rashly and are liable to make mistakes, and much more.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 15:28-29; 16:11-13; 17:1-54; Prov. 26:2</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-09', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:53', 0, 0, null, 'GuNYwy_7oOM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/GuNYwy_7oOM/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2300, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/09/2022) – Seeing My World Through the Eyes of Jesus', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-10-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '22:33', 0, 0, null, 'CJbPp8DoguU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/CJbPp8DoguU/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2301, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 68 | Get the Whole Story (Prov. 18:17)', '<p>Everyone carries their own perspective based on what they know and have experienced. But that perspective may be incomplete, faulty, or misguided, which shows us that information is a fickle thing. One person&rsquo;s report can seem true at first, but then when we compare it to a second opinion or another source, we spot potential limitations in the first person&rsquo;s knowledge; this changes our perspective, and we then draw a different conclusion. Thus, the truth is in the whole story, not just the first version we hear.</p> <p>Illustration: Movie plot from &ldquo;My Cousin Vinny&rdquo; (1992) about charges of murder and robbery brought against Billy and Stan, and how Billy&rsquo;s cousin Vinny saved them from being falsely accused of the crimes in court.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 18:17; Josh. 22:11-33</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-10-05', 'Castos', 0, '19:22', 9, 68, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/5b8fa0b4-1479-424a-b8e2-b5da426ac779-Ep-68-Get-the-Whole-Story-Prov.-18.17-.mp3', 'https://permalink.castos.com/podcast/4122/episode/1288198', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2302, 1, 'The Birth of Samuel', '<p>This expository teaching on 1 Samuel 1 covers several things that happened concerning the birth of the prophet Samuel. We are introduced to Elkanah, his wives Penninah and Hannah, the priest Eli, and his two sons Hophni and Phineas. Several mini-lessons are pointed out that we can learn from and apply to our lives as Christians today.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Sam. 1:1-28</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:45', 0, 0, null, '5okB0PMxiUo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5okB0PMxiUo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2303, 1, 'Following Jesus Together, part 2 – The Good Shepherd and His Sheep', '<p>In part 2 of this series we look at the three parables in John 10 where Jesus says that he is the good shepherd. In his exchange with the pharisees, Jesus compares the love, tender care, and guidance of a good shepherd and his sheep with the lack of care and concern of thieves, robbers, and hired hands. Jesus shows us the way and the value of following the good shepherd.</p> <p>Verses: John 10:1-5, 7-10, 25-30</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '51:14', 66, 2, null, '_c3SahnnNYE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_c3SahnnNYE/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2304, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/16/2022) – Persistence and Endurance – Don&rsquo;t Loose Heart', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-10-16', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:27', 0, 0, null, 'pGLZM397pHE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pGLZM397pHE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2305, 1, 'The Epistle of 1 John: Fellowship and sin', '<p>There are two themes in 1 John 1 that are important for Christians to understand. The first is fellowship and the second is sin. The first part of the chapter defines fellowship clearly, which helps us determine whether we are or are not actually having fellowship with others. The latter part of the chapter defines sin in a very honest and healthy way that shows how everyone sins, how that affects our fellowship with God, and how to be forgiven for sins.</p> <p>Verses: 1 John 1:1-2:2; Lev. 16:21-22; 24:15; Ps. 25:18; Matt. 6:12; 18:23-25; Luke 1:2; 11:4</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:48', 0, 0, null, '8-md7o-anUo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8-md7o-anUo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2306, 1, 'What Does it Mean to Follow?', '<p>The word &ldquo;follow&rdquo; implies much more than blindly tagging along behind. It has the connotation of one who deliberately decides to comply with specific instructions. The Apostle Paul decided to comply with specific instructions from the Lord. This teaching looks at those instructions and how Paul complied, and as a result he can say to us &ldquo;Follow me!&rdquo; as he did in several epistles.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 9:1-16; 26:10-16; 1 Cor. 4:11-13, 16; 11:1; Phil. 3:7-9, 17; 1 Thess. 1:2-6; 2 Tim. 3:10-14</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-10-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '40:23', 0, 0, null, 'jLQ5rGcyRf8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jLQ5rGcyRf8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2307, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/23/2022) – Pray For and Love Your Enemies', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-10-23', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:20', 0, 0, null, 'IqzLJRywbnQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/IqzLJRywbnQ/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2308, 1, 'An Introduction to Romans', '<p>The book of Romans sets the tone for the teaching in the Pauline Epistles that salvation is by trust in Jesus Christ. The first three chapters of Romans sets that thesis forth in a logical and powerful way, and contains several important &ldquo;mini-lessons&rdquo; in the process&mdash;all of which prove that everlasting life could be attained through trust in Jesus Christ.</p> <p>Verses: Romans 1:1-7, 16-25; 2:1-16, 25-31; 3:1-4, 9-11, 19-20, 27-31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:24', 0, 0, null, 'swnVWGAuSRA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/swnVWGAuSRA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2309, 1, 'Personal Reformation', '<p>On October 31, 1517, Martin Luther nailed his 95 Theses to the Church door at Wittenberg, Germany, and officially started the Protestant Reformation. But for every person there needs to be a personal reformation. All humans have an old sin nature, and to be conformed into the image of Christ takes focus and work&mdash;time, energy, and knowledge. The Bible and life provide us with wonderful direction and things we need to do to become more Christ-like.</p> <p>Verses: Amos 5:7, 12, 21-24; 2 Cor. 5:9-10; 3:1-3, 16-18; Prov. 4:7; Rom. 12:2; Eph. 4:17-29; 5:1-4; Phil. 2:14</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-10-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:50', 0, 0, 'transformation', 'tf21uSKdKx0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tf21uSKdKx0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(2310, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (10/30/2022) – Don&rsquo;t Worry – Trust God', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-10-30', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '11:34', 0, 0, null, 'S35EuiPINOE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S35EuiPINOE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2311, 1, 'Ezekiel 1: God&rsquo;s Chariot-throne', '<p>This is an exegetical teaching on Ezekiel 1 providing historical information on when and where the fantastic vision that Ezekiel received took place, and describes and explains some aspects of God&rsquo;s chariot-throne and the Cherubim that powered it. God&rsquo;s purpose in appearing to Ezekiel in such a dramatic way was to commission him to speak to Israel. We too have a commission from God, and we should take it as seriously as Ezekiel took his.</p> <p>Verses: Ezek. 1:1-2:5 ; 2 Kings 24:8-14; Ezek. 10:9; 2 Sam. 22:7-14; Exod. 24:9-10; 19:18; Rev. 4:2-3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-11-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:30', 0, 0, null, 'o2i83YMrNX0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/o2i83YMrNX0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2312, 1, 'Following Jesus Together, part 3 – &ldquo;Lost and Found&rdquo;', '<p>In Part 3 of this teaching series, we begin to look at the Good Shepherd, Jesus, in action and how he cares for his sheep. Jesus came to seek and to save the lost. He calls us to follow him, and sends us out to freely give what we have freely received. We should all be asking ourselves, &ldquo;What is my calling at this moment and how well am I doing at what Jesus has called me to do?&rdquo;</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 4:18-25; 9:35-10:8; Luke 15:1-7</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-11-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '56:49', 66, 3, null, 'V8r-zSV3xI0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/V8r-zSV3xI0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2313, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/06/2022) – Follow Me?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-11-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:20', 0, 0, null, '-kB0Sffy0DA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-kB0Sffy0DA/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null);
