(2314, 1, 'Paradise to Paradise', '<p>God wanted a family of free-will beings that He could fellowship with, whom He could love, and who would love Him, so He created humans to be that family. This teaching explores the first paradise God created for mankind and how, ever since the Fall, God has been working to restore His original plan: fellowshipping with humans He loves on earth.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 2:15; 12:2-3, 7-9; 15:1-5, 7-12, 17-21; 26:3; 28:13; Exod. 19:1-9; 20:1-13, 18-21; 24:1-8; 25:8-9</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-11-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:01:12', 0, 0, null, 'jXTHHSLS3PQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jXTHHSLS3PQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2315, 7, 'Appendix 13. The Bride of Christ (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 13. <strong>&ldquo;La novia de Cristo&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 13. <strong>&ldquo;The Bride of Christ&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-11-13', null, 0, null, 67, 13, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_13_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
(2316, 1, 'In One Ear and Out the Other', '<p>Listening well is hard work; listening to a person or listening to God&rsquo;s word. The key verse in this teaching: &ldquo;But be doers of the word and not hearers only, deluding yourselves.&rdquo; (James 1:22) Hearing God&rsquo;s word is useless&hellip;until we do what it says. God intends to bless us when we apply his word in our daily walk, helping us become more like Jesus.</p> <p>Verses: James 1:19-27; Prov. 17:27-28; 18:13; 21:23; 29:20; Matt. 7:24-27</p> <p>Teacher: Gary Burnham</p> <p>Gaither song &ldquo;Into the Word&rdquo;: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1FC07CuXvD4</p>', '2022-11-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:51', 0, 0, 'grow', 'Qd_enaBrmfg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Qd_enaBrmfg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2318, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/132022) – So, you Want to be a Leader', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-11-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '46:29', 0, 0, null, 'MHVvhr0QTEk', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MHVvhr0QTEk/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2319, 1, 'The Golden Calf', '<p>Israel had been out of Egypt for a month and a half when they came to Mount Sinai and made a covenant with God that they would be His people and obey Him and the laws He gave, and He would choose them out of all the nations on earth to be his people. But while Moses was on the mountain for 40 days, the people approached Aaron and convinced him to make a golden calf god that would lead them into the Promised Land. This teaching covers the record of the making of that god, the interactions that occurred after it was made, and the many life lessons in this passage.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 19:3-5; 24:4-8; 31:18; 32:1-35</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-11-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '1:05:05', 0, 0, null, 'zYhiBkfKfG0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zYhiBkfKfG0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2320, 7, 'Harmony of the Gospels', '<p>Valuable insight can be gained by comparing the Gospels to each other. The Gospel Harmony aligns verses of the four Gospels that speak to the same events in chronological order. The text of the verses is displayed side by side providing the complete Gospel record of each event in one place in sequence. The document was put together by Rich Lauer and is based on the work of John Schoenheit and Sue Carlson. It is an Excel spreadsheet, so you will need Microsoft Excel or software like Libre Office to use the file.</p>', '2022-11-18', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/Gospel Harmony.xlsx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 69, null),
(2321, 1, 'What Is The Wrath of God?', '<p>The &ldquo;wrath of God&rdquo; is mentioned throughout Scripture, yet it can sometimes be hard to understand in light of God&rsquo;s loving nature. This teaching explores and expounds on what the wrath of God truly is, how mankind&rsquo;s freewill choices play into this concept, how obedience to God is always the best decision we can make, and more.</p> <p> Verses: Rom. 1:18, 24; Gen. 18:25; Ps. 7:11; 50:6; Rev. 12:10; Exod. 4:21; Deut. 31:16-18 </p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-11-18', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '18:22', 0, 0, null, 'wahRPDU1P5o', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/wahRPDU1P5o/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(2322, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/20/2022) – To Whom are you listening?', '<p>** Note- intermittent audio choppiness in the beginning resolves as video continues. It&#39;s not your connection. :)</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:12', 0, 0, null, '6Gl_AiYVNAc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6Gl_AiYVNAc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2323, 1, 'The Last Supper and Communion', '<p>This teaching explores how, when Jesus broke bread and drank wine with the Apostles at the Last Supper, this actually involved two separate parts of the blood covenant. The penalty for breaking a blood covenant was death, so in Matthew and Mark Jesus said his blood was &ldquo;poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins&rdquo; because it was through Christ&rsquo;s blood&mdash;his death&mdash;that sin was paid for. The Gospel of Luke then takes the shedding of blood to ratify a new covenant, and Jesus&rsquo;s sacrifice was the blood sacrifice that ratified the New Covenant. So both the penalty for breaking the Old Covenant and the shed blood required to ratify the New Covenant were included at the Last Supper.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 15:7-12, 17-21; Lev. 4:1-3, 13, 22, 27, 31; Jer. 31:31-34; 34:8-11, 17-20; Matt. 26:26-29; Mark 14:22-25; Luke 22:17-20; Jude 1:12; 1 Cor. 11:17-22, 30; 2 Cor. 5:21</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p> <p>This teaching concludes with communion. If you would like to participate, have bread and wine or juice available.</p>', '2022-11-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '52:38', 0, 0, null, '-Jj-54rHOv0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-Jj-54rHOv0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2324, 3, 'Words of Wisdom | Ep 69 | I Am Always Right (Prov. 21:2)', '<p>Everyone likes to be right. But who&#39;s to say whether we actually are or not? Do we get to decide? If it were up to each of us, we would probably claim that most of our actions and behaviors are right. However, the desire to be right is so strong in us that we can tend to make up reasons to legitimize what we have done or are about to do. But only Yahweh can determine if we are deceiving ourselves or living out of a pure heart.</p> <p>Illustration: In the 1964 NFL season, Minnesota Vikings defensive end Jim Marshall recovers a fumble but then accidentally runs 66 yards to score a touchdown in the wrong endzone.</p> <p>Verses: Prov. 21:2; 15:11</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-11-21', 'Castos', 0, '18:11', 9, 69, null, 'https://dts.podtrac.com/redirect.mp3/episodes.castos.com/truthortradition/ec5aaee5-2189-4224-9ccb-46b276718af8-Ep-69-I-Am-Always-Right-Prov.-21.2-.mp3', 'https://permalink.castos.com/podcast/4122/episode/1326993', '/i/wow_logo.png', 1, 1, null, 1, 18, null),
(2325, 1, 'Be Thankful', '<p>Giving thanks is a mindset&mdash;it is living a thankful life. This can be hard, because there are so many things in life that are evil and ungodly that can cause hardships. Believers need to practice a &ldquo;replacement&rdquo; mindset. Instead of dwelling on the negative and complaining about those hardships we need to focus on all the things there are to be thankful for and eventually our brains become rewired to be more positive. Thankfully, there is a lot to be thankful for.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Chron. 16:34; Ps. 9:1; 17:3 Luke 6:35; 17:1-6; John 16:33; Acts 14:21-22; 1 Cor. 15:33; Gal. 5:23; Eph. 5:3-4; Col. 3:15; 1 Thess. 5:18</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-11-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '34:42', 0, 0, null, 'KBPwUIr_-Uc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/KBPwUIr_-Uc/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2326, 1, 'Jesus Christ – The Wisdom of God', '<p>A study of the usages of &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo; in the Old Testament shows that wisdom is often personified as a woman. Within Jewish monotheism, this figure of speech is always used to personify a function of Yahweh. It vividly identifies God as the only source of wisdom and expresses his active involvement in creation. In I Corinthians 1, Christ is called God&rsquo;s Wisdom. The identification of divine wisdom with Christ emphasizes the truth that God&rsquo;s plan of salvation &ndash; the message of the cross &ndash; defines God&rsquo;s wisdom in a final way. Now that Christ is raised from the dead, God&rsquo;s purpose in creation can only be understood in terms of him, since it is only in Christ that the divine intention for creation is fulfilled.</p> <p>Verses: 1 Cor. 1:22-24, 30, 11-13, 17-24; 2:7-8; Job 28:1,12-28; Prov. 8:1, 22-31; Jer. 7:16-18; Deut. 6:4; Col. 1:15-20</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2022-11-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '39:18', 0, 0, null, 'gidpHSwjlHA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gidpHSwjlHA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2327, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (11/27/2022) – Dig Deep to Build Your House on The Rock', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-11-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:52', 0, 0, null, 'yREjGcPiLa8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yREjGcPiLa8/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2328, 1, 'When Life Comes Crashing Down', '<p>When things appear bleak, hopeless, or insurmountable, where do we turn? The Bible is full of real-life examples of people just like us who persevered and came through the fire. These examples are recorded to teach us that we, too, can persevere&mdash;encouraged by their examples&mdash;and have hope for a victorious outcome. If they could do it, so can we!</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 15:4; Judg. 11:1-40; Luke 1:26-38</p> <p>Teacher: Dennis Hickman</p>', '2022-11-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:47', 0, 0, null, 'Ls3J26lbtvo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ls3J26lbtvo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 5, null),
(2329, 7, 'Names of the Devil (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 14. <strong>&ldquo;Nombres del Diablo&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 14. <strong>&ldquo;Names of the Devil&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2022-12-05', null, 0, null, 67, 14, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_14_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 4, null),
(2330, 1, 'Being Jesus&rsquo; Friend', '<p>At the Last Supper Jesus called the eleven apostles &ldquo;friends,&rdquo; inviting them into a deep, intimate, committed relationship with him. Jesus said &ldquo;You are my friends if you do&hellip;&rdquo; Friends &ldquo;do&rdquo; for each other. Are you holding up your end of the friendship?</p> <p>Verses: John 15:9-17; James 2:18-23; Heb. 11:8-12, 24-29; Exod. 33:11</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2022-12-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '23:44', 0, 0, null, 'Ndx2ySBQyhQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ndx2ySBQyhQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2331, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/04/2022) – Godly Self Care', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-12-04', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:31', 0, 0, null, 'egEUUmFSaMc', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/egEUUmFSaMc/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2332, 7, 'Retelling the Christmas Story', '<p>The Christmas Story is important because the birth of Christ is important. The traditional story of His birth contains many errors, and presents a cold, hard, and lonely picture about the circumstances of his birth. This document explores and reveals a deeper, more accurate understanding of the customs, time and place, and other details that truly make the birth of Christ an inspiring account of love, obedience, giving, and sacrifice.</p>', '2022-12-09', null, 0, null, 0, 0, null, null, '/export/library/Retelling the Christmas Story.pdf', '/i/thumbnails/christmasstory.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 79, null),
(2333, 1, 'The Lord&rsquo;s Prayer', '<p>Prayer is a very important part of a Christian&rsquo;s life. Jesus taught about how to pray, where to pray, and gave us a model prayer, which in Christian circles is referred to as &ldquo;The Lord&rsquo;s Prayer.&rdquo; It was not meant to be repeated verbatim over and over, but to give us a model of the kinds of things we should be praying for on a regular basis. For people who don&rsquo;t know how to pray, using the model of the Lord&rsquo;s Prayer is very helpful in formulating their own prayers.</p> <p>Verses: Exod. 20:7; Matt. 6:5-15; Luke 11:1-4; Acts 3:19-20; Eph. 4:32; 5:4; James 1:13; 1 Pet. 5:8-11; Rev. 22:20</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-12-06', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:36', 0, 0, null, 'VHdgTH0TUHg', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/VHdgTH0TUHg/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2334, 1, 'Translating the Bible - Meet Our Team: Revised English Version (REV)', '<p>Meet our team responsible for translating the Revised English Version (REV) of the Bible. We&#39;ve almost finished the Old &amp; New Testament with comprehensive translations from Hebrew and Greek.</p> <p>Visit the official REV website with added commentary, appendices, topics, and more at: https://www.revisedenglishversion.com/</p> <p>Donate to the ministry: <a href="https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate/" target="_blank">https://spiritandtruthonline.org/donate</a></p> <p>Translation team: John Schoenheit, Johnny Barnes, Jerry Wierwille, Bill Schlegel</p>', '2022-12-12', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '4:14', 0, 0, null, '4Ae-_garQuY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4Ae-_garQuY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2335, 1, 'Following Jesus Together, part 4 – &ldquo;Feed My Sheep&rdquo;', '<p>In this teaching, we explore a difficult conversation between Jesus and Peter. Jesus meets Peter at the seashore to restore the broken relationship between them and challenges Peter to rise up to his calling. In this record, we learn that to love Jesus is our first priority and that to love him is to serve his followers.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:1-6; John 21:15-22</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2022-12-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '48:45', 66, 4, 'reconciliation, discipleship', 'WMUth2_qqbA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/WMUth2_qqbA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2336, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/11/2022) – God – Jesus&rsquo; Rabbi?', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-12-11', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '37:12', 0, 0, null, 'uZjw-18Ipvo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uZjw-18Ipvo/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2337, 1, 'Believed and Fully Persuaded', '<p>The degree to which we believe the good news directly affects our confidence in it. If we are not fully persuaded about the message of Christ, we may feel ashamed when we are challenged, criticized, or mocked for our faith. To be persuaded is not to simply agree with the truthfulness of the message about Christ, but to have a deep, steadfast conviction that is ready to face any obstacle and a willingness to experience hardship, suffering, and loss on account of it.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 16:24; 2 Tim. 1:8-14; 3:12-15</p> <p>Teacher: Jerry Wierwille</p>', '2022-12-13', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:09', 0, 0, 'trust, perseverance, endurance', 'SXrQ4mBS6fA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SXrQ4mBS6fA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2339, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (12/18/2022) – The Practical Application of Christmas', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2022-12-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:39', 0, 0, null, 'RGLB_gNJDTs', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/RGLB_gNJDTs/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2340, 1, 'Why Does God Allow Bad Things To Happen?', '<p>In this video, we&#39;ll explore why God allows bad things to happen to good people.</p>', '2022-12-19', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '2:12', 0, 0, null, 'OQ8EkoLFmzU', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/OQ8EkoLFmzU/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2341, 1, 'The Magi', '<p>The Magi are an important part of the birth record of Jesus Christ. Sadly, they have been very misunderstood; there were not just three of them, they were not kings, and they did not follow a star to Bethlehem. But they were wonderful men who traveled for months and risked much to see their Savior, and the gifts they gave brought Joseph and Mary out of poverty and allowed them to provide well for their whole family, which included Jesus and at least six other children.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 2:1-23</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-12-18', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '49:24', 0, 0, null, '0bIe2yRlyJ8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0bIe2yRlyJ8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2342, 1, 'Jesus at the Temple, and Simeon and Anna', '<p>After Jesus was born, but before the Magi arrived, Joseph and Mary took baby Jesus to the Temple as the Mosaic Law directed. They offered two different offerings, the redemption money to redeem their firstborn son, and two turtledoves or pigeons, one for a burnt offering and one for a sin offering. While they were there, a man named Simeon prophesied over them, as did Anna the prophetess.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 2:21-38; Exod. 13:2, 12; Num. 18:15-16; Lev. 12:1-8; Isa. 42:1-7; Matt. 7:6; 13:55; Mark 6:3</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-12-20', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '45:25', 0, 0, null, 'Ubr3xslp8q4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Ubr3xslp8q4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 16, null),
(2343, 1, 'Becoming Like Christ', '<p>Believers have a great comfort from God: He accepts us the way we are. But we also have a great challenge: God wants us to become like Christ. Many people love the first part of the equation, but they struggle to be like Christ. Of course we have to fight our sin nature to grow in Christ, and that can be difficult. We fail a lot. But Scripture gives us the remedy for that: we let go of our past mistakes and press forward for the goal.</p> <p>Verses: John 3:16, Rom. 5:6-10; Gal. 5:16-17; Eph. 4:17-24; Phil. 3:13-14; 1 Pet. 2:2-3;</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2022-12-23', 'SpiritAndTruth', 0, '13:29', 0, 0, null, 'l98GAMypcAI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/l98GAMypcAI/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 7, 8, null),
(2344, 1, 'Joy, Celebration and an Everlasting Home', '<p>The five parables in Luke 15 and 16 illuminate Jesus&rsquo; explanation of why he &ldquo;hung out&rdquo; with so-called sinners. Jesus used parables (explainer stories) to get his life and death message of the Kingdom of God to the humble and the not-so-humble. These five parables form a unit which expresses the joy and celebration of those who choose to believe, and the potential fiery destruction of those who choose not to accept the gracious offer of an eternal home.</p> <p>Verse: Luke 15-16; Matt 16:15-19; John 3:36</p> <p>Teacher: Ellen Cutler</p> <p>The song at the end: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=03l96fPb-HQ" target="_blank">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=03l96fPb-HQ</a></p>', '2022-12-25', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:42', 0, 0, null, '4iXyei0j82g', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4iXyei0j82g/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 12, null),
(2345, 1, '&ldquo;One Another&rdquo; Phrases in Romans', '<p>A search of the phrase &ldquo;one another&rdquo; in the Church Epistles reveals a concentration of the phrase in Romans 12-16, painting a picture of how Christians are to regard and treat fellow members of the Body of Christ. This teaching explores some of them, and presents an overview of the Epistle of Paul to the Romans.</p> <p>Verses: Rom. 12:3-5; 13:7-10; 14:13-19; 15:1-7; 16:1-16</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p> <p>TheBibleProject videos:</p> <p>Rom. 1-4: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ej_6dVdJSIU" target="_blank">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ej_6dVdJSIU</a></p> <p>Rom. 5-16: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0SVTl4Xa5fY" target="_blank">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0SVTl4Xa5fY</a></p>', '2022-12-27', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:10', 0, 0, null, '3gcLqdyAAx0', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3gcLqdyAAx0/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null);
INSERT INTO `resource` (`resourceid`, `resourcetype`, `title`, `description`, `publishedon`, `source`, `sourceid`, `duration`, `playlistid`, `playlistsqn`, `keywords`, `identifier`, `externalurl`, `thumbnail`, `active`, `finalized`, `editcomment`, `edituserid`, `resviews`, `content`) VALUES
(2346, 1, 'Love One Another', '<p>Jesus commanded us to love one another as he loved us. The Church Epistles have many occurrences of the phrase &ldquo;one another&rdquo; which paint a picture of how we are to think and act toward fellow members of the Body of Christ. Three of the occurrences are in Romans 12, a chapter that provides vivid instruction in how to love one another.</p> <p>Verses: John 13:35-35; 15:12-14; Rom. 12:1-21; 15:13</p> <p>Teacher: Sue Carlson</p>', '2023-01-01', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '31:29', 0, 0, null, '_VyCMUBPVs4', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_VyCMUBPVs4/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2347, 1, 'Be Resolved!', '<p>It&rsquo;s good to make resolutions and resolve to do certain things. A key to making successful resolutions is to keep them simple and manageable. When it comes to human life, there are two primary resolutions that people should make: receive salvation so you will have everlasting life, and do what it takes to acquire rewards on the Day of Judgment.</p> <p>Verses: Deut. 30:15-19; Prov. 4:1-7; Matt. 4:24-27; 7:13-14; 12:30; John 3:16; Rom. 6:23; Gal. 5:23; 2 Peter 1:1-11</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-03', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '43:29', 0, 0, null, 'trxDRT50QUo', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/trxDRT50QUo/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2349, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/08/2023) – Laying Stumbling Stones', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2023-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:10', 0, 0, null, 'NA0J_R_ROow', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NA0J_R_ROow/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 1, null),
(2350, 1, 'Following Jesus Together, part 5 - &ldquo;Breakthrough!&rdquo;', '<p>In this episode we explore a major breakthrough in Peter&rsquo;s life and its impact not only on his ministry but much more in fulfilling the great commission&mdash;to make disciples of all nations. Peter was humble to hear and obey the voice of the Lord and had the courage to stand up to the criticism from his peers.</p> <p>Verses: Acts 10; 11:1-18</p> <p>Teacher: Jeff Tyler</p>', '2023-01-08', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:12', 66, 5, 'cornelius', 'B--QDTY3_1s', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/B--QDTY3_1s/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 11, null),
(2351, 1, '&ldquo;Put Others First&rdquo;', '<p>Christians are to put other people before themselves. We are to consider the wants and needs of others before we think of ourselves. This fights against our natural tendencies; we are hardwired from the womb to put ourselves first to survive. Philippians 1-2 have a lot to say about this, and when we do humble ourselves to the will of God and put others first, we shine like a light in a dark world.</p> <p>Verses: Phil. 1:27-2:15; Heb. 2:14-15; Gal. 5:16-17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-10', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '36:01', 0, 0, null, 'oUPcM0eOrQw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oUPcM0eOrQw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 17, null),
(2352, 7, 'Can We Pray to Jesus? (Spanish)', '<p>Ap&eacute;ndice 15. <strong>&ldquo;&iquest;Podemos orar a Jes&uacute;s?&rdquo;</strong> est&aacute; disponible en espa&ntilde;ol en Microsoft Word. Puede descargarlo haciendo clic en el enlace de abajo.</p> <p>Appendix 15. <strong>&ldquo;Can We Pray to Jesus?&rdquo;</strong> is available in Spanish in Microsoft Word. You can download it by clicking the link.</p>', '2023-01-14', null, 0, null, 67, 15, null, null, '/export/library/REV_Appendix_15_Spanish.docx', null, 1, 1, null, 1, 10, null),
(2353, 1, 'Choose Your Legacy', '<p>Legacy is defined as something a person leaves behind to those who follow them. God has made possible a legacy for every person to receive by way of the sacrifice of the Lord Jesus Christ. Every person has the opportunity to choose the path his life will follow. Will he choose everlasting life or the alternative?</p> <p>Verses: Pro. 13:1-22; Matt. 6:19-21; 1 Cor. 15:2-24; 2 Cor. 5:10; Eph. 1:3-14, 4:8</p> <p>Teacher: Joyce Adams</p>', '2023-01-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '42:22', 0, 0, 'inheritance', '6tk8uC9tMHY', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6tk8uC9tMHY/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 8, null),
(2354, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/15/2023) – W.B.D.U. - God''s Broadcasting', '<p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2023-01-15', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:27', 0, 0, null, 'cKX_P73kVFE', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/cKX_P73kVFE/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2355, 1, 'Don&rsquo;t Quarrel Over Opinions', '<p>How do we deal with the different ways people think about the world, God, and the Bible? Our &ldquo;natural person&rdquo; tendency is to think we are right and judge and condemn those who disagree with us. That is not how to behave! The Bible says we are to welcome others but not quarrel with them over opinions. That takes love, patience, and practice. We are to make judgments about ourselves and our own lives, but love and not judge others.</p> <p>Verses: Matt. 7:12; 22:40; John 5:21-30; Rom. 2:16; 13:8-14:23; Acts 17:31</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-17', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '55:51', 0, 0, null, 'vCrG5YHh7Zw', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vCrG5YHh7Zw/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 22, null),
(2356, 1, 'Pleasing God', '<p>Apologies for the glitches in the audio. We&rsquo;ll have it resolved soon for future videos.</p> <p>What&rsquo;s the difference between &ldquo;pleasing God&rdquo; and &ldquo;obeying God?&rdquo; There are many things that God does not specifically command us to do that we can do out of love, respect, or kindness that please God. When Paul wrote that he made it his aim to please God, he meant that he was always on the lookout for ways to go above and beyond simple obedience, and do things that would actually be pleasing to God.</p> <p>Verses: John 8:29; Rom. 12:1-2; 2 Cor. 5:9-10; Gal. 1:10; Eph. 2:10; 5:16; 1 Thess. 4:1; Titus 2:11-14; Col. 1:9-10</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '26:39', 0, 0, null, 'eeXIoXi7nko', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/eeXIoXi7nko/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 7, null),
(2357, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/22/2023) – Building Your Tower - Our Priority to Follow Christ', '<p>*** Link to article referenced in the teaching &quot;A Wealth Of Information Creates A Poverty&quot; by Mark Sagor</p> <p>https://compeap.com/a-wealth-of-information-creates-a-poverty-of-attention/</p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2023-01-22', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '30:51', 0, 0, null, 'vv0ZbsInUbM', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vv0ZbsInUbM/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2358, 1, 'The Sermon on the Mount—An Overview', '<p>The Sermon on the Mount is the first major teaching of Jesus Christ; it spans many different subjects but focuses on two major areas: personal godliness and relationship with others. After that, Jesus speaks of personal holiness, such as being salt and light, and he speaks of relationships with people, such as mending broken relationships, divorce, forgiveness, and caring for the needy.</p> <p>Verses: Matthew 5-7; Prov. 19:17</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-24', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '50:55', 0, 0, null, '6LXP_-STWhQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/6LXP_-STWhQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 14, null),
(2359, 1, 'Where is Your Trust?', '<p>Experts in different fields have identified several requirements for, or drivers of, trust in a relationship. These are: communication, character, competency, and reliability. The Scriptures impactfully show us that our Heavenly Father not only meets these requirements, He far, far exceeds them. Once we fully recognize and comprehend this, we will know that we can trust Him with all our heart, mind, soul, and strength.</p> <p>Verses: Luke 8:22-25; Heb. 1:1-2; John 1:1-2; Gen. 3:15; John 1:3-5, 14, 18; 14:8-9; Heb. 2:9-13; Exod. 34:6-7; Matt. 8:1-3; 21:12-13; 18:1-6; Rev. 19:11-16; Exod. 15:6-7; 2 Pet. 2:9; Dan. 3:29; 2 Sam. 7:22; Isa. 40:28-31; Gen. 18:1-14; Eph. 1:19-23; Prov. 3:5-6</p> <p>Teacher: Dr. Shawnee K. Vickery</p>', '2023-01-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:22', 0, 0, null, 'HgcBuJHtPlA', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/HgcBuJHtPlA/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 9, null),
(2360, 1, 'Sunday Fellowship (01/29/2023) – Jesus is King - The Book of Matthew', '<p>Related Links for this Teaching:</p> <p>Song: Hymn to Christ the King by Sarah Hart - <a href="https://youtu.be/mDvk5RWw1xk" target="_blank">https://youtu.be/mDvk5RWw1xk</a></p> <p>Referenced Teaching: The Sermon on the Mount - An Overview - <a href="https://youtu.be/6LXP_-STWhQ" target="_blank">https://youtu.be/6LXP_-STWhQ</a></p> <p>I think I need that! I need to know my MESSIAH! - <a href="https://youtu.be/ONYpyet-OmU" target="_blank">https://youtu.be/ONYpyet-OmU</a></p> <p>One For Israel - <a href="https://www.oneforisrael.org/" target="_blank">https://www.oneforisrael.org/</a></p> <p>This recording comes from the Sunday 12:00 Noon ET fellowship hosted by Michelle Ruth. This teaching is only one aspect of our fellowships! They are also a great time to talk with other believers, share stories of God&#39;s love in your life, and pray.</p>', '2023-01-29', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '44:06', 0, 0, null, '8RFsIO6BMzI', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8RFsIO6BMzI/mqdefault.jpg', 0, 0, null, 1, 0, null),
(2361, 1, 'Romans 5: Reconciled to God', '<p>Romans 5 is a great chapter of the Bible centered around human sin, Christ&rsquo;s payment for that sin, and our reconciliation to God. Christ died for us when we were helpless to save ourselves, and he reconciled us to God by his death. Romans 5 also gives some salvation history: how sin entered the world through Adam, and after him every human being is in sin and needs a savior, and how Christ is that savior from sin.</p> <p>Verses: Gen. 3:5, 22; Luke 12:47-48; Acts 14:21-22; Rom. 2:14; 3:22, 28; 5:1-21; 8:1, 18; Gal. 5:22</p> <p>Teacher: John Schoenheit</p>', '2023-01-31', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '41:58', 0, 0, null, 'ne-8ZepH4ZQ', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ne-8ZepH4ZQ/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 13, null),
(2362, 1, 'Update from the Board of Directors of Spirit & Truth', '<p>This video is an introduction to the Board of Directors of Spirit &amp; Truth. Each board member speaks about what he or she been working on in 2022 and what each will be working on in 2023. The sharings provide the members&rsquo; perspectives on the future of Spirit &amp; Truth and illustrate what is important to our ministry. The session is moderated by our Chairman of the Board, Jeff Tyler.</p>', '2023-02-05', 'SpiritAndTruth_VF', 0, '38:29', 0, 0, null, 'AftPwJt0yq8', null, 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/AftPwJt0yq8/mqdefault.jpg', 1, 1, null, 1, 6, null),
